title: DO NOT WASTE YOUR $$$$
content:
After 6 months, the volume in the right ear bud started to fade w/in 20 mins of use. I went back and read “verified purchases” and found numerous complaints of the same experience. The replacements did not work any better.

It’s disappointing to read how unsupportive customer service is to defective manufacturing of expensive ear buds.

title: tinny sound and painful fit
content: I was excited to see these come on sale on Prime Day.  I was tired of using wired headphones, and I wanted to cut the cords and get away from multiple untangling sessions every day.  They were very easy to set up, and connected to my Android right away.  I put Pandora on, and found that the sound was very tinny, with no bass (compared to a wired set of earpieces like from SkullCandy or iPhone).  I downloaded the Sound+ app and boosted the bass all the way up, but there was very little change in the sound quality.  After about an hour of listening, I had to take a phone call.  It switched without issue, but the quality of the phone call audio was even worse, with the voices of others on the call sounding very weak.  I had to crank it all the way up, which made it audible, but I had to make sure to turn it down before I went back to music.  I am very disappointed, and will be returning these after only 90 minutes of use.

title: Pretty Happy
content:
These are pretty good headphones. Really satisfied with the performance and they sound on par with my ol lady's Bose Soundsport.

They come with a downloadable app that's great. They have a locating feature, hear through ( which I love and allows you to hear surrounding noise without taking the product off), and different sound modes.

Amazon has you rate the noise cancelling, but they're definitely not noise cancelling. They're noise isolating, which they do pretty well. Really snug fit in your ears without causing irritation. I think that varies from person to person. Overall 5/5

title: Excelente relación calidad de sonido / tamaño
content: Excelente performance en general, calidad óptima de sonido.

title: Great set of war buds.
content: Great set of earbuds. Spend the extra money and enjoy. The charging case gives you multiple charges and has LED lights in and outside of case to tell you charging status. The music is great considering the size and the "pass through" feature in the Jabra app works great. Can't say enough about these wonders. Glad I spent the extra money.

title: These would be great - if they didn't have a really bad balance issue that makes them worthless
content: Great materials.  Good sound.  Fantastic battery life.  Unfortunately, none of that makes up for the issue so many people (including myself) are having with these.  My left earbud sounds normal.  My right earbud volume will never go high enough to hear clearly when there is any sort of outside noise, like traffic.  Adjusting the balance doesn't help (it just will never get loud enough).  Resetting to factory doesn't help.  Updating the firmware does worse... they problem went from "bad" to "ridiculous" after the latest firmware release.  This issue has been affecting people since day one of the product release.  People who have sent them in for a warranty exchange report receiving a replacement with the exact same issue (multiple times).

title: Great sound, but...

content: Well I listen to podcasts & talk radio about 8-10hrs/day. About 1 1/2 hours my ears started to hurt that's my only grip everything else is fine

title: Just like the reviewers said - i finally found the earbuds for me!
content:
After an expensive and exhaustive search for wireless earbuds - Jabra saves the day!

I've tried so many well regarded earbuds and either they were a hassle to work with, had connection problems, were too bulky, sounded cruddy, or most of all couldn't stay in my ears well (i apparently have very difficult mis-shapen ears for earbuds). So it's a RELIEF to finally find great earbuds that work, aren't a hassle, sound very good (maybe not the best though - depending on what you like), and STAY IN MY EAR!  And that's before even mentioning how well the batteries last on this thing.

I bought the Actives (for the extra $) just for the moisture protection. (Turns out a few weeks later when i told my date, she found them for cheaper than the non-Actives!)

SOUND: tight. clean. clear. I am an audio engineer so my preference is for "reliable reproduction of sound" aka sound accuracy. I'm not into boosted bass or trebles or any enhanced sound. Just give me reliable repdroduction of what the original recording was designed to do and I'm happy. That means, clear trebles, non-muddy mids, and clean/clear (albeit not boomy) low-end. This fits that bill! Rare!

BATTERY: long-lasting. i've only run out once (and that's after a flight and 1+ train ride home from a quick weekend trip). Sound quality remains constant (as far as I could tell on a flight and train ride lol) until battery life ends.

NOISE ISOLATION: these are very interesting in the noise isolation department. If you are wanting NOISE CANCEL - these will not fit your needs however, You DO get ambient noise for sure. however quite interestingly, the ambient noise is controlled to a non-intrusive vs intrusive level. The things you DO want to intrude (subway train stop alerts, flight overhead alerts, cars around you) - come thru. The things you don't want to intrude - train noise, plane noise - you definitely know it's there, it just doesn't intrude to the point where its' distracting you from your music.

FIT: no earbuds have ever truly fit and stayed in my ear. The design of these "locks" pretty decently and easy to get in your ear to the locking position. (Slide in, rotate backwards until it "locks" or stops). True to form, I do have to adjust them now and then but by far, I have to adjust these far less than any other i've tried. My focus is on my music moreso than adjusting fit. A first for me.

PRICE: compared to a LOT of earbuds i've tried, not too bad. Right in the mix or cheaper. I was starting to expect i needed to up to the $200+ level to get what i want but thankfully i do not.

CHARGING (CASE): This is the one area that could be easier. Because of its unique design (that makes it fit/lock into ear better for me) also makes it not so obvious how to place these into the charge case - because the "lock tab" is straight forwards). the mold in the case doesn't help figure it out. Also, the earbuds, although they stay in your ear well, tend to easily fall out of the charging case when you open it up and are ready to put them in. So there is a danger, if at the wrong place at the wrong time, you could easily lose an earbud opening the case and it dropping to the ground -  if that ground has any cracks or holes.

OVERALL: I've already recommended this to others and they also have reacted with "FINALLY!" after they got these too. The reviews that helped me decide to give these a try are true. These are probably your best bet if your budget meets the price (which I'm guessing it will, as most quality wireless earbuds are in this range or higher).

title: Cost
content: All around great ear buds.

title: All replacement parts on backorder from Jabra site!
content:
The earphones are good for the most part but my charging case broke and all 3 colors are on backorder on Jabra's site. I consider this a fatal issue worth giving 1 star as it is an egregious lack of customer support on an expensive product that Jabra has to correct as soon as possible if they want to be taken seriously as a bluetooth earphone manufacturer.

I recommend you do not buy these earphones as you will get next to no support from Jabra if something goes wrong.

title: DO NOT BUY - known defect left earbud static
content: Immediate problem right out of the box brand new with left earbud static.  Music/audio cuts out most of the time in left earbud with static coming only left earbud.  Right ear bud works fine.  Updated firmware, fully charged no help.  LOTS of people on Internet complaining of same problem with just the left earbud so this must be a defect in the product design. DON'T WASTE YOUR TIME BUYING THIS, Jabra should be ashamed they still sell this product with known/obvious defect.

title: Comfortable to wear!
content:
My husband bought these for me for mother's day and I absolutely love them! I use them ALL the time. They are comfortable to wear, easy to adjust, and the single vs dual feature is fantastic.

I also love how they cancel most external sound while they're in my ears. They are probably the best Bluetooth earbuds I have ever owned.

title: Live up to their billing
content: Very good sound.  Quite sophisticated in terms of options and being well thought out. They fit nicely and don’t look goofy like the Apple ear buds

title: Amazing sound quality, inconsistent bluetooth performance
content: These sound amazing.  Plenty of bass, mids, and highs.  I also have the Bose QC25 and the PowerBeats and these sound better than both of them.  The QC25 still do the BEST JOB EVER of cancelling noise on the airplane, but these do a pretty good job.  Note, these cancel the noise out because they fit inside your ear like an ear plug and as such if you turn off your music, they won't cancel as much noise out as when the music is playing, they are not active noise cancelling like the Bose QC25.  The issue I have with the Jabra is two fold.  #1 when you're eating on the plane or at a café the motion of your jaw actually causes your ears to decompress as well, and they will slide out of your ears.  This may be resolved by using a different size tip, they come with 3 sizes, I used the medium.  #2 issue is most important, the Bluetooth performance is subpar.  Sometimes when you put them in, the left ear does not work, and it's a real chore to get it working again.  There are no clear instructions provided by Jabra on how to resolve, but in my opinion they should JUST WORK.  The other issue I had was talking on the phone, people said they had difficulty hearing me when I was at a noisy coffee shop, so clearly they don't do a very good job in noisy environments of talking on the phone.  Overall this is a great product but I was not happy with using them to talk to my coworkers on the phone and having to fight with the left earbud all the time, so I returned them.  Note: these sound a MILLION DOLLARS BETTER then the Apple Earpods.  The Earpods are a JOKE!!!  Do yourself a favor, even if you don't get these Jabra ones do NOT BUY the Apple ones they sound the same as the factory headphones.

title: Jabri is good

title: Works nice

title: Great audio quality and flawless design
content: These earbuds are a great alternative to airpods and the sound quality is amazing.  I have not faced any of the issues reported by other buyers, yet.

title: Very Very Comffortable AND GREAT SOUND
content:
I read the reviews and even went to a few people on advice before I purchased these wireless earbuds.  I was concerned that since these did not have an ear hook (like bose) that they would not remain in my ear.  However they fit just fine and they are awesome.  I knew from some of the reviews that bass was lacking and that's a true statement.  I have a pair of jam wireless earbuds that have way more bass but they are not as comfortable as this pair.  So it seems that I had to trade base for comfort which in some cases are ok .  The only time the lack of bass really bothers me is when I listen to a song that I know that has a great bass line and its not there.  Don't get me wrong the bass is there but not like overpowering.  However I would still reckoned this pair, the left and right bud have never lost sync with eachother.  however you can listen to the right bud in solo mode I have not figured out a way to listen to the left on in solo mode I am not sure if its possible.  It seems like more people want to chat to me on my right side than my left.  I have not been able to exercise the app yet because I am out to sea on a ship with no wifi and to exercise all of the features you need internet.  So if you don't have internet don't expect the extra features.

UPDATE: Since I have been able to upload the App and they also updated the APP recently I know think this is the best pair of wireless earbuds on the market. Being on facetime and phone calls is a blast with these.  You don't have to raise your voice you can speak natural and the caller on the other side can hear you just fine.

title: Sound is good, but they are uncomfortable
content:
The sound is very good, but my main issue is that they are not very comfortable to keep in your ears for any prolonged period.  I planned to use them at work where I am on calls all day long, but it is tough keeping them or even one of them in my ear that long.

Also, I am finding that I am constantly resting them into my ear as they begin to slide out.  Especially if you try to eat with them in.  The movement of your jaw works them out of the ear.

I guess I should have gotten Apples earbuds.  I thought these would be better for the sound.

title: Good, not great
content:
I've had a number of bluetooth earphones over the years. Some have been very bad and some have been amazing. My Sony WI-1000X are by far the stand outs of the bunch. These Jabra earbuds appealed to me because of their compact design. Jogging with collared headphones can be irritating at times, so I thought I would enjoy this lightweight solution.

These earbuds are a mixed bag. I think it will be easier for me to format this review with a pros and cons.

Pros:
Lightweight and wireless
They have a feature where if you remove one from your ear it autopauses. (great for the office)
Easy one touch functionality.
Call quality is very clear

Cons:
Sound Quality is missing A LOT of low range, very mediocre sound
Requires a special case to charge - if you lose it, you're out of luck. The flimsy hinge on the case broke within a week.
Not a lot of customization available in the app

Overall, for the price, I think there's probably better out there. They're certainly nice sized and convenient, but I find that proprietary charging systems are never a good thing and the sound leaves a whole lot to be desired.

title: Accurate, very good

title: Fine overall but...
content:
Hard to figure out how to turn on the left earbud. They are not linked.
I returned 3 pairs thinking they were broken, before I understood you have to press the front of the left earbud button for 1 sec after you long pressed the right to turn it on...

title: Didn't stay in our ears.
content: I ordered 2 sets (for me and daughter) because of great reviews.  The sound quality is great on the Jabra ear buds, but they wouldn't stay in our ears.  We watched a video tutorial, and tried to make them work, but in the end we had to send them back.  I don't know how the battery life is because we never got to try them long enough before they fell out of our ears.  To their credit, Jabra provides 3 different size silicone caps.  They just didn't fit right for our ears.

title: Incredible Purchase
content: Zero regrets; these earbuds are phenomenal.

title: Excellent sound quality over bluetooth
content: The Jabra Elite t65 ear buds are great. Sound is excellent over bluetooth with respectable volume.

title: Discomfort, but decent
content:
Last time I owned Jabra, I was satisfied. I've tried a couple other headsets and wasn't fully on board, so I was eager to try Jabra again, and I chose this product.

Pros -- Decent UI through my iPhone, and using the controls on the earbuds themselves is easy to learn.  The sound cancellation is decent, cutting out about 95% of sound which is good enough for me.  I had one bud fall out of my ear once at the gym, but I was on a bench that angled my body on a decline; I also wear my buds a bit loose (see cons).  The case isn't too large, so it doesn't feel like you've got a huge bulge in your pocket (giggity).

Cons -- They don't hurt, but there is a snug pressure like I'm several feet underwater.  I have not tried the other ear fittings yet, though.  I do pull the ear buds out just a tiny tiny bit, wearing them "loose" when I'm at the gym, making micro adjustments when I'm on different stations.  When they're in (even just one), I can hear everything in my head; I can hear my breathing, I can hear the pulse in my head, and it is annoying.  When listening to music, my left ear bud will occasionally cut in and out.  When making calls, occasionally there is a bad connection, and I hear a terrible sound.

I enjoy using only the right ear bud while shopping.  I utilize both ear buds with little annoyance when I'm at the gym.  At the office, they are useful for calls, but they're not something I'd wear continually.  They are preferable, however, to larger headphones that can be heavy after extended use.

Would I buy these again?  I don't think I would.  It's not a bad product, and I'd actually recommend them to other people, but they're not right for me.  I've owned for a few weeks, so I've had time to acclimate to them--and it's not happening.  Considering I used some reward points on my Amazon card, I got these for a good price so I intend to get my money's worth out of them.

title: The best true wireless earbuds
content: There are a lot of mixed reviews on these earbuds but I must say thank god i didn’t listen to them. I have these true wireless earbuds paired with my iPhone 7 Plus and my Apple Watch the sound quality is unbelievable. My go to headphones were the V Moda M100’s the M100 are amazing in every way but for the gym I wanted a nice small pair of true wireless earbuds. So I went with the majority of people and bought a pair of Apple air pods. After numerous times of picking them up from the gym floor I decided I wanted inear wireless earbuds so I pick up a pair of jabra elite active. I now have my AirPods to my son. The sound on the jabra is amazing. There is no video lag from streaming services like Netflix or YouTube and best of all they stay in your ear the extra features on these earbuds just put it over the top like the hear through feature and the auto pause feature when you pull out one earbud. With the addition to the jabra application the sound quality is perfect for any type of music you want to listen too.

title: They work
content: They work well for their intend use. The should is good and the in call  sound is not bad either. The mic is lackluster.  I use them on 2 phones at the same time and Bluetooth does drop from time to time and then comes right back and will say "2 devices connected".  Its only a short interruption but it is an interruption no the less. over all if I was going to use them for one phone and just listening to music and the occasional phone call I'd buy again. 2 phones.

title: Cannot use either bud individually
content: These are very good earbuds. Great sound & nice app that comes included but I just cannot give more than the baseline 3 star review when a product at this price point cannot do one of the most basic functions that all of the cheapest pairs available have as a standard option.  The fact that you cannot use either Jabra Elite 65t earbuds separate of the other interchangably so that you can use one while charging the other & switch when needed is truly a glaring omission for me and a deal-breaker. I would never had purchased them if I knew they possessed such a handicap.

title: Excellent product, reliable, easy to use
content: Great product that's ready to go right out of the box. Excellent sound - bass is prominent. The Jabra+ app is a great supplement, especially the Focus features. Jabra nailed it yet again.

title: Great sounding earbuds, but noise isolation? Not so much.
content: The tone of music and clarity of voice are very good! -- until you get in a noisy place. The noise isolation was not as good as my wired Etymotic earbuds. In the fitness center, with TVs and conversations going in the background, you need to increase the volume too much. Of course, no earbud is perform as well as headphones in that kind of environment.

title: AWESOME! I got rid of my Apple AirPods and ...
content: AWESOME!  I got rid of my Apple AirPods and got these for the pure purpose of drowning out the noises in my office.  The noise cancelling is great, they fit in my ear perfectly and can hardly feel them in, have great battery life, and have GREAT sound - much better than the AirPods.  I would highly recommend!

title: The left earbud will go out, it is a common problem.
content: The left earbud stopped working after very minimal usage.

title: Great Earbud
content:
I have been looking for an earbud for about 2 years.  I have tried several others.  The one thing that I learned was that cheap earbuds are just that...cheap.  I looked at many different products after trying cheaper brands, and finally decided to purchase these.  They work very well.  The sound quality is excellent and it generally syncs up without issue.  I use these mostly at work and in the car.  For an earbud, I don't think you could ask for anything better that is currently on the market.

Occasionally, the left bud does not sync.  I believe this is an issue in which it was not seated properly in the charging container and possibly turned off.  In any case, I just put both earbuds back in the charging case (watching for the light on each to let me know it is properly seated) and then pull them out one at a time left one first.  That usually solves the issue.

I have also noticed that the buds cannot go as far away from my phone as another bluetooth headset that I use for working out.  This other headset is not an earbud though so again it's like comparing apples and oranges.

These buds seat very well in the ear and block out external noise when the proper size tip is selected.  This is beneficial to me specifically because I have a hard time deciphering voices when there is background noise.  The downside is a loss of situational awareness.  There is a pass through function, but it sounds odd.  It may seem that way to me because I am used to electronic hearing protection for shooting and this is not comparable to that type of device.

Overall, this is a great earbud.

title: Best Headphones Owned
content: As a true wireless experience, this headset with the Jabra application is perfect; I bought this over a year ago and every sound feature along with the find my Jabra feature... proven to be the best headphones to pair with my phone that I've ever had. The sound quality is phenomenal (as an owner of Audio Technica ATH-M50x, I can contest to this), the headphones themselves are comfortable, great noise cancellation, fantastic battery life, and people on the phone can hear me over wind. Running around or just the transit to work, I highly recommend this pair of true wireless headphones.

title: Poor sound quality
content: Poor sound quality, compared to the Bluetooth headset I was planning to replace.  I returned them and contue to use my old ear buds.

title: Decent upgrade to SoundCore Buds

I can't believe a $200 pair of headphones only worked for 4 months and I barely used them. Don't waste your money on these headphones if you are looking for a quality product.

title: BEST headphones
content: I love these headpones. I can honestly say they are the best ones i've ever owned. Quality constructed, fit, sound, battery life, etc is all top notch. Even great for the GYM.

I love these earbuds. I have had them for 6 months. maybe they aren't as loud as BOSE earbuds, but they are loud enough to cover up the sound of most other noises. I can wear them while i'm in the car and nearly all surrounding sound is unheard.

title: Great quality and long battery life.

They have great sound and connect to my android perfectly and effortlessly.
They have a 6 hour battery life with reminders that battery is high/medium/low, then stick them in their portable charger for an hour and they have another 4 hour life span.
The portable charger can hold 3 full charges for the earbuds. Extremely convenient. My wife wants a pair of these, I'll buy them for her when Christmas comes around.

title: Echo with phone calls for the person you call.
content:
People complain there is an echo for phone calls or face time with the iphone 8.

title: Alot of good a bit of bad.
content: Definitely the best all around work headphones with minimal compromise. I work in a steel shop and they have done great so far. Only gripe is the fact you cant solo the left earbud. Not the most comfy but not the worst.

title: Not A Good Fit
content:
Darn things wouldn't stay in my ear especially if chewing. When I would lay back on a bench or leg press machine they would slip out half the time. Spent a lot of time readjusting them in my ear.

UPDATE
Left ear bud stopped working after 46th day. I wouldnt recommend these.

title: Very good product but still needs a few adjustments
content: This was a gift for my husband who is delighted with this product. Sound quality is  very good but not as superior as other brands. The best feature for him is that the earbuds fit in nicely and don't jiggle during a run. The bad: from time to time the connection with his phone breaks up.

title: Audiophile a must have.
content: The pass thru feature alone is worth it. No need to take the out in order to hear someone talking.  Battery life is good and easy charge when dying with the case being a back up battery.

title: Overall? Unreliable.
content:
These headphones are great when they work. I would say every day, at least once, the headphones will cut out for about a second. That is only mildly annoying. The real annoying part is that every time I put my earbuds in the charging case- they do not turn off and start charging. Sometimes they will turn off right away, but they always reconnect at some point. So if I am talking on my phone without the earbuds- all of a sudden without doing anything they will automatically connect to the earbuds. Super annoying. And it just ends up draining the battery.

I reported this issue to the jabra support team and did not receive a response. Then I decided to call. They said they would send me a new charging case-assuming that is the issue. It has been over two weeks and still nothing has happened.  Called back in and was told that I would receive an email with shipping info by Monday. We’ll see... but the fact that this will take over 3 weeks to take care of after contacting them 3 times, I would say I am not very thrilled with these earbuds. Hopefully they can fix this at some point soon before I give up and just return them.

UPDATE: received the new earbuds and same problems kept happening. Not worth the price, can’t even use. Returned just in time to get refund.

title: Excellent product - highly recommend
content: I've waited roughly 3 months since beginning to use these earbuds before making a review. Wanting to buy some wireless earbuds that weren't the atypical "airpods" I looked for sometime on Amazon and other sites at various other options. Reviews for pretty much everything were all over the map; some great, some ok, some terrible. This was also true for the Jabra Elite 65T earbuds. After more research, I settles on the Jabra earbuds for a couple reasons; calls are routed to both earbuds making it easier to hear the call, the design of the earbud case is nice and it fits well in the hand - not to mention it holds 2.5x charge to keep your earbuds charged, the app is great for tweaking the sound to your liking. While not "heavy" in bass there is enough there to provide a balanced sound which is pleasant and sharp. There is a small multi-colored light on the bottom of the case which indicates the charge level of the internal case battery pack; presumably, green = 80%+, yellow = 30-80%, red = <30% (or similar). On long flights, I've managed to get 4-5 hours of battery life out of the earbuds before putting them back in the case for a recharge; not bad. One feature I also like is that if you dont have them in your ears all the time (like me), when you get a call on your phone, once you've inserted both earbuds the Jabra's automatically accept the call for you. I use these predominantly in an office environment or while on business trips in airports, etc. Never had an issue with sound quality or the connection dropping; so far they have been super reliable. Not sure they (or any earbud for that matter) are perfect for working out and although I've never had an issue with one falling out while I've been walking around, I'm not sure I'd be wearing them on a full run. But, there is a different version of these Jabra's which are aimed squarely at users who plan to do lots of running with these earbuds. Overall, from my 3-months of use, I really like these earbuds; they've changed my life in some ways and its awesome to be no longer using a corded headphone. Highly recommend.

title: Broke after 3 weeks, Jabra customer service is horrible
content:
I purchased these from my local Best Buy. I love the design and found the sound quality to be decent overall (both audio and microphone). The issue I have is that mine broke after 3 weeks of use. This is bad enough for a $200 pair of earbuds, but it got worse when I tried to get a replacement. Initial call to customer service didn't result in anything happening (I was told I would get a follow-up email, did not). Then I'm informed that to get a replacement, I have to send back the broken earbuds, wait an unspecified amount of time for them to be "inspected," and only then will I receive a replacement pair. This process could take upwards of 2 weeks. For a $200 pair of earbuds. That I just purchased.

Contrast this process to what happens when you buy Beats (they send you out an immediate replacement with a box and pre-paid shipping label to send your old ones back, ensuring a much faster and more hassle-free replacement process) and Apple (they replace their earbuds on site in any store or send you out an immediate replacement).

Like many customers, I purchased this with the intention of using them for work. This means that not only do I need a reliable product, I also need responsive customer service. This is a big reason I have always stuck with Apple products; they back their product and provide exceptional customer service once you've invested your money in their brand. Jabra is competing directly with Apple here (the Airpods were the only other earbuds I considered). My advice would be to go with Apple and skip Jabra if customer service and quality is important to you.

title: The Earbuds Are Great, But Customer Support Has Been a Headache
content:
I purchased these earbuds in December 2018 after doing extensive research (I also considered the Airpods, but ended up going with these based on the positive reviews and more discreet appearance).  I was really pleased with their performance for the first three months.  The sound quality is on par with decent wired earbuds and I had no issues pairing them with my various devices.

However, at the end of March, the charging case stopped recognizing my right ear bud.  As a result, I've been unable to use the earbuds since then.  On April 5, 2019, I contacted customer support and, after waiting 30 minutes, was able to speak to a rep.  The rep instructed me to e-mail a picture of my charging case, which I did that day.  On April 10, 2019, Jabra e-mailed me and asked me to send them a proof of purchase in order to complete my warranty request.  I provided proof of purchase that same day.  Over a week later, on April 22, 2019, I received an e-mail saying that Jabra was shipping me a replacement case.  Great!  Or so I thought.  I waited a week and did not receive confirmation that the case had actually shipped.  Earlier today (April 30, 2019), I again called customer support and was informed that the charging case is backordered and that they would let me know once it is in stock again.  As you can imagine, this news was quite frustrating.  They did not inform me about this information until I reached out to them.  Also, it appears from their website that the gold version of the case is in stock, but they did not give me the option of receiving that case.  It has now been nearly a month since I reached out to Jabra and I still am not able to use my earbuds.  I have to say, I expected better customer service given the amount that I paid for this product.  I will update my review once my issue has been resolved.

title: Disappointing signal-to-noise ratio on such a recommended earbud set
content:
Pros: The headphones fit nice and were quite comfortable.

Claimed battery life and water/dust resistance is nice.

Noise pass-through (lets you hear outside the buds) worked well enough (not high quality but did the job)

Wide Assistant support (Alexa, Google, Siri, etc)

Auto detection of removing from your ear to pause, and resumse music when you put it back worked very well.

Sound quality was pretty great, with good bass but not quite as much as I would have liked, even after attempting to correct with both the equalizer in the Jabra app, as well as using the music app's, Poweramp, equalizer. I got distorted bass much much easier than my current wired Audio Technica ATH-CKS55USBK which I never got distortion unless I went looking for it.

THE CON: This is the con that had me return these. There a very high noise floor that I could not remotely ignore, as well as a clicking sound. You can hear the noise/hiss when there is no media playing or a not-loud song or show, same for the clicking sound. I tried everything I could, such as disabling DVC (Direct Volume Control) on my Pixel 2 and while that helped reduce the noise/hiss, it is still present with no media playing or a quiet song/show. INCREDIBLY disappointing. It reminded me of cheap headphones but I am shocked to hear it on a $170 MSRP product. If you are walking around in public and jamming, you won't notice is at all. But if you are in a quiet office or not next to a freeway outside and have your volume at a lower level because the environment doesn't demand higher volume, you can hear the hiss/noise quite easily. That was a deal breaker for me. I had my Audio Technica headphones with me, and used them both on my phone and on my work computer with the same music and had no hiss at all, even with DVC on. I compared back and forth in 30 second stints of the same parts of songs. Such a let down on trying to go wireless.

title: Really slick execution
content:
I have a thing for earphones and headphones. I’ve tried many many of them over the years, from wired cheapies to top of the line Bluetooth noise canceling units. While these Jabras don’t have quite the sound of an excellent over-the-ear unit (especially in bass response), they are extremely well thought out and executed. Here’s why:
1. Battery management. Most small earbuds like these have poor battery life, presumably due to the small form factor limiting battery size. These Jabras have pretty good battery life on their own, but what makes them stand out is the auxiliary battery in the case. So, you can use them in the gym for a few hours and then just put them in their case and have them fully charged next time you need them. Great solution.  In addition, the earbuds automatically turn off when you remove them from your ears, eliminating the trauma of finding dead earphones when you need to use them.
2. Versatility. I like to use only a single earphone when running or biking on the road, so I can hear traffic noise. The problem with  other earbuds is that you wind up listening to only half of the music (the stereo channel that you have in your ear). The Jabras automatically switch to mono when you remove the left earbud, so you never lose the sounds from the left  track.
3. Comfort. While I know comfort is based on personal taste (some people can actually tolerate the torturous rocks that Apple calls  headphones), IMHO these are the most comfortable earbuds that I’ve ever tried. They just fit perfectly if you choose the right cushion size, and never come out of your ears even when sweating profusely.

Jabras sells a sport version of these which cost $50 more and are purported to be more sweat-proof and stay better in your ears. However, when you register the 65t’s with Jabra they give you a 2-year water- and sweat-proof guaranty, so I decided to save some money and go with the standard 65t’s. As already stated, there’s no problem with slippage, so it seems like a good bet so far (I’ve been using them daily for a little over a month now)

So why only 4 stars?  It depends on how you’re rating them. Compared to other Bluetooth earbuds on the market, they really deserve 5 stars. But if overall audio fidelity is your overarching concern, get a good pair of over-the-ear headphones like Bose QC-35IIs. While the Jabras have excellent clarity and high-end frequency response, they won’t give you the boom that you’ll get with good quality larger drivers.

title: Excellent, except for one missing feature
content:
This product astonished me, and I am not easily astonished. I still have not quite got used to being able to walk around listening to music or talking on the phone without having wires trailing everywhere. I know that Bluetooth functionality of this kind has been available for a while. But I was completely underwhelmed by my partner's AirPods. In my opinion, the 65T's are well above the standard of those AirPods. Someone has sat down and thought these things out from the very basics. They are very impressive.

However, let me get my one real criticism out of the way first.

There is no microphone auto-mute or mute-from-the-earpod capability. This seems to be a bizarre omission. Why give customers the freedom to wander around anywhere if they can't mute the sounds by which they're surrounded unless they tug out their phones? I gave up my Pioneer Rayz wired earphones for these 65T's, and if there is one reason that I would go back to the Rayz it would be the lack of the auto-mute feature on the Jabra earpods. It's a nuisance. Another reviewer has suggested that a firmware update could fix this. Come on, Jabra! If Pioneer can do it, surely you clever Danes can do it!

Now for the good stuff:

Fit in the ear: There are warnings about fit problems in various reviews. I had no problem. In fact, I paid too much attention to what other reviewers said: I really did screw the earpods into my ears, with resulting discomfort. In fact, all I need to do is pop them in. With the large earbuds, they work well as long as there is a seal at my ears. And once they're in, they stay in.

Sound quality: Good enough for me. This is so subjective a topic that that is all I can really say. There is a 5-band equalizer built into the Jabra iPhone app. I'd prefer a 10-band, but the 5-band is OK and is adjustable. I listen mainly to classical. If you are a bass nut you may want to check out someone else's 65T's: I can't advise you based on my listening preferences.

Bluetooth connectivity: Excellent. Some people have complained that they couldn't maintain a connection with the iPhone in their pocket. I have no problem from one end of our small house to the other.

Jabra 65T app: I've seen complaints about this as well. I don't really understand why: it seems to do everything it should (except for the microphone auto-mute!) and is reasonably intuitive to use.

Single earpod use: The ability to use just the right earpod for phone calls is a nice touch.

Phone sound quality: People cannot tell I'm on a Bluetooth headset. 'Nuff said.

Charging: A clever system of small LEDs tells you whether your case is charging or needs charging, and the battery level of the earpods themselves.

Overall, I'm very pleased. However, I've had them only 24 hours. If they turn out to be defective in some way in the near future, I'll update this review.

title: Absolutely buy a different set from someone else

It took them 2 weeks to get back to me with another canned response on how to send them the headphones for warranty replace. It has now been a month since they received my headphones from UPS and I have heard absolutely nothing back. My emails get absolutely no response and I've attempted to call several times, each resulting in 30 minutes on hold with nothing to show for it.

This company is not worth your time and certainly not worth the money. Just google "Jabra Support is horrible" and see for yourself.
