title: Can't find a fault
content:
Writing this after 3 days of use. Read a lot about this product- on Amazon, on Souq Amazon's affiliate in UAE where I bought these), and many other websites. Was not sure if I should for the Elite 65T or the Active. Eventually chose the Elite (non Active).

Packaging
Delivered in original packaging. Very well packed. It would be perfect for a gift- from such a large box emerges these 2 small earbuds. Set Up Was quick and easy. I didn`t require the Jabra Sound app to set it up. Just a slight touch on the right earbud and my phone found it within seconds. I use an Android- Galaxy S8.

Sound Quality
Excellent. For both music and phone calls. Haven't done many calls with it as yet but the music sound quality is exceptional. I use it primarily when I am running. Have done 1 5k and 1 3k in it and they were a perfect fit- didn't loosen, were fitted throughout the run. Unlike other headphones, which need to be `shoved` back into the ear every 20 minutes or so, these didn't require that. I also downloaded the Jabra Sound app and played around with the sound frequency settings- reduced the treble and increased the bass.

Other stuff
Music pause: Music pauses every time you take the right earpiece out or when you receive a call. Excellent feature and works flawlessly every time.
Powering off: You don't need to worry about switching it off if you are going to put it back in the case.
HearThrough: This is the special feature of Jabra which let's you hear regular conversations while listening to music. You can toggle it on and off. There is a perceptible difference in your experience (positive) when you put it on.
Noise cancellation: the others haven't complained as yet about my voice when I talk to them- again not many calls as yet, but initial feedback is good.
Battery Life & Voice Assistants Haven't had an opportunity to test the promised 5 hours+10 hours. But hopefully should hold up. Also haven't tried it with Google Assistant/Alexa.

Recommended: yes. I am sure the Bose equivalent are good too. Had tried them in the store- and the sound was excellent- but didn't get good feedback online, about noise cancellation. Also the small features in Jabra like HearThrough make the difference. I bought Jabra not because of the features I ready about- but recommendation of a friend who was using them.

title: Excellent
content: Birthday gift, works great and good sound, fits well in ear.

title: Static
content: There was a constant static in my earbuds when music was on and afterward for a few seconds. I did a firmware update but didn't have any luck fixing this. For something that costs more than airpods, they shouldn't be having issues.

title: The best on the market in almost every way, with a few minor problems
content: When I bought the 65t my first intention was selling it in my country, where it costs around 3x more, and then buy some cheap $50 earbuds to use. But then I started using them, and everything works so flawlessly that I just can't go back to any other model. The sound quality is great, it's comfortable enough to use for hours, which is also possible because of the great battery life. And there's basically zero connection problems, even when I used them in Manhattan, where I could also make phone calls and the other side heard me perfectly. The audio passthrough mode is extremely useful when you don't want to be isolated from the world, and it also connects to two devices at the same time, so I can use it on my phone and computer without disconnecting anything, whenever there is audio on one of the devices it goes to the earbuds. The connection stability especially is something that now I take for granted, then each time I use a different pair of earbuds and the connection drops I really appreciate the work Jabra did on making this work so well. The only problems I see are with the controls, which are in no way worse than any other model, but so far no brand has really been able to make great controls on true wireless earbuds, and this is no different. It's not bad, but it's not great either. Also, and this one I consider unforgivable given how good it is otherwise, I still can't understand who had the brilliant idea of using micro USB instead of type C. Really Jabra? Basically EVERY other device I have uses type C, so I can use the same charger and cable for my computer, phone, Nintendo Switch, portable charger, EXCEPT for my 65t. And some of them are older than the earbuds, so why not use a technology that's new, better and readily available instead of an old one that basically no one else uses but cheap products? And if there is one thing the 65t is not is cheap. That's the only reason I'm not giving it a 5 star, other than that it's an awesome product that's years ahead of basically all competition.

title: I like them, but I have a disturbing thought.
content: Great sound. Very snug for the noise cancellation which I like, but caused right ear soreness. What im worried about is if you have both pods inserted and remove one them, then the other detects it and the sound turns off. Reinsert the removed pod and the sound is back. So there is a signal among both pods to determine if your pods are in your ears based on distance. Since this is the case, then there is a constant, radio wave I’m assuming, crossing your brain to keep the sound playing. Begs the question if there can be any damage, although it takes a lot of radiation to damage brain cells, since they are highly selective cells and differentiated. Maybe it’s thought as an X-ray, you won’t feel adverse effects, if any, for approximately 25 years. I wouldn’t give these AirPods to children.

title: Living it up cord free!!
content: This is another winning Jabra product!  The level of comfort and sound quality is fantastic and I am so happy to be cord free!  I love that they come with a charging case and the ease of use over all.

title: Would be an OK novelty for voice podcasts if they were 1/4 the price, disappointing for music or daily use at this premium price
content:
After reading many positive reviews, I had high expectations for the Java Elite 65t headphones, but was disappointed after a few days of use. There are pros and cons but ultimately these don't live up to the hype and don't justify the steep price.

PROS:
- Solid and well-made.
- Comfortable and weightless for the first 30 minutes of use.
- Good-enough volume.

CONS:
- They don't stay in the ears for long, usually falling out after about 30 minutes, even with the largest rubber pads.
- Extremely frequent audio dropouts with my Google Pixel, which stays in my front pant pocket. This never happens with my car or bluetooth speaker. Maybe the headphones are so small that they don't have room for an adequate antenna.
- Terrible bass response, even with the equalizer cranking the bass frequencies to the max.
- Google Assistant integration is much more basic than I had hoped.  You don't get anything like the Google Pixel Buds. Instead if you long-press on the right headphone you can start talking to Google Assistant, so all it really does is save you the step of saying "OK Google".
- Not sure why, but my phone battery drains extremely fast when using these headphones, which doesn't happen with my car or bluetooth speaker.

title: These are a very good pair of truly wirless earbud
content:
These are a very good pair of truly wirless earbud. In order to get the best experience you have to download the 2 Jabra applications and install the software update. Then play around with the EQ settings.
The other thing I did was to install the  "Speaker boost" application (increases volume).
Finally I went to my phone settings to developer options ,go to "disable absolute volume" and enable it. This will allow you to increase the volume from both your cellphone and from the left earbud.
I am using a Samsung Note 8 which supports Bluetooth 5.0 . The connectivity is very good and no disconnects after walking away 15 feet .The earbuds are very light and fit perfectly in my ears.They block out a lot of background noise.The microphones are very powerful .Phones call audio is crystal clear. The charging is very convinient in its case .Not having any wires is great!
 I have used these for 4 hours straight for phone calls and music and the battery was still going.

My only con is that these dont support codecs such as Aptx ,LDAC or Samsung HD. Only supports SBC and AAC.

title: Safety
content: Battery life does not last as long as I would like, I purchased these earbuds in March and in June I noticed they weren’t holding a charge as long as posted and now in August 1st they are barely charging at all, I need answers.

title: So disappointed! Buds too big for my ears.
content:
I don’t know how many stars I should give those ears buds, I could not use them they are big and kept falling of my ears.
 My son in law likes them so I gave them to him.

title: Great audio quality and awesome fit
content: I love my Jabra 65T's, although I have noticed that my left ear bud begins to make crackling sounds when I am in areas where there is a lot of wifi signal. Otherwise, these are solid ear buds with great audio quality, great fitment and good battery life.

title: Excellent Ear Buds
content: Fits ear perfectly

title: Best battery life, decent fit and great sound!
content:
If you've been shopping for wireless earbuds for a while then look no further because i know the pain of looking for some. The main thing I love about these is the battery life. 5hrs using both at the same time!! And they're not bulky either. After using these for a couple months I can say that's pretty accurate. The passive hearing is good but the problem I have with it is that if you lower the music the passive sound also goes down. The app allows you to set how much sound to pass through but seems pointless because if you lower the volume of your music it literally turns down the output of the speaker. The app is great too but I wish the status bar that's always at the top of my phone would also display battery life or an option to turn on and off the passive hearing rather than having to open the app for both. Fit is good but not great. While I was surprised that the design does actually keep the buds in my ear even during workouts but if they're placed even slightly incorrectly chances are they'll fall out. Putting them in correctly involves a twist and tug basically. Talking on the phone is pretty good too. They can hear me clearly with no issues. Also I just discovered I can shut off the automatic pause option when i remove an earbud.

They're pricey but worth it. This is my sixth pair of wireless headphones in the last 5 yrs I got off Amazon. None before had the features or quality of these and I don't completely regret those purchases but if you add them all up they cover the cost of these.

title: Good Buy-Recommend Jabra Elite 65t Alexa Enabled True Wireless Earbuds with Charging Case
content:
Jabra Elite 65t Alexa Enabled True Wireless Earbuds with Charging Case was a great purchase.  I shopped several headphones and here are the results of the headphones I tested out.

JayBird Freedom 3
Let me start off by saying I had the JayBird Freedom 3 headphones for 5 years and although I was satisfied with the customer service of JayBird the Freedom 3 Headphones feel out of my ears while running.  I sweat more than the average person due to my hard long runs and these would never stay in my ears past 3 miles.  Overall I was happy with JayBird Freedom 3 but would not purchase again because they would not stay in my ears ruing my runs.  If you are lifting weights or doing light easy runs then I would recommend these simply due the great customer service.

Bose SoundSport Free Wireless Headphones
These headphones are one of the most expensive on the market and worth it just for the sound alone.  I used these during my hard runs and they stayed in my ears during the whole run.  As mentioned before I sweat a lot and they passed the test.  The sound quality is top of the line!!!  Awesome sound!  There are two reasons why I didn't keep these head phones.  1. When taking phone calls they would only have audio in the right ear.  This was awkward to me and I like hearing out of both ears.  2. I was very proud of my new Bose Headphones (True Wireless) so I showed my wife and her first comment was "you look like shrek!!".  I didn't find this funny so looked in the mirror and realized they stick out of my ears and to my surprise I did look like "Shrek".  Overall these headphones are awesome, stay in my ears, great sound, and worth the price but just didn't work for me.

Jabra Elite 65t Alexa Enabled True Wireless Earbuds with Charging Case  – Titanium Black
After wearing the JayBird Freedom 3 and the Bose Soundsport I wanted to test the Jabra Elite 65T.  Overall this are great earphones with "True Wireless" Earbuds.  Sound quality is not as good as Bose but still exceeded my expectations.  Battery life is great in the Charging Casae.  These headphones stayed in my ears during a 8 mile intense run.  As mentioned I sweat alot and these stayed in my ears with no issues.  They do not make me look like "Shrek" and are comfortable.  I used them to take phone calls and audio is in both ears....like this feature.  Easy to set up out of box, easy to connect to bluetooh, can connect to two devices.  Look great, feel great, and work great.  The pair I purchased do not have the heart rate monitor feature as I never use that feature anyways so didn't need to spend the extra money.  These headphones I am very happy with and an excellent "true wireless" feature.  I highly recommend these headphones for anyone looking for a top of the line quality "true wireless" earbuds.

title: Excellent headphones
content:
I love these headphones. Great quality, good sound, easy to use, and very convenient.
I liking being able to connect them to my phone and my laptop at the same time.

title: Pretty good product if you can get them to stay in your ears.
content:
These do not work for people with deep ear canals.  I tried all three sizes of the supplied ear buds, settling on the large.  This would work ok but due to the shape of the plastic body of the unit, I could not get it inserted deeply enough into my ear canal to stay there.  That said, they sounded very good immediately after inserting into the ear.  Bass was very present, and overall tonal balance was very good.  If your ear canals aren’t too deep, these may work well for you.
  Phone calls - Phone calls also sound good when you have a good seal in your ear.  There were some times that I had to move calls to my phone because there was too much background noise for the person on the other end of the line to hear me.  So far, I have yet to find a Bluetooth set of earbuds that was very good at background noise cancellation for the person on the other end of the call.  That being said, these were some of the best of the ones I’ve used.  This is almost impossible to do well without a microphone right next to your mouth.  Overall, if these fit your ears, they are pretty decent true wireless earbuds.

title: Pretty good choice.
content:
Pretty good option for wireless ear-buds. The sound is decent--not as good as my comparably priced wired buds--but the wireless is super useful. They stay in well and are relatively comfortable. They pair easily with my Google Pixel 2 (which is good since it doesn't have a dedicated headphone jack--the way of all new phones now apparently). Battery life is good and the charger case it comes with is small and handy.

Note that my first version of these had a TON of problems. Amazon replaced them free and my second pair worked more consistently. Upgrading to the Google Pixel 2 seems to have helped too--the LG G6 had trouble staying consistently paired with them, it seemed.

title: Too Large - Don't Fit my Ears, Simply Fall out
content: I suppose I have freakishly narrow ear canals or something because these absolutely do not fit in my ears.  Very disappointed that I apparently fall into some minority category of ear size that prohibits me from ever experiencing wireless ear buds.  Maybe in a few years the technology will have these small enough that I could try a pair.

title: Not reliable even with Bluetooth 5
content: My phone has Bluetooth 5 and it had connectivity issues in the left earbud which is annoying. Makes loud popping noise. They are quite large and not very comfortable. Sound lags when watching video. They can easily fall out of the charging case as it's not held magnetically. I really wanted to like these but unfortunately the connection issue was a deal breaker for me.

title: Great Product!
content: These are great. Much better than bose soundsport free. Sound just as good, smaller, and the jabra app is better.

title: The ONLY true wireless earbuds in my opinion!!
content:
Tried multiple true wireless earbuds in the past and have never been satisfied. Apple AirPods simply will not stay in my ears without extra grips and then it becomes a pain putting them on and taking them off every time you want to use them!
The JABRA elite 65T’s are EXCELLENT!! Perfect fit! Great sound, great pass through sound for when your outside running on the road or working in an office and still want to hear if someone is talking to you.
They fit great! Do not even come lose on long runs. Zero connection issues.

ABSOLUTELY RECOMMEND

title: The Earbuds I've Always Been Looking For!!!
content:
These have become my #1 set of earbuds.  I listen to podcasts all day while I work at my desk, so I need a set that's comfortable, works well, lasts a long time, and most of all sounds really good!  I looked and looked and tried (literally) dozens of different sets before I took the dive and bought these.  I was hesitant because they are so pricey, but clearly the less expensive ones weren't working for me.

These earbuds have made listening and talking on the phone with them a pleasure!  I can walk around with them (with my phone in my pocket), go into the store, and go from talking on the phone to listening to music or podcasts (or even YouTube if I desire) without missing a beat!

One thing that surprised me but has become one of my favorite features is that if you remove one of the earbuds while you're listening to something, they automatically pause whatever it is you're listening too!  Not live calls, of course, but what a great feature!  Now I just take one out if I'm walking down the hall and someone wants to talk to me and not only can I hear them, but my media waits for me to be ready.  OUTSTANDING!

The charging case is excellent.  I keep it charged so I can have the earbuds in my pocket and they'll charge from the stored charge in the case!  WOOHOO!!!

Yes, they cost more, but man, oh MAN are they worth it!

title: Product defective
content: The product met my expectations while it lasted, but it barely lasted 5 months of moderate use.  Even worse than the product quality is Jabra's customer service. Look elsewhere.

title: Do not recommend this earbuds
content: Only three months using this earbuds and the right one is already useless. After a few minutes of use the volume is reduced to almost zero. I wouldn’t expect this from this product specially if this is for active people.

title: Great sound, bad fit
content: Poor ear gels. Everything about these earbuds is great except for the ear gels. The earbuds would fall out when I chewed food or moved my head to the left or the right. Would be better if the made bigger foam tips for it and if they would fit in the case.

title: Long battery life great sound
content: The title says it all.

title: The fit and look of the Jabra Elite 65t is top notch
content:
Tried to get volume in left earbud higher because it was not near a comfortable level
The right earbud would only get above a whisper.
I tried all the usual things to make them work. after several days I gave up and returned them.
I am sure the Jabras are great earbuds.just not the pair I received

title: !! Poor sound quality !!
content: Noise canceling is good but sound quality is ok not that good

title: Connect well but sound quality is bad
content: Wow do these sound terrible. They connect to my Samsung 9+ perfectly every time (unlike the Sennhesier airbuds) but once connect, the music sound quality is bad - very tinny, no warmth or low bass. Will probably sound them back.

title: Good headphones!!!!!
content: Really good headphones for the price !!!!!

title: Not for me!
content: The headphones were really nice and a great quality. The sound was good for true wireless, nothing special. I just found them EXTREMELY uncomfortable for my ears. They stayed put through movement but it felt like I had a permanent hearing aid installed. I also found it difficult to take in and out of the ear/case like I was going to drop it every time. It was also hard to press the small buttons while in my ear and it hurt to push the bud in further when I want to skip a song or change the volume. Returning and going back to on ear.

title: They don't sound the greatest but they'll take a lickin'
content:
These head phones don't sound the best but for the price it's a good value.  Unfortunately, the silicone ear inserts are not that good inevitably causing them fall out during my workouts (at least one side does).  And, that is a big problem because one side fell out in the middle of a set today at the gym and I could not find it.  It seemed to disappear!!!  Had half the gym looking around the floor for it and we just couldn't find it.  I was sure it fell in a crack somewhere and I probably would never retrieve it.  Finished my workout and then returned for one last look before heading home and behold I found it (YES!!!!).  Clearly someone had either stepped on it or dropped a weight on it because it was pretty beat up.  Happy I found it but was sure it was fatally damaged.  However, once it got home and cleaned it up, to my surprise it works!!!  I couldn't believe it!!!  If you could see what it looked like you wouldn't believe it came back to life (should have taken a picture of it).
Summary - Other more expensive headphones may sound better but, I promise nothing will stand-up to the abuse of the gym the way these do!  I'm convinced they will stand the test of time, as long as I don't lose them first...  Can't give 5 - Stars because the inserts are kinda cheap (which is why I may lose them).

title: Don’t waste your money
content: Terrible product

title: they do not work for me
content:
they either fall out because they are in loose or i can not hear the music because they are pushed in too hard. for my ears and this design they just do not work especially for $180

one other issue is the controls located on the units that control tracks, volume etc. are so small my fingers have a hard time operating them and i don't have large hands.

title: Doesn't sync audio and video in Youtube app, terrible for phone calls in any slightly noisy room
content:
I truly can't understand how this is an actual issue, but it's true (you'll find other reviews online). In the YouTube app on iOS, the audio and video are out of sync with these headphones. Apple says it's a Jabra issue. Jabra says to contact Google and Apple. I have multiple other bluetooth headphones and have never had an issue with audio/video sync in the YouTube app. From my read, this is a Jabra issue that they refuse to deal with, or just don't know how to fix.

Also, in any slightly noisy environment these headphones are useless for making phone calls. The noise cancellation feature cancels your voice and raises the background, switch to your phone from the headphones and you sound great.

Summary: if you want your audio/video in sync in Youtube and want to make phone calls, don't buy these.

title: Buy them before they mess them up with  a new style,lol
content: I been having these for a month now , today I could say they really play music for 5 hours in one charge, the best Bluetooth I ever owned, worth every penny, not bulky on your ears , could be use for the hole day , could use the right one and not the left and still get calls and listen to music ,the best I’ve ever tried .

title: Tough review: Hurts my ears, but then I have small ears.
content: I can't give a bad review because my suspicion is that all of these types of ear pieces might hurt my ears. I was just disappointed when I could not wear the buds for long periods of time because my ears absolutely ached after an hour or so of inserting them. I think this is not necessarily the specific Javra product that is the issue but the overall design of these buds. The inserts that are planted deep in the ear are not the issue. The large core receiver component is...

title: Infuriating case
content: The sound quality is ok, but not better than other options. If I were going to keep these I’d cut off the tab in the lid and hold it shut with a rubber band. I also bought the Apple AirPods so I could choose between the two. I choose the AirPods.

title: Very good sound, but keep falling out
content: Seems like a great design, smaller than other earbuds.  Very good sound, but maybe not quite enough bass for my taste.  Biggest complaint however, is that one earbud (left one) kept falling out when exercising, even after trying different size cups.  Might just be my ear shape, but had to send them back.  Too bad. I really wanted to like them

title: He didnt want to take them off!
content: My husband LOVES these headphones! He didnt want to take them off!

title: So worth it
content: I love these earphones. The convenience of true wireless is so nice, and the sound quality is very good. I hear parts of my music in a new light constantly, and the balance between lows, minds, and highs sounds really good. The only issue is that they don't connect to my Fire HD 8, but that's a (IMO) glaring fault of the device and has nothing to do with the earphones themselves. Just be aware of it if you're thinking of using them with a Fire device; I'm not sure how they interface with other tablets. Being able to pause and tap into background sounds is really useful too. I'm really glad I splurged on them.

title: Great for calls and audio books...don't expect much for music.
content:
Good fit and easy to pair. Controls are easy to use but you do need to understand the context in which some actions work or don't...I hung up on someone when trying to turn on noise cancelling.

I'm mostly a business user so the average music quality is acceptable (very light on bass and mid-range).  Phone call quality is more than fine and the wind noise cancelling capabilities are exceptional when both buds are used and all four mics are active.

title: Good for the really sweaty people out there....
content: Good headphones for working out calls are only as good as the area’s you use them in but otherwise it’s a reliable set of wireless headphones

title: Static on hearthru when no music playing.  Annoying
content: Static noise when no music playing.  App needs work also.  Because of the static issues i would not spend this much on a Jabra again.  I expected much more

title: Yes they do work great
content: Love these. They are a little bit of a challenge to get use to. Figuring out how to put them on, but not impossible. Biggest issue is I cannot wander very far from phone. Like across the room. Buy honesty the best sound quality I have had and phone calls (with my phone close) are overall spot on. Only a couple of hiccups. What in life doesn't have a few here and there.

title: The case will eventually stop closing (possibly before they are a year old)
content:
I bought these when they were just released, so i've had them for a while.  It pains me to write a 1 star review because they are otherwise very good (maybe 5 star - and I know my AV devices) but the charging case, which is a mandatory part of the system, was designed with a very soft plastic latch that will inevitably wear out from daily use. My case now pops open in my pocket somewhat regularly, and these aren't even a year old.

This is either planned obsolescence, or just poor industrial design. But what irks me is the environmental impact that a single bad choice like this has. Tens of thousands of these will hit the landfills long before the other parts are dead, all because of a tiny piece of plastic that they could have invested a fraction of a cent more on.  Nice going guys.

title: Best on the market
content: The wireless headphone market is full of junk. air pods are over rated, nothing fits right, sounds like crap, not loud enough....but not these!  These are INCREDIBLE.  Best sounding, fits great, compact, so easy to use, tons of features, i can go on and on.  These are the headphones you were looking for, I can guarantee it. P.S. the app you can download to use them with is so so cool.

title: Amazing earbuds that do not disappoint...
content: This is the first thing I've ever owned from Jabra. I did a lot of reading reviews before settling on them. Let me tell you, they did not disappoint. These earbuds are much more premium than the price tag suggest. Worth every penny. Excellent sound, excellent battery life, phenomenal feature set. I find myself utilizing the "hear through" feature much more than I thought I would. Wonderful product.

title: Sound great - Bluetooth connection very easy
content: Love these earbuds and look so much less dorky than Apple buds

title: They lose connection with each other.
content: They started to lose connection with each other and made loud cracking sounds in my ear after a week of use.  Nothings worst than going on the train and your new 200$ headphones stop working...

title: Some of the best Truly Wireless Earbuds
content: This purchase was vaguely complicated for me because I was unsure of spending nearly $200 in uncharted areas for me, I had never purchased truly wireless earbuds before and I wasn't even sure if I needed them to begin with. Fortunately one bad decision later and I actually am very surprised how much I use these and how much I love them. Everything about them feels high quality and the audio is crystal clear, not to mention the biggest selling point, there's literally no wires and this creates a very "free" feeling when walking around or going to the gym. All-in-all I would highly recommend these.

title: Awesome
content: Love them . Worth it

title: uncomfortable (I have small ears)
content: I put these in my ears and immediately took them out. They weren't secure and could easily fall out, even with trying multiple earbud sizes. They felt uncomfortable when I could get them to stay in; within a couple minutes, my ear was starting to hurt. I'm certain these work great for lots of people, but just not for me.

title: Great sound until the left earbud stops working.
content: You’ll love these headphones...until you don’t. I lost my first pair, so I bought the second off a friend. In both pairs, I started having issues of the left headphone cutting out. Was hoping it would self correct since I liked the headphones soo much...but now realizing the folly in that as the problem continues to get worse each day

title: Perfect earbuds for now
content:
I had a bluetooth earbuds mainly connected to iPhone. And when I get to work place, it is a real pain in the ass to switch from earbuds to earphone(or the opposite) which is connected to Macbook.
So I was looking for multi point supported earbuds. I bought this Jabra Elite 65t supports multi point for 2 devices.

First impression's great. The product is well made and app's functionality is great. Sound quality is average but app has adjustable equalizer function. Battery life is ok especially with charging case. Charging case is small enough to put it in a pocket. Auto pairing is convenient but other BT earbuds do this as well. And I love hear through function by double clicking earbuds button. But about multi point functionality is not exactly what I imagined.

To switch from Mac to iPhone, there has to be a certain event like starting to play music by specific application or getting a phone call. So I was watching youtube from iPhone and then I click mouse button which make warning alarm sound on my Mac. It starts sending sounds from Mac(after alarm sound there's no sound at all). It doesn't go back if I pause youtube and resume. I have to switch to different app then get back to youtube and resume to change the source of sound.

I think it has better chemistry when using with iPhone. Connection to Macbook seems a little unstable. It gives me quite frequent pause of sound when connected to Macbook.(Maybe this is why they release a new version with usb dongle)

title: TERRIBLE sound, BEST fit
content:
The ONLY cool thing about these is they fit better than any earphones in the history of earphones
They sound TERRIBLE
I mean worse than the first ever in ear apple earphones

title: Left earbud does not work half the time.
content:
Within 1 day, the left earbud is not working for most of the time. Many reset of both the earbuds and phone and still same problem.

Bluetooth: Able to pair 8 devices, but will only connect to last remembered 2 devices (not consistent). If you wish to connect to a third remembered device, you will have to reset the buds to repair the two devices you want. Super annoying.
Using with laptop + phone connected. Phone will not able to play any sound media until the laptop is disconnected. Although when a phone call comes in, it will take priority. Priority for bluetooth: Call > Laptop > phone

Sound quality: Ehh, sounds like stock earphones.

Fit: very stable inside the ear. You will feed the intrusion of the earbuds inside your canal. Otherwise, quite comfortable.

title: ear bud connection fails at times
content:
sounded great at first but then the left earbud started cutting out on me
this would happen randomly and even after a full charge
it may be a lemon so i don’t exactly know if i recommend against buying these

title: After 3 months they no longer perform properly
content:
Here I am 3 months in. They were wonderful for the first few months, however recently my experience has degraded significantly.

Here's why:

1. The headphones no longer disconnect when placed in the charging case. This means I have to manually disconnect them via my phone's bluetooth settings. However oftentimes when I do this they will automatically reconnect a few seconds or minutes later. This requires me to either turn off the headphone by holding down the right ear button, or turn off bluetooth completely on my phone. I usually end up having to completely disable bluetooth for a period of time to avoid unintentional reconnection. I assume this is because the headphones are no longer making a solid connection to the charging case despite my attempts to clean the connection pads and pins.

2. The charging case no longer provides the headphones with two full charge cycles. In fact I'm lucky to get a single recharge from it. This is basically unacceptable as comparably priced devices offer 20+ hours of on time via the charging case. I now have yet another device that requires nightly charging.

3. The bluetooth connection quality has degraded substantially. Especially while running or moving quickly while exercising. The connection quality was great at first, but now drops in and out despite the phone being in my pocket. No idea why this has degraded. I do sweat in them, but that is why I purchased the active model.

title: Excellent.
content: Highly recommended.

title: Best sounding true wireless buds so far
content: Great sound if you download and use app that goes with them, the equalizer helps a lot you get more adjustments, features and user manual with app.  Easy to use, paired once to both my smartphone and iPad Pro works great with both. Perfect for videos absolutely no lag, love that you can press once to hear someone talk without pulling bud out, and if you pull one bud out music pauses automatically. Also found I can leave iPad in house go outside quite a distance and do not lose connection. Press and hold on left connects you to Siri, Google Assistant or Alexa which ever you prefer to use.  Only tried phone call once will need to try this feature more and update on that later. They do stay in have snug fit, but only 4 stars for now because they are not as comfortable as some people were saying, need to wear them and adjust some trying different ear piece sizes and will update on that later.

title: Poor fit
content: The earphones don't fit snugly in the ear no matter which tip I try.  They fall out at the most inopportune times and because of the poor fit the sound leaks out.  This was a waste of money.

title: Work great
content: Work great

title: Good except for the ergonomics
content: Agree with many reviewers these are painful to keep it for any amount of time and the sound isolation is mediocre. I ended up replacing the tips with the sport version’s foam tips which improved these problems somewhat but they require you to shove them deeeep into your ear to stay in place (no issues with charging case though). Other than that, battery life, charging speed, sound, and quality of the case are great. I’m glad I got these on Black Friday sale as they aren’t worth full price.

title: Bad Sound Quality.
content: Very disappointed in the sound quality. The highest volume is like medium level on other headphones. No bass at all. Very treble dominated sound. The equalizer doesn't help at all. Not worth $150. Returning these because of bad sound quality.

title: Anyone there?
content: Good deal.

title: Poor sound quality, fit and terrible customer service
content:
Horrible customer service.
The case does not wanna open. I literally have to wrestle with it every time. I called customer service to replace it and after 2 weeks they send me an email asking for more info.
Never buying Jabra products again.

title: Great
content:
Great product.
Keeps on working for about a year.
Same sound quality.

title: Great device with wrong connection
content: Nice device with great sound, but the only problem I have with this is just the connection to the bluetooth. My music and phone conversations always break down whenever I have my phone in my pocket. I am about to return mine and I will advise people not to waste their hard earned money to buy this. I only enjoy the connections when I have my phone at my hand. SO BAD!

title: Not quite worth the price.
content:
Pros:
Comfortable as far as earbuds go
Decent noise cancellation
Good battery life
Extremely portable
Cons:
Sound quality isn't exactly stellar (But maybe that's to be expected for any fully wireless earbuds)
Noise cancellation overcompensates for louder clicks and bangs
Very expensive even compared to other fully wireless earbuds

title: Good sound but do not stay in your ears.
content: The sound quality from these was very good, however they did not stay in my ears at all during activity. They kept falling out which defeats the purpose of buying active earbuds that you would want to use during activity. Had to send them back

title: Amazing sounding best yet!
content: This earbuds are amazing.  Best sounding to date.  Highly recommend and you can download app to change sound setting.  These are a major GO!(flossy carter voice)

title: Great sound. Poor connectivity
content:
Very good sound but they continually drop connection on both my iPhone and Android device.  I reached out to Jabra who initially was very quick in responding but now I can’t get them to reply after three attempts. Very disappointing. UPDATE:  I used Facebook Messenger to get someone from Jabra to respond. However, I was told that the sound breaking up when my device is in my left pocket rather than my right pocket was normal behavior for these Jabra earbuds. Interestingly enough my Samsung IconX earbuds don’t do that - no issues in either pocket.

I guess Jabra has set the bar low and seems satisfied with that. Again, very disappointing.

title: It's good but not for the price
content:
It was pretty good in terms of audio quality, a little flat sounding and lacks bass, but most true wireless buds will lack bass (or they lack battery life).

Speaking of battery life, it's not bad but it's not excellent. It's just average. I liked the charging case and the buds themselves look very good.

Also liked the built in Alexa functionality. Calling was OK; again not horrendous but nothing to drool over either. I liked the outside sound pass through you can enable via the downloadable app, made it very easy to talk to people while not having to take them off.

However for their price tag it really isn't worth it anymore. It's a slightly above average product for a very premium price tag. Instead I bought a pair of Melomania 1 from Cambridge Audio and the sound is on par (slightly better imho but everyone is different) and the calling is fantastic, as well as the insane 9 hour life from the buds and an extra 36 hours on the Melomania 1 case is just too insane. And for the price of 129.99 USD there's just no end to the goodness that is the Melomania 1.

title: Well all around
content: Really good earbuds all around. Two things to keep in mind: the case isnt as good as apple airpods and if you want to listen with one earbud only, you have to use the right one. The left is not self activated and is dependent on the right one

title: Worst Purchase Ever
content: I don't know where to start...these are worst electronics purchase I have ever made. The case is not designed to charge the 65t earbuds with the silicon tips on! They must be removed each time they are placed in the charging case and reinstalled when you want to use them! Can you imagine? They constantly disengage themselves from the silicon tip and fall out of my ears leaving the tip in my ear. One popped out and fell in a river right after I bought them. I got a replacement and tried to like them,,,ya right, they're terrible. Auto connect is a terrible idea: these turn themselves on from time to time  and connect for no reason. A real pain The app is totally useless, for ex. I want to be able to take out the right bud as I don't hear well with my left. No matter what I do with settings they disconnect as soon as I remove the right one. Volume is very low. I guess there is supposed to be a control on them  but I haven't found any way to affect the volume level. Sound quality is about on par with another pair of earbuds I got off ebay...for $8. Not $170. Jabra should be ashamed for charging more than $30 for these; and that's more than they're worth. The Jabra 65t is the worst electronics purchase I've ever made. These are horrible.

title: Not for you if you use more than one device
content: Sound quality is far better than many of the other wireless earbuds I’ve tried. However, I ultimately returned these. Why? Because of the Bluetooth pairing abilities, or lack thereof. You can pair a single device simply - that’s no problem. But if you are someone that wants to switch between devices (e.g., phone to iPad and back) on the go, you’ll be very frustrated. I won’t go into much detail, but there are many other devices on the market that do this without any friction.

title: The soundthrogh is a nice feature
content: These things are super great

title: Charging indicator
content:
I've been using this for a few days now and there is room for improvement. The biggest issue so far is charging. The case has no indicator that the earbuds are charging. There is a LED that lights up green, but it goes off within 2 seconds. I've twice now opened the case to find my ear buds not charged. I dont know if it's because they are not touching the contacts. There should be some sort of indicator that tells the user they are charging.

The second issue is the pairing. I am a right handed person. When I'm taking 1 pair out of my ears it's the right one. The problem is that if you take the right one out your music can keep playing. It just goes into mono mode. So now I have to get used to pulling out the left bud instead.

But so far I like the sound quality. I just wish the charging was handled better.

Edit:
I forgot to mention that if you take out both buds for too long. The left bud will power off. When you put the two back in your ear the left one will not have sound a a result. You have to force it back on before you can get the stereo sound back.

title: Excellent sound from wireless headphones
content: Used for working out

title: excellent sounding wireless earbuds.
content: These are one of the best sets of wireless earbuds available despite the following concerns. Only concern is sometimes does not bluetooth to my other devices  such as my fitbit Ionic (I phone always does connect).  The jells don't always hold in my ears even though you get a few sizes with purchase.

title: Not impressed with fit
content: I can't keep these in my ears no matter which size ear tips I use.  I gave them to my son and he seems to like them.  I went back to my wired ones that came with my iPhone.

title: Good product that hurts my ears
content: Super sounds lots of features but they do hurt my ears when  I wear them  too long

title: Great if your phone is in line of sight!
content:
If my phone is in my front pocket (pixel3) they will disconnect while im walking. if im walking and the phone is in my hand, they will still disconnect. If you are using them at a desk and dont need to walk or pocket your device then this is an ok set, however, at that point you might as well get a full pair of headphones.  For them being Bluetooth and less than 3 feet away, its pretty disheartening. I bought them at a reduced price, i would absolutely not recommend them at any price point over 75$.

As  they are primarily designed for phone use, software will only work with the apple and google store. If using windows, you will lose functionality.

title: overhyped wireless earbuds but still good
content:
So I purchased these after being disappointed with the bose soundsport free wireless. The sound on these are not as good as the bose but the latency is WAY WAY better. The EQ on these are a little flat, I don't understand how some reviews said that they are bass heavy cause they are not. The fit is really good, just make sure to try all the ear tips for the proper fit. These do not block out as much noise as many other reviewers have said but they do block out some. The sound through feature does work pretty good in an office setting but when I went running with these, I would use the app and the earbud itself to turn on and off the sound-thru and could not tell any difference, I could still hear traffic around me. For calls its ok but not great, make sure that the buds are pointing slightly down towards your mouth so the other person youre talking to can hear you well. I do like that it has an app to modify the EQ and sound-thru feature. The case is a finicky to get open, you'll have squeeze the sides and then pop up the middle. I was disappointed that the buds are NOT magnetically held in place like my old Crueser wireless earbuds. They do connect to my phone almost instantly which is great. I got these on sale and I got these to replace my crueser wireless earbuds that I loved but gave to a good friend when he wanted to borrow them and loved them too, if not for that I would not recommend buying these at the original $190 price and wait for a sale or buy some other cheaper brand. These are overhyped and should be a cheaper price and again had it not been for the two reasons stated above, I would have not bought these.
Do I recommend these? at full price... NO! on sale.. ok but I would recommend doing some research on some other buds at around or less than the sale price on these.

title: The earbuds and charging are very easy to becomes dirty
content:
The earbuds and charging are very easy to becomes dirty,
If you are Oily skin, I think you should skip to buy it.

The original eartips are not good and makes my ear uncomfortable
I replace the eartips with a pair of Spinfit CP100Z and it is much better now.

The Sound quality is very good
The bluetooth 5.0 connectivity is much better than previous Elite 65t
But some time still get jammed when somebody talking on the phone besides you.
Connectivity still good when you stay in a very crowd environment

title: Won’t stay in even when not active
content: $200 is a lot for earbuds that won’t even stay in standing still. If you’re sweaty at all or working out, forget it. You’ll spend half your workout putting them back in. What a joke for an “active” headphone

title: My Ear's Hurt
content: Have had them for 10 days and every time i use them pains my ears. volume control is not easy to use without hurting your ear. Rest all are secondary to me

title: Buyer beware
content: Didn't work, appeared to be new.  jabra warranty dept said to call Amazon for refund.. they couldn't help

title: Don’t use it that often
content: My ear hurts with the big bubbles

title: DOES NOT WORK WITH LAPTOPS
content:
THIS PRODUCT DOES NOT WORK WITH LAPTOPS. ONLY PHONES.

Which basically means you need two pairs of earbuds, one for your phone, and something else for you computer. Which is stupid and makes these a pretty lousy deal.

I have a new MacBook Pro and while it will connect a third of the time, it's infuriatingly inconsistent.

Also, the call quality is pretty lousy. Within a few minutes, most people will ask if I can use the phone instead of my headset because they can't understand what I'm saying.

title: Looks good, works decent
content:
They are fairly comfortable to wear - I am replacing BeatsX with them. Photos show fit and profile - not enough bald head examples on here!

Some pairing issues on initial pairing sometimes, but in busy NYC Bluetooth environments it’s to be expected. Rock solid otherwise.

title: Extremely Poor Phone Audio Reception - Big Disappointment
content: These are awful for clear cell phone/audio with an iPhone 10 xs. They are fine for listening to music. If possible I'll be returning them and likely purchase AirPods.

title: Left ear bud static issues
content: Overall quality of earbud is pretty nice, fit is great and very comfortable, sound is really good for a earbud accept left ear bud had a constant feint static noise when volume raised over about 70%ish?  Spoke with Jabra’s tech support and followed all procedures to no avail.  Was told it’s a very uncommon issue so I decideded to exchange for a new pair and same issue .... more I researched more I saw it’s a very very common issue... tried on 2 iPhone 10 so maybe they don’t get along to well with iphone10 just be weary purchasing these.  If you can get over the sound of static in the background of your music then def really good earbuds otherwise not recommended...

title: These are probably the best truly wireless in-ear headphones on the market right now.
content:
I'm amazed by these headphones. They sound great, are wonderful for phone calls, don't look obnoxious like the Bose and most other truly wireless headphones, and just plain work. Always. I haven't had a dropped signal at all in the past month plus that I've been using these. And the battery life is typically more than twice what I need. I was on a call for 3.5 hours with no issue. Also, these go into your ears easily and stay there. The app to control all the settings is simple and useful as well.

The only faults I've found with these are 1) I've been told (after asking specifically about it) that some outside noise during calls can leak into the call. Nowhere near enough that the person on the other end can't hear you, but enough that they can tell if you're walking around in the city or a park or riding a bike or something. And 2) They don't smoothly go back and forth between your computer and your phone. It takes some work to switch up the bluetooth connection. Of course, Jabra never promises that this will go smoothly. Instead, they say that these are optimized to work with your phone. Neither of these faults are a big deal to me, but may be useful for you to know.

If you want an excellent set of truly wireless in-ear headphones, I don't think you can currently do better than these.

title: Not comfortable.
content: I work in the construction industry.  These work great for listening to music and still hear my surroundings.  The biggest issue that I have is comfort.  After about an hour, my ears are sore.  I  guess it depends on the shape of your ears, but I find the whole unit to be too thick for my ears.  Kinda of a bummer.  You have to wear them for awhile before you really know.

title: Awesome call and audio!
content:
I've tried quite a few ear buds and by far love the quality of audio and calls with this.
I was using Samsung iconX which was nice and good and then moved to the new galaxy buds - was good fit, but horrible audio and call quality was bad.

This one has really good call quality. The only thing is it's slightly bulkier than my previous ear buds and you need to learn how to put them in your ears, takes a little getting used to.

One issue that I've been noticing is that the right one sometimes miss to charge or connect automatically (the green light doesn't turn on), need to pay bit more closer attention to it.

title: Build quality is not very good and sound on left has suddenly turned low
content: I was happy with the product till now until suddenly the volume on left piece sounds lower than the right one. Also while I was trying to replace the medium earplug on the left piece it came off easily from the base. Now am left without a proper fitting for my ear. It's being hardly a month and the device has already started to give me trouble. Never expected this from Jabra and that too for a premium device like this ☹️

title: Good sound
content: Sounds good, cuts in and out every now and then could be the phone though( s7edge)

title: Nice earbuds
content: I bought a set at my local store, not through Amazon. Anyways,  I have purchased a set of $40 GRDE EARBUDS  before and the was ok, and they sounded terrible with calls. So I saw these jabra 65T earbuds and figured I'd spend a little more $. They are not perfect,  however the sound is great, the fit is great with the correct size rubber piece. the battery life is about 5 hours on one charge which isn't bad. They dont bulge out of your ear like the Bose earbuds. the case on the other hand feels cheap like, one drop and it will break. I have not dropped it (yet) but I'm in the marines and I workout alot so in time I will drop it Haha.  I really think the price is a little high but not to extreme. they do connect as soon as you remove from case, also when you remove them from your ear they pause your media which is nice. They are small so a little difficult to remove from the case and ear if you have big hands. Now the noise cancelling is not the best, It works ok when activated and when it's off you can hear just a little more noise around you. When you receive a call it tells you who it is and you can say "answer or ignore" instead of picking your phone. I find this feature great, especially in the gym. Overall, I like the product and would buy it again. One last thing, it has "find your earbuds" as well, and when your near them you can send a signal to them to make a high pitch noise so that you can locate them.

title: They break easily.
content: They stopped working after 67 days. The right ear bud refuses to turn on or reset. None of the LEDS on the right ear bud turn on. I have tried trouble shooting and at this point they are useless $160 paper weights. I have submitted a request to Jabra support. These are supposed to bw the Active 65T model and  don't even use these in an athletic setting. Basically sit at my desk for 8 hours listening to podcasts. Hopefully Jabra will send a working replacement. For now this is 1 star. I'll update to 4 stars if they address the issue. Stay away from these!

title: For the price point and the features and construction, an awesome buy !
content:
Really loved the headphones!

Looks and construction : They are very low profile and the color (blue) looks premium. The headphones and case feel like they are made of the same material and it feels sturdy. Some folks mentioned the case opens up accidentally but I didn't have this issue.

Usage : Despite being so small they never slipped out, even once. The case is bit bulky in the pocket so have to play around with that so it doesn't look like you have a bulge. The buttons are hard to use - as in it hurts the ear to press them. You need to hold the unit while your press them so they aren't pushed further in your ear. Also it's very easy to press the wrong button (because they are so small)

Sound : Music sounds good but leaves a bit desired for a premium bassy feel. Volume control and range is adequate. The pass through feature works but not the greatest. Customizing the EQ didn't help as much as I was hoping / reading up it would. Hopefully an update is sent through soon.

Calls : The audio was great but the mic didn't isolate just my voice which lead to the other person asking me to repeat what I said repeatedly. Also you have to really speak up to be heard so maybe not the best option for public calls.

Battery : I haven't done a proper test but since I got this couple weeks ago, on a single full charge, this baby is still performing great!

Connectivity : Easy to pair and customize in app. But the Bluetooth range is subpar. When my phone is my left back pocket it cut off quite frequently (the Bluetooth receiver seems to be in the right headphone). But when I had my phone in my right pocket and a heavy bag covering it, it worked just fine. Strange.  You need an additional app to make the Jabra Sound+ work which is again strange. Also charging is still on micro USB.

I feel that this is a great product and should definitely be something you consider the next time you are looking for true wireless headphones.

title: Awesome headphones! Great sound!
content: Love these headphones. Music sounds awesome, phone calls are as clear as the phone itself, best in class, by far the best set I've had so far. The hear though sound is a cool feature, but not really that great. Alexa enabled feature can't make calls is my only complaint. Besides that alexa enabled on them is a cool feature.

title: Not the Best Experience for Apple Users
content:
I've only had these buds for about a week, but I wanted to put out a review as a warning to iPhone users. I bought these based off of the phenomenal reviews from the big publications about them being superior to AirPods, and from anecdotal reports of neighbors walking around with them.

However, while they might be better for non-Apple users, I think that iPhone/iPad users would be better served with AirPods or Beats.

Regardless of how you feel about the increasingly siloed nature of manufacture ecosystems, staying in Apple's ecosystem seems to yield the best results. I'm comparing the Jabra's with my two pairs of BeatsX headphones, which are an Apple product and use their proprietary W1 chip technology.

With the Beats, the connection with my phone is nearly instantaneous. I turn them on, and they're paired. There's a noticeable delay with the Jabra's.

With the Beats, I hold down the voice activation button and Siri comes up nearly instantly. With the Jabra's, you hold down the button, hear a beep from the Jabras, wait two seconds, and then hear the Siri tones. This delay in activating Siri is what's currently bugging me the most.

The final major difference is that once the Beats are paired to one Apple device, they're essentially paired to all of your devices that are attached to the same iCloud account. With the Jabras (or any non-Apple bluetooth device), you have to manually pair each device individually.

There's also been a lot written about how well the Jabra's design blocks out more sound than the AirPods, and how the "hear-through" technology provides the best of both worlds for isolating noise but also allowing in the amount of noise that you want.

However, the sound that is digitally piped through is not natural, and you won't confuse it as just ambient noise. It's clear digitized and processed. And in many cases, ambient noises seem to confuse the earbuds and get translated into weird, annoying beeps.

Overall, I think they're fine buds, just not as good as I was hoping after reading the great reviews. And I'm pretty certain that Apple users are better off with AirPods or Beats.

title: First totally wireless earbuds, total home run.
content:
Likes...
Battery life, I am using them connected to 2 devices, desk phone and cell phone. Music playing all morning, 5+ hours of battery life, even with Hear Through on. Put them in the case during lunch, complete days worth of use.
Dual Connection, I can play my music and can pick up calls on my desk phone. It pauses the music while on the call and resumes when I hang up seamlessly.
Size, the ear buds fit me perfectly, they do not stick out like Frankenstein bolts. They do not fall out of the ear.
Comfortable, I have been wearing them 5-8 hours a day since my purchase. I have had no comfort issues.

Dislikes,
Sometimes when connecting there is a high pitch noise.
Mic sensitivity, there is no adjustment and it works too well. In the office when I am on the phone, the people on the phone can hear other conversations that are 10-20 feet away from me.
Occasionally I get a .5 sec interruption in the music. Not sure why yet, testing with phone placement.

title: Worth the money!
content:
This is the best earbud I've ever tried. The sound quality is great and the bass is clear and loud, the buttons work well with a nice click when presses and there is a designated beep for each action when the button is pressed. The case is also nice I carry alot of items in the pocket with the earbuds (keys & pocket knife) but the case was never scratched or damaged. The battery life is more than enough for me the never really run out of charge, I charge them every 2-3 days. I also ride a motorcycle and in my helmet they work well for canceling out the sound or playing the noises through the speakers. And once I try the earbuds extras I found the size that fits in my ear well. I've had pebbles from the weedeaters hit my earbuds and they never scratched or stopped.
My only problem is that the case is quite large and annoying to have in my pocket, and I'd like to see type-c and magnets.

title: Very good sound, but fitment can be a problem.
content: These are very nice ear buds.  Well built and sound is very nice (although I am no audiophile).  However fitment was a real problem for me.  The left ear kept falling out - even when I was just sitting.  The right ear was fine, but the left ear was a problem and I found myself often on all fours looking for the lost ear bud.  I tried various different tips, even ordered the foam tips from Jabra, but it made no difference.  The left ear bud just would not stay in my ear.  So if it fits, it's fine, but if not you'll want to return this like I had to.

title: Al borde de la perfección
content: Casi perfectos. Si tan solo la cancelación fuera mejor.

title: Excellent quality
content: Great Quality, Received in a Timely Manner. Very happy Customer.

title: Don’t buy these
content: They were good for the first 2-3 months. But now, they don’t disconnect when I put them back in the case. So the battery runs out. I have to manually disconnect from them and always manually turn them on again. Gets very annoying. Seems small but it’s not. Also, you can’t use the left on its own; you always have to use the right.

title: I like them but they're better sounding headphones, but not with all these features.
content:
I was expecting bettter sound.  I wish they had better bass.  They have a lot of cool features so they're worth the money and the in calls sound great.  I like the equalizer, and the ambient sound feature.
i'd buy these again, but they're better sounding headphone.  Specifically the sol republics.  They're a lot less expensive and blow these away for listening to music.

title: Audio doesn't play evenly on both earbuds
content:
Right out of the box, these headphones do not play audio evenly in both ears. The audio played by the left earbud is noticeably louder than the right earbud. This difference in volume can be heard when listening to the built-in audio prompts as well as when the earbuds are connected to a device. For expensive earbuds, I was hoping for much better quality and reliability.

Outside of the uneven audio issue, these earbuds work alright. The Alexa feature is useless, but the audio quality (ignoring the volume issue) is acceptable and the battery life is alright. However, I would never purchase these earbuds again knowing the issue with the uneven volume.

title: Some good, mostly bad
content:
The sound quality and bass are great. I workout in a large commercial gym and get distracted easily, these block out pretty much all sound and deliver super clear, loud sound. The bass is very impressive too compared to most other earbuds. The Sound+ app is super helpful too and lets you configure different frequency ranges so I can enjoy my music how I like.

However, it's an extremely uncomfortable product. They give you different sizes for part that goes in your ear, so that isn't the issue. The problem is that the rest of the earbud is designed to rest in a indentation in your ear, for (what I assume to be) bass and noise cancellation purposes. This part can be super uncomfortable if it's too large for the space, and if it's not jammed in then the earbud falls out. I find myself removing the earbuds between sets because my ears would hurt too much.

Secondly, this is the second set of these earbuds I've received from this company. Both have had problems with the left earbud. With the first, the left earbud kept cutting in and out before eventually just not working at all. These cut in and out nonstop for probably the first 10 minutes of operation, but then stabilize.

Overall, you can get good earbuds for much cheaper than these. Save your money.

title: Call Quality Problems
content: I love these earbuds, BUT, the call quality is terrible. The mic is so sensitive that the person on the other end of your call could hear a pin drop, the flip flop of your flip flops, a passing car or strong breeze, and the unspoken thoughts of significant other. Seriously though, the mic is so sensitive that you cannot use the earbuds to take calls in a public place. Its even difficult to use them outdoors as every sound, natural and man made, is picked up. I get constant complaints. Forget using them for professional call if you are anywhere but a soundproof room. It pains me to say that I would not buy another pair of these for routine use. That said, they are otherwise great.

title: Very high quality earbuds for medium to large ears.
content: These are wonderful wireless earbuds.  They power on and connect automatically to my phone when i remove them from the case.  When I replace them, the case charges them back up.  The case itself is rather small and easily fits in my purse.  If the earbud comes out of your ear, the other one stops playing so you know you’ve lost one.  In fact - they’re perfect except for the fact that they won’t stay in my ears very well.  I can walk around with these in, but there’s no way I could exercise or run with them in.  I have small ears and this is a constant problem with earbuds for me.  The sound is quite good and the app that goes with them is easy to use.

title: sound quality is great
content: very good

title: Left bud sounds slightly louder
content:
I decided to get these for the for the battery life, good connection and cause Jaybirds I've owned keep breaking from sweat damage, despite being "sweat proof" with no IP rating, so these being IP56 really stood out to me.
I'm happy with why I got them, but disappointed with odd unexpected issues:

Biggest issue I have is the sound channels are unbalanced. The left bud is slightly louder than the right one. I've returned and exchanged them twice, so that's 3 pairs and I noticed the unbalance on all 3. It's very subtle, but I believe all the headsets have this issue. Seems like most people's hearing is not sensitive enough to notice but it bothers me enough to alter the balance levels on my phone to compensate.
I've talked to support and they might be adding a balance slider to the sound plus app.

Next big issue: intermittent white noise in left bud. Sometimes the left bud will have this hiss while playing audio. I can make the hiss go away if I take off the left bud (this disconnects them from each other) and put it back in my ear and the hiss goes away for a while. Again, all 3 pairs I've had experienced this issue.

Next issue: hear through (the feature where you can hear your surroundings) It cuts out constantly in the right bud, when I navigate my phone. It works consistently if I'm not using my phone, but for some reason, navigating the device causes constant annoying ambient sound skips in only one bud.

Despite these issues, I plan on keeping these, and hopefully the issues get corrected in firmware updates.

title: I bought these for 140.00 because they were randomly on sale. I would have paid more.
content: These are comfortable, well fitting, and sound great! I did a bunch of research on earbuds and these fit the bill. Well worth the money. I’ve had no issues in the 3-4 months I have owned these. I keep them in my pocket and put them in when I just need a musical escape or want to take a call. These connect easily with my iPhone and other than the app which for some reason likes to disconnect the earbuds (maybe 3 times since I’ve had these) but easily fixed. Remove the earbuds from the Bluetooth menu and reload. Boom! Fixed. Could have been user error to be honest. Rarely do I do reviews but these garnered one. Buy these earbuds and don’t look back.

title: Streamline, Great Sound, Great Microphone Quality
content: I'm very satisfied, the sound quality is great while listening to music and the microphone quality is very good while talking on my cell phone.

title: Fly restrictions
content: Not happy with the fly restrictions

I'm keeping them but honestly the sound of Bose is just better, but the noise cancelling on these is excellent.  If you want to submerse yourself in the music these basically remove outside sound completely but also have the option to shut it off so you can hear outside noise for safety i.e. a run in the city or whatever.

title: Worked great for 2.5 months...
content:
I like the form factor of these earbuds and they're very comfortable in the ear. Not the world's best sound quality, but perfectly acceptable for my needs. However, I've run into two major problems with these earbuds that make me question the quality of Jabra products.

I purchased these on December 16, 2018. On February 28, 2019 (about 2.5 months later, I began having major issues with Bluetooth pairing. Every time I go to use these with my iPad or iPhone, I first have to de-couple the Bluetooth connection, reset the earbuds and re-couple with my device. EVERY TIME. Obviously this is unacceptable.

Then, the next day, the right earbud began playing at 25-50% volume. That is, with the volume set to max on my device, I can barely hear audio from the right earbud. The left earbud plays at max volume, however.

I'm very disappointed. Given the high price I think it's unacceptable to have these major problems after less than 90 days.

I've contacted Jabra customer support (which is of course closed on weekends); we'll see if Jabra lives up to its warranty terms.

title: Call Me Impressed
content:
So I picked these up at a box store...you know.....as it was on "sale" but I see that they were the same price here on Amazon as well. Anyway I have a few electronic devices, one that came with headphones which are good. I'm using the Elite 65T for my Note 8 currently. I also have a pair of Jaybird X3s and I like those as well, but I wanted something without the "cord." I was looking at the active model, but I was also deciding between the Bose SoundSport, the Jaybird RUN, and this one. This one was the winner as the price swayed me.

It initially came with the medium tips attached to them and the fit was good, but the sound wasn't what I expected...…...but when I switched them out for the large, that made all the difference and the fit was much better. I did download the app and I'll toy with it to dial it in. I'm holding out for the 5 star on the battery life until I get more use out of it. Not bad for the price of $130 as of this writing.

If you are on the fence on this you ought to give these a try if you can get them at the $130 price.

title: Exceeded Expectations
content: i was looking for a pair of wireless earbuds after the release of the airpods. except i didnt want airpods because not only do they not stay in your ears, they do not cancel noise at all. after being referred by a friend to the jabras, i was hesitant due to the batch of 1-star reviews, but i did end up ordering them because of the credibility my friend had. i now use these earphones everyday and nothing bad has ever gone wrong. the extra features on the app is a bonus and i can now listen to music without having to unintentionally listen in on conversations. the noise cancellation works perfect, they fit in my ears and they also stay in my ears. the case is easy to open and close. the earbuds are perfect and the ONLY thing i wished was a cover for the battery case and a place where i can hook the case somewhere so i dont have to hold it or put it in my pocket and have it lightweight sticking out.

title: Not happy
content: Fall out of my lil ears all the time.  Too big

title: Solid materials, good battery, terrible CS and connection
content:
Got these after a recommendation from a friend on quality of microphone for phone calls. Working a job that requires time on the phone and out and about, I needed something that could be used for calls handfree and with quality sound.

For the first week, they did make my ears sore. But after that I had no issues with comfort, and the battery life was great and quality of case and ear buds were nice. Could connect to work phone and personal at same time with seem less transition. People could not even tell I was using an ear piece to talk with them.

However, after about 2 weeks, I could have my phone in my pocket and simply turn my head and the sound would cut out. Emailed Jabra and was simply told to reset. Did not change anything. Then, when in a somewhat loud environment (anything that wasn't within my car or at home) people could hear the outside noise more than they could hear me, even when the surrounding sound was minimal. Emailed Jabra again and they never responded.

I am not an electronic snob by any means, and these seemed so perfect for the price point. But being unable to use them for calls while walking in public completely defeated the purpose at a price of $190. Sure, they are great for listening to music if you look directly at your phone the entire time, but beyond that prepare to be disappointed if you need them for anything more. Terrible customer service and a mediocre product. There are plenty of other options out there for strictly sound quality for much cheaper. Hopefully the tech improves over time and I would love to try them again.

Luckily I was within the return window at Best Buy and got my money back. Solid materials and battery life, but no need for $190 to listen to music with these.

title: WOW

What I don't like is that they are very slippery and if not very careful you could drop one of them and never see it again. They seem to work best with my phone right in front of me. title: Not good for calls - Pretty good sound quality - Great features  - Great for exercise
content:
I'll start with the bad and work up to the good:

Poor Call Quality - I've seen these headphones advertised as having good call quality and it was even reviewed as such by CNET and several other consumer tech blogs. Got them for that reason but am very sad to say that they are really no better than the other wireless headphones on the market. They will pick up any and all background noise and drown out your voice with it. After going through Bose Soundsports, Jaybirds, and other Jabras, I think it's safe to say that there is no product that bridges active performance and call quality.

Sound Quality - I am no audiophile but will try to present a useful perspective based on my experience with other headphones. If you are also not an audiophile who geeks over "highs mids and lows" then rest assured that these are plenty good for our plebeian ears. Compared to the Bose Sound Sport Wireless that I used to own, which generally gets top sound quality reviews in the active-branded headset genre, these sound a little less bass heavy with equal clarity.

Features - The app really unlocks a lots a lot of innovative utility from these headphones. The "hearthrough" feature is actually quite good, effectively allowing you to toggle the noise cancelling feature of the headphones - I get a lot of mileage out of this feature when running and walking through the streets as well as in my open office, where I can leave it on when it's quieter (so it's easier for my teammates to get my attention when needed) and turn it off when the space gets noisy. An equalizer (that I admitted don't use that much) makes it easy to adjust the mix with an appreciable effect. Different preset modes can be customized too allowing you to control almost everything the headphones do.

Fit - This will obviously vary with each person's aural anatomy but I was really surprised by how well these buds fit and stayed in my ears. I frequently run sprints and circuits on an open field. My old Bose Sound Sport Wireless, which at that time were in my opinion the GOAT of fitness earbud fits, frequently got jostled loose during these workouts. I was then surprised that I never encountered this issue with the Jabra Elites! No matter how rough the movement, these buds stay in. I have zero anxiety about every having these just fall out of my ears and into the gutter, as is common with wireless bud owners. That being said, I do recommend that any prospective wireless bud consumer try out any buds on their ears to confirm fit before shelling out $200 as this is bound to vary.

Take one star off though because the awkward battery case:  hard to open, and unintuitive way the buds fit into their seats.  I dropped the right bud several times when struggling to open the case.

I am a former Jaybird X1, X2, X3 earbuds.  They are good, smart designs with excellent customer support.  And that's precisely it.  They required great support because they don't last long.  I sweat a lot during runs, and the Jaybirds don't have IPSxx.
