title: Utterly useless and laden with proprietary tech
content:
Part of the reason these things are so terrible is endemic to all bluetooth headphones (unlike normal headphones, you have to constantly make sure  to charge them or they'll die on you, they're expensive, they fall out of your ear), but the thing that's unique to jabra is that absolutely every single thing about them is proprietary. The foam around the earbuds, the ones that fit into your ear, keep falling out and while they'll be HAPPY to sell you another 20 dollar proprietary foam earbud.

But let's say you have an unlimited supply of foam, what else is the experience like? Miserable. The sound quality is pretty good but they're constantly slipping and falling out, the proprietary charging case (the only way to charge them, of course) only works with the proprietary gels, so if those slip off they're completely useless. I really, literally think jabra just purposely handicapped this product to scam it's customers.

Do you know what I never wanted to spend as much time as I just have thinking about? Earbuds. Do you know what these things mean that I have to spend much time out of my day thinking about EARBUD MAINTENANCE? I know tech company executives probably love that, but do you really want to spend time out of your day thinking about earbud management? I know I don't. It's the exact opposite of "It just works".

This is one of the worst products I've ever bought. Expensive, easy to break, and expensive (and impossible to fix) all for foam gels. Even if you have the money to buy replacements, and I do, they're out of stock.

Please please please do not buy these headphones. I'm not just being hyperbolic, there are absolutely, ABSOLUTELY NO benefits to them over a pair of regular earbuds, and they have severe drawbacks that render them unusable.

title: Not worth it

title: Broke after 4 months, warranty not honored
content: Well I liked them for the first three months until these sound reduction issue showed up. I wish I would have researched more before buying. Theres a bad batch and or the sound app is causing an issue.  Right earbud all of a sudden lost 90% of its volume. I contacted jabra via email  for warranty  replacement. No reply  I had to call a few days later to see if they recieved my email, they did just ignored it.  They played dumb like none else is having this issue. I jumped through all the hoops unpaired, updated, uninstalled sound app, reset earbuds, sent in copy of receipt.  It took forever for them to reply  after that.  Dealt with Felipe  and Josh.  Finally they said they their shipper would send a return label and for me to send back the earbuds and case,  then they would inspect it. And then order a new one and when it arrived they would send it out.  (Online reviews say this process takes weeks)  I said ok.  Waited, never recieved.  Dont know where to send and I am not shipping back $160 earbuds back to corporate without a return slip.  Called them up again after a few days,  they said they cant issue another return label because they paid for one that I never recieved and I would have to pay for the shipping. I said fine email me info on where to ship, waited for days never recieved.  Seems they want to make it as difficult as possible to fulfill a warranty  claim. I sent out email after email to the generic warranty email that some random person checks,  finally recieved  an email back from Sarah apologizing  and saying a return label will be sent out right away, I thanked her and waited  for days.  Nothing.  So far this is about 7 weeks with a right earbud at 10% volume.  Sent out an email a day for a few days  and  uninstalled the earbuds, reset them, uninstalled the sound app, cleaned up the charging case and earbud  contacts with a qtip and rubbing alcohol.  Then the right earbud started working better maybe 80% volume. And now the left earbud is at only 20% volume  sent in another email inquiring if they have heard of this, if it is a battery issue or the software.  Got a response back real quick from Olivia saying I voided the warranty  by "performing unauthorized repairs"  at this point it has been two months, of broken $160 earbuds.  Manufacture cost is probably  $20 , but they chose to have an unsatisfied  customer have to leave a bad review and let friends family and coworkers know dont by jabra they no good/defective.

title: Great quality
content: Headphones it working great so far no complaints.Headphones it working great so far no complaints. Sound quality in fit is perfect for me.

title: Good build quality
content: These Jabra Elite Active 65t earphones feel sturdy and pair easily with my phone. Sound is tight with little sound stage, with adequate bass and smooth mids. Highs may tend to sound a little sharp on certain tracks so i have set my earphone equalizer setting to compensate for that all the time.

title: Great sound quality.
content: Very goo sound quality, with easy to use on/off and volume on the buds.  Good battery life, with an easy to use carrying case/charger.  Fit my ears well and are very comfortable.

title: Customer Service Issues
content: First of all, for the first 4 months that I had these, they were amazing. Of course I have other wired headphones with better sound quality, but when it comes to an wireless earbud that stays in my ear, is sweat resistance for workouts and has an above average sound quality, these are awesome. The biggest complaint and the reason for this review is the lackluster customer service. Everyone that I did speak to was very kind, but response time was poor and I was not offered an acceptable solution. My right ear bud started to go bad 3 weeks ago and I contacted support to open a case on 4/10. They had me go through different diagnostics to try and solve the problem but ultimately it did not fix the issue. I then had to go through the site to file a claim to have the product replaced. It is now 2 weeks later and I finally received the return label. The problem is that they will not ship the new ear buds until the current ones are received. I travel constantly and will be leaving the country for 3 weeks in five days therefore I called customer service to ask if there was another solution... even if I gave them a credit card number to send out a new pair so I would have them before I travel but apparently the only solution they can offer me is for me to return the current buds which will take 3-5 days to arrive and then they could expedite the new ones to me in 2 days. For the price of this product and the fact that they stopped working correctly after only 4 months, I feel that the company should do more to remedy the problem. Now, I will have to buy a different pair of wireless headphones before I leave because my current pair does not work. I will not be buying Jabras this time.

title: Good, not great.
content:
They're OK.

If we're being honest, they're worse than a decent pair of wired IMEs.  I ended up buying them because my new phone doesn't have a headphone jack, and I figured I'd try something new.

If we compare them to the other "True Wireless" ones I've tried, they do pull ahead in terms of feature and overall performance.

My top considerations:
- getting a good fit can be hard, but it's doable given the tips provided.  I ended up having a different sized left and right tip.
- they are comfortable enough for the battery life.  I wouldn't imagine wearing them for more than four hours.
- the charging case is a little cheap, but it works fine
- connectivity is decent, but I still had some dropouts
- noise isolation is just OK, and volume doesn't go high enough for some aspects of my commute

title: the sound quality is good, they block out the outside noise very well
content: FINALLY, a pair of wireless earbuds that actually work.  Hallelujah! I've had the Jabra Elite Active 65t's for a couple of weeks now.  I've ran with them 5 or 6 times, I wear them while lifting weights and just hanging out by the pool.  The setup and connection was very simple, the sound quality is good, they block the outside noise very well, and they stay in the ear perfectly.  So far, I have no complaints.  I strongly recommend them if you're looking to cut the annoying wire on traditional earbuds.  Good work Jabra!

title: Possible hardware flaw with HearThrough.
content:
I've had these earbuds for a couple of days as of this writing and my experience started out well. After installing the app and tweaking the settings, I took it for the usual test and burn-in period. They sound great and look nice (I got the navy-copper color). You can find general reviews online so I won't bore you with the specs and such.

My problem with them is the HearThrough feature. I specifically got these earbuds because of this feature, which utilizes the onboard mic on each bud to pick up ambient sound so you can hear your surroundings even if you have them on and listening to music, as they have pretty good passive noise isolation. Unless the ambient sound is LOUD, it doesn't get picked up, i.e., you don't hear it. For example, I can barely hear mouse clicks even though I'm less than two feet away from it, and even then, I'm probably making the connection that it's supposed to be making a clicking sound. I tried to have a conversation with someone with this setting turned on and it simply did not work.

Furthermore, I noticed a crackling sound on the left earbud whenever HearThrough is on and the mic is picking up a high-pitched sound, such as jingling keys, glass hitting glass (as in microscope slides), etc.

Without HearThrough off, the buds are great. But I feel like at this price point, everything should work. The last firmware was released on December 2018... if it's a software issue and there's a fix, it should have been released by now, which leads me to believe it's a hardware issue. I contacted the Jabra customer support so hopefully they have something.

title: It's important to know that the manual is not there just for show, it's legit pretty useful.
content: I liked the sound quality specially the bass and I slightly dislike the color of it #allblackisbetter. I used it primarily to workout.

title: Not tight to head through runing
content: It sleeper from ears

title: Far Too Irriating to Use in Real Life
content: Using the buttons was far too finicky and quickly annoying, so returned.

title: Not for “active” athletes as described
content: I purchased these as a Christmas gift for myself. They worked great until the warmer weather came around. I am now noticing that they fall out of my ears quite a bit when I begin to sweat. This is very disappointing because the description reads active and they don’t perform the way they are advertised.

title: Great quality
content: Sounds better than the majority of wireless earbuds and has a good battery life. Only complaint and only reason I didn't give it 5 stars is because the buds don't stick in the case magnetically like other brands do. So I have to be really careful when putting them in or taking them out or else they'll fall out

title: Na
content: Not as loud as I would like

title: Don't bother buying anything else
content: These are awesome.  They fit perfectly, sound great, and work with little to no ort.  Just take them out and stick them in your ear and you are all set.  Highly recommend.

title: Excellent sound, fit, battery life *and* active noise canceling
content: These are tremendous. Excellent sound, fit, battery life *and* active noise canceling. Plus they sort of disappear into my ear. Highly recommend

title: Great fit, comfortable, sounds great
content: Love everything about them, they sound great and fit well. They seemed to stand despite moving around a lot. The only issue is in the left ear turning the volume up-and-down or forwarding tracks. You have to actually depress the button and it hurts your ears and there's really no place to hold them to keep them still or from going deeper into your ear because you have to press the button a little on the hard side to make it work.

title: Must Buy!
content: Great earbuds! They have been a pleasure to use. I’ve had them for almost three months now and don’t have many complaints. My wife has used them and she says they seem very large feeling in her ears. Not the silicone tip but the unit as a whole. They are definitely smaller than a lot of other options like Bose. Battery life is awesome! I’m working my way toward heavy user but right now one charge on the case and it will last me for a week or more. Love the red (honestly looks more orange to me). I do feel self conscious wearing them out in public because they are definitely noticeable. But that is the way I wanted it anyhow.

title: Easily top notch earbuds.
content: These things are awesome. My ears are on the small side so the left one fits pretty tight. That being said, my right ear fits perfectly and I don't even notice it inserted. Has really good sound and feels well built. I like that they don't stick out really far which makes them less noticable. The battery lasts longer than I need and I like the way the case charges them automatically. Phone calls work and the other person never complains about how I sound. For the truly wireless earbuds, these are the best ones out there.

title: Great earbuds overall, could use a better fix for the left earbud sound/connection challenges.
content: I think these overall are great. I rated a 3 on sound quality only because the left earbud goes out and does not always connect consistently and the left neoprene like earbud doesn't quite fit perfectly.  I wish there were added options for sized adapters on the earbuds to allow for caring shaped ears.

title: Great sound quality, fit, battery life
content: I had tried about eight different brands of wireless earbuds over the past several years. I have smaller ear canals and had trouble finding wireless earbuds that fit properly/stable during my ultra and trail runs. Finally, I found the Jabra 65t. They fit well, are stable during long runs, especially on trails, have great sound quality, and great battery life. I like to be able to hear what's going on around me, so the HearThrough feature is a really nice feature.

title: Good earbuds
content: Good ear phones. Perfect for workouts running, biking, elliptical and weight training. If the tips were foam instead of silicone it would provide better sound. I bought some foam tips after using the jabra earphones and there’s a big difference. Still a good product though

title: Good earbuds except the fit...
content:
Good sound quality. Very easy to pair and connect. It automatically connects to your phone after opening the box. The battery experience is actually better than I expect. I am not saying it is longer. Since the box can charge the earbuds, it feels like the earbuds have pretty good battery life. But, of course, I never use them for more than 3 hours for one time.
The only thing I don't like is it does not fit my ear very well. There is one part of the earbuds is slightly larger than my ear. So I couldn't put them deep in my ear. It really sucks that way. I may return this just because of that.

title: So far great
content:
Seriously good sound for such a small ear bud. Had issues with blue connecting to two devices but tech support helped me out with a unit reset. Comfortable in the ear, don’t poke out like Mushrooms the way the Bose Sports do (which are the most comfortable in ear headphones), and don’t look like your brains are leaking out of your ears like the iPods.
These are not noise canceling but the noise rejection from the fit is very good. Walked around costco and couldn’t hear a thing.

title: great fit
content: The kids love them and they stay put during work outs.

title: They are the best truly wireless earbuds you will find for making calls in 2018
content:
The sound for music is incredible. The fit for my strangely shaped ears is very tight, but that is on me. At least these things have no chance of falling out. I suffer from extremely sensitive ears and have an embarrassingly small ear canal. After dealing with some discomfort and pain I found a position that works very well.  In fact, I keep them in my ears every chance I get for as long as I am able to and my ears just don't get fatigued and that's saying a lot for me.

I love the built-in white noise options, they are amazing when I want to tune out the world and get focused on study.  However, the hear-through option doesn't let me hear enough of the outside world to keep them in around my wife and kids all the time, but the hear-through works well enough.

They do not have the best sound canceling options when making phone calls in very loud windy weather, but in normal situations they are great. No one calling me can tell I'm on the phone with earbuds.  It feels magic to be not only handsfree but truly wireless. Stepping away from my phone with earbuds in works great if I pop downstairs for a sandwich.

Connecting with Google Assistant is akin to a Star-Trek Next Generation moment. It works amazing with Google Assistant on my phone and if I had an Amazon Echo Dot set up, I'll bet it would work just as well. It does take some practice to push the buttons. The charger case is amazing and it's not actually a big deal they don't get held in place with rare-earth magnets. It would be nice if they did, but it really isn't necessary.  The trick is to squeeze the sides of the case very firmly (long-ways) while you pop open the top. I never run out of batteries although I got down to 9% after two very long sessions.

The app interface is good enough and I love the preset equalizer options to switch from listening to audible.com and podcasts to rock n roll music.

If the phone calls had the better active-sound cancellation and the hear-through option could pick up the soft-spoken people in my life I'd give these earbuds more than 5 stars. But there is room for improvement on these two very important features.

I've read every review and watched every youtube video on these earbuds. I've spent an embarrassingly long time researching all the front-runners of truly wireless earbuds of 2018 and Jabra Elite Active OR Jabra Elite Sport beat them all.

Also Amazon delivered them to me by 8:45 PM the same day I ordered them around 10:00 AM.  good job.

title: Just too uncomfortable
content:
Everything good and bad people have said about these earbuds are true. They are great except for two big deal-breakers for me

1. They are uncomfortable. When I wore them for moderate lengths of time they really started to make my ears sore, to the point of causing me to dread putting them on. And if I don't want to wear it, why bother?
2. They block out noise really well. Well that may sound like a positive, it actually was an annoyance because I would have to physically take out my earbuds when I wanted to hear something to talk to someone. But because they are wireless earbuds, I can't just let them dangle, so I have to awkwardly hold on to them in the meantime and risk losing them. Sure there's a hear-through mode, but the sound quality is pretty bad, and to activate it you have to painfully press on your earbud twice. Also my main use case is running outside, and the lack of sound permeability is actually dangerous for that.

Meanwhile I tried out the Airpods and am extremely satisfied. Sometimes I forget I even have them in.

title: Design and built quality
content: I liked the design and shape of the wireless earbuds. The app is amazing. You can easily update the firmware of the earbuds and has user manual integrated. The earbud fits in your ear nicely (kind of snug tight) and doesn't fall out during workout activities. Also it is waterproof somehow (or sweat proof). The only downside is the sound quality. It let me down on this. With some adjustment to the equalizer over the app, you can improve the quality of the sound, but the quality of sound is not near apple EarPods or similar Bose products.

title: Connection is terrible
content: If I put my phone in my jacket pocket, these no longer connect...  WHAT?! It's 3 feet away from my ears and in a cloth pocket. I got these for commuting and flying and all sort of situations when you would want to use wireless. They hurt my ears after about 45 minutes or so. But the connection is AWFUL. When connected, sound is good, but for it to not stay connected while in a pocket on my person, that's ridiculous. I really wanted to try a brand other than Apple, but my friend's airpods work when shes 2 rooms away from her phone. These do not compete with that.

title: Like the pass through feature so you can hear ambient sound.
content: Has an earbud locator function, pass through to hear ambient sound (have a conversation with someone), and tone adjustments.  Lasts about 6 hours of continuous use.

title: Love these earbuds
content: Love these earbuds... Sound is great. Nice isolation when needed and very good hear through feature. I am able to listen to music at my desk. Also great for when I walk outside and keep me aware of incoming traffic and people around me. Like these better over the Sony Xperia Ear Duo

title: Great for a true music listener!!! Great sound quality!!
content: So first off I love music!! I’m very particular about sound quality and I have owned a lot of ear buds!! But these things are great! Sound so clear no distortion, great hands free calling and they fit really well even during workouts. They don’t fall out and they block out all the noise. You even can cycle between noise cancellation I am a fan of jabra after trying these hands down! The only thing is the volume don’t go really high but the noise cancellation is so good you don’t need it too!

title: Not a Fan
content: These earbuds don't stay in ears very well. They feel cheap and also the charging holder is two cheap pieces of metal, the buds don't snap into place like you might think they would, so there's a constant fear that you may have put them in wrong and they won't be charged for when you need them. The other thing is the connect between the earbuds is terrible! Half the time I've used them they connect one bud to my phone and I have to spent 10-15 minutes trying to get the other bud to work and the app really doesn't help beyond informing you that one bud isn't connected... These are truly awful, I've used much cheaper in cost bluetooth earbuds that have been eons better quality than these.

title: Very cool earbuds
content: At first it took time to find the perfect fit, but after that, the product was very nice, confortable and has a great sound.

title: Truly Wireless, Truly Wonderful
content:
Before buying a pair of these Jabras, I had been using the ROC yolk BT buds.

Those have wonderful sound, but they also have a yoke that goes around your neck, with wires connecting to the buds.

So when I heard how good the "truly wireless" Jabra Elite 65t's were, I decided I had to try them.

Well, I can testify that they are as good as advertised.

They sound great, look great, fit great.  And they offer a new level of ergonomic polish and convenience.

Initial setup was pretty simple, although it's annoying that Jabra makes you download two apps rather than one.  (One app is Sound +, the primary control app with EQ and options settings; the other is -- um, I don't know, an app that's necessary for reasons I can't explain...)

My first impression of the Elite 65t's sound was that it lacked low-end punch, especially in comparison to the ROC's, which, well, rock. Fortunately, simply by engaging the Bass Boost EQ setting, I ensured that all was again right with the world.

Now the little Jabras sound splendid, with a full bass, detailed mid-range, and crystal highs.  The sound stage is also wide, if not quite as far-reaching as that provided by the ROC's optional 360 mode.

But let's talk about ergonomics.  Take these buds out of the charging case, and they turn on automatically.  Put the first one in your ears, and you'll hear confirmation that it's connected to your device.  Put the second one in, and you'll hear a brief report on the battery charge status.

Similarly, replace the buds in their case, and they shut off automatically.  In addition, any time you open the case, an LED on the outside of the case briefly shows the case's battery charge status, while an LED inside shows the buds' charge status.  Pop a bud out of your ear, and your music pauses automatically until you replace the bud.

The buds supposedly play for five hours on one charge, and the case provides fifteen hours of charge.  That's more than enough for my needs, whether I'm working out at the gym or walking around town.

Then there's the way the 65t's fit -- deep into your ear canals, where they stay put remarkably well, whether I'm working out riding a LifeCycle or striding around briskly doing errands.

They also lie pretty flat in your ears, looking neither like Frankenstein electrodes nor ugly white mucus dripping from your ears like the infamous EarPods.

At the time of this writing, I can't comment on how well these Jabras handle phone calls, as I use them almost exclusively for music listening.  Nevertheless, they have four microphones, two on each side, so they're supposed to pick up your voice very well.

Because of their deep fit in the ears, the Jabras offer quite good passive noise cancellation.  Good enough, in fact, that the manufacturer has a "pass through" option you enable with two taps on the right bud, allowing more ambient sound to enter the mix.  I do find this helpful when I'm talking to a store clerk, making it unnecessary to remove either or both buds.

Finally, though these aren't as waterproof as the Active and Sport buds in the Jabra truly wireless range, they do seem to resist sweat quite well -- I haven't had any problems despite working up a good sweat after twenty minutes on the LifeCycle.

The only downside of these Jabras is the price.  They ain't cheap, but they do go on sale from time to time, so if you set a price tracker, you will probably get lucky before too long.

Otherwise the 65t's are music to my ears and likely to yours as well.

PROS:

* Excellent sound (with Bass Boost enabled).
* Superior ergonomics.
* Good looks, secure fit.
* Five hours of battery life in buds, fifteen hours in charger.
* Battery case recharges via USB in two hours or less.

CONS:

* Somewhat pricey, but worth it.

title: Great
content: Excellent quality

title: Great Sound, Good Features
content: Will never go back to a wired headset, I love how these feel, fit, and sound compared to other bluetooth devices. 5.0 is great. The only thing I don't like is proximity pause / play, its cool but if I want to take one ear out and continue my music I have to turn the left ear off first, its just annoying I wish there was a disable/enable for that feature

title: Disappointed!
content:
I bought these even after reading the negative reviews that talked about issues with connection and sound. Unfortunately, they are all true.

1. After a few weeks of use, the earbuds had a hard time connecting with my phone and would just make a staccato noise - in order to fix this, I would have to manually restart the earbuds every time I wanted to use them.
2. I had issues with the connection being extremely inconsistent. I'm an avid cyclist and wanted to use these for my bike rides, but I found them frustrating to use because of the connection issue.
3. The earphone volumes are not balanced. The left side is definitely louder than the right side - this is confirmed by MANY users. Jabra can't seem to updated their firmware to fix this issue (I'm sure they've tried many times)
4. The Jabra app is almost useless (at least on android). It doesn't really offer any special features apart from an EQ selection, but you can do this through most music apps already.
5. Jabra support is incredibly slow in their responses and they just send the same instructions listed in the manual. Jabra finally got back to me and offered to send me a replacement, but by then I was already frustrated with the product and the service.
6. I decided to reach out to Amazon about these issues and they were kind enough to accept a later return (thanks Amazon!)

The only good thing was the sound quality. It's got a great flat response that works well for calls and music. It's not a GREAT sound quality, but it works!

title: Not for taking calls. Don't buy if you want to speak to people
content:
Like the sound (a lot)
Like the comfort
Like the controls
Like the battery life
Case is a good size, but needs magnetic attachment as I've dropped the case from about coffee table height and had the buds pop out and shoot across the floor.
Hate, hate, hate the microphones. People cannot hear me. I have a Jabra steel headset and have never heard a complaint or anyone ask me to repeat myself in noisy and windy environments, so Jabra knows how to make microphones.  But I've taken calls in a soundproof booth with these and people have trouble hearing me. This makes them useless in an office environment. A shame, so close.

title: Poor Customer Support and Warranty
content:
The Sound+ App is great! But The product it supports, Jabra Elite 65t, has extreme performance issues, and customer support is non-responsive.

For example:

1. I contacted customer service by completing warranty request form concerning the charging case clasp is broken after only a few months which is still under warranty, no response.
2. The right ear bud has stopped turning off when placed inside charging case, problematic.  The earbud then randomly connects to my iPhone while inside charging case causing me to miss phone calls, unacceptable. Still under warranty.
3. The right earbud doesn’t automatically connect to my iPhone’s bluetooth when removed from charging as it once did, aggravating. Still under warranty.

All of this is aggravating and it is irresponsible for Jabra to not even address my issues.  I have seen that many other customers have address these same issues with NO RESPONSE!

The Jabra Elite 65t, for the price, should be much better and the company should stand behind their product better!  Again, I have submitted a warranty request and still no response.

title: Sound quality
content: I bought these mostly because I wanted to able to take calls if I needed to while working out. I have to say they work really well and no one knows the difference. A bit pricey but so far I am pretty happy with them.

title: Nice
content: Nice earbuds perfect shape and high quality sounds

title: Please read before purchasing
content:
I am very disappointed with my purchase of the Jabra Elite 65t and my experience after the sale. I am keenly aware that losing a single customer is negligible to a huge company in the context of a global market. With customer service being unable or unwilling to resolve my issue, the best I can hope for is to prevent other customers from making the same mistake by posting my experience to every website where this product is sold. This review may be lengthy but I will be as factual as possible.

I purchased the Jabra Elite 65t from the Jabra official web store on 3/29/19 in new, unopened condition. They were shipped by 4/1/19 and I received the item very quickly.

I used the earbuds for about 3 weeks on about 4 occasions for a combined total of 6 hours. I only used the earbuds in an office setting at work. I was happy with the sound quality and several features such as the hearthrough and microphone for calls. Bass was lacking according to my own music tastes, but for such a small driver as well as the true wireless technology I was pleased overall. The Sound+ app was useful and I talked several of my coworkers into purchasing them as well.

The problems began when I needed to charge my earbuds and realized that the notification LEDs on the charging case would not respond. After several hours plugged in and using various cables/charging blocks (including the supplied cable), my earbuds we’re still at 0%. I notified Tech Support on 4/27/19 that my earbuds appeared to be working but the charging case was defective. I received a response quickly the same day and was told to reinstall firmware. I followed the instructions and the problem persisted.

I immediately followed up with Tech Support on 4/27/19 after following their instructions to inform them that my problem was ongoing. I received no further communication from them.

Now outside of the 30-day return window, I contacted Jabra customer service by phone on or around 4/30/19 and restated my problem. The customer service rep seemed disinterested and slightly annoyed but was not overtly disagreeable.

Eventually my case wound up with the warranty department and on 5/2/19 I received an email showing an invoice for a new charger case. While this was an acceptable resolution, I was not informed that the item is currently on backorder. After receiving no further updates since 5/2/19, I contacted customer service by phone on 5/22/19. The customer service rep was polite and finally informed me that they were not expecting my replacement item to be available until the end of June which I find unacceptable.

I asked if there were any other options available to me which would arrive sooner and she suggested a total replacement of all the equipment. The process would require Jabra to send me a shipping label. Afterwards, I would be required to return the equipment and upon verifying receipt, Jabra would send me a new set of the Elite 65ts. Incidentally, this would not only cause me additional inconvenience but would also arrive by the end of June.

I have worked customer service and would never disrespect a representative by raising my voice, cursing, or being generally unpleasant. Realizing that this experience would not end satisfactorily for me, I thanked her for her time and began writing this review.

Overall I was pleased with the earbuds themselves, but a product that cannot charge and therefore does not work is useless to me - thus the reason for my 1-star review. This was my first and last experience with Jabra products. For the price I paid I expected a bit more. Please be aware that if you have any issues with the product it may take months to resolve.

title: Bluetooth connection constantly disconnecting
content:
Really disappointing product and support.  Earbuds connected fine out of the box, but over time would constantly forget the bluetooth connection and have to be re-paired with the device.  Even then, after re-pairing, if you didn't listen to music immediately they would drop the connection within 5 minutes and have to be re-paired.

Attempt to receive support through both Amazon and Jabra has been disappointing, as both basically said to update the software and re-pair the device which I've done multiple times.

Don't waste your money.

title: Best wireless headphones
content: I bought these headphones as an everyday headphone and I have not been disappointed. The fit is perfect, they stay in while working out and are sweat resistant. The noise cancelling works very well and is great that it can be turned on/off. They are a little expensive but are totally worth it. Compared to other headphones in this price range these are my favorite by far.

title: They were great until...
content:
I bought these for my son as a gift.  He loved them!  Until...

The right earbud now doesn't realize when it is in the case.  He can't tell if it is charging and it doesn't turn on when he takes it out of the case like it should.  Bigger bummer - he contacted Jabra, got a ticket number, and now crickets...  What gives?  These aren't even a month old!  It's not like these were $10 headphones.  Have others had this same experience?

title: Great for Commute
content:
I really love these for my commute on a train because they really block out the extra (loud) noise to be able to enjoy the music or whatever you might be listening to.  I don't love them for this reason in the office because I cannot hear what I need to hear when I'm in the office but that may be something you're looking for so in anycase, they block out extra noise really well.  They almost sound like they plug your ears though, which can be annoying when youre walking and hear every step, if that makes sense.

With that being said.. the hear-thru mode is quite shitty and sounds wonky so I only use these when I want to immerse myself into the music because I don't like how the hear thru mode sounds. (it sounds fake? and maybe every so slightly delayed)

I agree with others when they say that the left one for some reason doesn't stay ini the ear as much as the right ear.  but overall these have great sound and when theyre on and running they are great.  I use them mostly on my commutes, and use my apple airpods in the office.  The airpods are still the winner for convenience and ease of use.  But the sound is better on these (but perhaps because it plugs up your ears so much so that you can't hear anything else?) still good. would recommend regardless.

title: Not worth the money
content: I bought these with hopes they would be my next amazing gym headphones but these are absolutely terrible. They would not stay in my ears no matter which size rubber bud I tried. My first workout with them I spent the whole time adjusting them trying to get them to stay in my ears. They’re also a little heavy for how small they are so I think that contributed to the problem also. The sound quality is also very poor. They sound like your cheap headphones from Walmart. Do not waste your money on these. You might as well buy the Bose or Beats headphones.

title: Fall out of my small ears easily
content:
I tried all three bud sizes. Not a one kept the relatively heavy buds in my ears as I shook my head.  I didn't turn them on,  just packed them up for return. They just cost too much to mess with that. Normally I wouldn't review on fit alone, but others have had this issue.  I've got relatively small ears. Usually the large gels solve any poor fit issues,  but these things are just too heavy for it to matter.

I can't say don't try them,  but definitely have a low threshold for sending them back for not fitting.  Decide before the return window is up. I already had another pair in mind as a backup plan.

title: It's more like 4.5 stars - its not perfect but pretty close.
content:
These are awesome! They work great and I've had no quality issues.  As product design engineer, I will tell you its quite a feat that this team pulled off.  Are there areas to improve - yes! But from every other wireless earbud I've tried these are the best so far.  They do not fall out when running or cycling hard and they are reasonably comfortable.  Everyone has also commented how great my calls have been.  For the next gen I would improve the following if anyone from Jabra is reading this:
1. The snap on the case is a little finiky - needs some improvement here.
2. The left and right buttons are great but the UX is a bit rough.  Can we add swiping rather than a push button.  Pushing a button is hard to do when running and can hurt if you've been wearing these for over an hour.
3. More size ranges of earbud silicone sleeves.  Medium is too loose and Large is a bit too tight.
4. The app needs a little bit of work.  I'd add shortcuts to controls screens. eg. pass-through.

Update: I can't Skip a song on the earbud without upping the volume so I changed this review to 4 stars.  Like I mentioned before the UI needs work.

Otherwise - its still going strong and love them.  Wish I waited for the sports version.  oh well.

title: Great product
content: Really happy with the Jabra Elite Active 65T wireless earpieces.  I've tried a bunch of other manufacturers but was never satisfied with the fit or performance.  The pass through sound feature is the best.  It allows for me to hear my surroundings and still have a tight fit.  Great product!

title: Failed. And Jabra knows better.
content:
Worked well for one day then broke down into static and pops. Resetting didn't help and Amazon finally replaced them, while I also was opening a case with Jabra directly. And then some web searching, and Jabra's comments about mystical magnetic coupling between the buds, turned up that Jabra has known for a long time that any electromagnetic interference can cause this. If you are two feet from a lamp cord or wiring in the wall, or perhaps a Qi charger? They won't work right. Great if you are outdoors or in the car, totally unreliable around AC wiring. And Jabra apparently knows this?!
 Disappointing, especially because once you get them fitting right, they stay in tight and comfortably. Hearing calls in both ears, a great plus. Many good features but a killer flaw if you want to use them at home.

title: Great sound and stability
content: Bought as a gift for my son.  He says the sound is incredible and they stay in his ears as he works out.

title: They’ Great
content: Daily for phone conversations

title: Already breaking
content: I’ve had these for less than a month and they are already crackling and sound like they are blown out. Other than being  aesthetically pleasing (which they really are), Jabras are not worth the money you pay for them. Hinestly, I would just buy those ugly AirPods instead. At least you know they’ll work.

title: I wish I would've gotten another color
content: Maybe it's just me but from the picture, I expected the Gold Beige to be a two tone gold color. Its mostly just plain beige which makes it look like a medical device. I like the earbuds but really do not like this color....

title: Nice earbud to own
content: Overall quality is pretty good. Battery life is excellent especially with case to recharge but batteries last about 4 hours on one charge. I am an over the head headphones person. Last pair was beat studio so had to get use to sound difference with an earbud but after a couple days it grew on me. Sometimes not to often they do have to be readjusted as so they do not fall out. Very happy with my purchase I would recommend.

title: Great pair of wireless earbuds, one of the best I've tried
content: These earbuds are definitely worth it. Although they are priced somewhat high compared to many other wireless earbuds, their sound quality is unmatched (compared to $160 and below options- haven't tested Sennheiser's $300 wireless earbuds) and their battery life of 5 hours+ is great. In addition, they fit comfortably, have excellent connection, and come with different sized tips for people with smaller/bigger ears than normal. They are a solid alternative to the AirPods and have the same features as Apple's product (auto pairing after initial setup, music stops when you take the earbuds out of your ear, etc.). Finally, these earbuds are great for people who work out and prefer greater noise cancelling capability due to their in-ear design.

title: No Bass
content: I read several reviews on these.  I currently have the Jabra Elite Sport but the blue tooth connection drops frequently so I thought I would try the Active 65t.  The Sport set has superior sound.  There is no bass at all in the 65t.  I am returning them.

title: Great product at great value
content: Great sound and works so convenient for me. I downloaded the app that went with it and I have the setting to allow sound through. well, it didn't allow enough sound through when I wanted to hear others speak. Otherwise, great stuff!!!

title: Great for working
content: If you're listening in an area with a lot of interference they tend to pop in and out. I work in maintenance and use them throughout the night. I work around 480v and whenever you get too close to panels they lose signal for a sec. I guess that's a good warning \/(0~0)\/ they were uncomfortable at the beginning but I'm still kinda getting used to them. For me at least if I don't have them in just the right position in my ears they hurt. But great sound quality for what it is.

title: Cool Device Poor Sound Quality
content:
I wish I liked this product better, having researched a bunch of different wireless earbuds on the market the JE 65T seemed to get the best reviews by techblogs so I chose to ignore the 3.5 star avg amazon review, but I was wrong for doubting y'all.

Pros:
Long batter life, charging case makes it very easy
Cool features, music stops playing when you take an earbud out, wireless controls are a great feature
App is great (much better than bose connect), cool function let's you control EQ
Solid material quality

Cons:
Really bad sound quality,  I mean really bad, tried tweaking the EQ levels but didn't do much
Constant static in left earbud even without the "hearthrough mode" function on
Shotty connectivity, often cuttting in and out at times
Painful, the earbuds were hurting the cartiledge in my ears
Not snug for my ears, tried all 3 earbud adapters, still had trouble keeping them in while exercising

Bottom line, the technology isn't there yet.  Has lots of potential with all the cool features but the two most important features for me were sound quality and fit, both of which were very poor.  Had to return this item, going to wait it out another year or so and hope the technology comes around.

HTH

title: support is not good, product is fine (until it's not)
content: I purchased these in September 2018, they worked fine until a couple of weeks ago.  The left earbud was not quite dead, but you couldn't really hear it.  so I sent it in to Jabra support (even though they originally said I didn't have to send it back).  It appears that you have to call them if you want to move the process for return forward, and calling doesn't work either at certain points in the process.  They told me yesterday that there is a shortage of replacements, so I don't really know how long this replacement is going to take.

title: Great
content: I love these.  I work out and sweat like crazy. No issues.  The sound is better then my BOSE and I love the true wireless capability.

title: Stopped charging after 4 months
content: They worked great for about 4 months. Now they won’t take a charge and customer service has been completely unhelpful. I am bummed they were wonderful when they worked.

title: very uncomfortable
content: Very uncomfortable and because they are so small they are difficult to hold onto when inserting.  The size is also a problem for adjusting volume.

title: Great battery, Great Bass, Amazing Surround, and GREAT RANGE!
content: I absolutely am addicted to these headphones, they are great all around and fantastic for phone conversations as well. I love that I can adjust the EQ in the app and have various "scenes".

title: Sonic Heaven
content: I have been using headphones for almost 50 years. I have heard music through just about every manifestation and permutation over those years. I can honestly say that my Jabari wireless earbuds are simply the most amazing. Before I bought these I was using the large wired and wireless Master and Dynamic M60. They are very, very good but the Jabari Elite 65t is as good in every respect. What matters to me most? Clarity of sound and these earbuds have that is spades. I use them mostly when I am walking and I hope they will be my companions for many years to come.

title: Poor sound quality and no bass
content:
We tried master reset and firmware reset and no sound improvement. Customer care walked us through eq and other multiple adjustments and nothing. All the reviews we read mention nothing about poor sound, makes me think we got a lemon. I will reach out to Jabra customer care again for further direction. Will adjust rating if corrected or replacement works better.
Update: after multiple hrs on hold with customer service they cannot correct the poor sound issue. I did notice more recent bad sound reviews, I am not the only one that feels this way. These are going back today.

title: Good sound in both earbuds
content:
I've had these wireless earbuds for a week. So though I can't speak to its experience on a long-term basis, I can say a few thoughts on it so far.

Pros:
1. Good sound in both earbuds. No distortion and fairly balanced.
2. Clear when on the phone with others. I received the feedback that I was easy to understand and they were not even aware when I was driving or walking around.
3. Easy to pair with my phone and use. Sometimes I use one and other times I use both. The right earbud is the primary one with controls, so if you're using one, this would be the one.
4. Good fit in ear. I have never used wireless earbuds before and I had some reservations based on some previous reviews. The package comes with a variety of earbuds to choose from, so it isn't a big deal. I switched out the original one and fit right in. I even got a tattoo for 3 hours the other day and was listening to music the whole time while lying on the table -- no falling out, aches, or itches in my ear as previous reviewers described.

Cons:
1. Not for sports use. The other day I took a brisk walk and it was warm outside. When I began to get sweaty and warm, the fit of the earbud started to change. I would imagine that it is not an ideal choice if you are going out for a run or doing an active sport.
2. Charging case a bit tricky to open. I use my nail but it takes some getting used to.

All in all, well worth the money and I am satisfied :)

title: Highly Recommend
content: I love these. Better than apple ear pods.

title: The earbuds don't fit and don't stay in my ears ...
content: The earbuds don't fit and don't stay in my ears. Even when I used the different tips that came with the earbuds. I tried other tips I purchased too. The buds should go in deeper. When I increase the volume above 75%, I hear a pop.

title: Great sounds and perfect for workouts
content: I use these for workouts and running and have had no issues with them. Sounds quality is excellent. The fit is pretty good, I don't have issues with them falling out but they are not the most comfortable after an hour of exercise. I don't use the app or heart monitor very much since I use other methods to track my exercise but from playing around with it, it does give you a complete set of data to help you maximize your workouts. Would definitely recommend this to my friends

title: Okay sound quality, kind of uncomfortable
content:
Its noise cancellation is amazing, at the cost of comfort. Using these for a long period of time is uncomfortable and kind of hurts the ears. The sensation of having my ears completely sealed was also quite unsettling.

The sound quality started off strong, but quickly deteriorated after a short while of using the earphones.

The battery life is very good, but you can't extend it by using one side at a time, because when you take one side off, they both shut down until you put it on again. This means you also cannot share it with a friend.

title: The product works but the sound isn’t great
content: The sound on these is tinny and no bass their “equalizer” app does nothing to improve sound quality

title: great sound plus they won't fall out while doing sports
content: I use the earbuds for riding my bike.

title: Poor quality
content: Broken at the second months I purchased it. Low quality product.

title: More than happy with the purchase
content:
I ride rapid transit as a part of my daily commute and have been wearing disposable ear plugs due to the loud screeching wheel noises caused by a poorly maintained train system. I wanted to buy a headset with noise cancellation, but as I researched headsets I found that noise isolation may work as well at a much lower cost. That lead me to the Jarba Elite Active since they were ranked in almost all of the Best of reviews.

I read the consumer reviews on Amazon and it was about 50/50 between broke immediately and greatest ever so I decided to give it a shot. It took me a couple weeks to get them completely figured out (they have a lot of configuration options) but now that I know things like to insert the left bud first and then the right, don't sit or stand close to high energy electrical components, the left side is volume, forward or back when listening to iTunes, etc., the right side for calls on and on... I think they are everything I hoped they would be. I can ride the train in completed isolation even when the volume is turned down on the music while I am reading or working. I hear nothing!!!

Straight out of the box the right side fit a little tighter than the left, which I can hardly tell is even there, but that is it. I charged them and have been using them trouble free for a month without any unsolvable issues (all fixed through configuration changes). They have never felt like they were going to fall out and they look more like headsets than a piece of jewelry hanging out of my ear. And, I am hearing things in the music that I have never noticed before, and my previous headset was Bose QuietComfort.

The associated app has worked without issue as well. Not much more to say other than I got exactly what I wanted.

1 Year Update:

I couldn't be happier with my choice of ear buds. The Jabra Elite Active have performed day in and day out without issue. I put them on when I start my commute to work and they run for about 4 hours before they tell me the batter is low. It takes about 45 to fully charge in the case before they are good for another 3-1/2 hours or so on the commute home.

No issues with the software or charging case. Dropped one bud while waiting on the train and of course it bounced down onto the railroad tracks. Luckily there wasn't a train so i was able to hop down and retrieve it. Still working fine.

I would not hesitate to buy again.

title: I will never rum out of battery
content: Sound quality and batery life

title: Junk
content: I bought this product yesterday, and I'm returning it today. The ear buds did not stay in my ears, no matter how many adjustments I made. In the end, my ears hurt from trying to get them to stop from falling out. The buds fell out between 15 and 20 times. The sound is good, however and people said they could hear me fine. The battery case is poorly designed and difficult to open. The battery time is poor. I've given this a one-star only because there are no zero stars. A terrible product, overall. FAIL.

title: Well, I can't ship it back so I'll leave a review instead
content:
I currently am in Afghanistan serving as a contractor. I've been here for almost a year now and I recently purchased these after losing my Bose Soundsport. Within a week, I experienced static coming from the left earbud at higher volumes. As many people have stated on this page, this is a common problem with the headphones. After a week, I dropped the headphones in the case once. The case still charges, but the earbuds do not pair after pulling out of the case and placing in the ears anymore. I wouldn't even call the drop I had a significant drop as they fell from my waist to the ground. Now the earbuds barely charge and just act "wonky". In my honest opinion, I should have just purchased some of the Bose Soundsports again, as they provided me a flawless 6 months of no problems, except for the sticker on the side of the earbuds coming off from use while sleeping.

Since I'm in Afghanistan, in a remote area where we do not have regular mail services, I cannot ship these back.

I will say these were relatively comfortable but besides that I was disappointed with the sounds quality, the craftsmanship, and the reliability of the device. First and last purchase with Jabra unfortunately. Took me $180 to figure it out, oh well.

title: Audio Delay
content: The product seems great at first, the build is a little cheap for the price, but they fit comfortably in the ear. The problem is, the earbuds have a very noticeable delay that is unacceptable with the price.

title: Disappointed
content:
I absolutely loved these headphones for 2 months. At the two month mark the left earphones sound dropped to about 25% of the right ear. I contacted Jabra and they told me to do a reset and reinstall the update. I did both, to no avail. The headphones are now unusable. I have heard nothing more from Jabra. I am very disappointed with their customer service. I am a bit of a wireless headphone addict and have several pairs. I have had headphones from Senso and Jaybird. Both companies, within a week had immediately replaced the defective headphones. I didn’t even have to send the defective headphones back. I guess some companies are better than others. I won’t purchase anything else from Jabra if this is the way they back their products. $170 headphones that lasted 2 months...
Update: I finally got through to Jabra.  Their answer is to return the product to where it was purchased and get a refund or replacement.  So....  They pass the buck and don't seem willing to back their products.  Again, Senso and Jaybird sent replacement headphones within a week.

title: My husband loves them!
content: So glad I got these for my husband for his birthday!

title: Only for women with really big ears
content: From what I can tell the sound quality is good.  But they are big and blocky and in order to get them to stay in my ears, I either had to jam them in uncomfortably or hold them in with a finger.  Not acceptable.  Also, they only came with one size of ear gels and I had to order the small ones separately in order to determine that they really didn't fit.

title: awesome headphones
content: love em, where them all the time.

title: Best Headphones I've Owned
content: Don't normally do reviews and these are pretty solid gym headphones but after my flight I had to write one. The noise cancellation is GREAT. Had a crying baby behind me for 2 hours and a quick double tap on the piece and it was silent the entire way. I wish when pushing the buttons it didn't push in your ear but it's a compromise for truly wireless I guess. BUY THESE!!!

title: READ THIS CAREFULLY....
content:
These headphones have great sound, but only when you blast the volume high (which sucks because it really does cancel noise, which makes blasting the volume up hurt).

The noise cancellation is great 👌🏽 Can’t hear anybody or other noise during my workout, but when I recently updated it, there was a new feature added where IF I paused my music, the headphones would open up and pick up noise around me, but then when I would play my music, the noise cancellation would activate. It’s pretty convenient, especially when you know many people at the gym and you find yourself talking to a lot of people.

The bass is very good, but it’s only good when the volume is high. Again, I don’t like to blast my music because these headphones are really good at noise cancellation, so when you blast these high, they hurt your ears 👂. There’s an app where you can control the sound of the music, which is a great tool when you want to go all out on bass or go high on treble.

These earbuds have a great function where IF one or both of the headphones fall out, your music is paused.... BUT if they had a secured fit, then this wouldn’t happen.... 🤔 so it is a useful function, but it foreshadows something that every hardcore, intense fitness man or woman hates more than injuries.... which is headphones FALLING OUT OF YOUR EARS!! 😤🤬🤬

If you’re intense like me, and love to do any form of HIIT Cardio, jump rope, sprinting, etc., then you most definitely hate it when headphones fall out. Well, these headphones do just that. At first, they stay in your ear, but once you start to sweat, these headphones pop right out of your ears. 😤
In fact, the right earbud just fell as I was typing this sentence. These earbuds fall out when you eat as well.

To sum these headphones up, they’re great for:
1.) Low Intensity Cardio or Steady State Cardio
2.) Most Resistance Training workouts
3.) Weighted Calisthenics

This is NOT for:
1.) Athletes
2.) HIIT Cardio
3.) Listening to music while eating
4.) Anything that requires High Intensity movements

Crap, the right earbud fell again while I was eating and adding a headline for this product 🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️

Don’t buy these if you’re into high intensity exercises and like to listen to music while eating (😤😤😤😤)

Going to Return these

title: Great set of bluetooth headphones
content: They remain in my ear and are comfortable to wear for long durations of time. I also liked how they easily pair with multiple devices simultaneously, allowing me to take calls on my cell phone while also being able to handle slack calls on my laptop. The passthrough feature is nice as well when I am at the gym and stop to chat with someone. Overall, a great set of headphones. Wish they had a little more kick to them, but sounds quality is good. That is why I gave it a 4 instead of 5.

title: High quality headset
content: Working like new after 10 months using every day

title: Terrible sound
content: I really wanted these to be great.  On the first pair, the left ear woildnt play. On the second pair, they would go in and out when i walked.

title: Don't last
content: I want to love these, but I don't. After about 4 months they started disconnecting and reconnecting no matter how close I am to my phone. I use them for conferences calls for work and they'll cut out on me mid-sentence. Would not recommend.

title: Not suitable for small ears
content: If you have small ears,  this product is not a good fit for you.

title: Ugh. Just ugh.
content: These came highly recommended to me and I cannot understand why.  I played with the EQ endlessly and cannot get beyond 1995 KOSS Walkman level sound on them. I am using the smallest adapters yet these still make my ears sore after only a new minutes use.  I hate to think that I have to be one of those people wearing AirPods, but the sound and fit is just so much better.

title: Best Earbuds Ever
content:
I almost had these earbuds for a month. They are great because those regular iPhone headphones never fit my ear. Here is a list of pros & cons:

Pros:
- Suction cups so that they always stay in my ears
- Great for running. Never slips out.
- Great for conference calls. Microphone is not amazing but better than any other wireless headphones
- Great design, especially the blue ones with the copper logo

Cons:
- Battery life is not that great but the charger container is a sleek and portable
- The sound quality is not amazing but then again it is wireless
- The noise cancellation is just ok. I really don't understand the HearThrough technology.

title: Solid Pair of Wireless Earbuds
content:
I quite liked these headphones when I first opened them up.  Pairing to my phone was fairly easy and the fit and finish of these earbuds and the case was very much to my liking.  They hold up in the ear to treadmill runs and sweat, without them coming close to falling out of my ears.

Sadly, I noticed almost immediately that the left earbud was noticeably louder than the right, creating a very distracting imbalance (think the left being at 100% volume and the right being about 70%.)  Adjustments proved useless, and I had to send my first pair back and request a new pair.  I'll update my review after the replacements come.

*8/29 Update*

With my replacement I find that the audio is finally balanced decently between the left and right earbuds, and with no connection issues to speak of, I am pretty satisfied with these earbuds.  Recommended provided you don't get a glitchy pair (which are out there based on reviews)

title: Poor customer service and product quality
content: I tried a few pairs of the Elite 65T.  I kept having the same issues with the left ear bud overpowering the right ear bud and creating an imbalance to the left side when watching any videos on You Tube, Hulu, Netflix, Amazon Prime and when listening to podcasts.  The only time they weren't grossly imbalanced was when I was listening to music.  I tried factory reset, language resets and firmware updates.  Nothing fixed the problem!!  When I called Jabra Customer Support, I would wait no less than 30 minutes and when I did finally get to talk to someone they would act like what I was experiencing was an anamoly.  I have given up on Jabra and moved on.  I purchased a pair of $50 Jbuds.  No, they don't have all the bells and whistles, but they work, the sound is balanced and good on all media platforms.

title: GREAT Earbuds, no connection problems
content: I have been looking at these earbuds for quite a while, but was hesitant to pull the trigger because of a number of less than glowing reviews, specifically the reviews that noted they dropped connection fairly often. But I own other Jabra headsets that I like quite a bit, so I finally purchased a pair, and I have to say that I am completely delighted with these earbuds!  I've been using them for about a month in a variety of situations: biking, working out, on a plane, in the car, on conference calls, and they are easily the best wireless headset/earbuds that I have owned.  Great fit in my ear, easy to connect and use, really good sound, and despite what others have said the phone app is pretty straight forward and easy to use.  But here is the best part, in the month that I have been using these, the earbuds have NEVER lost their connection with the phone, and I have never had any skips while playing music (using with an iPhone 7).  And as others have mentioned, this is the first headset I have used for calls where I don't always have the volume on maximum because they are plenty loud.  Very happy with this purchase.

title: Design flaw with fit
content:
I bought these to use them at the gym. I tried them out for the first time today and had nothing but issues with how they fit. The medium size ear tip fit me the best but if you cant get the earbuds to sit perfectly in your ear the sound is either muffled or completely cut off. The problem is the sound tube that goes in to your ear is extremely small if this tube isnt straight in to your ear and is off to an angle then the sound gets muffled. While i was working out the earbuds would slightly adjust in my ear from the sweat/movement so i was constantly trying to re adjust the earbuds so i can hear my music properly. I ended up taking them out and not using them half way through my work out.

On the plus side they were very comfortable and the sound was pretty good but this design flaw makes them unusable for me

title: it works
content: it works

title: A painful mixed bag.
content:
So this was a harsh experience for me, but I enjoy what works.

First and foremost these barely fit my ears. These earbuds rely heavily on the shape of your ears, and while I can get them in they hurt A LOT at first and even after a week I find it hard to keep them in more than a few hours and after my ears are sore.

As for everything else its great, but nothing mindblowing. What everyone says about volume is true, and often I need it at max to feel like im getting meaty sound and sometimes i wish it could get even louder. The mono for your right ear is convenient, but incredibly inconvenient when it won't do the same for the left ear or even connect with just the left ear.

My only other gripe is that the earbuds self determine when they are in your ear, and at least once a day they cut in and out like I took it out of my ear for no reason and will randomly stutter.

While these feel good for a truly wireless earbud they are also my first and its been a earache and a headache. I can't solidly reccomend these because they rely heavily on your ear shape to work and if my ears were any narrower these would be unusable. If you can somehoe find out if they fit your ears before buying then its a great product but otherwise you are rolling the dice.

title: Bluetooth pairing problems
content: I bought these earbuds primarily to listen to music and was very disappointed to discover that they don't pair with either of my mp3 players (an older iPod Touch and a brand new Sony Walkman), or even with my computer (a new MacBook Pro). They did pair easily with my iPhone, but unfortunately I don't listen to music that way and they've therefore turned out to be relatively useless for me. Apart from these connectivity issues, it seems like a good product (sound quality, battery life, ability to stay put in the ear).

title: True wireless
content: Couldn't be happier with my purchase. The sound is fantastic, and I love the features.  The range is amazing.

title: Only worked for a short time
content: This product worked very well for about 5 months and then all of a sudden the right earbud volume is so low you can barely hear it. Mine are still in like new condition. Amazon won’t do anything to make it right. I have not yet contacted the manufacturer so we’ll see how that goes. I’ll update when I figure out if this will get resolved but for now I would not recommend buying these earbuds.

title: Worst earbud for that price
content:
I bought this less than 6 six months and having issues with left ear bud where I cannot hear anything from it.
It does not even charge properly in the charging case. When I place both my ear buds in the case it is still connected to my phone and not charging.
During listening to music it sometimes makes static noise which is the most annoying thing

title: They can and will fall out of your ears.
content:
Don't get me wrong I love the concept of the product.
The problem for me is I can't get them to stay in my ears.

If you get absolutely any moisture from sweat,  they will start to slide and you'll spend more time with your hands trying to push them back in than actually enjoying them being wireless.

The sound quality I'd rate as above average.
 I could do without the frequent audio drop outs while listening to music.
The noise cancelling isn't bad, never any issues with calls.

All in all i'd say they are good for leisure, if you plan on doing any kind of activity with a lot of movement,  be prepared to catch them and be annoyed as they slide out every 20 seconds.

title: Pretty good but...
content: Case does not have a good battery life if you listen for long periods and takes a while to change the earbuds themselves.

title: Don't waste your money
content: So annoyed.  These are not cheap earbuds and they skip during workouts (running and walking).  I have them paired with a new Google pixel 3 phone and have used different apps to troubleshoot... But they all skip during play.

title: Only lasted 3 days.
content: Everything about the earbud was great except for the fact the case only lasted 3 days. Now when I put the earbud back, it no longer turn off the earbud. The earbud sounded great  just wish the quality of it is a little better. Will have to return it and get something else.

title: Great Earbuds
content: Bought this set as a gift. Very well received and loved.

title: Love them
content:
I love these earphones.  They are great for my workouts.  They never come out and they have even passed my "drop test".

Would buy them again.

title: NOT a Seamless Experience
content:
EDIT: called Jabra support and it looks like the issues may have been from a defective case. Their support was actually very helpful and easy to work with, so I'm hoping my issues can be resolved soon.

Pros: good sound quality.
Cons: everything else. This is a broken product which doesn’t work as advertised. The buds cannot detect that they have been removed from the case, so after putting in your ear you have to press the button on the right side to turn them on which isn’t painful but certainly not comfortable. You would think the left bud would turn on when you turn on the right, but no, then you have to repeat the process for the left bud. Same issue when putting them back in the case. The light blinks but they stay on, unable to detect they’ve been put away until they drain your battery completely. They’re also very slow to connect to Bluetooth so turning them on is a real mission.

Sometimes they disconnect after the end of a call. Sometimes they randomly activate the pass through feature (to hear outside sounds) and it can’t be deactivated until turning them off and back on.

They are advertised to be able to connect to multiple devices at once, but as soon as you connect a second device the first one stops working and has to be re-paired.

Firmware updates don’t work either, if you try the device just blinks purple incessantly for hours until the battery drains, meanwhile you can’t use them all day.

I’m sure most other products out there have similar issues, but they also don’t cost almost 200 dollars and aren’t advertised as a premium product. If you’re shelling out that kind of money and especially if you have an iPhone do yourself a favor and buy EarPods for the same price as these, they aren’t as good on sound quality and isolation, but on a day to day basis they won’t be the cause of constant frustration.

title: Do Not Buy These Earbuds
content:
I gave these one star because it is not possible to give them zero.

Cons:

Uncomfortable - They feel bad in the ear.  Their shape is odd and that may be why they do not feel good in the ear.

Noise Leakage - They do not block much incoming noise. You really have to crank up the volume and jam them into your ears to block out any external sounds.

Lack of controls - You can't put yourself on mute when you are on a phone call, you have to use your phone to take yourself on and off of mute.  There are no controls for fast forward/ next song or rewind function.  The only controls are volume up and volume down.

Hear Through Function - it double tap the right bud and it is supposed to allow more of the sound in your environment in. It only works if you choose to mute your music.

The app - clunky, does not do much, and when you change the equalizer there is significant lag between making the change and hearing the change.

Pros:

Easy to pair.

title: Amazing product
content: Great quality

title: I many amazing features!!!
content: Love these headphones!!! They are so loaded with features.  I love that the sync simultaneously with multiple devices to eliminate pairing/unpairing.  The App stores multiple setting modes for EQ.  And the hear-thru feature is the very best thing ever in the office and when running.  I can lists the o music and still be aware of my surroundings.

title: Most importantly, these don't fall out
content: These actually fit nice and snug and I'm able to run with them in. This was the third pair of truly wireless earbuds I've tried and I finally have a pair that I'll keep. They also have excellent sound and easy to use controls for volume. I really like the size and weight of them. More than I wanted to spend, but you get what you pay for and these ended up being worth it.

title: Sound quality is ok. Wireless creates more problems than it solves though.
content:
At first they connected great. Took a while to rotate around in the ear to figure out how they fit, but they are definitely not going to fall out. The hearthrough feature is good, so despite that they are noise cancelling, they project outside noise into the earbuds.
Biggest problem so far is that when reconnecting them, sometimes the left bud straight up won't connect. There's no on button or anything that i've found, so I've really found no solution to this. Want to know how many times this happened when I had wires?

title: Great for Wireless Sales Calls
content: I have tried many different wireless products for heavy duty sales calls. I suspect I have tried more than twenty products with limited success. These are the first product which worked properly in all facets of use. The only complaint I have is the fidelity for music use does not achieve the same standard. I changed the ear buds for a better fit and this improved the fidelity somewhat. This is the first month so I will report back at six months. Overall highly recommended.

title: As advertised!
content:
Was worried that the buds wouldn't stay in my ear. It's like someone measured my ears and tailored made them for me. The case is cool once you figure out to press it to open. Want to leave them in all the time but my wife gets mad :-)
Sounds like there's a speaker in the middle of my head. Really cool!

title: Occasionally cuts out but sound quality is good.
content: Okay honestly, these earbuds are pretty great in all aspects BUT there is one thing that annoys me and i can't seem to get over it. Either the bluetooth connection is weak or something is wrong with the buds but they keep cutting out occasionally. I notice it when i turn my head or walk with my phone in my pocket. They just cut out randomly and i'm sad because they actually are really great in all the other aspects. But if you're gonna be a bluetooth earbud, you gotta have good bluetooth connection.

title: Well worth the money
content: Comfortable and practical

title: Not what I expected
content: Dislike

title: Very very poor for phone calls
content:
I travel a real lot and wanted these for two reason: music/ movies on the move and to take business calls. They fail badly at phone calls, returned the first set as I thought they were defective, they were not. I can through hear them just fine with one or both earbuds in but it picks up every single sound other than my voice!! even when I am not near noisy are but wind, babies and virtually any and all outside noises can be heard on the other end. No reviews talk about this aspect and I did not want to carry multiple wired and wireless earpieces.
They are not good for cycling as there is a lot of wind noises no matter what the fit is, Using the Hear Thru makes it worse of course. they are good for walks, the gym, and indoors they sound the best, They dont fall out, I only press them in a bit over time but not an issues with fit or comfort and I use large tips. The block sound fairly well but not like my custom fitting wired ones. You can hear outside by either the app or double tap the right bud and that works well but is very hissy so can grate on your nerves after a while but easy to jump back and forth, you can hear cars well walking but wont ever use them for cycling ..too much wind noise for music and they cannot hear you either!!
The good parts are they connect to multiple phones, watches etc easily and distance is good from the phone, less good on a Gamin 5x Plus, but that's most likely the watch bluetooth poor being  too low.
Battery life seems good and have yet to go empty after 3-4 hours of movies on planes and using them for Google maps while walking and driving. the Case fits in your pocket and realize you will always need to carry one due to losing them and charging them, mostly you would lose or ruin them in your pocket without the case.
 The controls are ok to use once you read  directions and realize the right and left do different things.

title: Bad product, Bad company
content: These worked fine for about a week. The right earbud stopped turning off and charging when I put it into the case. I emailed Jabra customer support, and it took them two days to reply to me with generic software reset "fixes" on what is clearly a faulty hardware issue. This company does not care about you, only your money. Returning immediately, do not buy.

title: Do NOT buy this if you intend to use it for calls
content: This product would be great if you intend on not taking calls.  However, if you do plan to, look else where.  The microphone in this product will amplify quiet noises if you are not speaking and will send a massive amount of feedback to the person on the other line.
