I tested this myself (as I purchased it for my mother to take meetings on) and when I was talking on the other line the earbud's mic (currently being used by my mother) would pick up on my voice and send it back essentially creating an echo effect.  They are okay for a call if you intend on not letting the other person talk I suppose.  Overall VERY VERY disappointed with the call quality which is the only purpose these were purchased for.

title: Gym must
content: Love it

title: Left earpiece stopped working after 6 months
content: I enjoyed these headphones while they worked.  Unfortunately, after 6 months the left ear piece started to get static, cut in and out then stopped working all together.  I contacted customer support and it was determined that they would replace the left ear piece.  They said I would receive a tracking number when it shipped.  Three weeks later, I still don't have a tracking number. Plan to spend at least 20-30 minutes on hold before talking to a customer service person.

title: It's a worth a try
content: When I purchase headphones, it needs to produce quality sound as I am an audiophile. First and foremost, it does produce great sound (not amazing, but great). As many will mention, if you are looking for bass and treble, this is not for you. However, the mid's and high's are great for this price. The volume does not max out too much which is good so you do not get deaf. I do not use Alexa or Siri, but the functions would come in handy. I needed headphones that I can take to work out and use at work. I like how it comes with a case that is able to recharge the headphones. What I do not like is the battery like of five hours, but it is a small set so it is understandable that's why it only lasts that long. Make sure that you get the Java Sound Plus app to be able to control other functions such as finding the device, control the equalizer, and motion sensors. The headset does an okay job of blocking out outside noises. There is a function that you can hear the environment for when you are exercising outside and you hear cars or your just your surroundings. However, I do not need that function. I tried doing a few HIIT exercises and it stays secure in my ears. I had to use the ear set that it arrived in, but it does have smaller or larger options. I found that the default (medium) was perfect for blocking out sound and maintaining the sound quality that I wanted. It is definitely a great investment. However, I purchased mine at a local military electronic store for 150 so I thought that I got a deal out of it.

title: Work as expected.
content: No complaints, pretty much what I expected. When use during a phone call, the call quality on the other end isn't as good has being on the phone, but what do you expect with something in such a small package. Love the charging case.

title: Jabra 65t delivers....
content: First try with true wireless Bluetooth headphones and very pleased with the Jabra 65t’s. Fit is solid in my ear canal with the large ear buds, and controls for volume, pause and taking calls work nicely.  I like the Jabra app that allows you to adjust the treble/bass along with allowing outside noise in or sound cancelling.  Strong performance for music, podcasts and phone calls.  All in all, they deliver what Jabra claims.  Recommended.

title: Terrible ear fit design ruins an otherwise excellent product
content:
Battery life and sound quality are fantastic, however getting the fit right is painful. I tried the foam tips for a month but they are degrading quickly and last a few weeks a pair at best. They also make it incredibly awkward to close the case without removing the tips. The bundled silicon tips are useless and would not keep them in my ears for more than a few minutes at a time. Unfortunately I was too generous in trying to make them work and missed my return window.

How these are considered ‘active’ is beyond me since they fall out without me even moving.

If the earbuds that come bundled with iPhones don’t fit your ears these probably won’t either. Don’t make the same mistake I did.

title: Good quality
content: Worked out of box

title: Nice
content: Music

title: Five star
content: Sound quality is surprisingly very good

title: No good
content: Only one day working terrible

title: AWESOME!
content: The sound quality is amazing. The only down side is the right one is the only one you can use by itself, besides that zero complaints.

title: Annoying and Unfixable Sound Imbalance
content: I ordered these on Black Friday and was excited about finally solid wireless earbuds. Within a week I noticed a sound imbalance where the volume of the right ear bud is much lower than the left. I spent hours trying fixes, including factory reset, not using the app, using different tips, and nothing. I googled it and found a whole Reddit thread on the issue and no solution from Jabra.  I contacted Jabra and they emailed me a fix, that if you try twice, you can return or ask for a new pair. I just received the new pair and the same problem exists. I will be returning these as well and going back to wired buds until technology finally advances enough.

title: Decent Battery Life, Great Sound, Odd Case
content:
The pros of this:
-the ability to turn on/off noise canceling is very nice. This feature uses the microphone to actually push through the ambient audio.
-Feel within ear--this works well and feels snug in my ear. It does not stress my ear to use these for long periods of time
-Audio quality is great
-Battery life is acceptable. Around 4 hours
-It connects quickly and easily to multiple devices

Cons:
-The case is very difficult to open. I have multiple times pushed hard to open the top of the case where the force to open makes the buds fall to the ground.
-You can only use the right bud solo. You are unable to use the left bud without also having the right bud in place.
-you cannot share buds with someone to watch a show together.

title: Cool headphones (just one thing)
content: These headphones are great! I use them at the office for remote meetings and at the gym. The only bad thing is they hurt one of my ears a little bit after wearing them a long time.

title: left earbuds cuts out randomly
content:
i love these headphones when theyre working properly. occasionally thenleft earbud will cut in and out, when my phone is in my pocket. makes no sense though because i can walk across the room and not cut out..

batterylife is not as good as airpods, but i still think theyre similar.

still might return them because the dropping issue but not sure.

title: Awesome!
content:
Used the smallest buds and they are great!
The app works well with Iphone 11 max pro

title: Stylish and great for sports and phone calls.
content: Great charging. Sound quality is typical of jabra--not up to audiophile standards but fine for most. The quality for phone calls is good and the autopause when a bud is removed is also nice. Biggest downside is that I can't get these to pair to both my iPhone and iwatch. I can have it paired only to 1 or the other. As I like running sans phone this is a big downside.

title: Overrated
content: The product is over rated the sound quality is alright but not worth this much money. Many better options.

title: Great sound, difficult synch.
content: The Jabras fit my ears well and produce a full rich sound.  I've worn them on 5 mile runs and they stay securely in my ear.  it also has great battery life, due to the convenient charger case in which they sit when not being used.  My only frustration has been with a difficulty it has in synching up with my Apple Watch and iPhone. I go back and forth between the two and the bluetooth synch is always problematic, requiring many attempts until it is recognized.  It's a waste of time and after owning Beats earbuds, seems like a ridiculous step backwards.

title: Best one’s I had
content: I tired many wireless earbuds , this one beats them all

title: AMAZING❤❤❤
content: These are amazing blue tooth earbuds. They beat airpods by far with their noise cancelation and sound quality, strongly suggest you get!!!!!!😍😍😍 Superb bass and cool gadgets that come along with it! I'm in love!!!!

title: They do cut a little here and there
content: Workout

title: Decent sound, fits good, gets warm, limited wear.
content: This item fits well, sound is decent, not great for the price point at all. Best part I guess is the swear resistance rating, and no wires. Beware though, these are not for long wear, watching movies etc. As they do get rather uncomfortable after 30 minutes or so and warm and noticeable. You will not be forgetting that you are wearing these.

title: Nice but hurt my ears
content: Hurt my ears

title: They sound very good and battery life is impressive
content: They sound very good and battery life is impressive. But, they constantly want to run away from home: they just don't want to stay in my ears. The three tip sizes really don't help. I almost lost one or the other several times on a overnight filght to Europe. Maybe it's my ears?!?

title: Sound is poos and reliabilty is worse
content:
Only one ear works, I have spent several hours on the Jabra support line in 2 calls.  In the end, they agreed to replace the product but the return process takes 3 hours of calls, drop-offs, and coordination.  All this might be worthwhile if the source was good, but it ain't.  Also, they do not stay in my ear.  if you want to work out with them and you happen to get a pair that produces sound from earbuds, you will need some tape to keep them from falling out.  They are super slippery with sweat.

This is the 2nd time that I have gotten a bum steer from the NYT reviewers. I tried the Jabra over-ear headset Wire Cutters recommended.  The product had lots of Gizmos and software but they also suffered from inferior sound quality, I sent them back.  They are both great products if you like to play with the software but if you care about music, or even podcasts, look elsewhere.  More important,

title: They are excellent quality and sound.
content: ARRRRRRG. I really like these headphones they work perfectly are easy to pair and the app comes with a tone adjustment graphical interface that allows one to adjust sound for your taste.... Great Base. So... OK, My left ear is too small!!!! The Jabra Elite 65t. is uncomfortable in only my left ear. After wearing them about 30 minutes my ear, the cartilage, not the canal hurts enough that I have to take them off. I thought I could get used to it. But I can't. The right is perfect and I don't even know it is there. So BUY these... I just have a weird ear shape... I must be somewhat asymmetrical and I really.... really wish I could use them :(

title: Great headphones that fit comfortably
content: I absolutely love these. The reason I am giving them 4 stars is that many times I just want to have one in and these make that kind of difficult. Sound is great though and they are comfortable. (I did get these on prime day at a significant discount, not sure I would pay full price for them)

title: Great earbuds
content: Great fit, sound, comfort, battery life and connectivity.

title: Great wireless earbuds!
content: These are the only earbuds that have stayed in my ears. For some reason, I have always had issues keeping others in my ears even if I wasn't active. The Jabra, however, stay in my ears perfectly even while I'm working out. They sound outstanding and keep a charge longer than I expected. When both earbuds are used, the noise cancellation is top notch. I highly recommend these!

title: THESE ARE PERFRCT
content: Amazing ear buds that stay put even during hard workouts! Sound quality is a notch above the rest and connects to device right after removing from case!

title: Obsessed
content: Obsessed! I love these! I haven’t worn them running yet so I’ll update that when I do. But so far I love them.

title: Sound quality is incredible
content: Second pair I liked them that much

title: So painful to wear that sound quality and features are pointless
content: Yeah, the sound quality is great and the app has very cool features but these are SO UNCOMFORTABLE. They’re downright painful to wear for more than about 30 minutes. Several reviews I read said you get used to it after a few days, but honestly it just got worse. I had my husband try them on and he also found them painful. Obviously I’m returning them. I’m so disappointed!

title: Customize to your ears for great sound!
content: I’ll admit that I was very disappointed when I tried them out... until I read the instructions (duh!). I switched the size of the buds that fit into my ears and it made an instantaneous improvement to where these now sound incredible. They’re much better than the fruity ones(you know the ones) and the bass is pretty spectacular when considering how small these are. Battery life is great and pairing to the phone or other devices couldn’t be any easier. If you’re in the market for wireless buds, give them a try.

title: Great headphones, could use a little work though.
content:
The base stuff that these headphones say they do, they do great. No complaints there (except for the earphone tips), but my main gripe is the software part of the headphones.

The hearthrough feature is a great addition and is able to pick up a variety of sounds around your environment. But it sounds like your hearing the world through a fishbowl at a pretty low volume.

Alexa enabled, this feature was something that I was surprised and excited for, but it's far from perfect. When you say a command, it responds pretty accurately but the last few words cut off leaving you wondering if your whole command went through.

A cool feature that Jabra didn't say they had was independent music playing with Alexa. I have not gotten it to work on the headphones themselves but if you have a Echo, you can command them to play your selected music on your headphones and it will work seamlessly.

I hope they fix these issues in future updates, because for their size these are a great pair of headphones.

title: Excellent headset, reasonably good manufacturer support
content:
I love the way these headsets perform.  The basic functions all work as expected, the sound quality is great, and the battery life is quite good.  I've had occasional hiccups with the earbuds "forgetting" a Bluetooth connection, but I seem to experience that on all Bluetooth devices.

After 9 months of regular use, I had an issue with the charging case - the light indications did not match anything described in the user manual, and I could no longer update or charge the earbuds.  I successfully resolved the issue using Jabra support.  I found Jabra's phone support to be excellent (despite long hold times), but their email/web support was slow.  After several exchanges to diagnose my issue and make a warranty claim (mostly via email), Jabra sent me a new headset and case to replace my old ones.  The support engagement took 30 days from my first request to receiving my replacement headset.

title: Waste of time, spent more time in settings than using the headphones
content:
Very disappointed with the quality and application of these headphones.  I always buy Bose products but I lost my previous Bose buds so opted to try something new.

1. They do not fit easily in ear or remain in the ear canal. I changed to the smaller size but they still managed to get loose and fall out of my ears more than once!

2. I downloaded the App and wasnt too happy about the app settings. The only good thing is the Hear Through option.

3. I could not get my music to play through my headphones for a long time even though my Amazon music app said I was connected to Jabra headphones. only calls would come through.  After a few test calls and messing with the apps (Amazon music and Jabra) I finally got the music to play via headphones.

4. When I took the headphones off and disconnect the device from my phone, the Amazon Music App would not shut off. It wouldn't play the music on the speakers either. The music would come out sounding like the audio on a call without speaker phone. I exited the app many times and the music kept playing. I'm sure it had something to do with Jabra headphones since I've never experienced it before.

5. I spent so my time trying to get my headphones to work, I hardly got to enjoy them. I canceled /refunded my purchase within hours because it should not be sp difficult.  I think I'll go back to Bose products.

title: Excellent Sound, Fit, and Recharging
content: These are my first earbud, wireless, blue tooth earphones and am very happy with them so far. I use them to listen to podcasts and music and find the sound quality excellent. I needed to adjust the sound on the Jabra App after I found the bass and treble a little weak, but that was definitely improved after adjusting the settings. The fit well and snugly in my ears out of the box (do provide other earpieces if you need them). They are comfortable and are not as large or noticeable as the Bose ones for example. The charging case is very small and slips into my pocket well.

title: Please 86 the silicone tips in favor of foam!
content: These things are a luxury, specifically with foam tips. I got this Jabra mainly for sleeping. The neck band style bt I had didn’t survive for long before I woke up to them broken in two places.  Maybe the subconscious feeling of strangling in my sleep made me take action. I skirted the issue with these buds. I’m a side sleeper and these things rock to the point that I can’t seem to make it more than 8 mins or so through a podcast before the lights go out. The Comply foam tips compatible with these take the sound to a whole new level. Why only 4 stars?...the lame, unstable silicone tips. With such a good product why does Jabra need to take a dive by supplying inferior accessories?  The app is a neat companion... a must download. Mine are copper and black bought at BestBuy on a Cyber Monday sale

title: Poor Fit
content: So these do not stay in my ears when I work out; they stay in one ear and not the other, and I'm relatively certain my ears are symmetrical.  It was a waste of money.  I would look for a pair that has more certain fit for workouts.

title: The perfect ear buds for sweaty runners.
content: These ear buds are perfect for sweaty runners.  It locks in and does not fall out. All the features are simple to use. I've finally found the perfect ear buds.

title: Keeps falling out of my ears
content: The sound is good but they keep falling out of my ears so they’re not very practical for me. I just heard that they’ve improved the fit, but I bought these in July and it’s too late to return them. They’re ok as long as I don’t go anywhere with them. I’m afraid to lose them. Unhappy.

title: Great purchase
content: Very good bluetooth buds

title: My top choice
content: The best. Worth every penny and it works wonderfully during workouts.

title: Everything they said they do they do! I am so impressed.
content: They work exactacly like they said. I was sceptical. I read at least 1000 reviews. All different kinds of types of ear buds. I just got them today.  First thing I did when I got home from work. The batteries had 80% charge. I listened to some music mad a bunch of calls. They worked perfectly. I'm really just shocked. Everyone who has bought stuff off line knows how it Is. The stuff you buy isnt as good as they claimed. Not the case with these. In glad that I got them.

title: Excellent!
content: Excellent relation quality-price.

title: May be good for others but not for me
content:
I gave these buds two weeks.  I looked at a lot of different true wireless sets for about a month before buying these.  I was disappointed in them in the end and sent them back.

Good:
Sounds great
Blocks outside noise fairly well
Great battery life
Easy setup

Bad
Painful ear fatigue {this is subjective, bad for me probably has good fit for others)
Tend to want to fallout, especially with some sweat.
Poor Bluetooth connection (would repeatedly lose signal while the phone was in my pocket)
Can't use the left Bud by itself

For the cost, I just couldn't justify keeping them. They were just too painful, wanted to slip out, and tended to have a poor connection.

title: Sound cuts out continuously during the first week
content: I've had these for less than a week. They are already constantly cutting out when I'm at the gym. It is super frustrating. The sound quality is not as good as other headphones I've owned. I'm not sure if I trust anyone wireless headphones at this point.

title: Meh
content:
They’re pretty comfortable, stay in during workouts, and pair easily with my phone/iPad. However, the sound is tinny and thin, no matter how much I jack up the volume and the equalizer. Did I get a defective one?

During phone calls on sidewalks (as moderate traffic went by) I’ve found it hard to hear what the other person was saying and been asked whether I was standing in a toilet because of background “swishing” sound. So: fine in an office or home gym; but not what the reviews had led me to expect – and not an upgrade over my $50 Avantree Joggers.

***

After more time with these I’m amazed by how poorly/inconsistently they pair with my iPhone. They regularly drop pairing in the middle of a workout or don’t establish it at the beginning. A second paired device leads to the headphones cycling between being paired and unpaired. I spend an inordinate amount of time restarting them or my phone to try to reset the connection. Thoroughly frustrating.

title: I'd like them better if they didn't always fall out
content: These sound pretty good but, frankly, I had to send them back because they were always falling out of my ears despite trying several different sized buds. And I have to say I'm glad I did because I ended up getting a pair of Bose wireless that fit better and sound amazing.

title: Best true wireless earbuds I've ever had.
content:
So far I've had these about a month and they are great. Easy to put in your ears and fit nice and snug. They come with multiple silicon ear fittings but I used the ones pre installed.

The dual buttons on the left ear are kind of a pain to push but I find if I grip the whole earphone it works well without pushing into my ear.
Battery life is great lasting several hours on one charge, I constantly put mine in the charger case through my work day so I can use them through an 11 hour shift without them dying.
Charger case charges really quickly and has great color coded light to tell the battery life of the case and the earbuds.

title: Love hate relationship!
content: I opened these headphones and fell in love. The box was hard to open until I broke it in after a week. After a month I noticed difficulty with syncing both ear buds coming out of the charging box. Last week I was in the gym and noticed that one of the ear buds started to go out ( the same one that was not syncing correctly). Jabra has made earbuds for phones since I was a kid, my dad loved this brand so it was easy for me to depart from apple and get these. The design is awesome, over the phone people can hear me, they just didn’t stand the test of time which when you spend this much you def want the to last longer than a month in a half. Other than that I had a great experience. I can’t return them because I guess the window closed for me to return them. So I must continue my journey in search for the perfect ear buds. These came sooooo close.

title: Best sound quality
content: I have purchased blue tooth earbuds in the past only to return them. They never had the bass quality I would get in the wired earbuds. These earbuds surpass the base and overall sound quality of my wired earbuds.  Extremely pleased with my purchase.

title: Great, When They Charge
content: These provide excellent fit, noise quality and perfect function. That's when they would actually charge. Got a couple of good uses out of them, but then they'd never charge again after that. Others have noted the same thing, thankfully I was able to return to Amazon before the window closed. Back to corded headset for me!

title: Very worth the price
content: The absolute best pair of Bluetooth earbuds I’ve ever owned. I’ve had 5 pairs of Bluetooth earbuds and these are by far the best.

title: Left doesn’t work by itself
content:
Sound and feel great
The left one doesn’t work on its own
Returning for airpods😕

title: Good fit and sound. Got two duds that have static.
content:
Pros:
- Great fit. I have been using them in the gym and rarely if ever felt the need to adjust. On the other hand when I used Samsung IconX I constantly felt it was going to fall out.
- Easy to pair, and works well both with my phone (Galaxy S8) and my laptop (Macbook). IconX cannot be connected to Macbook thanks to Apple and Samsung war.
- Good sound quality both for music and call.
- Some useful features in the app like controlling hear through and equalizer.

Cons:
- I am on my second pair and both times the left earphone produced some static. That was surprising and not something I would expect from these relatively expensive earphones. I will be returning and ordering the Active hoping that I was just unlucky these two times. This is the reason for a 2-star review.
- The left earphone sometimes just doesn't connect/turn on. Easily solved by pressing and holding the reduce volume button but it'll be better if this didn't happen.
- Minor: the charging indicator blinks when fully charged. If you leave it charging at night, you have a mini disco ball in a dark room. This can be fixed with a firmware update but I am not sure many people share this pet peeve.
- Minor: USB-C would have been better since that's what the current standard is but I can deal with the fiddly micro USB for now.

title: Just a costley piece of junk.
content:
I am a big fan of using a in ear headphones like anyone else during my workout time. I never found anything wrong with the previous  items that I used. This one was gifted by my wife and you know what, it hurted my ears so badly and got a outer ear infection within a week's use. Initially, I felt a slight discomfort in my ears for about hour and half use everyday. Then it started to irritate my ears badly which took me to the urgent care next day.

I was paranoid to use earphones when I workout but it really took great time to get rid of that. This product is totally worthless for the cost, the sound quality is poor and other features aren't really needed if it is meant for activity tracking. I have smartwatches for that purpose as it is always on me.

All I wanted is a quality sound when i workout. When there are many other products with best sound quality out there in the market why this one? Wrongly decided. This is just a piece of junk including the case, opening the lid needs lot of pressure to take the earbuds out so crap.

title: Static.
content: Like others...static in the left earbud.  Going through the warranty process now.  They get one chance and I'm out.  $200....come on.  I had better sound on some $50 mpows.

title: Easy to set up but not comfortable
content: I bought these as reviews said super comfortable.  They hurt my ears so when you push the side button, they hurt more.  I have a pair of LG headphones that sit on you neck and the buds extend or retract when not using.  The sound is much better & much more comfortable.  I'm trying to get used to these but not what I expected from such an expensive pair of buds. Fairly disappointed.

title: Love It!!!
content: The first pair of earbuds I don't regretting buying. Absolutely love it, works flawlessly and as described.

title: Buy if looking for premium ear buds.
content: Wow great product. Not certain if would still be willing to pay full price but at $120 they are well worth it. I have multiple less than $20 Bluetooth headbands some that are even decent but the comfort and sound quality of theses are outstanding. I did lots of research comparing theses to Bose . Yes, these Jaber Bluetooth are best in class. Highly recommend if you want a pair of premium earbuds and the price is in your budget.

title: Great for hassle-free, truly cordless listening.
content:
Sound quality is great (better than the neckband, retractable earbuds I'd been using for the last few years). The instant connection and smart features like pausing when you remove one of them and the 'hear through' are great. I considered several of these types of earbuds and it came down to a very expensive, but very high-quality set, the 'original' wireless buds (orange ya glad I didn't say A----?) :) Both of those others are amazing in their own rights, but the factors that tilted me toward the Jabra are:
 - Noise Isolation - I like the 'earplug' quiet that I can enjoy. There are times I want to hear the world around me, other times I want to shut it out.
 - Hear Through - for the times I want to be more aware of the world, I double-tap the right bud and the mics pick up outside sounds and transmit it to me. It does sound a bit tinny (think mid-quality hearing aids) but it's certainly nice to to have the option to block or allow outside sounds into your world.
 - Controls built in to the buds - this means they're a bit larger, but not nearly as large as the really premium ones I was looking at (BTW, I have the noise-cancelling, wired earbud versions and they truly are amazing - size and price put these ahead of those better-sounding ones). I like having the buttons so I don't have to rely on Siri or pull the phone out of my bag/pack/holster while hiking to change volume, etc.

So those little white buds or those big ones with the amazing sound are great, just didn't quite hit all the points that were important to me.

So why not 5 stars? The case. While it's great to charge them, there are two issues I have with it:
 - The lid is VERY easy to pop open. I leave the case in a small cubby in the car dash and many times I find the case has popped open and the earbuds are rattling around in the storage space.
 - It's awkward to clean them - if you don't immediately wipe off the eartips before putting them in the case, you're going to have some waxy buildup in the case (one thing the little white buds are MUCH better for).

So - there you have it, great sound - very convenient and NO CORDS. I hate the cord dragging across my chin and transmitting all that sound right into my ears. These are amazing!

title: Decent audio and mic - IF there isn't wind, or wifi signals
content: Sensitive to wind and wifi interference.  Otherwise, in good conditions (gym, home, etc) its good.

title: Buy this product you won't  regret it
content: A very good earbuds

title: Good sound, very prone to interference
content:
I loved the sound quality but found these were very subject to interference from outside sources.  Other reviewers noted the master connection is to the right headphone, so if you put your phone in your left pocket it tends to drop audio in sync with your movement.  This problem gets very annoying when you are on a call and you can't hear the other side.  It sounds like you're on a very old VOIP connection.  When I open the fridge, something with the fridge interferes with them and the audio drops completely until I close the door.  Someone walks by me on the street and the audio drops.  Or in a park with nothing around.

I figured the majority of reviews were positive so I took the risk of buying these and ignoring the few negative reviews which sounded a lot like mine.  The physical design is well thought out and not very noticeable, but the whole package is not good.  Something in the bluetooth is very wrong for certain owners like myself, and being in a noisy wireless environment prohibits using these where other headphones do not struggle.  I don't like airpods, they don't provide any sound isolation, but the obvious comparison here is that these sound issues never occur with airpods.  Same for most other bluetooth headsets like Jaybird, even the cheap Anker set that was 1/8 the price of these never drops audio when I walk around.

title: Love these gems!
content: I so far have found no detractors from the purchase of these. They fit in my ears wonderfully, and stay in! I have not had any issues with dropped signal, and have used them with my iPhone sitting across the room even. I do worry about the connector on the case breaking, it is somewhat flimsy, so I have been extra careful with it.

title: worth every penny
content: I love these more than the music i use them to listen to. Ihve had them for a little over a month and they have yet to disapoint. Battery life, sound clarity, and fit are just the top 3 of a long list of everything jabra does oh so perfect

title: VERY POPULAR IMBALANCE ISSUES
content:
I owned this earphone for less than half year, used for less than 5 hours total, and now the right ear sounds about 50% volume of the left side, and after a quick search, I found many people had the same issue.

Contacted their support, and repeated got some instruction to try fixed it through firmware toggling, but that did not help after numerous tries. Such low level issue is totally unacceptable for an expensive pair like this.

title: Enjoy
content: Like the way they look in my ears

title: not comfortable
content: I do not like these wireless earbuds.  They do not stay in, are difficult to get back into their box and overall not worth the money.  I ended up giving them away.  I would not recommend this product.

title: The one for everyday use
content:
Like: battery life (fast charging), call quality, and design. Firmware support.

Dislike: no ANC, sound quality when compared to Sony WF1000X. Case doesn't hold the pair down.

Use: daily while working, commuting, and during workouts.

There's not much for me to dislike. It's the best I've owned so far. Tried several different brands and none were good for calls. On my ears, great fit out of the box.

title: Not so much a pair of earbuds as a single
content: Very poor quality. The left earpiece drops out completely or snaps in and out. I used the app and updated the firmware to no avail. So I replaced the first pair. The second pair identical poor performance. So not a fluke just bad design and poor quality.

title: A solid product with some quirks.
content:
These are the first headphones I've bought in YEARS that were not Jaybirds. They have their quirks but overall they're still a solid product.

I've had very few issues with them calibrating, a common complaint among other buyers. (Read the instructions)

Overall B+

title: Great battery life
content:
Great battery life, perfect pairing and work fantastically. As I'm walking around I might get an audio desync for a fraction of a second but it instantly resolves itself and is rare enough that I can't say how often it really happens. Would definitely recommend if you are looking for reliable true wireless earbuds.

Edit: So my left earbud had an issue that required it to be replaced under warranty. Jabra's CS is pretty awful.  While they accepted the issue and replaced it without too much problem I had to call them 4 or 5 times during the process, giving multiple days (or a week) between things and every time no progress had been made until the call. The 2nd time I called after a few days of waiting to find the status I was informed the buds had to be returned and that the first rep told me this. He hadn't and the rep I was then talking to then made a return label and emailed it to me. Each call after that was essentially basically the same, "What's the status of the claim?" "No change, but now that you've called we'll put it into the queue for the next step which will take a few days." Each call was a 20-40 minute wait on hold and the whole process took about a month. I wouldn't avoid Jabra in the future as a result of the experience but the lack of quality CS will definitely weigh against them when I look at future products.

title: Not worth it at all...
content: Clearly for the $170, you're paying for newer technology...not technology that works well. First, can only connect to a smartphone, not a pc or mac...so it's very limited. I was hoping to be able to watch movies on the laptop or play games. Secondly, when listening to music on my smartphone...the quality sounds like a $10 pair of wired earbuds. Very poor quality for what I expect in ANY headphones. Will be returning these and finding others like the Sennheisers or waiting till the technology is actually quality.

title: Instantly impressed
content:
A few days ago I finally broke down and started to look into wireless headphones / earbuds. I lost my trusty corded Air Earbuds (I know... I know...) and needed / wanted something better in lots of aspects. But I was skeptical of AirPods so looked up alternatives.

Initially when I came across the Jabra Elite 65t I was impressed by the coverage. Wirecutter is a go to for me so I bought them to give it a shot. The 65t regular are solid but then I read more about the active series. That’s what I’m reviewing.

And holy crap... these are so impressive. Packaging for both products is the same but the device itself is way more than marginally better. The finish on the active model of the elite 65t immediately stood out. Looked like a higher quality build and the copper is slick. And then I touched the ear bud. It’s was noticeably more pleasant than the Elite 65t. So I popped into my ear. I’m not kidding when I say that it’s genuinely like they aren’t even there. They are insanely comfortable. The Elite 65t needed some twisting around in my ear to get to the perfect spot and depth but the grip and comfort of the Elite Active 65t was just instantly comfortable. If taken in and out a few times and never more than a small rotation of the mic arm to be perfect fit.

The sound quality is superb. The HearThrough feature is excellent. Just mainly wanted to highlight fit, comfort and design.

title: Good sound stays in ear.
content: They stay in my ear when jogging in rain, though the left hurts my ear. I am going to try and use two different size fittings between left and right. Volume button a little hard to push but works fine. Very unimpressed by the case. It seems a little flimsy. Is difficult to open. Ear buds have to be manipulated to insert into case properly. Plug connect feels flimsy and the charge cord is very short. Besides the case, I really like the buds. Good sound, good fit. Can have more than one Bluetooth connection at a time, but as others have noted sometimes it losses connection. I need to look into under what conditions this occurred. Overall I like them.

title: Worth the price
content: I have small ears and they fit in wonderfully. Won’t fall out lifting weights or running. Some of the complaints i’ve Read can be alleviated by putting in and taking out the left ear bud first.

title: Only lasted 7 months, barely.
content: I wanted to love these. I bought them in January and now in August, they're almost useless. I'm an active person, I use them everyday (work, gym, communting). In May, the left earbud stopped producing sound but was still able to control volume. This was a common issue in the forums I read to try to fix it. I reset it, let it die, charged them completely, I don't keep them over charging in the case, etc. Now, I only have use of the right (brain) for about 5 hours before they die. The case is also finicky and it doesn't hold a charge well either. I'm very disappointed because all the articles I read said these were top ten for wireless sport earbuds. I won't be buying these again.

title: Great quality.
content:
Pros: Great sound and bass. It definitely stays in the ear no matter how much you move around.

Cons: I wish you can choose which earbud can be the primary one at any given moment than just having the right earbud being the primary one. Ambient sounds a poor quality.

title: Reason for review: You never know what you have until it's gone!
content:
I thought my Jabra Elite 65t was stolen from my car because cash was missing.
I was extremely upset they stole my headphones! I used the "Find My Jabra" application on my phone to see it had recently been in an area about 40 miles away and I had not been near there for 3 days. (the location application was not working accurately- only down side of these headphones)
I missed the perfect base and freedom of truly wireless music for anything from workouts to yard chores.
I broke down and started to order a new set, and just before I completed my order I found my original pair!
That is when I realized I owned these for two months and I had not written a review. Now I know it deserves a perfect review!
(Side note: I wouldn't go into the shower with the headphones in, but I wouldn't do that with the Jabra 65t ACTIVE headphones either)

title: Best true wireless headphones I've ever seen
content: Great sound quality, best I've experienced with true wireless before. The controls are robust, the phone app is great and offers a lot of customization, and the charging case is reliable and sturdy. Only small downsides are the limited earplug selection out of the box, so-so range, and the slippery charging case I have dropped a few times.

title: Perfect fit
content: Very good battery charge, cradle could be better(IPods better) but really good quality

title: The sound is perfectly Synchronized in both speakers no delay true wireless!
content: Great product the sound is great u can add effect to the sound with the Jabra app easy to update the software for me the problem was the way it held in the ears it felt too uncomfortable too big, of course not everyone is like me for some people is probably just perfect, it charges very fast honestly I love the sound effects and the technology, other things I didn’t like was the way it sound when u press the button on the Bluetooth to turn on/off or to alter the volume it hurts the ear is like you just pushed deep in your ear and every time you click it sounds too loud .. the way around that problem was to use the phone key to alter the volume they need to change that to a magnetic touch system that be perfect

title: Great headphones.
content: While I think this is a great product I do have an issue. But it’s not the product it’s self which is why I still give it 5 stars. The sound quality is top notch. However, if you have smaller ears these can be a little uncomfortable. Sadly they will not work for me I used them for several days and my ear just can’t get the fit right even with the extra rubber parts.

title: Really nice pair of headphones.  Don't make you look dumb like airpods do!
content:
These headphones are really nicely made.  The sound quality is fantastic, but the seal isn't super tight.  It might be my ears.  I did purchase foam tips and used then for a while, but ultimately decided to use without the foam tips.  I use them for running and for general music listening and phone calls.  They stay in my ears with no problems during runs.  These would stay during pretty intense excercise.  They are comfortable and sound great.

The battery life has been really nice...I've had no challenges in long flights.  The case works really nicely and can charge the headphones.  It still uses micro-usb....would be nice to get this in usb-c.

They did a nice job with the app and provide several different profiles for sound and various settings.  One of the best features is to enable the hear through mode where you can hear ambient noise around you.  This is useful to be able to hear cars when you are on a run.

I use these both with my Galaxy s9+ and my work iPhone.  Neither phone has issues connecting.  All the controls work.

These work great for phone calls also.  Wind noise is amplified a bit....as per people I have spoken with.

All in all - I am very pleased with my purchase.  They sound great, have great battery life, stay in your ears, are comfortable, have a lot of useful features....and....don't make you look like an idiot with white rods sticking down from your ears.

Do your research, read all the reviews, and make a good decision with your money.  Don't buy the airpods because everyone else is looking dumb walking around with them.

title: Thumbs Up, I love these. Run don't walk all over the place order button.
content:
I've had Samsung, LG, Jaybird. I put these on top.

Pros:
Great fit, great sound, great battery, works with 2 phones at the same time. Strong Bluetooth link.

Cons:
The hearthrough and sidetone features are annoying and for some reason won't stay off.

The charging case plastic doesn't feel like it comes with earbuds that cost over $150.

Verdict:

I love these. I've had other true wireless earbuds and these are my best Bluetooth experience.

title: Very happy with product
content: Got these for my mom as a gift and she loves them. She says they are comfortable and they really stay put in her ears. She also loves the option to turn noise canceling on and off.

title: Worthless!
content: Right earbud completely went out and can barely hear anything out of the left earbud. As much as these cost, nothing like this should happen!

title: Great product
content: They work great and easy to use.

title: Used for 24hrs
content: These paired with my S9 + (Samsung) and Ipad Mini 4 with no hitch. they pair back as soon as you take them out of the case. I use medium earbuds and they are super comfortable. I am very happy with the sound quality and the pairing response.Alexa/Google Assistant response was great. After wearing for 3 straight hours I forgot that I had them on! they fit and weight is great. They do not protrude out but stay in-line with the depth of my ear.

title: Great mobile headset - also great on desktop
content: Carry them everywhere I go.  Only time I switch to using my handset is when there is a lot of background noise - walking through airport, in train, etc.  Otherwise they are great.  They don't do a very good job of noise cancellation but that's probably because the mic is so far from your mouth.  I actually have two pair - Active and Standard - Don't really have a preference for one over the other.  Keep one with my keys and every day carry stuff and keep one on my desktop (see pic).  Leaving it plugged in and open works fine.  It disconnects from Bluetooth when dropped back in the case.  Answers a call when I remove from the case.  Would love a machined or molded stand with some weight to it but my home-brew stand works for now...  Only improvements I would prefer is a little better latching mechanism (feel like the plastic latch will wear out) and wish the buds were magnetically retained.  I've dropped them more than once.

title: My headphone investment
content: While these headphones are by no means inexpensive, I don't mind investing my money in a good set of headphones. I mainly bought these for the gym, but am finding myself using them around the house too. The freedom of true wireless buds is a big plus to me. For wireless "buds", these have very nice sound quality. They connect right as you remove them from the case. Sometimes you have to manually connect them if you have a 2 or more devices with bluetooth turned on. They look much more attractive than those white Apple earbuds too. As long as you monitor the battery life of your case, you almost never have to worry about battery life. My old headphones would always surprise me mid-workout by dying, leaving me with no music or podcasts for the duration of my workout. These never to that. I would give them a try if they are within your budget. My only issue was the high price tag.

title: Fantastic sound, sleek design, and extremely practical
content: This met my already high expectations for the product. At first, it seemed that the left earbud's volume was slightly louder than the right, but this either went away or the difference was so minimal that I stopped noticing. Regardless, the sound quality is phenomenal and the fact that they turn on and connect to your device immediately without pushing a single button is highly practical. They also look incredibly sleek (the look is far superior to that of the apple airpods). 10/10 would recommend.

title: Cool noise cancellation
content: Everything is true, they are really cool

title: Not worth paying 200
content: Stop working in 6 months no reason wast of $ 200

title: waranty
content: it worked 3 mounth

title: Poor sound quality
content: I bought as an option for sports however comparing to apple ear pods side by side the sound quality is abismal. Besides that product adjustment in the ear is really bad as it is very thick. All of that for almost 200 dollars, not worth it. This product should be priced at around 60 dollars.

title: Best earbuds available
content: Best earbuds on the market, in my opinion. Retuned AirPods as they did not fit my ears. Returned Bose as they had too many glitches on phone and video/audio functionality. The Jabra 65t’s are exactly what I was hoping for. Audio sound quality is solid - love the equalizer ability via the app. Phone functionality is flawless. Fit is customizable and comfortable - plus I don’t look like a total geek in public like Apple and Bose. No Bluetooth connectivity hiccups experienced. Really love the “hear through” features on call mode and audio mode. Carrying case is small and is easy to use. Only challenge I found was the learning curve learning to fit them in ear and how to easily identify left from right earbud - but in two days of use, I don’t even think about it anymore. Thanks Jabra for making the best earbuds on the market!

title: These are the ones for your iPhone.
content:
I have an iPhone 7plus that has no audio plug. So, I’ve tried a lot of Bluetooth headsets. I have not tried the expensive and easy to lose Apple buds, which I am sure are OK, but look funny to me with the white sticks coming out if the ear like you’ve got a childhood ear infection all over again.

Anyways, I jumped on the chance to check out these awesomely great Jabra buds and am super happy with them. I also own a Jabra 75 over the ear headphone with boom mic that is my indispensable set for sitting at my office desk, so it was not a shock that Jabri could do it again in bud form.

Pros:
1. Snug fit in the ear with included sets of ear cushion inserts. They stay out and block sound in a way the Apple design can’t.
2. Sound: it’s just great, including the bass. I like listening to music in these. It’s very good, not just tolerable.
3. Mic quality is excellent according to my coworkers who I talk with. I spend hours a day on phone calls and I have to talk as well as listen. These keep me understood
4. Battery life is five hours. I’ve run them down and believe the 5 hour claim is conservative.
5. Compact charger case. This is an awesome tool. It has micro usb as it’s charger port, so it is easy to charge the charger. Top: don’t try to open it by slipping your fingernail into the front crack of the case. Grab it by the side edged instead. Easier.
6. Looks unobtrusive compared to white drainage stick.
7. Setup was easy, although I did need to look at the instructions because you have to pair both sides the first time.
8. App: the app is useful. Change the equalizer without going to settings. Yay!
9. Don’t have to turn them on and off. Putting them in the case puts them in standby. Also can pause songs by taking them out of your ear.
10. Controls are accessible by adult human hands.
11. Supports iPhone control set for earphone remote.

I could go on. All said, these are not cheap, but they are durable pro gear that I use every day. Sturdy, practical. Great stuff.

title: Sound quality similar to wired and no drops: Wireless earbuds have finally matured
content:
Bottom line: I'm impressed with these -- reasonable sound quality, easy to use and fit, and few to no sound drops. I had a pair of Doppler Labs Here One buds that had a lot of promise but failed miserably with everyday use. Way too complicated to use and pair and they dropped the signal all the time. I'll note I've not tried Apple's AirPods, however, the wired counterpart tend to fall out of my ears, so I haven't been excited to try them.

Enter these Jabra Elite Active 65t Earbuds. They came in a cute little rechargeable storage case (but overly large cardboard product box) and easily charge via Micro USB (a cable but no AC charger is included.) There are three ear gel sizes to choose from, the medium work well for my ears. After inserting the earbuds deeply into my ears (using the pull the top of the ear trick; learned from fitting earplugs), I've got a good seal and they are unlikely to fall out under any "active" activity (mostly walking for me; I'm not a runner, but I did simulate by shaking my head). I wish that spare ear gels would be included in the package, however. I might be on the lookout for some other styles that provide more isolation (I'd say the included ones have average passive isolation); I imagine Jabra and or other vendors will soon follow in the marketplace. They have been plenty comfortable in my ear for a couple hours at a time.

Pairing was easy with my iPhone 8. You can pair using the native Bluetooth functionality in iOS and then use the Jabra Sound+ app to customize your sound "signature", the hear-through function, among a few other features. The full user manual is also conveniently located in the app (just a quick start paper guide is included in the box.) Firmware upgrades are also easily handled through the app.

The sound quality -- well, they're wireless and small. No huge bass but totally passable and reasonable mids and treble. Make sure you fit them as deep in your ear as reasonably possible for the best sound quality. I can count the number of bluetooth drops with the phone in my pocket on one hand -- and the majority of those happened when a NYC subway pulled into the station (perhaps bluetooth interference from a mass of train passengers or simply the metallic cars) causing a very brief disruption. Otherwise, I can roam around my small 600 sq ft apartment and the signal only drops at the far edges of my place. When making phone calls, the other parties had no difficulty hearing me, but when outside, the wind noise was noticeable but did not make phone calls impossible.

Controlling your music and volume with the right taps and pushes on the earpieces takes a little getting used to but quickly becomes second nature, unlike the Here One earbuds I used previously. The commands on my phone were immediately received and processed accurately. Charging the buds in the case is easy. I haven't reached the max 5 hour battery life before putting them back in the case (the case holds two additional charges.) There's an easy to see green light on the charging case to confirm it has power.

These are an absolute keeper and I'd say that truly wireless earbud technology is finally maturing. I imagine we will see more and more of these come out in the next few years as the headphone jack goes the way of the dodo. I use Jabra office headsets at work and have always been impressed. Surprisingly, a two year warranty is included like those. Always thought Jabra/GN Netcom was an also-ran in the consumer space, but these earbuds prove that's untrue and if the quality remains, they've got a good product lineup ahead for consumers that I wouldn't hesitate to recommend.

title: 1 star right out of the gate.
content: Just got these bad boys today.  Well, so far I have been charging the case/headphones for about 3 hours now.  The headphones still will not turn on.  Have tried different cords and wall chargers.  Guess we will have to see what happens when the replacement set of headphones gets here.  Oh, and they were missing the extra sets of gel buds for different size ears.  Searched through all the different parts of the box like support told me.  I would kind of expect this from a $20 set of headphones but, when you pay these prices you expect a little more.  Like they say, you get what you pay for.  $20 pair isnt sounding so bad now.  Crappy part is I cant even give anyone a review on quality.

title: Rugged and dependable blue-tooth headset option
content: Went through one cycle wash already; solid product. I purchased another. One for travel bag one for home office use.

title: Great
content: It's ok

title: Not worth it
content: The app that is supposed to control this product's dynamic settings + performance only worked half of the time. At this price point, it just isn't worth it. I was surprised at how often people complained about not being able to hear me...which made this product pretty useless for my particular business-related needs.

title: Don’t waste ur money
content: These are not as they appear, there very lightweight but bulky. Can’t use left one without the right one in ur ear. They r not magnetic so they will pop out when u open the difficult case that it comes with. Volume is not very loud to my liking. And they feel like they will fall out. I returned mine almost as soon as I bought them. Spend the extra money to get a quality pair and return if it’s not up to par.

title: Loved this purchase
content:
My husband loved this earphone as he is not an airpod person. The sound quality is awesome and will definitely refer this to people.
He is been using it for quite sometime but no complaints so far.

title: Great for media, not great for phone calls
content: Great for music, great fit and for exercise, high quality sound, and nice to have some control functionality from the earbud.  For phone calls, not the best product.  I have owned the Apple Airpods and Jabra Active Elite 65t.  For me the Airpods are far better for phone calls (specifically for folks I call - better quality of sound for them) while Jabra’s are better for media in general and for sports.

title: First Impressions of the Jabra Elite Active 65t
content:
Just received this product on Wednesday but i'll write my initial impressions and update as I go.

Background: I'm a runner and have been looking to have good bluetooth earbuds to use while running as well as when i'm on the go.  Having the ability to listen to music as well as take the occasional call while running through the airport would be great.

Pros:
* Nice small compact earbuds that has a relatively nice charge.
* Only done some limited activity (cardio) so far but the earbuds have stayed in the ear.  I sweat a lot from the head so earbuds would always fall out during exercise.
* Love the ability to control a lot of things from the earbuds.
* HearThrough works pretty well.
* Paring is seamless and painless.  They connect to the phone pretty quickly and don't have any issues (yet) with the earbuds connecting to each other.

Cons:
* Voice commands via Alexa ability isn't enabled yet.  Siri works fine.
* The app could be more refined as there was a registration issue (fixed today) and sometimes the app will cause the ear buds to disconnect for some reason.
* Earbuds seem to hurt my ears a little after wearing them for more than an hour.  I am debating on whether I should get Comply Foam Tips to resolve this issue.
* Buttons can be painful to press -- feels like you're jamming the buds into your ear.
* Base seems to be lacking but you can modify it via the music equalizer in the app.

Update 6/11: Got the Comply Foam Tips (the sports kind) but they don't really fit well on these ear buds.  I ended up reverting back to the original tips and it's actually been fine.  My ears have adjusted to them I guess.  I'm using them to and from commutes as well as my workouts with no issues.  Haven't been really using the buttons much yet though.

title: Exactly What I was Hoping For
content:
The earbuds rest perfectly, and without discomfort after several hours of use. The sound quality and loudness potential is far greater than either of the jabra pulse models, or jaybird 3, which are the earbuds I've been using until now. I use these when running, and at my desk, listening usually for 1-3 hours at a time. I put them back in the case when I'm not using them, and I end up having more than enough charge for a whole week of listening! They are very good at blocking noise, much like on-ear gel earplugs. The app allows for ambient sound to play back at a diminished volume, which is a little surreal, and feels like I'm living inside of a conference call.. but it's useful sometimes. I must say, this is the most satisfied I've ever been with earbuds! I've spent a lot more money on other models and brands, usually with sexier marketing, or popular appeal, only to be underwhelmed or disappointed with quality or unnecessary features.

Note: These may not fit small ears particularly well. Also, I don't use Alexa for anything, so I can't vouch for that feature.

title: Five Stars
content: Best true wireless headphones I have owned. Far better than any Apple product.

title: Too large
content: These are a little large for my ears and constantly fall out.  Sound is reaalt good

title: I LOVE THESE HEADSETS !!
content:
I must have purchased 20 headsets of the past 5 years...  These are the absolute best headsets I have ever owned!!
Sound quality:  A+ Great bass and highs
Fit:  I am a large man with weird ears, I have never owned a pair of headsets that fit INSIDE my ears.  These state put, right out of the box.. I moved around TRYING to make them come out, I couldn't !!
Battery:  Got a full 5 hours, paused for another 15 minutes to charge and they lasted the rest of my day.
Case: Fantastic!  fits right in my pocket.. SQUEEZE on the side to open.  Thankfully, I viewed a YouTube post to learn this.
Only complaint:  the manual is extremely small. A quick online search will teach you much more.
They are so good, I ordered a Bluetooth transmitter for me TV and Computer so I could use them with those devices. And thankfully, the headsets can be logged onto to two bluetooth devices... so I can watch TV on my TV or computer and still get alerted to phone calls.
FREAKING FANTASTIC !!!!

title: Amazing Battery Life & Stay Put
content:
For the last three or four years I have been using the waterproof Sony Walkman 4gb and love them.  The only downside is that they are Mp3 players only so I decided to get some ear buds.  After researching my needs/wants I selected these and my biggest concern was battery life. and how they stay in your ear.

I've had them for a few days now and today I decided to test out the battery life.  I put them on at 6:00am and had music streaming and it only stopped when/if I received a phone call.  At 11:30am I got the first notification that the battery was low.  Yes! 5 1/2 hours of constant use.  I then wore them another 30 minutes before they died but I was very happy to know I can use them that long non-stop.

As for how they stay in your ear, you just put them in one way and then slightly twist them and they basically lock in.  Sounds odd but it works and they stay in great.

The only downside for me is that my ears start hurting after about an hour of use but I got used to it a little.  When I took them out it's as if my ears were like "ABOUT TIME." :)  I think that is just my not being used to wearing ear buds.

Overall I am VERY happy and think they are amazing works of art. :)

title: Solid headset
content: Good product. Holds up well during workouts, great sound quality. I get some people complaining of issues when I'm speaking but could be related to poor cell service. I would recommend.

title: Subject to the same issues as many truly wireless earbuds
content:
First off, my major annoyance is that I've been using these for a total of about 2 hours and already had to extract a silicone tip from my ear, which is a bit ridiculous.

Anyways, on to regular reviewing.

Pros:
-Sound is good for the price point
-Stay in pretty decently for not having any positive retention like Jaybirds or Bose Soundsports
-App is fairly intuitive and opens automatically when taking ear buds out of the case (necessary for eq to work and passthrough)
-Alexa integration worked

Cons:
-Tip fell off. Already. In my ear. This is the entire reason I hate in-ear headphones because it's always at a really inconvenient time [to find someone/a way to extract it]
-The buttons suck. Feels like I'm mashing the buds into my ear to get anything to work

I'll continue to update the review as I use them more.

title: My New Favorite Headset!
content: This is so far the best wireless headset that actually felt wireless and secure. It’s super expensive but it was worth it...for the most part. Literally my only issue with it was the price. Yet I bought it ssssoooooooo

title: Initial adjustment awkward, but after ‘breaking in’ they’re awesome.
content: First bought these and the eartips really weren’t working for me. Used the size that fit me best but still was far from ideal, I really had to initially pull down on the earlobe, place the buds deem into the canal, and have them stay in that way (which is the proper wearing technique). About a week later, they’re fantastic! ‘Molded’ to my ear shape and I found the angle I like. That was perhaps the only downside I’ve ever experienced with this thing, apart from YouTube videos with a standard viewing account not automatically resuming play after taking one earbud out (though I figure that’s more a YT software issue than the Jabras). Everything else is great, the case isn’t nearly as problematic as most reviews make it out to be and the battery life is really solid. Pressing the tactile buttons may at first seem discomforting, but within a few days becomes pleasing and functional. A really well rounded product and much more solid than Oral B’s AirPods (I’ve tried both). If you’re looking for wireless earbuds, you can’t go wrong with these!

title: Small/abnormal ears need not apply ...
content:
(Disclaimer: I did purchase, but not from Amazon.)  Ever since wireless and true-wireless earbuds were invented, I've had to admire them from afar ... I'm an adult, but I have small ears. Earbuds just don't want to stay in my ears (unless they have the little hook/wings to keep them in.)

But after reading so many reviews of people SWEARING they stay in, and after watching Jabra's video ad (asking the viewer to shake their phone so the model shakes his head from side to side, showing that the earbuds don't fall out,) I decided to try once more. Once again, I was disappointed. They just won't stay in.

YES, I used the small-sized pads.

YES, I read the instructions on how to twist & turn them into position.

YES, I applied gentle pressure to insert them into the ear canal while turning.

And, yes ... they still fall out.

Sure, there were a couple of times they would rest gently in my ears, but as soon as I started normal activity (walking briskly, etc,) they'd fall out. I had to keep pushing deep into my ears to force them to stay. I felt like I needed a degree in anthropometry and ergonomics just to figure out the right way to make them stay. Using earbuds shouldn't be this difficult.

For those super-humans with the perfect ears (who apparently Jabra designed these for,) enjoy them!

But, for the rest of us sub-standard humans with aural deformities not worthy of such luxuries as this, move along ... There's nothing to see here.

title: Bad quality.
content: I went through like 3 of them. They kept messing up.

title: Enjoy these more than my AirPods
content: These are great wireless earbuds, noise canceling, and sleeker than AirPods. They are also sweat proof, so they’re perfect for the gym. The app that accompanies the product is very useful. It has a “Hear-through” function that uses the mic to provide some of the surrounding sounds for walking around the city when noice cancelling may not be the best. The only negative thing about these is the material and latch of the charging case. It feels a little cheap to the touch, and I’m scared of breaking the latch, since it isn’t very easy to open. A magnetic latch would have been better.

title: Unusable. Don't buy. Too much lag and stuttering.
content: Pathetic. Waste of 165$. Both earbuds get randomly disconnected and there is always stuttering. Tried with Samsung Galaxy S9 plus and Samsung Galaxy S10 but problem persists  on both. It's so bad that earbuds ate almost unusable. Updating the firmware to latest did help as well. I want my money back or fix for this annoying problem.

title: Best truly wireless earbuds
content: I researched for months for the best truly wireless headphones. I believe I made the right decision. These sound great. I've had them for months now and no issues at all. Connection is seamless and has only ever broken once for a mere second. Sound is great for earbuds, if you get a good seal it makes a big difference. They stay well in my ears while doing HIIT workouts and running, barely any movement. Battery life is amazing. Highly recommend. Great product.

title: See above
content: Pain in the ass

title: Battery lasts long, they stay in all ear shapes and sizes, and the buttons in them are super handy
content: Better than AirPods. Best Bluetooth I’ve ever tried, and I’ve spent years trying to find the perfect headphones. The battery lasts like 10 hours straight, the case charges fast, they don’t stick out of my ears as much as AirPods do, and their noise blocking is so nice. They are perfect. They stay in my ears and the sound quality is amazing. Honestly shook. They have buttons on them, which arliepods don’t have, so you can pause, turn up or down, and skip and so much more without even using your phone or taking them out. The only downside is that if you want to use one, you have to use the right one because the left can’t be used by itself. Compared to all other Bluetooth earbuds, Jabra is amazing. Seriously. So worth it.

title: Right earbud suddendly stopped to work
content: When initially the earbuds worked just fine. After a while my right earbud started to make weird sounds which I thought came from out. Gradually those sounds became bigger and suddenly my right earbud stopped to work. I've tried everything. Pairing then unpairing. Nothing. For the money I paid I expected to last longer

title: Multi-connect FAIL!
content:
For what I bought it for it failed on 2 out of 3.
 First what it did well.
1 Sound is acceptable. Not as good as my H800 but acceptable.
2 Charging case is nice and I like the way it secures and can only be opened by pressing the sides.
3. reasonably comfortable. Although extended wear may change my mind.
4. For travel I do on a plane, it works well with my phone and I am looking forward to that.

Why it fails:
1. The big reason for this was the multi connect capabilities. Using it to listen to music on the computer and meetings and have it auto switch to phone for calls. It doesn't do this well. I was on a phone call and it kept repeating 2 devices connected/disconnected during my call. I don't think the other person heard it, but it repeated it over and over. Terrible. I finally had to turn off the bluetooth on the computer to make it stop.

Consequently, I will not use it to replace my Jabra Supreme for phone calls and it is absurd that I need to carry two devices.

title: Slippery little buggers
content:
There are many things that I like about this earbuds.  I use them mostly with an Android phone and bought them after a lot of research looking at all the truly wireless earbuds in this price range.  I had narrowed it down to these versus Apple Airpods and ultimately got these for better Android integration and a better deal on a "used" pair from Amazon Warehouse.  (They didn't appear to be used at all.  Probably just a previous customer return that someone decided not to keep.)

They paired easily right out of the box.  I'm not an audiophile, so not as discriminating as some people, but I think they sound excellent.  I'm used to using wired earbuds and find when they seal in the ear canal, they are capable of delivering full, rich sound.  The medium ear gels are the only ones that fit me, but at least they give you a set of small and large in case they don't.  They do get tiring after about an hour or so of use.  Mostly because your ear canal is supporting all the weight of the earbuds.  Although they aren't heavy, they are heavier than wired earbuds, which I can wear for hours without even noticing them.

I've had no video sync issues with YouTube or Plex, my two most-used video apps, which was my biggest concern about truly wireless earbuds after reading all the reviews.

I can't give these a 5-star review for a couple of specific reasons.  First, these things are really, really slippery.  The plastic they are made of is just way too smooth and they too easily slip out of my fingers when I'm trying to put them in my ears or put them back in their case.  There's no way to get them to emit any sound to find it if it's lost, so I could see this being a big problem if they are dropped in a public place like an airplane.

Second, the case is horribly designed.  Like the ear buds, the plastic is really smooth and hard to grip.  The case should take zero thought to open, but the first time I tried to open it, I had to fiddle around with it for at least a minute to figure out exactly how it worked.  It is really difficult to open in the dark since there's no way to tell front from back by touch.  Sticking your fingernail or thumbnail in the little slit does nothing to help you open the case.  It's easiest to open by pushing the lid inward as with one thumb as you are squeezing the sides of the base with your other thumb and index finger to get the latch to release.  Sound complicated?  The fact that I had to type all that out in the first place just to explain it proves there is a flaw in the design.  The latch and lid feel really flimsy and I'm really doubtful it's going to last very long before it stops latching.

All that said, I'm satisfied with them.  I'm admittedly anti-Apple, so I was relieved that I didn't have to buy Airpods to get a good set of truly wireless Bluetooth earbuds.

Edit after 1 month of use:
These are more like a 3.5 than a 4.  I'm still having issues with how slippery they are but have gotten more used to them.  I'm constantly afraid I'm going to lose one when using them out in public.

I dislike the case even more now that I've been using it a few weeks.  I use these almost exclusively at night before going to bed and it's a challenge to put them in their case in the dark.  It's possible, but just way harder than it should be because they have to go in the case just-so or you can't close it.  Combined with how slippery they are, it always takes longer than it should.

I like the HearThrough feature that lets you hear ambient noise while wearing the earbuds, but with my Google Pixel, HearThrough cuts in and out with my right ear bud constantly if no media is playing.  I haven't heard anything from Jabra e-mail support after report it to them,  This alone may make me decide to return them to Amazon before the window closes because I don't know if mine are defective or if it's a known issue.

The fit has been great for my ears.  They feel really secure once they are in and can wear them for hours without noticing them.  If I decide to keep them, this will be the main reason why.

title: HEADPHONES DON'T DISCONNECT WHEN PUT IN CHARGING CASE
content: I am now on my third replacement pair of this headphone, and i have to say that i am bit disappointed by the same recurring issue happening over and over again. i get a pair, it works fine for a month or two, then you finish a call one day, put them back in their case thinking that they will disconnect and recharge as expected  but they stay on. Next thing you know, you get a call, you pick up form your phone, thinking that the buds are in their case doing bud things, but no, you spend the next 30 second shouting hello and hearing a faint mousey voice from somewhere on your desk and thinking you are slowly losing your hearing. I honestly do not know if at this point my local Jabra agent is messing with me by sending me faulty headphones to see me lose my mind or if it is just an issue with these buds.

title: Great product!!
content: It is really easy to use. I loved it!

title: The bad outweighs the good.
content:
I did research on a number of products and was optimistic these were the right choice. Today is my first day using them for my routine workweek and I'm not satisfied. See below:
1) It takes a few seconds and sometimes minutes for the app to acknowledge it is connected to your phone. So switching between presets can be annoying. I've also noticed the app dropping out connectivity at times when changing through presets.
2) I left the office for a walk and tried making a phone call outdoors. The person on the other end had a hard time hearing me because of some slight wind. Also, connectivity got worse when I put my phone in my pants pocket (this stayed true while I was indoors as well). However, this was extremely annoying.
3) Went to the gym this morning and I commonly jump around machines. I must have walked only 20 feet away and the connection became staticy and it was very annoying.
4) Every now and then, there is a routine static that you hear every few seconds. I think it goes away eventually but why is it there in the first place?
The good:
1) They do fit well in your ear. I ended up using the larger earpiece in my right ear and the medium size in my left. Used them while lifting weights this morning and no problems staying in the ear.
2) The hear through option is taking me a little bit to get accustomed to but I do see the value in it.

title: Great ear buds for work and play!
content: Amazing!  As advertised and better. Easy, lightweight, great mic and great for conference calls.  Love the charging case

title: Fit well under Bose noise cancelling headset.
content: I do quite a bit of woodworking. I wear the Jabra under Bose noise cancelling headsets.  They fit without any problem and reduce the noise levels even more.  Also can hear whatever I would be listening to more clearly with the noise of power tools compaired to using only the Bose headset.

title: Stay Away
content:
I bought a pair of these from Amazon Warehouse.  During the first week I had them, there would sometimes be an issue with the left (slave) earpiece not connecting.  I would put both earpieces back in the charging case and then reinsert and the problem seemed to go away.  Shortly thereafter, the left earpiece went completely dead.  I contacted Jabra and performed a complete reset as they recommended.  The earpiece still did not function.

Worse still, after sending them back to Jabra, they denied the warranty because they said I bought them Amazon Warehouse, therefore they were used, not new.

I now see that Jabra offers a LEFT earpiece by itself on Amazon for $59.00.  Why would they do that unless they knew there was a frequent problem with this piece, as there is simply no other reason to but a single, slave earpiece?

I would recommend looking elsewhere before spending your hard earned money on this product.

title: Bad seller
content: The package was open and the ear bud where used. They are listed as new.

title: At last!! Good buy!!
content:
Much, much better than anticipated. Excellent sound and fitting. Very minimal connection skips. Just yesterday at the health club I mistakenly left my phone on a machine and walked at least 40-50 yards when I realized it and even then there was no connection lost during primetime at the club. Battery life is as also excellent. The phone app is also a plus. I would highly recommend these. Don’t go
