For those cheap ones as I have tried, and returned, them as these far exceeded my expectations. No muffled music or unclear phone calls. Go with Jabra.

title: Excellent wireless ear phones
content: Excellent wireless ear phones, excellent sound and perfectly stable wireless connection. I have had no signal drops while using them which is a great achievement by Jabra. Highly recommend this product!!

title: Everything I expected wireless earbuds should be
content:
I bought this item for my daughter, but of course I took it for a test drive before she got it :-)
lovely package (charging case), amazing looking buds. I was afraid that we might have a problem fitting it into my/daughter's ear, but it was a perfect fit, steady and comfortable. The sound was clear smooth and I couldn't detect any faults though I'm not much of an audiophile. installation was a breeze, using the dedicated app on an Android phone. As for battery life, well we didn't get to a point where we need to stop and recharge it during the day use, it is being charged every night (as a routine).
The best feedback is seeing my kid walking most of the day with these earbuds stuck in her ears.

The only cons. is having to shout to get my kid's attention. (The pass-through feature is great :-)

title: good enough for me
content:
I use this when exercise.
It is fixed in ears and sound quality is  good.

title: Great sound but not good for sport
content:
I returned these ear buds - because the left ear bud kept failing after about a month of use.  I could get it working again with all the available hacks and fixes online but it would always stop 5 minutes in a run leaving me fuming for the next 25 minutes.

The Good Stuff - These sound great. They are easy to use and are very comfortable in your ear. I wanted these to work.  I like the hear through feature and the sound cancellation.

Ultimately these were advertised as sport headphones and that is where they don't measure up.

Gym - They sound great but are prone to falling out if you make a facial expression while working out.  If you are training to be a champion at Expressionless Weight Lifting this might be a good training aid.  I tried hard to maintain no movement in my face but it was irritating.

Biking - These are not suitable for biking because if they fall out while you are on a bike, your chances of losing them for good are high (intersections, busy streets, etc.).  I tried with the "hear through" feature but the wind noise through the microphone makes it not feasible.  They are okay with the sound cancellation but not recommended for biking for safety reasons.

Running - These were actually most successful during running...at first.  They sounded great and they stayed in my ears fairly well.  I think running in Houston may have pushed the limits of the sweat resistance in these ear buds.  After a month the left ear bud kept failing - too much sweat caused it to seal against the ear too much and stop functioning.  Sometimes it would just fail altogether.  In pressure on the ear buds to hold them in would stop them form working.

I think if you only used them in an office setting, they would be okay. Or if you wanted to work on facial expression control at the gym...

title: Reliability issues.  Jabra warranty service came through.
content:
Pros: Actual product.  Best available at this price point, at least when I purchased last year.  For me, they are very comfortable to wear.  Only downside functionally is the buttons are a challenge to use while in ear.
Cons: Left earbud failure (no light/charge) at 9 months in.  Jabra Phone support is understaffed (long hold times), but helpful when you finally get through.  Troubleshooting generic instructions out of date (refer to software features that have changed) and not specific to issues you report.  Phone support opened ticket and sent form to start a warranty exchange if necessary.  However, it took a week to receive back response and receive the shipping label, with no communication in the interim.  Process could be improved.  I also inquired if an advance exchange program was available (credit card hold -> ship replacement before old is received to make things faster), but there is not.

Once the defective item was shipped back in, replacement actually shipped out pretty quickly, I received them the next week after the defective pair shown as arrived on tracking.

title: Not so impressed
content: It is hard to keep in your ears, they are too big. I have not gotten it to answering the phone correctly.

content: I like them they work fine for me

title: Not Bad..
content:
Bought this Product because I was looking for a Wireless Bluetooth headphones.
Saw prior reviews on it, many were positive, decided to take a shot, even though I had a bad past experience with the Samsung Icon x 2018 vers.
My product was "used" so I can't say for sure..but I have my personal likes and dislikes
Sound quality for media/music is good..cannot complain..
I like the "Alexa" integration voice commands with the headset and seems to work "okay".
Phone conversations were not so good unless you're in a Semi quiet area, but.... battery life was pretty good.
My issues were sometimes one side would randomly lose sound, but not long enough or frequent enough to get upset about it.
Earbuds may provide some discomfort after lengthy use....
And charging case used to turn off/disconnect earbuds automatically, now I have to turn it off/ disconnect manually by holding right earbud button down till it flashes red 3x.
Also sometimes you may lose sound in the left earbud so you will have to put it back in the charging case to get back sound.
Other than that..I still recommend it for daily use, as I'm still using them till this day.

As soon as either of us walked in the front doors, the earbuds starting cutting out. The left was much worse than the right, but ultimately neither worked. I'm beyond disappointed in how poorly these earbuds worked. I returned these immediately.

title: Sound comes and goes
content: Sound quality was good when it was there. Problem is the sound cuts in and out from my phone less than 2 feet away.

title: Fits great, good battery, sound quality not so well for price
content: Decent wireless ear buds. Not sure if I had detected ear buds, mines had low static noise that was kind of annoying. Tried working with its settings thru my phone and its app but couldn't fix it. Fits well in ears. Battery life is good, should not an issue as you can charge with its portable case. title: Falls out too easily

title: Great
content: Fit well

title: Very nice!
content: Great product very durable! Great fit and snug definitely won’t talk out. Wish they were louder but still sound great

title: Won't stay in, range Is horrible.
content: These will not stay in my ears no matter what I do, the range on them is horrible. If I walk into the next room from the kitchen to the living room they cut out. I had high Hope's for these and researched and thought these would be one of the best, I was sadly mistaken.

title: Great product
content: The  best

title: Really nice.  Thank you Amazon Day Price
content: Just got these today.  Easy set up, straight forward controls.  Fit better than I thought it would.  Doesn’t make me look like the owner/worker relative at the Quicky Mart always on an ear piece with a big mic speaking a foreign language while I’m trying to get some last minute milk.

title: Great Wireless Active Headphones
content: Great product. I hardly ever use it for more than 2 hours straight, but it seems to easily last 4 hour Netflix binge sessions while my fiancé sleeps. The recharge case is kind of a nuisance to open at first, but you eventually get used to it and have peace of mind that if it’s difficult to intentionally open then it will be less likely to accidentally open and get lost. I really like that the case has multiple charges because having to pull out a usb chord frequently is something I do not miss. It’s also really easy to see how much charge is left in the earphones and the case. Phone conversations work well. I haven’t had any complaints on the volume or clarity of my voice on work conference calls. The hear through feature is a feature that I will look for in all of my in ear head phones going forward. Very comfortable and I appreciate the compact size. I had no problem running with them. I’ve had better sound quality from wired headphones, but I think current technology has to make a bit of compromise in this area in order to maximize battery life and increase comfort (which I feel is the right choice for these active wear wireless headphones).

title: Fast delivery
content: My husband loves it

title: Video and Sound are not synchronized
content: Video and Sound are not synchronized. I was trying to write to support team at jabra.com but they didn't answer.

title: Great sounding wireless earphones
content: Fits perfectly in my ear! I love the option to bypass the noise canceling for “situational awareness “ but great for traveling, watching videos without disturbing others.

title: Great gym musical solution
content: I wanted a wireless solution for the gym that I did not have to worry about with sweat. These fit the bill in every area. Great sound and lasts all workout.

title: Jabra did good but not great
content:
Used these for the gym and at work. I was debating between these and the Samsung iconx. The buds are pretty comfortable overall with the ability to listen to them for about 3 hours before fatigue. The sound quality was great for what these are. Controls were not great, with the volume and skip on one side and play pause on the other. I found it annoying when listening to just one ear. Even with both in, pushing the control buttons made the earbuds jam into my ear. Also, the right ear is dominant so you can not listen to just the right bud by itself.

Ended up going with the iconx because of the better controls and ability to use either ear independently. Not sure why other companies are not following that trend.

title: Making workouts more entertaining
content: I love the Jabra Elite Active 65t True Wireless Sports Earbuds for running, doing yoga, or just milling around the house. They sit snugly and I've only knocked one out when I knocked it while wiping my face with a towel on the treadmill. They remain charged for quite awhile, and the case charges them again quickly. The hear-through function makes me feel safer/more in tune with the world around me on an outdoor run. Highly recommend for workout headphones!

title: Should be seamless
content: Left earbud often doesn’t work

title: Great overall
content:
I bounce between Bose and Jaybird ear buds for working out along the way airpods for daily chatter

Let me tell you how I feel about these , first of all th fitment so far is on point! Better than my bulky Bose and my awkwardly designed Jaybirds
Sound quality and connectivity sits between the Bose and the Jaybirds, so far nothing gets close to sound quality and vocals of a Bose
App is amazing and I love it simple and easy to navigate for on the fly tweaking
There is a latency of when you remove one bud when someone is talking to you music still plays in the other but yet again you can't beat the apple airpods for that functionality
Overall I am very happy with my purchase and will definitely buy the be coming to gen when they Come out

content:
I spent maybe 30 minutes with these after unboxing them. Pairing was easy, and the app worked fine. I just didn't like the sound, mainly due to a a serious lack of bass. No amount of fitting or adjusting the equalizer (either via their app or the Samsung music app) could provide the bass sounds that just weren't there. I have a much older Bluetooth headphone, Jaybird Bluebuds (that have the wire between left and right earpieces), and they have much better bass response that I'd rate as fully competitive with better wired headphones.

As such, these Jabra headphones got returned.

title: Good for listening bad for speaking
content: Microphone produces feedback loops and other side hear themselves talking with slight delay

title: Pretty Nice Headphones

title: Very good

Noise cancellation could be better but overall quality is great...

title: There good

content: These wireless buds have pretty good performance. I have experienced feedback issues if I use them in proximity to other electronics.  I also have to be careful when I'm moving my head a lot. They tend to slip out of my ear. The noise cancellation can definitely be improved. I anticipate the technology will improve over time.

title: Call Quality is Terrible
content: Sound is good and they fit well, great for working out. But the call quality is god awful. They pick up all the outside noise, but none of your voice. I literally cannot have calls on these without having to mute my line every 30 seconds for a passing car, it is like they amplify those noises picked up by the mics.

title: Great buy!
content: I got these as a birthday gift for my husband and he absolutely loves them. He uses them every day at the gym and said he loves that they stay in while he’s doing his more intense workouts. They look great, feel good, and work beautifully.

title: Jabra > Beats by Dre
content: I was very suspicious about these headphones not having an ear hook. Was between the Jabra and beats by Dre with ear hook. Jabras have far exceeded my expectations. I do high intensity training and wanted workout headphones that would stay in regardless of the exercise. These have been great, no adjustments needed through an entire workout. Wear then at work too. Sounds great, call quality is awesome. Just what I needed.

title: Not for me...
content: The sound quality and the Alexa feature were the highlights of the product. I noticed that in between wifi and data there was a lot of distortion. Even when I had my wifi off on my phone, there were zones where the headphones would start to crack and distort. I don't think my ears are made for truly wireless buds, so the fact that I felt discomfort after prolonged use, I don't really hold it against these Jabra's. I ended up returning because of the distortions and fit.

title: Great option for folks who don’t want another apple product
content: I am a jabra fan.  I use a headset of their pro model all day at work.  I didn’t want to just mail it in and buy apples products to help with their Trillion dollar estimate so I researched for months before I got these.  First impression wasn’t great - they hurt my ears and felt awful.  They took a bit to pair with my phone, but that was my problem.  When I finally got them rocking I was pretty impressed.  I changed the ear jelly to the largest and things got my better.  I could wear them all day and even made them my primary earpiece for phone calls from clients and customers.  They are larger and people look at you funny at first, but then they just think you are super important and need hands free for counting all your money.  I would buy them again

title: Great for 3 months....then trash
content: These earbuds were excellent when I received them.  I was enjoying them so much and talking about how they were worth the price.  HOWEVER, after 3 1/2 months the right earbud would go soft....distorted....dead...after about 10 minutes.  Check the forums and you will see that this is apparently a common problem.  I was impressed with the Jabra customer service as they accepted this as a warranty claim and sent everything needed to return them for replacement.  HOWEVER, after waiting about two weeks I called for an update on the replacements.  BACK-ORDERED they told me!  Ugh.  The customer service rep said it could be another 2-3 weeks before they shipped.  Sooooooo......I'm not sure how to rate these JABRA ELITE 65t earbuds because I paid good money for them....but don't have them!

title: Wouldn't recommend.
content: Not for all ear types. Not for working out.

title: Not good enough
content: I really want to like these earbuds they have a cool app the earbuds feel like quality and the experience overall just seems cool. However I just bought a pair from Best Buy and will be returning them because in comparison to all their bells and whistle the sound quality speakers have been trash in comparison to the sound quality I get with the free headphones you with your iPhone . Just try to listen to a song with their earbuds and your iPhone free headphones and compare for yourself. Which is sad because I really thought by them being a speaker brand that they would have superior sound but nope! I should have listen to the employee at Best Buy that said the sound quality isn’t up to par.

title: Not reliable. Poor quality for high price.
content: Purchased in July. Worked for 8 months. Right earphone died. Not connecting to charging pod. Wasted $186. Going back to wired earphones. Jabra is not a good product for its price.

title: Wonderful headphones
content: These things are amazing. Great sound quality and they always connect to my phone without fail. The app works well and has some nice features. Would be great if you could adjust sound levels per ear.

title: In love
content: I'm impressed. So much so that when my husband got his a day later I got mine and put a rush on it. I love THEM! They come fully charged! Put them in your ears and poof the voice tells you what to do. Fits perfect in my ears. I'm in love. Love the charging case too.

title: Mobility
content: Awesome headphones to use anytime.

title: Quality sound
content: Bought for the wife to workout and for everyday wear and she loves them.

title: ... trying no to be angry but I am very disappointed with Jabra for the quality of this product
content: I brought these head phones and they arrived today and would not go into pairing mode the right earbud would not turn on for any reaseon will be sending these back really need the music to help me focus been really trying no to be angry but I am very disappointed with Jabra for the quality of this product. I have seen a lot of reveiws like this on one on other sites

title: Did not like
content: No good

title: Jabra Active Elite 65t
content: Jabra has a nice phone app to work with the earbuds.  Sound quality is very good.  Functionality of the earbuds is good.  Unfortunately they just did not fit my ears well and caused constant irritation.  Your mileage may vary with your ears.  The nice thing about Amazon is being able to return product.

title: Worked great but broke after 2 months + poor customer support; clear why users flock to Apple
content:
Loved the product, but extremely unsatisfied that it broke after 2 months and the quality / responsiveness of customer support. As another reviewer mentioned, rapid response and replacement is critical in this space, moreso when competing with the likes of Apple and Bose (whenever friends or myself have had faulty pairs of their products, they were warmly received with immediate replacement; not the case with Jabra at the moment, unfortunately).

If they were able to contact me and arrange expediate replacement or crediting of the purchase (it's still within the stated 1 year warranty) I would be a staunch supporter and promoter of the product and happily revise my review.

title: They have wonderful sound quality and with the Jabra app you are ...
content:
In my opinion these are remarkable earbuds worthy of five stars.  They have wonderful sound quality and with the Jabra app you are able to customize the sound and how the earbuds respond to outside noise.  What I found amazing though is this.  I keep the earbuds in the charger case in my pocket when I am not using them.  Well, I threw my pants into the washer with the charger and the earbuds in my pants pocket and they survived the wash and rinse cycle!  Both items work just as they did before being washed.

Update.  After going through the wash the earbuds worked fine but I later discovered the charging case had suffered a fatally from the water.  The lights on the charger worked until a day or two ago when they failed.  The final realization came when the buds went dead and wouldn't recharge.

title: Decent sound, uncomfortable
content: These were uncomfortable in my ears.  I have Airpods and bought these for better sounds and battery life.  The build quality was not up to Apple standards and I find them fairly uncomfortable after an hour of wear.  Sound quality is good and battery life is longer than I can keep them in.

title: Good product, but not for every ear
content: I very much enjoy these earbuds. They function well after the initial setup and the battery life is long enough to enjoy hours of continuous play. They have good range and the functions on the earbuds allow me to move throughout the house without needing to carry around my phone. The one negative is that they may be a bit large for some people's ears - specifically my wife. This works out for me though because I get to keep them all to myself.

title: Sound quality is not good
content:
These are good for talking on the phone, but not for music listening. There is no bass whatsoever and high mid-range is over-pronounced.
And they do not stay in place while I exercise in gym, specifically when running.

title: Well worth the money
content: Love these things. They did hurt my ears at first if I left them in for a few hours but they dont seem to anymore. Love to talk on the phone with these. Well worth the money

title: One of the best wireless earbuds
content: Great sound quality...quick pairing...very comfortable

title: Great Sound quality but some software gripes.
content: These Headphones are great. The sound quality that these wireless headphones is some of the best I have heard for their price ever. My Main complaint is Auto Pausing is pretty hit or miss and I would like both headphones to continue to operate with that setting off. These headphones will drain your battery faster than Pixel Buds and Airpods will so for long plane rides or road trips you may need a mobile charger.

title: Better than the ip55 rating. LOVE THEM !!!
content: Well ! My wife , was doing the laundry and did not check my pockets. She put a shirt of mine in the washing machine along with my jabras  which were in the front pocket. They washed for 50 minutes and they still work perfect !!!!  LOVE MY JABRAS!  I think they are better than the ip55 rating. “ Strongly recommend them”

title: Best true wireless headphones hands down
content: I bought these headphones basically on the reviews alone.  The headphones sound amazing for what they are.  I wasn't expecting much out of these, but they are louder and have better sound quality than all of the wired wireless buds I've used in the past.(lg, bose, and sony)  I literally just leave the case on my car charger and have them charging when I drive.  I've never seen a low battery warning and I usually have 2 hour gym sessions.  By the end of my session I usually have more than 80% battery left.  They're not lying when they say the ear buds have 5+hours on 1 charge.  Connection wise, with bluetooth 5.0, I can watch videos on my pixel without having the early Speed Racer audio sync effect.  The earbuds also fit great!  Like mentioned earlier, I workout for 2 hours sessions usually and they have never once been close to falling out.  There are plenty of other ear pieces in the box to get your fitment just right incase you do have problems, however.  I don't miss using my big over the ear headphones at the gym, other headphones would fall off doing abs or a set on bench, these never fall out or get in the way, and they are hands down the most comfortable headphones I've ever worn.  I've had them for 4 months now, so I'm comfortable giving these ear buds my recommendation to anyone whose on the fence between these and other true wireless headphones.

title: Perfect product!
content: Perfect as advertised. Sound quality is awesome!

title: Going on my 3rd pair....
content: So... I'll be going on my 3rd pair now, trying to get one that doesn't have a terrible static issue in the left earbud. Tbh, if you're paying close to $200 for buds, they better work perfectly. These things are not worth the headache. Jabra's QC must be awful or just non-existent if this is an ongoing issue with their headphones. I don't see how anyone in QC would allow such terrible static in an earbud to pass off as okay.

title: Great Bluetooth Headset
content: Easy to figure out, great sound, great mic, great all around product. A+

title: AWESOME!
content: Hubby loved these!!

title: Love this product
content: 5 hour usage time is great

title: Best thing ever!!
content:
So I’m gonna start with what I don’t like cause there’s only 1 thing: when you’re on a call, the people on the other line can hear everything around you.
Ok now the good stuff! I felt compelled to write a review because I accidentally washed the left bud in the washing machine today (it was in a pocket) aaaannnd it still works!!! I’m not sure if they’re waterproof but it looks like it! 20min in the wash.
Comfortable, stay in no matter the exercise and I go pretty hard sometimes, rarely need recharging.
I also bought the used ones for $103 (instead of $160) and I see absolutely nothing wrong with them! Highly recommend!

title: great ear buds
content: ear piece fits well fabulous sound

title: A bad mic and difficulties connecting make this hard to recommend
content:
Despite having 4 mics phone calls are impossible. In a quiet office its very difficult to be heard, outside its impossible. For some reason noises from across the street come in louder than my voice.

It randomly has a hard time connecting to my phones and will sometimes drop one or both at random. When I try to play audio it will sometimes play it out of the phone despite showing as being connected. Also, I play a lot of podcasts or youtube videos at 2x speed, which can sometimes result in a staccato like effect where only short bursts of noise will play until it finally syncs up properly. I never seem to have this issue when connecting to any of my rental cars so I'm assuming the issue is with Jabra.

Lastly, the little magnets they use in the case to turn off/on the headphones can sometimes get dislodged.

Other than that, I think the sound quality is good. I like the app. It fits in my ears snugly for regular use. With exercise my ears sweat and it can sometimes get loose, especially if I'm jumping around. On the elliptical or weight training its usually fine. I don't recommend falling asleep with them in on a plane as they tend to fall out when I roll my head and can get lost easily.

title: High frequency/pitch noise
content: There is this constant high frequency noise on my right bud.

title: Don’t buy these. They stop working quickly.
content:
Left earbud stopped working within 2 days.

Did a reset per the manufacturer.

After searching online, this is a recurring problem for people who buy these.

Great concept - guess the tech just isn’t there yet?

title: Excellent!
content:
I have had these for about 6mo now. First pair of wireless headphones, upgrading from a pair of wired noise canceling earbuds.

While they don’t have active noise canceling, the only time I am reminded of that is on airplanes. I love these things. They just “work”. And I have an older phone — iPhone 6s that doesn’t have BT 5.0. Yet range is good, sound is clear and mic is good for calls.

I would buy these again in a heartbeat. Great purchase.

title: AMAZING PRODUCT! With one very minor flaw that everyone should know
content: This is a fantastic product. Reliable, durable, and the sound quality is fantastic.  If i had any notes for a buyer, it would be that you can only use the right headphone as a single. If you only put the left earphone in, with the right being inside the case, it will not work.  This can be problematic for folks with difficulties with their right ear. Otherwise, this product is a must buy for anyone looking for quality wireless headphones

title: Great headphones, pros and cons compared to Galaxy Buds
content:
So now that Galaxy Buds have come out and undercut these headphones, I felt it was relevant to give a review and comparison. I would give the headphones 5 stars except I feel I do need to take the price into account.

Compared to the new Galaxy Buds, the sound quality is noticeably much better on the Jabras, even to someone who is not particularly an audiophile. Jabra also seems to have done a slight refresh on the case design in the past year or so, as there were some subtle changes. Customer service was great--they sent me a new set when I had an issue with my old case.

Still, the design of the Galaxy Buds case is a bit better, a bit smaller, and easier to handle, although the battery life suffers for it. I own both and travel with the Galaxy Buds and use the Jabra for my home computer. If you care about audio quality I think you should go with these, if you don't care about audio quality much or at all you can consider the Buds at the lower price point.

title: Calls are bad but great for music
content:
Good:
Sound quality and music
Idea and software updates

Bad:
Not cheap for the price factor
The person on the other end hears sounds around you more than you and it’s annoying
It doesn’t disconnects if no activity like Bose so battery runs out quickly

title: Great headphones
content: These headphones are amazing for the gym, as well as, chores around the house.

title: Convenience, compact, versetility.
content: Nice!

title: Really impressive sound
content:
Since many have reviewed these and they're generally proclaimed the best truly wireless earbuds, I'll chime in just to compare to some other earbuds I have known well:  Ultimate Ears Super.Fi 5, Ultimate Ears Triple.fi 10, Jaybird BlueBuds X, and Jaybird X3.  The music sound quality on these is at least as good as all of them except the Ultimate Ears Triple.fi 10s, which are still my gold standard.  But these Jabras are not far off of it, at least for regular phone-powered use.  (They sound much better than the Jaybird X3s that I recently purchased, which are perfectly fine headphones at about 1/3 the cost but are ridiculously bass-heavy, wired together, and also use a ridiculous proprietary charging cable.)  For truly wireless headphones, I'm really impressed by how good these sound, and the Jabra app makes fine-tuning to suit your tastes really easy.  The controls are intuitive and work well, and the HearThrough feature is really clever to allow you to keep them in even when you need to hear the outside world.  It's hard to imagine better truly wireless headphones at this price point, and everything seems very well thought-out and tested.

For those thinking these things are underpowered bass-wise, make sure you're trying different tips to get a good seal in the ear - changing to the largest included tip made a big difference for me.  They're nicely balanced, and with EQ adjustments can definitely get very bass-heavy if that's your thing.

Final note:  After updating the firmware, I had a lot of interference/connection issues between the left and right bud and was about to declare my pair a lemon.  But after about 5 minutes that went away and now they're back to sounding perfect.  Hopefully that will last.

title: Consolation Prize
content: I weaved my way through several wireless to these - resisting these and the AirPods. No joke. I wanted to love these and not have to look elsewhere. I like 4/5 of it's features. But I had to go with the AirPods after a side by side comparison. Mostly because of ease of use, stay-in-ear capability, and over function. That's all I'll say. Consolation prize never won in my book.

title: Prefer Bose sport. Found these bulky and unconfortable.
content:
I bought these and returned them before even opening after trying my husbands set.

I found them unconfortable and awkward looking.

My husband loved them originally but now wants to return as finding they don’t stay in well.

title: Fits in my pocket discretely.
content: Love my music and able to have a good call in the meantime. Very nice true wireless headset.

title: Like the design.... worth the $'s.
content: Fits firmly in my ears. It's discreet and comfortable for long meetings. I have multiple premium headsets and the audio quality is near par with some of them. My need is to have good looking Bluetooth device that has good audio quality that is true to the source and discreet without the tangling wire . This device checks my requirements to my satisfaction and exceeds my expectations. It is little pricey but worth the money just for the look compared to the protruding white apple pods.

title: Great sound.  Awesome fit
content:
These buds are awesome. I realized that the sound quality was limited by the source (Pandora). When I play hifi stuff from Tidal they sound amazing

I’ve also had people say they sound way better for phone conversations than the Bluetooth in my car

I didn’t try the other ear pieces that were included because the ones that were on there fir perfectly

title: Solid headset, feels great and sounds good.
content:
Pros:
Case is nice, and charges easily
battery life is great
hearthrough is super cool
App is solid
connects easy

Cons:
Little spendy but not bad
bluetooth could be stronger, after about 20ft things start getting iffy

will post more once I have had them for more than a few days.

title: Great!
content: These are BY FAR, the best fitting, best sounding truly wireless earbuds I have ever tried.  WAY better than the Apple Earbuds.

title: Like the design and functionality
content: My first pair of earbud and so far it works accordingly.  I use it leisurely for one hour at the gym and one hour on the train.  Sometimes I forget to charge it, and it can still go a few days without charging.

title: Too big. The screw-in lock-in system hurts
content:
The active 25% off sale tipped the balance and I decided to buy a new pair. I tried them for about an hour before *having * to take them off. I'm sure you have read if not watched a number of mostly positive reviews, so I will skip to my summary of why I wouldn't recommend this headphones.

They look good, but bulky, the sound is only reasonably good and the range didn't impress. But by far the most important thing that you should know is that these are too big and coupled with the lock-in system that inserts them into your ear canal, your ears will most likely hurt after more than 30min of continued use. To make things worse, pressing the buttons means pushing them further in...

If you have normal sized ears, be aware that the lock-in fit will probably hurt. And if you can't keep them in for more than 30min, all the great features that these headphone promise are useless.

title: Best true wireless product I’ve tried
content: I’ve used them a lot and still haven’t charged them.  They get a little uncomfortable after a while but nothing crazy.  Sounds great, I can hear cars coming when I’m out walking, almost amplified.  I got them on sale so I’m thrilled for what I got for the price.  True wireless is the best

title: Major go
content: Used only once so far at the gym they feel really bulky at first but quickly got use to them and they feel very secure. The sound quality is really good as well

title: Great Quality
content: My only  complaint is the max volume is not loud enough

title: A little disappointed.
content: Shortly after getting them, I started having problems with the right ear bud. It would occasionally start making a high-pitched ringing or screeching sound, a little like microphone feedback, and I needed to turn it off and back on for it to go back to normal. So there's that. I can't really speak to the noise canceling or moisture wicking properties, didn't really try those out. If not for what I assume is a defective ear bud, they'd be good.

title: I paid for this?
content:
I come form being a mid range wired audiophile, shure se215, dt200, akg 702, etc. I bought these to replace my shures for motorcycle commutes, and they work... Sorta.
Pros-
Sound decent. I have no complaints about it compared to my se215s.
Can fit them inside my Arai helmet.
They stay put in the helmet and when walking around.
They look decent
There battery life is great.

Here's the same issues everyone else has.
Cons-
These are wide and hurt my ears if worn to long.
Taking my helmet off is very tricky, they like to roll out and press again my head (very painful).

The Bluetooth connection is very finicky, it works fine in my pocket and jacket but if i kneel down and my leg and torso encapsulate my phone the buds cut out. The buds are 1 foot away even!

My left bud actually seems a tiny bit louder than my right, no way to adjust either.
A lot of reviews of the app talk about how it breaks or ruins the buds.

In conclusion, these are still my cheapest, most reliable, best fitting option for travel and motorcycle rides so far. So cons asidei guess these will work but if you aren't in a hurry to buy, wait a few more years. The tech will only get better.

title: Had these for only 2 months...
content:
Had these for only 2 months and the left earbud decided to lose its sound output. It felt like having music come in from the right earbud and having an ear plug in the left ear.

I don't recommend buying this product.

title: The best for the $
content: Easy to use, nice sound and looks great. Much better than what Apple is putting out.

title: Didn't Love the Fit
content: Overall, these headphones do what they say they're going to do. They have good isolation, I liked how quiet it made everything and appreciated the Mic quality. I really didn't love how they fit in my ears. I changed the rubber ends to the smallest ones, and, while that fit worked, the actual earbud hurt my right ear. Not necessarily a product defect, I just found that the experience wasn't as streamlined as I wanted. will probably just end up getting airpods.

title: Fall out during workouts
content: i really want to like these but I can not get them to stay in my ears when working out. I asked for support and they said there wasn’t support for this type of issue. Would not recommend if you are going to use them to workout.

title: Good for the couple months
content:
I really enjoyed it for couple of months. The sound quality was good, it was robust and the battery life was surprisingly good. But now after using it for two months, I'm starting to face some issues:
- left ear bud is louder than the right
- right ear bud keep going on and off (or probably low and high volume, not sure)

The right ear bud volume fluctuation is super annoying. Going to contact support to figure out what can be done about this issue.

title: Outstanding Sound Quality
content: Amazing sound quality. Very rich bass for those Jazz lovers out there.  The ability to shut out outside "noise" is a great feature for those working in an open office environment.

title: Fits perfectly
content: Sound could be better. The volume is a bit low.

title: Missing Charge indicator
content:
What I find hard to believe is that there is no charging indicator on the outside of the case.

I have had a few occasions where I put them in the case, made sure they aligned, closed the box and then came back to use them a day later and they haven't charged.

So now I put them in, then wait, then open the case connect to them via mobile check if the battery charge has increased and then close the lid again.

I think it's crazy not to show when the earpieces are charging on the case. To have to open the case to see a red light, orange light or green light that flashed for a few times and then goes off is not good design. We need an indicator to tell us that they are charging. I have another pair from another company which a clear top so I can see that they are charging.

This is really my only negative.

title: Can easily compete with Bose and AirPods
content:
These headphones are pretty good. They stay put easily and come with different size earbuds. The charge on the headphones last about 5 hours, and they charge while in their carrying case. You are also able to simultaneously charge the case as the case charges the headphones.

Pros:
-Sound quality is really good. Almost no difference from non-Bluetooth headphones.
-The noise cancelation is great. My roommate is the loudest snorer on this planet, I just put these headphones in and then turn on some light rain noise and his snoring is gone.
-The headphones come with and quick option to hear-through. You just press the button on the right side headphone twice and it will activate the microphone and let you hear everything around you. It can be convenient for staying aware of your surroundings on a jog.
-The Jabra app is easy to use.

Cons:
-The microphone is actually a little lacking. If you’re anywhere other than a quiet room by yourself your voice may not get through well.
-The right headphone has to be used at all times. You’re unable to take out the right headphone and keep listening, but you can with the left headphone.

title: Mismatch my needs
content: Despite these are really nice and quality headphones, they absolutely mismatch my needs. It's not possible to use them separately - I mean left earplug  doesn't work without right one. All other earphones in that price range can do that and this is exactly what I really needed. I feel really sad and disappointed, because this headphones are absolutely useless for me.

title: Will not stay connected after only 1 week of use!
content: Didn't have for a week and keeps disconnecting and connecting want stay connected long enough to listen to the music  and sound quality is 2 out of 10 edit they have switched them out a couple of times and now I have a good pair! That stay connected!

title: Excellent battery life. Good sound quality.
content: Had this for about a month now. My impression is very positive. Battery life is excellent. I have not run it down to empty yet and it's consistently match the rating of 4 hours in a single charge. Bluetooth connection is stable too, I have not had any issue with it dropping between the left and right or with the phone. Sound quality is very decent too, no complains. I just wish the earbuds and charging case feel a bit more solid. It is very light so can't complain too much.

title: Best Airpod alternatives
content: I don't where to start with theese they are absolutely amazing definitely a good alternative to airpods great sound quality amazing design except the case because the buds aren't held in the case by magnets and because of that I lost one bud lickly the left one because if you don't have a the right one the left one doesn't work by its self that is the only thing that I would say is a con the sound isolation is absolutely amazing I would put both in at work and would be able to hear anything with music playing lightly I would definitely recommend

title: Best Bluetooth Headphones
content: I've owned Beats and Bose Bluetooth headphones and many others. I am active, run/workout 3 or more days per week. These headphones are sweat resistant, sound is great and battery life is stellar. The app is must have with the headphones; you can adjust sound setting such as bass and treble, also turn on a feature called noise passthrough that allows you to hear what's going on around you even during music play. All of that is awesome, but the most important thing is that these headphones are durable! Two Bose and two beats headphones broke on me in less than 2 years around 6mo. Per device!

title: Minor connectivity issues, but overall a great headphone
content: If i wasnt for the random connectivity issues i sometimes have with these headphones and my Galaxy S8+ these would've recieved a 5 star rating

title: Great pair of earbuds
content: Love the sound on these. Use them to listen to music and watch movies on my iPad.  Love not having the wires.  They can be inconsistent when using them for phone calls.  You can your caller but the caller sometimes cannot hear you.  Therefore,  I just use for listening to tv and music

title: Excellent wireless earbuds.
content: I use this product mainly during my commute to and from work. The product is easy to see, the battery life is excellent and it is comfortable to wear as well. After you have used it for a while, you will not realize you are wearing them.

title: Stopped Working, Poor Support
content: I liked these fine while they worked, which was for 11 months.  Then the left earbud stopped playing content, though weirdly the controls on the button still worked.  I went to the internet to look for a solution and what I found was that this is a very common problem - left earbud works for a while, then dies.  There is a very big quality control issue with this product.  If you think your warranty will cover the potential problem, be aware that the manufacturer will require you to pay to ship the buds back to them for repair.  As a consumer with so many other choices, you can afford to be particular and go with a product with a better reputation for reliability and support.

title: So well designed, you'll wonder how you lived without them.
content:
Everything about the implementation of these things speaks to the quality of the Engineering team at Jabra; the hardware, software, and firmware are all crisp.  I could go on and on, but I'll address what people care about:

The battery life is phenomenal.  I don't listen to music 15 hours a day or anything, but I am popping these things in and out constantly.  The case is the perfect size to feel comfortable always having it with you while adding a ton of extra capacity.  I go a couple days forgetting to charge the case, they're fine.  I go a day forgetting to put an earbud in the case,  it's fine.

The sleep / wake battery saving is incredibly effective, and super snappy.  I'm never waiting for these to reconnect.  Range is great.  I'll have one in at work, leave my phone at my desk, go to the bathroom down the hall, and they still are streaming through the wall.

They fit me really well.  I'll forgot I've got one in my ear for hours, and when I take it out I somehow feel less comfortable.

Call quality while driving is better than anything else I've tried.  The hear-through is very well implemented.

The phone app is well designed, does exactly what it says it'll do, and does it well.

If I lost one, ran over it with my car,... I would cry -- and promptly come directly to this page and order another pair.

title: Left earphone hiss. Not at this price point.
content: There's a hiss in the left earphone. Seems like a known issue: I returned one set with this problem, and got a second one, and same problem. Internet confirms -- lots of forum posts on this. It wouldn't merit a one star review if these were $30, but at nearly $200, it's not acceptable.

title: 4.8 Stars
content: Excellent sound, good noise canceling. Great fit and very light once inside the ear. Good connection for a long distance. Wish it was not dependent on the right side, and I could listen using only the left side. Also wish for wireless charging. May get the darker color next time since it looks a little like a hearing aid.

title: Great all around
content:
*note* after reading many complaints from previous reviews, please make sure you have the latest firmware version updated.

I use these headphone everyday as a traveling professional to handle phone calls, music, exercise.  As no one product is a master of all trades, these are excellent for what they are.

Noise canceling - theyre never going to be my bose quiet comforts, however they handle airplanes, airports, city streets, office, and gym well enough to pass.

Phone calls - solid connection with the other end hearing me clear.  However, the external microphones do pickup a lot of background noise so be aware of your environment.  If youre in NYC during rush hour people will hear all your surrounding noises so be mindful of that.  Its no different if you were using the phone as is.

Exercise - these buds dont slip, move, and stay put both indoor and outdoor activities.  Sweat also doesnt seem to add to any issues with ear security.  Ive worn these a full 6 hours before and never experienced the "ear phatigue" most headphones cause.  They are comfortable and deliver what I need them to day in and out.

Overall a great purchase, just make sure to stay updated on the latest firmware for optimized performance.

title: Works fine but would not buy again
content:
After a decent amount of research I decided to give these earbuds a try.  They work fine...but they are not worth the price.  Sound quality is fine and the range is okay (it reaches about a third to halfway across my one-story house).  I'm also not convinced they are noise-cancelling.

I WILL say that these little suckers a durable.  I cram these in my ears and they fall out after 5-10 minutes if I'm doing good. I've tried changing the earbud cushions to the different sizes in an attempt to keep them in place with no luck.  I'm mostly impressed they are still alive.  One popped out into a bucket of soapy water...still works.  Another time one fell out, hit the pavement hard, and rolled down the hill...still works. Additionally the earbuds do really irritate my ears.  It makes them itch and feel like a bug is crawling in them.  I like the earbuds I just can't wear them for long.

On a personal level I regret buying the rose gold color.  This was my mistake, but I did not realize how beige the sides were and that is what is mostly seen.  It looks like I have tumors coming out of my ears.  I try to cover them with my hair when I go out. Learn from my mistake.

title: Best for listening music and clear voice call
content:
Highly recommended for listening music and very clear voice call. I am using every day, for 8 hours mostly music and few hours for Messenger voice and video call as well.
The only comments is the size, hoping next model rejoice just a little da length and the over all size

title: Worth every penny
content: Great sound and deep base. Love em!

title: The best
content: Lo mejor en audio inalámbrico

title: All of the above.
content: It's the best.

title: I can't express how much I love these headphones.
content:
These headphones are awesome! I purchased them thinking I'd hate them, since I'd been using my boyfriend's airpods for a while and really started to like them. However, I wanted a sound canceling experience and the airpods sometimes bothered my ears if I wore them for too long. When I got these, I was very surprised and happy.

Pros:
They have a "sound through" feature that makes it so you can hear through them, which I had no idea when I bought them. This is SO perfect since you can choose to have them like an airpod experience or through regular noise resistance. I've worn them biking regularly, and feel confident I can hear traffic and other important noises through the feature. I also workout with them, a lot of cardio and they don't shake out of my head one bit.

When you take one out, the music stops. This is something I loved about airpods, and I'm glad you can optionally keep it with these.

The battery life and case are stellar!

The volume/skip play/pause/siri controls are awesome. Way better than the limited controls of airpods.

They don't look too bulky

You can connect two devices at once!? (macbook and iphone!)

Cons
I've had a little bit of connectivity issues with the left pod, but it's extremely quick and not very often. Sometimes they're also too big for my ears, but I have smaller ears so that's pretty common for me. I've found a way to adjust them so they don't hurt for longterm use.

It took me a while to figure out how to turn them off, and sometimes they turn themselves back on after you take one out and accidentally touch the sensors again when you put them down. They can start playing music again when you think they should be turning off

title: love them
content: love them

title: Love them!!!!
content: Love my Jambra EarPods.  The sound is amazing. They fit great.  My Only complaint is battery life is not long enough for me.

title: They’re good but buy them new not used
content: Liked the size and case. The noise canceling was it to good though.

title: Needs improvement
content: I love this device.  what I dislike is the way it fits in the ears. very difficult to put In, so I don’t use it as much.

title: Not worth the money
content:
I really wanted to like these. But I should have heeded the advice of previous reviewers.

These headphones have a persistent background static that is present with many types of audio (particularly with podcasts/classical music).

The “audio stop” feature when you take out one ear bud is attrocious. Music pauses in the earbuds that remains in your ear, but continues in the one you remove. I tried to turn the feature off, but that didn’t work either.

Lastly, recently these have started cutting out sporadically (despite the fact that my phone is inches away).

Here’s the cherry on top: customer service is ATROCIOUS. I filed a claim with Jabra December 15th. They didn’t reply for three weeks. Then they said they would send me a replacement earbud (just one earbud, rather than the set). Then no word for another month, when they notified me that there’s a back order and I won’t receive the earbud for an ADDITIONAL month. I tried calling them but of course no one picks up.

Tl;dr - Jabra is an awful company. Spend your money elsewhere

title: Battery life is good
content: I wish my it would fit tighter but overdid a good product

title: I Love it....😍😎💋
content: Good bass and sound. Battery last long enough. There app is great. I love them.

title: Great quality
content: I love how these stay in place while I’m running. Great quality

title: Download the app for better sound and auto adaptive customization. Great headset
content:
Very impressed so far.
One flaw, does not magnetically attach inside charger case. Lost my left earbud within the first 2 hours of ownership. Found it later that night at the restaurant where it fell out. Luckily they are durable as well and got kicked into a corner under a bar stool and didn't sustain any damage.
Still sounds good (made equalizer adjustments with the app). Bass is not overly powerful but the high-hat hits come in a little sharp out of the box. Several settings can be save for sound and automatically switch over based on what is happening (can pre-set for: music, calls, and noise filtering).
Can listen with one earbud (right only) , but take one out of your ear and it will automatically pause music (cool!) put it (left bud) in the case, press play and it resumes with the single (right) earbud.

UPDATE: after using for a while, I've noticed these give my left ear "fatigue" due to the shape. Unfortunately it's just a tiny but too large for my small ears and I can't wear them for long periods of time (over 30min)

title: Terribly uncomfortable...
content: These headphones sound AMAZING, the noise cancellation is fantastic and the app is a Godsend, but they're just so hard to wear for more than 30 minutes at a time...

title: The right ear works for 15 seconds and then fades out and even distorts
content: I have had these ear pods for about 6 months and now the right ear bud works fine for like 30 seconds. Then all of a sudden slowly gets quieter and quieter. I did check my right ear bud in both of my ears it's not me it's definitely the ear bud. If I let it charge for like 30 mins it will go back to normal volume, then get quieter again over time and stay like that. It sits at about 25% normal volume, so I hear my music or phone calls. Search the internet and you will see lots of people have this issue and Jabra says too bad. None of the fixes work either.

title: Falls out if I nod my head
content: Sound is okay but frequently disconnects and constantly falls out of my ear, no matter which tip I use. Also, you can't tell left from right without. flashlight and magnifying glass, which is very annoying on the subway or in dim light and would be so easy to fix with one little indicator dot. This is, in fact, a really dumb design flaw in most earbuds.

title: Comparison to B&O E8’s
content:
I couldn’t find a review to line up the B&O E8’s and the Active 65t’s so here’s you go:

I’m a huge audiophile owning everything from B&O, to my current Martin Logan’s. So to me, spending an extra $100 to see if B&O would outperform the Jabra’s is well worth it, or so I thought.

I put one of each in each ear to truly compare the difference.

Treble: Same
Mid range: Jabra
Bass: Jabra
Sound stage: Jabra
Connectivity: Jabra
Ease of use: Jabra
iOS App: Jabra

So the sound blows away the audio “experts” at B&O. The B&O sound more like what I would expect from Sony.

The connectivity is flawless from jabra. There’s a voice prompt that informs you of everything; “connected, not connected, looking for Bluetooth”, etc... while on the B&O you have to decipher a light located on the inside of ONLY the right earpiece.

The button on the B&O do not click or inform of any press while on the Jabra you can clearly decipher a press to know it’s been activated. Important when you want to change tracks while running or activate any function while on the go.

I felt the B&O sticks out more than the Jabra’s. And the Jabra’s find their correct orientation much easier than the B&O.

The rubber ear pads fit much more snug on the Jabra’s. I can feel very comfortable with my sprints using my Jabra’s while the B&O feel more flimsy.

The soundstage and full rich sound on the Jabra’s are very good compared to the B&O. The B&O sound empty, lifeless, and boring. The B&O app is attrocious for anyone that cares about detail in sound. The B&O splits audio frequencies in the terms “warm, excited, relaxed, and bright”. While the Jabra shows a full range EQ bar. Not sure what B&O was thinking but clearly the designer of the app was not an audiophile.

I wrote this review to help someone that truly cares about the best sound quality. I’m now headed back to Best Buy to return the B&O. The review between them didn’t even take ten minutes to decide which is best.

I’m very happy with Jabra. B&O, you’ve proved that money doesn’t always buy happiness🙃.

title: I’m glad I made the purchase.  They work great and have a lot of carefully thought out features.
content:
This is my first pair of wireless headphones.  I purchased them to replace a pair of Bose wired earbuds that I used for exercise.  I made the decision based on some reviews I had read of wireless exercise earbuds.

I’m quite impressed with them and very happy that I purchased them.  I keep finding new features and they work better than I thought they would.

I pair them with two devices.  The first is my phone.  The second is a Bluetooth transmitter that I plug into my TV when I’m jogging on my treadmill.  I expected to need to un-pair and re-pair each device when I wanted to use one or the other but it seamlessly remembers and uses both as appropriate.  There is a very small delay (a fraction of a second) in watching TV this way but it isn’t enough that it bothers me.  I have to concentrate on delay to even notice it.

The headphones provide a variety of voice prompts that help use it.  The app notifies the user and updates firmware when available, and guides the user through making the update.  The user interface is carefully thought though, all the way down to the colors of the LEDs in the charging case that indicate various things.

The headphones have a pass-through feature where they use the external mic to pass audio so you can better hear what’s going on around you.  I don’t recommend using these while exercising in safety critical environments like bicycling.  The feature works well but is masked by whatever you are listening to.  But it works great if you use it to hear people talking to you while you have them in.

I’d suggest a couple improvements - first is the ability to reprogram some of the buttons (at least one of them).  You can use a button press to activate a voice assistant (either Alexa or Siri).  That’s not that useful to me.  I’d rather have the ability to turn on or off the pass through feature. Another improvement would to to increase the response time of the pause.  If someone’s talking to me and I need to pause the headphones, it takes several seconds.  It would be nice to mute the voice immediately even if the actual pause takes a couple seconds to register on the phone and I miss a few seconds of audio.  The ability to “pause and active pass through” quickly would be perfect.

title: Pretty unreliable and ultimately very frustrating...
content:
They worked without issue for about a month.  Then one of the earbuds would stop working requiring that earbud to be put back in the case to re-sync.  Then the volume became imbalanced between the R/L earbuds...  Support is pretty clueless and the resets don't help.  The firmware update 2.25 seems to have made things worse.

Regret the purchase and wouldn't recommend.

title: Right ear bud kept going out
content: Only one of the heads sets would have decent quality. The right ear bud you could hardly hear it. It was so very frustrating. Jabra support kept telling me to reset it. That never worked. $200 is not what I would pay for these.

title: Comfy and intuitive!
content:
Very easy to set up, intuitive to use!
I have *very* small ear canals and struggle with fit on most earbuds. The smallest buds on the Jabra fit comfortably and securely.
I use these for calls at work and  walking outside, and everyone said they could hear me clearly.
Volume does not go very high, but with the snug fit ensuring noise cancelling, it's quite comfortable and clear.
My previous bluetooth headphones didn't have a battery indicator, so I really appreciate the light on the charging case.

title: Almost 5 stars, but the casing is too slippery...
content: The earbuds are made of rather slick plastic, and it takes some careful effort not to drop them while trying to put them in your ear, or back in the charger if your hands are dry.  Otherwise, they sound fantastic for the price, and the sound pass-through function works very well to keep you situationally aware of your surroundings.  The app is nice since it allows you to store different EQ presets.  The earbuds pair very quickly to your Bluetootch device.  If they just used a less-slick plastic for the earbud casing, these would be perfect!  If I could give 4 1/2 stars I would, but it's not yet worth 5 stars.  Still highly recommended based on how well the unit works.

title: Best earbuds by far
content: Great sound and seamless connection and operation. Need to get the ear fit right first couple times. Best BT earbuds I’ve used by far.

title: Do not waste your $
content: When I saw this I was excited to see a competitor in the market but sadly I was mistaken. The left earbud always sounds slightly faint in the sound quality compared to Bose or even Beats is downright terrible. Sound quality is decent but when listening to music it is very mono and flat even with equalization.  To have the battery life is mediocre and I have found the charging case allows you one extra charge. One thing that was disappointing is not knowing when the air buds are fully charged. I will not be a returning customer of Jabra products.

title: Right ear wouldn't connect
content: Did not work, returned

title: One earbud died a few weeks after the warranty period.
content: I was reasonably happy with those until one earbud died a few weeks after the warranty period. At that price point I can't recommend.

title: Wanted to like these, but static-y left earbud made me return them
content:
Pros: great fit, super compact charging case, excellent connectivity between audio source and earbuds.
Cons: anemic sound, very sensitive to interference.

I really wanted to like these. After spending many years with Bose products, I wanted to see what other brands had to offer. These were very highly recommended by many tech websites and product reviewers, with the caveat that true wireless earbud technology isn't all there yet. These earbuds have the most recent, highest fidelity iteration of Bluetooth technology (Bluetooth 5.0)...but it's meaningless if the audio device (e.g an iPhone) doesn't support the same. I has happy for a couple hours until I started noticing the less-than-satisfactory audio.

Overall, the sound is a little thin. It might be because the buds aren't that well sealing (easily solved by getting better fitting ear pieces) despite the overall excellent fit. The equalizer on the companion app can really meaningfully impact the sound quality depending on the song...but it's ridiculous to have to pull up and change the equalizer every time the song changes.

The absolute biggest problem was a persistent, underlying static in the left earbud while audio was playing, specifically. I'm not sure if this were due to interference from other devices because it happened ONLY while the left earbud was playing audio and not while the audio was paused, but it was definitely, wholly unacceptable. I might have gotten a defective left earbud; apparently this is not uncommon, judging from other reviews and sources, with this product.

I've since picked up a pair of the SoundSport Free and haven't had any static problems.

title: Good features, very average sound.
content: I was pretty disappointed in these. They have a ton of features, which I would never use. But its cool they are there. At first I was really excited, this is the best fitment Ive been able to achieve with truly wireless buds. But the sound is very average. I would say its “flat” and the eq settings in the app didn’t give it a enough of a kickstart.  I purchased these for the gym, and was extremely underwhelmed. I honestly have a set of 30 Ankers that sound better. I can’t justify paying almost $200 for buds that don’t wow me in the audio dept.

title: ... are plugged in to ears and design is not great. Quality of sound is very good
content: Earbuds are Very harsh and I feel very suffocating when they are plugged in to ears and design is not great. Quality of sound is very good.

title: Very useful
content:
The good - I loved these earbuds!  They were comfortable, practical, and had great sound for most indoor use.
The bad - In outdoor use they seemed to pick up every bit of wind noise for both the called party and myself; much more than switching to cell phone only.  Also, listening to music, indoors at moderate levels seemed to produce a base reverb.  Not a pleasant sound.  These are great for general use listening, working out, running, etc, but not exactly high fidelity and not great for outdoor phone use. I'd recommend them for most uses.

title: Poor Connection
content: Sound quality is Excellent, quality is Excellent only thing that makes it behind from other headset is the connection strength. When I bought is I use to listen to the song while my phone is out but if I put the phone in the pocket it keeps looking sound and same thing if I put in the next room.

title: OK, but not great in a crowded market
content: There are a lot of options today for wireless in-ear sport earbuds. These, while better than Sony's truly middling offering, still really fail to shine in comparison to Bose or several of the others I've tried. They aren't really comfortable, their charging case is bulky but does not have a ton of battery life, and the bluetooth range/reliability was worse than any other wireless buds I've used before.

title: Love the Quality and Style Design of these Jabra Elite 65t
content: I was a bit skeptical on purchasing these since I've never heard them before, but I loved the discreet and stylish design of them, so I took the plunge and bought them. That decision was one of the best I've ever made on Tech. These sound amazing, fit incredibly comfortable, have noise cancellation, with the option of Hear Through technology, which allows you to still hear your surroundings while listening to your music. They're just as amazing on phone calls. crystal clear.

title: Really excellent features, sound quality and in-ear security
content: Got these last week and have used every day since. Very comfortable when in the ear  and unobtrusive (and the box comes with other earbud sizes for different ears, but the ones it came with worked great for me). Good audio quality, and the app allows for adjustments to your preferences. Connected in seconds to my iPhone with no connection issues and stay connected even when halfway across the house from my phone. Secure in the ear. Used these while mowing the lawn on a riding mower and they block a significant amount of noise and held in my ears just fine with no looseness or unblocked external noise. Hear-through feature doesn't work great for voice, but that's a minor gripe. It picks up other noises (keyboards and that kind of thing) better than external voices. I'm extremely happy with them so far. The case charges from almost empty to full in about 30 minutes using the USB adapter in my truck. Batteries last longer than I can stand having earbuds in, but these don't hurt the way apple's earbuds do. I can wear these for hours at a time and not hurt. Great purchase, look forward to using for years.

title: My New Fav
content:
I’ve been a Jaybird fan for approx 5 years now and even dipped my toe briefly into the AirPods pool before going back to my trusted Jaybirds. I’ve heard so many great things about these Jabra earbuds so thought I’d give them a try. I can honesty say I’M A CONVERT. Way more functionality than Jaybirds and AirPods and the sound is great! They are not bass heavy and even though I like quite a lot of bass they produce just enough to satisfy my bass preference. The in app equalizer helps with that.

Really good comfy fit and great call quality too. I would highly recommend these earbuds.

title: Poor connection
content: Poor bluetooth capabilities.  Ive also used some sony headphones and never have had issues with connection quality.  The jabra continually disconnect or have issues while playing music.  Unless my phone is directly next to the headphones it doesnt work well.

title: Great sounding buds
content:
I originally posted my review on the best buy site because that's where I purchased my pair. I decided to post the review here for greater visibility so that it can help more people inform their decision on whether to buy these. So there it is:

Excellent Sound:
I've had these for a few weeks now. I've very pleased with their audio quality. Besides the Jabras I mainly use audio technica ATH-M50x. With those headphones being my main point of reference, I can say the Jabras represent highs, lows and mids quite well. What I find most impressive about them, however, is their stereo separation. I don't know if it's specific to the Jabras or inherent in truly wireless earbuds, but the separation between left and right channels is noticeably distinct and has resulted in a fun experience listening to music. I listen to many genres, including but not limited to hip-hop, rock, pop, and electronic.

They provide good isolation. I commute daily by subway and they do a fine job of blocking out external noise. I like that they pause automatically when I remove them from my ears.

I can't speak to the battery life because I've never listened for 5 hours straight. I keep them in the case when not in use and I'd estimate that I use them between 3-4 hours a day. Using them in this manner, I think I've been charging the case maybe every 3 days after I see the light on the case turn red.

My preference would have been to give them 4.5 stars. They do suffer from terrible interference from time to time. I haven't been able to figure out what causes it. At first I thought it was proximity to other bluetooth devices. Then I thought it was putting my hand in my pocket over the phone and somehow blocking the signal. I keep my phone in my left pocket and I thought maybe it was my body blocking the signal to the right earbud. But it happens randomly. The only thing that I can pinpoint for sure that causes interference are the anti-theft gates that some stores have at their entrance. The once that sound an alarm as you pass through them if a security tag hasn't been deactivated. Those gates always cause the earbuds to hiccup. My hope is that a firmware update makes them more stable. But to be clear, this type of interference happens maybe 5% of the time that I'm using them.

Update 1: Regarding interference issues:
After noting the interference issue cropping up from time to time it finally occurred to me that it wasn't an issue with the jabras but perhaps an issue with my iphone 6 or bluetooth itself. I did a little googling and found that sites stating that the water content in our bodies can interfere with the signal. With that being said, I can't rightly fault the jabras. My hope is that when I finally get around to upgrading my phone, it will have a more powerful bluetooth transmitter. Over all 5 stars for the Jabras. I love their sound.

Update 2: Another problem cropping up
Another couple weeks and a new issue has come up. When you put the earbuds in the charging case, they're supposed to automatically turn off. Lately, the right earbud turns off but within a minute turns back on and connects to my phone while it's still in the charging case. Before making this discovery, I thought  the battery on the charging case was draining faster than usual. It wasn't until a few times when I had switched to wireless headphones and the audio dropped out did I finally figure out what was happening. I sent an email to jabra support about this problem. Their recommendation was to unpair, forget the device from my bluetooth settings, and resinstall the firmware. Didn't solve the problem.

If you've gotten this far, I'll leave this final thought. These earbuds are not perfect. I have to remind myself to turn the earbuds off before putting them back in their case. And it's important to remind people that the sound quality for many earbuds will depend greatly on how well they fit and seal in your ear canal.  For me, the price and the flaws have been worth it for how good they sound. Love listening to music with reverb on these. Classic rock sounds fantastic.

title: Very good earbuds with some annoyances
content: These earbuds are pretty good most of the time.  By “pretty good” I mean the sound is good, the microphone works well and I’m generally pleased.  The problems are these: the left bud often gets disconnected from the right and you have to turn them off and sometimes put them in the recharger to get the left one back; the battery drains faster than advertised; they are OK during workouts but not completely secure- mine fall out about every 20 minutes of aerobic workouts.  Keeping track of the recharging box has been an issue of mine; I have already lost one and had to replace it for 80 bucks!  I kind of wish these could be wirelessly charged through other means than the box.  Still, I think these are good ear buds.  I wear them a lot and mostly get along just fine.  The price is good and I trust the Jabra brand when it comes to devices like these.  From what I can tell, most of the wireless buds have the same kinds of problems as I’ve found with these.

title: I wanted to love them
content:
Ugh. These left me so disappointed. I wish they would have worked. In the end, I have decided to return them. They have several pro's but the con's were too much to overlook, especially for the price.

Previously, I owned beats x, which died on me after 1 year and 2 months. In that year and 2 months never once did they drop connection or cause me issues by being connected to multiple devices. The Jabra's cannot handling being connected on multiple devices. They do have the capability of connecting but it distorts functionality. The devices interfere with one another and this causes serious connectivity issues, and frequent dropping. The left ear bud randomly shuts off often...annoying. It has to be returned to the charging case to reconnect. After ensuring they are only connected to one device while in use, I still experienced dropping, not as bad, but far too much for the price point. I also hated the case, they are not magnetic like most true wireless. The earbuds barely sit down in and go flying, when you open the case, which is actually quite hard to open.

***Worst of all, these aren't compatible with computers!!!! WHAT?! Why would I want a pair of ear buds that doesn't work on all of my devices? They do work for audio on my device, but the microphone is not compatible. When investigating this, Jabra states in their FAQ's that they do not guarantee any functionality with devices other than mobile phones...

I loved the app, the ambient noise and different modes. I loved the hear through functionality and I actually thought these did a decent job for noise cancelation. The ear tips, could be better, but comfort-wise these aren't bad overall. The sound quality is decent, and I preferred it over beats x. Sadly, I am returning these and buying a new pair of beats x. I wish the connectivity issues weren't so bad, otherwise I would've loved to keep them.

title: Microphone Performance not as expected
content: The microphone was collecting background noise, doing it very annoying for the other person in the line. I stopped using it after I got a  complain from one colleague in a meeting involving many people. “When you unmute your microphone we hear a very annoying sound” , I was alone at home, so not even in the street where I would understand the challenge for the microphone performance. The design is very nice, though. Sadly, I returned the product.
Por el precio esperaba más…

title: as advertised
content: wonderful product , I had to pass though it was a bit large and didn't fit too well in the ear for me . Will definitely fit others better

title: If AirPods don’t fit, look no further.
content:
Picked these up at B.B. since Amazon is temp. Out of stock.

I use these at the gym and I’m a box jump, cleans, CrossFitty type guy and need something that won’t move.

I have gone through nearly every brand of truly wireless headphones including Bose, AirPods, and the lesser known brands Best Buy carries.  They all fell out of my ears no matter what tips I used.

The Jabra’s stay in my ear.  The sound is as good/maybe a little bit better than Powerbeats3 but I don’t have to deal with the wire.  The Bluetooth5 is *almost* as good as Apple’s W chip.  Setup was very easy on an IPhoneX and the connection was solid.

Battery life is at least 3 hours which is all I need so I’m happy about that.

title: Fall out easily, settle for AirPods instead
content:
Note: bought through bestbuy since I was so excited to get these I didn't want to wait for Amazon.

On the surface there's many things about these airpod competitors that make them better than airpods. They have better sound quality, block out more noise, the built in buttons allow you to fastfoward, rewind, and adjust the volume, they're compatible with android's google assistant, and they have an Android app with many settings. However, the only thing that matters at the end of the day is whether they stay in your ear, and these do not. Despite trying all the different tips, I consistently found these would fall out when I was doing the dishes, when I laughed (because of the jaw motion), or when I played virtual reality games. Despite being a die hard Android user, I bought a pair of Airpods and they do not fall out of your ear.
