title: Good for working out but otherwise weak/bad
content:
These are a solid option for working out but otherwise compared to either B&O PLAY by Bang & Olufsen Beoplay E8 Premium Truly Wireless Bluetooth Earphones or Apple MMEF2AM/A AirPods Wireless Bluetooth Headset for iPhones with iOS 10 or Later White these are weak.  While the sound quality on these is not really bad, if you are paying attention to the music these are not really good.  The midrange on these is mushy/muddy.  The lows and highs are not too dissimilar from Airpods but compared to B&O, which has the best sound on the market for earbuds, the lows on these are just not good.

Even at low volume, the noise canceling is not bad at all.

If you are wearing these while you watch videos you will not be happy.  When tested with an iPhone 7 Plus, there is a small but clearly noticeable lag between the video and audio.  These are flat out bad for watching anything with people talking.

On the plus side these are almost as easy to set-up as Airpods and they are far superior to the initial setup with B&O.

The Jabra app is good. It walks you through the setup and has a useful little manual.  The app makes updating the firmware a breeze.  It does have an equalizer that helps deal with the weakness on the low end but forget hearing the real lows that you get with B&O or good full sized headphones.

The one place where these are superior is comfort/stability for working out.  These have three different sized tips so they are as secure as B&O and far more stable than Airpods.  So, if you want something to use when you jog (and AirPods fall out of your ears) and you don't want to drop $275 for B&O these are the way to go.

title: Great sound and battery life
content: They sound great!  Good bass and clear treble at all volumes.  I have never run out of battery using them for music at the gym (90+ minutes) and on phone calls (60+ minutes).  I have only a couple complaints.  I have tried all the different size ear gels and the medium size fits best.  If you go too big or small the audio quality suffers.  The medium is best but still requires frequent adjustments during gym workouts.  This sounds strange but I find them to be slippery.  I have to be careful as I have dropped them numerous times.  Also the case is slippery and takes finesse to put the buds in and out without dropping buds and/or case.  I have never experienced any of the connection drop outs other describe.  Although they have microphones in them to allow the "HearThrough" feature I still feel like I have to yell to speak.  Overall excellent earbuds.

title: Sound quality is very good but battery life is lacking!
content: I really enjoy using these at work but by lunch time they need to be recharged!  That is disappointing.  The sound quality is great.  The buttons take some getting used to (memorizing which does what).

title: Cheap product that doesn’t last long
content: Initially loved these earbuds, great sound quality and battery. However, I started to notice the static noise in the background which really threw me off when listening at lower volumes. Then I became agitated with the pairing process on both android and iphone, I find myself often having to forget the device and setting up the device like new constantly. Connecting these to a PC is also a pain. Not even 3 months after I bought these they stopped working entirely despite me taking very good care of them. Sent them in, got them replaced after a grueling, long process. Then, another 3 or so months pass and here I am with the same issue. If you’re looking for wireless earbuds please just invest in airpods.

title: Wonderful buy
content: A tad uncomfortable, maybe I’m just overly sensitive....But overall a fantastic set of earphones. Recommend them for anyone. Zero concerns of them falling out for a workout and per a recent trip, they cancel the noise even when flying.

title: bad fix. Totally disappointment
content: Purchased and returned within an hour, weak sound, bad fix. Totally disappointment. If I could give a zero I would. Purchased the Bose sound sport free and very happy. Not looking back!!!

title: useless in noisy environment
content: Bought and returned. If you want to use it on the train or keep other's voices out while walking, these won't work. Battery is pretty good. volume can be too low to use, and basically no bass.

title: really great - wireless phone calls without cord tangle! (and does not hurt my ear)
content: The Jabras work great in general and for my use of them (I mostly use it for phone calls and I only use the right earbud); they hold a charge and the sound quality is great-- both in terms of the audio and the call microphone. Also, they fit in my ear painlessly and snugly even though I have small ears (e.g. I cannot wear apple products because the part that goes into the inside part of the ear is way too big and hurts way too much, and although I love my rowkin wireless earbud its sharp edges kind of hurt my ear too so I can only wear it for about 30ish minutes at a time; in contrast, the Jabras fit comfortably! they are larger - in that they fill the whole 'ear pocket' (to make up a term for the medium indented part of your ear!)- but the part that goes into the inside part of the ear is smaller and comes with a few sizes of rubber tips to fit different sizes).  By removing those dang cords from my phone calls this tiny practical improvement puts a smile on my face! In short: I recommend this highly if you want a quick tiny improvement to the day to day annoyance of the cord-tangle.

title: Best wireless headphones
content: To start I use them in a loud work environment where ear plugs are required. These serve as good as ear plugs are. I have owned my pair for I say 10months and never had problem, I use them at full volume every day and they are still crystal clear. I work 12 hours and a single charge lasts me about 8 to 10 hours with no ear uncomfort. Plus the case charges them pretty fast when they do die I can use them again quickly. I have dropped both headphones and case plenty of times and still have zero issues. The audio on videos is synchronized perfectly unlike other wireless headphones. They are worth every penny.

title: LAUNDRY PROOF AND DRYER PROOF !!
content: I do cycling and I leave it in the jersey by mistake and it went to the laundry : water and then to the dryer. I found it in the dryer the next day almost crying !!!! I turned on and everything is working perfect.. awesome !!!

title: Pretty Comfortable and They Sound Great
content:
I've had these for about a week.  I've used them to listen to music sitting at my desk at work and I've worn them to the gym several times.

What I Like:
1. The buttons - you can control almost everything you need from the buttons on the earbuds.
2. Battery Life - I don't have to recharge them through the day, I just put them in the case when I'm done and the next day they're charged and ready to go.
3. Sound/Fit - 3 different sizes of silicon tips are included and it's important to use the size that fits best.  I suspect that people who complain that these have no bass are using the wrong size.  I tried the smaller set and I had no bass and tinny, the largest ones were uncomfortable for my ears.  I didn't like the feeling at first, they hurt when they were in for any length of time or when I pushed the buttons, but after using them for 2 or 3 days, that is no longer an issue.
4. Auto Stop/Resume - When I take them out, my music stops, when I put them back in, it starts again.  This feature works well.
5. Call Quality - Calls sound great and I can speak in a normal voice and the person I am talking to can hear me.
6. Range - I can get pretty far from my phone (Pixel 3) before there are any connectivity issues.

What I don't like:
1. Hissing Noise - When I'm not playing music, there is an annoying hissing sound.  I've tried various internet fixes, but none of them seem to solve the issue.  For me, it's play music or take them out of my ears.
2. Hear Through - All this seems to do is add a little more noise, I don't actually hear people better with this turned on.
3. The Case - This is a nitpick, but I would rather it use a USB-C cable instead of the old micro USB.  It's my only device that uses the older cable.

Despite a few cons, I really like these earbuds.  I feel like they're the best wireless headphone option for Android at the moment.

title: Love these I just wish you could do one ear ...
content: Love these I just wish you could do one ear in the left vs the right. I wear a headset at work  and it mounts on my right which means I have to take the earbud out to use my headset.

title: Awesome earbuds!!
content: Bought these for my husband and he absolutely loves them!!! Impressed with the sound quality and comfort!

title: Broke after 3 months
content: Stopped working after 3 months. Won’t turn on. Tried everything.

title: Great Quality, But Earbuds Don't Fit for Me
content: I was really looking forward to getting these wireless earbuds, especially since they're actually 100% wireless. I think they're excellent in regards to the features that they offer and their sound quality is really good. My main issues have been more with the physical design and how they fit my ears. The battery life seems to run a little under the five hours, which is pretty good considering their small size. Then you get an additional 10 hours with the charging case. The app that's available allows you to keep track of their charge, as well as customize a bunch of listening options. When making calls with these earbuds, the sound quality is very clear and there's not a lot of background noise that the caller hears on the other end. Again, my biggest issue is with how these earbuds fit my ears. I tried all of the different tips and can't seem to get a comfortable fit that will stay in my ears. I don't know if I just have oddly shaped ear holes that don't hold them very well, but it has been an ongoing issue for me with many earbuds. So if you're a person that typically has trouble with earbuds fitting and staying in your ears, then you might want to test these before you buy or even skip these altogether. So overall I really enjoyed the features and quality of sounds, but just can't fully embrace these with the constant ear issues that I continue to have.

title: Spectacular
content: Spectacular auricular for day use

title: Left easrbuds doesn't work most of the time.
content: the sound quality and functionality of these earbuds is great when they work UNFORTUNATELY the left ear bud does not work most of the time. I have tried reinstalling the Jabra software on my iPhone, turning the Bluetooth function on and off on my phone, and reinserting both earbuds back in their case to start over. it is very frustrating because I really like them when both earbuds work but that doesn't happen very often.

title: Absolutely the worst product experience I’ve ever had
content:
About two months after receiving the product the left earbud started to cut in and out and when it did work it emitted a static so loud that no music behind it could be heard. Dealing with Jabra product support is a special kind of nightmare. After being on hold for one hour I was run through the standard uninstall your app a check this or that routine.  I have been turned over to some kind of special escalation person who will call me back in 1 to 2 days, which is unacceptable because at this point I have a very expensive pair of headphones that simply don’t work. It's clear the issue is with the hardware, not software but Jabra seems dedicated to making it look like I'm the problem.

The right thing to do would be to offer to ship me a replacement or some other more effective relief. Instead the company is going to make me, the paying customer, jump through hoops that our absurd.

I should have learned my lesson from my previous pair of a Jabra earbuds which also didn’t work very well after about two months. The product quality plus the customer experience have convinced me to never, ever, do business with this company again.

My advice to anybody considering this company or these headphones is to run as fast as possible in the other direction

title: I PURCHASED THESE A MONTH AGO AND AFTER A WEEK THEY DON'T POWER ON
content: I PURCHASED THESE A MONTH AGO AND AFTER A WEEK THEY DON'T POWER ON I RETURNED THEM TO JABRA AND WAS TOLD I GOT TO WAIT UNTILL THEY MAKE ANOTHER ONE BEFORE THE WARRANTY EXCHANGE TAKE PLACE HERE I AM ONE MONTH AND COUNTING.I WOULD NEVER BUY ANOTHER JABRA PRODUCT.

title: Stopped Working After 4 Days!
content:
To me, the thought of spending $200 on earbuds was not only ludicrous, it was also unimaginable. I've had the same pair of $20 SoundPEATS heapdhones for three years, but they finally stopped working, so even though I knew it meant I'd be broke for some time, I decided to splurge on these.
I was not only in heaven the first couple days I got them, but I also showed them off to everyone I knew. So freaking cool! Alas, this fairy tale came to an abrupt end just four days after I purchased them.
On the fourth night of ownership, I put the 100% charged earphones in and the left ear didn't come on. I turned them off. Turned them back on. Still, it didn't work. I disconnected Bluretooth and reconnected. Still, nothing. I put them back in their case and took them out again. Nothing.
I'm sure I could call Jabra and maybe even get some technical support. Maybe they'll tell me I have a defective pair and send me a replacement. Maybe, they'll tell me to return them to Best Buy and get another pair. None of this matters. Because when you drop $200 on a pair of earphones, they should NEVER stop working. No glitches for $200 earphones. No excuses. Also, how can I possibly trust another pair wouldn't do the same thing? Would you give away $200 of your hard-earned money in hopes your earphones never stop working? I wouldn't.
There is no way Jabra can regain my trust again, and a new pair would only leave me worried they'd stop working after some time.
Also, can we get back to the fact that these only worked for four days? I spent $50/day on earphones. As my three-year-old would say, "Not nice, Jabra. Not nice!"

title: Software issue makes right headphone weak. RMA process is terrible
content:
I purchased these back in May of 2018. They worked until around July when a software update made the right earbud almost silent compared to the left earbud. It's still needs to be in your ear to use, but isn't audible at all.
Some had said this could be fixed by downloading a language pack or doing hardware resets. Unfortunately, mine wasn't fixed by there steps.  I started an RMA process in November of 2018 and it was completed in 2 weeks after having to remind the tech about my problem, take multiple screenshots of the issue. Once the RMA was completed I would then be sent a new Right Earbud. Then I find out that they are on back-order. It's need 4 months and I still haven't received a working Right Earbud!

Overall, the quality and battery life of this set was great. It stays in my ears while working out and the sound quality is pretty good. It's the best wireless earbud set I've purchased, and I still wear them even though I only get sound from the left ear. Overall though I wouldn't recommend using these though because of the wait if anything goes wrong.

title: Not exactly comfortable
content: It took some time for my ears to callous over, but they bother me less than they used to. I've read some other reviews that say changing the tips help with comfort, but I haven't tried that. It seems more like it's the actual shape that doesn't exactly meld with my average size ears. Anyways, like I said, I'm used to them now, they don't bother me as much -- but I'm not sure if I'd buy them again given the chance, might try something different.

title: Too many problems.
content:
I encounter several problems with this product and the customer support is bad.
The left earpiece's volume becomes significantly lower than the right earpiece a while after power on.
After connected to the phone, the headset sometimes goes into phone call mode (even if not making phone calls), so the music volume becomes very low.
Sometimes the headset just won't play the music even if it's connected.
At the beginning, I was happy with this product as it fits my ear very well and it looks very stylish. However, I am very disappointed now as many problems surfaced.
The customer support is not responsive at all. I got reply in 3-4 days after inquiry. And that was just a automated reply (it stated so in the email signature).

title: Unreliable hardware
content: Do not buy these headphones. On my second replacement pair now. First ones the right ear bud sound faded out overtime. With the replacements the right earbud stopped working entirely. Customer service is not good enough to put up with these breaking all the time especially given their high price point.

title: Best I've tried yet
content: Loving these earbuds. I had spend a small forture on Nuheara ear buds and they have been complete crap, disconnecting from phone nonstop and wouldn't stay in my ears.  These ears buds simply work, no connectivity issues and they fit in my ears.

title: Works great - worth the money
content: Works perfect. Simple to use and charge. Lasts a while on a charge and sounds great.

title: Had to return
content: When I turn my head one would stop working. It was very aggravating

title: A Leader In Headphones Meets Sport and Voice Command
content:
I've loved every Jabra product I've ever owned, and these are no exception: easy to pair, stays in pretty well (unless you totally sweat like a pig like I do), and the ability to use Alexa voice commands wherever you are in (or out) of the house is welcome, especially to use the announcements feature or control lighting when working on a sketch at the table.

Great product!

title: I want my item
content: opened the box and found only one earphone for another company and did not have the same request. I think it's a scam

title: Used to love. Not anymore
content: Even after being put away in their charging case, they will still automatically connect to your phone’s Bluetooth. Incredibly annoying.

title: Works as expected
content: Works as expected. Wish there was a little bit more bass I would have given a five

title: Great product
content: I bought my boyfriend these for Christmas and he is so happy with them. The ratings are based on his opinions since he uses them every day at work.

title: 5 month of use
content:
Great Pair earbuds-
-Music good, not great
-Controls are great
-Google's assistant works great!
-Volume up and down works well
- Battery is good enough but can be better
Talking to my wife in O'Hara airport well that is priceless-- Lisa could hear me so clear

Buy Jabra if-You are always on the go and take a lot of phone calls ( Ths is the major benefit of getting Jabra)
DO Not buy if you only listen to Music- ( sound is ok)

title: Perfect
content: I have small ear canals so most earbuds are painful to wear for long periods of time.  These fit great, feel great and in my opinion they look great.  I use for conference calls, working out and shooting hoops.  They feel secure and never feel like they will fall out.  I found my perfect earbuds.

title: Size of earbuds.
content: I actually liked everything about the product except that they are too big I have very small ears and small ear canals, Maybe if they just a little bit smaller that be perfect.

title: Great App features, easy to use and a beautiful fit.
content:
These are solid performing ear buds that come in a brilliantly designed case with high quality sound.  The controls are easy to use and you can achieve an excellent fit using the ear gels that are included.  In fact, they fit better in both our ears than the Bose set we own.  Aesthetically, they are very cool looking.  They have a built in microphone and it’s easy to take calls.  Other thoughts are:

• Easy to pair via Bluetooth with our Samsung phones.
• Requires that you download Jabra’s free App, which has many nice features.
• We love the customizable equalizer in the App.
• They are small and fit comfortably and securely in your ear.
• The fit is ideal for physical activity such as running and walking.
• There are lots of attachments for fine tuning fit on an individual basis.
• Compare to the general field, sound quality is very good.
• By fiddling with the App, you can customize the sound the way you want it.
• You can store several equalizer configurations for different types of music or effects.
• They come in a secure little case that is easy to stash in your pocket.
• The case recharges the buds when they are stored.
• The ear buds will remain fully charged for an extended period of time in the case.

title: Spend less money for a better battery life, and pairing.
content:
I did a great deal of research both here on Amazon and on Youtube. With the research it seemed like a safe bet to go with the Jabra Elite Active 65t. Not so.
At the same time I purchased a set of true wireless ear buds here for less than $40.00. I have had MUCH better results from the lesser cost ear buds.
1) Jabra claims to last for 5 hours. Not so. Battery goes weak after less than 5 hours, even when ear buds are not in use. The lesser cost units stay charged all day long, some times as much as 10 hours on a long work day. I have used the lesser cost units many days with frequent calls and have not had problems.
2) Jabra claims to have a very good pairing system that stays connected.  Not true. I frequently needed to take them out of my ears, place them in their charger pod, then replace them in my ears.  With the lesser cost units I have only had to do this once or twice in the history of using them. One of the times was after an extremely long day, with extreme heat. Acceptable.
3) Size. Jabra Elite has a larger body. They seem to fit well.  I found it surprising that with a larger body they couldn’t provide longer battery duration.  Frustrating.

End result?  I will likely be sending these back for a refund because they just don’t live up to the expense of nearly $200.00. I can buy 5 sets of the lesser expensive units and still have money left over.

title: More durable than advertised
content:
These are the best earbuds I've ever used.  I agree with the positive comments in other people's reviews, so I won't be redundant.

A unique comment I have is that my pair seems to be a lot more durable that the IP55 rating that Jabra has given itself.  In the year since I purchased them, I have accidentally put my earbuds through the laundry three times, and they are no more worse for the wear.

title: Use the app to set Hear-through mode for music.  Otherwise, double-tap R earpiece to toggle.
content: Music audio quality is excellent as is phone conversation.  Try different sized ear pieces; it’s tough to keep these inserted without a snug fit.

title: Great sound, best for I've found, and NO CORDS!
content: Had the Bragi Earphones, these are exponentially better. Fit has always been an issue with me with any earphones, and these are the best I have tried. Soung is fantastic, battery is great, I really have no complaints. Worth every penny. Once you cut the cord you'll never go back.

title: Ok sounds quality, poor microphone performance
content:
This is a good product for listening music while working out. The sounds quality is good, and the earbuds never fall while running for 30 minutes.

But this is not feasible product for the calls. Microphone picks up every noise out there, so you cannot expect to have calls on the streets. Bluetooth is also shaky performance. You have to literally hold the phone, otherwise it keeps skipping the noise. People said that it is unbearable to have conversation through this earbuds and asked to switch to iPhone.

It was a huge disappointment as I loved the Jabra headphone which is both great for listening music and for calls.

title: Broke after accidentally dropping on CARPET
content: This product was good for the first 2 weeks but after someone asked me a question, I missed catching the earbud as I was taking out of my ear. It fell 2 feet onto the carpet floor. I put both of the earbuds into the charging case for later use. the next time I took them out of the case, the one that landed on the floor cut in and out repeatedly with any shift of my head. THIS PRODUCT WILL BE THE REASON I NEVER GO BACK TO TRUE WIRELESS EARBUDS!

title: Best true wireless earbuds out there.
content:
After 3 months of use I can safely say that this was a very good purchase. I was looking for true wireless earbuds which will provide good charging time and decent audio quality. After doing a *lot* of research I ended up buying the Jabra 65t active.

I was not disappointed!  Though the price tag is a bit steep, these are diffidently worth it - the long battery life, and the ability to charge them while they rest in their case means almost never worrying about npt having enough juice for the gym.

They endure hard lifts and sweat and usually stay snug enough in the ears.  I took one star off because initially I had experienced some white noise in the left bud. I've grown accustomed to it by now, but it was very annoying at first.

title: Great Wireless Earbud
content: You don't expect booming base from a wireless earbud, and these earbuds are no exception.  What you want is the convenience of no entangling wires, operational controls at the earbud itself, comfortable fit, consistent BlueTooth connection, and clarity of sound.  You get all of that with these Jabra Elite Active 65t's, but you also get the protection of water/sweat resistance.  With telephone calls and with music, the clarity of the sound is truly remarkable.  Not much bass, even with the equalizer on the app set to "bass boost," but if I want more bass, I'll wear my more cumbersome Bose headphones -- excellent sound with those -- but also irritation and ear sweat if worn for much time at all.

title: Great Product!
content:
Excellent sound and near instantaneous pairing.
Never fall out

title: 2 weeks in...not impressed
content:
Summary: bad sound quality and “rustling” noises / underwater feeling. Leaning toward returning.

Pros:
- Super easy set up and quick connectivity once paired.
- Good mic quality for calls.
- Fit is pretty good - I like how they sit in the ear. Comfy and secure.
- The case is nice and small and easily fits in a pocket.

Cons
- Sound quality is quite bad, even for buds. just hollow and really no bass - practically un-listenable for music. This is after maxing the base in the app. The bass just isn’t there at all, even for buds. Talk/podcasts is fine, but that’s not saying much for $200 headphones.
- Inside my head "underwater" sound and feeling. This is probably a relic of any sealed earbuds, but my own voice, breathing, or any movement of the buds in my ears creates low-level rumbling noises (microphonics?) that are incredibly irritating and really a deal breaker. Quite irritating for a headset that's intended to be used while working out / breathing hard. Similar to the cord-drag rustling noise some headphones have.

title: An unexpectedly great fit for me
content: I bought these admittedly on a whim after reading all the positive reviews. I usually expect that actual experience will never be as great as many reviewers claim. I have ears that typically have a hard time getting most earbuds to fit in my ears securely and not hurt my ears after >5min of wear. I also struggle typically with most wireless earbuds to quickly stow them away quickly. These were surprisingly comfortable in my ears for 30+ minutes. They did start to get sore after an hour or more but by rotating their orientation in my ear slightly it usually fixed the problem (my problem spot is the back lower rim of my ear where the outer portion of most ear buds rest). I was pleasantly surprised at how well the gel tips block out noise even passively. I was used to the silicon tips that never did anything and was convinced that only the comply foam tips would work for that. I was pleasantly mistaken. They work well and provide a great seal. It was between these and the AirPods by Apple. My ears could never tolerate Apple’s style of ear buds (the Air pods use the same shape) due to soreness caused after less than 5min of wear. The sound is great. My iPhone 6s has issues with sharing these wireless earbuds with other devices (according to the threads, all iOS devices do this) so it detracts from the benefit of these being able to pair with up to 8 devices at a time. I love the ‘hear-through’ setting so I don’t have to completely tune out my work surroundings, I can just turn down the noise somewhat. They automatically turn on when pulled from the case, and turn off when returned to the case. They automatically connect to my phone effortlessly whether I’m using just the right earbud or both. Switching between using one or both ear buds has been extremely seamless as well without any bothersome connection issues. I highly recommend this product.

title: Great Set of True Wireless.
content:
These headphones are great. Use them all the time at work, around the house, and working in the yard. I haven’t used them for running yet, but I will.

I was worried that they would fall out but, after having them for over a month a using them almost daily, they have never fallen out once.

They sound great, there is no static, no delay between the two headsets.

If you want to only wear one you have to wear the right one.

The app is a good addition, lets you customize the sound you hear, either to preset sounds or customize.

The hear through function so it pulls in ambient sounds, or turn off hear through so it’s noise canceling.

So far, there are no negatives to these headphones.

Great buy.

title: No regrets!
content: Sounds better than I thought they would, and also amazing clarity while talking on the phone.

title: Love these but they aren't perfect
content:
I haven't done many of these reviews, however I want to share my experience with the Jabra Elite 65T truly wireless headphones.
First off some context, I work in both an office and outdoor setting and I wanted these to help me detangle from my old headphones.
I never want s these for working out or the gym, but I gather I'd hate them if I did.
First let's look at build quality.
I'd give the quality a 4/5 ... The headphones for me are comfy out of the box. They fit well and feel comfy. The charging block itself is strong and has fallen few times from me just not remembering where I had them and they still work and hold great charge. My only problem here is the opening of the case itself. At first I would pry it open, not know there's a push down then pull open type of setting 😂. My bad Jabra.
Sound quality 3/5
For me the sound quality on these are awesome, with great features built in to the eq to change it to your liking. My score is however is low because of my experience with them chipping out ever so often as if they're too far from the paired device. I'd literally be jamming to some tunes with it in my hands, then I put it in my pocket and it's chipping in and out. Sometimes chipping in and out while it's in my hand, guess it hates the way I dance to Migos lol. Truth is the sound quality doesn't matter if it's a hassle to enjoy it. These require very close proximity to the paired device, you wouldn't be able to stay connected if you're not in direct line of sight I've found and that's no bueno.
Noise cancellation 4/5
Noise cancellation works pretty well here, no complaint on that part. I even love the hearr through function of the headphones that amplify your surroundings sounds for better hearing. It doesn't always do well with voice amplification however and sometimes goes into and idle mode where there's no hear through at all, just dead muffles from a plugged ear until the phone rings or you get a message, etc.

Overall 3.5/5
Sadly I'd overall give these headphones a 3.5. I found them affordable enough for what I wanted them for. However they haven't delivered fully on that dream of being truly wireless. Given the poor performance of the connection even in pocket, muchless when I'm in separate rooms and some other things.
I look forward to the next iteration of these headphones as I'd love to try one with a few updates that address the issues I have. Great sets but they just aren't as perfect as they could have been.
Cheers everyone.

title: Left earbud stopped working after 3 months of use.
content: I was excited to find a wireless earbud set that didn't have any wires connecting the 2. Sound quality was pretty good, and the battery life was great. The left earbud just stopped working after 2 months of use. At first, it would crackle as if it was trying to connect to the right earbud. After a week of that, it just stopped working completely. I am back to using my old Epic 2 earbuds. I realized the sound quality is better than the Elite 65t. I would not recommend purchasing these earbuds, especially at the high price tag.......

title: Met my expectations
content: I use this for my work calls and loved that I can move around without worrying about a cord.  I can walk from my loft office to my kitchen without lossing connection to my phone.

title: Not bad..great quality
content:

title: Jabras vs Apple AirPods
content:
My AirPods we’re getting pretty busted after a year and a half so I decided to give these a try when they went on sale for Black Friday at a much better price and I figured for the money, they’d tide me over until Apple releases a next-gen AirPod. However, the more time I spend with them, I’m actually finding them preferable in a number of ways with a few caveats.

They connect just as well as the AirPods did with my iPhone XS Max. Sound quality is noticeably better and richer. Noise isolation is much improved.

At first, these were a little painful to wear for more than 15 minutes but comply tips helped some, and now I’ve gotten used to them and they don’t bother me as much if any.

I especially like the mode that can enhance background sounds to allow for listening to surroundings while listening to music and it can be turned on and off in app for more isolation.

I regularly do 10K runs and haven’t had any issues with sweat. Only other complaint is that because of their tighter sealed off fit, I tend to hear every foot strike through my skull while wearing them. At first, it was pretty annoying but I have gotten used to it. As my cadence is around 165 spm, that would be 165 thuds I would hear every minute, so the first few times I kinda had a headache but now it doesn’t bother me as much. AirPods never had this issue, but probably because the fit in my ears wasn’t as sealed off.

Case is a little larger than AirPods, but not much. I honestly like it better. The reason my AirPods crapped out is because the way the charging slots are down in little tubes in the case which would get kinda nasty and was difficult to keep debris free and clean, leading to inconsistent charging. About a year in with those, I’d often find myself getting to the trail only to find one bud was dead while the other was fully charged so it was anyone’s guess whether they would work or not, even after running a delicate pipe cleaner in to swap the contacts the night before. The Jabras have a much better charging setup, imho. The contacts are easy to wipe clean as needed. The buds themselves also seem easier to keep clean and tips can be replaced if they get kinda crushed up, which let’s be honest–if you’re working out in them (which is 90% my use-case for wireless ear buds), it’s gonna happen. Only plus to the AirPods case design was the slightly smaller size and the magnetic lock-in of the buds inside the case when open.

Battery life isn’t as great as the AirPods, but still more than adequate for my use. I just charge the case once or twice a week.

Audio stays connected pretty well. I have noticed on rare occasion brief audio cutout, but it’s so rare that it doesn’t bug me.

Jabras work well for calls. However, only the right bud supports single-bud use. Remove it and the left bud doesn’t work. Not a deal breaker for me.

I don’t know if I had paid full price at $170 for them, but on sale these are a great buy and the 2 year warranty is a plus. Compared to the AirPods, they are less conspicuous (which I like) with better sound. They connect well to newer devices as they incorporate newer Bluetooth tech. There are a few caveats, but most of them I have now gotten used to while others are not significant enough to warrant returning.

title: Tough to be in terms of cost and sound quality for a truly BT experience
content: Originally tried the Sony and Optoma NuForce BT in-ear phones, got too many dropouts on city streets. Both sounded very good, but could not abide the cutting in and out. Bought some Nuheara IGBuds and liked them fine, a bit expensive but I did manage a 30% discount. Only problem is they have to be on the left side for consistent connectivity. Just for kicks, I tried the Jabra Elite 65t from Amazon Warehouse and wow, these phones are especially impressive at $118 (plus tax). I know they are $149 new, but decided to save a bit. So glad I tried them. SQ is a bit better than the IQBuds, which have more functionality from a tricked out perspective. But for the price difference, no contest. The Jabras are keepers while the IQBuds are going to spend more time in a drawer. I do use the IQBuds now and then too, but Jabra is just an overall better sound to my aging ears. They also are a bit smaller, though both have excellent comfort.

First off it's not super easy to open, you have to press in and bend the lid a little to unlatch it (I still can't get it the first try every time after a month of using them) and the lid is a little flimsy. I'm afraid if anything breaks it will be the lid to the case, and the headphones won't change probably unless the case is latched keeping them pressed on the pogo pins. All said and done great headphones but poor case design, especially for what they cost.

title: Sounds great when they work.
content:
These are almost as expensive as airpods. I read the reviews, did my research and was excited to try these.

I'm not a audiophile, but they do sound fantastic. The Sound+ app allows a lot of extra configuration and allows for software updates.

The standard ear pieces fit snug and does a pretty good job with sound isolation. The battery life runs for a solid 5 hours which is more than enough in my case.

However, the biggest issue I am having is audio balance. The left bud is waaay louder than the right bud, and adjusting the balance on the phone settings decreases overall volume to almost nothing. When using a single bud, like I do at work, it takes a good 20 minutes of quiet audio and then the balance fixes itself until the next time you connect them.

I am not sure if it's a hardware or software issue, but it's a huge downfall for such a great pair of true wireless buds.

title: Magic
content:
I just love these. I bought the gold (more like khaki) to be less obvious, but they're still pretty obvious. I don't even care. It's wonderful to just touch a button on my ear and answer calls hands-free. The sound is fantastic, and no one yet has complained about not hearing me well. Thanks to these babies, I despise holding a handset to my ear nowadays.

In the car, at work, and at home, I talk on my Jabra ear buds always. If the phone isn't ringing much and I'm not listening to music much, the battery holds all day long. With constant audio use, I get the full five hours before putting them back in the case to charge for a little while. Bass could be a bit stronger, but overall they are wonderful.

My workplace no longer has cubicles, so these earbuds are lifesavers when coworkers get loud. I turn on calming music and tune them out. I love how seemlessly the audio on my cell phone switches to these when I put them on. Most of the time I have them on anyway though. I love to cook, and it's great to have these as opposed to trying to hold a phone between ear and shoulder. Also, I don't always want to talk on the phone, but sometimes feel obligated, depending on who's calling or why. With these in my ears, I have much more patience than when I have to hold a phone against my head.

The Jabra app is great. I enjoy the "cave" ambient sound, the quick visibility of battery status, and easy access to instructions for use. These have great audio, they're super easy to use, and no one on the other end of a call seems to notice that I'm not holding a phone against my head.

title: Good Quality, Great for Calls, Not Great for Music and Podcasts
content:
Background:
My phone is a Google Pixel 2XL and have been using Pixel Buds wireless headset for the past 18 months. The sound quality of the Pixel Buds was great for me, but people always had trouble hearing me and I would unintentionally, regularly drop calls due to the Buds terrible controls. I chose the Jabra Elite 65t for the great reviews and reasonable price. I have been using Jabra for the past 3 weeks and my impressions so far are:

Pros:
- Call quality - great. My call partners don't complain about sound quality or wind noise and I can hear them clearly.
- Charging Case - small and sleek.
- Comfort and Fit - excellent. The Jabra fit very well in my ears and I never have to worry about them falling out. A massive improvement over my Pixel Buds.
- Assistant Support - excellent support for Google Assistant. The Jabra also support Siri and Alexa, but I did not try those, as my primary assistant is Google.
- Controls - the Jabra are easy to pair and react quickly. Volume is simple to adjust using the left ear piece, however, I find that I have to really push on the piece to activate the function, which pushes the ear bud uncomfortably into my ear.

Cons:
- Music / Podcast quality - very mediocre. Music and podcasts sound puny. Bass is weak. I tried adjusting using the Jabra equilizer app, but the change was not noticeable. The Jabra are not even in the same league in this category as the Pixel Buds I was using previously

Bottom line - I like the Jabra a lot for their phone call function, ease of use and excellent comfort and fit; however, they are poor for music and podcasts.

title: Best of the Bunch for In-flight Use
content:
I bought these specifically to use on shorter flights, as I've gotten tired of lugging my headphones around, along with my HD player and headphone amp.  I was looking for a solution that would work well with my Samsung Galaxy Note 8 phone, which supports 400 gig micro sd cards.

Though I've given the 65t 5-stars across the board, that is compared to other wireless earbuds.  I'm very pleased with the sound quality though, again, that is compared to other earbuds.  They don't equal a good pair of over-the-ear headphones.  However, sound quality is surprisingly good, and certainly good enough for what I want them for.  The sound field is relatively wide and, with a little EQ applied, I can hit my sweet spot for bass and treble response.  Mid-range is clean and bass isn't too muddy.

They're reasonably comfortable -- at least as far as earbuds go.  For longer flights (more than 2 hours), though, I'll probably rely on my Bose QC-25s.  The 65ts are not active noise-cancelling, but the fit is comfortable and secure and should block most exterior noise.  The "hear through" feature is welcome because it means not having to take them out of my ears when the FA comes around for drink orders. :)

Jabra has a nice app for Android and iPhone -- I use the Android version.  The control it provides is pretty basic but it does include 5-band EQ and lets you control "hear through" and other features.  It also handles firmware updates to the 65t.  I've tried pairing it with my non-Bluetooth Fiio X5ii HD player through a Taotronics 8A08 Bluetooth transmitter and it works very, very well.  The Taotronics is about the size of a matchbook, so if I don't feel like using my phone (which has decent, but not audiophile quality, audio) I can use my Fiio.  Both the 65t and the Taotronics support AAC, which means better quality audio and lower latency -- the latter is important if you want to watch videos.

I'm pleased with the 65t and recommend it if you're looking for good-quality wireless earbuds.

title: Sound quality is very good...as long as you aren't running or jumping

When sitting and not moving around, the sound quality is great and the connection so far is reliable and speedy.  And they are pretty comfortable to wear even on a long call.  But honestly not sure if I will be able to use these for a lot of my workouts which is disappointing because that was the main reason I bought them!

title: They could be great, but something is wrong...
content:
I was really excited to receive these as a replacement for my Jaybird X2s. I was looking forward to the true wireless on my runs and minimizing my accessories. Out of the box, I was impressed with the look and feel in the ear with a snug fit and good sound. While I think a magnetic close on the case is preferable, the case was compact and feels nice to the touch.

The initial connection seemed like more of a struggle than it should have been but once connected to my Pixel phone, the music came to life and I was pleased. Next, I connected to my Garmin watch (with music / worn on left wrist). Again, the initial connection was tedious, but again, once connected, the sound was really nice. Then the problems developed...

Go on my first run, connect to my watch, music playing.... then I leave the house in a very typical residential neighborhood. I get about 10 - 20 feet from my house and the music starts to persistently drop out. I never lose connection, but during the entire 4 mile run, persistent drop out - both ears. I go for a second run and wait to connect until I get to the street, but that did not help. On the third run, I use my phone (back zipper pocket), but again that did not help with the dropout; it was unchanged.

I call Jabra; they think it might be the master earbud (since it is in both ears) and send a replacement. That was no help. I switch back to my JBX2s and still have no issue with either my watch or cell. I call Jabra back. At this point, the CSR says well, it is obviously environmental. Environmental? She held the position that during an entire 4 mile run (out and back) and an entire 5 mile run (loop), that this environmental interference was so pervasive that it continuously caused dropout. Not even 5 seconds of continuous, uninterrupted, music. She maintained this position despite my JBs, in the same environment, performing flawlessly.

I take the Jabra to another location, about 5 miles from my home, and encounter the exact same issue. But in trying to diagnose this issue, (I wear my watch on my left wrist and the master earbud is in my right ear), I noticed that if I held my hand near my heart that the drop out would stop. So, on my next run, I wear my watch on the right and the problem is resolved. But that means that the music device must be within a meter (and no interference) to work. Unacceptable.

I am not sure why it works better inside (maybe the Bluetooth signal is stronger bouncing off walls). But these are advertised as "Active" and for them to suffer the dropout that they do, when it is represented up to 10 meters, is simply unacceptable. At a minimum, they should sell a left that is a as master. I mean, I might be dense, but the music should play consistently without dropout rather than dropout consistently.

When all this was presented to Jabra, the response was flippant, along the lines of, "Oh well, it must be environmental...not our problem, good luck," without regard for the same environment not causing in issue in other earbuds. This is clearly a problem with the Bluetooth range of these ear pods. I hope there is a software fix for this. If not, the device is defectively designed. That would be a shame because these have real potential.

Product returned. Hopefully Jabra will correct this deficiency. Until then, buyer beware.

title: High Quality and Easy to Use
content:
Likes:
Simplicity: They are very intuitive and simple to use once you get the hang of it. Take the left one out and they stop, put it back in and they start playing. Tap right side once to stop or play. Tap right side twice to allow outside noise in or out.
Battery: Have not had any battery issues while using for several hours. If you're always putting them back in the case they'll always stay charged.
Comfort: They're going to feel a little bit different compared to other earbuds your used to. With that being said, after using a couple weeks they start to feel more normal. These also don't irritate my ears and are much more comfortable than even less invasive headphones that simply sit in the ear.
Quality: The sound quality is great! I notice instruments that i normally dont get to hear when listening to speakers. The bass isn't crazy or anything. But I'd say for a small pair of bluetooth headphones, the quality is as good as you're going to get for the size. As technology continues to develop I'm sure you'll be able to get higher quality drivers in a small shell but for now I think they sound great. If your going purely for sound, I wouldnt do earbuds or wireless, I'd go over-ear.
Dislikes:
My only dislike is that sometimes the left ear can sound a bit staticy. The only reason why I didn't take a star off is because I've figured out how to resolve the isssue. I simply pause the music for two seconds and try it again. Usually the reconnection fixes the problem instantly. All it takes is hitting the pause button and then resuming. It doesn't happen all the time only every once in a while and I've heard of this happening with just about every brand of wireless bluetooth earbuds.

Overall, I love these earbuds. They look good, feel good, sound good and perform good. They're also not too bulky they don't come out further than the silhouette of your ear, meaning you wouldn't be able to see them coming out wider than your ear.

title: Great so far, but needs improvement
content:
Pros:
- They look good and don't stick out of your ear really far like the Bose ones. I tried on the Bose ones and they looked
  ridiculous because they stick out so far.
- Truly wireless
- Good sound. The "hear-through" seems to work well.
- Google assistant seems to work pretty well with them

Cons
- Physical buttons - In order to change the volume/skip song, you have to push physical buttons on the earpiece, which
  means it gets pushed into your ear canal and is really uncomfortable. I think it would be way better if the buttons
  were not physical but just a touch or tap to change it.
- Speaking of buttons, I HATE when headphones or speakers make you hold down the + or - buttons to go to next
  song or previous song. It needs to be the double tap or triple tap on the main play/pause button. Thats how my old
  Beats were and it was nice.
- Can fall out of your ear fairly easily. I changed to the smallest rubber insert which helped a little bit but they still fall
  out sometimes if i am moving around a lot (jump rope, burpies, etc.). Maybe its just the shape of my ear.

title: Great Headphones HORRIBLE Customer service!
content:
When I purchased these, I really liked them! The sound quality is great and the battery life is excellent.
Where this goes wrong is after 6 moths of light use, I started having issues with the right earpiece. The audio level would drop and get distorted. I called Jabra Support and was on hold for over 45 min until I got dropped. I called back and finally another 52 min later I  spoke to a CSR. I was told I would receive an email with a link to fill out the request for a replacement and to submit my proof of purchase. I filled out the form and uploaded the receipt. When you click on the submit button nothing happens, No confirmation etc. I tried this with two different browsers to make sure this wasn't the issue and I had he same results. Two weeks later, I get an email stating that my info has been received and I would get another email when the replacement part ships. Fast forward 5 weeks I receive an email with a totally different name in the heading than mine and stating that they haven't shipped the item and it is estimated to be another month till it ships. WOW! I'm looking for another brand cause I'm tired of the wait! See screen shot of the email from Jabra.

title: all good

title: as they are quite small and easily lost if I kept handling them
content:
I ordered these, as I drive and get in / out of a vehicle all day for work and it is much easier to use a device such as these vs. a headset or corded earbuds.  I wanted to be able to wear them for up to 8 hours at a time, as they are quite small and easily lost if I kept handling them, even if used in their charging / carrying case.

When I first started to use them, I found them to be very easy to connect to my phone's bluetooth and even fit into my ear.  The dual use (Main earbud and secondary earbud) really improved the sound quality and exterior noise blocking, but there are a few times that there is a static or brief interruption of the connection.  I really only use the main earbud, again for driving purposes, so that issue isn't a big one for me.

What I did find to be annoying, which led to the reduction of stars to "It's ok", is that everyone's ear canals are different, so what works well for one person won't work well for another.  That's the case with me...  These are quite comfortable for an hour or so at a time, but if you are looking to use them in a manner such as I am, then the ear really stars to get sore after that amount of time.  Unlike corded earbuds, these aren't just small circles placed into the ear, these are the entire ear piece with all the electronics placed within the ear.  Any kind of sweat and activity will eventually loosen the original tight fit and require a readjustment.  I did use two of the three size adjustment pieces (small / medium) to see if that helped and it did, but not enough to change my overall rating of this product.

If you are ok with the above information and you have an ear canal that works well with these, then I would rate them a 4+ star, but as it depends on the person, I couldn't really go below a 3 star rating.

title: So worth it!
content: Like everything about these earphones. I wish it could be a bit louder but I do understand they are earphones, but great battery life and all other features are super convenient.

title: Great set of earbuds. Wish the tips were better.
content:
After reading a few negative reviews, I was most concerned about (1) Bluetooth connection reliability, and (2) audio lag when watching videos. Personally, I haven't experienced either of those issues when using either my Android phone or my MacBook.

The biggest issue I've had is an annoying amount of static coming from the left earbud. It seems to start up when I turn the volume up past about 75%, either from the button on the left earbud, or from my laptop/phone. It seems to be interference related, because the static is worse at my office and in some parts of my house. I did some googling and found a few other people complaining about the same problem. None of the fixes I found online worked for me.

The second biggest issue I've had is that the stock earbud tips are really uncomfortable and don't seal well (I have narrow ear canals). The stock tips also don't have a wax guard over the sound hole, which seems like an oversight.

In the end, I bought the Comply tips designed for these earbuds. They're great and it turns out that they help immensely with the static issue because the better seal lets me use the earbuds at a lower volume where the static isn't a problem.

Overall these earbuds are great. Sound quality is awesome, the form factor is fantastic, and I haven't run the batteries down all the way yet in a few months of daily use recharging at night. I would have given them five stars if only they came with some better tips.

title: Best wireless earbuds out there now
content:
Clear well balanced sound.  Good bluetooth connection to my iPhone.  Have not had drops.  I like that they automatically turn on when I take them out of the charging case and turn off when they are put back.

Best fit for me was with the medium size tip.  However, it does not feel as secure when sweat gets in there during a workout.  The Comply true wireless tips make it more secure.  Even though they appear to be smaller than the stock medium tips that come with the earbuds, they have a tighter fit, that is more secure especially during a workout.

Noise cancelling these are not.  Outside sound does get through, especially between songs.  That happens with both the stock tips and the Comply tips.  But you can't hear it when the music is playing.

title: Great earbuds, work well and easy to use.
content:
Very happy with these earbuds. they came a week earlier than expected and so far have exceeded my expectations. i find the very comfortable as they fit snugly in my ears (though this may not happen for everyone) and the sound quality is quite good, especially for truly wireless earbud which tend not to be as good as wired ones.
The only problem I have is the very rarely when using them to watch videos on my laptop they will stop for half a second, then resume as normal. This only happens on my laptop, the connection with my phone is great. It's also very helpful that they can connect to multiple devices at the same time, it makes using them quick and easy.
 The battery is as expected, I've never used finished both the earbud and case charge in one day. The case is more compact than i had thought and is easy to use.
Mic quality is quite good and the hear-through feature is extremely helpful. the buttons on the side, something that many truly wireless earphones don't have, are easy to use and very helpful. Overall these earbuds are very compact and efficient, and i'm very happy with my purchase.

I believe this company is engaging in the practice of just trying to wear me down until I give up trying to get a refurbished unit. title: Best headset I have ever owned.

title: Jabra's are simply no AirPods
content:
Very cool looking compared to my black-skinned AirPods. However, 3 major considerations that you most likely didn't hear well from the other reviews.
1. Voice Assistants. Just updated the firmware (May 22. 2018) on my 65t's. Still no Alexa implementation. "Coming soon". Well, that sucks. Siri works fine (if you like Siri but I don't). Reading the ads and the reviews, I thought Alexa would have been ready by now. It isn't. Of course, the AirPods only respond to Siri, which really is (and always has been) sad. Kudos to Jabra for at least having Alexa in the works. I'll judge the earbuds when Alexa makes it to the Jabras.
2. Fit. The Jabra's aren't as easily inserted as the AirPods. They are fairly glossy and not as easily gripped. The choice of the rubber inserts is VERY important. Let's say that the fit is critical, which is true for all earbuds. The AirPods are much easier to seat. However, you either like the one-size fits all AirPods or you don't. Fortunately maybe, the AirPods fit me very well. The charging case on the Jabra is noticeably larger, which makes slipping them in a front pocket a bit more difficult. At least being larger, the Jabra's won't be as easily washed in the washer as the AirPods (twice now, they survived luckily). I still like the AirPods better. Sorry, Jabra.
3. Sound. As much as I wanted to like the Jabra's, they just didn't have the bass or the width of the sound field like the AirPods. Even with the Jabra iPhone app, they still didn't rock real bass. I don't usually like separate apps for earbuds (like Sony, Bose, etc). Just another step to getting the best sound. Surprisingly, the AirPods have significantly deeper bass and a much wider sound presence. Yes, I tried all the different rubber inserts and the equalizer for the Jabra's. Still not what I have expected from other reviews.

So, the Jabra's were very disappointing and are going back. The AirPods are still in my pocket. Try the AirPods, the bass and sound quality are the best of the wireless earbud bunch.

title: Fantastic Balance Between Sound Quality, Usability and Safety
content: I purchased these to wear while cycling, and nothing more. I had Bluetooth earbuds (with wire between the buds) in the past and they worked okay, but the wires always seemed to get in the way. These truly wireless earbuds stay in and sound great but one of the best features, if you cycle outdoors, is these earbuds have a setting to allow the ambient or surrounding noise to pass through so you can hear what is going on around you . . . like cars coming up behind you. And if you want to block out the ambient noise just switch settings and they deaden or almost completely block out ambient noise. Great earbuds. A bit pricey but fantastic.

title: Issues With Left Bud

At max volume I can't hear it but between 50% - 75% it is noticeable. When I pause it stays for a couple seconds and then I can hear the audio "click" off and it's silent. As soon as I hit play again it returns. The audio is also slightly biased to the left so it sounds like the stereo is 5° to the left of center. Got these because of a sale but they're going back.

content: These speakers are amazing! Really great sound quality. I've tried out at least 10 different pairs, including JAMs, and this one is by far the best sound quality. And I love the equalizer capability on the app to pump up bass. There are many different presets and the "hear through" option is really useful where you can still listen to music but also  to your surroundings if you need to. I usually leave my phone in my coat pocket at the gym and these earbuds will stay connected the whole time i am working out. I would definitely recommend these Jabra earbuds.

Then, all of a sudden -- i use them at the gym and i start getting "low battery warnings" after just a couple of minutes use.  Now (again, after 2 months use just on weekends) - i charge overnight and get 2% charge.  I tried charging just the case with out the buds, both, different cables, but no luck.

While the headphone jack wasn't a technological masterpiece - it worked.  All of these "new solutions" are patchwork and don't seem to work... and just fixated the consumer electronic companies into selling half backed products that don't work in the hopes of the same crappy stuff over and over.

I contacted support and tried their methods to correct this (standard routine of re-pairing, reinstalling the firmware, ...) and it made no difference.  I returned my initial pair and got another thinking it was a defect but the 2nd pair behaves exactly the same.

Even though I'm in the Android ecosystem, I tried pairing some AirPods to the same device and they worked without issues.  The device was left upstairs and I was able to go downstairs to the other side of the house before they cut out.

2/2 attempts to use this product and it's a complete failure.  Looks like I'm getting a set of AirPods since they work as expected.

title: Problem pairing and not very water resistant
content: Disappointed by the Bluetooth pairing.  Sound gets cut off or choppy when I put my phone in my pocket while running.  I have to hold my phone while running in order for the connecting to be consistent.  Also, it is not as water resistant as I had hoped.  After running and sweating, I find the sound quality drastically decreased.  For this price, I really expected much more.

title: Not the Hype it's made up to be
content: Sound quality was ok and mic is good, but overall is product is not as outstanding as some reviews make it sound. The high price point is not worth it in my opinion, especially given how big these earbuds are in your ears. They really feel massive and did not properly fit in my ears despite trying out the different tips. Also, they don't even pay for the return label if you're unsatisfied with the product!

title: Beautiful quality
content: By far the best headphones I have ever owned. Compatible with all devices. Incredible sound quality and clarity. Phone call quality is superb and it reads out loud to you who is calling/texting you. Battery is also great and just as good as the airpods. Also lots of functions directly on the headphones including pause play next song previous song volume up/down answer phone calls access Siri/Google Assistant and basically everything you could think of doing with wireless headphones. HEAVILY EMPHASIZING THIS RECOMMENDATION!

title: Missing extra ear pieces
content: I bought these as used-like new. The packaging was a little torn, as anticipated. Although, the box does not contain the extra silicone ear pieces that are supposed to come with this product. They fit decently with the ones that did come on them, but I feel like they’d fit better if there was a choice of different size pieces. I’m a bit dissapointed, but since they fit in my ear okay and work great, I’ll deal with it.

title: Great sound
content: Great ear pods!!! Only thing I noticed is that when running the vibration from your steps comes through very loudly as your ears are essentially blocked. Turning volume up does drown this out to a degree but is worth noting.

title: Perfect for the gym
content: I love using these at the gym. They have never had connectivity issues for me and I do not have to be particularly close to my phone for them to work. I use them all the time when doing housework too and they do a great job canceling out the sound of the vacuum.

title: Great sound, great mic, HORRIBLE case
content:
These offer great sound and a great microphone with a snug fit in your ear. Battery life is good and can be extended two times with the case.

My only main issue with these is the case itself. It feels cheap with a latch that's too hard to open, and the earbuds aren't magnetically connected in there, so they can pop out if you open the case too harshly (which could happen due to the latch). Also, these charge still via Micro-USB and not USB-C.

Compared to the Anker Soundcore Liberty Airs (although they still use Micro-USB also), this case is embarrassing and should be Jabra's #1 priority to fix in the next version.

title: Don't trust the pics, these fall out!
content: Awful. Absolutely will not stay in the ear. Not running, not in the gym and not on a bike. Amazing conceptually but a total fail. Quality is really great but in practice this was a complete waste of $200. Maybe sitting still on an airplane ride these might work?

title: Poor customer support, would never recommend
content: Worst purchase ever, one headphone quit working shortly after purchase, reached out to Jabra multiple times with no response.

title: Returned bc of poor call quality w iPhone 8
content: Connectivity poor w iPhone, thought the mics would be amazing but it doesn’t matter if the wireless connection isn’t there - switch to AirPods and couldn’t be happier - call quality is 10x better on AirPods w an iphone

title: Best Sound Highest Comfort
content: Best Blue tooth ever purchased! I have medium to small earlobe - don’t even notice they are both in !

title: Phone connection only.
content: Painful in ear.  Does not support connection to computer.

title: Would not stay in place
content: It took me forever to decide on a set of wireless earbuds and after a lot of research and deliberation, I decided to get these.  I was super excited to receive them and immediately paired with my phone (easy!) and registered them (easy!).  I quickly tried them on and couldn't get a seal in the right ear.  No problem, I figured I'd try them out on my commute the following day.  I brought along the extra sets of ear gels in case I had the same issue.  Sound quality was great, but I could not get the right earbud to stay in, no matter which gel I used or how much I jiggled and maneuvered it. Just when I thought I had it in, it would plop out onto my lap.  The left one stayed in using the medium gel, no problem, though I think it would become painful after a while.  I didn't find it very comfortable, but bearable.  Maybe I have a deformed right ear canal or something, but nothing seemed to work on that side.  I was on my train for over two hours messing around with these things, but could not get them to stay put (and that was me sitting; I would have lost it in 2.5 seconds if I had been anything other than stationary).  So, as much as I want to keep these, I'm returning them :(  I'd say if you don't have trouble with regular earbuds, you're probably OK - I've always been hit or miss with earbud fit, but was hoping these would be The Ones.  Alas.

title: Nice
content: Just got these in today and still messing with it. I love the hear- through festures in these, i dont have to take the earphones off to hear.  The sound in these are pretty good but i can hear some hissing but that could be from the music itself. You can definitely hear the bass in these but its not going to blow you away but its better than most of the other headsets.

title: Great (but don't get the gold/beige!)
content:
I also have a set of Mifo o5—a cut rate brand—and think that's an interesting comparison.

The audio 65t audio is better but comparable, but the noise canceling is where it shines, of course.

Build: I actually prefer the metal build of the Mifo buds and case, but the fit on the 65t is perfect (at least for my ears).

Battery: the 65t is fine. The noise canceling uses more battery life, so it doesn't last as long as the mifo,but more than that the mifo case has a beefier battery, meaning longer between case charging... But the 65t case is lighter.

All in all, I definitely prefer the 65t, but I was surprised at how well the mifo stacked up.

One caution: do not get the gold/beige: the overall impression it convey is not "futuristic luxury" but "medical device." More than once, people have asked me if I have gotten hearing aids when I'm wearing these things.

title: Don't buy these if you need to use them to make phone calls.
content:
This review is only focused on using these for phone calls.  The amount of background noise this device picked up made them unusable for me on phone calls.

I tested this by leaving a voicemail first with this set of headphones, then using a 3-4 year old Plantronics headset, and finally a speaker phone with  some reality cop show on in the background.  This headset fared worse than the other two options at how loud the background tv show was and how well you could hear the message I left.

This device gets great reviews and it might make a great set of headphones, but they were useless for phone calls for me.

title: Five Stars
content: love the product, I just wish that I was able to change the song from the earbuds

title: Short range for Bluetooth
content:
The sound is great.  I love the fit.  They have a good battery life.  The Bluetooth range is very poor.  My cheap Teblab earbuds get twice as much Bluetooth distance.  These are fine if you are "wearing" your phone.  But I use mine in a shop and have the phone sitting on a shelf out of harms way.  I am lucky if I can get 15 feet from my phone without the Bluetooth breaking up or completely dropping out.  Since I work in a dusty shop I don't want my phone to close.  But I will have to come up with something if I want to use this around my 30x30 shop.
If you have your phone on you all the time then get these earbuds.  If you are separated from your phone by more than a few feet you might want to look into something else.

title: Disappointed
content: I was very disappointed because the earbuds do not stay in my ears.  The sound is good, but if it will not stay in my ear...what is the point.

It's super annoying and unbearable.

title: The best for calls. Just OK for music. 3.75 stars overall.
content:
Phone calls are great and crystal clear for both parties. Does a good job of filtering out normal background noise. Don’t expect to be in a loud environment and other person not hear. They aren’t that good, but good enough for everyday calls. I use these for conference calls on my cell and skype calls from my Laptop through Bluetooth and they work great.

They are comfortable and will not fall out. The app is great and very useful. You can use only 1 bud but it has to be the right one. Left will not work by itself.

I am not quite an audiophile but I am more experienced and critical than most. I am picky about how I want my music to sound. Sound quality on these buds is just ok for me. These sound like a pair of $40-50 wired ear buds. My biggest complaint with these is the bass and volume level. At max volume these are about 70% the volume of my $50 Sony wired buds. No distortion though. Bass is lacking but present. Those really deep notes are weak even with the eq set to bass boost.  The overall sound quality is no where as polished as the Bose sound sports for about the same price.

As for games and videos, yes there is a delay as most Bluetooth headphones have. What’s weird is that the delay varies. In the Xfinity stream app and also Netflix there is little to no noticeable lag at all, which is great. Browser videos, YouTube, and Facebook videos are hit or miss. Some videos have a huge lag while some are only a slight delay. Games have a huge lag as well which make these basically unusable for that purpose.

If you have 170 bucks to spend and phone calls is your #1 priority, these are for you. If bass and sound quality is what you want Bose is MUCH better. As a traveling salesman I’m happy with my purchase since calls is a major reason I selected these. I will be keeping my wired buds in my travel bag for music and movies on the plane.

title: Great sound for all types of music.
content: The sound quality on these earbuds is beyond good.  I did have to play around with the rubber tips to find the right fit for my ears. Once I found the best fit they were comfortable, stable and solid.  I tested head movements and didn't have any problems with the buds falling out.

title: Dont waste your time to buy this
content:
For the price, i did not except that when you are doing some exercises which is hard, the earbuds loose the connectivity. This is very galling when you are concentrate on your training and you earbuds start to sizzle.

So please, if you are considering to do a real training, don't buy the jabra elite active

title: These are excellent!
content: Love these ear buds...the best I've purchased so far! Worth every dollar!

title: DO NOT BUY!!!  If you have a problem, be prepared to wait.
content:
For the price of these headphones, you would hope for a quality product.  If there is a problem with the product, you would expect the company to try their best to make you happy.

I bought these headphones in October of 2018.  I'm writing this review in April of 2019.  The left earbud is dead.  Jabra is willing to replace the earbuds but you must ship them back and wait for them to send you another set.  I asked support how long that takes and their response is 3 weeks...

I cannot believe that Jabra will not cross ship or do anything to speed up this process.

These headphones are not abused.  I wear them every day during my commute for about 20 minutes each way.  I wear them while walking.  The left earbud sound quality degraded to the point that I can no longer use them.

I contacted support and they sent me an email detailing how to reset them to factory, then update the firmware, then rebind.  Same issue.  Contacted support again today hoping they will send  me a replacement set.  They will but it is a huge turn around time.  I now have to go buy another set of earbuds to use while waiting to get these back.

Buyer beware - for a $170 set of headphones, you would think they would last more than 6 months without breaking.
 To add to that, you must wait around 3 weeks to get them replaced.  This is not good customer service for what is supposed to be a quality product.

I have had other bluetooth headphones that have lasted much longer.  I definitely will not buy another Jabra product.

title: Great wireless ear buds
