The active elite have amazing connectivity using Bluetooth 5 technology.  The jabra sound app is a big plus with an equalizer, a locator for where the earbuds last left their case, software updates, etc.  The earbuds are excellent for voice calls and they even announce who is calling before you decide to answer.  Music tracks can be paused, forwarded or reversed via small buttons on the earbuds.  You can even adjust volume from the earbuds.  There are other functions such as sound pass through and Google assistant, etc.

My only criticism is that the earbuds are not magnitized so that they would be better held within their case.

If you don't believe me on how GREAT these earbuds are, just do a You Tube search for Jabra active elite 65t and see for yourself.

title: Much better sound quality
content: I ordered these to replace my Samsung Gear Icon 2018 ear buds. Much better sound quality. Recommend using these with Comply SmartCore Variety Pack Premium Memory Foam Earphone Tips. These help to add more bass and aid in keeping in place during workout

title: Sound great
content: Great for work! I’ve had them for about 3 months. I usually only work with one in

title: Unbearable hissing from left bud
content:
Liked everything about the bose soundsport frees except the audio delay so i tried these bluetooth 5.0 jabra elite active 65t based on pretty overwhelmingly positive reviews. The sound and fit are decent and the connection was solid but after every action or during music playback there was a hissing whitenoise from the left bud for 2-3 seconds which ended in a small pop.
Some reviews mentioned this and kind of shaked it off like it was some minor inconvenience but it is actually unbearably annoying.  Looking deeper into the issue it seems very prevalent and nobody seems to have a fix or even acknowledge it when its brought up in discussion. For the people that do mention it they also mention that the issue persists after two or three exchanges so this seems to be a pretty common issue. The hiss is loud enough that it muddies up the sound quality and ruins the experience. Even worse when there is no music playing and after every action or notification you are reminded that you are wearing earbuds by this obnoxious hissing assaulting your brain.
Im not sure why this major issue is not being discussed or getting any attention from any of the tech review sites or reviewers or when it is addressed it is made out to be not as bad as it is. I'm returning mine but if this issue is addressed i would be happy to try again.

title: The best I've ever owned
content: Great headphones, actually my second pair after my dog ate my first pair. I had those for a little more than a year. Headphones have always hurt my ears so I was hesitant to spend so much on a pair I couldn't try on first, but glad I did!

title: Great headphones, but the fit is a gamble
content: These are great headphones. Great sound, battery life, and noise cancellation. The only thing is that they are a really weird shape and you have to have larger ears to accommodate the design regardless of the earpiece size that you select. If they fit your ears, you'll be happy with everything else.

title: Left side ear will not work
content: I do like the sound that you could hear out of listening to the outside noise with a push of a button but just like a good amount of people I have found out the used earbuds had the same issue. The left ear stopped working if it was not held at a certain angle. I think there was something lose inside but I wasn't going to open it up.

title: Don't buy it
content: The left earbud is not working at all after the software update and I try company support they don't reply back.

title: Love these earbuds!
content: I have been using these earbuds for about 6 months now. I use them about 5 days a week. They have been flawless for me. Sound is great. Noise cancellation works great. Fit my ear great. Very happy with the product and would recommend to everyone. Batter life is excellent as well. Enjoy!

title: Volume issue but otherwise a decent product
content: Use it mainly when at the golf driving range but sometimes after I swing, the volume automatically rises.  It's annoying because it gets too loud and then I have to stop after a few swings every time.

title: Unstable quality
content: As other people have written wanted to really like these earbuds but I have been thru 2 pairs and the same thing occurred within a couple of months. The left earbuds stopped producing sound. When they work, the sound is awesome. The Alexa assist works great. I went thru all the troubleshooting I read and what Jabra suggested. They did exchange the first pair for the second which again failed after a couple of months. My experience has not been good so I do not recommend.

title: Great, but sadly, no MUTE function.
content: Excellent, would have gotten 5 stars, but no MUTE button.

title: Good connection and great fit!
content:
I would say these are a great investment over those $20-30 dollars wireless (wired) bluetooth earbuds.  Sound quality is not bad.  Fitment is great!  Will not fall out.  I've been to the gym and these work well enough to not fall out or even feel like falling out.  I usually am annoyed when I hear drops out because of bluetooth connection, but these connect really well and stay connected really well.  Usually the other earbuds I would hear drop outs now and then, but these have no problem.

I got mine from a Amazon warehouse deal (Much much cheaper $130 ish plus tax).  It was probably a return because it came without ANY ear tips.  A bit frustrating, but luckily I have some from my other earbuds.

title: Great fit, Terrific construction and Sound, Terrible customer service
content:
These are the best headphones, they last on average a month before I have to charge them. I use them often for working out and they almost never disconnect when you go far from your phone.

My left Headphone started crackling then disconnecting every 5 seconds lately, attempted to reach out to Jabra to get it covered under warranty. But, its been a month now and 15 separate attempts go unanswered. Terrible Customer Service, be warned.

title: Good sound, faulty after 6 months, poor customer support
content:
I bought the product almost 8 months ago now. It worked well for the first 6 months, but since then it stopped turning off automatically when placed back into the case, which means my phone audio output remains routed to them. Only workaround is turning Bluetooth off on my phone, then back on a few hours later.

Contacted customer support about 6 weeks ago now, and after some initial troubleshooting they asked me to submit a warranty request form, but since then they've gone silent despite multiple attempts on my part to get any kind of update.

title: Surprisingly Great Airpod Alternatives
content: Currently using these earbuds on a Pixel 2 XL, headphones sound great and usually connect to the phone without issue. Only complaint is earbuds require the Sound+ app to work and I always have to exit the app and relaunch it when the headphones connect in order for the phone to recognize the earbuds for audio.

title: Good for Riding, not for activity
content: These are not bad headphones in the definition of headphones. However, if you want to be any kind of  active (including riding a lawn mower) these are not your forte. They fall out even if you attempt to move your jaw. If you plan to use these on an airplane only they’re perfect but dont expect much else out of them.

title: Good sound, IF they stay in your ear.
content:
Generally above average sounding monitors. Battery life is on par with competitive offerings.

Downsides: not overly great build quality for the price. Also, they DO NOT stay in your ears, especially under heavy sweat. Even with largest ear attachment there is no seal. After 20 minutes of a workout they begin to fall out of my ears even when standing still.

title: Great sound with a good equalizer
content: I've only had this product for a few moments. The case seems pretty durable The earbuds are a little heavy but I can get used to that. The app is really cool and the equalizer is nice. Found the perfect sound for me. The sounds skips a little bit when removing one earbud but that's fine I've yet to update it so we will see what the update brings. I'll check back in after awhile to give everyone an update

title: Overall good, but slightly on the expensive side
content: Earbuds are great in general. Unfortunately the connection seems to be very unstable at points it makes you want to rip them out of your ears. It happens at least once a day on my 20 min walk to work. They're great for running and dont fall out of your ear. I had a pair of nose wireless before and the chord that connected them drove be crazy because it would hang on the heavier side when running. These are a great upgrade.

title: Kinda OK
content: This is an OK product. The sound is pretty good. But, I expected it to fit better. Other reviews, both on Amazon and elsewhere, suggested that earbuds would be able to fit most or all people with some tweaking. The various size plastic ear things didn't provide me something that fit well. The documentation suggests inserting the bud into your ear and twisting it to set it securely. That helps a little. But, after walking just a little way, I spent more time playing with the bud, tying to keep it in, than listing to a pod cast. I can't imagine it staying in for even a few minutes if I was running or doing a vigorous workout. I don't have any of my materials so I am probably stuck with it. I might use it when I am stationary.

title: Very good when you can score a deal
content:
First, I bought these as "refurbished", and sold through Jabra, for CONSIDERABLY less than the new price here (as of 10/28/19).

Very quickly:

Sounds pretty darn good.  Not real bass-heavy, but nice sounding, completely satisfied.

Fits very nice in my ears, perhaps a bit too big, but they don't move at all; again, satisfied.

The app offers a "pass-through" option, which turns on the mics so you can hear the outside world better.  This is fantastic when needed.

Case is initially quite difficult to open, but once I realized that if you squeeze the sides while lifting the lid, the process becomes much easier.  Docking a star for that poor engineering.  Also, I am not a fan of the charging light operation.  One time it blinks, another time it doesn't; I really never am sure where the battery level stands.  Additionally, when the buds are placed in the case, again, I am uncertain if the buds are truly lined up with the charging dots...

Overall, for the price I paid, I am very satisfied, would recommend, but the full price new is a bit steep.

title: Right earbud stopped working after 9 months..
content:
- Bad build-quality. Didn't last a year.
- Serial number is not recognized at the Jabra customer support website.
+ Good sound quality
+ Good connectivity (if your gadget has bluetooth 5.0)

I regret purchasing it on eBay, since I do not get a warranty.
If you're planning to buy this product, I recommend that you buy it from a reliable seller that offers a warranty.
Although it might cost you extra, it will be worth it in the long-run!

title: Excellent product.
content:
As described.  Great product.

Left earbud went out.  With no hassle, they sent out a replacement after one phone call.  I work in a harsh environment, 8 hrs a day, 6 days a week.  Wear them constantly.

title: Gave my airpods away
content: After replacing the standard buds with "Comply SmartCore Sport Pro Premium Memory Foam Earphone Tips with SweatGuard" made everything from 90% to 100% perfect.

title: Works as described
content:
does what it is supposed to do

purchased april 2nd right channel dead by oct 31

title: Great Wireless Option That Hurts Your Ears
content: I love having a wireless headphone option but, because of the occasional pain of sticking these bulky(ish) nuggets in my ears every day, I ponder a prospective return to those wired bast*rds from Apple.

title: Charger Problems
content: They were working perfectly fine until the charger stopped charging the earphones. I connect the case with the earphones until the light goes green. Then the light inside the case changes to red, I take earphones out and they connect then disconnect and turn off immediately.... I haven't been able to use them cuz they wont charge...

title: The default fits they have arent the best, they fall out whenever i smile and am sweating
content: I like how they work well and stick in my ears most of the time.

title: Decent but not perfect
content:
I actually purchased these from a brick and mortar store as I wanted the black earbuds and they carried them locally.

My initial impressions are:

These were easy to set up and pair with my iPhone. They connect easily each by taking them out of the charging case or by turning on each ear bud - depending if I put them back in the case or manually turned them off.

I put them in my ears with the medium tips that they came with. Most of the time I use either medium or small tips. The medium tips have an excellent seal but bothered my ears. I use in-ear buds all the time but never realized what ear fatigue was. The medium tips didn’t really hurt but made my ears feel tired. I switched to the small tips and what a great difference. The buds actually were now comfortable.

Sound quality with these is pretty good for truly wireless buds. Of course not as crisp and with great separation that I get with my IEM’s but decent quality nonetheless. I used the app with the equalizer to change up and add more bass but honestly don’t hear any difference.

Call quality is usable. I can hear the caller perfectly and the caller can hear me okay - not great but much better than other cheaper truly wireless buds.

The controls on the earbuds are fine and work good - no issues.

The silliest part of this purchase is the charging case. I like that it’s small and that the lights are good signals. I hate that it doesn’t have magnets to keep the buds in charge. And the cover design is just bad. So far it works but I’m afraid that the small plastic clasp that hold the top tightly will wear quickly and not hold the buds in for charging. With the top price of these buds, you would think the charging case would be as good as all the cheap ones out there.

I can’t say how much time I get on a single charge, as I don’t ever use them to the point of running low. When done, I pop them back into the case, so they are pretty much always charged.

I haven’t had any problems with the left earbud not working, any disconnects or stuttering. The audio lapse with videos is only noticeable in the YouTube app. Netflix has no noticeable latency.

Overall, decent earbuds but for this price, should be “great” rather than just “decent”.

title: Great For Music
content: Great For Music, decent bass, they fitted perfect in my ears, I did not have to Change the tips, Good For calls, people can listen your Voice clearly, the only thing I do not Hear them very well, Life battery is good, charging case very easy to use. I Love them.

title: Cut out regularly
content: Sound quality is great, but they cut out regularly. It’s so frequent I stopped using them and would not recommend them.

title: Not bad but!!!!
content: These buds are technically fine however they won't stay in my ear and I found after 30 min actually starting hurting.  They need to add some sort of stabiliser for the ear like Bose.  Just a thought.  Also the case was a bit stiff to open I noticed.  The  build quality and sound are worth the money and of course not everyone's ears are same so just because they didn't fit mine doesn't mean they won't fit yours.  Just saying!

title: Poor connection
content: Very Poor connection. Mines always disconnects

title: Bad call quality
content: Call quality. The call quality for me is good. The problem is it picks up every little bit of background noise. I tried using these for work and the level of every little noise in the background is amplified. Also, I was on a call in public and the person I was talking to could here everything but me.

title: Who would pay that much?
content:
Why would anyone in their right mind pay so much for these?
There are other wireless earbuds that are just as good and they cost $40

title: Bad for calls
content: The mic is picking the ambient noise, ao the caller can not hear your voice clearly in crowded places or street.

title: Only one issue I’ve found
content: The sound quality is great. I bought these specifically because the app has an equalizer. I listen almost exclusively to metal and I wanted to make sure I could control the sound coming out of the earbuds. The equalizer allows me to do that. They are also comfortable. I’ve been able to wear these all day with no or very little discomfort. The only issue I had with them is the earbud tips themselves. The material they are made of is so thin and flexible, that when they warm up from your body heat they can’t hold the earbuds in place. I kept having issues with them just falling out of my ears. The issue was easily fixed however, by buying replacement earbud tips made of memory foam.

title: Great for others, just not for me.
content: Device is great but does not fit my right ear. It is very uncomfortable to wear for that ear. I would recommend for others but they are not for me. They would be awesome and if you could just wear the left ear without the right but that is just not an option.

title: This Bud's for You!
content:
Sorry, I couldn't resist.
Seriously, I am a fan of most things Apple, but I had to draw the line at the Airpods. I didn't have a necklace to match! (They look like weird earrings to me) Also a big fan of Bluetooth earpieces for use with my iPhone. I hate holding a phone to my ear and voice assistants are best enjoyed hands free. After many purchases I settled on the Jabra Stealth. I love it. It is by far the best I have used, but while fantastic in every other way it is not really intended to be your go to for music. Enter the Elite 65t. I bought it for music, but it may force my Stealth into retirement. My experience so far; Nice look to these, professional and low profile! Easy set-up. Good battery life made great with the charging case. Sound quality good, but you need the right size gel to get the base you want. Passive noise canceling, again, the gel fit matters. The call quality surprised me, great on both ends. I actually had a friend that I chat with regularly noticed the call quality was better not knowing that I was on the 65t. Well thought out controls and quite comfortable.The sound app is very helpful. Summary point: I would buy these again!

title: Everything I hoped they would be
content: I spent hours on the internet trying to find the best truly wireless earbuds for the lowest price. After much deliberation,  I settled on these. Some reviews clearly are not written by audiophiles, so I was struggling in my selection. I'm glad I chose these. They are everything I hoped for. They fit great in my ear,  with no feel of falling out while exercising.  When interested correctly into the ear canal,  they sound fantastic for an earbud. Very full sound in all genres of music. They charge quickly and connect very fast when removed from the case. I haven't charged the case in two weeks of going to the gym for an hour at a time. I'm extremely pleased with these,  and I was happy to get on sale at $119.  Worth every penny. This is a true and honest review,  no compensation whatsoever.

title: One earbud lower volume than the other
content:
I really want to like these headphones bluetooth connection is great, controls are decent, the charging pod is wonderful, the noise cancellation and calling are great but as headphones they are decent until they aren't. After about a week of use i noticed that the left earbud was slowly losing volume, I went so far as to have my ears checked to make sure it wasn't my ear that was the problem, it wasn't. Other people have reported this issue and it looks like the company has not made any attempt to fix it.

Like I said I really wanted to like these headphones, but when they don't work as headphones what is the point?

title: Fantastic earbuds with one annoying flaw
content: I don't need to echo all of the good things that others have said. Overall these are just great. But one annoying flaw that they don't mention in the documentation/description is that the noise filter (what brings out your voice and mutes other noise during a call) only works on an actual phone call, not on VOIP calls. So if you are using Google Voice, WhatsApp, Messenger, Skype, or any other VOIP protocol, you'll have to be in a quiet environment, as outside will be very loud for the person you are calling. My spouse said that things like passing traffic or even running water from a sink were very loud and disruptive to our conversation. So just keep this in mind if you make a lot of VOIP calls. Hopefully there will be a future firmware fix for this...

title: Lost Jabra!
content: What I was afraid of, the earbuds falling out, did happen.  Do NOT use them biking, because I just could not find it in the ditch even with a metal detector!  They are good for walking and easy jog.

title: Gone bad after 3 months.
content:
For the price I really wanted to love these.  They were uncomfortable at first but I figured I would eventually get use to them.  I found myself tolerating these buds, but after 3 months I can't say they ever fit comfortably.

The sound is pretty solid.

It has been 3 months since my initially purchase.  As of a week ago I found that the left earbud has lost sound.  The buttons work, but I get no music.  A quick search will show plenty of users with this same issue.  Currently waiting on Jabra's customer support to respond; but based on comments from other users, that doesn't sound to promising.

Before this sound issue I would given it 3-4 stars, based on the quality of the sound and the long battery life / portale charger.  But there is something truely flawed with this product if a series are customers are reporting the same issue at the same time.

title: Has the potential to be great, but...
content: ... be warned that there is one major problem ( which is, in my opinion, sort of a deal breaker). I've been through several sets of these earbuds (both 65t and 65t active) and each time the left earbud is noticeably louder than the right earbud. It's really annoying when using the earbuds for an extended period of time. Firmware updates and reinstallation have not fixed the problem and I'm starting to think this issue either can't be fixed or will never be fixed. Just something to consider if you're thinking of picking this one up.

title: I loved this earbuds for 3 months until they suddenly burned out!!!
content:
I would have rate this earbuds with 5 stars if they would have been working at least 1 year!

So, I bought this earbuds from here at Amazon on October 17th, 2018.
I loved them since the first time I received the package! They are good looking, an amazing sound! Easy to pair! Everything was as they advertised!

Today (January 30, 2019) I was at work, sitting on my desk listening to music when the right earbud started to heat up and the music suddenly stopped. I took off both earbuds, left side was normal and I turned it off, but the right one was each second even hotter than before, I immediately turned off my Bluetooth device and tried to turn off the earbud, but nothing worked, it was already burned out.

The Jabra Elite 65t are now a piece of trash.
I want to know how I can get a replacement since it didn't pass even 4 months since I bought them and they stopped working and it's supposed to be under warranty.

title: customore service horrible you can never get threw
content: they fall out of ears when bending or doing exercise

title: Love them
content: So easy to use and they sound great. Worth every penny.

title: Just okay
content:
Bought these based off a tech review. They don't seat well in my ears and fall out frequently so i'm constantly twisting them back in place and when one come out it shuts off the other one which is super annoying on a conference call. i spend a lot of time looking for one on the floor or accidentally hitting the button and hanging up.  I don't want to install an app to use headphones. I haven't tested the batterly life to zero but they've lasted through multiple meetings. the case isn't designed super well; kind of hard to get them to site right back into the case. kind of par for the course for jabra products i guess.

The sound quality is decent and i've asked a couple meeting participants how i sounded and they said crystal clear.

I think there are probably better headphones out there for the money.

title: Great product
content: Great product so far. I have had Bose and many other brands of pods and single ear pieces for music and daily as my phone headset. These have worked the best for me and have had the best sound quality and base out of many of them. I have probably had 20 different ones over the last 10 years. Did tons of research and read tons of product reviews. The Jabra Gt was the only device that popped up on almost all of them so I gave it a shot and they did not disappoint. I know how frustrating it is trying to find the best one out there as most of the reviews are people who are being paid to review the product and won’t get paid or used unless it’s a good review. These are worth the money and I hope they last a long time or I don’t loose them. Slot smaller than they look and very comfortable. Love the voice control as you don’t have to press anything to answer the phone. Just say “answer” and it will.  I don’t give five stars easily which is why I rated at a 4. It would have to make me dinner and clean the house for a 5. Also only use the reviews that say verified purchase as all others aren’t people that have purchased the product. I hope this helps you make your decision.

title: Buyer Beware
content: Buyer beware. These continually drop when connected to a Microsoft Surface. Anytime a notification pops up, they drop for 5 seconds and reconnect. When using for TCs they are basically useless

title: Wouldn't stay in my ears
content: I will start by saying the sound is great. Better than my Apple EarPods. But, they won't stay in my ear so the sound quality doesn't matter. Had to return and stick with Apple.

title: Insane value!
content: Great product so far, solid built, easy to set up, pairs up quick, and audio quality is top tier from something so small. You'll love features like audio pass through, pause when a bud is taken out, the case charging, etc. Highly recommended!

title: Absolutely amazing fit & sound. Super fast Bluetooth pairing on IOS.
content:
I've recently been in search for the perfect wireless earbuds to exercise in.  I’ve tried PowerBeats3, BeatsX, Bose SoundSport Free, AirPods for running / gym sessions and they have all disappointed either with fit/comfort,  sound-quality, and/or sweat-water resistance.

My main issue with the above is probably the ability for them to stay in my ear while working out or running (PowerBeats3 stayed on my ear, but never kept its seal in my ear so sound quality was terrible, plus the wires get sticky with sweat).

The “twist” lock of these Jabra Elite Actives 65t ensure they stay in my ear no matter what I do...so secure not a single adjustment is needed during workouts. They simply stay put. Amazing! AND they are COMFORTABLE! I knew I wanted to stay away from anything with wingtips (like the Jaybird) because historically, wingtips hurt my ears. So no wingtip fit is an important feature of the 65t.  If i don't need a secure fit (example at the office), I just slip them on without twist locking them and they stay comfortable all day.

I had concerns about Bluetooth connectivity (I’m on APPLE ecosystem), but I have had no issues with automatically connecting out of the charging case (synced to 2 devices at a time)...by the time I remove them and put them in my ear, they are connected. Not quite AirPods convenient, but damn close. Charging case is small, sleek, and fits in my pocket beautifully. These Elite Actives are the earbuds Bose and Beats should strive for in the active space. AAA+ Jabra! You’ve made a life long customer out of me.

title: Sound is surprisingly pleasant and warm
content:
I really like how they sound. Not bad for such small things.
Very warm soothing sound to listen to vocal Jazz like Melody Gardot.
Nicely done. But then again the sound of her voice can melt your heart using any device :)
Earbuds have very low profile, which is very nice.

The only truly bad thing is, they pick up surround noise much better and louder than voice when used for phone calls.
God forbid wife is wearing them talking to me while doing anything or being in airport or cafe!
I barely can hear her voice behind crazy loud noises around her.
Very annoying.

title: Love these things.
content: I love these earbuds. I’ve never been able to get earbuds fit in my ear well at all, and definitely not without hurting my ears with prolonged use— until I bought these. They fit well and sound great. I was concerned with some reviews reporting that one of the earbuds disconnects before I purchased. And I’ll admit, it’s happened to me like 2-3 times. However it happened when I left the earbuds out without use for a long period of time. The first time upset about it, but realized that it resyncs when I put the earbuds back in the case before using them. They don’t have noise cancelation, but the sound isolation does a good enough job. The hear-through feature does an awesome job of allowing ambient sound back in when you want it, which helps me when I’m walking around the city. Buy with confidence.

title: No problems with Earbuds, but case needs work
content: I understand they want the case to be tight for charging, but I use large earbud rubber attachment and I can't close the case.

title: great earbuds if the software is fixed and weight is reduced
content:
Good: water and dust resistance, great sound, great battery life

  Bad: App (Android) is buggy, weight is a bit high, inserts could be better

I bought the last version of these (Jabra Elite Sport) and had to return them because they didn't sound great and were not comfortable.

These are a lot more comfortable but still heavy and after a couple of hours of wearing them, you definitely know they are there. In fact I knew they were there the day after wearing them. I think the reason is their weight which can probably be helped with some better earbud inserts (like memory ones).

At the end, the biggest problem for me was the software. The app would loose Bluetooth connection and start going crazy with notifications, while the earbuds were in fact still connected and playing music.

It's a shame because these earbuds have so much potential with their sound quality and dust/water resistance ratings. The battery life is great too.

title: Disappointed
content:
Overall, these earbuds came so close.
I've been on the hunt now for truly wireless earbuds for a few months.  I tried the Bose Soundsport Free's and these Jabra's and returned both pairs.

The Bose
-- excellent sounded quality
-- great charging case
-- serious bluetooth connectivity issues and lag (this was the deal breaker for me for the Bose)

The Jabra's
-- excellent connectivity
-- average sound quality
-- below average case

The Jabra's had absolutely no connectivity issues.  They never dropped and I saw no lag when watching videos.  The sound quality was disappointing though especially having just tried out the Bose for a week.  These were just thin sounding even when I achieved a really good seal in my ear and when adjusting the sound profile in the app.  The weakest link though was the case itself.  It may sound strange to mention the case, but since there are no wires and short battery lives, the cases become VERY important.  The Jabra case had three main faults.  1st - it was very had to open.  You have to awkwardly squeeze the top front of the lid to get it to release.  It honestly feels like you are going to break it. 2nd - the earbuds are not magnetically held in place inside the case (like the Bose), so when the case finally does flip open (remember you are having to put too much pressure on the lid...see problem 1) they WILL fly out. 3rd - the case charges the earbuds but doesn't have any charge level indicator on the case itself...it says that it has about 3 earbud charges in it when fully charged, but you never really know how much is left.

None of these individually are deal breaker problems, but taken in total mean that the Jabra's just weren't worth the money.  I returned them after a week.

title: Great Fit
content: I recently returned my Samsung Galaxy ear buds because they fit loosely in my ears no matter how I adjusted them.  These Jabras fit exceptionally well (they are a little larger, but the larger shape sits better in the ear and provides a comfortably tight fit).  Sound quality is good.  Controls are on par with Jaybird and Samsung.  Also, I use these for work calls as I'm sitting at my laptop and so far I have had good feedback from callers on voice quality.  Looking forward to using them for hiking and exercising.

title: Great ear buds, can pair with anything...
content: Great buds. However literature fails to indicate how to pair with a PC and seems to indicate the ear buds are for phones exclusively.

title: was good until they stopped working, now getting a replacement seems like a massive hassle
content: Loved them for a couple of months then one day the right earbud which is the master stopped working, rendering the device useless.  Jabra support kept me waiting for 2 weeks then offered me completely unhelpful advise.  I need a replacement asap I'm very unhappy

title: Good product marred by bad customer service
content:
The Jabra elite 65t is a great completely wireless headphone. While they last.

I bought my jabra 65t back in March and used it extensively for working out and daily commuting. I'm a heavy sweater so the water proofing is a must. The sound is stellar. Very balanced. Pairing was easy and the controls are intuitive. The only qualm I had was if you did any high intensity or high movement workouts they would probably fall out, so the fit isn't perfect despite trying multiple earpieces.

I had no problems with the Jabras until about a week ago when during a core workout the left ear fell out no more than 2ft and hit the mat. The faceplate fell off and stopped functioning. I have had the earbuds for no more than 6 months. Customer support said accidental damage is not covered and gave me a coupon for my next purchase.

For a (at the time) $150+ pair of headphones, you'd expect them to last longer than 6 months. Follow that up with customer support who doesn't care and takes about 3-5 business days to respond to each response. You've lost a customer for life. 100% chance this customer service experience extends to their new line the 75t.

Sound: A+
Fit: B
User experience: A-
Customer service and experience: F-

title: ... and I can unquestionably say that these are much better in almost every way
content:
I went from the bose soundsport free to these and I can unquestionably say that these are much better in almost every way. They have a more solid fit inside the ear and do a fair job of maintaining sound quality and volume. The bose soundsport free needed to be at nearly max volume while at planet fitness in order for me not to be able to hear the fans going overhead, meanwhile with these I can keep them at a more reasonable level.

The most important distinction though is that the bose soundsport free are currently incompatable with windows 10 and suffer from an insufferable number of bugs if you intend to use them with a windows machine. The bugs with the bose soundsport free include - video / audio desync, and constant dropping of the left earbud. These have been bugs since the beginning and are not showing any immediate signs of improvement. By comparison, I can use the Jabra elite with windows and my phone and have found no bugs or conflicts of any sort that could not be easily resolved.

The only feature that was better about the bose headphones was that the case was magnetic and opened much more nicely, but that was meaningless in the face of the Jabra's many other positive qualities.

In short, if you are considering whether to get these or the bose soundsport free I would  highly, highly recommend these.

title: Jabra has made a return customer out of me
content:
I've been using this product for over 6 months now while working the shipping department at a Distribution Center. Lifting boxes for 12 hours straight.

  Connection to my cell phone is quick and easy right out of the box. As soon as you pull the right bus out of the case thereafter, it will connect automatically.

  Sound quality is excellent. Easily on par with my V-moda M100 headphones, though not as nice as my Sennheiser 85s. There is a bit of audio delay, unfortunately, so they can't be used with apps like Smule.

  They fit nicely, and I haven't had them fall out except for when I tried to wear them under my Shoei motorcycle helmet. Even then, they were comfortable, and only popped out because my helmet is very snug, so it gripped the buds when taking it off.
  Though, to be honest, it took some time to get accustomed to the things. The same design that keeps them locked in place can cause a bit of pain until either they get broken in or your ears do.

  The battery life is fantastic! As I said, I wear at least the right earbud at work, typically for at least 4 hours at a time, and they charge enough during my 20 minute break window to keep going for another 4 hours. It's absolutely brilliant. The only time they've ever died on me was when I forgot I was wearing them and didn't put them in the charging case. Even then, it was a quick 30 minutes in my pocket, then back to death metal.

  The hear-through technology is great when I'm walking around Walmart or something, and at times is even better than natural acoustics. However, if you work near machinery like I do, you'll want to turn it off unless you can dance to the sound of screeching and distortion. But, it's really easy to turn off in the app.

  Voice communication is crystal clear coming through the JE65's as well. I can't comment on what the other party can hear, but I haven't had any issues at all except people sometimes ask if I'm okay because I look like I'm talking to myself (I have shoulder length hair, so these things are invisible to onlookers when I wear them).

  Alright, so here's my biggest selling point. That's right, not the audio, not the battery, not the secure fit, but rather the unbelievable durability. I've used them for 6 months in a warehouse. I once dropped the case (with the left earbud inside) and the right earbud (which I had popped out to concentrate for a moment) from my pocket onto a concrete floor from 15ft scaffolding. The right earbud looks good as new. The case has some scuff-marks but opens, closed, and charges just like it's supposed to. I didn't find the right earbud until I had clocked out and used my phone's disconnection radius to triangulate the signal. Any audio device that can survive the kind of abuse my earbuds have taken deserves a 5-star rating.

  A word to the wise, place your JE65s in the top of the case, aligned with the mold, then close the bottom. Perfect charging connection every time.

  So, why should you buy the Jabra Elite 65s?

- Long lasting
- Tough and durable
- Very loud when appropriate
- Can be painful at first, but never falls out

  Coincidentally, the same list my wife gave me after our honeymoon.

title: Nice sound but painful with a bit of a buzz.
content:
Really hurt my ears for some reason. The plastic just dig into the sides of my ears.

A slight buzz in the left ear. It got worse with louder volume.
