title: So the sound quality to me is on par with Jaybird x2's and I really like the no wires
content:
Had a preorder on Amazon but they could not get them on time so i ordered through Jabra.  So the sound quality to me is on par with Jaybird x2's and I really like the no wires.  They are barely noticeable when you have them in your ears.  The big issue for me that I cannot get them to stay in ear for more than a 1/2 hour of walking.  Either one or both will pop out.  I have tried each combination of the small to large silicone ear pieces and they just do not work for me.  Always had a problem with silicone so I have been using the Comply foam tips for several years.  The comply tips I have did not work well with the Elite Active.  I think partly because of the way they stuck out of my ear.  Comply has a new pair, TrueGrip Foam which do work.  I tested yesterday and had them in my ear for over an hour.  But the TrueGrip Foam fit very loosely on the buds so when you remove them the foam tip stays in your ear.  Easy to remove.  The buds will charge in the case with the foam tips on.  A big plus.  Hard for me to blame Jabra for my ear types.  If you order try them for fit as soon as you get them and make sure they work for you.
Edit 10/1/18  Contacted Comply about the TrueGrip Pro and they told me that they just released a different version called SmartCore.  Bought the variety pack which included two different styles, 2 pairs of the round and 1 pair of the sport style.  Tried the sport style and the earbuds never fell out over a run/walk for 90 minutes.  The only thing I noticed was the sport style caused the earbuds to stick out my ear a little bit more.  Also have to take them off for charging.So also been using the airbuds with the silicone ear covers and they never fell out of my air.  Major difference is the sound quality.  The airbuds do not sound as good as the Jabra's.  This is a good first attempt by Jabra but at this price point I feel they need too look at including 2 things in the future, 1.  Magnetic charger with a better closing mechanism on the charger (present one kind of cheesy for $180- earbuds, 2.  Foam tips should have been planned for the charger and included.  Many of the earbuds in this price range and above include both silicone and foam so buyers have options.  Sennheiser has a new pair coming out in October.  Price will be a little higher, but will be interested to see how they stack up.

title: Great sound!
content: Comfy and great sound!!!  I use them to watch movies on my devices as well as for music and the movies sound amazing as well!!!

title: Great quality build and sound and fit
content: I cannot say enough good things about this product. I have been very happy even though this was a refurbished item. The quality seems top notch. I really enjoyed the rechargeable case. I also really like how small they are and how comfortable they are to wear when I work out. I don't go running but I could imagine it would be problematic if it fell out of your ear because it would be hard to find. Overall the sound quality is great although I prefer a bit more volume this product has been good for my ears for not going too loud.

title: not happy as yet ,..
content:
It's now been several weeks with this product..
The good is that the sound quality is much better than most I have used before.
The comfort is good and for me can be enhanced with the comply ear tip ..the silicone that is supplied can cause discomfort over long use .

The Very BAD ... is that this noise cancelling as advertise does not seem to work .
You are able to reduce the noise around you etc..however it's all amplified to your recipients.  They all complain about every sound in my background being amplified.
So too I can hear their background noise way above them .
I have reached out to Jabra that has ask me.to reset ...having done all they ask it's the same ..additionally it has connectivity issues seconds at a time with phone in my hand .

In the end the only resolve from Jabra is that I send back to dealer for replacement..sad ..
This earbud is NOT worth the cost ... its ordinary.

title: Amazing!!! I use them daily
content: Absolutely love these. They are amazing. Seriously, 100% worth it. I use these at work all the time and people often don’t know I am using them visually or audio wise over Skype. Music sounds great. I love the auto connect to two devices and the seamless switching between both devices. Can’t recommend these enough

title: AVOID!  Background noise makes these unusable in most environments go with Airpods.
content:
I got these because Apple Airpods won't always stay in my ears.  These stay in my ears.  That's about all the good I can say about them.  I switched back after about three weeks of trying to use these.

I tried using them on the train, and it was hard to get people to hear me over the background noise.  I basically had to scream into the microphones in order to be heard.  Needless to say, I could not do that on the train, and it is not appropriate in most other environments.  Before I got these, people had no trouble hearing me through the Airpods that these replaced when I was riding on the same train.  Same thing happens in restaurants or other public places.

Basically, the only place these wind up working well are in a very quiet place.  That would be your own private space (like your office or your home) or a library, where you shouldn't be talking anyway.  Gee thanks.

Also, these do not connect consistently, and sometimes they stay connected to the device after you hang up the call, thus draining the battery even more quickly.

title: Great product
content: One of the best Bluetooth buds around

title: Could've been better but I'm very happy
content: Overall this is a great piece. Make sure to contact Jabra customer support with any issues you have they are very helpful and there are many settings or features you may not know about and think you have an issue. Id highly recommend these earbuds and would tell you to contact Jabra with any questions and you are in good hands.

title: great headphone, horrible case/charger
content: I purchased these in December, less than a month later I had a "purple light of death" on the charging cash(wouldnt charge/recharge). Amazon was amazing and worked out an exchange and I was happy. Fast forward 4 months and the same exact thing occurred only this time it was past the return/exchange time-frame and I was left to deal with Jabra. I jumped thru all their hoops and sent in pics and proof of purchase and they finally sent me another "charge case", were back in business. You would assume that the story ends here, it doesnt! Less than a month after getting my replacement charger the exact same issue all over again, more pics, more proof of purchase, more drama! Now I ask Jabra for a refund, I think I've been patient and their response was "you'll have to talk to Amazon" and they offer to send a replacement set . I agree to the replacement set (no real choice as they wont refund my money), but I have to send back the broken set and "wait for the process" only this time, I get an email that says "these are on back-order and you should have your buds in 3-4 weeks". I call Jabra again and now i'm offered a different color that "might be in stock", but was told in no way was I getting a refund. Bottom line, buyer beware.

title: Was working awesome
content: Love these things but now it sounds like the  hear through speaker maybe blown it sounds static when someone talks to me or a sound happens

title: No regrets!
content: Great sound, stay in pretty well (rarely pop out.) I have a hard time fitting buds to my ears with most brands, so none are perfect. Sound is great even on calls. People say they can hear me fine too. Very happy with purchase.

title: Use what's good for you only
content: I  love it I am using to listen music and talking on the phone

title: Like these so far
content:
They connect very easy to the phone.  I love the outside sound pass through feature.  Normally, when wearing ear buds, I need to hear what is going around me.  There is a setting for them to not block outside noise.

The noise cancelation is passive (bud plugs ear and thus blocks sound).

Comfort seems pretty good and they stay in ears very well.

title: Great sound
content: Great sound.  Has to adjust the rubber ear thingys a few times until I was able to get a decent fit.  Follow the directions to help with proper sealing in your ear canal.

title: Using functions becomes uncomfortable
content: Sounds great but if you try and use the functions on the actual ear bud to change a song or something it will push it into your ear and it becomes painful. So I just use my phone for the functions.

title: Stay put in ear
content: Not as much bass as I’d prefer, but the sound is not too bad.

title: Great when they work. But then they stop working.
content:
I've gone through three pairs of the non-active Elite 65ts in the last year- two new, one refurb. Used them daily (non-exercise, just commute, while doing chores, etc). After 2-4 months every single pair had the same problem- the left bud would stop sending audio from the phone- sometimes it was still connected and could control volume but no audio 90% of the time.

When they work, they work great. Lots of options for fit, and when I found the right size, they stayed in the ear and were fairly comfortable, and they isolated sound well (not active noise-cancelling, make sure you understand the difference). HearThrough is a great feature and easy to toggle quickly. But then they stop working. Three times with three different sets of buds and cases.

Just ponied up for the Sony WF-1000XM3 which are expensive, quirky, bigger (especially the case) and I'm not a fan of the lack of volume control. But man do they sound great and have impressive noise cancelling capability.

title: Great in ear wireless headphones
content: I was not sure of getting this, matter of fact, getting any in ear headphones I don't like them much. I use Sony's 300$ on ear headphones amazing sound. This Jabra tho cuts the outside noise and provides great quality sound. I've been using it couple days with a single charge of battery case and itself. Recommended!

title: Getting That Elusive Missing Bass + Comfort
content:
These given to me as a gift bought from another retailer.

At first I was tragically disappointed in the bass even after using the in app equalizer, but then I decided to try the different ear buds and when I tried the large ones a magical thing happened, the bass truly appeared. Now they sound great! I also re-tweaked the EQ (see photo). They also do an ok job (not great) of blocking outside sounds

Comfort is o-k. Like a 6-7 on a scale of 1-10, but once I've had more time to wear them I may edit this. The best trick I can offer to get good comfort is to suggest you don't over-rotate them into position - rotate just enough to get a good seal. In other words as you rotate the mic towards your mouth (clockwise in L ear, counter-clockwise in R ear), don't over do it.

Also a tip on opening the case -- pinch the sides just below the hinge line then pull open with other hand, very easy.

title: Great as long as your phone is in the open
content: These ear buds are great with sound, battery, and staying in your ears. But the Bluetooth really sucks. I'll put my phone in my pocket while I walk and the music will cut in and out. Apart from that I really like how they work and all the features they have.

title: Great earphones for travel and exercise
content: Love it. But they fall off when not inserted properly.

title: Great earbuds but too big for me.
content: Great headphones, the only reason I gave it 3 stars is because the bigger part of the earbuds that should sit on your outer ear does not fit my ears. After wearing the earbuds for over an hour, my ears start to get sore.

title: Terrible static / cuts off on left ear
content:
Updated firmware through the Android app. Phone sitting 18" from my face. The left ear cuts off constantly for a fraction of a second.

If I connect to my laptop, which is also 18" from my face, and I turn my face to the left (so the left ear if away from my laptop) the left ear drops audio constantly.

For the price I would have expected something better.

title: Is there a better true wireless earbuds???
content: I am impressed with the sound,fit and the quality of the unit...I use it for listening to music and phone calls while working out or traveling back and forth on bus or subway...hopefully it will last.

title: Good
content: Great but mostly for men I think

title: Poor fit
content: Tried these for 5 months and never got to for well. Sound is not very good. But comfort it horrible and they fall out repeatedly if not repeatedly adjusted...wish I had returned first day...too late now. Should have given up on them sooner.

title: Hab
content: I own over 8 true wireless ear buds.  By far these are the best in every way.  From sound quality, comfort, battery life and much more.  Love the Jabra app and adjustments you can  make including the equalizer.  I lost one of them and was able to purchase 1 earbud which paired automatically.  Would highly recommend

title: Did not work after 3 months
content: Lost battery power quickly and stopped working completely even after charge for 3 months. Never dropped them and took care of them but they stopped working.  Not worth the money.

title: Absolutely stellar
content: The audio quality is good for music and calls. Mic works extremely well. Hear Through feature is great. Bluetooth pairs seamlessly and automatically when the earphones are taken out of their case.

title: They're no AirPods but are better in some ways
content:
Love that volume is adjustable.
Charging case is a little bulky and feels cheap, don't love the clip on the lid.
Other than that I love them, sound quality is amazing, buttons and functions are intuitive.
So far haven't figured out how to only have left earbud in (single operation right only). But perfect for working out and isolation from sound.

title: Kinda peeved
content: This is what came in the order of my headphones. Kind of hard to listen to anything out of these. Tried to get these as a gift for my wife. After talking to a guy that I could barely understand for about 15 minutes he said they would send me a real pair. They ended up sending me a replacement pair, but not in time for the celebration of her birthday. Felt pretty jack ass when she opened up a box of wires that had nothing to do with the headphone advertised on the box.

title: Great wieless earbuds, not great earbud tips
content: Overall these are the best earbuds / earphones I've ever used.  They hold a good charge, the dock/case charges them quickly, and even with sweat on them I just rinse them off quickly and dry them and they are good to go.  The only complaint is the same one I've seen others say about these: the tips they use on the ends....they are not comfortable at all.  Picked up a set of "Comply Sport Pro" tips and now they are super comfortable for hours.

title: Works with iPhone but does NOT pair with Apple Watch
content: I was hoping these would be a nice change from AirPods. Paired easy enough with the iPhone, but have been trying to pair them with my Apple Watch all morning and they just wont. Everything is updated, have the app, etc. etc. I'm not a tech dummy. LOL The Apple Watch (yes fully updated) sees the 65t's but they simply will not pair. Time after time, all it shows is "Not Paired".  Any ideas on how to make this work, please reply/comment. Guess it's a return and back to AirPods. Having things "just work" (and simplicity) is so much better than maybe a fraction of a difference in sound quality. Did like the snug fit of the Jabra's, but if they do not work the Watch... then what's the point.

title: Worth the $$
content: Luv, luv.

title: Awesome earbuds, would buy again at full price
content:
I bought these a year ago and have not had any issues. I love these earbuds, they're super tough and I use them all the time for indoor cycling, lifting, sitting around at home or work, on the bus, etc. I've dropped the case with buds in it probably 5 or 6 times now and it's still going strong.

I haven't had any "left ear static" issues either. I use a OnePlus 6 so maybe it depends on what phone you're using.

The call quality is average, but I admittedly didn't care about that when buying this. I can hear people just fine, but they say I sound a little distant, idk. They can hear what I'm saying and that's good enough. It's not like I'm leading conference calls or anything super important like that anyway.

Anyway, just thought I would leave this review to cancel out some of the negative.

title: Great earbuds for everyday use not so great for "active" use
content:
Got these earbuds a few days back and love the sound quality. There are noise-canceling features and a feature that eliminates that to help you be more aware of your surroundings. Perfect for my commute, listening at work, and taking calls on the go. When I tried running with these, which was the whole purpose of my purchase, I was less than satisfied. I went on three runs to test out each of the bud sizes and none of them created a secure enough lock to keep them from falling loose. Had to stop my runs each time to snag the fallen earbud, which as a runner, is infuriating.

TLDR: great buds for everyday use, terrible for intense activities

title: Going back to semi wired Bose Sound Sport
content: The controls are on the side of the earbuds, vs. the top for my last pair (Bose Sound Sport). Adjusting volume is near impossible without some discomfort. You have to push into your ear, shoving the earbuds deeper into the canal and/or putting more pressure on the ear itself. I found it very uncomfortable, and not very practical. I am returning them.

title: Awesome Jabra Elites!
content: I purchased these for my husband for Christmas 2018. They have not disappointed us in the least! He uses them on a daily basis. The fit is fantastic and the sound is stunning. He is able to take phone calls for work and such and the calls come through crystal clear. These earbuds are a great buy. My guess is that they will last a long time.

title: Are you kidding me?
content: After reading various tech reviews I decided to give these a try.  I've been using AirPods that sound great, fit great, but look a little goofy.  I thought these earbuds would be an upgrade.  I was astonished at the tinny sound and poor fit.  Maybe it's just my ears, but the Jabra's aren't in the same league as the AirPods.  Returning.

title: DO NOT BUY THESE
content: Listen. The sound quality is fantastic. Easily the best sounding earbuds I've owned. Battery life is great. The case works. They're not uncomfortable as some reviews have said. Yadda yadda yadda. BUT. As some people have pointed out the left bud is bad. After only 1 week of use my left earbud has a problem with static and doesn't maintain the connection to my phone. I'm returning mine and waiting for the new Airpods to come out. Save your money. These are waaay too expensive to have them give out after 7 days of use.

title: Fall out of your ears!
content: I can’t get them to stay in with any earpiece just walking around my house. I tried to get tech support, they were worthless, unsympathetic and unhelpful.

title: Not bad
content: Not bad

title: Four Stars
content: They stay pretty well, but do fall out of my ears. Rest is good.

title: Worst Bluetooth Headset I’ve Owned.
content:
Worst connections problems of any Bluetooth earphones I’ve owned. I thought 5.0 would solve all the No device connected problems I’ve experienced with other (cheaper) 4.1-4.2 headsets but the 65T was worse. I’d get those messages while holding the phone in my hands. When you report problems to Jabra support they just blow you off. The second problem is the ear jells aren’t adequate to hold the ear buds in your ear. They lack the ear wings found on the Elite Active ear buds which would help to solve the problem of falling out of your ear.
As for the call quality it’s good. Just as good as my $10.00 ear buds that  you can find at a discount store. I also had a problem with the App installing completely. When you report any problem to support they just blow you off saying it works good on my phone. The app equalizer is nothing to brag about. If you have a iPhone it’s much easier to use the iPhone’s music equalizer to adjust sound levels. To conclude my whole experience with Jabra and the 65T has been a negative one, and I will never buy a Jabra product again.

title: Great product
content: I've been using these head phones for two months now and I'm so pleased with them though I had a bit of a rocky start.  At first I found turning the head phones on to be extremely cumbersome and like I couldn't push the button down on the left side.  It was so bad I thought I was going to return them but that only happened for the first few times before it stopped.  Now, as soon as I take them out of the case, both earbuds turn on automatically so I haven't had any issues sense.  I love these for hiking and generally running errands but haven't used them to talk on the phone so no clue how well they would do.  I've worked out a few times in these and have noticed that sometimes they feel like they're going to fall out but not sure if this could be fixed with one of the larger ear bud covers.  I work out in my garage so don't typically have to wear ear buds but if I had to work out in a gym every day then it could be problematic.  Overall very pleased with my uses for them.

title: Great while it lasted
content: Bought in May 2018. Left one died today 9/23/18. RIP. Past warranty. You'd expect for expensive ear buds they'd last longer or have a more confident warranty.

title: Great quality but NOT FOR SMALL EARS....
content: I love the quality of the sound and battery life. However, I have small ears and I have the darnest time keeping them in my ears without them hurting.  They fall out occasionally on the street and after few long hours of wear my ears are killing me.

title: Left earbud does not work after less than 24 hours.
content: Disappointing after having high hopes. Received the earbuds yesterday and the sound was good.  However, the left earbud is already not working after less than 24 hours. Disconnected the earbuds and reconnected to my iphone, but the left earbud still does not work. Called Jabra customer service who walked me through a couple of possible solutions, but the left earbud still did not work. Sending back to Amazon and requesting a refund.

title: They are the best
content: Best pair of earbuds I’ve ever owned, they have adjustable sound effects etc. they fit the every day lifestyle of anyone. I’m a drummer and they work perfect to drown out outside sound and when I’m talking to someone I can change it to we’re I can here everything that the person is saying and be able to have the best sound quality at the same time

title: Wrong color way for a premium price.
content: I ordered the Gold Beige color and did not receive that as the picture shows. I’m not going through the hassle of returning them, but paid a 20% premium to the cost of the titanium black model I received so was definitely ripped off. The charging case is maddingly difficult to open. The sound quality and passive noise reduction are excellent. Even with the largest silicon tip the left unit will not stay in my ear, YMMV. Overall a disappointment at this price point. I’m just going to give them to my son.

title: Was completely ripped off by Amazon (SCAM)!!!!!!!
content: So I bought a pair of these last week because I have been shopping around for wireless headphones and found that jabra 65t are the best headphones for my needs. Long story short I buy them for $140 dollars which is the standard price for them all across the board. I received them yesterday, everything appeared to be in order.  However, upon opening and testing them out, I noticed that the left earbud was making a really loud static noise. Assumed maybe I did not have them properly paired or maybe not fully charged. But after a few hours of trying to figure out the problem came to the conclusion that the left ear bud was defective. Could not get it to work with out a really loud static noise that could not be turned down. So second part of the story is that I go to exchange them and now they cost $90 more then when I purchased them. Now at $230, when you look at competing sites they are still only $140 and amazon told me that they can only refund me and not exchange. So now if I still want these headphones that I bought the extended warranty for, I will have to be an extra $90 dollars to do so on Amazon. If you ask me it seems like  a complete SCAM. 100% disappointed and 100% would not buy from amazon again in the same situation. Seems beyond convenient that they are not willing to exchange only refund.

title: Great purchase
content: Owned many pairs of headsets, this pair works with two phones, has many customizable options, works with Siri, you cantrol almost everything from the headphones themselves... worth the money x3.  With a two year warrant,  come on people

title: Lasted approx. 90 minutes before total failure. Second round lasted four months.
content:
Pairing was easy. So were the firmware updates. The sound quality was better than I expected given that they're bluetooth, but not as good as my RHA T10i's that these have replaced. Fit nice in my ears. They worked after initial pairing, put them in the case. Took them out of the charging case the next day and they immediately turned on and started communicating with my iPhone 7. Used them for about 90 minutes, put them back in the charging case. Went to use them the next day, and the right earbud will not respond to any inputs. The charging case says that it is fully charged (green LED), but it will not communicate with my phone or even reset (no LED illumination on right earbud no matter how long I hold the button down) to allow for re-pairing. Left earbud turns on and lights up both red and green per usual.

Have a replacement coming thanks to Amazon but will not be amending the 1 star rating until they prove they can last more than two uses.

Update, 9/24/18: Left earbud has failed. Absolute garbage product. DO NOT BUY

title: Open says a me!
content: They sound great. However, opening up the case is an absolute pain. And it's the only way to charge them. If you can get past the case/charger then you'll have the best sounding wireless earbuds on the market.

title: Hard to find a better pair of earbuds.
content: These absolutely destroy AirPods in sound quality and noise suppression. So much so, I feel bad for people I see still wearing and trying to use AirPods. Apple will never get it. So I recommend to get these.

title: Great product!!
content: OK. After having the Jabra elite 65 for almost 2 months I can feel comfortable to write a review. Well this is an amazing product. Start with the bads: my biggest fear is to loose them! And no matter how snug they get in your ear they can easily fall from a slight unaware touch. The microphone is good for conversation but it catches all noises around as well.. Regarding the hold in the ears, they hold good but I won't feel comfortable runing with them above a street grating or something.. That's the bads.. Now goods: looking great! The material is high quality even the case. Sound is the best I heard for a wireless earbuds. The control buttons and app are wonderful! Battery life is a non-issue, I charged them over night and never ran low with a lot of music and conversations on a daily basis.

title: Love my Jabras!
content: Like everything I purchase  that I feel is an investment, I do a lot of research first.  The Jabra ear buds came out on top in all the interviews and articles I read. And I am happy to say they live up to the hype.  These are really great earbuds...In sound and comfort.  I especially like that I can take my left one out and still listening to my music or audiobooks with one in my right ear. And the battery life is really great too.

title: Amazing Product
content: At first was hesitant to purchasing these of AirPods. Am so glad I chose these. Sound quality is 10/10. Calls amazing. They are so comfortable and secure in my ear too which I was worried about. Can’t go wrong with these

title: Five Stars
content: Best earbuds I've ever had. Worth every penny! Comfortable, good sound and very functional.

title: Worst noise cancellation, worst call experience
content:
1- Worst noice cancellation ever, during calls I get only complains about how noisy it is and then am forced to use my phone directly instead of the my expensive Jabra 65t.
2- Very poor case, not easy to open or placr your earbuds and not protected from falling at any time you open the case.
3- Not comfortable the have them on for a long time.

title: DO NOT BUY
content: This is a rip off. The product does not work. The instructions were so brief they were laughable, they would not pair, and the online support knew nothing above basic problem shooting. DO NOT BUY

title: Great ear buds!
content: Great set of ear buds. Worth the money, and better than the Bose. They fit in your ear not on them. No problem for running or movement activities

title: Best true wireless solution for my specific scenario
content:
For my specific use (Cellphone and PC at the same time) these are great, sound is just good and calls are crystal clear in both ends (I tried the skype test call to test mic quality and it sounded great), I've not had any issue so far (almost 1 year of use) and the overall feeling and looks is high quality and good crafted, except on carrying case which after some time could feel flimsy and fragile.
The only cons for me are:
The voice that alerts you of battery low is too high
You cannot change ear gels, I used to use comply but those does not fit these earbuds.

title: Gre sound quality
content: Fast connection and great sound this product is one of the best .

title: Best Wireless Earbuds Around
content:
I have a few Jabra products and these new wireless earbuds are my favorite thusfar!. When I first put them in, I was a bit worried they would fall out my ears but I had no problems whatsoever. In fact, after a few minutes I had forgotten they were there.  The sound quality is amazing but I had no worries in that department, with them having the Jabra name.
The set up was super simple and let us talk about the battery life for a second. 5 hours of battery life and 15 with the charging case!  Now that is what I am talking about!
If you are looking for quality wireless earbuds, I HIGHLY recommend these!  I will be purchasing a second pair for Father's Day, my husband will be happy and will hopefully stop stealing mine!

title: Good sound quality, phenomenal battery, ehh fit
content: The sound quality is great, the app is great, the battery is > 15h it advertises (I've been seeing like 20 or 22 hours) and the noise cancelling + hear through is awesome. BUT BUT BUT the fit is meh at best. It took me a while to play around with them to make sure they don't fall out but on my 2nd day I had them fall out on concrete and get a bit scratched. I also don't trust them to be in my ear for long exercises so I adjust them every now and then. Also when using the on-board buttons, to avoid pushing them further into your ear, I would suggest holding them with one finger (or two, like middle finger and thumb) and using your index to hit the button.

title: These hurt my ears.
content: I really wanted to like these, but I can't get past the fact that they hurt my ears.  The sound quality is very good, I will say that. If they didn't hurt me, I would definitely keep them.  I'll be returning them.

title: Look no further
content: Love them , can’t be happier. They fit snug , cant hear anyone or anything around me even as low as 4 on the volume .

title: Good while it lasted (not long)
content:
It was good, while it lasted (not long)...

Within a month of buying them (and not heavily using them) the left ear piece gave out... Stopped charging, disconnected continuously, absolute pain! Contacted Jabra support, got an email once a week. So after 10 days of use (on and off) and 20 days of it sitting in a drawer waiting for emails to figure out how to fix it, I returned them to Amazon directly.

Thank you Amazon, no thanks Jabra.

title: AUDIO IMBALANCE
content: Audio imbalances. Right ear bud has much lower volume than the left one. Did not expect this flaw from such a popular brand like Jabra

title: Right earbud stopped working after only 3 months
content: Sound quality is fine. Everything about the earbuds is fine but the quality is total garbage. My right earbud stopped working after only 3 months. At first it got very quiet compared to the left one then it just stopped putting out sound all together. The right is the main earbud so I can't even use the left on it's own

title: Works well
content: Had to re-set the headphones when the left stopped working. Otherwise, they work well.

title: Great Sound and extremely easy to set up!
content:
I have tried many different pairs of wireless headphones. By far these are the absolute best. They truly set up with the push of just one-button and the sound
Quality is fantastic. What really sets these headphones apart from many of the other ones I have tried which includes air buds from Apple is the app that is available via free download that allows you to control and fine-tune the settings all from your phone. If you are thinking about purchasing these don't hesitate they are worth every penny of the price and there is a huge difference between these and the knock-off brands that run 50 $60 you won't be disappointed.

title: Was almost scared off from the negative reviews
content:
I heavily researched this pair of earbuds before finally making the purchase. Lot's of talk about the microphones not picking up a user's voice, the left sounding louder than the right, a constant hissing sound. I waited a month before posting this review and I can say that my experience has been none of the above.

I ride my bike to work every day. I have made calls while riding my bike. With a winter hat over the microphone. Have never had a problem with the person on the other end hearing me.

Sound quality is astounding. Ran multiple speaker tests and are near in sound range that is capable from my Audio Technica M50x. Obviously not the same in bass and sound movement, but pretty darn close for a pair of buds that have no wires.

They connect very easily to both my phone and my work laptop (windows 10 DELL). The range that I can move from the computer is astounding. Have taken walks around the office with no dropping incidents.

The sound quality issues I mentioned above almost scared me away. I have heard heard hissing at times, but only after I reconnect the left after just using the right. But the hissing goes away after less than 60 seconds.

I read that the Jabra app might be causing these audio issues, and i chose to not download and risk a drop in quality. I've had zero issues since and I would advise skipping the app as well.

Overall very happy with the pair. Hopefully they will last a few years before biting the dust.

title: I love them!
content: They work great, sound great, and fit great! I mostly use these for talking on the phone and listening to video clips while my baby is sleeping in my lap. The only thing I dislike about them, is that I can’t listen with only the left earphone. I still love them though

title: Constant audio dropouts 😠 earbuds sound unbalanced
content: First off let me say these are really good earbuds. They check off so many boxes like good battery life, good sound quality, secure fit, adjustable music equalizer and and an app that has many features like hear through mode. Also call quality is pretty good and better than most other earbuds. There dust and water resistant IP55 or IP56 if you have the active version, and there pretty comfortable (especially if you use the comply foam tips). They also look really good particularly the active version, I really like the matte finish. The charging case is small and easy to fit in your pocket although I wish it was USB-C instead of micro USB, and it would of been nice to have the earbuds magnetically secure in the case. The controls are nice and simple, volume up and down on the left earbud as well as touch and hold to skip or go back to previous tracks. Tap once to play or pause music and answer or end phone calls on right earbud, tap twice to enable or disable the hear through feature, and tap and hold to trigger your voice assistant. I really like the hear through feature, and sound quality is pretty damn good. SO.... You may be asking your self why I gave these earbuds only a 3 star rating after all of the positive things I had to say... Well the big DEAL BREAKER for me is the persistent, constant, frequently audio dropouts. Now if I didn't have this problem I would have easily gave these earbuds a 5 🌟 rating. Even though they are Bluetooth 5.0 im constantly getting audio dropouts. And I also started having issues with the left earbud being lower in volume than the right earbud. It's inconsistent, sometimes they will be well balanced and other times it will happen again. I recently bought a brand new pair of the active 65t version and experienced the same issue with the Bluetooth stability. When I'm walking the music will cut in and out at least every 15 to 20 seconds which completely ruins the listening experience and it really frustrates me because I really wanna love these earbuds, however I paid 200 bucks for this product and the audio dropouts are just unacceptable. If Jabra could fix this issue with a software update or something I would gladly give the elite 65t a 5 🌟 rating..... But in the meantime I'm just waiting for the Power Beats Pro... 9 hour battery life, great sound quality and most importantly... GREAT BLUETOOTH STABILITY.  Fix this Bluetooth connection issue 😡 Jabra you have a great pair of earbuds don't let this issue ruin your image.  UPDATE 6/9/19: As I mentioned above these earbuds have so much potential. The sound quality is ok, although the bass could be improved. Mids and highs are pretty good. But like I said before the constant audio dropouts are so frustrating I just wanna take these stupid earbuds off and throw them against the wall. I realized that even when the phone is in my pocket I still get dropouts. It's even worse when the phone is in my left pocket, the music completely stops. I shouldn't be experiencing these issues with a pair of 200$ earbuds. And apparently Jabra isn't doing anything about it. I CAN'T WAIT FOR THE POWER BEATS PRO TO COME OUT SO I CAN LISTEN TO HIGH QUALITY SOUND AND HAVE GREAT BLUETOOTH STABILITY

title: 6 reasons to buy or not buy it
content:
3 reasons to buy it:
* fantastic quality sound and the bass is very good.
 * Elegant design .
* Application is distinctive and has many characteristics.

3 reasons to not buy it :
* Not comfortable for ear and painful for long time.
 * Earphones are not touching just buttons.
 * Clipboard is not magnet and does not have type c.

title: Poor Battery Life
content: I thought the sound quality could be better but my main beef with these earbuds is the battery life. It doesn’t last for the amount of time advertised and the charging case sucks. I put my earbuds back in the case to charge and wouldn’t you know it, 4 hours later they were still dead. I checked the battery on the charging case and it was fully charged. So unhappy with these and they are not cheap. I expected better quality

title: Works great - works well for business calls, and has no dropouts
content: I've used the Jabra 65T for a couple of weeks now.  It works great in all settings and is the best bluetooth I have used for business calls.  I have had no dropouts, disconnects, static on calls.  They fit well in the ears and are comfortable and work great when running.  I have bought and own a number of different bluetooth devices including Bose, and B&O.  B&O is better for music, but has so many hiccups on calls (people can't hear me, static) that I have stopped using them - issues are usually when battery is dieing.  The 65T are a highly reliable and stable product.

title: Look somewhere else
content: I have had several ear buds and these are the worst. They are the most uncomfortable and can actually hurt after about 15 minutes of use regardless of what size you exchange the ear piece for. The sound quality is average and everyone else was right about the bass. They also have a tendency to connect and disconnect a lot or on some occasions not connect to another bluetooth device at all. Was very disappointed in these and I don't think I will be investing in another Jabra product.

title: The reviews are true.
content: This product is absolutely fantastic. I purchased these over Apple Airpods due to reading numerous reviews online. I am not disappointed.

title: Hear Through feature is a bust
content: I got them for the hear through feature so I could use while I’m at work. They definitely don’t allow you to hear people around you. It picks up noise a bunch of background noise but it’s terrible with voices

title: Get your self a pair of these and lose the Airpods.
content: These have become my go to earbuds for the gym. My airpods don't see much use now that I have these. These seal the outside noise so much that it's like having noise cancelling. Airpods don't do that at all even with tips I bought to get a better seal that you have to put on and off each time. Do yourself a favor and just get these. Less conspicuous, great fit, great sound. Battery life is amazing.

title: Mala experiencia
content: Despumes de un mes de uso el audífono derecho dejó de sonar.  Los audífonos se caen si estas haciendo ejercicio.

title: Some of the best earbuds out there!
content:
Likes: Good sound quality. Good fit. Good battery life (about 8hrs at mid/low volume). Works very well as headsets for phone calls, too.
As for volume and battery life: That of course is dependent on your liking? With the good fit I found I didn't need to have the volume up to hear my music while working in a fairly noisy place. But if you like to blast your ears the volume will do it, but I am sure the battery will not last near as long.
Also, they have a ambient noise bypass. which is they will let other noises through so you can hear things around you.
Dislikes: Well don't really have any. Some might say they are to pricey but I say you get what you paid for. I have had other cheaper earbuds that just sucked in some way. Could have been low volume, or poor fit, or piss poor battery life.
Well with these you wouldn't have to worry about any of those problems.
IMO they are well worth the price.

title: Survived a wash cycle at the laundromat
content:
Update: 1/2/2019- These earbuds still work along with all the buttons, it pauses when I remove one and resumes when I put it back in the ear. The charging hub still works as well and I don't find  myself needing to charge them as often. I've used it multiple times for phone calls. My husband recently purchased one over Thanksgiving and is also very happy with the overall sound and quality.

I accidentally left these in my shorts which went in the wash for a cold 30 minute cycle. I’ve only owned these earbuds for 2 months!! I thought these were done for. I figured I’d try charging them in it’s compartment and the light came on. It charged fully and it’s as if the wash never happened...good job Jabra.

title: Earbuds do not work alone
content: Warning you can not use each earbud alone. This is so disappointing I don't want to wear both earbuds at the same time for work purposes. You can only use the right earbud alone therefore for defeating the purpose of having two for my particular case.

title: They are great
content: Got tired of my beats n over ear headphones and I'm glad I did so these are way more comfortable and easier to get around.

title: Great ear buds, but not for those with small ears.
content: These earbuds were really nice, the connection to my iPhone was instant, I also really like the auto pause feature. The only thing is even with the smallest silicone piece for the buds they were still to large for my small ears. I could only wear them for about 45 minutes before I had to remove them for a few hours. Other then that the sound was decent as well as the other features.

title: Phone calls
content:
These earbuds maybe good for some people but not for me.
I dont use them to hear music at all. so, sound quality is not a big interest to me.
 the most important thing is the quality of phone calls and that was the only reason that made me buy these earbuds as jabra announced that with 4 microphones these earbuds cancel the ambient sound near you so the other part you're talking to would only hear your voice and not get distracted with other noises.
Actually thats not what happened!! I used these for only 2 days and everyone I've talked to complained that they cant hear me clearly because of the noisy sounds near me.
Im not saying they are bad. They are good but the thing that make these earbuds unique "phone call quality" actually dont exist.

Over all:
1)Sound quality is very good but not compaired to bose sound free (although, better than most of the true wireless earbuds in the market)
2) design is great but not suitable for people with small ears.
3) microphone quality is good unless ur in a noisy enviroment.
4) connection: good but, sometimes the left bud dont connect so you will need to put it back in the case, close the case and re-open it and take it back (not a big deal for me but other people might not like it)
Over all 7/10

*update*
Used them in the gym and when I sweat the earbud will loose its seal so you will need to push it inside your ear again every now and then.

title: Started out great, now not working.
content: These worked great for a few months, now the left one barely puts out any sound. There is no balance adjustment in the app, and the latest firmware update did nothing. I don’t recommend buying these, unless you get them for half off, that way when one stops working (and it will, just do a web search), you are getting your money’s worth.

title: 1 Day and I'm returning
content:
I was interested in purchasing a pair of wireless ear buds and I am a fan of Jabra so why not buy these.
Pros:
1. Noise cancellation is top notch.  It does a great job at drowning out surrounding nose.
2. Sound quality is amazing.  My music and videos sound great.  My calls were clear for both myself and the person I called.
3. Very easy to connect to my phone.
4. Easy to use (volume and disconnecting a call)

Cons:
1. THEY ARE NOT COMFORTABLE!  I was concerned because there are no ear hooks and they just sit in your ear.  You have to twist them to make a snug fit.  My ear aches after just one day of use.  Actually not even a full day.
2. While the sound quality is great I'm concerned that they will damage my hearing because they are in your ear vs. sitting on your ear.  I actually have a slight ringing in my ear that has not gone away.
3. They have fallen out multiple times.  I have twisted them as instructed but they began to loosen and I subconsciously tilt my head to try to hold them in.

I will be returning these.

title: Better than air pods by far
content: Amazing earbuds , these replaced my air pods, they are much better than air pods, good quality and great sound , best wireless buds out there rn

title: Simple to set up and they STAY IN when I run - So happy!
content:
I've been running for over a decade and have used many types of headphones.  I've always been afraid of wireless because I worried they would fall out and get lost.
I got these for Christmas and I am impressed.
1. First, and most importantly, they don't fall out when I run.  I have done 6 runs and they haven't fallen out once (after I figured out left and right, see complaint #1 below).
2. The sound quality is really good - not 'superb' like with my indoor headphones for music, but for sports headphones they are very clear.  I can choose to hear 'surrounding noises' when I run outside but turn that feature off when I run inside on a treadmill.
3. The App is easy to set-up and use on my phone.  I'm not great with tech and even I found it really simple.
4. I love that I can skip or repeat tracks without having to dig my phone out.  That is a big deal at the end of a long run when I just want to hear that one certain song that keeps me motivated.
I have two complaints:
1. It is hard (for me) to tell the left and right apart.  They will go in my ears either way, but if I get them backwards they will fall out after I start running.  There is a small 'L' and 'R' on them but with my eyesight I can't see it.  I'm going to put a drop a nail polish on one to tell them apart easier.
2. The case is hard for me to open with my older hands.  I have had to get someone to open the case for me every time so far.  I am hoping it will get easier after some uses.

title: Good Ear buds but concerns with sound quality/comfort
content: I got these and tested them for 2 weeks. Overall great experience no lip sync or video lag issues. My only gripe was that because they sit and block your ear canal I could not use it for more than 45 min (heats up/discomfort) I tried all sizes. Sound quality is good but I did a small test with my old apple wired earbuds and immediately I could tell the difference. The equalizers seems to me are just for show..base boost is not really base boost you can play around but nothing really changes.

title: Excellent Bluetooth connectivity
content: Comfortable to wear and easy to control while they’re in use

title: Buzz in left earbud
content: The audio is fine and the app is good but there is one major problem that ruined it all for me. After about 1 hour of use I began to notice that there is a buzz in the left earbud, it is always there weither you are listing to music or watching a video or not playing any audio at all. It is incredably anoying. I spent to much money on this to go through the hastly of tring to get a replacement or spend hours trying to fix. I tried to fully update the software to no avail. Ive seen many good reviews so maybe I just got unlucky. Another problem that is more minor and I could live with is that the case is somewhat difficult to open and to close it with the earbuds in they have to be in a specific position. Overall good sound and build but the buzz just ruins it 2/5. would be 4/5 without static

title: Controls from only one side, too bad
content: I don’t like that you control it in only one side

title: Best of all true wireless I've tried
content: I tried both Samsung Buds, the Bose sports, and JLs. These have MUCH better sound than Bose(which I dont understand, usually known for their sound quality, they were junk and required you share location access to use the app, no thanks). The Samsung Buds were ok, but not great sound and they started losing sound between the 2 buds fairly quickly, dropping out and the JLS were justdidnt seem like good quality. I am only a few days in on these and will update if anything changes but they're loud enough to deafen you if you like, have a great app, fit AWESOME, and the sound quality is the best I've tried.... Will probably buy their Sport edition just to have a second pair with heart rate monitor. Took months to find the pair for me.

title: A solid bluetooth wireless option
content: Overall I like these headphones and would recommend them. My only two qualms are it is hard to get a good fit for the best bass experience (they have to be way in your ear canal for bass to work) and they aren't all that comfortable if wearing for more than an hour or two. However, on the positive side, they pair easily, have a great app, sound great once the fit is right, and even work well with my Fitbit Versa when playing music, which is a rarity.

title: Okay for 2 months - then it doesn’t charge
content: This product is inherently flawed - the copper charging pins will corrode with sweat - and they will stop charging if you use them for running after a few months. The headphones are also not as waterproof or sweat proof as you would expect and at 3 months the left earbud no longer works - the biggest issue Jabra’s absolutely worst customer service - they maybe will respond or maybe not - and if they do you will have to jump through weeks and weeks of hoops to get any replacement. If you call their customer service be prepared to invest up to two hours on hold. The problem is with these flaws you will have to at some point contact their customer service so therefor their poor customer service is very relevant to this product review.

title: An Unhappy Marriage
content:
I want to love these headphones. I really do. I don't want to be another douchebag finance bruh with an airpod sticking out (literally) of their ears. It's a pain for me to walk to my midtown offices where you'll most likely see them powerwalk to their corner offices in their custom-made suits. I'm not about that life. So I decided to see what's out there.

Samsung? eh.. I do use a S9+ but I've never been a fan of their audio products. Bragi? seems too startup-y and worried about them not being around for too long.. Bose or B&O? seems like they're behind the curve with the 4.x bluetooth tech when 5.0 is available.. plus wasn't too sure about their water/sweat resistance considering my active lifestyle.. Jaybirds? I've used their "wired" bluetooth headphones but wasn't really feeling the look. So the only option left were the elite 65t and the active version and I chose the elite 65t simply because of the low-key colorway.

Setup
Pretty easy. I connected it to my Galaxy S9+ and 2 laptops and it was a breeze. Just a simple long-hold of the right side bud button and find it available on the various devices.

Fit
The small bud size that is equipped as the default wasn't creating a tight fit in my ears so at first, it sounded very air-y. after trying on the other earpiece options, I found that the largest one fit my ears the best and creates the ideal fit & outside-noise blockage.

Material quality
It's plastic. Everything's plastic. And I have no issues with that. One potential issue I see is with thin piece of plastic that holds shut the case. That thing was not designed to last so optimistically (opening & closing the case around 10 times a day), it'll last 2 years at most. I've learned to be very gentle in my approach.

Audio Quality
Very good. Companion app helps a bit with equalizing the low, mid, high (also you should probably download it to get the latest software updates). I generally listen to hip-hop, rock, classical and personally I think it covers the various genres very well. You really need to get a good fit in order to fully appreciate the audio drivers.

Day-to-day usage
Ok so here's where the story goes downhill and never recovers. Is it just me or is Bluetooth "5.0" just a blanket marketing term? In my old job, I've used Bluetooth 5.0 headsets (connected to PC) and walked around my office without dropping any audio (I actually went outside to the 1st floor just below my desk on the 5th floor and it still worked. amazeballs). I was expecting the same from these headsets. Instead the audio constantly skips when my phone is in my pocket. Ok.. maybe my pants are lined with some sweat-wicking materials that's interfering with the signals possibly? So i try on my suit pants (I don't wear full suits thankfully) to check and yup, still skip city. OK so I guess I'll just have to adjust my life to fit the needs of the phone and start holding it while walking (I do walk alot living in the city).. But nope. Still cuts in and out. It's a shame really.

Another thing that irks me is that whenever I take out my headset there's a very subtle static-y noise. It gives me a nice wake-up around 2pm when food coma kicks in tho.

Another thing that annoys me is that sometimes when I take the earbuds out and I don't take out the left buds quickly enough, the right earbud will connect by itself thinking that I'm going 1-bud for a phone call so the left bud won't work until I take out the right bud, put it back into the case, and take em back out quickly or at the same time. Annoying.

One thing I do love is the hear-through feature (enabled by double-pressing the right earbud button). I bike around the city often and being able to hear the cars, other bikes, and pedestrians is really helpful and got me out of possible accidents. However I'm never certain about the direction from which the sound is coming from so I essentially go into a Meerkat-like state and check all my periphery to see what's going on. I do think the soundstage (available in more higher-end audio equipment where various audio sources can be "placed" in different "spaces" to give a spacial effect) is a lacking feature and/or is too subtle to even be called a soundstage. A big miss in my opinion.

Battery life
It's ok. I get a good 5 hours per charge and the case can give another 2 charges so at least the battery life is as advertised. I haven't figured out the battery life indicator on the case yet but wish it was a meter rather than a blinking light but i'll learn to live with it.

Mic Quality
It's great. It has more mics than you'll ever care but it's honestly the one redeeming factor of the day-to-day experience. I'm constantly on a skype call through my phone or laptop and after testing it with skype's mic test & hear-back feature, I can say that the quality is top notch. I've used it with Google Assistant while hitting around 20mph on 8th ave in NYC and even with the wind-noise, cabs, etc. it worked flawlessly.

One annoying thing is that when it's connected to 2 devices and I'm switching from listening to spotify on my phone to getting on a call on skype on my laptop, it doesn't always switch consistently. Sometimes I have to disconnect it from my phone for it to be "dedicated" to the laptop but I've seen that happen on other bluetooth headsets so can't knock jabra too hard for that.

Conclusion
Overall, if you're sitting at your cubicle and want to isolate yourself from the world (but maybe listen in on the office gossips using the hear-through feature), it's great. If you're on the move constantly and can't afford to hold your phone close to your ears, it's a hit or miss.

title: Good quality
content:
Works very well easy to connect nice long lasting battery pack for convenience in charging on the go
One  quirk noise canceling feature for phone calls Icould be better not of high quality but not too bad needs improvement  if a must keep in mind when buying

title: I returned them because I have a very narrow ear canal
content: These wireless earbuds sound very good. I would have loved to keep them.  Unfortunately, the left earbud did not say in place. I have a very narrow ear canal in my left ear. I contacted Jabra to see if they could help me find a smaller silicone plug for the left ear but they didn't have suggestions.

title: Horrible, unresponsive support
content: My earbuds stopped working after a few months (no water damage or anything) and support would randomly stop responding to my emails, as well as never replying to my warranty replacement request. DO NOT BUY.

title: Had to return
content: Brought a used set ($77.00) and had to return them because the left earbud went out. I will buy a new set for about $125, they are very good earbud though.

title: Good sounding, but not a must-buy.
content: Good sound quality, but not satisfied with the noise cancling. Do not buy if your looking for good noise canclation. And after a couple off minutes of use, your ears get stiky and uncomfortable. They are though very secure and will never come off your ears. But overall, it has great sound quality and a great build design.

title: Headphones are great but Noise Canceling is misadvertised.
content: The headphone are great with great battery life, upwards of 5 hours. However, it says it have noise cancelling, which is false. It only isolates using the seal from the rubber, no active noise cancelling.

title: When they work they're amazing, but too often they do not
content:
These headphones are super hit and miss.  The sound quality, battery life, and comfort are all amazing.  I have used the Jaybird Runs and Airpods and think these destroy those across the board.

The problem I'm having is with sound cutting out, mainly in the left headphone.  At first I thought it was just my house as I have a ton of different wireless devices, but even in the wild I'm running into random pockets where there is some kind of interference that completely destroys the functionality.  The sound keeps clicking and then connectivity will continually go in and out.  I ride public transportation and will often have to go to different cars on the subway to avoid whatever is causing the interference.

I had initially planned to just deal with it, but I've had to swap them out for a back-up wired pair that I keep just in case  too many times at this point.  I had previously been using several generations of the Jaybird Xs and never had this issue, so it's disappointing that it's happening with this (more expensive) pair.

title: Poor fit.
content: Poor fit

The sound quality is so great that I’ve heard guitar lines in some of my favorite songs that I never picked on before.  That helps me when learning a song now and I can use the app to hear my guitar playing along with the song I’m listening to.  All-in-all I will never need another set of earbuds ever again!!

title: Better sound worse fit.

The initial pairing went great...phone calls no issue... caller couldn't even tell that I was using ear bud. Music sounds rich and full with good highs and lows. I highly recommend these.....Update.... having a slight issue at the gym with these.... they tend to want to fall out or at least loosen up when I'm grimacing during heavy lifting. Little annoying

title: Footsteps noise
