Anyway, it’s February and three weeks later they were still in the same place luckily no one got them. Through all weather conditions, rain and frost..sun and heat. These suckers survived to tell a true tale. I recommend getting a pair because lord knows they last!

title: Terrible mic. Dont hold a candle to airpods
content: Very disappointed in my jabra 65t all the reviews say how great the mic is and how clear you sound talking even outside. This is definitely not the case. The jabra 65t behave exactly like my 20$ mpow earphones I use for the gym. They make it sound like you are standing in the walkway of a stadium. The mic will pick up the music in Starbucks instead of your voice. If you want to experience what your caller hears turn on the pass through and all the ambient noise will be in your ear too. The fit is great. For music the sound is good and the noise canceling functions. I bought these specifically for conference calls and because jabra is supposed to be known for its mic technology. These things dont hold a candle to my wife's airpods and are definitely not worth the money. Android users should look elsewhere

title: Performs as advertised.
content: I have tried several earbuds and have not been satisfied with battery life or connectivity. The Jabra earbuds are fantastic.

title: My go to headphones for work and play
content: I wanted to wait until Summer to add my review.  Why?  I read the marketing hype about how the earbuds will stay in your ears even when working out, and how they were sweat and water resistant, but wanted a real-world test.  This Summer, as temps work towards 100 degrees plus, these earbuds have been my constant companion.  Whether blocking noise for work, listening to a podcast while cooking dinner (although the noise cancelling makes hearing the sizzle of my pans difficult), or turning over my garden, these earbuds are the best!  Great sound, unbelievable staying power in my ears, and easy instant-on Bluetooth connection.  A great set of earbuds!  Highly recommended!

title: Terrible audio quality
content: I'm so bummed because these actually fit my ears really well. The audio quality is something of a $5 headphones. They sound like they've been blown and there is a constant hiss when connected. What you read about the 0.5 second audio is also true - videos are unwatchable with this delay

title: Awesome sauce
content: These are awesome!

title: 9.5 out of 10 earbuds
content: Fantastic pair of truly wireless earbuds they do pretty much everything correct one downside I have about these earbuds is only one person can listen to music at a time you can't give your spare ear bud to your friend and listen to the music

title: Another great product by Jabra! A huge High Five in our book!
content:
Our family has lots of Jabra products, these earbuds are our newest addition and I love them. I workout 4 to 5 times a week and was a bit worried the fit would not be 100 percent for all the activity that I do, but, YAY, they are. The sound quality is superb for music and phone calls.
The battery life has not let me down and I use them a lot. For those who are not the best in keeping their products charged (like my husband) there is a rapid charge which gives an additional hour of talk time.
With Father's Day around the corner and all the graduations, this is a wonderful gift. My husband is getting these for Father's Day so I can stop scolding him for taking mine!
What about the price? For the quality of this product, it's worth every dime. If you're looking for a good, reliable, quality and comfortable product, it's right here!

title: Great sound, very easy to use
content: Great sound, very easy to use. Definitely a must buy if you love wireless listening. The Jabra 65t active is well worth the money,

title: Excellent sound. Owned Bose earbuds for years and was ...
content: Excellent sound. Owned Bose earbuds for years and was skeptical about the fit of these at first, but another review mentioned these were perfect for working out in (well worth the extra cost for the active model) and can confirm they stay in ear even when running. Sweating doesn't impact fit or performance. Had these for about a month and no connection or battery life issues. These look relatively good in ear if that is a dealbreaker as well compared to other true wireless that look bulky and stick out weirdly.

title: Definitely 5 stars
content: Definitely 5 stars

title: They do not work for long and have multiple issues.
content: I have had problems with these earbuds since I purchased this product. I have had issues with sound, right vs left, Alexa and just not working. I have done the troubleshooting with Jabra and they keep having me do a complete reset, which I have done several times. They worked with issues for about 4 months. I have been so frustrated I just went back to using my wireless Jaybirds that work fine. I have contacted the support several times and keep having same issues over and over without any offer of replacement. These were expensive earbuds.

title: Best True Wireless Earbuds!
content:
Amazing fit! They never fall out and they're super comfortable.  The sound is great too.  The app allows you to personalize your sound with an equalizer. Having the ability to adjust the volume level on the earplug instead of having to pull out your phone is great too.  And 5 hours of play time in a true wireless earbuds is unheard of, but Jabra has done it. When someone comes to my desk at work I pull one side out,  the music auto pauses, and when I put it back in the music starts right up where it stopped.
I have 5 other true wireless earbuds and these are, by far, the best.

title: Waste of money and bad product
content: I don't know where all these high ratings are coming from, these were a gift and I ended up switching these out for my $15 Bluetooth headphones. The left ear is permanently stuck at several levels lower then the right and I'm not sure why since they balance perfectly when first turned on and then plumet a minute or two after. The sound quality is nothing special and they do not cancel any noise coming in. I ride the train to work and can never hear any music even with the volume at full blast in my right ear. Even if they both worked I would have to damage my ear drums to be able to hear my music/podcast/audiobook. They are not incredibly comfortable either and will just pop out of my ear regardless of the size of ear cap I tried. These more match the quality of a bad knock off product than something over $150. I even allowed several updates to pass with no resolution and based on the online google searches I am not the only one to have these problems.

title: Would not recommend

Also the ear buds if your moving too much slip out of your ear guess you have to have a specific ear type. Plus they are pretty uncomfortable for the price I am truly disappointed.

title: Not easy to get them to stay in your ears
content: I was really excited to get these and had analysis paralysis for a long time before finally choosing the Jabra, based on the reviews.  Maybe my expectations were too high.  The sound quality is OK.  The technology to adjust volume and engage Alexa takes some getting used to and I'm still working on that.  My main problem is that I am having a very difficult time trying to consistently get these to stay in my ears.  I like to go running with these and, while they haven't completely fallen out yet, there have been a few times where they've come very close.  I reach up to check on them because the sound gets a little noisy and they're barely still in.  Maybe I'll get used to this and will provide an update.  However, I'm following the instructions about the best way to insert them and it just isn't snug enough for me.  Not bad, but just not what I was hoping for from earbuds intended for exercise.

title: Great item

title: Poor customer service
content:
Tl;Dr - mediocre product, terrible customer support, DO NOT BUY

I write very phew reviews on Amazon, but the poor quality of this product and the even worse level of customer support from Jabra warrants it.

I'll put it simply, do NOT purchase this product. The headphones are decent at best, and I'm not audiophile. My left earbud stopped working and Jabra continually ignored my requests for a return.

After sending numerous emails over a four week period, Im finally giving up. I will never purchase or endorse one of their products again.

title: Don't buy - earbuds failed in 2 months, warranty wasn't honored
content:
I'm extremely disappointed in these earbuds, the Jabra brand, and Jabra's customer service and strongly recommend that you do NOT purchase this product or another Jabra product.

My earbuds failed to work properly (right earbud volume was drastically lower than left earbud) within 2 months of purchase with normal use at the gym. After 2.5 months of back and forth with customer service (usually with a week between emails from customer service) - including filing a formal warranty claim - Jabra's customer service never sent me a replacement device. They also stopped responding to my emails entirely once I submitted the warranty claim. This includes me sending them two warnings that I would leave a negative comment on Amazon and file a claim with the consumer protection agency.

These earbuds worked for only 2 months and then Jabra's customer led me on for months before simply not responding. They never sent a replacement device either. Now I'm out $160+ for faulty earbuds that can't play loud enough or evenly to be heard on a treadmill. Save your money and your time - don't buy Jabra brand products.

title: Love them
content: I purchased these for my husband who absolutely loves them. The noise canceling is amazing yet if you are going to be in a place where you must hear the outside noise there is also a way to do that. The noise canceling is amazing yet if you are going to be in a place where you must hear the outside noise there is also a way to that thru the downloadable app. I researched many wireless earbuds before purchasing these and I am very pleased to say I am happy with my purchase.

title: Great earbuds for office or on the go, slightly disappointing sounds quality
content:
These earbuds are phenomenal when it comes to fit, convenience, design, reliability and microphone quality. I have been using them for about a week at work, leaving them in for long stretches and not once have I ever felt that they might fall out and they are surprisingly comfortable even using the standard silicone buds. The design is sleek and user friendly. Once they are connected to your phone the first time you are good to go, never needing to go through the hastle of pairing them again, at least with my Note 9 that's been the case. I haven't experienced any of the connectivity issues mentioned in other reviews (perhaps a firmware update has addressed this issue since those reviews were written.)

The only complaint that I have is that the sound quality is a bit lacking for the price range. I wouldn't expect these to compare to a pair of Sennheiser or Bose over ear headphones on terms of quality but at $170 I would expect them to at least be comparable to my Bose wired earbuds which only ran about $120.

If sound quality is the end all be all for you in a pair of headphones/earbuds I would reccomend sticking with something a but more substantial. Wireless earbuds just haven't gotten there yet, but if you are looking for something incredibly comfortable and very convenient then I would recommend these over any other product I have tried or owned including apple air pods which don't even compare to these even in terms of sound quality.

title: Jabra Elite Earbuds
content:
I've used several different brands of wireless earbuds.  I can't use a wired headset/earbuds with my phone and I'm pretty rough on products so they only last a few weeks with me.

I think these may be my favorite.  The fit is wonderful and the profile is discrete.  They don't poke out like many do (think Uhura on Star Trek's ear piece).  But star of this earbud set is sound.  Sound quality is really good.  No static or background noise.  I was able to sing to "Girl on Fire" with the window open going down I85 in Atlanta.

The biggest con is the battery life.  It lasts a day but I use them a lot.  I don't know if other similarly priced buds have the same battery life but I'm a bit disappointed given the cost of these

title: Get them, my dude
content:
Couldn't be much happier with these earbuds.

- They fit me perfectly, and don't fall out, even when running.
- I think they look pretty good - not too bulky like others I've seen.
- They don't sound as good as my Bose headphones, but they sound just fine.
- The case makes it super easy to charge the buds.
- I can hardly hear my environment even when they are on low volume.
- In the app, there is a HearThrough feature that let's you hear your environment a bit more. Works good enough.

The app also let's you adjust EQ, which is cool.

The only thing that would make these better for me would be longer battery life. They need to be charged for a bit during lunch to last throughout the work day. However, the battery lasts as advertised, so nothing surprising here.

title: Great earbuds but they won't reliably stay in my ear
content:
The earbuds tend to fall out if there is much activity or if they are not placed exactly right in the ear.  I’ve tried all the different sizes of ear adapters and read several descriptions of how to get a good fit and none provide a good fit that will stay in my ear.  I’m not an audiophile but the sound quality is quite good and much better than my previous Bluetooth earphones and better than the AirPods.  The equalizer in the app does help create a better sound profile.

They have some noise isolation but they are definitely not noise canceling headphones.  The noise isolation is largely dependent on how tightly they are in the ear canal which also has a negative impact on comfort.  Noise isolation is pretty good if they are deep in the ear but that makes them quite uncomfortable.  I’m not sure but the HearThrough option in the app seems to amplify/distort outside noise rather than remove it like active noise isolation does.  When turned on, it made the sound from lawn equipment sound really weird.  Either way, traffic noise, car horns, lawn and construction equipment can be heard quite well with or without HearThrough enabled.  This is quite different than the Bose noise canceling over the ear headphones that nearly completely block out computer fans and a distant car alarm (which was going off as I wrote this).

It is kind of nice to have the additional functionality associated with multiple buttons vs the Apple AirPods.  Still, it can be difficult to find just the right spot to change the volume or skip tracks.  Mostly it is easier to just pick up the phone than it is to remember which ear phone (right or left) is for volume and whether to tap or hold for the function you want.  Also, using the buttons can tend to push the earphone deeper into your ear which is not what you want to do.  Still, in some circumstances, this works well if you use it enough to remember which button and to hold it when pressing.

Due to the fact that the earphone’s noise isolation and sound quality are dependent on being buried deep within your ear, they are not nearly as comfortable to wear as the Apple AirPods.  I’ve worn them for a couple of hours so it isn’t bad but it is definitely not comfortable.  It would be really nice if they came with the extra clips to fit in the ear like the Jabra Elite Sport, but they are not worth the $50 difference in price.

The recharging case is a nice feature which allow you to recharge even if not tethered to power.  Also, storing the headphones in the case pretty much ensures that they are charged each time you use them (if properly inserted in the case).  The case can be difficult to open (I still struggle with this) and seating the headphone precisely in the case is important as one time I pulled the headphones out of the case and they were nearly dead because they didn’t recharge.  This is different than the AirPods that just drop into place in the case with no worry about making sure they are seated correctly on the connectors.  It is also really nice that they connect to the phone when you pull them out of the case so that by the time they are in your ears, you are connected rather than having to push a button and wait for the Bluetooth connection like my previous earphones.

One nice feature that I discovered is that when you get a call, you can simply say “answer” and it will take the call rather than trying to find the button to answer.

You can use these in the shower or in the rain (they are splash proof) but they tend to cut in/out.  My guess is that they are pausing and starting because they think you have removed them and reinserted them as the water splashes on your head.  Still, it was nice to see that the “rain” didn’t cause a real problem.

They almost always stay put in the ear (if properly embedded in the ear) when sitting at the computer or lying down but walking or bending over tend to cause them to get loose and running or other more active workouts cause them to fall out pretty regularly.  They also tend to fall out when you roll over if worn in the bed.  The worst is when you step off a curb and they fall out and bounce down the street.  Luckily this caused no damage and I don’t even see a scratch after this happened twice.  Now I’ve learned to hold my hand to my ear when stepping off the curb but I shouldn’t have to do that.

Overall, I’ve found that I like them much better than my previous set of $20 wire-between-the-headset Bluetooth earphones (but 6X the cost) but falling out of my ears may be a deal breaker.  It is still a tossup between the AirPods and the Jabra.  Jabra has better sound quality but the AirPods are more comfortable and fit easier into the case.  Between the Bose Quiet Comfort and Jabra, there is no comparison in sound quality, comfort and noise cancellation (Bose is in a completely different class) but these are much more convenient and tend to get much more use than the Bose for general use and just walking around.

title: Great product but bad support
content: These earphones are good but unfortunately, I received one with a defect.  My left earbud always disconnects whenever it is 3-5 cm away from the right one. Which renders it completely useless because obviously between the left and right ear are about 25-35 cm away from each other.  I called Jabra support and they never answer the phone, their support it is total trash.  It is a real shame because they made such a great product. Obviously, I will never purchase from this brand ever again. So if you want to buy this product I really suggest you go to the stores and test them out. Do not order these online.

title: Sound and work great, but...

At least 3 other people tried these with me, they all say that they could not hear me well at all calling with these. The other 3 people do not have deep tone and they sounded fine when they called with them. So the best guess is voice tone is an issue. BTW I have tried a few other True wireless buds, and most do not work well if you have a deeper voice tone. Only a guess, but maybe it's the noise canceling is the issue.

title: Issues with left ear bud(s) elite 65t
content: I gave three stars based on issues with the left ear bud(s). The first one died within a month. No problem, they sent out a replacement under warranty. When I lost the “new” left one a few months later, I purchased another left through Amazon. It came quickly but was very staticky and continually dropped in and out of sync with the right ear bud. Called customer service. the same day I received. Sat on hold for an hour. Rather than replace, I was told by Jabra customer service that I had to send both my latest defective left and my working right ear buds back and they would send a new pair. I use these for work and resisted since the right was working fine but was told they would cross ship as soon as the package was logged by UPS and should have them by within 4 days. Following up over a week later, and sitting on hold for another hour, I was told the previous customer service rep lied. They will not cross ship. The package has been received but not processed so it will probably be another week and a half before I get the replacements. Fingers-crossed that the left works....This is why I buy Apple products. If Apple had a noise cancelling version of the AirPod, I wouldn’t even bother.

title: Comfort is lacking

title: Excellent Connectivity
content:

This product is excellent and I am experiencing none of the reported issues. The connectivity to the phone is far greater than my expectations...I live in an old house with two foot thick brick walls and I can go anywhere in it and still have perfect clarity.

title: Great quality
content: After going through 2 pairs of Jaybirds in about 6 months a few years ago, I decided to switch back to tried and true wired headphones. After my last pair finally kicked the bucket, I decided it was time to upgrade. These headphones are definitely worth the upgrade! The batteries last several hours and the charging case let’s me go about a week between charging. The noise cancellation works well, although the hear-through (or whatever they’re calling it) tech still needs a little work. It works great sometimes, not so much other times. When bike riding, the microphones it uses pick up quite a bit of wind noise - to be expected - with running it isn’t so noticeable except on really windy days. The sound quality is excellent even at the higher volumes with good bass for such small headphones. You never realize how much your headphone wires get in your way until you get rid of them... big frustration saver during intense workouts. They can go up to about 20 yards when I’m inside the gym before cutting out too. Overall definitely recommend these headphones!

However it works great with single side mic when i am indoor in a totally silent environment, the quality is awesome for calls. Cant comment how it sounds for music as I dont listen to music but I would assume it is great for music and i do not have an issue with the speakers.

title: No problems.

title: Good but not if the right earbud cannot be replaced.
content: My first wireless earbuds were good experience. My walks to and from school became really great with NPR podcasts through the unfriendly U of Montana campus. Sound was ok relative to my Noble wired earbuds, and good compared to Koss Porta on the ears headphones. Bluetooth connectivity walking through the campus was erratic and frustrating. Nothing I did, a 2019 software update and fiddling with my iPhone XS Max would hasten a 100-200 yard walk with no sound. I lost my right earbud when it fell out just as I bent over a flushing toilet. My hand dove without hesitation into the water to no avail. I paid for another right earbud immediately without reservations. I expected to receive a replacement in 1 - 2 weeks maybe closer to 20 days after 3/24/2019 because it’s Missoula , MT. I started to write to them around 4/20/2019. After 4 communications including a pleasant and  quick connection to lady she assured me that I would be notified as soon as a right earbud shipped from China. I wrote 2 more times around 4/24/19 and the 4th email came around 4/26/2019. It said that there is essentially no time even after a month when a right earbud will be produced and shipped to me for the $49.99 I paid. That seems like a long delay. Well I’m starting to look elsewhere including buying another set of the same buds. The Bluetooth connectivity is far from infallible and the right earbud has always been unpredictably stuck in my outer  canal. I’d rather buy a newer better different product at this point but this appears to be the state of the art.

title: Disappointing
content: I’ve been very disappointed with the call quality on these - which is why I purchased in the first place. The microphone picks up considerable background noise and makes them nearly unusable in any pubic place. Given the price and performance, I would no purchase again nor recommend.

title: If you're paying close to $200 for buds I don’t think this is the right choice
content:
This wasn't' available on Amazon so I picked it up from Best Buy:
These hurt my ears to have in for any length of time and they fall out.
The audio constantly skips even when my phone is in my purse; cuts in and out often.
They are easy to lose and hard to find.
App is non-intuitive.
All I can say is that the microphone quality is good.

Also, I missed so many calls because you need a pliers to be able to open the case, I swear to god!

title: Great buy
content: Love them . work as expected . listen to music at work . cancles out noice . talking on the phone is excellent as well . I have had to problems !!

title: Bose sound a hair better but these are better all around.
content: So I’ve been looking for some good true wireless earbuds for a while, bought a cheap pair, they were ok, then sprung for the bose. They sound amazing albeit not loud enough, however I was one of those nineties kids who had 4 10” woofers in my trunk so I am sure I have some hearing loss. only thing is that calls only come through with one earbud and there is a huge amount of sound leakage. The jabras are lovely. I love all the features with the calls and the background noise modulators. Although they don’t sound quite as good as the Bose. These are a keeper. The case is garbage though. My Bose snap into place to charge and the just set in the case. If you want an AirBuds alternative these are it. Sound good, call quality is good. I asked my callers if they could hear me in noisy situations and they reported I sounded up front and clear. I recommend these for all around use. The Bose are my favs as far as sound goes, but these are just a hair under than them sounding a tad tinny. If you want an all around great performer and the case won’t annoy you pick these.

title: Excelente earbuds
content: I like the flexibility and quality of the item.

title: Very, very unconfortable for premium buds
content: The good; great sound and base. The bad and the ugly: ultra unconfortable, the gel tips are made for martians. You may go forward or back one track ( with the side buttons) but if you want to go a few tracks back.....forget it ( well, the Samsung buds do it). As you press the forward or back button on the ear bud, you put pressire on your already unconfortable ear ( bec of the gel bud).

title: Great all purpose wireless earbuds
content: These buds are amazing. They stay in place through running or working out. Sound quality for music and call quality are amazing. Highly recommended.

title: $180 Junk.  Jabra has no helpful customer support
content:
I purchased the Jabra Elite Active 65t as a replacement for my AirPods after one broke.  I intended to use these for road biking as well.  I’ll cut to the chase and say this was the single worse electronics purchase I have ever made. Everything about these screams cheap, including the wailing feedback these puppies make in your pocket if you have the ambient mic on.

I took these for one test bike ride and one fell out twice.  In 1.5 years of AirPodsni has one drop.  So I did some Internet research and tried again, screwing them into my ears.  This time no drops.  Next ride, after the same routine of twisting them into my ear one fell out on a busy road. It was not retrievable.

Best buy won’t take thenm back, jabra will only give me a 20% off coupon which I’ll never use.  Even when I had two if these the plastic case was flimsy and cheap feeling. Sound is on par or worse than airpods. Ambient mic is a stupid gimic.  They suck at noise blocking to begin with and the headphones squeal in mice in your pocket if you dot turn off that stupid feature.  Battery was horrible as well.

If you want to waste $185 I suggest finding something more fun than this junk.  Almost any headphones is better than the jabra elect active 65t.

title: hurts my ears, falls out
content: While I can't deny that the sound quality is amazing, after 10-15 mins they begin to fall out of my ears. I've gone through all 3 sized ear bud covers without success. Because they keep falling out (i'm not moving around, sitting the whole time), I'm constantly pushing them back in. After several times of doing that now they are hurting my ears, to the point I'll take them out going back to plug in ear phone set. I was excited to have a cord free Bluetooth ear buds, that I even looked past the high price for them. If I could find the receipt I'd be returning them getting my money back.

title: One star is TOO HIGH OF A RATING !!
content:
These things are terrible.  Started having trouble within the first month.  They completely quit working within 4 months.  THEN the fight with their support/warranty people started.  That has been going on for almost 6 weeks now and they keep making excuses.  Do yourself a favor and buy something else.

Update, still no resolution.  Horrible customer service.  Do not buy jabra!!!!!

title: Best I've Ever Had
content:
I had been a long time beats by dre headphone user because they were gifts from my parents and it was easy and they were good. Then they broke and I got a second pair and months later they broke again, and I'm pretty sure they broke because of my sweat. I use my headphones for workouts, and I sweat a lot. Like a lot a lot.

These headphones by Jabra have been a game changer. I wear them more often and I love love love them, and I was skeptical. They have not once fallen out of my ear from running (warming up for soccer), olympic lifting, jump roping, and yoga. The sweat doesn't phase them either, they are exactly as they say. Worth every penny, this is a quality product and I'm so glad I invested.

title: Horrible horrible horrible
content: The sound is very very horrible for over 100 dollar product. It was a waste of my money. If I could return it and get my money back that would be awesome. Used it 2 hours and battery died on them

title: Great buds, sound and loving hands-free technology but ear ...
content: Great buds, sound and loving hands-free technology but ear tips did not seal for my workout gym experience; I bought after-market triple-flange ($7 - 5 pairs) tips that did the trick ...I’ve asked Jabra to make tips OME.

title: almost perfect
content: Great headphones, just choppy on android phones no matter what you do.  They have a tendency to have a choppy playback while moving and the phone is within 2 feet.

title: The left earbud will stop working.
content: Alright, I hate to do this. I love these things. They're great. But, whenever I walk near a welding machine or someone elses bluetooth, the left earbud will stop working. This sucks, because the qualitg is beautiful. And I expected more for 200 dollars.

title: Almost Perfect.
content: The sound is great for a true wireless headphone. The features are amazing, I really like the hear through feature. The only problem is the fit. Does not fit all size ears and unfortunately, my ears do not like the fit.

title: Received item used and full of war was DISGUSTING!!!
content: I received this item with loads of ear wax in it that I had to clean out of the ear holes. They did not send me a new model and I paid full price to receive an item that was definitely used. Even if it were to work at full capacity I would think something is wrong with it since someone else touched it. I am not satisfied with the money I spent.

title: Perfect for me
content: Amazing set of wireless earbuds, a little costly but totally worth it

title: Disappointed
content: The sound quality is amazing and it holds a charge for a long time. Also very easy to located with the app if you mis-placed the. Sadly, no matter how many times I tried the different silicone ear bud covers, I could never get these to stay in my ears - they kept falling out and I almost lost them. Unfortunately I was forced to buy a wired pair so I can run with them and not worry about them falling out. Very disapointed as I waited months to buy these.

title: Not worth the money
content:
I really like the case for the plugs and the style and fit of the plugs. They paired up quickly and easy
The sound is average at best.  Even with the equalizer on the app, it was still very tinny.
The battery life is not nearly as long as advertised. I sometimes only get an hour or two even after freshly charged.
I expected much better sound and performance for the price point.

title: Love these headphones
content: Great product

title: Not bad but not what I had hoped for.
content:
The units aren't bad as far as aesthetics.  The sound isn't bad but greatly lacks base, even with base boosted and treble lowered.  The fit with the limited number of eartips wasn't horrible but could have used three sets of foam as well.  The battery life is awesome.
Just ordered a set of Comply to see if it improves the sound quality as well as the fit.

I do like them but they leave a lot on the table.

I compared these with my 8 year old Monster Turbine Pro Copper (wired) ear buds.  I thought the technology would have improved the sound performance but not even close.

title: Great Purchase
content: If you want to listen to music wirelessly. This is a great purchase. Not so great for talking on phone.

title: Convenient earphones
content:
Slips out of ears during sweaty workouts.
I bought a case with a clip that I attached to my keys to have at all times. Pretty convenient!

title: So great, love them!
content:
The best: it stays in my ears, the sound is really good, the noise cancellation is really good, they feel like they're a part of me. The ability to hear 'through' the earphones is a really cool and useful feature.
The worst: if i have my hair down, nobody can see that they are in my ears so people start conversations with me and I cannot hear them. This is not helpful at work.
I recommend them 100%.

title: Hands down the best.
content: By far the best Truly Wireless Headphones on the market as of May 2018! I want to begin by saying that I previously purchased and extensively tested Bragi, Jaybird, and Samsung earbuds. Bragi has the hearthrough function, but terrible sound. Samsung and Jaybird have better sound but no hearthrough, voice quality and connectivity issues, and still only sound mediocre. Jabra delivers on all those functions. Out of the box they sound good, but with a little tweaking through the Sound+ app they sound amazing! They connect no problem and do not drop out, unless of course you take one earbud out then as it should the music stops playing. The voice quality is on point, it cancels out background noise so the caller can hear you clearly. I believe this is thanks to the four microphone placement, which picks up on your voice with ease. The battery life is extremely acceptable considering they are completely wireless. In a full shift at work i can listen for most of my shift and if they are low on juice I pop them in the case for a half hour and they are good to go again. They stay secure in my ear with no worry of jiggling loose, however I highly recommend putting great focus on testing out and finding which tips are the best seemless fit. I thought I wore a medium but tried the large and noticed how much more of a seal I had achieved. With that seal the sound is at its peak performance. The rest of the headphone sits nicely so that it is not rubbing all day against the tender parts of your ear canal. Lastly, the hearthrough function... Wow. Now this function relies heavily on 2 factors. One, the microphone. Two, the software. With the Bragi I could barely just sense loud bangs or someone screaming at the top of their lungs, but Bragi had only one mic placed terribly on each earbud. Jabra has 4, yes 4 microphones with 2 of them jutting out towards your face. As for the software I cannot say but I can actually HEAR people, including myself,  if they are trying to get my attention. The app also allows you better control over the function.

title: Great wireless earbuds
content: I am very happy with these earbuds. I tried the airpods for a couple days and returned them and got these instead. I think these are so much better. They have MUCH better noise isolation, I think the button features on each earbud is more intuitive and offers more functionality, and the app that supports these earbuds is great. I also think the sound quality is better than the airpods and these fit and stay in my ears way better. My two minor complaints about these are that I wish the case opened more easily and I wish the charging cord was longer.

title: Left Earbud Does Not Connect. Fully charged. Out of Box.
content: Could not connect left ear bud on brand new pair. Fully charged, fresh out of box. Manufacturer customer service email says disconnect and reconnect. Um, tried that. $200 but buggy. Do not have this problem on $40 headphones. Move on. Avoid. Save the trip to Kohls to return a day after you receive.

title: 4 of 5 stars
content: Good product but powerbeats pros have better sound and are more comfortable.

title: Sound quality is poor given the price.
content: For such an expensive pair of headphones, the sound quality was just okay.  The speakers lacks bass and treble.  I've gotten much better sound quality from a pair of wired earbuds for a quarter of the cost.  Microphone quality was fine for calls in quiet environments, but it's terrible in noisy environments.  The other side could hear people around me and it's impossible to hold a conversation. The wired headsets are much better. The biggest thing going for it is the convenience and portability.  Nice to not have to deal with wires.

title: Great! Unfortunately I lost them right away. 😑
content: Sounds amazing and every feature is great as well as a great battery life. Unfortunately I lost them within a month.

title: Great call quality for a true wireless earbud
content: I had a specific purpose for wanting a new pair of ear buds. I like listening to music some, but mainly I need headphones/earbuds for conference calls at work. Many reviews I read across the internet touted these ear buds as the best for being noise cancelling, but I found very little information anywhere on call / mic quality when I'm on a conference call (how well can OTHERS hear YOU). I took a chance on these ear buds and thankfully after my conference call this morning, I found that I was very clear sounding to those on the other end of the call and I could hear the others on the call quite well. My coworker said if I'd hadn't told him I was listening via true wireless ear buds he would have sworn I was using a headset with a mic. I'm very pleased with those results! Hopefully someone will find this review useful. I realize many people just by wired headsets/headphones for conference calls because of mic quality, however I wanted something I could use in the office and outside of the office (I travel a lot and needed a good product for listening to movies and music on the plane). These seem to fit the bill perfectly!

title: Make sure you use the right tips to get good bass!!!!
content: the sound on these things is amazing.  While dont expect car seat rumbling bass.  The bass is still very rich and great quality. My absolute favorite feature is the noise canceling and voice pass feature.  if you don't want to hear the outside world well tap tap and poof they are gone and with the same tap tap allow the outside world back in.  The sound is very impressive with a single earbud.  If you want that rich bass you have to make sure you have a good fit with the tips otherwise the bass is just ok. The battery life is awesome too, you can wear them beyond 5 hours with the volume at mid however if you want to crank the sounds you will get about 5 hours and a VERY quick recharge about 20-30 min and you are back in the game.  Lastly you will experience some cut out if you place it in your left pocket otherwise very minimal cut out love these BUDS.

title: Jabra is elite has good quality sound
content: When talking to someone with Jabra in your ear it sounds like hearing someone speak through a microphone

title: These wireless ear buds have superior sound quality and with the EQ customizing sound to ...
content:
I have to give the Jabra 65t 5stars. I have no Quams doing it either. These wireless ear buds have superior sound quality and with the EQ customizing sound to your choice is a pleasure. Very easy to set up and bind via Bluetooth. Volume control and on off control are readily accessible. It takes a bit of practice to use the buttons but I found I was using the buttons in a few hours. It’s great to have everything from volume to battery level all accessible via two buttons!  I have read some reviews where users had difficulty putting the earphones into position to charge. Read the manual!! There is no need to align the earphone connectors to make contact with the brass contacts in the charger case. Just make sure you put the phones in the correct charging holes left/right and close the lid. The lid is designed to push the buds snugly against the charging contacts. There is absolutely no need to align the buds. They will be aligned once the cover is closed.
I have 4 wireless sets of ear buds and as many wired. None of them can compete with the Jabra 65!! Get them. Yes they are a bit pricey but you get what you pay for.
Steve

title: Very nice
content: I like

title: Don’t live up to the hype
content:
I was so excited to get these! They had good reviews, the colors are fun, and I was so pumped to be totally wireless!
I was very quickly disappointed. For starters, they hurt to wear...now that I’ve had them a couple of months I have gotten used to that...sort of. But the biggest issues I have with them:

1. If you sweat a lot they do not stay in. In really intense workouts they fall out and I have to dry them and my ear and put them back in. Total pain.

2. The left earbud does not always pair. The only way I’ve found to fix is to take both ear buds out, put them back in container, close the lid, wait a few seconds, then take them out of the box and put back in ear.

3. The hear through feature only seems to work on the right earbud. I am not sure if I have a faulty pair or if this is normal.

If I had bought these myself rather than received as a gift, I would not have kept them.

title: Was really hoping for more with my second pair
content: The headphones fit in your ear really well, but the sound quality was not good at all. I think I may have gotten a bad pair because they should not sound this bad. It’s almost like the drivers are blown. I can’t get clear sound at all. This is nothing like my first pair I bought.

title: Left Side Not Working
content: Make sure you do an internet search for "Jabra left earpiece not working" before you buy these. I wish I would have known. It seems it's a issue. It's taken over a month of emails from Jabra to get them to do anything about it. At this point, I'll just buy a different brand.

title: Nice
content: Nice headphones

title: Ok convenience to use for the price
content:
Runs out of battery faster than expected. Not very convenient to put on.
Otherwise everything as expected

title: Left earbud static after three days. UPDATE: working but still testing to see if it does it again
content:
It was good when it worked. I have had it for three days. Yes THREE DAYS, the Left earbud has been making a static sound at all volumes. I have looked online and seen this is a problem with these headphones. I have tried to update firmware but it still did not work. Plan on returning.
UPDATE 1: starting working again. Don't know why going to continue using for a few weeks before changing the review

title: Good Sound Low Longevity
content: The bass in the right ear went out after a couple months rendering the overall product close to unusable. Sounded good while it lasted

title: Way better than expected
content:
These things are just right.  They cancel just enough noise so that I can still  hear what is going on around me in case there is an issue.  They greatly reduce the sound of people dropping weights in the gym which is a big plus because that is annoying.  The pass through is just as amazing.  I can hear people when they talk and I'm safe when on the road.

I have only had them fall out 1 time and that is because I didn't put it in right.  The only downside is that using the Alexa/Google assistant screws up for some reason.

title: I Like these Earbuds!
content: Since I'm used to traditional headphones, these earbuds are going to take some getting used to. Otherwise, I love the sound quality.

title: Wow! Great sound! Excellent fit!
content: I was eager to try these earbuds after reading the reviews. They seemed to be good quality and most importantly I was looking for a set of wireless earbuds that stayed in place. These have met and exceeded my expectations. Beautiful sound! Snug, comfortable fit! The app and customizable features are a plus too but I was happy before that.

title: Best Truly Wireless Buds
content: Great sound quality. Incredible microphone for calls. Jabra app comes with extras that are worth the price of the buds alone. All this and the slimmest, most comfortable fit I've ever experienced.

title: Works great.
content: Works great.

title: Spotty connection already.
content:
So I like others, I really want to like these guys. And i do for the most part. After owning the actives for 2 days now, I already have issues with the earphones.

In the first hour of use at the gym, I lost connection 4 times. That was crazy to me, however it may just have been the building because outside it works fine. It has also dropped connection in my house. So that can be pretty annoying. Also, the charging case doesnt always charge my left ear piece reliably. I've contacted customer support, so we'll see what they say about those things.

Fit is good, although it tickles my ear a bit after being in for a while. And sound is good for me. I jumped rope with them for about 20 minutes and they never fell out.

I'll update if anything good comes from their customer support.

title: Great sound but defective after a couple of months.
content: I love the sound quality and flexibility offered by the headphones but after 5 months of owning them, the left earbud stopped playing sound. Very disappointing but Amazon was awesome in service recovery and replaced them immediately. Hoping the new pair will last longer but looking at reviews this seems to be a common complaint.

title: Great when they work, except they rarely work.
content:
This seems like a good product that's marred by manufacturing and QA issues. I bought these because they're the top recommendation on Wirecutter for wireless earbuds, and they're allegedly the unanimous "best AirPods alternative" on Android.

Audio cuts out for me in the left earbud constantly. Sound quality and volume is great when it actually works. At first I thought this was just a connectivity issue, but moving the headphone around and re-setting it back in its charge case seems to re-align something to fix it temporarily, but only temporarily. It seems like something in the internals gets out of whack and you have to get it to set just right for it to work correctly.

I'm going through Amazon's "replace and return" option now and hoping the replacement doesn't have this issue. A quick Reddit search came up with tons of troubleshooting q&a's along with other suckers like me who expected this to work the first time out of the box.

The headphones work great for calling, microphone picks up much better than I expected. I just wish these worked in the left earbud more than 50% of the time I'm using them. Dealing with one earbud cutting in and out is so infuriating, especially since I got these so I could be hands-free while commuting on the train to work. The quality issues are frankly unacceptable for a product at this price level. These are pricier than AirPods!

That said, I'd be willing to pay easily 25% more for these if they actually worked. Sound quality is great and I was pretty impressed with the microphone quality when using them for phone calls.

title: So far these are working out perfectly
content:
So far I’m pretty happy with these. Sound quality is great, nicely built and snug working out. My only issue is I wish I could use a left only solo earbud for podcasts. I’m left ear dominant.

Still nice.

title: Totally recomended
content: awesome earbuds overall, good sound, confortable, discreet, awesome battery life and very good looking buds. there has been an issue were one bud was louder than the other one,  hopefully there's gonna be an update to fix that soon, my advice do not update until a new fix comes up. other than that very recommended for everyday use and sports .

title: Case Too Tough to Open
content: I really loved the feel of these in my ears, but getting them there was the problem.  The case is not easy to open.  I thought it was me, but even my son had a problem.  You have to push down on the little bar thing at the same time you pull the top open.  Sometimes, it took a few tries.  I also had to juggle to get them into my ears to get that nice fit.  And it wasn't easy to pick up a call then switch to the buds (once I got the case open and had them finally into my ears correctly so that they wouldn't fall on the floor).  So, much as I liked them once they were in and connected, I ended up returning them because they were sadly just too much work.

title: Great performance, great fit
content: I have had so many earbuds and always had issues with the fit either uncomfortable or fell of my ears, not to say about doing exercise with them.  I was looking for a truly wireless headset and after several reviews I decided to try on these Jabra. Excellent fit, comfortable you can do almost every active exercise and feel confident that it will stay in your ears, sound was great and looks amazing. Definitely I feel it was my best choice.

title: Great sound and nice customization features
content: I knocked a star off this review because I had to return the first pair after one of the buds quit working after a few days.  I called Jabra support just to make sure there wasn't a fix I didn't know about and my experience was very good.  And getting a replacement pair was easy, of course - this being Amazon.  Other than that glitch, I love these earbuds.  After adjusting the tips and EQ curves to my liking, I haven't regretted the purchase for a moment.  I wear them for several hours at work, while exercising, running etc and find them comfortable, the sound quality is very good, and they don't fall out of my ears.  Being able to leave my phone across the room while exercising is one of those little things you don't think would make a big difference until you do it.

title: Just not right for me
content:
Great features, great app but just never fit properly. I followed the directions, used every provided ear tip but it just never fit right. I even tried the dozens of ear tips from previous ear buds I have owned over the years. Some fit much better but the Jabra's have a tiny ridge on them that keep the tips from coming off, my replacements did not have this so the silicone tops remained in my ear.
I wanted to like the because they had all the features I want: noise cancelling, an app that allows you to tweak it and an EQ. Water proof, supposed to stay in during jogging and box jumps.
I will add one more thing for the designers, that bulb at the bottom that sits in the depression of the ear lobe is too big for some, when I could get it to seat properly and stay it still hurt having them on. I don't know how some women will have these fit. I have had dozens of ear buds and this is my 1st issue with any of them. :-(

title: was great while it worked, warranty support has been atrocious
content:
They worked great, I used them on the airplane mostly and for walking around.  Got the "Active" model but never did any thing more that walk.  Left earbud stopped responding.  Have had a support case open for a couple months, went through their troubleshooting and back and forth.

Said they would send an email with RMA, that was over a week ago..  getting frustrated.

It's exasperating that they send marketing emails every other day, sometimes for the same earbuds that I bought, at a lower price than I paid for.

title: Left earbud is louder than the right
content:
This is my device pair, first one Jabra does a warranty swap to "fix" the unbalanced audio.  But it's still not fixed.  Really annoyed that they are not balanced.
I can't recommend these!

title: Will buy again.
content: This was a great gift.

title: Good looking earphones terrible sound
content: Earbuds look great but sound is horrible,  my $30 pair sounds exactly the same as this $170 ones. Definitely not worth the money. Plantronics backbeat are less than half the price sound way better and are by far more comfortable.

title: Great product, I little hard to use with the ...
content: Great product, I little hard to use with the iphone but with a bit of understanding it has performed well. The battery life is good and the sound is much better than the last ear buds I tried. They stay put and are comfortable to wear. I recommend this product.

title: Good
content: Good

content: So far they work perfectly - except when are are going thru a Store security entrance, that signal messes with the bluetooth.

content: Sound quality was very tinny and hollow.  Tried compensating with app equalizer but didn't make a difference.  Devices hurt when in the ears.  Couldn't wear them for more than 10 minutes at a time.

title: Bad Call Quality
content: While on calls I can hear myself very loudly, and it's extremely annoying. It's as if I was sticking my fingers in my ear canal and speaking.

I searched for related issues online and apparently this has been a on going problem for these headphones for a while. I contacted tech support and the told me how to reboot the headphones. Unfortunately after following their instructions my headphones are still not functioning properly. I'm really upset that a purchased a pair of$170 headphones that not only don't work/ they didn't even last a month. I purchased them on June 12th and Amazon says it's outside of their return date so now I'm stuck with them

title: Ok not great
content: Wanted to love these for travel and talking on phone. Every person says the noise comes through bad when I try talking on them. They work for music but I did lose one on a plane so make sure you set up the tracking that lets you find one if it falls out when you fall asleep. I did find it!

title: Tiny much smaller than expected
content: They were so tiny I returned them with trying

title: Favorite feature become worst nightmare,,,
content:
** UPDATE ** DROPPED 1 STAR ** NO CUSTOMER SERVICE **
9 days with repeated attempts to contact Jabra customer service.  I noticed Jabra has people watching Amazon reviews and posting comments... too bad they don't have people in customer service returning calls and emails.  $170 and they lasted less than 2 months.  I should have bought some of the $40 knock-off ones... I thought the extra money spent on the name brand (Jabra) provided quality and customer service.  I was ripped off.

*********

Three things I have never been good at:
(1) Remembering to turn things off
(2) Remembering to plug things in to charge
(3) Putting things back in their case

My favorite feature of the 65t was that I could accomplish all three with just one action; specifically, placing the device into the case triggered auto-off and initiated charging (I kept the case plugged in on my desk).  Phone rings… pop the case open, pull out the buds (which turned on automatically) and I was ready to take the call.  If listening to music when interrupted by a visitor, I could simply pull them from my ears, drop into the case, close the lid, and the devices turn off (disconnects from phone and music stops).  No fumbling to stop the music or turn them off to keep the battery from draining.  I was the envy of the office…

Just under 2 months in and the auto on/off has stopped working.  How did I find out?  Well, buds were in the case (on my desk, as usual) but still on and connected (without me knowing).  After multiple missed calls (the buds were connected and therefore “ringing” when the call came in) I realized they weren’t turning off.  If I turn off manually, then I have to fumble around to turn on manually (both of them) before I can take a call.  Tried reseting… no luck.  Tried un-pairing and re-pairing… no luck.  Contacted Jabra customer service… luck???  Waiting to hear back.  If they work then they are 5 stars for me… until then the best (and most generous) I can give is two stars; one for each month they worked.

title: Comfortable earbuds
content: Excellent wireless earbuds.  Easy to pair with cellphone.  Very comfortable and has 3 sizes to fit properly

title: That damn left earbud...
content: This product ranks highly on all of the lists for wireless earbuds, but if you dig into the user reviews there's a consistent theme.  The left earbud either cuts out or stops working altogether.  I ordered them in spite of that.  I was initially very happy with the product and would have absolutely agreed with the comments on the best of lists.  That is until 2 days after I got them the left earbud started cutting in and out and shortly afterwards stopped working completely.  It was fully charged but just never connected to my phone or the right earbud ever again.  I tried every solution on the internet.  I contacted Jabra and tried all of their solutions.  Nothing.  Initially Jabra's customer service was very responsive but the second I needed to send the product back in for a replacement they suddenly became waaaaaaaaay less responsive (another complaint in the user reviews).  I couldn't get them to send me a return shipping label.  Well, I decided that I didn't want to wait multiple weeks because of their crappy customer service.  I returned the product through Amazon (amazing response time) and bought a competitive product.  I cannot recommend these at all.

title: Great quality
content: 5/5 - they fit much better than air pods.

title: Absolutely the best headphones I've owned
content: I've had these a while now - wanted to wait to write a review. Amazing sound quality, completely comfortable and secure, no connection issues. The noise isolation is outstanding - completely shuts out noise at the gym so I can hear my music. I love the ability to "let sound in" when someone comes up to talk to me or I need to be more aware of my environment. I've tried several true wireless headphones (in addition to wired Tarah Pros and Jaybird X3s) and these are amazingly superior in sound, comfort, and noise isolation. I used to fly only with my Bose quiet comfort over-ear headphones - but tried these on my last flight and the sound isolation is so good these are all I will need to travel with. Highly recommend.

The sounds quality is fantastic and bluetooth connection is flawless and easy.  Highly recommend these to anyone!

title: These are total garbage.  Had two pairs and both broke in the same manner/way
content: The left earbud on both pairs (one a replacement) would eventually start shorting out and then altogether stop working.  In addition, customer support for Jabra is horrible.  Took a solid month of me forcing a back and forth conversation through phone calls and email exchanges to get a replacement.  Avoid these.

title: Far more negatives than positives - also broken
content:
Positives:
Sound quality is decent.
Connectivity was initially good.
The "hear through" feature is cool and actually worked well.

Negatives:
After a few uses the left unit would choose not to reconnect after being removed from the ear.  This could be fixed by putting it in the charging case, then removing it and reattempting.
The case itself is difficult to open, and works reliably only by squeezing the plastic on the sides to "pop" the top.  Not sure how this was what they went with vs. a magnetic or other functional latching system everyone else seems to be managing with ease.
If you've been an AirPod user, you'll expect them to stop playing your song/book when you remove a unit.  They do this about 60% of the time, which is not enough to make it a feature you won't count on - so you go back to manually pausing like the old days.  I actually had them pause successfully, then heard them start playing again on their own a few seconds later sitting on my desk with contacting nothing.
The ear fit is via 3 different cushion sizes.  If one is for you then you'll be happy.  For me the small was so loose the sound quality was extremely poor.  The medium was too tight leading to discomfort, and the feeling that I was wearing earplugs.
As a final quality indicator, I dropped my left unit on the tile kitchen floor from waist height.  There's something rattling inside and now neither unit will connect.
I'm glad some consumers are enjoying these, but I really couldn't recommend them.  Especially considering the number of options at this price point.

title: Sound great if you can keep them in
content: My husband bought these for me, and I was so excited to get them.  They sound great, both streaming and on a call, and the other party says the call quality is good; however, they are kind of big and will not stay in my ears.  If I yawn, talk, eat, or get up and walk around, one or both fall out.  The battery time is okay, only about 4-5 hours.  I get much better battery time out of other wireless earbuds I own.  These are a good idea, they just need some work.

title: Complete GARBAGE!
content: I bought these for my wife as an early Christmas present. I have Apple Airpods, and wanted her to have nice headphones as well. All of the reviews out there said these were as good or better. So not true! The Jabra Elite 65t have absolutely ZERO bass at all. I installed the Jabra app and maxxed out the bass, and still nothing on the low end. I even paired them with my phone to make sure it wasn't my wife's phone, and no change. I have $15 headphones that sound better than these. They also did not fit her ears well because they are so big. The case is also very hard to get opened, and when you mange to pry it open, the headphones like to go flying out. Nothing about these are quality. If you want quality, stick with the Apple Airpods. I desperately wanted to like these, but there's nothing to like. Complete junk!

title: Right Earbud Doesn’t Work

Calls, music, and voice guidance audio all do not work through the right earbud. The controls all work but no sound. I have submitted a request so we’ll see what happens with that.

title: Must-Have Game Changers
content:
This is my second pair as I also have the Elite Active 65ts. I haven't bought bluetooth earbuds for years but after considerable research, I decided to give these a spin. I LOVE them. Hands-free, convenient privacy, you avoid smudging your phone with facial oils, they sound great, and low profile so they're not sticking out down your face so you look like a fanboy clone.

They come with 3 different silicone tip sizes to help you get the perfect fit. I do many different types of cardio and never have an issue with them feeling loose or slipping out. Battery life is OK and the charging case fits into any pocket or purse.

I can definitely see myself wearing these out in a short amount of time due to how often I use them. And when that happens, I'll go right back out and buy another pair.

title: They just work

title: Great headphones.

title: Best. Headphones. Ever.
content: This is the first and only review I have ever written and I use Amazon for 90+% of ever purchase I make. That's how amazing these things are! Best sound quality I've ever heard, across all devices, speakers, headphones, any and everything that makes noise. The bass is mind blowing! They're also the most convenient thing I own. Auto pause when you remove one of the buds from your ear, auto power on and off, the speak through function allows you to still hear the environment around you because of the amazing quality of the noise cancelling, it never runs out of battery because of the auto charging dock which holds 5 full charges (I believe... It may be 2, I don't remember but it honestly doesn't matter because they havent died once) literally the only downside to these bad boys would be damaging them or losing them and jabra has you covered there too with the water resistance, 2 year warranty, and freaking GPS track. Are you kidding me?!? I know I sound like a fan girl(I'm actually a 31yr old man), but seriously this is the single most amazing product I've ever purchased. I work at a body shop with lots of loud noises and a dirty environment and these things have kept up every step of the way. I cannot overstated the value of these things or how highly I recommend them. Quit worrying about the price and buy them. You'll be glad you did!

title: Great sound quality but picks up everything
content: I wish it wouldn’t pick up all the noise around you. Bought these for business and they pick up everything.

title: Best true wireless headphones out there
content:
This is definitely just my opinion but I do feel that as of now, these are probably the BEST ALL AROUND true wireless earphones you will find. I have these as well as the Beoplay E8 earphones. I purchased both planning to return one of the two pairs but never did. Never returned the Beoplay E8's because they just sound amazing but if I were forced to choose, I would choose the Jabra's. The Beoplay E8's do sound great, but you wouldn't really be missing out on anything if you just went and purchased the Jabra's.

These things are all around amazing. The sound is great and they are more than loud enough (if they aren't loud enough for you please stop wearing earphones and see a physician). They fit extremely comfortably in my ears which is a huge feat because I have small and oddly shaped ears and have never (until now) found earphones that can fit in my ear comfortably and stay there. Another awesome thing I love about these is how easy it is to connect via bluetooth. Once you connect them to a device all you need to do is take them out and put them on. Usually by the time they are in my ear they are already paired and they can take 2 devices which is also awesome if you are always working with a computer. Because of this I find myself using these much more often than the Beoplays (which also says a lot as I am one of those audiophile types and the Beoplays have AMAZING instrumental separation to the point where you hear everything and in a well balanced manner).

They don't really have the best sound isolation (the Beoplay's absolutely clear outside noise; it's like wearing over-ear headphones with awesome passive noise cancellation). With these, you will definitely hear some outside noise but it isn't absolutely terrible, just raise the volume a little and you should be good as long as you don't destroy your hair cells. That said, they do have a cool hear-through feature which works ok (Beoplays are actually better at this somehow).

Lastly, these things are great with phone calls which makes sense; from my understanding this is the area of tech that Jabra really has it's roots in and it shows. Easy to take calls (I have it set up to my phone's default voice command system so it may differ by device but if I get a call I can just say "Answer" or "Ignore") and everyone sounds very clear. I'm not sure how I sound on the other end but haven't had anybody tell me anything yet so must mean something (I made a call with the Beoplays once and they told me they couldn't hear me very well).

All that said if you are looking for true wireless earphones and these are in your price range, take them. Don't even bother with higher-end earbuds UNLESS music is the absolute (maybe even sole) selling point for you. If you absolutely need that 3D/vast feel to the sound of your music then get the Beoplays, otherwise I absolutely recommend these over anything else ESPECIALLY those damn apple airpods. I say this because this company (Jabra) has made these absolutely amazing earbuds only for companies like Apple, that are already extremely well established, to produce poor quality earbuds at high prices for everyone to lap it up (don't get me wrong their bluetooth pairing is seemless but that is really the ONLY selling point; they're ugly, sound crappy, are expensive, have no sound isolation, etc.)

DO YOUR RESEARCH.

title: Went through the wash and still work great!
content: I don’t often write reviews but felt the need to here. I bought these in April for marathon training and have put hundreds of hours and miles on them. They sound great and I love that I can either allow or block background noise. I get pretty sweaty on long runs, my ears included. Every now and then I’ll have a run where one side seems to slip a bit and I need to adjust it every 5-10 mins, but for the most part they comfortably stay put. But, the main reason for my 5 star review is that after a half marathon this weekend I stuck these in my pocket, forgot about them, and washed and dried my shorts. I was devastated when I realized what I’d done! After a full night charging and un pairing/repairing them, they work just like new! I couldn’t believe it. While I wouldn’t recommend washing them, I am beyond impressed with their durability!

title: Not bad

Sofar they haven't disconnected, they have enough buttons to do volume and skip tracks, they are more comfortable than the jaybirds, they have the cool passthrough sound, and watching videos with them is doable (still a little lag but not as bad). title: Sounds great

title: Buy 'em and Love 'em
content: After considerable research I settled on these. I know Jabra has been a player in the bluetooth headset arena for awhile. But I will admit that upon opening the well packaged pair it read "welcome to superior sound" I was skeptical. Well I am skeptical no more, these guys deliver in every way. Calls are clear, been told on the other end I sound clear, and connectivity is consistent. The sound reproduction for all types of music in my opinion is outstanding. The sweet spot for me is lower to mid volume, the soundstage is balanced and full. They can get a bit "tinny" when the volume is pushed. With that said, they are plenty loud enough. ****** Play with the different sizes of cups and settle on the largest one that you can "stuff" comfortably into your ear canal. It will measurably improve the bass response. The app is also very handy, you can tailor the sound with the EQ, switch the pass through mics on or off to name two. Once you "twist" them in they WILL NOT come out of your ears. Gettem.....

title: Good idea but bad quality phone calls
content: The in-ear sound quality is great. However, when I make phone calls using Jabra the other person struggles to hear me clearly, or they hear themself echoed back. I cannot use these headphone for phone calls which is frustrating since that’s why I bought them. I would not purchase them again unless this issue is fixed.

title: LOVE THESE! I'm wearing them probably around 5-8 hours every day.
content:
So I have now recommend these to EVERYONE  I see using wireless/cordless headphones. I have gotten 6 people to purchase them and they love them. The sound quality is there in my opinion they bet boss and other top of the line options that are truly wireless.

Pros:
Fitting. I have ALWAYS had trouble here, but the right head phone sits perfectly and i can keep it in for about 4/6 hours before it starts to hurt. They dont fall out and if I got on an intense run or just lounging around. I also use one when riding a motorcycle for quick trips and it stays put and still comfy in a tight helmet.

Comfort: see above statement. The only one they doesn't fit well is the left one and i think that is more of a me thing than design as it exactly the same.

Battery: Amazing. So like stated i use these a lot i my charge them twice a week.

Case: strong slick case.

App: the app is decent nothing to be mad about really the UI could be more interesting I guess, but it does the job.  Also the ear bud tracking has come in handy a couple times when I just leave it on a table or something.

CONS:
App: WHY CANT I TRACK MY CASE...

Water proof/Active use: So if you sweat so much you start having the salt come off you this will DESTROY these buds. I know they say they are but if you just got done working out and don't rigorously clean these before putting back in the case after about 4/6 month you will noticed a drop in charging, paring, audio quality etc.  I actually got them replaced because of this.

Warranty replacement: OKAY with some grains of salt, they took FANTASTIC  care of me for my warranty replacement, but to get to that point it seems super rigid, complicated, and I almost just didnt do it due to the initial hassle. Guys if I have your app left me do the entire warranty replacement from the app..

OVERALL: Buy them. Enjoy, and promote the product if you truly enjoy and want to see more from them. Give feedback on the pros and con's you find so the next series will be even better. Thanks again Jabre!

title: Overall it's a good wireless earbuds but after using them for more than ...

title: Best pair of wireless earbuds I've owned
content:
I wanted to wait for some time until I made a review on these things to see if they held up. Turns out they're standing the test of time. I dont leave the house without them. Solid for noise cancelling, the ability to keep them in but utilize the outer microphones to hear things around you is awesome. Battery life gives me about 6 hours, the pack gives me about 3 charges before needing connected. Working out is also a breeze. Never had them fall out once.

I have 2 complaints. The first is cleaning. Cleaning the ear piece can be a pain. The second is the charge port type. While, I know this model is slightly older, I hope any new models come with a USB C-type.

Overall, buy this. Trust me.

My first impression with these earbuds was positive but quickly noticed that I could only hear sound out of one (the left) bud. I then googled it and discovered that **MANY PEOPLE HAVE THE SAME ISSUE**. No one knows how to fix it and Jabra isn't responding.

title: Doesn't fit me.
content: They looked and felt amazing, sounded even better.  If you are into having an app and eq, you have all of that.  I was looking for replacement tips, preferably foam ones and a ton of the research showed that they would need to be removed every time before putting them in the charging case.  Because they wouldn't fit comfortable in my ear, and i couldnt modify them to help, unfortunately they needed to be returned.

title: Like cheap plastic
content:
They start with an extremely insubstantial feel. Like cheap plastic. A child's toy. Without a magnetic connection from H'phones to charger (like the Bose SSF), other than charging contacts, it's very difficult to seat them in the charger.
Another direct comparison to the Bose SSF, is that with Bose I can use one bud L or R st work. With Jabra even with the auto off set to OFF if I remove the R Jabra bud, the left one turns off! Anotjer bad news comparison to Bose SSF. the ear tips. First they must be shoved all the way into the ear canal to remain in place. Even with the smallest ear rip, it still becomes excruciating to keep in for a long period of time. In my case, 2 plus hrs of audiobook listening at work. The left bud became unstable and crackly at high volume.

But the real reason for the one for the one star rating and the last bad comparison to Bose SSF, the eartips can and do pop off open removing.  Mostly they end up falling on the floor. But this time the right rip stayed in my ear canal as I pulled out the bud!

It took a coworker performing emergency surgery with a toothpick to remove it! So back to Amazon they went.

App is better than Bose. Hear through feature is awesome. Battery life is better than Bose SSF. Sound is great as long as you push the buds through your eardrums. EQ is responsive and easy to use and unlike the Bose SSF, no lip sync issues. No cutting out, like the Bose. Firmware update  downloaded quickly.

If you like a broad range of audio adjustment, they're fantastic. Yet even with Bose's crafted sound and lack of noise cancellation the Bose SSF overall sound is light years superior to the Jabra or any other earbuds. The Bose are also far louder and remain stable without any distortion at the highest volume.

Sent the Bose SSF back to checkout the Jabra. For me it was a huge mistake and will soon be rectified.

Back to Bose to stay!

title: Jabra Ear Buds
content: Great product! Really like the interaction with my Samsung Note 10+

title: Worked great for 11 months, then stopped working
content: I write this review with only 1 week left of the 1 year warranty and after contacting Jabra support to get an RMA to return for repair.  The earbuds worked well up until now.  Mainly used them specifically to listen to podcasts and news so I cannot really vouch or report anything regarding their sound quality (for music).  But its very disappointing that they only lasted less than a year before they have become unable to charge (or hold a charge).  The LED lights are confusing and the manual does a poor job at explaining why the earbuds blink red, then green for a few seconds, then back to red.  Green means a good battery charge and red means battery is exhausted and mine blink between the two and show 15% charge on my mobile device.  So basically, the batteries arent charging.  The case (which is a battery within itself) shows fully charged (green LED) but the actual earbuds dont hold a charge.  Went through all the troubleshooting steps on the Jabra support website with no luck.  I'm requesting an RMA to return.  If Jabra stands behind the product and repairs/replaced, I will be sure to write a follow up and change my rating.
