title: very nice ear buds
content: price my be a little over for ear buds,and I have been through a lot of different brands.This one is very nice and stands up to everything that it says that it does.I would highly recommended this brand,as you will not be disappointed.

title: Some features don't work - even after warranty replacement
content:
I picked the Elite Active for not only wireless convenience, decent sound quality, affordable price and to be able to use the buttons as advertised.  However, didn't get all I had hoped for...

There seem to be various bugs that cause you to need to 'reboot' the earbuds OFTEN by putting them back in the case for just a moment then they work again - until it happens again.  Sometimes several times a day.  Common moments of pressing Right button or pulling out one earbud to pause, then sticking it back in and it wouldn't play in one or both sides.  Not consistently but often.  However, the one I can recreate over and over is with the left earbud's Forward/ Reverse Track button, it does NOT work! It keeps playing the same track, press again, it stops and requires you to reboot the earbud by putting it back in the case.  Not convenient in the middle of a bike ride.  The volume up/down does work so that's good.

These bugs happened with my original purchase and the earbud they warrantied!  Maybe it depends on the music app but seems odd it would; I use Amazon, Pandora, Podcasts, Audible, etc.  All the same result.

Jabra's customer service experience left much to be desired.  12/3 after over an hour on hold, instead initiated online request taking 7 days to get a response. Had to email them 2x over the next 10 days to get a response with a link to the warranty form. Completed but no auto response was sent so waited another 7 days, still nothing. Called to find out if even was received/accepted, etc. holding for 30 minutes and was told it was in the queue and would process right then.  I started the ticket on 12/3 and got the replacement 1/9 which seems was mostly due to lack of response.  However, maybe there are so many problems with their products, they are just that busy.

In general, the sound quality is pretty good, but for the money and the number of problems with product and customer service, I wish I would have gone with the Bose SoundSport earbud for a little more money - they may look big but the sound is WAY better too.

title: Easily fit to any ear size and great sound!
content: These earbuds are incredible. I have small ear holes and the option of 3 different sizes means I found the perfect fit. They stay in comfortably and they are so easy to pair with my phone or tablet! The quality of sound for phone calls and music is great, no issues hearing at all. I love the charging case not only for charging but for storage. I can easily toss the case in my purse and not worry about the earbuds falling out. I have owned many Jabra products over the years and they last forever so these are a great investment.

title: great earbuds
content: Im a cyclist and needed earbuds that could operate with just one ear in use, these have been great! Sound quality is amazing and you can use the hear through feature to still hear what's going on around you. I haven't quite figured out how to use the functions on the earpiece such as skipping songs etc I've been using my phone. the app is super helpful and you can fine tune your equalizer using the app.  Battery life is about 5 hours of playtime which is great considering how small these things are. They feel very secure no matter if I'm biking or running

title: Very nice earbuds works great
content: So far very simple to use and the jabra app makes setup a breeze audio quality is top notch thank you very much

title: Just right!
content:
Just the right size, right sound quality, right light weight material and just the right amount of battery play between the buds and it’s battery case.
So far they are also working very well when I watch Netflix on my IPhone too!
I love these and I highly recommend them!

title: great product
content: it was a little expensive but i use them every day at work. lots of noise at work and with 2 taps of a button i can cancel out all the noise around me. when i need to hear my surroundings i just hit it again and i can hear pretty much everything around me again.

title: Work great
content: Husband loves these!

title: For wireless buds, they are loud and have great sound.  Giving my AirPods to my kid.
content: Just got mine yesterday.  They rule.  Very, very happy.

title: PERFECT FIT imperfect right earbud!!!!
content:
I preferred ear phones, that had some type of anchor, whether it be over ear loop or the wing that anchors over the ear lobe, that is until I decided, after reading many reviews, to purchase these. The tips for the ear buds come in three sizes. Try each one because only one is a perfect fit! Once I found my true fit they proved to be very comfortable and stay in my ear for as long as I choose. I wear mine for several hours at a time.
With the use of the chargeable case I get about 15 hours of use.
I've used Beats, Sennheiser and Bose. I have to say that these Jabra earphones are my favorites. The sound quality is great and can be further fine-tuned with the help of the JABRA APP!
Update:
I reviewed these earbuds too quickly! About 3 weeks ago, I noticed that the volume in the right earbud started fading. I went on line and was shocked to find that this was a very common problem with this brand. The volume is now nonexistent in the right. Since the left cannot be used alone, I have to shove them both in my ear to use them, with no sound coming out of the right.
I notified Jabra and they gave me troubleshooting directions, which I followed, even though I had already done them from on line tips. It still did not work. I filled out my warranty for replacement of the right earbud, and it's been about a week  I have not heard a thing!
I will contact them again but will definitely be going back to Sennheiser. I have not tried their True wireless yet.

title: It's alright, but not the best.
content: Sound fades in and out while I am driving and speaking, the other person has to ask me a few times to repeat myself.

title: The best wireless headphones available!
content:
These headphones are an amazing contender for a true wireless experience. I was looking for a wireless in-ear headphone and had narrowed it down to the AirPods, these, and the Bose SoundSport Free. I initially purchased AirPods and wanted to like them. I really wanted to join the craze of people with little white pods hanging from their ears, but they couldn’t keep up. Every run I went for, the left one would fall out. Maybe it’s me! Maybe I have weird ear canals, but the only solution was to purchase third party covers and have to put them on before each use and remove them before putting them back in the case. I ordered these and returned the AirPods. Hands down, better quality. Sound quality - amazing. I have Sonos speakers in my home and value sound quality, these do NOT fall flat. I love that the case is sturdy. You have to squeeze the sides for the top flap to open so there’s no chance of these headphones rolling out and being lost. The app that accompanies the headphones is a nice addition, but rarely used. The HearThrough option is convenient, but not used often. It’s nice that you have so many options with the buttons on the headphones. Other reviewers mention it being uncomfortable having to hold down the volume rocker to skip a track, but I don’t mind this at all.
If you are someone who values sound quality or needs a headphone with an interchangeable tip, these are for you!

title: Great true wireless!
content: I love my jabra elite earphones! Great sound quality, even on phone calls. My husband said it sounded like i was using my phone when we were on a call together. So i dont have to wory about bad sound at the other end when im talking to clients. Comfy ear buds. I wore them for 6 hours on a long drive and did just fine. Long battery life especially when you keep them in the case when not in use. Easy to pair. Cant say enough good

title: Amazing headphones
content: I run over 70 miles a week and sweat a ton and I wear these headphones for almost every run and haven't had a problem yet. The sound quality is great and they seem to be very durable.

title: Fantastic!
content: Wasn’t sure what to expect when I bought these as the last pair I purchased from a different company were weaklings, but these guys ROCK! Completely beyond my expectations. Enough bass, clarity, and Bluetooth is perfect. This was a good purchase.

title: Jabra Should Stay with Wired Headphones.
content: I have a couple of Jabra wired headphones for work and was thrilled when my employer offered these. The call quality is really bad. Drops calls every few mins fades in and out. My $10 blue tooth headphones have better call quality

title: Customer service is laughably terrible
content: I enjoyed the product very much. Up until about 6 months it was flawless but after than certain features started failing. Automatic connection/playing when placed in your ear stopped working. In certain places you simply couldn’t hear from both earbuds at the same time and had to only have the right one in. Even when an audio jack is connected and the ear buds were in their case stored away it would play the audio to the earbuds instead of the jack like if they were still connected. As a reasonable person I contacted their customer service to see what the problem might be or to get a replacement/repair. Safe to say it’s been over a month since I’ve contacted them and no word on a repair or replacement shipment eta. The customer service is practically non existent, responses take more than a week with some even getting ignored only for the same subject to be addressed next time you get a response like they didn’t read your last 2 emails. No communication whatsoever. If they sent you a replacement, place a hold on your account, then take it off once they get your broken buds like Apple does, it wouldn’t be a big deal. For all the music addicts out there who need it for their commutes, workouts, daily activities and whatnot, you know how much it sucks to be without something other than your phone speaker for a while and it’s really topped off by a careless customer service. Take this in mind when thinking about purchasing from Jabra.

title: Great compared to pixel buds
content: Put in my earbuds today and after thinking of how pleased i was with them wanted to add a review. Surprised at the negative reviews -- after several months I haven't had any issues. I previously owned the Google Pixel buds (stolen, sadly). Those are a similar price point, but these are imho _much_ better. Comparatively, they stay in better, block out noise better, and have better sound quality. I don't generally use the mic so no comment on that. My favorite feature is one I didn't ask for -- the way the music auto-pauses when pulling the earbud out -- I don't think I could buy another pair of headphones that did not do this. Charging case works well, I don't have any issues with fit. I use them with my a Pixel 2 phone and have had no issues -- never had to re-pair, fix connection, etc. I generally use them for working out, or to focus at work. I purchased a pair for my wife as well (last November) and she's not had any issues either, FWIW (used with her iphone 7)

title: Save your money
content: I got a pair of these and like so much of Chinese technology, only one earplug worked. Plus they are cumbersome to turn on and slippery to handle. Additionally, when inserting them into the ear it is near impossible to not connect with the connection button and turn the thing off. I have spent hours fussing with these little devils with no success. I immediately wrapped them back up and contacted the company, got no reply and there is NO CUSTOMER SERVICE NUMBER. I am sending them back anyway and will contact my credit card company regarding this matter.

title: Good, not perfect!
content:
Bought these to replace a pair of (non-Active!) 65ts, one of which our dog chewed into uselessness.  Not Jabra's fault!

Pros:

* quick and easy Bluetooth connectivity
* robust connection
* decent range (I carry my iPhone in my pocket, am 6'/1.8m tall) and never have any loss of signal
* battery life beyond my needs (approx. 2 hrs/session)
* easy interoperability with Siri
* microphone and earphone functions support telephone conversations quite satisfactorily
* Jabra app helpful to adapt to changing ambient environments

Cons:

* don't fit comfortably in my ears - have to "twist and lock" occasionally
* ergonomics of case are awkward, "popping" the top sometimes causes the buds to fly out and hit the floor
* attractive to Airedale Terriers! :)

I have, or have had, Hear Ones, IQ Buds (both F35 and Q83 "Boost"), the aforementioned 65t non-Active, and Fflat5 Arias, all of which cost more than the Jabras (a lot more, since I tend to buy the newest and greatest, rather than wait till the market sets a price for them), and the fact that I use the Jabras most often for the early a.m. dog walk speaks for itself.

I thought I needed better tips, so bought the newly-released Comply tips for these.  They have made a marginal difference, but I'm still more confident wearing the IQ Buds, or the Hear Ones (no longer in business) from a stable insertion standpoint.

I definitely would NOT use them for running or a high-energy gym workout - I am sticking with the Jaybird Freedoms for those applications.  Even with the better-fitting wireless earbuds, I don't feel confident that they'll stay put during a strenuous cardio interval, or even doing free weights.

title: Can NOT change tracks when paired to fitness watch :/
content: LOVE the sound and fit.  Only bought these for my 3 mile runs (3x/week) to PAIR with my Fitbit Versa.  Soooo disappointed that, when paired to fitness watch, you CANNOT change tracks on the earbuds.  WHAT??!! In this age of technology??!!  So, I bought the cheap Senso wireless buds (not true wireless) which, at $40, DO CHANGE TRACKS on the earbuds.  I will continue my search for true wireless buds that "track changing " works when paired to watch.

title: Perfect so far
content: These are everything i could have hoped for. Great fit and sound. I was shocked by the bass. I also love the hear-through functionality option where you can hear the sound around you.

title: Good sound but bad connectivity and short battery life
content: I can say that I loved these completely wireless headphones for the lools, functionality, sounds and convenience. But there were a few deal breakers that unfortunately made it more of a hastle to use than I could tolorate. For one if the earpieces are slightly off axis to each other the music will stop because the software will think you removed one of the headphones which activates the pause music music function. This got old really quick specially when working out when you have to stop your exercise to fix the allignment issue. The other deal breaker was the battery life for although the case offers extra charging capability I was not able to finish a workout with one charge. Which meant that I had to put them away for the last hr of my workout..... These are again very beautiful, well built and sound great but unfortunately the few issues it has are not worth the money to keep. Hope their future models improve in this as they look to be a very promising compertitor to what is out there currently.

title: Happy customer
content:
Pleasantly surprised about the quality and fit.

If you’re looking for a wireless headphone look no further if the price fits your budget.

title: As easy to use as plugging in a pair of wired earbuds.
content: The completely wireless aspect of it was something to get used to and the right ear bud was uncomfortable in my ear at first, but it really grew on me. I can listen to music for long periods now comfortably. I also love the charging case. I haven’t had problems with a lack of battery when I’m trying to use it. It’s a seamless connection and it’s very convenient how it automatically pairs when you take it out the case. I’m very happy with my purchase. I used to use a Bluetooth headset that rested on the back of my neck. I had about 3-4 different ones. I’m never going back since I got these. I never use wired headphones these days.

title: High volume level is too low.
content: I purchased two pair of these based on reviews and product description.  I primarily wanted and love the "totally wireless" aspect of the Jabra.  I love the charging case.  Everything about  these  says "Classy".  But apparently the people who wrote good and excellent reviews don't listen to their music like I do because the volume level sucks!  The high volume on these Jabra Elite 65t ear buds is equivalent to the medium volume level on my Skullcandy Titan earbuds.  I would not recommend spending this amount of money for these no matter how fancy they look.  The bottom line is always quality sound and sound level in the ear.  If you like listening to music at a low mellow volume, these are for you.  But if you like to crank it up, keep on looking because these are NOT it.

title: Bass needs improvement for music.
content: Bass sound for music listening is not  good.

title: The best wireless Earbuds.
content: These are easily the best wireless Earbuds out of all the ones I have tried. The battery life is great, the sound quality is excellent and is customizable to add extra bass using the app if desired. The are designed well and fit very comfortably in my ear, I don't even notice they're there. My only complaint I'd that the case does not close using a magnet for easier assess like the Apple Air Pods. Other than that they beat the Air Pods and I highly recommend these for anyone looking for Wireless Earbuds

title: Money for these jabra earbuds can be spent on another brand for half the price I was very upset
content: The  right earbud didn’t hold a charge after a month . I was very angry cause I’m always working out and the money I paid for these earbuds that shouldn’t happen so I bought some 50$ earbuds and sounded so much better and the battery lasted much longer than Jabra my advice is save your money spend about 50$ on a pair not these I felt I was robbed big time the way they advertise these earbuds

title: Good Sound
content: Don’t always have the feeling of security when I’m walking around with them but sound is amazing.

title: Great Wireless Headphones
content:
I bought these headphones to replace another pair from another company that were horrible. I have never really used ear bud type headphones before so I was a little skeptical.  After using these for the past week, I can tell you they are great. Phone call quality, noise cancelling are the best.  I ride mass transit in most days and they cut out all the noise.

They fit tightly in my ear, and come with 3 different sizes of ear buds so they should fit most people. Mine came about 60% charged so I could use them right away. Using them for over 2 hours a day for the past week, I still haven't had to charge them yet.

So far, these are the best I have tried.

title: Learn from my tough lesson-Continually falls out of ears-Out $170 after 1 month of ownership
content: What value is good sound quality and features if these earbuds get lost so easily? I've only used them four times. During the first three uses they fell out twice. Both times I felt it falling and was able to catch it. The third time I was not so fortunate. I had just disconnected while ordering at Starbucks and a few minutes later when I went to press the 'on' button, I noticed the one in my right ear was gone. I frantically retraced my steps several times but to no avail. The other problem I've had is how slippery the exterior is so that even getting them in my ear was an issue. It shouldn't have a glossy finish.

title: No good for business calls
content: I'm no audiophile.  The sound is good.  The fit can be a little uncomfortable, but nothing intolerable.  My issue is that these HAVE to work for business calls.  If I can't use them in an airport or on a busy street or in a coffee shop, they're no good to me.  My boss says to me as soon as we're on a call, "I'm getting alot of background noise.  Can you drop the wireless earbuds?"  They're going back.  Buying AirPods - even though I wouldn't give Apple a dime if I could avoid it.  In this case, it seems I can't avoid it.

title: Hear better!!
content: Perfect fit too..

title: Didn’t fit my ear, but return process was easy
content: I really wanted to like these, but couldn’t even make it out of the house without them falling out of my ears. Had to return. At least the return process through amazon was painless.

title: Sound quality sucks
content:
Item worked fine for a few weeks then left one stops working.. tried the support the reset and nothing works
This is really sad because I bought these only because they came highly recommended

title: Great fit/ sound!
content: These are every bit as good as I had hoped they'd be!

title: Connectivity for calls fifty fifty if that!
content: Music quality is great for Bluetooth like them alot needs  jabra app to program functions is down side. Connectivity for calls iffy. So if you want for music a five star calls three.

title: Music is awesome. The phone mic quality is the opposite.
content: I loved the music and podcast quality. However, when using for calls, the other party had a hard time hearing my voice. The volume control buttons are tiny and you need sensitive fingers.

title: Read the instructions word for word
content: Outstanding earplugs, I am in love

title: No USB C.
content: The fit and sound quality are excellent but the charge case is not very sturdily built. Right out of the box I noticed how thin the locking surface was. I feel like opening that thing a few times a day is going to wear it down after just a few months. The same thing goes for the charge port on the back. Micro USB is notoriously flimsy and upgrading to usb c in the production costs CENTS per unit. For now I'm going with an old magnetic charger from my last gen phone so I don't wear out the port. I would have gladly paid more a wireless charging case.

title: bit overprices, but overall a good product
content: bit overprices, but overall a good product

title: $200 pair of earbuds defunct after 6 months
content: Initially I loved these headphones, they worked great and fit perfect, even when running or in the gym. I've had them for 6 months total and for the last 2 months the Right ear bud has been diminishing in quality and its to the point now where it's barely working. Jabra customer support has been no help, and unfortunately I'm passed the time frame to return to Amazon. So I'm out of luck. $200 pair of earbuds defunct after 6 months

title: Stopped working after a month
content: Randomly stopped working after a month or so of non-daily use. Trying to get a replacement now. Lots of hoops to jump through. Then found out they are on back order. Hope the new ones last longer.

title: Cool Execution, Standard Sound
content:
Very cool product. Headphones look subtle and cool. Charging case feel high quality.  Small enough for comfortable napping, and stays in your ear well enough to run.

The problem I have is the sound quality. It’s not doesn’t sound BAD, but it does sound like a standard headphone. This knocks two stars off of the review because for the price I paid for them, I want them to sound noticeably good. It seems like the main features they’re trying to sell are the microphones for calling and for voice assistant, but I bought them for music. If the headphones are almost $200 after tax and they do not sound great, then they aren’t going to work for me.

title: Great Earbuds, Issues with Reliability
content: Everything about the earbuds and app is great for normal and workout use. However, the left earbud stopped working after 3 months and the warranty program took months to complete. At the end Jabra was out of stock of the left earbud replacement so am still waiting 4 months later with only a right earbud. A co-worker had the same left earbud issue after 1 month of use.

title: A great set of earbuds. **UPDATED**
content:
I love these ear buds and have very high hopes for their longevity.  I go through earbuds at a maddening pace.  I've had expensive and cheap, wireless, corded, and now true wireless.  All earbuds I have previously owned would work great and then the wires would begin to get loose and eventually go in and out and drive me crazy.

This pair fits my ears perfectly and are extremely comfortable.  I was worried they would fall out during my workouts.  But, they stay in nicely and never distract me.

They are easy to use and pairing was super simple.  But my favorite part about them is the pass through feature.  Here is how it works.  The earbuds really shut out the outside world.  If you are wanting to focus on the music, you can do that easily.  But if you want to listen to what is going on around you, you can tap the right earbud and turn on the outside sounds.  It is so cool.  I can walk around and if someone needs my attention, I can listen to them without having to take the earbuds out of my ears.

As I write when I review every pair of earbuds I buy, I will edit this review if they crap out on me prematurely.  Honestly, at this price, these better last a good long while.  But so far, I'm very pleased with them.

**UPDATE**: I have had these over a year and they are still going strong.  I have dropped them a few times and they were not affected.  They still sound great and function flawlessly.  My only complaint is that they do have to be recharged fairly often.  I can go about two and a half hours before they run out of juice.  There are times when I clean and mow grass that I have to switch to other buds while these recharge.  Luckily they recharge pretty quick.  Overall, I am still very pleased with these earbuds.

title: Great Product
content: Great sound. Great noise cancellation. It has great mics, great for phone calls. Can be uncomfortable but my ears usually adapt after wearing a while. Only thing I don’t like is that the right earpod is the onlu one you can use for “one ear mode.” Overall love it.

title: Large, uncomfortable and very short lifespan
content: The sound quality is great, but only if you use the large tips, which are fairly uncomfortable to wear. The outer diameter is very large and is painful to wear for more than a short time. Once I figured out how to get them in my ear properly, they are good for short periods and do a good job of blocking outside sounds and good call quality. Unfortunately, they constantly disconnect and reconnect to my phone and computer, get interference from nearby devices, and after few months the left one shows connected but has no sound until I spend several minutes connecting, disconnecting, taking it in and out of the case before the Sound app realizes it is not actually connected and then let's you reconnect it.

title: Best designed earbuds. Impressive Quality and Features.
content: I bought these earbuds to replace a cheaper pair I thought I lost.  I am totally in awe of these Jabra Elite 65ts.  Everything about them is superior to the low end earbuds. The sound quality, the controls, the dual microphones for talking, the equalizer, the design, the battery life, the voice assistant capability, the phone app set these apart from the others. They are pricier but are not the most expensive earbuds out there. I love these earbuds, they are well worth the money. For those of you who have doubts about  pricier earbuds, you should check these out.  I highly recommend these earbuds.

title: Good performance
content: Great quality set of earphones follow by a great app to customize the sound for even better performance..I'm like..wow! Thumbs up..worth the $$

title: Great sound, but fit is not good for small ears
content: The sound quality was absolutely AMAZING!  Unfortunately, they wouldn’t stay in my small ears for more than 5-10 min.  Kept falling out.

title: Defective product/bad costumer service
content: After using for a month or two the left earbud sound level got very week. The customer service says no warranty for used products from amazon? wasted money...spend your money on other brands.

title: Amazing Earbuds
content:
These are by far the best wireless earbuds I have ever used. Walking to class in a busy downtown area, my music is all I can hear. In the gym, the headphones stay in place whether I’m playing basketball, running, or lifting weights, and I don’t have to listen to weights slamming, people grunting, or the gym music playing over my own.

The sound quality is awesome for such a small design and I am thoroughly impressed by how much noise is cancelled by them. The hear through feature is nice, however if your music is up too loud it’s kind of pointless because you can’t hear someone over the music anyways. But with this feature on, pausing the music allows you to hear them without having to take the headset off completely which is nice.

Battery life is great given the small size of the earbuds. Having a couple extra charges in the case is a plus and they do charge relatively quickly. I have had Bluetooth headsets before, so I’m used to remembering to charge them/the case.

They are comfortable to wear for long periods of use. When I’m at the gym, I almost forget that I have them on. Wearing a beanie or headband that is a little tight can cause them to push into your ear a little more and be less comfortable, but that’s not really a fault in the design.

The design overall is great as well. They don’t look as pretentious as the Air Pods. They look sleek and refined but still sporty and definitely not too bulky.

All in all, definitely worth the money if you use your headsets a lot.

title: Won't stay in ears.
content: I bet these are good, but they won't stay in my ears. Hopefully of enough people say something they'll make ones that do stay in your ear.

title: Audio was out of sync and I had to return them
content: These are nice and sound good, especially with the iOS app but my pair had audio sync issues. The audio in the left earphone was louder and a little slower. I tried pairing them over and over and nothing fixed it. I then searched and found a lot of similar issues for people on Reddit and elsewhere, and there didn't seem to be a fix so I returned them. It was a bummer because they sounded good...

title: Almost perfect...
content: They are beautiful, fit easily and sound great. ONE FLAW: customer service. They easily paired with my iPhone in seconds. Then I easily paired them to my iMac. Then the wouldn't pair back to my iPhone. It took multiple attempts to remove it from my phone and computer to get it to work again. Customer service was a robot. Then when I gave a more detailed account of my issues I got a note saying I'd hear back from someone in 2 business days. ANYONE who has worked with Apple knows you get customer service with minutes of texting them (or calling) and they'll spend the time to sort through your problem. CUSTOMER SERVICE makes the difference to me between Good and Great, so that definitely has me wondering if I shouldn't have gone with the ear pods, but I like this design better and assuming this problem doesn't keep recurring (warning: it has), then I'll stick with them. If I abandon them, I'll write it up again here.

title: Great
content: Super easy to use and love the sounds.  Easy connection.

title: Nice sound quality, good fit
content: My teenage son gives these two thumbs up. They stay in his ears really well, and they slip into a little case for charging. We recommend storing them in that case any time you take them out. He set them on his desk once and we had to search with a flashlight later to find one of them under the edge of the couch nearby. For a man, it's a good fit in the eardrum, comfortable, and stays in place well. The quality of sound is also really great, and I can attest to the fact that it dampens sound because I have to tap him to get his attention if he has these in. Great for studying and blocking out the sounds of a busy household.

title: Easy peasy
content: Long lasting charge, connects immediately, love the charging cade

title: The case would no longer close properly after 4 month
content:
The case that came with my Jabra headphones would not close properly after 4 months.  I went back to Jabra to ask for replacement.  They indicated that although I had the headphones through Amazon, that they would not honor the warranty as the I bought them "reconditioned" from the Amazon.  It was not clear to my that the Jabra warranty was voided.

Jabra is the only company that I have had this situation with

title: Best overall value for daily use.
content: Dropped one in the hot tub and it floated for a few seconds...that was 3 weeks ago and still works great.

title: Should have purchased these first...
content: I have been through 3 Samsung Gear Iconix latest edition due to having to return them because product use issues and finally threw them in the trash...Came upon these...Love them....Love them......I should have purchased these first!!!!!!Thank you Jabra..!!!!!!

title: Tremendous listening audio and comfort.  The lowest marks possible for calls.
content:
Update - These are the most wonderful wireless earbuds ever!  Awesome fit, comfortable for long periods, terrific sound!!  However and this is HUGE.  On phone calls the mic picks up every noise and amplifies it.  it is so distracting those on the other end of the phone demand I switch off the earbuds.  I cannot even wear in my quiet office because key strokes are so loud when I am on a call.  So disappointing.  Long ago gave up trying to use traveling in the airport.  Related to using during exercising.  When my wife calls she wont stay on the line while I am on the treadmill or other equipment.  Cannot ride my bide and take a call for same ambient noise levels.  But the sound listening to music is awesome while exercising.  So in summary, for all uses besides calling these are awesome and worth every penny.  Just beware for call.

Really solid item.  Excellent for exercising, running or cycling.  Fit secure and have good noise cancelling on my end.  Very comfortable for prolonged use.  Downside taking review down is those on the other end during calls.  Worthless earbuds when using in public.  Those on other end of phone say the ambient sound is louder than my voice and picks up everything.  To the point they have to monitor their volume control and turn down volume during calls.  Just no ambient noise filtering or cancellation for those you call. I travel a great deal and worthless for this application unless I find a quiet corner.  Have adjusted settings on app.  Reviewed Internet for solutions including Jabra site.  Nothing has helped.  Go for it if you don’t use for calls much in public.  If I could get my money back I would as my primary reason to purchase is handsfree traveling without wires.

title: Work as advertised
content:
Been using the Elite for a few weeks now and have true wireless earbuds really improves the wireless experience. Setup is a breeze and I've only had hiccups once or twice with the bluetooth connectivity but a quick reset fixed things.
I purchased the regular ones (vs active) and they are pretty snug in my ear during workouts and runs on the treadmill.

title: Great sound, comfortable, convenient
content:
I got these earbuds as a gift, and I love them. The sound quality is great, and the companion app has an equalizer.
  They are very comfortable and fit snugly in my ear. the material feels smooth, and there is no problem with it feeling cold after being in the case. Sometimes my ear gets itchy after using them for a long time, but that happens with all earbuds.
  The buttons are easy to press and the fact that they are physical buttons means no accidental pressing. The controls are simple and easy to learn, and I like the fact that the music pauses when you take a bud out of your ear. A feature I love is Hearthrough. By pressing the right button twice, I can hear what is going on around me. My hearing is slightly poor, and I actually find it easier to hear people when using Hearthrough versus without earbuds.
  The connection is great. The earbuds connect as soon as you take the right earbud out of the case, and I have had no connectivity problems.
  My only complaint is the case. It is difficult to open, as you have to press on the lid to open it. It feels very clumsy compared to the magnetic lids of most true wireless earbuds.
  My earbuds have never run out of battery, even though I use them very much. I simply plug the case in nightly, and never have to worry about battery.
  Overall, these are the best earbuds I have ever had, true wireless or not. I highly recommend them.

title: Meh
content: Sound quality is fine, everything else average. My big complaint they are constantly falling out. I hate fighting my technology.

title: Headphones are great when they work; Jabra support is terrible
content:
INITIAL REVIEW: (Left earbud doesn't work; chirping noise when returned to case; Jabra Support is terrible)
Everything was great for the first 3 months. Then, as soon as my return window and support window expired, the left earbud stopped working and now there is a chirping noise when I return the buds to their case.

The Jabra Support site is pretty sparse, and there wasn't any documentation about the chirping. I opened a Jabra support ticket yesterday morning and so far (almost 36 hours later) I still haven't even received an initial support response. Would not buy again because these are even more expensive than Apple AirPods, but the post-sale support is pretty bad considering the cost of the item.

I may update this review in the future as my support issue progresses, depending on if I ever hear back from Jabra and if they help me with my issue.

DECEMBER 2018 UPDATE:
Jabra finally sent me a replacement pair of headphones, and I haven't heard the chirping yet on the new ones. I hope it doesn't come back. I bumped it up one star (from 2 to 3) because they honored their warranty, but the support team was slow and not super helpful. It took over a week to even get a warranty *request* initiated with the support ticket.

title: It's good because it's wireless
content: Sound quality is about as good as a good set of wired earbuds. Nothing special about the design, except that it's simple and easy to use. Included eartips don't really fit that well. Connecting is easy. Battery life isn't amazing, but it charges quickly in the case. Ultimately, it's a good price for the awesome convenience of having zero wires. I look forward to seeing this technology improve in terms of sounds quality and cost.

title: Not a good buy, a GREAT buy.
content: I cannot express enough how much I absolutely love these. I’m constantly on the go and having music to listen to is almost a must. These are so comfortable and produce such a high quality sound that even after I get home or to the office I leave them in cause they’re so comfortable to wear and the sound quality is too notch. I really like the fact the linking of the two where if you take one out of your ear the sound pauses automatically and automatically starts up when you put it back in. Digging these baddies big time.

title: Comfortable and good sound control
content: They are easy to use and sound quality is very good.

title: Best earbuds I have ever owned
content: I love these earbuds! I have used them so much at the gym and around town that I'll forget I even have them in! The sound is great and no issues hear. I even use them at work with just the right one in! Takes a little getting used to but if you read the instructions and give it a bit of time to get used to these are amazing. The app could use a bit more work but overall 10/10

title: Excelente compra.
content: Un producto excelente.

title: The Seamless Connectivity of the AirPods with None of the Outside Noise
content:
These earbuds are fantastic! I had been looking for noise-isolating earbuds with the seamless connectivity of the AirPods and had struck out a few times. I owned—and ultimately returned—the previous model of these, the Jabra Elite Sport, because they wouldn’t let me connect to multiple devices. Every time I wanted to switch between my computer and my phone/tablet, I had to re-pair the earbuds. Every time. That got old fast. These earbuds switch seamlessly between all of my devices (3: comp, tablet, phone) by simply activating sound for the most recent source. Then there was the issue of wearability. My ears would start to hurt with the Elite Sport after about an hour or so. I worn these for hours at a time and don’t even feel them.

This model addressed every issue I had with the old one. Although I tend to have to switch out cushions with noise-isolating earbuds, the way these fit into my ear was perfect out of the box. The also lock into my ears effortlessly, so I no longer have to pull on my earlobes in weird ways to get them to plug my ear and block out noise.

Battery life is fantastic. I’ve worn them for 3-4 hours straight and they still have juice in them when I’ve checked. I haven’t needed to use the case to do an emergency charge because they’ve died on me in the middle of something, which was one of my fears when switching to battery-operated buds vs. wired buds.

Last thing I’ll mention is range. Without realizing it, I just walked away from my tablet to what was easily 50-75 ft away and the music never stopped. Great earbuds, totally worth trying if you’re looking to go wireless without sacrificing any of the “advantages” of wired headphones.

title: Units are too big to stay in my ear
content: I really wanted to like these earbuds.  I like the features and the app makes it so easy to set everything the way I want.  But they were too big to stay in my ear!  I used the smallest plugs, I twisted them in my ear canal as instructed. If I yawn, chew, or even smile too much, they pop out of my ear.  I kept pushing them back in, which just made my ears sore.  I had to accept they weren't a good fit and returned them.  It's not the ear piece that goes into my ear that is the problem.  The whole unit is too big for the size of my ear, so there's no way to get them to stay in.  Bought the Jlab Jbuds Air and they are smaller units and fit in my ear much better.

title: Don’t buy!!!!
content: They have pretty good sound. The charging box broke about 2 months in and it was difficult replacing. Then about 5 month later they stopped holding a charge. After waiting on hold for 20 mins I was told I can ship them back with the receipt and they will review it and I should get a replacement pair in a few weeks...

title: False Advertising: Not For Calls
content:
False advertising, plain and simple.  Don't fall for the sleek ads, this is not intended for calls whatsoever. I was walking on the street and the person on the other line described the backgrounds noise like "a buzz-saw" and a "waterfall".  Sound quality is mediocre at best.  Hearthrough feature continuously cuts in and out rendering it... annoying af?You can spend however much on your product marketing but if this is the result, I will not trust your company again.

I had that for $20. I don't need to pay another $160 for the exact same problem.

title: Excellent
content: Fits very well in the ears. Much better than my Eratos earbuds (clumsy & large). As a result, sound quality is good. Best wireless earbuds I’ve found so far & ive tested lots.

title: Defective after a couple weeks, customer service doesn’t acknowledge anyone.
content: Lasted couple of weeks before I have problems. The earbuds won’t turn off/disconnect when I put them into the case which gets annoying. I miss notifications/phone calls when the earbuds are put away because they are pairing to my phone when they’re supposed to be off. I have sent several customer service requests and waited on hold for 30 minutes. There is no customer service. It’s a scam. They got my $200 and ran with it. Sound and battery are good at least.

title: Amazing till they break
content:
The Good:
I did not expect to like these earbuds as much as I did. I thought it would be OK, but my gosh, I've converted. I do not plan to go back to wired headphones after picking these up. Great comfort - the buds stay in the ear effortlessly through even vigorous exercise.

But, it does go DOWNHILL.

The Bad:
My left earbud is basically a useless piece of plastic now, after only 6 weeks of ownership. No water damage or hard drops or anything. It seems to be a bad solder - the speaker only plays when I physically squeeze the earbud housing.

As much as I love this product, it's simply not cool that it was built so cheaply. I'd encourage avoiding the device until they sort out their durability standards.

title: Should have gotten airpods
content:
TLDR: Horrible connection with any of my devices, lack of bass, falls out of my ears with minimal head shaking, kinda bad customer service, and no bells and whistle like NFC, case tracking, magnetic earbud holding, or wireless case charging makes this a huge disappointment.

I got these for Christmas and while using it, I noticed that it would just randomly cut in connection, even when my phone is right next to them. While this isn't usually a problem for me, these earbuds just would always fall out whenever I slightly shake my head, which always gives me a small heart attack from the fear of dropping it behind a car seat or something. After less than a month, the right earbud stopped working, and because the way the earbuds work, you can't use the left one without the right. So after waiting for nearly 3 months and multiple phone calls, I got my replacement, but between the long wait time and just the horrible connection quality, I just put them back into my junk drawer and continued to use the wired Sony earbuds that have treated me much better. Even though I'm sick of apple and their overpriced products, I know they at least can deliver a quality product at a similar price.

title: Great headphones
content: Got these for my fiancé as a gift. He loves them and has used them almost everyday. He says the sound quality is great and they are easy to set up/pair to your phone

title: I wanted to love
content: I liked everything about these except for the fit. I just could not get a secure fit. I really wanted these to work for me. I loved the functionality and features.

title: How small they are and fit in my ears thru my workouts!!
content: Thank You!!

title: Best true wireless product I’ve tried
content: The fit was very comfortable and worked for me. The thing I like most is the call quality. The person on the other side can hear me well. These don’t have ANC, but the passive noise cancelling was impressive. When I wear them I don’t hear much outside unless I turn on the “hear through”. Overall great product. I’d recommend them.

title: Very nice overall quality for the money
content: I have bought 3 pairs of these already, for gifts for family, you have to get the comply foam go along with it to make the best out of the sound quality.  Fits nice in the ears without fatigue for  more than 4 hours. Connectivity is good, no lag.

title: Great for Runners!
content: Love these earbuds and would definitely recommend over Apple's Earpods as they stay put while running and don't look goofy hanging down below your earlobes.  Sweating creates no problems and sound is amazing - no breakout whatsoever.

title: very finicky device
content: I like the buds, but the connection and having one on vs two on is very finicky, sometimes it just works, sometimes you have to turn them off and turn back on with the sound app to get to work properly. Also have a hard time finding them when I scan for bluetooth from a device that doesn't have the sound app loaded. Not bad, Not great and seeing as they were a Christmas present, I'm kinda stuck with them :-)

title: Three Stars
content: The ear buds are good but the battery life is only good for about 5 hrs.

title: Can't be heard - left ear bud stops working and won't easily turn back on.
content: People could not consistently hear me on calls.  The left ear bud repeatedly stopped working and tech support was unable to fix the problem and were generally unapologetic about the issue.  I don't think I'll buy any Jabra products given the poor support and lack of concern about their product not functioning properly.

title: Great Experience with minimum flaws!
content:
Cons:
Biggest drawback I felt is that the left bud doesnt have mic, however in airpod you can use left or right to answer calls.
Rarely the person hears echo of his own voice while Im on Jabra earbud, something which the company must rectify!
Rarely, the earbud receives call with full distortion, I have to swap it to mobile audio and back to get it fine, strange!
The above rarely would be like once or twice in 30 calls.
Pros:
Amazing battery life, quick charging.
Clear and crisp audio, good noise cancellation, other person dont recognize if Im on earbud or not.
Can connect to 2 devices at time, so I can watch video on laptop and listen audio in my mobile, useful.
Fits perfectly into ear.

Verdict : The price should be lesser, rest all good.

title: Disconnect constantly
content: They constantly disconnect and cut out every few seconds while listening to music very disappointed cause they are good quality and fit in my ear while being active.

title: Great truly wireless earbuds.  Everything works fine except jabra sound+ app
content: The best true wireless earbuds that I have bought.  it fits into my ears absolutely perfect and does not come off at all.  very comfortable and I can listen as long as I want without any discomfort.  Music sound signature and quality are excellent for what it is.  It does not the biggest bass which is perfect for me because I rather listen to Jazz or refined vocal songs.  However, the only drawback for me is that my phone does not fully download and work with Jabra sound+ app.  I have Huawei Mate  SE and maybe it might be my phone problem.  Other than that, everything is good.

title: Pretty good sound
content:
After a few weeks of use I lost the right bud and was unable to locate it using the app. I liked the product but too expensive to lose and not easily replaced. I wouldn't purchase this product or ones like it unless they are a lot cheaper.

Overall the sound was pretty good but the connection was a little weak while walking.

title: The Jabra’s are the best. I still use my AirPods for conference calls ...
content:
I purchase the 65t’s from Jabra direct and have had for almost two months.  I own Apple AirPods and have tried the Anker Zolo Liberty + through Kickstarter.  Overall for the price and sound, the Jabra’s are the best.

I still use my AirPods for conference calls as I can still hear the outside world easily, but the sound for music is much better with the Jabra’s. Just make sure you have the right earbud piece on or a tight seal as this will give you better bass response and over all a better sound.  Also, I found them to get better with about 10 hours of burn in or use.

Of all the wireless earbuds - The B&O are the best sounding...unfortunately, the constant dropout of the left earbud every 10 minutes become annoying and is a problem with them as the left is a slave to the right earbud - if they fix this, then the B&O.  The Anker Zolo's while nice - the left earbud died and I was refunded.

Over all I liked the Jabra's and the trick is a good tight fit in the ear.  Otherwise I still would go Apple AirPods if you also really use them for phone conversations. (FYI - The Jabra's are very good for phone conversations - just need to dial them in on the app). FYI - I use a Apple iPhone X with these.

title: Love the buds, hate the app.
content: The 65's are a good fit and have great sound but the app is not friendly at least to me. Barely look at it. But back to the buds, they slip right into the ear and do not lose traction...love 'em.

title: Game changing headphone
content: By far one if the best products I haveever bought,sound quality amazing, app integration very impressive,really enjoyed the presets if sounds that the app offered. Ability to perform firmware updates using the app and charging case was a major selling point for me,in addition the integrationif Alexa/Siri was neat, inly complaint was the left ear headphone mechanism is very tricky compared to the right ear. The right ear is built very responsive to touch whereas the left is engineered dufferently so beware of that. Overall superb product :)

title: Audio Dropout
content: The left ear doesn’t connect consistently and drop out every 5 seconds. Horrible purchase.

title: Great product for the price
content: These are great headphones.  I was at first wary of them because I have heard of the lag between video and sound and I use these at the gym while i watch videos on the bike.  Technology seems to have solved that issue.  it did take me a while to figure out how to sync them up.  They are not BOSE and I probably couldn't tell the difference.  The bass is fine as is the overall sound quality.  I got them for a black friday price and didn't pay the $160+ so they were a great value for me.  If you are on the fence, go ahead and buy them.  You'll love them

title: Good audio quality, fantastic range, great feature set
content:
I rarely write reviews, but these are so good I felt like it would be a disservice not to. I've been using Bluetooth headphones for at least 5 years and there by far the best earbuds I've ever used, and the best Bluetooth headset for phone calls I've ever used.

I work out almost everyday, use them at work, and enjoy carpentry, and they work well in all scenarios. They only have a 4hr battery life, but the case will charge them in transit *fast*. The battery life has never been an issue in the past 5mo.

Likes
=====
-Audio quality
-Range: seriously, the range is sick. My gym is in my basement and I was listening to music after a workout, walked up three flights of stairs, and only then did I realize I left my phone in the basement and the headphones were STILL CONNECTED AND STREAMING
-The Hear Through feature: I don't think I'll ever buy another pair of headphones without this feature
-build quality: I've dropped them several times outside of the case and they're still going strong

Dislikes
======
-case's latching mechanism isn't super, so it's conceivable they could fall out

I highly recommend this product for quality, price, durability, and future set!

title: Great product
content: I like just about everything about these. Great overall product

title: It's garbage
content:
Broken right out of the box. Left ear doesn't work, even after charging.

Buy something else. There's obviously an issue here that Jabra isn't fixing. Look at all the other reviews.

title: Best true wireless earbuds I've tried
content:
Surprisingly good sound quality. Initially I was unimpressed, but after swapping in the large ear flanges, I got a really good seal (surprisingly because the posts are pretty short so they don't go far in) and all of a sudden there was the bass. Because they seal without going as far in to the ear, they're also really comfortable. I'd almost say I could forget I'm wearing them. I've had them a week so far. I've made many calls (admittedly all from indoors -- haven't tried a windy location yet) and callers say I'm very clear. Calls come through in both ears.
The UI is well thought out; the buttons all work as they should, and are pretty logical. Google Assistant worked first try too. The Hear Through mode is very useful.
The only thing I can say that's not totally positive is they're a little hard to get out of the case because they're light and beveled and a bit slippery. Some grip around the back would be useful. But that's very minor and I got used to it quickly.
I tried cheaper true-wireless earbuds and returned them. These are the ones to get. Expensive but worth it.

title: Too big for Asian ear
content:
I bought this one as a gift for my friend she uses only one site as right site, earlier she try to use left site but it doesn't work what can I do? I looking on the policy return window already closed. Would you please give me a suggestion I am appreciated
Best Regards,
Felix Phetngao.

title: Not for the gym!
content: If you're not active these are great. I bought them for the gym and they're constantly falling out! For $180 you'd expect better from ear buds "made for working out" but I wouldn't recommend these for anyone active at all.

title: Good Sound Quality
content: Good sound quality.  Blue tooth connection is strong.  Sound isolation is good when they are in place. Would have given it five stars but they fall out of my ears.  They fall out when I ride my bike, which was my initial reason for purchase.  Two hours into a nine hour flight, one fell out while eating dinner on a plane trip from Europe.  Upon arrival, I had to wait for everyone to exit the plane so I could find it.  It had rolled back three rows.  For the price they should have come with more options for staying in they ear.

title: Performs as expected
content: Use them during my exrrcise

title: Work great but would add/change some stuff.
content: They are great headphones but wish some things were different. I wish you could use each headphone individually so one can charge while the other is playing. I wish you could share one of the ear buds so me and a friends could listen at the same time. Those are just wishes. One very annoying fault these headphones have is when they are in hear-through mode and you are clicking between different things on your phone, every time you change screens or pull up a new tab or something there is a slight lapse and the headphones stutter and cut out. This doesnt happen if listening to music only when using hear-through to listen to your environment. Very very very very annoying. But otherwise the sound quality is great. Call quality is great in both directions. Battery life is fantastic.

title: Bad. Really bad.
content: Very bad experience. The buds do have some nice features, namely the design is appealing and the connection is smooth and stable BUT they are terribly flawed from a sound perspective. The issue is that if you wear them tightly you completely lose volume and bass (I suppose they are designed to use part of the inner ear chamber as a woofer/resonance chamber) and the noise cancelling effect ends up distorting the sound, to the point that you almost don't ear any music and/or you hear an extremely bad echo. You can avoid that by wearing the buds loosely but they will move and fall off while you workout, so being this WORKOUT BUDS the issue completely defeats the purpose. If your idea of workout is sitting still on a bench admiring the girls these earbuds are definitely the product for you, in all other instances, avoid like the plague. Returned after 2 workout sessions (with 2 different sizes of plug to see if the issue went away - it didn't).

title: More comfy than Apple buds
content: I like these much better and are much more comfortable than the Apple ear buds.

title: When the product works it's great.
content: I bought these back in July 2018. They worked great and I loved them. That lasted for about 2 weeks. The left earbud stopped pairing with the right and works maybe 1 out of 50 times. I called customer support the day it stopped pairing and they sent me an RMA. Unfortunately, I left the country a couple days later and wasn't able to get around to sending the earbuds in to get replaced until about a month after the fact. The RMA slip had expired by that point which was expected so no issue. I tried emailing and calling to get another RMA sent out but never heard back. So, I decided to live with the fact that the left earbud doesn't work 90% of the time. Then a couple weeks ago I finally decided to try again and get a new RMA. I spoke with tech support and gave them my case number. The guy told me he was going to send out my RMA the next day. So, I was like okay cool, sounds good. It has now been 2 weeks and I have not received any RMA.....I'm currently on hold trying to get a hold of tech support. I decided to write this review while I wait. So, like the headline says. The earbuds are great when they actually work. However, I am giving the product a 1 star review due to poor customer service and the fact that the product stopped working properly a couple weeks after purchasing.

title: Significant lag when watching video on iPhone Xs
content: Sounds alright and connects to iPhone alright, but the audio has a significant lag when watching video. This is a deal breaker for me as I want to use these to listen to music but also to watch videos.

title: Great sound and easy to use!
content:
I freakin'  love these earbuds. They are incredibly comfortable and won't budge during my workouts or runs. These buds tuck nicely into its oval shaped charging case, which stores the pods in between my workouts and keeps them from getting lost. I find that the charging pod case is extremely hard to open. Actually, you have to squeeze and open the case at the same time to lift the lid to get it open. Love the google assistant feature as well. These buds can last 5 hours on their own and then an additional 10 hours if they are charged up in between workouts. ( Much longer than my Apple earpods. )

You can find other less expensive wireless bluetooth earphones, but the alternatives either aren't sweat resistant for workouts, or don't fit as well. So overall, they are a very good set to own.

title: Connectivity with Bluetooth transmitters.
content:
Understanding the constraints of this Bluetooth device would be helpful in making an inform purchase.
I called Jabra support with a connection issue while pairing with my Taotronic TT-BAO-14 transmitter. This is the conclusion.
“”Hi Keith,
The earbuds do not officially support usage with anything except for mobile phones and tablets. We are unable to assist with the connection to the Bluetooth Transmitter as it is an unsupported device.””
I am waiting for a response from Taotronics on their device.
All is not equal in the Bluetooth world .

title: awful
content: got these for christmas and i was very excited, but these are a joke. havent been able to connect to any device but one, and now the sound is cutting in and out with that one. cant return them because i got rid of the box so im stuck with these $200 pieces of trash

title: Wear them everyday.
content: Love these, better than air pods

title: Best Earphones I’ve Ever Owned
content: These earphones are great. Great sound quality and they fit snug in the ear. I’ve put them to the test during my workouts and they’ve never fallen out. The noise cancellation & hear through comes in handy on the subway and in loud places. I plan on buying another pair soon!

title: Not great for exercise
content: “Active” is misleading...they don’t stay in your ears if you sweat at all.  Should have bought the sport version that have wing tips. Sound was fine otherwise for non-active wear.  For what they cost, disappointed.

title: Don't stay in my left ear...
content:
I would like these more if the left one would stay in my ear.  LOL.

I tend to tilt my head when I exercise.  Not sure what that says about me.

Consequently, anything on the left side is going to be disadvantaged gravity wise.  The left bud constantly falls out no matter what I do (haven't tried epoxy yet. LOL)

Other than that they work fantastic.  Sound is great.  Love the look.

title: Perfect running headphones
content: Love love love these. Great for working out and jogging. Or sneaking music in at work. Thanks!

title: How to get a replacement??
content: One side stopped working just a few days after the return window ended

title: High quality and durable
content: These are excelent quality earbuds that have survived many very sweaty workouts, and unfortunately a few good drops on the asphalt.

title: As advertised..
content: Great sound with the EQ. Fit is okay, without being uncomfortable.

title: They're durable
content: The greatest air buds by far the best,out do iPhone air buds any day

title: Worth every penny.
content: These are keepers. Well worth the money. Only down side is, it takes some getting used to not hang up on people when you touch your ear. Other than that.... great ear phones, great sound, nice recharge case, beautiful hook up to Bluetooth, and the app let's you keep them with in with a mike so you can hear your surroundings. Very cool feature.

title: Unfortunately not a fit for me
content: I really wanted to like these but I couldn't find a size that fit my ear. One size was too tight and it hurt my ear. Next size down was too loose and they would tend to fall out and let too much ambient noise in.

title: Good earbuds with some negatives
content:
Pros:

Sturdy
Love the charging case
Battery life
Comfortable
Won't slip out while I run, box, lift weights
Connects moment you take them out of case
Accompanying app

Cons:
-Sound is fine. But for the price I expected better
-Bluetooth connection is meh. You can't get very far from your phone. I have $35 headphones with better reach

title: Best workout headphones!
content:
I LOVE these headphones. I feel like they have truly changed my life for the better.

Prior to buying them, I looked at so many online reviews trying to decide what wireless headphones would be the best. I was down to my top 2 - Bose Soundsport Free Wireless and the Jabra Elite Active. I ordered both and really was leaning towards Bose. I am the owner of the Bose Soundsport II and wow, those headphones are amazing. I really thought Bose would offer me just as good experience with the soundsport free headphones and boy oh boy I was so wrong. I read reviews about how they stuck out of your ears and man, they weren't even kidding. Those headphones were huge! Jabra in comparison was amazing. They are small enough that they don't stick out of your ears. I've used these headphones while walking around in my neighborhood talking with my mom and people have looked at me like I was crazy...they thought I talking to myself because these Jabra headphones are so small that they weren't noticed! Furthermore these Jabra headphones come with EXTRA features, which I didn't even realize existed! They have an active mode, focus mode where you can let background noise in or filter them out. There's definitely a difference. Furthermore, they come with preset soothing ambience sounds that you can play while trying to do work. Do they fall out of your ears? NO! It has not happened yet. One final thing I love - ability to connect to more than one device! I just realized a few days ago, I can pair my Jabra headphones with my phone and iPad. This ability has made life so much easier since I don't have to switch between devices everytime. I have not noticed any lagging with videos, listening to music. The sound quality is good.

title: Great Purchase
content: This is by far my husband's greatest gift ever! He tells me every time he uses them.

title: How are you making it worse???
content:
I had a good first month with this headphone. I liked it so much I bought the active as a backup. At first the sound was good, connectivity was good, Sound+ app was good. I don't know how it became so terrible in the end. Below, I'm going to compare "before" and "after", which points to when I first received the headphones and now.

Before:
Headphones connectivity was good, even on the bus where everybody was listening to some kind of device.

Jabra  Sound+ app had lots of configurations to mess with. Two thing I actually used were hear through and auto stop when headphones are taken out. I disabled it so I can give a headphone to a friend right next to me and both of us can listen

After:
Headphones disconnect for no reason. Sometimes when I'm facing a certain way, othertimes it just disconnects every 15 seconds for 5 seconds and then come back. This can happen anywhere and doesn't matter whether how close the phone is.

The sound app features are gone. The auto stop is no longer possible. The detection is made by range of one ear piece with another so you would have to be cheek against cheek against someone if you want to share the headphones. Worse yet, I can't tell if the headphones's intermittent stopping is related to this feature is not since I can no longer control it.

Worse yet, the headphones are really bad. It can't hear you while in your ear so sometimes I have to take out the right ear piece and use it as a microphone. However, thanks to the removal of the autostop, the headphones will turn off whatever I'm doing.

Jabra, fix your firmware. It's easy, just revert your codebase. Whoever is making updates is making retrogrades. STOP IT!

title: Better then expected
content: I purchased a pair for my husband and myself and they work great. They stay in place and are very comfortable.

title: Tough and Convenient but, not perfect
content:
After using these for over 6+ months and now going into the New Years, I can confidently say that these headphones are worth while for the average consumer. I work in a restaurant and a warehouse, and these headphones were constantly exposed to oily environments and I have dropped than more than a few times and they still hold up. Don't let the plastic housing fool you, these things are strong and only suffered 1 minor scratch.
Even now the battery life still goes up to 5 hours on a full charge and ~3 hours with hear-through mode on. I have noticed though that it takes longer to charge, ~10min longer compared to when I originally bought it.
I'm no audiophile but the sound quality was good enough for me. Currently, sometimes the left bud produces some background static which is annoying but nothing a hard reset can't fix and overall I'm glad they provided an accompanying app with a equalizer even though to me its basicly useless. The mic picks up a lot of background sound but is able to clearly pick up my voice when I talk and the proximity to your phone/device while in use is managable at 30 ft without any obstructions, otherwise, it's nearly impossible to use it in the house with a wall or two blocking the signal and you will most likely have to have it on your person. The hear-through mode and the ability to activate the google assistant via long press on the right bud is honestly my favorite feature and reason to would recommend it to others and give this 5 stars. It allows me to be hands free from distractions while driving, hear co-workers, listen to announcements on the bus/subway without stopping my music.
Overall great for the average commuter and fantasticly long lasting product. I bought it as a Christmas gift during Black Friday and would probably do it again this year.

title: Falls out of ears
content: Doesn't stay in ear at all. Really really uncomfortable. Wish I could return.

title: Sound quality
content: Like the sound quality

title: Absolutely in love!!
content: Hands down my best headphone purchase of all time, and I owned a pair of Bose QC 35 II. This product is way better than the price.  To start, the headphones are loud and comfortable. It was a bit awkward to put in at first but you get use to it by the 2nd-3rd time. They do not fall out of my ears. They work decent with phone calls (7/10 calls are clear on the first try without reconnecting or constant “hello??s”) The app works wonders in having personal sound settings. The Bluetooth connection varies from device to device. I just got an iPhone XS MAX and the connection is far superior to my old OnePlus 5. Overall these headphones excel in sound, call, and Bluetooth quality. Great headphones for a bomb price

title: They _NEVER_ Turn Off (until the battery is drained)
content:
Unlike two other pairs of 'true wireless' bluetooth earbuds, these _do not turn off_ when placed back into the charging case. It's ridiculous that I can turn them off by hand (holding down their respective power buttons until their LEDs flash red), but the moment I put them in the charging case, they _TURN BACK ON_ and re-connect to my phone. If I happen to receive a phone call while my earbuds are in the charging case in my pocket, then I am extremely frustrated when the person I'm attempting to speak to cannot hear me and vice-versa. It's only after a few seconds that I realize this mistake has a occurred and I have to switch the audio control _back_ to the handset, but by that time they've already hung up, thinking the connection was bad.

I'm sure the audio quality is fantastic, as well as the noise cancellation, etc. But until these function _AS THEY ARE INTENDED AND EXPECTED TO_, they are completely useless for my needs.

title: Water proof is an understatement
content:
To start these have great sound, battery is awesome, noise isolation is more like noise cancelling; I use in flights to watch movies on an iPad and hear nothing but the movie.

I know these are active so expect they would do well with sweat, rain that type of environment.

Today I got stuck in a downpour, puddles in minutes. The right bud fell out into a puddle, was pushed against the edge of the lawn and it took 3-5 minutes to find.

It was in about 2 inches of water for that long. I thought for sure they were done.

I wiped it off and let it sit for an hour. Figured I would give it a shot.

They turned right on, connected and sound perfect and calls remain clear.

Worth every penny. Thank you Jabra, job well done.

title: Favorite pair of earbuds and headphones.
content: These are my 2nd pair of bluetooth earbuds and i gotta say this was a great purchase. I came from the jaybirds x3 and they are so comfortable and never fall out. Battery life is great,  connectivity is fantastic,  highly recommend.

title: Nice when the charger worked. Useless now.
content: It would be nice to have a working charging case. I liked them while they lasted but now they’re bricked since the charger is defective.

title: Perfect headphone
content: Good quality product, sound quality is exceptional

title: NOT for Apple devices, not compatible
content:
Absolutely hate them. Two fatal flaws:

1–They hurt the ears after twenty minutes
2–if you use multiple Apple devices, and it is paired to 2 or more Apple devices (two different phones for example or one phone and one iPad), even if paired and showing in the Bluetooth menu of your device, it simply won’t ever switch to the other one again. You can press on the Jabra all you want in the Bluetooth settings of your device, it will say « cannot connect » even though it is paired. You have to « forget » the Jabra then re-pair again EVERY TIME.

Not compatible for anyone who wants this paired to more than one Apple device. It’s going to be returned ASAP.

title: Very comfortable
content:
Really good for running,  working out
Small fits well. hear through works great for gym or running - and priced well too

title: Very pleased with this product
content:
My only minor complaint is the charging case the earbuds use. The cover feels like it won't age well with constant opening and closing. Would have much preferred magnetic lid.

Everything else is positive, comfortable fit in the ear, excellent battery life, good audio quality and the mic works very well during calls, much better than some others that I've used.

Very happy with my purchase!

title: Great fit! Great Sound! Easy to use!
content: They are clear and work great! The app allows you to customize the sound! They fit perfectly and if you want them to fit even better you can buy cheap memory foam tips to seal the deal

title: Compact
content: Very compact!  Long periods of use make my ears sore (2 hours).  And the buttons on the buds are not intuitive... theres a learning curve to use effectively

title: Very Impressed
content: Great sounding. easy to use. I have found them very comfortable. One thing as with most earbuds, You have to get the correct tips installed. If the tips and the fit in your ears are not just right they will sound like crap. So try different tips for each ear till you get the correct fit. Sweet when you get it right.

title: The fitness features WILL NOT work with iPhone X
content: Do not buy these earbuds for the fitness features!!!  If you read the reviews the earbuds will not connect to the application ( trust me I know, I’ve spent three hours trying to get mine to connect and it’s a known issue that their garbage) and gets like one star in the App Store. So that means no heart rate, workout feature, ect... If you want standard ear buds with no extra features, buy them. BTW, I own an iPhone X and my phone, the earbuds, and the application are all updated.

title: I love these.
content: I use these when running and they fit really well with good sound quality.  Phone reception is easy and clarity is very good.

title: Wouldn't recommend
content:
Pros:
Great sound.
Easy to charge and keep charged.
No wires.

Cons:
Extremely uncomfortable.
Poor fit.
Clicking noise due to Bluetooth connection.
Case is impossible to get open, the trick is to put your thumb across the length of the lid and pull it open. Nothing else works.
Sound pass through is from playing sound from the mic, which doesn't work. You just hear your breathing.

title: Good thing
content: Nice device! Contact steadily, good sound quality, nice desigin

title: Disappointed
content: Although the product has multiple size buds, I had a difficult time fitting any of them correctly in my ear, even with the requisite twists into place.  More importantly, I also had difficulty pairing via Bluetooth to my iPad and iPhone.  Sometimes they just could not connect, even when I followed the instructions and once reinstalled the software.  For this price, it was a big disappointment.

title: You really can't top these.
content: Best wireless headphones for fit and sound I've ever had.

title: Comfortable, truly wireless headphones with great build quality
content: I love the fit and sound quality. Because they fit in your ear they do a great job of blocking outside noise - so much so that there is a “focus mode” that stops your audio playback and lets hear your environment through a microphone. This is so you don’t have to remove the earbud to have a conversation.  The carrying case is also a charger.  It seems that they thought of everything with these earbuds.  I wish there were color options other than black to make it easier to find in your bag. I would definitely purchase these again.

title: Ear canal fit a problem
content: The buds appear to be pretty well made.  My problem was with the ear canal fit and bluetooth drop out.  I tried all the "donuts" to get a tight seal, the largest seemed to work best.  Once the seal was made there was plenty of bass response.  They almost always felt like they were going to fall out, and in fact they did on a few occasions .  Its surprising that a neck lanyard wasn't included.  The bluetooth link was constantly being dropped.  I know that all bluetooth devices suffer from this, but it was excessive, several time a song.  The sound quality was acceptable, especially when a good seal was made.  The volume buttons on the left bud were a little hard to use, the right off and on were okay.  I have since moved on to Bose Soundsport, and for me is better overall.
