title: Best headphones I have ever had
content:
Good sound.  Didn't break when dropped 5  feet. Battery life is nice because they charge every time you put them away.

Update, over a year later. Still the best headphones I have ever had. The charging case is cheap and costs 70 dollars to replace.  The headphones are completely worthless without this accessory.

Update, new charging case broke the left ear bud. It now cracks and pops constantly.

title: Awesome product
content: Enjoying the sound quality, noise cancellation and volume control.  Well suited for a range of activity including sports, and the units stay in place without need to adjust.  Great product and worth the price.

title: Jabra are the WORST
content: I am trying to arrange a replacement for faulty ear pods and the support email ignores me completely!!!

title: These are great!
content:
Was a bit worried when I read all the bad reviews on here, but ended up getting a pair anyway. They are well made and works great. I have not experienced any hissing sound or static. The charge last pretty close to advertised time.

The only thing is I made sure is to buy from Jabra Direct seller instead of other ones.

Also get the Comply True Wireless Pro tips. I tried several replacement tips and they are the most comfortable.

title: Phenomenal performance
content: I love the product: the way it fits, the sound quality, the easy pairing, and the battery life. The only thing that could be improve with the headphones would be to have them magnetically lock inside the case. They fall out way to easy if you’re not paying attention.

title: Poor Sound Quality
content: I bought these ear buds to primarily use at the gym. Pros: they look good, pair easily and work well for calls. Cons: terrible sound quality when listening to music, they do not stay in your eat with movement, drastically overpriced for what you get. I would not buy these again.

title: Lost connection after a few seconds with iPhone 8plus
content: Had to return the Jabra Elite 65t due to connection issues with my iPhone. After a few days of use the earphones would not hold a connection with my iPhone for more than a few seconds. Working in IT Support I used everything I knew to get them to work. unpair/repair, reboot phone, made sure iOS was up to date, and messed with the Bluetooth settings. Tested them with my girlfriends Android and they worked fine, the earphones seem to have issues working with iOS. If you have an iPhone avoid these until Jabra can iron out the issue but if you run Android you should be fine.

title: Awesome earbuds
content: These are awesome and fit nicely in the ear and stay put. Love the sound quality and how small they are

title: Awesome product
content: These are the absolute best I've tried. The sound is very balanced, and the app allows for a ton of customization. The fit is wonderful, it sounds great on calls, charges fast, the case is perfect sized, and I love how it pauses music when you take either one of the buds out. I also love being able to skip tracks, and activate Google assistant. Only thing that could make it better would be a little more clear bass. That's it though.

title: Contacted Jabra about Warranty
content: Jabra's are not working properly, and when I contacted them, they never got back to me. Customer service is so important, and it's disappointing that Jabra does not value that.

title: Battery pack shortens & sound quality okay
content:
Pros:
-Fit is nice. It fits snuggly and it's never fell out of my ear while I run or lift weights.
-You can activate the microphones so that you can talk to someone without taking off the earphone.
-There is no noise cancellation, but it does block outside noise because they are in ear.
Cons:
-The battery life of the battery pack life reduces greatly. I have only had the battery pack for a few months and only charge it when it's red. Now after two sessions of 1.5 hours use of headphones the battery pack will turn from green to red.
-sound quality- honestly I think the airpods are better. I compared it with my friends airpods, and I feel like the sound from the airpods are crisper.

title: Horrible support
content:
These are okay earbuds. I didn't like it for 3 reasons:
1. Physical buttons: pressing a button pushes an earbud deeper to your ear. Pretty uncomfortable feeling.
2. Every time you remove or insert left earbud, you hear some clicks in the right one and a little delay in sound.
3. You can't just give one earbud to someone nearby to share sound stream.

But, the most disappointing is the fact that support didn't reply to any of my 3 emails. I just got automatic responses with ticket id's but nothing else! I was ok with just replacing the product or getting advice from them, but now I'm willing to return it.

title: Disappointed
content: They are uncomfortable, they feel like they are going to fall out no matter what size ear gel you use, and they don’t get loud enough.

title: ... for them from Amazon so I got mine at Best buy. They worked fine the first day
content: Didn't want to wait for them from Amazon so I got mine at Best buy. They worked fine the first day. Wasn't super impressed with the sound quality. Now they were in the charger overnight and the right one won't turn on, only the left one. Tried to manually power it on and nothing. Charged overnight again and still nothing. Taking them back for a refund.

title: Zero bass, connection with app causes static
content: I wanted to like these and gave it a try for about three weeks. Sound quality is good, and the bass exists, but you would have to jam them into your ear with your finger to hear it. The iPhone app offers alot of control, but unfortunately when the app is running, it makes the earbuds buggy and static-y. I had some issues with only one turning on when I took them out of the case.  They are solidly made, but in the end not for me - too many issues.

title: More than adequate
content: Hard to find the right fit intially, but once you do, very few issues. Fairly secure, can fall out if you are sweating or with vigors activity.

title: Loud and sturdy!
content: Love them since they are louder than most truly wireless earbuds

title: Overall very pleased
content: Love that these stay in place while running.  Too bad I need to use my phone to skip songs through spotify.

title: Bad call quality, good for music
content: The sound quality is great the best ,the volume is not that great but no the worst.the downgrade of it is the call quality ,call quality is really bad specially while driving.for that price I expected a better call quality. I only use it for music.

title: Wasn't impressed
content: I have a pair of touch to earbuds, they were $28. These are a lot more. As far as sound quality and volume these Jabra are better, but  not by that much and  certainly  not worth the $140 difference .  They have twice the battery life at 5 hours. These have push button rather than touch control like my other ones. These also do not have the magnetic grip battery charge which is a lot quicker and easier to use than this setup. These do have more options, like an app with an equalizer amongst other things and these are supposed to have voice control. The price difference between these and my other ones is huge and in all honesty I am disappointed, because the difference in quality is not that huge.

title: no bass, cannot get secure fit
content:
I don't know what I am missing that all of the other reviewers are getting. I think these sound good but there is absolutely no bass. I have not been able to get a secure fit with any of the added tips. I have never had problems with this with my jaybird 3s or even my cheapo Jlabs ($48).
I have tried every position possible with each set.
I think the issue is the buds themselves are huge and somehow don't let me push them into my ears far enough. They also fall out without much movement.
They are very light and clearly about 95% plastic and feel cheap. Sorry I spent my $165 so I get to give my opinion.

title: Personally
content: Omg where do I start! Personally love em!

title: Big price tag with even bigger disappointment
content: Left earbud started giving static noise after 1 hour of use. Then sound drop/mute started. This is after software update which was supposed to rectify the issue. Very disappointing.

title: no regrets
content: my husband says these are the best.

title: Fit
content: I have small ears ,and the buds hurt while I.

title: The best NO Wire headset if you dont want to look like your in Something About Mary
content: The sound is so good and the connection is so quick.

title: Quality is outstanding.
content:
After many hours of deliberation I settled on a different, cheaper pair of wireless buds. I made a mistake. My first impression of these is that the build quality is fantastic. The fit is great, bass is just thumpy enough. I'm glad I returned the others and opted for these, I'm not disappointed.

My only gripe is that the buds are not magnetic with the case like many other models, hopefully in the next version they implement that.

title: Exactly what I wanted
content: Great product

title: Poor range, but great sound.
content:
I so badly wanted these to be five stars. I did so much research before I purchased, the most expensive headphones I have gotten. And overall I am ok with them, they are comfortable and the sound quality is excellent with great noise canceling. However.

The range is very low. My phone must be within six feet of my headphones for them to connect. I can no longer leave my phone in one spot in the gym and do my various lifts :( I had to get an arm band to keep my phone with me, thus kinda defeating the purpose of bluetooth.

They also fell out of my ears on my second run. Now that is the only time they fell. I am 5"9' and they fell onto concrete and only have a little scratch to show for it, so they are durable. But I am now pretty vigilant to press on them regularly to make sure they are staying in now.

On a side note, as long as they are close together they work with only one in. I am deaf in one ear and this is wonderful for me. One in my pocket, one in my ear.

title: These will absolutely be outdated in a year.
content:
They're alright. If you don't mind spending lot's of money on trash, they're really not bad.

They fit a bit snugger than say the AirPods, if that's what you're looking for. But beware, they fit a bit snug, and my experience became a nuisance trying to exercise with bulky plastic rubbing against my ears.

The connectivity was pretty decent, but I had a hard time pairing it without the use of their app. Wow, so cool that they have an app just for the earphones? No, it just adds another step to what should be very simple.

The sound quality was alright. Like yeah, it sounds pretty clear, but it's 2019, what headphones don't sound clear? If you're going to drop some money on earphone sound quality, this isn't quite spectacular.

This review might sound harsh, but these earphones were $169.. you shouldn't settle for what should be $30 earphones.

title: Overall good
content: Overall a big step up from the cheap $40 pair I had previously bought. Only issue is the skip button requires you to hold the edge of the button on the left ear. Hard to do while running. Wish you could reprogram the buttons.

title: perfect
content: perfect sound. does not lose connection. battery lasts an amazingly long time. i fly every week and have had bose, sony, JBL. this is my go to headphones for traveling now. the case is so handy. a good tip that people dont realize as people have mentioned the case is hard to open, you are not supposed to pry the case open with your finger nail, you should grasp the top of the case and apply slight pressure as you pull it open. hard to explain but so easy to open instead of trying to pry it open with a finger nail

title: Love these
content: Pretty comfortable and they don't fall out. They come with a fabulous app that plays background noises like thunder and ocean waves. I like to use them at boring events / meetings surreptitiously.

title: Sound sucks at any volume or style of music
content: They are super big and start to hurt your ear after a little bit. The sound on these SUCK, bass being the worst I have ever heard on a set of ear buds. You wont be able to listen at high volumes due to distortion. Only pro is I have never had an issue cleaning them or moister effecting them. I would be okay spending $60 at the very max on these.

title: Overall fantastic, though I really really really wanted to love them
content:
I was so excited for these as I wasn't over the moon for the airpods so i researched heavily and decided to get these.  Here's my breakdown:

Pros & Cons:
 Look 5/5- then look amazing
 Fit 4/5 - over fit well but dig in to the ears when using adjustments
 Sound 4/5 - Excellent sound
 Charging Case 3.5/5 - overall nice but a bit fat and no magnets means then fall out sometimes
 Controls 2/5 - with only volume and track selection on the left ear means when only listen to the right you don't have controls.  BIG bummer.  When you change the volume it digs the earbud in your ears, super uncomfortable.
  Pairing 3/5 - too many times the left wouldn't engage and had to put back in the case then back to my ears then would be ok, but that is not acceptable.  (that is whats nice about the airpods, they just work)
  Usability - 2/5 - because of the controls and because you can't use the left by itself.

If you can overlook those flaws they are great earbuds, just not for me.

title: Almost perfect, absolutely worth the buy.
content:
Almost perfect headphones. They look good, feel good, and stay in your ears good. Also good noise cancelling, but if you need to be aware of your surroundings the HearThrough feature picks up the environment and plays the audio into your headphones.

Battery life is 5 hours which is hard to get used to coming off of the Powerbeats 3 which was 12 hours, but the case holds 2 full recharges. Sound is okay, nothing wowing but solid. Phone calls are amazing, again coming from the Powerbeats that microphone was horrible for talking. Not at all an issue with these Jabras.

My biggest complaint about these headphones may be a small one for others: it has very clear audio latency issues when watching videos. The sound does not match up with what you are watching, it’s probably due to the fact the headphones are cableless so they take longer to sync with each other and the phone.

That said it’s a real minor issue and what you are getting out of it is a truly wireless experience.

title: Does what it claims but
content:
They were good headphones while they worked but all the research I did suggested that others had the same issues as me that one side was way lower than the other. After a whole month of use and troubleshooting I gave up and returned them. For the price they shouldnt have these prevalent issues. Normally I would say I got a fluke but so many people on forums had the same issue. Sometimes one side would just not work at all.

Were decently comfortable for extended periods
Good volume for train rides and gym
Would never fallout, big plus
Touching the buttons would need you to push into your ear and it was annoying and somewhat painful.

title: Not my favorite...
content:
I had a Jabra bluetooth for some years, the switched to a Plantronics. While these are more comfortable, i bought them for three reasons:
1) stereo sound when listening to music
2) I could listen to music during a long bike ride without damaging the device
3) I could opt to only use one during my normal day for phone calls

What has my experience been, relative to my expectation?
1) THe sound quality is not nearly as good as any of my wired earbuds. The lows are almost non-existent
2) THey are comfortable and fit well, especially during the bike rides. For phone audio, they are great
3) When I use only one, my call recipients complain that there is an odd "feedback". Once I activate the second one, no one complains. I don't know why this is, but it does mean that I really do need to use both when making phone calls...to stop folks from complaining.

title: Great purchase
content: Exceeded my expectations. However, left one won’t stay in my ear, but works for others.

title: Love ‘em
content: There’s only one default u remove one ear bud they both turn off.  U have to wear both in order for them to both work.

title: Great but not for my ears
content: I have a friend that swears by these headphones. I have had these for months but have decided not use them very often because they are so unpredictable. Some days they stay in my ears some days they fall out. I use them primarily for exercising and I more times then not they fall out. In my opinion they are too expensive to take a risk on.

title: Are these defective? Left bud didn't work out of box!
content: This product is defective out of box. I can't get the left bud to work! It was so annoying, no matter what troubleshooting I figured out. Customer service was no fun and I just gave up. I wish I could just get a replacement to actually try them out. I am going to reach out to Amazon and see if they can help. I wanted to love these! They look good and the size is good. I am forced to continue my boring jaybird x3s.

title: Design doesn't' make sense
content: So my biggest complaint would be that you can only use the right earbud by itself. So personally I like to only have one earbud in so I can still be aware of what's going on around me especially at my desk, but I can only use the right. The left only connects to the right earbud so if that right earbud isn't in your ear, the left WILL NOT WORK. Not to mention since I only use the right bud, I lost it at work being it was the only bud I used. That means I have a case with a useless left earbud. I went to see how much it would cost to buy another right earbud to discover you can only buy BOTH BUDS AS REPLACEMENTS. The only thing I really enjoyed from the ear buds was how long the battery life was. Other than that, I'd go with something different. Maybe spend alittle more for those Pro Beats.

title: Falls out of Ears Constantly
content: The sound quality and noise cancellation are phenomenal. However, the ear buds constantly fall out of my ears. These are supposed to be for exercise, but I can't use them for exercise as they fall out of my ears even when I'm just walking or sitting. I have to tap them to my ears in order to be able to exercise with them in.

title: They are great!
content: I use these every day for 5+ hours. They are great!

title: Just awesome
content: Superb !!

title: NOICE
content: This is the first pair of wireless headphones that've actually worked for over a month for me. With my last two pairs, at least one earbud had given out in that time. I'm no audiophile, and I don't need these to be super waterproof, but the sound is always great, and I kinda like that I can adjust the bass and crap with the app. No complaints.

title: one of the best wireless headphones in a long time
content: Love these headphones, this is a second pair I got for my self and my gf. Easy to use, sound quality, functions, everything works as it should be and great price. Well done Jabra on this set

title: So close
content: These had great sound and features.  I loved that they could support two bluetooth devices at once so that I could easily transtion from my phone to a tablet.  And the audio pass through was handier than I expected.  My problem though was that I was one of the unlucky ones who seemed to be between sizes on the ear tips.  One size was big enough to be a bit painful, while the next size down would keep losing its seal, which lead to bad sound and the earpiece becoming loose in my ear.  I'm dissapointed that they couldn't inlcude more than three sizes.  I've bought cheap $20 headphones that come with a whole bag full of different ear tips.  Sadly I had to return them because without a good fit they just wouldn't work right (ironically, even the inside of the packaging makes some remark about great sound starting with a great fit).  I even tried ear tips from some other headphones I had but the Jabra ones are much shallower than usual, so they wouldn't work.  Here's hoping Jabra can provide some better ear tip options on their future products because I thought the rest of the design was great.

title: easy to lose, should have a string connecting the two earbuds for when in use
content: Earbuds are easy to lose, would be great if there was some sort of string between them for when in use. Otherwise great!

title: Best ear phones I've ever bought
content: I mainly use this pair of ear phones for working out but occasionally I do use them now to take calls since I can't hear people well at all through the ear speaker of my phone. I'm writing this review too after just putting them through a cycle in the washer and maybe 2 minutes in the dryer, and I'm experiencing no difficulties whatsoever. I thought for sure I destroyed them but they still work and charge. The only small cons I have are the fit sometimes when working out and the controls. If you smile or tighten your face in some way, they tend to slip out just a tiny bit. To control the volume, the front of the left bud is down and back is up. Also I had a problem getting the alaexa to work, which was just more to test, I won't really use it. But to have the comfort of no wires, great sound, and ease of use they deserve the 5 stars. Also a trick with the charging case, which is slightly annoying to open, if you press more so on the left or right side of the front to push open, it'll be easier than pushing directly in the middle or with two thumbs

title: They would not stay in my ear!
content:
I really wanted to like these based on all the positive reviews and for the most part I did like them. So far, out of all the earbuds I've tried, these had the best call quality which is what i based my purchase on. My biggest thing was that if I was working out and happened to get a call, I could take the call without having to go through steps to turn off Bluetooth to answer the call. So for the call quality checkbox, it's positive! I'll sum up my impressions as follows:

PROS:
Great call quality
Great sound quality
Good price for all the features you get
They paired very easily and every time i took them out of the case.
Case was small, compact and inconspicuous like the iPod case
Convenient button on the earbuds to hang-up or answer calls

So-So qualities:
Volume control on buttons was not as smooth. In other words, you had to ensure you held the earbud in your ear (because it's a little big and awkward) to turn the volume up or down.

Micro USB charging vs. USB-C. This was really not that big of a deal for me since I have numerous cables lying around the house for both. However, given that I have the Galaxy Note 8 which is USB-C, it would've been nice to only have to carry around 1 cable.

The different soundscapes were nice. (I used the rainy day a lot for focus and concentration). But I really didn't have to have that feature embedded in the software because I could've downloaded a program to do the same thing.

Active Noise Cancelling - this was okay. When I was in a busy grocery store talking with a friend, they could hear noises in the background but could still hear me fine.

You can use only 1 earbud at a time; however, it can only be the right earbud which is the master. You can't use the left earbud by itself.

CONS:
No magnets in the case to hold the earbuds securely. This was a big deal for me. You had to be careful when you opened the case because of the possibility of the earbuds popping out of the case. No bueno!

They are a little on the large side and did not securely stay in my ear. I kept getting the feeling that they were slipping out of my ear. Therefore, I had to keep shoving them back in which really sealed my ear like i had pushed earplugs in really deep. Not comfortable at all. And this happened with all the different sizes of buds they had to offer. None of them provided that secure fit over time. I've tried less expensive earbuds, like the MPOW which had a real nice fit, but unfortunately the call quality was trash.

If the case was magnetic and the earbuds were made a little more ergonomically to fit in your ear securely, I would have definitely kept these headphones. The other thing is independent earbud use. It would be nice to be able to use the left earbud independent of the right.  Hopefully, they can improve on this in the future.

title: Comfortable Ear Buds.
content: Nice audio sound.  Comfortable

title: Great product for the price
content: My second pair and dispite what others say these are the best, good quality and sound.

title: Average good product.
content:
It's a good product but I expected more sound quality in music. It's fine.
Good for calls, you can hear in stereo, what adds a better quality of the call. I would expect to be able to install the App no only in my phone but also in my PC. I was unable to find a version for PC yet. This is a product that could be found in many stores. Price in Amazon 189.99 + taxes + shipment + handling fee at the hotel. Better to go directly to a store.

title: Stopped working within one month. Jabra will not fix or replace them.
content: Worked great for about three weeks before the left earbud started to become progressively quieter and quieter until becoming completely useless within two months. Jabra wouldn't let me turn them in for replacement or repair without the original receipt, which I no longer have access to. Terrible customer service. Long story short - huge waste of money. Go with a more reputable brand. Highly recommended if you can only hear out of your right ear.

title: Excellent Sound Quality; Great Charging Case
content:
I’m generally pretty critical of Bluetooth earbuds because most of the time I find the sound quality for music to be lackluster. Not so with these Jabra Elites.
I use these at the gym, so durability is important. They have a two-year warranty against sweat. Since I am listening to music, sound quality is also important, and fortunately these have great music quality. They ship with three different sized ear-buds which is important because have an effective seal in the ear canal is everything. If the buds don’t make an effective seal, the bass suffers. The downloadable software includes it own equalizer. This is great because I can set an EQ setting specific for the Jabra earbuds, which allows me to leave my primary Spotify EQ untouched on the setting I use it for outside the gym.
The buds fit snugly and stay in place while exercising. When I’m done, I return them to the case where they start charging back up. Jabra claims a 5-hour battery life on the buds themselves, with the case adding an additional 10 hours. Having the case double as an external battery is brilliant. I would rather re-charge the case periodically and have it keep the earbuds charged rather than having a low-charge warning beep in my ears throughout a workout. I also love the fact that when I remove the buds from the charging case they automatically turn on, and they automatically turn off when I return them to the case. It’s just super convenient.
These aren’t cheap – but if you want great sound, durability, and convenience, these are a great sound solution.

title: Amazing
content: Sound amazing. I wear them all day with no issues at all.

title: Ear volume Created Extreme Neck Pain
content: After about a week of wearing these units for my work from home sales calls, I started to experience extreme neck pain when I would wake up in the morning.  I visited my dentist (since I sleep apnea mouthgards) to find out why it seemed as if was clenching my teeth, and he didn't know what it was.  I then visited my chiropractor, who adjusted my neck and it would feel fine until that next night of sleep.  I went to a massage therapist and their therapy seemed to work, until the next night of sleep.  I then began to realize that maybe it was these ear pieces, and I stopped wearing them so often.  My neck started to improve and I was waking up with less pain.  The earbuds seem to be taking up some much volume that they affect my jaw in some way, and I have to stop wearing them.  Too bad, since I like the way they sound.

title: Really good headphones
content: I really love these headphones.  They are great design and seem to work great on phone calls despite the reviews I read.  I will say this, they can be painful sometimes in my ear, but then I just need to readjust them.  The noise cancellation isn't that great, but that is compared to over ear.  I guess for ear buds they are good.  When I go on longer runs they stay in my ear just fine.  They are great for working from home taking calls.  And they are great for traveling.  So I am really happy with them.

title: Hands down the best!
content: I have been a very loyal Apple customer so when the Airpods came out, of course I bought them.  After numerous flights and becoming frustrated with the noise leakage with the Airpods I came across these.  Wow!!  What a change these are.  These are exactly what I have been looking for.  Very good fit, very good sound, very good support!  I had a little problem with getting these to activate on my iPhone and iPad but one call to the support line and it was fixed.  Even though they don't advertise these as noise cancellation, they do a very good job of blocking out exterior noise.  Call quality is superior and sound is fantastic.  Very highly recommend these.

title: While the sound is good, and the app allows for customization in that ...
content:
My 65t's arrived today and I had high expectations, based on others reviews. While the sound is good, and the app allows for customization in that regard, the Sound+ app looses connection with the 65t when switching the headset back after connecting to a 2nd device. Also, anyone looking to use these independently as a single earpiece for phone calls on your left ear must look elsewhere. The 65t's have to be used in tandem, and from what I can tell, the left is slave to the right. This is not an issue if you're a right-ear dominant, but I'm a leftie. I would have added a star if the comfort was pristine, but after just a couple hours in a coffeeshop with these things in, my ears were begging to be released from the agonizing strain caused by the silicone buds.
Although these have Bluetooth 5.0, without a compatible device, you're lucky to make it past 10 feet before music begins to cut out.

title: Jabra Elite 65t Ear Buds
content: I like these a lot.  The earbuds definitely has great sound and outside sounds are not heard.  My experience using the earbuds eventually hurts my ears.  It could be that my ears are too small and require smaller silicone replacement ear buds that fit better

title: Incredible true wireless earbuds.
content: Their appearance is beautiful and they fit incredibly in the ear. The colour is vibrant and very close to what's pictured. Sound quality and noise cancelling work wonders and alongside the integrated functionalities of the earbuds make this a great pick. Software limitations cause this to lose versatility as it is unable to answer WhatsApp calls with the multifunction button on android 9. Something easy to overlook nonetheless, a fantastic product to own.

title: Best Bluetooth Headphones I have ever had!
content: These in-the-ear headphones are great. The sound from my phone is clear and distinct.  They are very comfortable once you get the right tips on them.  The controls are easy to use.  I especially like that all you have to do is press the right earbud and what you are listening to stops.  You can increase/decrease the volume using the left earbug but it is easier just to use the phone controls.  I do have a bit of trouble with the right earbud falling out if I am bending over.  Since I use them while I am gardening to listen to audio books, it is somewhat of a problem.  Not a big problem since it only happens now and then.  Probably has something to do with my right ear.  Also, the pass through sound feature is great.  I do love them.  It is SO nice not to have a cord hanging down when I am trying to do stuff.

title: good but left earbud keeps falling
content: good but left earbud keeps falling

title: Comfort and great sound.
content:
My wife is a big fan of these wireless earphones. Her one issue is that they aren't particularly good at noise isolation. The television in her gym is sometimes turned up a bit. In that case she will hear the tv over the sound of her music or podcasts. It's for that reason that up to this point she has used noise canceling headphones.

Other than that she has found that these are great for listening to music or movies around the home. They are very comfortable and produce very good sound. The charging case makes it easy to keep track of the headphones and transporting them. The ease of use is a big plus too. Overall she is very happy with them.

title: Love these!
content: Exponentially better than the Bose truly free earbuds they replaced. They fit my ears perfectly, they hold a charge for a long time, they’re low-profile against my ears, and the sound is better than I expected.

title: Useless for running
content:
As the product is designed for sports, I review it accordingly.  I like many features of the product, but the primary reason I bought them was for running. These earphones produce a loud, dull sound sensation in my ears with every step I take. This is okay when I am static or lifting weights in the gym. However, it's unbearable when I run in the treadmill or outdoors. All I hear is BOOM, BOOM, BOOM, BOOM... This sound is loud and imposible to ignore. It FULLY drowns the music if you are running at a middle or fast pace.
If you are thinking of buying the earphones for running, DON'T. You'll regret it and feel frustrated.
I'm back to my SHURE earphones for running, with wire and all.

title: Great little earbuds
content:
I got these earbuds for multiples reasons. I use them when I working out, running, and on the airplane. They stay in my ear even with a lot of movement, unlike Apple's airpods. They also have sound canceling to use on the plane. It's more compact than the Bose QC's and Sony's M3. They are also cheaper than the new Sony XM3. I can't speak of the sound quality of the other products, but the Jabra Elite Active 65t earbuds are great and you can adjust their sound profile.

I recommend these earbuds!

title: Best on the market.
content: I'm sort of an aficionado when it comes to earbuds and I can tell you by far with having tried about 12 different sets of true Wireless and wired headphones that this pair is by far the best pair of true wireless headphones on the market. I'll also comment that any negative comments on these earbuds are probably from people that are technologically challenged..

title: Only Buy New and Unused
content:
I recently purchased a new and unused pair, and I love all the features and have been blown away with how securely the earbuds fit in my ears. The Bluetooth connection has been perfect with my iPhone and my Apple Watch. They also work fairly well with Siri. It’s awesome to go on a 40-minute run with nothing but my clothes, my watch, and my ear buds. No wires! I love it.
I compared with my brother’s AirPods, but I needed to use EarBuddyz to keep them in my ears. It just wasn’t worth the hassle in the end. I like being able to take them out of their case, put them straight into my ears, and put them back into their case. It’s the best.

I previously purchased a “Used - Very Good” pair, but they had the Bluetooth connection issues described in other comments. The earbuds only worked if in a direct line of sight of the right earbud.
I went for a walk and if I put my phone in a pocket, I immediately lost connection. I had to hold the phone in front of my, or hold it specifically in my right hand. Even when holding it in front of me to type a text or select a new song, I lost connection if I turned my head to the right!
That was ridiculous. The headphones are comepletely worthless if the Bluetooth connection is so easily disrupted.

title: Very nice
content: Really good wireless earphone they hurt after awhile but amazing sound

title: Bad ear buds
content: I thought they were a good product but right from the start the right ear bud either didn’t work, no sound, or the sound was so low you could barely hear it.  I tried switching ears and the same thing when I put it in my left ear. I researched it, recharged it, unpaired it and repaired nothing. Such a shame.

title: Awesome earbuds
content: Love theses, great for running

title: Do not buy
content: Great for the first 10-20 minutes. Then you’ll have non stop issues with these earbuds falling out. In a 45 minute run. These fell out 6 different times.

title: great sound
content: product met my expectations. sound great, battery life is good, comfortable

title: Terrible for calls, microphone doesn't work
content: The sounds quality and noise cancelation are nice. But the phone quality is terrible. The people on the other line of my calls can never ever hear me. Additionally, the voice activated commands don't work at all. When there is an incoming call, you will get promoted to say answer or decline. The headphones are never able to correctly understand what you say.

title: Awesome
content: He loves them

title: The hype is real with these!
content: What I liked about these Jabra Elite Active is everything! Feel and sound are great! Been using two months straight now and no complaints.

title: Stopped working after 6 months
content: Great sound, comfortable fit, good battery life, charging case makes the earbuds hard to lose.  Unfortunately, it stopped working within about 6 months -- various online comments indicate that this happens to some units. Fortunately, this is within the warranty period, but it's still a hassle to return it. I use the earbuds to listen to music in noisy areas while I work on my laptop, so this is an inconvenience.

title: awful sound quality and too often it gets delayed
content: sound delay is unbearable on android for some of the apps.  disappointed.

title: Dope
content: Dipe

title: defective
content: the pair I received were defective so I had to return -- you could hear so much background noise! unusable for work :(

title: Bad sound quality and fit. Will be returning.
content: When I tried these out for the first time, I was surprised at how poorly they fit and sound. For nearly $200, I expected great sound from a reputable company like Jabra. These were intended to replace my old wireless earbuds that cost only $30 but sound much better. I spent my entire workout trying to get them to fit in my ears more securely, and the sound is tinny, even with the bass boost turned on. I will be returning these.

title: Jabra 65t functionality
content: Works very well, the sound is clear, volume control easy to use. However, here are a few items which need improvement: 1. The device and its charging box are VERY SLIPPERY, needs to have these items knurled for easier handling. 2. It is confusing to turn ON and OFF the device, there is no confirmation especially when OFF. 3. It is also confusing when it is thought to be OFF and then inserted into the charging box, the green lights turn on the two earpieces and the charging box. Is this an indication that it is charging? If so, have distinctive flashing patterns to indicate the various functions.

title: They fall out, be careful.
content: Maybe it's just my ears but these fall out when I get sweaty and moving. The sound quality is ok, nothing to rave about. The phone quality is about as weird sounding to the people you call like any other BT headset I've used.  They're handy.

title: Spectacular buy
content:
Pros:
 -best secure fit, perfect for running
 -best comfort, great for sleep
 -best sleek and low-profile design
 -best Bluetooth connectivity
 -good battery life & fast charging
 -great build quality
 -perfect button functionality
 -great sound quality and clarity
 -great noise-isolation & cancelation
 -intuitive app features, including GPS tracking and equalizer

Cons:
 -no magnets, falls out of case easily
 -uses micro-usb rather than usb-c

Verdict:
 Don’t waste your time with any other TW pair on the market, as I’ve purchased and tried nearly every flagship pair and have been sorely disappointed with at least one of their qualities. The Elites score well in every single category, which you will certainly not find with any other pair. Sound quality is very impressive, coming second only to the $300 Sennheiser TW Momentum.

For active use: buy from Jabra
For the audiophiles: get Sennheiser

title: Not even close to Airpods don't believe that for a second or you will be disappointed
content:
I purchased these as a backup to my airpods. I was really hoping these would be as good as a lot of the reviews I read but they are not. These are far from what I would consider a premium pair of wireless earbuds. Airpods are almost perfect except that they are hard plastic. If apple would only convert them to soft and sealing rubber tips they would be untouchable.

The Bad. There are a few key issues with these which makes them far below a $180 set of wireless earbuds and nowhere near airpods quality. 1. The left earbud does not operate independently!!!!! WT_? I could not believe this as the $40 set of el cheapo wireless buds I have even do this. Total deal breaker.  2. The button function on the buds, which is programmable via the app, never seem to do what I want them to do and they require a physical press of a button which requires mashing the bud into your ear to get a response instead of using a touch. 3. The connection always produces a good 10-15 seconds of cutting in and out before the signal gets clean the first time I connect. Also, I will occasionally get interference and hear odd noises through them. 4. When you remove an earbud it will often continue to play indicating there is no ear sensing tech or its just really poor. 5. The app to control the earbuds features works spotty at best. It does not always recognize they are connected. The app does nothing until it senses they are connected so this renders the app unreliable and thus unused.

The 65ts are good at a few things: 1. They always connect and connect quickly. Honestly, this is the one thing they do better than airpods because they connect to 2 devices at a time. However, the distance is not great. It's acceptable, not great. 2. They are comfortable and lightweight. They dont look like it but they are.  3. They have good battery life. I would call it about the same as airpods maybe better. But I use the 65ts much less so that could be part of why it seems better. 4. the app contains equalizer settings and a listen through mode which sends sounds through the mic so you can hear through while wearing them.

I used these with my iPhone XS Max and my 2018 iPad Pro and my 2016 Macbook Pro. So my review is based on use with these 3 devices. Also, in comparison to the Airpods I am using the original airpods not the new airpod 2s. As, aside from siri im not aware of any real difference.

title: Right Earbud Malfunctioned After Two Months
content:
First, I just want to say that so far Jabra customer service has been terrible in trying to help me with this issue. This is the main reason I would not recommend buying this product. If they took care of the issue in a timely manner I would be happy to recommend these since up to the point that there was an issue they worked great.

The issue I encountered was that after two months the right earbud has started to decrease in volume as soon as I start using to the point where it is inaudible and I have to put in both earbuds but can only hear the left one.

I reached out to Jabra two weeks ago and they got back to me with the standard software resets etc. which I was happy to do but nothing worked. I reached out again but haven't heard back for the past week. I really don't like the look of Apple's AirPods but I feel like they would have at least been able to given me decent customer service if this happened with them.

title: Great - with a slight learning curve
content:
The headphones are great but have a bit of a learning curve. You need to use the Jabra GN app to adjust the eq. The default setting is rather flat and lacking bass definition. I adjusted that in the app and the sound was much better. They have a lot of well thought out features and are really easy to use.

I listen to a lot of podcasts and they are great for that. I love that they turn on automatically when I take them out of the case and automatically pair with my ipod. I made a phone call with just the right ear piece in and the phone call sounded really good. These are the type of earbuds that fit snugly in the ear canal. I find that after a few hours this type of earbud becomes uncomfortable so not something to use all day while working. This type of earbud also blocks out outside noises so you can't really hear if someone comes up and talks to you. Jabra thought of this and has a "hearthrough" mix feature that pulls sounds from the room into the ear pieces sorta like a hearing aid. Very cool if you want to hear what is going on around you sometimes. What is really cool is that when you take one of the earbuds out of your ear, the playback stops and then starts up when you put the earbud back in your ear. A really cool feature.

I also really like that the case/charger will recharge the earbuds a few times even when not plugged into USB. I used them outside and had no connectivity issues so these are great for doing yardwork or chores around the house.

They stay snug in the ear so a good option for using at the gym.

title: Sound quality is good, but overall the AirPods are better
content:
After owning Apple's Airpods for a year, I decided to give these a try when they went on sale for $120 during Amazon's sale day in July.  While the sound quality on these is better on these, here are several reasons why the Airpods are better:
1) inserting and taking out the Jabra buds into their case is not as smooth as putting the Airpods into their case.  The Airpods just drop right into their case, plus it is easier to know which is the right/left one for their proper slot.  The Jabra buds are loose when they go in, and it is easy to mix up which is the right/left one.  Plus when opening the Jabra case, you have to be careful that the earbuds do not fall out as you open them as they are not securely fit in these.  The Airpods are snug in their case as you just drop them right into their slot.
2)  The battery life on the Jabra case is not as good as the Apple case.  I could go a whole week before having to charge the Apple case.  The Jabra case lasts a few days at most.
3)  When you open the Airpod case, you see the battery life remaining on the charger and each airpod on your iphone right away. For Jabra, you have to open their Sound app. to get battery life remaining.
4) Most annoying, only the right Jabra earbud will work by itself in your ear.  The left Jabra earbud will not work for playing music by itself; you need to have the right earbud in as well.  For me this was a big inconvenience as many times I like to just use one earbud while doing work or whatever.

As I said earlier, the sound is better on the Jabra earbuds and they also block outside noise much better than the Airpods.  The Jabra Sound app has equalizer settings that allows you to adjust treble, bass etc. which you can't do on the Airpods.

Overall though, if you are an Iphone user, the Airpods are I think the better option as they work more seamlessly with iphones.

Update October 2019
Just to give a shout out to Jabra's customer service.  I had a problem with my charging case and  they sent me a replacement case within a week of when I contacted them.  So at the very least you get very responsive customer service with them.

title: Oddly shaped ears, heavy sweater checking in
content:
Pros: Excellent sound quality, nice to look at. Better battery life than other buds I've tried (about 3 hours before they need to go back in their charging case). App works well.

Cons: I couldn't get a good fit without third party foam tips. Old micro-usb port. Volume +/- buttons are reversed. Some skipping noticed.

I really enjoy a good pair of earbuds. I haven't really been particularly happy with anything in about 8 years since the dog got ahold of my favorite (discontinued) pair. I've gone through sets of Apple, Samsung and Bose since and haven't been particularly happy with anything.

As the title states, while my ears look fairly normal (I believe) it is very rare I find a pair of buds that stay sealed in my ear. Additionally I sweat quite a bit and this adds to the problem. I noticed a much better fit with these, however right at the 2 mile mark of a run the left earpiece would slide out and require drying off. While at the gym the left side would again dislodge when I would lie on my back. Jabra's website states the rubber tips in the "Active" are anti slip, that hasn't been my experience.

Despite the slippage I was very happy with the sound quality and features so I purchased third party foam tips. These did the trick and I can say they now stay in place. The downside to the foam is that in order for these buds to go back in their charging case I either need to remove the tips or maneuver them in very carefully before closing the lid.

I do have some quibbles in regards to the features. First, no usb-c? Lower priced Samsung earbuds come with this. The left bud has 2 small buttons, the forward one turns volume - while back button is used for volume +/change songs. I feel like these buttons are reversed, forward should be volume up.

I will also say that these earbuds do occasionally 'skip' on me, where others have not. Not frequent but it does happen (Samsung Note 8)

While I did need to purchase foam tips and said tips add a little trouble, once these buds are in place I'm one happy camper.

title: Great true wireless earbuds
content:
There are tons of reviews for the Jabra Elite Active 65T earbuds with tons of details and information, so I will keep my review short.

I have many earphones, but these are my first Jabra brand earphone. I am switching from Jaybird X3 earbuds which worked very well using Comply foam tips for exercising (mostly runs, but also gym exercises). But I wanted something with no cables for sports and the Jabra Elite Active 65t fit the bill. I very much like these true wireless earbuds, but as with everything there are pros and cons:

Pros:
- I am using the supplied plastic tips and so far they stay in my ear well and have not fallen-out.
- The sound is very good. As expected, not as good as high-end wired earphones - I am comparing them to Etymotic Research ER4XR earphones or Sennheiser 650 headphones, but I did not buy these for high quality audio listening and both of those are far more expensive as well. Still, the sound is very good, so absolutely no complains there.
- The battery life so far has been excellent. I have not charged them once since the first charge, and the case is still charging the earbuds well.
- The bluetooth connection has been solid. I have not had any drops once connected and during workouts. I have even walked far away from my iPhone X, and had no issues.
- Once I figured-out how to open the case, I really love it. It is small so I can keep it in my pocket and putting the earbuds in it is super easy and they charge, turn-on, etc. just as expected.

Cons:
- These are very small earbuds. Even after seeing all the pictures, I was surprised at how small they are. Of course that was a design goal and I do like that they don't stick-out too far when in my ear, and look cool. But the small size means the controls are sometimes hard to work with and you can press the wrong button on the earbud by mistake.
- They are not very comfortable for wearing for a long time (past one hour). I will try different tips, perhaps the Comply foam tips and see if those would help.
- On only one occasion, when I pulled the earbuds out of the case and put them on, the left earbud did not play the music. As stated by others, I put them both back in the case, and then put them back on and they both worked. This has not happened again, so I am not concerned that it's going to be a problem.

I would recommend these for anyone that is looking for true wireless sports earbuds. I was planning to buy the Sennheiser Momentum True Wireless and was waiting for more reviews to see how they compare. But they are not designed for sport and are also much more expensive, so I am happy with my purchase.

title: Heavy on treble, no bass, kept cutting out.
content: Was looking forward to these headphones, expected a great experience.  Despite the cost, and Jabras reputation, the sound quality was so poor as to render these headphones worthless.  The treble was shrill, and there was no bass.  Furthermore, they kept cutting out (I have a Pixil XL which provides a strong signal).  To add insult to injury, I have to pay for my own return shipping for this defective item, and have to hassle with taping multiple hazardous materials warning labels on the shipping box.  Odd, but the box that I received the earbuds in had no such warning labels.  All in all, one of my more unsatisfactory experiences with Amazon, and with Jabra.

title: Great product
content: There are so many of these on the market now it is hard to determine what is what. I am very happy with these. They are easy to wear (last a long time before they begin to feel uncomfortable). The batteries last a good long time and the case recharges them quickly. I have worn them running and cycling (indoors) and no issues with sweat.

title: Perfect for the gym
content: I've always hated to wear wired earbuds or even bluetooth headphones while I work out. These are excellent. They've never fallen out of my ears. You need to experiment with the different sized earbud sleeves. I went with the larger size to get the best fit and sound. The different sizes do affect the sound quality. There was one occasion that the left earbud lost its sound and after messing with it I found that that was sweat on the sensor which caused it to quit playing. There are embedded sensors that stops it from playing when pulled away from the ear. So a quick wipe and it worked again. So far the battery life has been really good. I've never had them die on me. This is a perfect solution to those wanting to get away from wires and bluetooth headphones.

title: Charging case breaks after 8 months
content:
I owned this for 8 months. The design of the earbuds are great for my ear. They are comfortable, no pressure to my ears and I think I can wear this for hours. I actually slept with this a few times and did not hurt my ears.
The sound quality is good, it can reduce background noise and enjoy your music. I does not disconnect or lose connection while you are listening and that includes the other pair. Other brand that I had have that problem where the other buds disconnects and it sounds like its having a hiccup that I have to move my head closer to the device.
It has hearthrough which so you dont need to remove them when having a conversation. Even when your audio is paused, you still need to remove them as they do not work properly. You can barely hear a regular conversation and you have to ask the other person to speak louder so its more appropriate to just remove them. The microphone is not the best. It is advertised as great to use on skype but even skype will prompt you that your mic is of low quality. People I talked to in skype prefers my laptop's intergrated mic rather than this device because of the bad background noise it is capturing and its poor quality.
The worse part of it is its case, after 8 months of use, the hinge which is held only by thin weak plastic broke. I use it 3 times a day 3-4 times a week and the device is not abused. The issue is the design. You have to press it inwards to disconnect the lock which bends the upper part of the hinge weakening it everytime you open it. You can search the comments regarding this review section for the same problem. I have read about it did not believe them but should have listened. My thought was it was a matter of abuse and as long as you use it with care, it will be ok. I contacted Jabra support and they determined that it was not covered by warranty since it is "accidental damage". Not worth it for $150 earbuds lasting only 8 months. Very disappointed.

title: They're going to fall out.
content: I was very excited to get these for my birthday.  I opened the box and put one in for fit.  It immediately fell out.  I must not have pushed in and seated it well.  It immediately fell out again.  Let me get the larger plugs and try them.  It immediately fell out again.  On closer examination,  these things are designed to fall out.  Virtually all the weight of the device is always pulling away from the ear.  I've used a Platronics ear piece for several years, and it has never fallen out.  For $175 I'm not going to take a chance on losing one the first time I turn my head.  Back they go.

title: Sleek n comfy
content: Perfect fit and great sound quality.

title: The sound is excellent, and both right and left work together
content: The sound is excellent, and both right and left work together. Was only able to link it to one device, haven't figured out how to link to multiple. They are a comfortable fit in my ears and work well for the elliptical machine at the gym with my tablet.

title: Fantastic BuD! (For 6 Months)
content: I had given a 5 star review owing o their outstanding sound quality. I've now had 3 pairs of these buds fail with low volume or other issues. So buy these if you are happy to dispose of them in a few months.

title: Really good headphones! Not exactly for active people.
content:
These are some seriously good headphones! I enjoy them very much. They connect very easily and instantly, sound great with some customization in the equalizer (taking into account their size). The carrying case is so compact and allows you to put away the headphones very easily.

There are a few minor improvements to be made to them:

-The case isn't very secure, light taps and bumps are enough to knock it open.

-On top of that, the headphones sit in the case. There's no magnet or anything holding them in, only gravity. So at a slight tilt, they'd fall out.

-The headphones themselves could be more secure. While they do fit well and hold normally, I notice that when it's hot out or when I'm bumped around a bit during a commute the headphones would come loose. The left one slipped out once or twice.

title: Perfect, just what I was looking for
content: Love these headphones. The fit great, music quality is excellent as well as call quality. If you want in ear Bluetooth headphones these are perfect!

title: Recommended for active lifestyles
content:
I’ve been using these for quite a while now. I use them while at my job and while working out.

The Pros:
-Easy to connect
-Sound Quality
-Lasts a long time on one charge

The Cons:
-Ocassionally the syncing for a video will be off slightly
-The small charging case is strangely hard to open (small nitpick)

title: They fall out of my ears, in bathroom, on the street at night.
content: I'm returning today a set of Jabra 65ts, that were Wirecutters' fav. I didn't mind spending $170 if the sound quality was superior, but it's not. AND, the REAL reason the Jabras are going back is that they fall out of my ears, notwithstanding trying several of the different silicone earpieces provided...and when you're walking the dog at night and they fall out, how are you going to find them in a pile of leaves? One dropped out of my ear and just missed the toilet (AFTER the fact if you know what I mean). Another time one dropped out and missed going into a sewer. So after a half dozen drop outs since 12/25, I'm ready to call the question. The other problem is that they fail to reliably link to my iPhone X after having been initially paired...so I deleted and then re-downloaded the app and THEN they linked without a problem. But I've done that three (3) times. That's enough. So, regretfully, they're in the box waiting to be walked over to UPS, while I wear my Aukey EP-B40s, which at $29 at Amazon, I can have a red and a black pair and keep one in use and the other charging.

title: Earbuds are falling :(

I tried all 3 sizes of the inner part, and ran with it few times before I gave up.
They are still falling out the ear when you start to sweat.
Disappointing :(

title: Great value

Sound quality  9/10
Comfort  10/10
Battery 9/10
Overall  9/10

title: Quality Product - some minor complaints
content:
I've never understood high-end ear buds.  My experience has been that once you go over $50, they all sound pretty much the same (this is not true of headphones).  That being said, I purchased these for the wireless feature and they work fine.  However, they don't sound any better than my 10-year old wired Marleys.  Also, to me noise-cancelling is what you get on Bose headphones - you flip that button and the whole world goes quiet and it's done electronically.  Unless I'm missing something, the "noise-cancelling" feature on these earbuds comes from the fact that they're essentially an ear-plug.  The noise is reduced but I can still hear some ambient noise.

Overall I am happy with the purchase.  I live near a noisy marina and I bought these so that I could sit on my deck and not have to listen to dance music or worry about wires and they work fine for that.  I have not experienced the disconnecting issues that others have reported.  This is a quality product that does most of what it advertises.  I don't really use them to talk on the phone that much but when I have, the people on the other end have complained about me "breaking up".

I have not taken these on walks or runs and would not be comfortable doing so as the only thing holding them in is the friction of the ear plug and there is a decent amount of weight to them hanging out of your ear (relatively speaking).  I don't think I'd feel comfortable taking these out into the world on a bus, etc..  They are made of some super slick material and really hard to hold onto and I am constantly dropping them.

The earbuds themselves have controls on them, which I consider a major drawback.  The panel is the size of a dime and I don't know how anybody with normal-sized hands could operate the controls.  Instead, whenever I adjust or remove them, something happens like the track skipping to the next one, the sound turning on or off or the volume adjusting.

Pros:
1. Wireless!
2. Decent sound.
3. Proven technology.
4. Battery lasts a decent amount of time.
5. Has a decent app for tweaking sound, if you're into that sort of thing.
6. Well-made.

Cons:
1. Expensive.
2. Sound good, not great.
3. Not noise-cancelling.
4. Tend to fall out.  Could use bigger earbud pads.
5. Slippery and easy to lose.
6. Controls on buds that are hard to use.

title: Not a good fit for my small ears
content: I have small ears. They keep falling out and are uncomfortable to wear with the smallest fittings. Disappointed. They seem well made and sounds is good for the few times I have tried them.

He probado varios auriculares sin cables, pero estos son los mejores que he tenido hasta el momento. Tienen muy buena duración y son fáciles de usar. Tienen un buen sonido y buen aislamiento en lugares públicos. Los uso para entrenar. Los recomiendo.
Actualización, luego de varios meses de funcionar perfectamente, sin ninguna razón aparente dejo de funcionar el auricular izquierdo, es frustante.

title: Worth the price

Ear fatigue is about 2 hours, battery life is real good and distance from my phone is good.  Connectivity is easy and using them for phone e calls work good.  A really good by I would by from this company again.

title: Great earbuds, Jabra has crappy warranty conditions
content:
Gonna add my two cents to the 3k other people here.  I think these buds are great.  Some of the best sound you'll get out of "truly wireless" earbuds and not spend $300.  They do take some getting used to, especially with lots of complaints about ears hurting for the first couple weeks.  My ears hurt too, it seems that this is by design (??) because that's how Jabra engineered them to stay in.  The ear cups have a "sharp" edge that grips onto your ear canal.  This is uncomfortable at first but I eventually built up callouses or whatever, and it's not a problem anymore.

The plastic carry case is great, not bulky, and I forget it's in my pocket most of the time.  The hinge on the lid feels VERY fragile and I often feel like one accidental push in the wrong direction will snap it right off.  I am always super careful when I have the case open so I don't put any stress on that hinge.  If you break the hinge, the charging case won't work because it relies on the pressure from the lid to charge the buds.  They aren't held in by magnets or anything.  So again, break the hinge and you'll be shelling out $60 for a new case.

My biggest complaint is Jabra's warranty conditions.  My left earbud driver went out after 6ish months.  It still "worked" as in the buttons still functioned, but no sound came out.  I contacted Jabra for a warranty replacement, jumped through the typical hoops of rebooting the device, pairing it to another phone, bla bla bla.  They eventually sent me the warranty replacement form which required I provide proof of purchase AKA the store receipt.  I bought these at Best Buy and didn't think about needing the receipt.  So once I "found" the receipt, I processed the form and got a shipping label.  They said I have to ship the broken buds to them, then they will ship functioning ones back.  Ugh.  Seriously, this is the only company I've dealt with in the last 10 years who requires you to ship your product to them FIRST then they'll snail mail you back a replacement.  I've had warranty issues on phones, a Nest thermostat, and  other electronics and have never had to ship them mine first.  Now I get to use crappy earbuds for the next 3 or 4 weeks until Jabra gets around to shipping me a replacement. Grr.

I use mine with a Google Pixel 3 and with the companion app for Android they are very feature rich in a way that I think would satisfy audiophiles. Super happy with them, would absolutely recommend.

title: Ok, let me clarify things. Read on.
content:
It took me a while to finally make the decision to purchase these -- on Black friday sale. The reason? While most reviewers online raved about these earbuds, the rating on Amazon.com is super low (3.6 stars at the time). I usually never consider anything less than 4 stars on Amazon.com. However, I've been wanting these for quite a while and given the black friday sale ($149) I thought I'd give them a try. Never looked back!! Here's my detailed review of this awesome product:

Pros:
1. Fit: Perfect. Honestly, the fit of these earbuds comes close to perfection. These buds won’t fall out of your ears no matter what you do. They use some sort-of rotate-and-lock mechanism (my own terminology) and they feel like they’re locked in place.
2. Noise-Isolation: Really good. This comes from the fact that they lock in place completely blocking the pathway to your ear canal. Comparing them to my Bose QuietComfort 35s, I dare to say that these are at least not worse at blocking outside noise.
3. Hear-through feature: Good. I haven’t been able to notice much difference between having the hear-through feature on or off when music is on. However when the music is off you can really tell the difference. In essence, you can use these as noise enhancement. When I have them in my earn with music off and hear-through off, I can hear everything so much better than without the earbuds.
4. Bluetooth connectivity: Very good. Firstly, these buds connect super-easy to your device (iphone for me) for the first time. After that it’s perfection. You take them out of the case and by the time they’re in your ears, they are connected and ready to go. Also when you’re done, just take them out of your ears and put them back in the case - that’s it. I did notice some connection drops in completely open spaces but never indoors.

So-so features:
1. Volume: Could be louder but it’s loud enough. Don’t get me wrong, these earbuds are pretty loud and in combination with the noise isolation, volume comes close to perfect. However, for some songs, if you’re one of those who want to put the volume to the max and get in the zone, you might be a little bit disappointed. However, that’s also a bad habit so it’s probably a good thing that these earbuds don’t do excessively high volume. Ps. I often find myself listening to songs at 60-70% volume, so again, they are relatively loud. Just not excessively so.
2. Music: Good. I don’t have much to say here cause I’m not an audiophile. Music is pretty ok. Not amazing but that’s to be expected and using the Jabra app you can customize bass, treble etc.

General advice:
1. This goes for all true-wireless earbuds. Find a systematic way to save them and their case everytime you take them off your ears. It’s so easy to lose them. In 2 weeks of use I found myself looking for them quite a few times.

Final thoughts: I couldn’t recommend more. Airpods are definitely worse. I find myself using my Bose QC35s less and less. Wired headphones? Never again..

title: Don't buy
content: Returned and purchased Bose which was the best decision

title: Best wireless earbuds on the market
content: I have had these for a few months now and wanted to leave my review. The buds come with 3 sizes of tips so the fit is awesome. I wear these at work and they drown out as much background noise as earplugs. Battery life is great. About 5 hours of straight usage. The case gives a full 3 charges so you can use these for about 15 -20 hours. While at work double tapping on the right bud turns on hear through and makes having a conversation possible without taking them out. These are well worth the cost and I am safe saying one of the best quality earbuds I have used.

content: I put these through the washer and dryer (on accident) and they still work perfectly!! I would 10/10 recommend these headphones and 3/10 recommend putting them through the wash.

title: Quality poor but sound is really good.
content:
First, I would like to preface with saying that I really enjoyed these headphones when I initially began using them. They were responsive and the Bluetooth connection was working very well.
After 3 months of regular use, the left earbud began to cut out on sound. I did a standard troubleshoot; reset and updated the firmware.
After contacting Jabra requesting a refund. It was still in the warranty period for a refund. Jabra did not respond until after the warranty period to deny the refund. They offered to replace, pending an inspection. After another 3-4 weeks of no communication, they finally sent a UPS label.
I’m giving these a two because I think Jabra does try to work well with this type of product, but their business focus is on commercial equipment.

title: Better than Air Pods
content: Much better sound. Siri functionality is delayed but still usable. First set had a faulty left ear bud mic but was replaced free of charge by amazon. First return that I had some issue with but I believe it was just the person on the phone. I didn't want to like them but absolutely love the convenience of the small charging case and tiny form factor of the ear buds. The fit is everything when it comes to sound so play around with placement within your ear and the different size earpieces.

The Bluetooth pick up on these is terrible.  Constantly having issues connecting and getting errors that make zero sense.

If you connect them they sound and look good but the buttons are ridiculously designed.  Maybe if I had skeleton fingers I could avoid hitting things that shouldnt be in the set up to begin with.

title: Be careful

title: Call quality is excellent
content: Phone calls and music

title: Great all around.
content:
I've ran with these a handful of times so far and my experience has been great. I dont have to worry about them falling out of my ears at all. The buttons on the earpieces are really useful as well. If i take one earbud out the music stops. When i put that earbud back in and press the button the music comes back on. These dont seem quite as loud as my Bose do but perhaps thats a good thing. All around I am pleased.

*Update*

Just installed the app. Tweaked the noise cancellation feature and the music presets. The best headphones i've ever owned.

title: Believe the recommendations
content: I found something rare in this product, and that was that it was recommended from multiple unrelated sources.  I had tried other methods of wireless earbuds and found them unsuitable for various reasons, so I thought that I'd give these a try.  I'm so very glad I did!  The sound quality is fantastic, with excellent bass, and they fit in your ears very tightly, giving you 3 different sizes of pads from which to choose.  The pass-through mode is wonderful, allowing you to hear almost as well as if you weren't wearing any earbuds at all.  Even with the pass-through mode, they will last for at least 3 or 4 hours before needing a charge, and the charging case will store 2 full charges.  They also will give you an hour of inactivity before shutting themselves off, which is plenty of time.  This product is pricey, but it's worth it, especially if you are considering even more expensive offerings from Bose or Beats.

title: Top notch. Great fit
content: Works great.. Love these things..not the best at blocking sweat as it still get in my ear like the old wire buds.... sound quality is 2nd only to Bose.. these have more features and fit wonderfully... would recommend over Bose unless sound quality is your only preference

title: Get Ready for the Left Earbud Pop
content: Great product when it works. Google the left earbud pop. Joke.

title: Great Passthrough with ok sound
content: They sit good in the ear. Can be fidly at first to keep them in correct in the ear canal . Never had them coming out. Sound is ok. You can adjust the equalizer to get them sounding right the way that you want to. They look good . They do not protrude too much compared to similar buds. Good style. Can be hard to lower/raise volume and change tracks because the button to press is very firm so you have to put kind of hard to do the volume- change tracks. Ear wax can get trapped in the holes so you end up cleaning. NO indicator on the charger case to know if its charging or low in battery. The pass through feature is great because sometimes you want to know what is going on around you and this does a great job doing that. Other wise, the noise cancelation is alright when the pass through is off. The only gripe with this is that the design sometimes  clogs one of my ears to the point where the sound is unbalanced and have to adjust it just right so sound comes out even. Worth the money but if your looking for good ear buds on a budget get the Jlabs Air instead

title: Worth it

title: Outstanding...
content: Did quite a bit of research on small scale wireless options...these are fantastic. Great fit, secure when working out, great audio quality and satisfies a wide variety of needs - from straight up listening to music, to phone calls, etc. Highly recommended.

I would give it 5 stars for the mic,sound and battery.  I got the elite version but now I'd really recommend the active version instead. Because the elite one still falls off the ear even after repalcing the ear pads.  The problem was solved in the active version as they added a small wing to prevent it from falling off.
The charging case for the active has space for that wing whe the elist charging case won't have space for this eing even if you buy it as accessory to prevent it from falling off.

Otherwise both have the same great mic and great sound quality. It also can connect to two separate devices at the same time (phone and laptop)  which is a great feature.  All in all, I love it and o would give it 5 stars instead of 4 if it doesn't fall off the ear

content:
I really like these.  They come with 3 sizes of rubber tips, and I changes out the original (medium) ones for the smallest size.  After that, they have been very comfortable.

The Bluetooth connection is quick and strong, and people can hear me well.  I wear them at the gym doing all types of exercise, and they don't fall out.

Again, very happy with the purchase, ans would recommend them highly or buy them again in a second if I lost them.

title: Don’t buy.
content: These are kinda junk. You can’t use the left alone. They’re kinda uncomfortable and the sound quality isn’t all that great. Would not buy again

title: Returned them after trying them for the first time...
content: Terrible fit, heavy for the ear, just terrible design and execution, in every way.  I now have the Powerbeats Wireless and they are superb.

title: Good sound and features. Poor fit.
content:
I have tried the different ear cushions that came with the kit but I still have problems getting them to stay in my ears - particularly the left one.  They tend to start sliding out, especially if I am eating, talking or otherwise moving my jaw.  I realize that this something specific to my personal ear form but I suspect that will be the case for a relavant number of buyers.  The in-ear design, with no secondary around-the-ear hook, just isn't going to work for everyone.  I would NEVER attempt to wear these while walking down the street or in most public areas where they could easily be lost if they popped out of my ears.  I plan on trying a pair of the foamy ear inserts (not included included in original kit) but I'm not sure I will be able to stand that insert stuffed in my ear.

Sound and features are OK.  No problems getting them to pair.

Hear-thru feature seeems a little gimmicky to me and seems a little laggy.

One annoying little thing (but common to most bluetooth earbuds that permit simultaneaous pairing to mutliple devices I suspect) is that you have very little control over which paired device gets use of the earphones.  Several times I have been on a web conference only to have my cell phone steal focus from the PC because of some notification beep.  Only way I have found to prevent this is to remember to turn-off bluetooth on one of the devices (and then try to remember to turn it on again).

title: great headed head phones
content: i love everything about there bad boys

title: Works great!
content: These are great.  They fit well and dont fall out.  Also, they work through clothing which is key to my training right now.  I had a different pair of ear buds that would not work when I placed my phone in my pocket.  These work perfectly for my long distance runs with my phone on my pocket.  So happy.

title: Well worth the money!
