But the 2x charge of the case is pretty cool. The range for bluetooth seems pretty good also. Ive had this on at work connected to my computer and left my office to go down the hall to the kitchen and it was still working fine. All in all pretty good for the price. Havent tried having a heavy workout with them on yet but my brother has and said its great.

title: Trouble with connection between earbuds.
content: They are great when they work.  Just have a lot of issues, multiple times daily, with connectivity issue between earbuds.  I have heard it’s not an uncommon issue among true wireless earbuds,  but at this price point I did not expect to have to reset the earpieces several times throughout every day.

title: Air buds great, pair with iwatch fine!
content: Bought these earbuds because I was tired of my other earbuds not pairing to my Apple Watch 3. And then trying to pair the two buds together.  That is not the case with Jabra Active elite 65t. These earbuds pair to my watch and each other first time every time.  I read one review where the person could not pair them to his Apple Watch. The Apple Watch 3 pairs fine.  I left one star off because when I only pair with the Watch the connection is not as strong.  I walk with just my Watch in the morning and listen to music from it. If I do not keep my arms halfway up, the connection breaks up and the music playback skips. So cannot walk with my arms down. Sound is great, noise canceling great, just wish connection range was better wit my Watch and my moving arms.

title: Great Sound, Light, and Excellent Battery Life.
content:
I have to start by saying this is my first pair of truely wireless earbuds but i have had wireless headphones before This far exceeded my expectations as i was thinking it would be similar in performance to my previous set of wireless headphones, but Jabra really has something nice here. The sound quality is surprisingly good for earbuds. The bass is very good and you can really hear clear sound separation between instruments for these powered ear buds.

I never though I would enjoy my earbuds so much they are so small and convenient with such good sound quality i find myself bringing my ear buds to a lot more places than i normally would consider bringing them. For that reason i would recommend this to anyone looking for a good starter pair of wireless earbuds!

Pros:
Light
Sound
Carrying case is cool
Excellent battery life
Easy bluetooth controls

Cons-
buttons arent great

title: No good for calls
content: Easy to use, decent, though slightly tinny, audio quality for music, podcasts and calls. My reason for 3 stars is that the microphone doesn’t appreciably filter out noise.  I have tried repeatedly to make calls from the street or just outdoors and on all occasions the person on the other end couldn’t hear me clearly or at all because of the level of background noise.

title: Well worth their cost
content: These are worth every penny. Great, comfortable, unobtrusive, easy-to-use earbuds. I do tai chi and calisthenics with them with no problem.

title: Just hope you get a working set!
content:
I ordered these from Amazon a couple of months ago, from day one they broke up whenever they were inside my pocket, in my coat pocket, or whenever the phone was being held more than 2-3' away while walking. It's absolutely infuriating to just be walking and then all of a sudden the music starts unbearable crackling, fuzzy, skipping forward in the track, etc.

I emailed Jabra's support, it took them days to get back to me, when I replied and told them all their resolution methods didn't work, they stopped responding. It's been 2 weeks since they've replied to me. I have no hope they are going to resolve this issue. So this seems to be almost $190 completely down the drain.

When they do work, i.e when I am sitting perfectly still or wearing them in my house. The sound is good and the battery seems to last a long time.

Personally, knowing that there is a small risk that your $190 ear buds might just not work all together, I'd skip on these.

title: Easy to lose.
content: Only had these for a day before they fell out of my pocket. A new feature could be a phone alert if the earbuds are not within 15 feet.  Will have to go back to wired headphones

title: Struggles Mightily With Signal Interference
content:
Nice sound quality for wireless. Easily bested by less expensive wired earbuds (Shure 215). Sound significantly better than Airpods. Isolation also significantly better. Jabra seems to fail when immersed within a strong WiFi signal. My left earbud significantly lowers in volume, crackles, and even cuts out completely when close to my home router Airport Express + Apple TV (3-5 feet) at home. This also happens at the office, where I work for an incredibly large company in a world class building with WiFi always at near peak performance everywhere for thousands of employees in the building. As I walk to my car, volume in the left earbud slowly improves to normal.

I’ve switched back to wired.

Not recommended.

.

title: Right side failed
content: After about a mount of use my right earbud stoped working I don’t know why but it happened so be careful when ordering

title: I love these. They are great for phone calls and ...
content: I love these.  They are great for phone calls and podcasts.  They have a comfortable fit and fairly non-obtrusive.  The sound is pretty good for what these are, but I would like a little more volume.  The bluetooth connection is pretty stable and I have not had any drop outs due to bluetooth.

title: Super Impressed with the earbuds!
content: I've had a pair of Motorola Buds for 4 years.  Although they've served me well, they finally began showing signs of their age so I began to research replacements.  Several good sources pointed me towards the Jabra Elite Active 65t earbuds and I've got to say that I'm impressed with them so far.  Sound quality is excellent, controls are easy, they are comfortable in my ears and they don't stick out too far nor look awkward.  Fingers crossed that these will serve me as well as my old Motorola's did.

title: Issue with left earbud
content:
The left earbud is 'popping' and has static because it sounds like it's having trouble connecting with the right earbud. Remember: the left earbud doesn't function without the right earbud because the left one is the slave.

I'm returning these for hopefully a fully working set. I'm going to assume this is just a bad apple.

title: Poor reliability
content:
I expected a lot more for the price.
The right ear bud "popped" several times before it cut out altogether after pairing with my iPhone. Now it pretty much doesn't work at all or at such a low volume as to be non-functional. I quit listening to music with the Jabras and now just listen to podcasts with them. This occurred within six months after purchase.

title: Disappointed not as loud as I’d hope
content: So I had bought these for the gym. I do a lot of calisthenics so I’m always moving and jumping around. Two things got me the first gym session I wore these. The right piece had fallen out. Not too big of a deal for me since I kept them for about another 2 weeks or so. My main complaint and with other wireless headsets is the volume. To me it just doesn’t go high enough, and I am one that gets into my workouts when the beats are bumping nice loud and crisp. I really wanted to keep these but the volume limitation is a deal breaker for me. Prior to this I was using the cheapo senso branded wireless headsets. They go pretty loud but they get distorted on some songs. I’d love to have that volume with the crisp clear sounds of this headset. I’ll be looking out for their next iteration and hopefully it can go much louder than the current one. And yes I did use the eq on the phone, Spotify , and any other app that had that option but it just doesn’t go loud. I returned them. They do have amazing battery life.

title: Not for outdoor use!
content: As a runner, cyclist, gym-goer, and walker, I wanted non-wired bluetooth earbuds that would allow me to listen to music on the go. In that regard, the Jabra 65Ts sadly didn't work out.  No matter which of the different earbud sizes I tried, the earbuds quickly and nearly immediately fell out of my ears, over and over. On my first pair, one fell off and rolled into traffic and was run over by a car.  I bought a second pair.  Of the new pair, one earbud fell out while I was riding my bike over a bridge and plummeted to the bottom of a deep canal. So if you are doing any kind of outdoor activity, I would suggest NOT buying these.  (Also, once ONE earbud is lost or destroyed, you cannot pair it with a different one).

title: Fall from your ears
content: Very frequent fall from your ears when running ans sweating. Cause pain after some time being used.

title: Great sound but they will fall out if you look down.
content: The sound is 5 star great and they stay in fine while sitting or walking in upright position. I’ve  tried fitting the earpieces by changing included ear gels  with some improvement in tightness of fit, but if I bend over and look down the right one often falls out and sometimes the left.  I wish they had aclip or something to keep them from falling out. I continue to enjoy them anyway and I haven’t lost one yet.

title: Great sound, long charge.
content: I LOVE these. After you get used to the buttons & how they work, this is a fabulous product. Seamless function, great sound quality, about 5 hrs. of charge & that is really nice.

title: Good
content: Decent, kinda pricey.

title: Jabra
content: Excellent product

title: Terrible. Waste of Money
content:
Two weeks after purchasing the earbuds the left one stopped working almost completely.
The noise as barely audible from it, tho the right side was fine.
No matter what I tried, nothing helped. I wrote Jabra's customer support several times
hoping to get a replacement. But all they did was give me the run-around and send me useless
DIY fix instructions. I found several complaints online from customers who experienced the same issue.
Apparently, it is a chronic issue with this product.  Since then I've purchased two pairs of Boss headphones
and they work wonderfully.  The Jabra earbuds are trash.

title: Great earbuds - 5/5 stars
content: I have went through a number of Bluetooth earbuds - mostly cheaper products. I decided to take the plunge and spend the extra on these earbuds after doing some research on other products. By far the best earbuds I have ever purchased. Stay in my ear great when lifting weights or running. Sound quality is great. Battery life is great, especially if you put them back in the case when you are done using them. I recommend them to everyone that asks about them.

title: not working
content: The sound quality was very bad, picking up too much noise from outside when making phone call. unlike their commercial video that they can make phone call on the subway. there is no way you can do that, on the other side of the call will hear like a tornado when making phone call. Talk to Amazon tech support before i returning it, but their support does not know anything at all.

title: Not accurate with info transmitted to app
content: fits nice, Not accurate with info transmitted to app

title: An expensive paperweight
content: I liked them when I first got them but I use them for work and I have had many complaints about change in volume of my voice during a call. I don’t know how to alleviate that so I have discontinued use. A very expensive paperweight

title: Overall a decent headphone, but turns out to be lack luster especially in sound quality
content:
The sound is pretty decent, not anything to write home about. The Bose Soundsport headphones are quite a bit better in sound quality. The microphones work very well and the connection is quite strong!  The biggest issue I had with them was that I couldn't get a good fit with any of the ear gels and I have regular size, shaped ears. They would either be super uncomfortable with wearing more than an hour or with the bigger ones they would fit fine the way they are suppose to and then slowly slide out ,which is a lot more dangerous when you have no wires!
TLDR
Pros: Connection, Call Quality
Cons: Sound quality is only decent, fit is hard to get right and be careful they might fall out

title: left earpiece flawed
content: The left earbud failed to work almost immediately. Since it was within the return window, I foolishly elected for a new pair instead of getting a refund. Now the replacement left earbud has failed outside the refund window. Do not buy these earbuds.

title: Best earbuds I have ever owner
content: I love them. They are extremely comfortable, they stay in place, and they hold up to sweat. If you lose them, you can use the app to find them, or if they turn off it has a map in the app of where they were last turned on. The sound is great and the hear through function is phenomenal. They are also extremely light and the charging case is compact.

title: Terrible customer support
content: The microphone on my earbuds stopped working a few weeks after receiving them. I contacted Jabra who gave me the typical troubleshooting steps which didn’t work. I filled out the warranty form and no one has contacted me about a replacement. AirPods and Apple service might be the way to go.

title: Replaced twice
content: I like the product when it works. I purchased this through Best Buy and it worked for about 6 months then the right ear volume dropped. Sent in for a replacement, and within 2 months the replacements right ear volume dropped. They just sent me another one. I would definitely avoid these

title: Works great, flawless sync, comfortable.
content: Although I have the Bose Soundsport Wireless (not the Truly wireless newer model) I like the idea of these headphones due to their size and the two year "water" warranty as I plan to use these to workout and do yard work.  I was slightly skeptical as I tried the Jaybirds in the past and didn't like the fit and the video/sound sync was off.  These resolve ALL those issues and are great.  I can't use the Bose when mowing the yard as they stick way out of my ears and my ear protection doesn't fit.  These fit nicely in the ear with limited protrusions.  They sync easily to my phone and computer and I like how the app allows you to change the noise cancellation options.  When I have the full cancellation option on I can hear nothing (this has annoyed my wife tremendously when she has tried to talk to me in this mode.  There is no video/sound sync issue.  The only negative I have is I have sometimes dropped them when putting them in my ear as there is s specific way to do this and they can slip out.  But that is more my issues than Jabra's.  I can't recommend these enough.  They certainly don't look like Q-tips hanging out of your ears.

title: big and uncomfortable for all of our ears
content:
i was looking for a pair of wireless earbuds for use in my wife's phone. She had tried Apple airpods, but didn't like the feel of them, so we read reviews online and decided to try the Jabra elite 65t. We tested them out for a bit before ultimately deciding to return them.

Pros:
- easy setup, but not as good as apple airpods
- decent sound for playing music. we both agreed that the sound quality, although tinny sounding at first, was slightly better than airpods.
- multiple inner ear pieces to vary the fit.
- has an auto pause feature when you remove them from your ears. might be nice for some people but we all hated it so we turned it off

Cons:
- big and bulky. you have to cram it in your ears, and sort of wedge it in until it feels stable enough. even then, it feels like it would fall out if you did any quick motions with it. you also definitely can tell its there and it is very uncomfortable. definitely not as stable as airpods.
- everytime I put them on I have to remember which ear they go into, which is not obvious from shape until you get used to it. theres a little L and R on them but its hard to see, so I fumbled around a bunch each time I go to put them in. I don't have this problem with airpods.

in general it's not a bad set of headphones, but for the price you could just get airpods, and add one of those clear rubber earbud skins to make them fit better.

title: To much interference
content: To much interference left earbud...

title: Sounded like $25 earbuds
content: I bought a pair for my wife's birthday. I listened to them and wasn't impressed in the slightest.  They sounded like $25 earbuds. I compared the sound quality to my daughter's Airpods and the Airpods sounded amazing. There is no way these Jabra Elite Active 65t were real unless they make absolute garbage. They felt and looked great just the sound was horrific. Even when using the Jabra App and turning up the bass there was hardly any and sound like crap. I had paid $189 for them.... and yes I returned them. These had to be Fakes!

title: Disappointed
content:
Voice quality for calls is subpar.  People complain they can barely hear me.  Never had these types of complaints with my Beats.

Uncomfortable to wear for more than 15 minutes.

title: Does not stay in ear!
content: I can only use them by holding one in place.  The sound was good, but I don't want to walk around with my hand to my ear.  I guess I will have to return.

title: Sound Matters
content: I purchased a set back in August or Sept. And they were great up until mid March. The sound in the right earbud would start at an average volume, then it would gradually decrease. I thought maybe it just needed to be charged. So I would do such. But to no avail, even with a fully charged battery, the sound quality would be poor. Add in the left earbud, the sound in the right earbud would no longer exist. I've contacted customer support and they would send trouble shoots, no explanations. I followed their troubleshoots and the problem is still not solved. Unpaired, re-paired, updated language update several times, recharging, restarting, etc etc. Nothing. Do yourself a favor: look elsewhere for quality true wireless earbuds.

title: Not loud / noise canceling enough to hear while on the train
content:
These sound great in a quiet room and I like using them while washing the dishes but they suck outdoors or in noisy environments like the subway.
Noise cancelation is not that strong and the volume level does not go up high enough.
The carry case charging is nice.
Tips don't come in enough sizes, I'm between the small and medium.
Not really worth the money.

title: Fantastic design crushed by bad quality
content:
Avoid. While, these are the best true wireless ear buds I've used, including Apple's AirPods, and they have the best mix of functionality, sound, and battery life with the fewest compromises, the quality & durability is bad.

Ater less than 1 month of light use (and no moisture), they no longer connect when opening the case, and the left ear bud only connects 10% of the time. Currently, I can get it to connect by holding down a volume button, which seems to wake it up.

I expect this will continue to degrade until they are garbage, and at this rate, I'll be lucky to get 90 days out of them. I tried a new brand, and will hard pass on Jabra products in the future.

title: gret tws headphones
content:
It was for gift,
My sun. Happy )

title: Durable and reliable
content:
These are some tough earbuds. i dropped them doing 22 miles an hour on my bike and once i found them i cleaned them off and popped it in my ear and it worked like a charm.
the one thing i do not like is it does not carry much bass to the music. 4 hours is about as much as i can get on a charge. i would recommend these two anyone that asked.

title: Horrible for Calls.. Good for Music..
content:
These earbuds are advertised saying they have 4 microphones hence they are best for taking calls as they remove the wind noise. That's all a joke. I bought 1 pair of these and replaced them thinking it might have been a faulty unit but the new unit has exactly the same problem.

Pros
- Good for music and gym.
- Connectivity is good
- Small size is easy and convinient to carry
- Long battery life

Cons
- the call quality is horrible and when I say horrible I mean you cannot take calls with these if there are any noises in the background. Even if the noises in the background are minor, the microphones enhance that sound many fold that the person on the other end feels like you are in the middle of a war zone. I had to always switch back to the phone to take calls.
- the fit is also not meant for all ears since the shape of the earbuds have a unique shape that completely fills the ear. Hence if you have smaller ears, you won't be able to keep these on for more than an hour or two at a single stretch.

Overall I would say that if you just need these for music you can go for it but I would recommend going for something cheaper than this is music/gym is your only need.
If you want to also use these to sometimes take calls, don't buy these. I am still in search of truly wireless earbuds that are good for taking calls.

title: These are the best!
content: I’ve been totally impressed with these ear buds.  Jabra is a European company that has specialized in earphone technology for decades.  They know what they are doing and the product reflects that.  Impressive sound, secure, comfortable  fit, great battery life and charger is small and easy to carry.

title: Sound is lacking and they feel like rocks in your ears
content: The sound has zero base, it's pretty tinny. If you need the base, look elsewhere. They are hard, and big, so they feel like rocks in your ears. Reviews said the material was soft, but it is not at all. I can handle about 30 minutes with these on before they start to hurt. They fall out occasionally, although only on harder jolts. Not much good for vigorous workouts, though. Overall, I'm not impressed. Especially with the great recommendations I saw for them on Wirecutter. Where can I find some wireless headphones with GOOD sound that don't hurt my ears?

title: Amazing earbuds
content: I bought these as a gift for my boyfriend to wear at his job. He has to be kind of discreet about it so he wanted wireless ones. I did a lot of research, and ended up on this pair. He ABSOLUTELY loves them. He wears them all day every day at work and hasn't complained once. He loved that they came with other sized ear pieces, and he says he can turn them up so loud h doesn't even hear his machines running at work (which he says he didn't think was possible). He said the only downfall is that sometimes (not a lot) and at random times it will like "skip" even though it's playing MP3 type music. But it doesn't seem to bother him. Thanks Jabra, and Amazon. These things are awesome.

title: Alright but kept falling off
content: Honestly this product was very good in every aspect just the biggest problem was it kept falling off my ears whenever I make sudden movements so unfortunate I had to return it

title: Good headphones, but dog destroyed them
content: Overall these were solid headphones, I don’t know if they were worth it for the price though. The carrying case was small and easy to carry, headphones were lightweight and only hurt my ears if I wore them for several hours at a time. My biggest downfall is I used these a lot to talk on the phone and routinely had complaints the background noise was horrible and you could barely hear me if there was noise. Contacted support and they got back to me within 48 hours. Unfortunately, I didn’t get the chance to try what they suggested. My dog was trying a new medication and had an adverse reaction to it, I forgot to put my school bag in the closet and he completely destroyed the case and the headphones. The level of destruction was actually impressive, the case was broken into 3 large pieces and the headphones themselves were completely crunched. But he’s a 55 lb pit mix and if his ability to destroy toys is any demonstration, I’d say the case stood up pretty well considering.

title: The worst part is I only use it an hour or ...
content: Broken within 8 days of purchase. The left earphone has static, and most of time no sound. The worst part is I only use it an hour or two per day since I purchased this headset.

title: Uncomfortable and impractical
content: Very uncomfortable and they keep falling out. Impossible to do everyday chores with, much less jog or run. Sound is tinny. The mic is good. The plastic on the insert cuts into our ears. Also, if you remove one from your ear, both of them turn off. They're uncomfortable and impractical.

title: Good
content: Good earphones only thing that sucks Is u can only use the right one in dependant u can't charge the right and use left

title: Review for 1st 3 months of use
content:
Great quality, very durable, sticks to ur ears without having to worry that it’s going to fall out and the call quality is excellent.Everyone that I called,I asked them how they heard me and they all said that they could hear me clearly.  Pairs great with app use.  Once in awhile it would have issues pairing both buds, but it didn’t take long to rectify.
Like this product so far
One thing that bugs me is trying to troubleshoot a new headphone that I just bought.  Why am I troubleshooting something that is new?h

title: Great to play MP3's and will connect to smart TV and other devices, even a roundabout method for SmartPhone FM play.
content:
There seemed to be a lot of debate on how to do it, but without too much trouble I was able to find the right method to play the FM radio from my smartphone through these.  The method was pretty simple, but it may not work for all phones.  I downloaded an app from the playstore on the phone called Mono Bluetooth Router.  It was made for those applications that use a single Bluetooth in the ear speaker and mic to talk with hands free calls.  The main problem to play an FM broadcast radio, is that on a phone you almost always need the earphones (wired ones) plugged in to act as the antenna.  When that's done the phone automatically shunts the sound to the earphones, and not the speaker or any Bluetooth connection.  With the Mono Router installed, it captures that sound and ships ito to the Bluetooth device in this case the Jabra Earbuds.  The whole process took less than 10 minutes to finish.

Next, I looked up the Bluetooth connector on my LG OLED tv and connected it, again no problem and I got excellent sound from anything playing on the TV or streaming to it from my ROKU.  Pairing is easy you hold the button down on the right earbud for 3 seconds and search for the connection on your source device, phone, TV etcetera.  Then connect, and you'll hear the sound over the earbuds.  To change volume up or down press the button right or left on the left earbud and the volume changes.  I got an occasional minor dropout for a second maybe, but I don't think I have 5.0 Bluetooth on my phone probably 4.0 or less.  It did not seem to be a problem though especially if I was sitting and not walking around.  The charging case is very convenient, although a bit tricky to get the earbuds aligned right over the charging pins.  With the charging case you can charge the buds twice more for up to 15 hours before having to go back to the charger.

It came with a USB cable with a common connector (common because it's on my Kindle, my old flip phone, and even a rechargeable pepper mill I just reviewed).  Most people have the standard USB slot in a computer or other device or the plug adapter, so this device didn't come with one.  A little cheap on their part for such expensive buds, but OK, not a much needed.  The buds have microphones on each, and when wearing it suggests to turn them towards the front.  I felt the sound was a good as could be expected within the Bluetooth transmission.  If I had a good 5.0 device, it could probably be better.  A lot of money to spend on earbuds to be sure, but these are very well made, and the innovative charging case adds a lot of value there as well.  Comes with three extra sizes of ear inserts to give you the most comfortable fit possible.  Though solid, these are very light and I wore them for a few hours, watching anime and youtube videos with no discomfort.  Recommended if you like high end wireless sound.

title: I really wanted to like these....
content:
I really wanted to like these. I had been eyeing them for quite awhile and when the price dropped momentariliy to $149, I instantly bought them. Two days later I returned them.

They looked good. They fit very well and were very comfortable. The issue was that there was constant dropout. I bought a cheaper set that had a much better sound than the Elite 65t (even with the app downloaded and use of the equalizer). The cheaper set always stayed connected (with the exception of a certain spot by my job where I knew it would drop).

This set would lose connection with the phone in my pocket. The whole point of purchasing them was so that I wouldn't have to pull my phone out of my pocket to change the volume or change songs.

title: The best true wireless earbuds you can buy
content:
I did plenty of research, and these looked the most promising, and they totally delivered. The fit is perfect, don’t fall out while exercising, sound quality is great, and call quality was impressive, even while outside on a very windy day.
I’ve tried the Jaybird Run, and it doesn’t compare. The Jabra has better sound, better fit - even without fins, able to adjust the volume on the actual earbud - something most true wireless earbuds can’t do, 4 microphone technology, on phone calls the audio is in both ears, automatically pairs when you take it out of the case, can pair with multiple devices, buttons are easy to press - the buttons on the Jaybird were really hard to press, really pushed into my ear, and they are also much nicer looking, which is especially nice when walking out in public. And from what ive seen looking around, many of the flaws of the Jaybird are present in just about all other true wireless earbuds, even ones more expensive.

title: Bigger ear buds
content: After a while they tend to slide out the ear.. either bigger ear buds or stronger material ear buds

title: volume doesn't get loud, slips out of ears
content: took a chance on some expensive earbuds.  i "upgraded" from jaybird's x2 earbuds.  although the jabra's are a nice touch on true wireless, 2 of the 3 most important qualities in a pair of earbuds this expensive fell short.  1. battery life is good, and i have no complaints; 2. the volume doesn't get loud enough.  i typically find myself with these on, full volume, with no audible satisfaction.  i feel like i'm constantly craving more.  i'm not deaf.  i can hear just fine, but i think the volume on these is absolute trash.  3.  i sweat a lot when i work out.  these will slip out of your ears.  i wear the correct sized tip, and the earbuds do create a suction type sensation in the ear, but sweat is bound to get in between your actual ear and the rubber ear tip itself, and that is what causes these to slip out.  please reconsider another brand and save yourself $180 if you're in the market for true wireless earbuds.  10/10, would NOT recommend.

title: Great sound, great battery life
content: I've had these for almost a year now. Battery life is great and sound is great! They don't look as cool as iPods but they are waaaay better~

title: Great purchase
content: Everything is great! Exactly like I expected!

title: Broke in my ear.
content: Only 2.5 months old and the earbud piece separated and a piece got stuck in my ear. I had to have someone use tweezers to get it out.  I only use these in the gym and I’m not doing anything crazy - just regular weight workouts. Seems dangerous to me.

title: Top quality sound, comfort and noise cancelling.
content:
These are the best earbuds I've ever owned, full stop. I use these primarily in the gym and have never had an issue with them falling out or losing any functionality when they become wet with sweat. The included tips are comfortable for long durations without causing any aches or soreness when you remove them. Excellent design and features. I dont really use the step count feature as I have other wearable for that, but I did play around with it and compared it to my galaxy fit 2 and galaxy watch active and they seemed to be every bit as accurate

I really like the active pass through for when you need to be aware of your surroundings, like when jogging outside. It's a bit odd at first hearing what's around you via the built in mics, but you quickly get used to it.

title: Really convenient
content: Tone a little light on the bass. Otherwise pleased.

title: Rip off - unbalanced sound
content: Don't buy these, save your money. Mine have never worked correctly, and I reached out to customer service and that wasn't helpful either. Basically, they worked for a month and then the sound in the right ear became inaudible. I've done every reset, updated software, etc. Never again...

title: Not the best option for good sound - try the Bose Soundsport Free
content: Bought these because I accidentally put my old Bose Soundsport wireless earbuds through the washing machine and finally killed them. The Jabras do look great and the functionality is awesome - very easy to use. But they just don't sound great. As soon as I used them I immediately felt disappointed by the sound quality - they feel flat, no depth, no bass, no "wow" feeling, definitely not worth the premium price. I returned them and bought the Bose Soundsport Free earbuds and I'm happy again! If you're like I was and you're deciding between Bose and Jabra, I would suggest Bose.

title: Stopped working.
content: Ordered back in July 2018, it is now January 2018. The left ear bud stopped working. I never used them hard or with the volume up all the way.

Tried liking these ear buds but it’s just not worth it for the price. Cannot keep buds in ear for a long period of time because they become very uncomfortable. The sound quality is also not that great.

title: I’m using them with an iPhone X and no one can hear me talk without a lot of static
content: I’m using them with an iPhone X and no one can hear me talk without a lot of static

title: Hit or Miss, I got a Miss
content: I got these headphones with high expectations, charged them up and went to test, no sound of the right ear, but plenty out the left. Follow allow the troubleshooting I could find and reached out to the support team, to their credit they were okay, but not helpful in end. Worked through every fix in the book and nothing. Do a quick google search on the issue of no sound out of one ear and you will find lots of posts about this problem and related problems. QA is not catching these manufacture defects. Spent my entire evening troubleshooting and got nowhere. Returning for a refund as I don't have anymore time to troubleshoot this and I'm not inclined to try another Jabra Product for a while after this experience. I really wanted to test drive these, because they are hyped by so many people as being a good product, but that's just not the experience I had. Gonna try Sony again as I've not had issues with their sports headsets.

title: Ridiculously uncomfortable
content: It hurt to wear. You should wait for a next generation

title: Superb, high-quality, wireless buds; works perfectly with iPhone 7 and MacBook Pro
content:
WOW!  Absolutely fantastic sound with my iPhone 7 and MacBook Pro.  Setup was very intuitive and quick, with the only confusion arising from the need to install the Jabra 65t app on my phone in order to complete the installation.  I have very large ear canals, so I was concerned that the standard medium silicone inserts would not fit well, but they actually worked out quite well.  In the end, I swapped the mediums our for the large cups, and I get an excellent seal and isolation, and they are comfortable enough that I can go for 2-3 hours with these buds inserted in my ears without being aware of the buds in my ears (can't say that about any other similar buds, which usually get painful after about an hour).

The sound quality is simply superb and rivals my older Etymotics buds (that I'm now retiring).  Volume controls are intuitive (on the left bud), and power/call control is on the right bud.  Yet again, a Jabra product that doesn't require the use of a user's manual.  I'm also a daily (happy) user of the flagship Jabra Engage 75 binaural headset -- my daily work headset -- and the build and sound quality of the Elite 65t is right up there with the Engage.

After (literally) decades of being a dedicated Sennheiser fan, I've now completely switched over to Jabra and feel that I am getting the greatest possible value for my money -- and a lot of money it is, as an early adopter ($600 for both the Engage and the Elite).  Couldn't be happier and more thrilled with this purchase.

title: Wireless Earbuds
content: Work very well, much better than the beats 2 that i was wearing.  Don't have to turn up volume to ridiculous levels to hear music when running by streets, but do have to turn up podcasts.  Quality product.

title: Life Changing
content:
Fit and stay put wonderfully.  Sound is more than adequate for movies/casual listening.

The only improvement I would suggest is that the carry-case/charger should be wireless.  Plunking this down on a QI charger intead of pluggin it in would be awesome.

title: You won't be dissatisfied
content: The quality of sound and clarity are amazing. Great for relaxation or workouts.

title: Great earbuds
content: These earbuds provide great sounds quality.  They also give you the option to block outside noise or "hear through".  Went from wired earbuds to these and really appreciate not having tangled cords.

title: Too big for my ears
content: These were cool except i think my ears are too small. Even with the smallest silicon option the earbuds hurt and would periodically fall out. I couldn't risk losing $170 since I like to go ocean fishing and they fall out.

title: Sounded great until the stopped taking a charge
content: Earbuds easy to set up, fit comfortably. Stopped charging after about two weeks.  Technical support was unable to resolve issue.  Sent them back for refund.

title: Great
content: Great

title: Not as expected for sound and material quality
content: I must have received a defective item as Bluetooth keeps dropping and reconnecting (battery fully charged) and left right earpieces are not really synching.

title: Nice quality and great sound
content:
I thought I would save some money and tried out a cheaper $55 set of earbuds. I reviewed many options and even though the reviews on the cheaper ones stated poor bass and low end quality I gave them a try. After a trial run on a few songs with prominent bass lines I decided to return the original purchase and went with the Jabra Elite based on multiple good reviews. Not disappointed in upgrading! If you want good sound quality these are a great option for the money.

I did want adjustable ear pieces so that ruled our the Apple AirPods. It would be nice if the Jabra came with a universal charge bank capability and magnetic seating in the case but overall these are a great choice.

title: Good earbuds
content: Tried the ear buds, the sound was good (not great), the battery life is about 4hr but the negative for me was the bulkiness of the unit.

title: Great sound quality.
content: The Jabra Elite 65t earbuds are great. My personal experience wearing them validates all of the great reviews I read before purchasing them. The sound quality is excellent. The equalizer allows you to set your music they way you like it. I personally like a nice crisp bass sound in my music. Despite some reviews that said the bass is okay, I find it to be better than good. My music sounds so clear and lively. I definitely recommend them to anyone looking for a top quality pair of wireless Bluetooth earbuds.

title: No issues, work great
content: Would recommend to anyone in the wireless earbud market that doesn't want airpods.

title: SO IN LOVE!
content: These earbuds are AMAZING! My biggest want when purchasing earbuds are that it will drown out background noise. The sure do! The sound quality is great! It is so comfortable in my ears. My hubby tried to steal them from me even before they arrived. Its a really good thing that I work at home so he was not able to grab them before I did.  The sound quality alone is bar-none! I highly recommend this to EVERYONE!

title: Excellent product. Truly waterproof proven.
content: I’ve been using it for 3 months. And they are comfortable, don’t slip out in the sweat. Sound quality is good, however is not the best. I forgot them in my pocket and put them in the washer machine. They still work fine. Calls are clear. The only bad thing is that there is a little delay in the audio in relation with the video.

title: Picks up noise background
content:
I am normally skeptical when I receive a recommendation. I saw the video of this with the guy talking to his girl on the train not hearing all the background noise. I had to try it out myself and see if it is true.

People on the other line could barely hear me talk. It was picking up all the background noise around me instead of minimizing the noise. I ride an SUV with off road tires. The bluetooth was picking up the tire noise and was amplifying it.

I am going back to my airpods that is better than this bluetooth.

title: Super comfortable, decent sound, great price
content:
I have always been hesident of buying a totally wireless Bluetooth headset. I was concerned about the fit, sound quality and the connectivity. These were on sale for$119 for Black Friday so I decided to take the plunge.

First of all the fit. While this headset looks a bit bulky it fits like a dream.  They are snug, secure, and don't even feel like they are there. This was my biggest concern. I used the gells that it shipped with, but there are 3 other choices.

The sound quality is very good. The bass is a little lacking, but it is pretty good. I had a problem with the volume being too low but it turned out to be an issue with a setting on my S8.

There are some issues with drop out, and that is probably the main reason I can't give 5 stars. I get drop outs every few minutes. I should note that I also get some drop out on my 2017 Hyundai sonata, though it does seem to drop out more with the headphones. It is somewhat annoying, but not that big of a problem for me personally.

Overall I am satisfied. They fit well, have decent sound quality, but have a few issues with drop outs, though perhaps no more than any other headset.

If you are looking for absolutely killer sound and no drop outs, this might not be for you, but for $119 I think they are well worth it.

title: Good quality as I expected from Jabra.
content: I am very happy with the choice of this product. I saw reviews of different products and these Jabra Elite came up on top consistently. I will buy again when I wear these out.

title: Poor sou d and battery quality
content: Only about noon and battery already dying,  sound issues with multie callers both directions. Previous Plantronics went all day easily. So far waste of money

title: Good buy
content: They don’t fall out if you’re ears.

title: Don’t buy garbage
content: The left ear stopped working in 3 months. Don’t buy these customer support is useless.

title: Good headset overall
content: It's a little static if rubbing good, some complaints when recieving calls person calling says voice sounds statically

title: Most amazing and best truly wireless earbuds!!
content: Great sound and incredible features. Can control the sound mix and "hear-thru" technology from the app on my phone. I can even locate them if I should somehow drop one...this was so useful after one of my cats knocked the case off my desk! The "hear-thru" feature is amazing! You can select whether or not to block out ambient noises and have true noise cancelling earbuds. Plus, if you're listening to music, you can pull one bud out, the music pauses, and then pit bud back in for music to start. Very excellent purchase for the price!!

title: Great sound !!
content: Very nice sound !! I added true grips and man ooo man they sound so good ..

title: Potentially breaks when other Bluetooth items paired to phone
content: I am having major issues with these ! They worked perfectly for the first couple of months and then all of a sudden started making a screeching sound in their case (I think they interacted badly with another Bluetooth item (Muse meditation headband) I paired I my phone). Well they never recovered / worked properly again. They were hanging up calls, turning on in their case etc. Jabra customer service provided no help whatsoever and sent me a link to the handbook (which I had already read 3x troubleshooting). I ordered a replacement pair and they are not working as well as the first ones initially did. Connection is crackling and other annoying things. Not sure if I should order a third or go with a different company ...

title: These are the best
content: My husband is a truck broker, constantly on his phone.  These have been a game changer for him.  So efficient.  Easy to charge.

title: Sounds cuts in and out!
content:
Sounds cuts in and out! even when I sit down and do not move. It seems to cut out ever 30-40 seconds. I find this unacceptable.

I like the fit. I find them comfortable. The sound is great. They charge quickly and the charge lasts a long time. I wish the sound would not cut out so often.

title: Disappointed of call quality
content: Unlike Jabra's claim that its call quality is superior to other truly wireless earbuds, the call quality of my Jabra elite active 65t is terrible. To be precise, if I am in doors the the receiving end can hear my voice very clearly. However once I step outside, especially in a noisy scene such as a subway or the bus, the earbuds pick up EVERY f* surrounding noise and covers my voice. People tell me that they cannot hear my voice due to the loud surrounding noise. This is disappointing as Jabra's ads are promoting call qualities in noisy scenes but fails to deliver  in its selling point. I contacted customer service and there response was to update firmware and if that does not solve it, 'go get an earbud with a mic'. Did some more research and it seems this happens to only some of these products but no apparent fixes have been mentioned. Planning to return

title: Left Earbud Consistently Doesn't Charge
content: This has happened to two different sets of earbuds I purchased. I was hoping it was an isolated issue the first time, but unfortunately this has started to happen again with my next set.

title: Jabra Elite Active 65t
content: Jabra has gone above and beyond greatness with the Jabra Elite Active 65t. One of the best Bluetooth wireless earbuds I .have ever purchased. Sound quality is super and call quality is crystal clear. Great job Jabra.

title: Great wireless earbuds
content: Good quality for listening and talking. I use it for work calls all the time.

title: High quality sound and materials. No drop outs.
content: Small and comfortable. Pairing was a breeze. No drop-outs at all. High quality sound, though bass was somewhat light, even when adjusting the equalizer in the App, but you can't fit a woofer in your ear. If you want tooth rattling bass, go over-the-ear. There is a half second sound delay for videos (YouTube). Phone calls answered with a button push, which stops music temporarily. Excellent call quality. Best I've had by far. Would get again.

title: Great product
content: Work great.

title: and still searching for something to beat the Jaybird X3
content:
I know the X3 are not true wireless. I want true wireless, but no one has yet to come close to the Jaybird product and until a manufacturer does I will keep the annoying strap between earbuds.
Masters and Dynamics will be the next attempt at true wireless.
While the Jabra had an "I can like with it" sound quality, the volume was limited and the occasional millisecond drop in the stream was too much to take.

title: Superior sound but ....
content:
There's nothing wrong with the earbuds, but I just want to help others if they are still debating if they should buy this pair of earbuds or not. To be honest, don't. You can buy some less expensive one and wait for the next version or Jabra if you love the brand.
Pro:
Superior sound. If my Bose QC35II is 10, this one is 8.
Awesome connection. I can leave my phone in the living room and going around the house without losing the connection.
Good battery.

Con:
Heavy. I have to let my ear relax after awhile because this pair is heavy, heavier than the other pair of earbuds I have been using
You can only use the right one for mono because it's the master one. Sometimes, I want to give my right ear a break but still want to use the earbud but that's impossible for this pair.
The box: not easy to open and no magnet to help putting the earbuds in like other brands.

title: it can be connected with two deviced at same time
content: They are light，very comfortable to wear, fit very good in my ears. Great they can connected with two devices at same time.  I use it  connected with my Huawei mate 10 pro and Samsung Gear 3 watch, no problem found so far. Very good sound .Good bass.

title: Jabra Elite 65t NOT so Elite
content:
After trying out the Bose sport (major disappointing) I purchased the Jabra Elite 65t at Best Buy. Right out of the box they look sleek and have a very low profile design and look good in the ears (unlike Apple’s Qtip terrible look) The charging case felt cheap and was a major letdown, for $170 dollars I expected a magnetically sealed case and as well to secure the earbuds in place while charging. The left earbud fit perfect however the right earbud just didn’t fit very well. I tried all the tips that came in the packaging and couldn’t get that snug feeling with the right earbud. They paired fairly easy to my iPhone XS Max and I had no issues pairing the earbuds. The sound quality was good, and much better than Apple’s AirPods. I downloaded the app and tweaked the sound quality which improved the overall experience.

While listening to music with my new Jabra Elite 65t the left earbud just stopped functioning and I could only hear music emitting from the right earbud. I removed the left earbud placed it back in my ear and nothing. I removed both earbuds placed them in the charging case and after repairing them I was back in business. This was a major disappointment and the first issue I had with the 65t.

At the gym, these earbuds wouldn’t stay snugged into the ear canal while lifting so if you made any facial expressions the earbuds would dislodge from the ear canal and you could hear the environment around you, from the overhead music being played at the gym, to people talking and all the equipment being used. I had to keep readjusting the earbuds and it got annoying very fast.

The call quality was good, but not great. You could hear the person clearly on the other end, but I was told I sounded like a robot and my voiced was muffled. After repeating myself several times during the phone call I had to disconnect from the Jabra Elite 65t and finish my conversation on my iPhone without the 65t.

If you spend $170 dollars on a pair of true wireless earbuds you expect, a working set of earbuds, decent phone call quality on both ends, and a good charging case that is magnetically sealed. The sound quality was good however it wasn’t $170 dollars good. I own a pair of Senso Bluetooth headphones which I bought on Amazon for $40 bucks and they sound just as good.

The Jabra Elite 65t are way overpriced for what they offer and how they perform. Do they sound better than Apple’s Airpods? Absolutely, but practically every Bluetooth or wireless earbuds sound better than Apple’s AirPods (expect Bose SoundSport free sound about the same) for $170 dollars and with all the connectivity issues that have been reported all over the internet along with the left earbud losing connectivity while I was using them was enough for me to return the Jabra Elite 65t.

title: Two faulty units
content: I purchased the Jabra Active 65t in July 2018.  About 2 months later, the right earbud would no charge anymore.  Jabra support sent me a replacement unit, but in November 2018 the replacement started having communication issues between the left and right earbud.  So I got two faulty units in a row!  Too bad, because the sound quality is really good, but the build quality of these units are pure trash.

title: Top sound quality and perfectly fit
content: i have both Apple AirPods and the Jabara Elite 65.  Better sound quality and excellent fit go to Jabara by miles. AirPods do not not stay in my ears and require silicone cover from a third party. Because AirPods do not stay in your ears, then the sound quality is compromised unless you consistently push the pods in your ears. Jabara has an excellent phone app which helps customize the ear buds I was hoping the case would be magnetic similar to AirPods.

title: Not worth $200.00 dollars
content: These things have tarable connection and the sound feels off in both earbuds this is definitely not something to invest your hard earned money in to not worth it trust me

title: Terrible for phone calls!!
content:
When trying to talk on the phone with these, not only can the other person not hear me very well, they can hear the ambient noise much better. The mics for ambience seem to be better for picking up ambiance than the voice mic for talking. Very dissapointed.

Music on these are nice. But again, terrible for taking calls. Changing the settings does nothing to help. These are my second pair as I was hoping it was a bad pair. These are going back as well.

title: Decent quality but form factor & poor call quality not worth the money
content:
Pros:
- Good quality music
- Decent build quality of headphones & charger

Cons:
- Painful to use after wearing for 1 hour, especially with glasses on.
- Useless when taking calls with a little background noise. To the recipient, background noise seems amplified compared to your voice. I can really only use it for calls in quiet conference rooms. Not in the car, on the streets, etc.
- This might be because I don't have a snug enough fit, but when I run with these, sound quality is poor.

Overall I wouldn't buy these again if I could revisit my decision.

title: Brilliant!!
content: I got these earphones a couple months ago and they comparing to the AirPods I have, The Kant’s elite active 65t earphones beat them in all categories. They have a very comfortably formed for to my ears and have outstanding sound quality!

title: Left ear defective?
content: Okay, firstly I would like to say that these earbuds are really amazing. I’m impressed with the build quality and especially the sound quality. I feel like having the sound+ app is crucial to make the sound even better, depending on your preference. They haven’t fallen out of my ear during my workouts and that’s amazing. They feel secure in my ears. Battery life was decent, I have never used them for the 5 hours consecutively so they haven’t died on me yet since I always put them back in the case. The ONLY problem with MY pair is that the left earphone keeps cutting off like every 3 minutes or so. It goes quiet for a quick second and comes back to line. But it makes the static noise as it does, becomes distracting. It also happens when I get into a certain position when laying down, and I tilt my head to the right, the left earbud sounds like a static tv. Might just be defective but not sure how to get in contact with the seller. I’m still giving it a 5 star because I’m pretty sure I just have a defective product, other than that, everything was just amazing.

title: Sounds great, but left bud loses connection from time to time.
content: These pair of true wireless earbuds are definitely great-sounding. I use it everyday for my commute to work. One thing I notice is that the left earbud loses connection. I have to reset the pair just to get it back up and working again.

title: Hurt ears, replaced silicone tips with foam. Way better
content: Great for talking and listening to music. Recommend buying foam tips for them. Started hurting ears with original tips. After foam, ears feel good, improved sound quality and noise canceling

title: Very good
content: Very good

title: I really had high hopes for these
content: They came on time and were exactly as described.  I charged them up for a business trip.  These items kept cutting out on phone calls.  They were very disappointing and they were sent back.

title: Maybe its me...
content:
First the sound really wasn't that robust. I was underwhelmed with the fact I had to turn the volume almost all the way up to get it where I liked my other devices (I don't really ask much from said devices...I'm 55 so...).

THEN they began falling out. I tried all of the tips. When I went to the gym they stayed in for roughly 4 minutes. I tried several different insertion methods with no luck.

I thought "maybe I can wear them around the house, just not to the gym". Nope! Still kept falling out albeit it took a few minutes more than at the gym.

Bottom Line: I paid way too much for these for the lackluster performance. I am not ruling out that the fitment issue is because I am a mutant or something. I didn't see where others had problems keeping them in so maybe its the size / shape of my ear canals.

Im pretty disappointed since the idea of them would be awesome for my needs.

title: Bought these because I read a great review. I've tried virtually every major wireless earbud
content: Bought these because I read a great review.  I've tried virtually every major wireless earbud.  These fit great & are relatively inconspicuous compared to some. But I can't recommend them.  The good: Ear fit, weight, connectivity.  The bad: low volume, very thin sound.  The Bose Free Soundsport are still the best ones out there.  They sound much, much better than these.

title: Great quality, die out every 4 hours. Customer support sucks.
content: Loved the product at first but soon after one of the earbuds lost bass and didn’t sound as good as the other one. Also when I tilt my head a certain direction while using them for either reading a book or play basketball they will lose all sound and become super staticky. I’ve been trying to get a hold of Jabra support for the past 3 hours with no response. Maybe I should have just bought some EarPods.

title: Not for small ears...
content: Great product,  but they were way too big for my ears. My brother loves them.

title: Easy connection, good sound and voice quality in office environment. Charger works well. Overall quite pleased
content:
I am basing this review with these earbuds and a current Samsung note 8 using an android Oreo system.

Let me preface the review by stating that I have used multiple different headsets and am generally disappointed with the results of Bluetooth headsets. My current favorite is the LG HBS1100 for daily use. Although that headset gets equivocal reviews, I find that it is very convenient and has great reception. Sound quality is also excellent. I have not had issues with a retractable earbud nor had any failures. My major complaint with that headset is it does appear to have issues after about a year of constant use and it is not a "forever" headset.

I have also used the LG HBS912 which essentially is a less expensive version of the HBS1100.

For working out,LG - TONE Active HBS-850. That's the waterproof version of the LG Bluetooth

All of these headsets use a retractable earbud and a collar that sits on your neck. It has great reception and works well for my point of view. But wearing that collar certainly looks a little bit bizarre

I've been looking for a good pair of the wireless earbuds and have been following all of the reviews.

I tried a pair of the Samsung wireless but they only work with Samsung phones and are not universally accepted by all Bluetooth receivers.

I followed the recent Jabra headphones but found battery charge in the reviews were not great

I noticed many of the reviews on the set of wireless earbuds are when they were just released. They have come out with some firmware updates which have attempted to address many of the issues. Ultimately, I decided to take the plunge and buy these earbuds.

My overall experience is been excellent. I have read all of the negative reviews and from my point of view have not experienced any of major issue. The sound reception is quite good, and when using them inside an office or in a closed environment, people can hear me clearly. I often take conference calls from other persons or do telephonic consultations and while sitting in my office using these earbuds the people at the other end of the phone tell me can hear me clearly and the sound quality is good.

The hook up with regards to Bluetooth was quick and easy. Not only does it hook up to my cell phone, it connects to the Bluetooth on every device I own. The video sounded delay is nominal and when watching TV I can enjoy the Bluetooth transmission with only a very small amount of noise video difference..

Charging cases easy to use. I plug it in at night. When I'm not using the earphones there in the case in constantly recharging. When I do use them they hook immediately up to my phone on removal and it sinks without an issue.

I have not use them outside in conversations as I do appreciate sound noise would be a problem. Also, they are not waterproof but merely water resistant so I do not use them for working out. I have use them when listening to streaming radio and working in the yard. They are very good to use and very convenient. If someone calls me, they immediately switch to the phone mode and people can hear me quite well.

It does work very nicely with the Google app assistant. I have not been able to make it work with Alexa. However, it will work with Google and make phone calls, find locations, and all other Google app assistant uses.

The device gets four stars for the following reasons:

1.)  You can use the device with only a single ear piece. It is possible to go within the settings and make the right ear the dominant phone ear. Unfortunately, the sound control on these headsets is on the left ear piece. You can control overall device sound from the phone. But if the earpiece is set to a low volume, you need the left ear piece to control sound.

2.)  As other people have noted, to save power the system turns itself off if there is no signal or transmitted music or voice after period of time. Reconnecting is simple by simply pushing the button, but it would be nice if there was a method of keeping the earphone on at all times while it's in the ear.

3.) The charging device itself is somewhat bulky. I have not yet found an easy way to carry it without having this device look lumpy in my pocket. One wonders if there's not a simple way of having a clip or some attachment to allow you to hang it on something or if a smaller  case for simple storage would not be possible.

4.) When you get the headsets, they are not tuned for best sound. Within the Google system, it is possible to individually and personalize the earphones. I use that and got great results. Also, the Jabra app works but it is very rudimentary and most of the adjustments are not as good as simply using the Google custom sound features. I would suggest anyone buying these headphones to attempt to use the Google custom earphone feature that comes with the android operating system.

I have not had any of the issues of left right ear disconnect as noted by other reviewers. Also, I think the sound is quite good for listening to music and streaming podcasts. I do not use these if I'm listening to a dedicated stereo system and do not anticipate these would be used for evaluating the highest quality sound reproduction

If I had to summarize my experience to date, it would be enthusiastic but guarded. Anyone buying these headphones needs to understand they do require some adjustment either within the Google custom earphone app or using the job wrap. I have had absolutely no problems with Bluetooth immediately connecting and from a connection point of view they are perfect. The carrying case is somewhat inconvenient but it does afford the opportunity of recharging and long-term use. At the end of the day I simply put them in the case and recharge them overnight.

I cannot give a long-term review analysis as I have only had him for two weeks. However, if any issues do occur I will certainly be back to post my concerns.

If you are on the cusp and concerned about negative reviews, I would look at them as possible early firmware issues. When I got my earphones I updated the firmware which is very easy to do and I have not had any problems.

title: A stellar purchase
content:
I hesitated due to a few naysayers in Amazon's review section, but after reading stellar professional reviews from tech sites, I decided to buy these.  After six months of heavy use, I'm delighted to say it's one of the BEST purchases I've made.  I had never heard of Jabra, but it's staggering how much better these are than the Airpods, Samsung's Icon X, and the rest.  I hate sounding like a paid shill, but that's the truth.

So why are they better?

1.  Unlike the rest, these support multipoint - I can connect to several devices at once.  For example, I can stream music from my laptop and seamlessly take a call from my cell when it rings.
2. Aesthetically, these look way cooler than their competitors, from the dorky AirPods to the comically bulky Bose Soundsports.
3.  They fit more securely, charge faster, and have more color options than their competitors.
4. The battery life is superior, as well as the sound.  The only true wireless earbuds that sound better than the Jabras are from Sennheiser, but you lose all the other features and they cost way more.  The trade-off is not worth it.
5.  You have more microphones, so the sound quality is superior during phone conversations.
6.  The Jabra has more tactile controls, so you can do way more without reaching for your device.
7.  They have a much higher water/sweat resistance grading.
8.  They have every feature worth anything from the AirPods, such as Live Listen (called HearThrough on Jabra) and integration with digital assistants.  Jabra also has an excellent app with features like an equalizer, different modes, soothing sounds (thunderstorms, pink noise for sleeping, etc).

Possible drawbacks?

1.  Some competitors have great features Jabra lacks - Samsung's Icon X, for example, has 8GB of onboard storage, which frees up the need for a device at all!
2.  While the fit is very good, the Jabras could benefit from wingtips to be totally secure.  The Jabra Sport version has them, but I wouldn't recommend it because it's an older model, so the earbuds of the Sport aren't as good as the Elite.  For their next version, Jabra may want to consider including wingtips.
3.  The case really needs magnets.

All told, however, these are still the absolute best true wireless earphones on the market to date.

title: My Go To Buds

title: Good product with some minor issues.
content:
First of all, I've been using this product practically daily for a month now. I previously used traditional wired apple earbuds so that the extent of my earbud experience. Given that, purchasing Jabras has been a huge boost in my overall quality of life.

Pros:
-Really good battery life, I was worried about this at first but I charge it maybe once or twice a week, and I use it quite frequently. Definitely lasts a lot longer than I thought, also charges very quickly.
-Sound quality is noticeably different from regular apple earbuds. I've been able to pick up new details in songs and it's been very enjoyable to listen through all of my favorite songs again.
-Fits very snuggly. The shape makes it so that you never have to worry about it falling out, great for exercise or movement.
-Very attractive design, when worn. It's not noticeable enough to be a centerpiece like the airpods but it still has enough prescnece to be noticed. A lot better for those who don't want to be as flashy but still value an attractive aesthetic.

Cons:
-The case feels cheap. The overall shape is a bit awkward to fit into pockets but mostly, the top of the case feels flimsy to use. I haven't had any issues yet but whenever I open the case, I can feel the material's shape change under pressure. Hard to describe but I suppose I just expected a bit more from the case given the high price of the product.
-Slight static like sound when taking them off. Nothing major, but again, something very minor that'll always be there. Although it won't make or break whether or not someone will buy it, it's still something I'd hope gets fixed.
-The sound system is not very flexible. The music stops playing on the left earbud once it's far away enough from the right one. As a result, you can't really share the earbuds with a friend and have both listening to it at the same time. Pretty annoying but it's fine if you don't have friends.

I'm sure there are more pros and cons but this is just what I've come up with on the top of my head. None of the cons would dissuade me personally from purchasing the product had I known beforehand. I don't have experience with other Bluetooth earbuds, but I still believe this is a very high-quality product. If you're an avid music listener and value sound quality and imrproved quality of life, I can whole heartedly reccomend this product.

title: Update Included - Customer Support is Horrible
content:
Update:

After emailing and calling another 2X I finally was connected with a supervisor via email. They have now given me a a store credit for the full price of the device (Elite 65t) or a replacement Elite Sport (I took the store credit to purchase a replacement Elite 65t).

Just a note that they can fix problems if you push... it just shouldn't have been as hard as it was to get them to address the problem. Jabra needs to work on providing their tier 1 support reps (probably a 3rd party company they outsource support to) with more tools to solve warranty/logistics/etc. problems. Also, for a tier 1 phone rep to say it takes 2 business days for a supervisor to review tells me that Jabra is not staffing supervisors with call center resources efficiently.

Final Comments: Okay product. Poor customer service.

-----

Original:

Summary: Poorly Implemented US Customer Service:

Like everyone else, I placed a warranty claim for the Elite 65t black and they are currently on back order. While this happens, they have no ETA, no sympathy, and no solutions. I sent 2 emails via their web form (never got a reply to either) and called (spoke for 30 minutes) their phone support who promised a call back in 48 hours (it has now been 72+ hours).

In short, I've had to make warranty claims with Samsung, Apple, Google (HTC), Sony, and others over the years. I've never had a customer service team drop the ball as many times as they have in the past 3 weeks as Jabra. Shame on their inventory/logistics team, CSR leaders, and/or partners they've hired. While inventory mistakes/delays/outages happen, not communicating delays to customers and making them reach out to you while waiting for replacements is poor practice.

I'll note that their phone CSR even mentioned that the way they are treating customers is poor and they he had limited options to make it right. He said they were only allowed to give 10-20% discount coupons and really couldn't go "above and beyond" like he has with other company's CSR programs.

title: Good, expect more from Jabra and at this price point
content:
I was hoping these could replace my beloved and much missed "Here Ones" which were discontinued a little bit ago. Everything about these headphones is competently made but does not blow me away. I found them an easy fit, unlike the sports edition which I cannot fit comfortably for any reason.

The sound on these is decent, won't blow you away. These are not audiophile equipment, nor should they be judged as such. They lose signal every once in a while like every BT device I've ever owned.

The worst part is the Jabra app. I am not even certain which of their many apps I'm supposed to be using. If I could adjust the filtering / real world balance with these, they might be real winners. Right now I'm using them for audiobooks, phone calls, and long walks with my daughter.

title: stay in ear
content: They stay in the ear.  On motorcycle

title: They quit working 7 days past return
content: They quit working 7 days past return date!! Buyer beware. Not the first this has happened to.

The deal breaker, though, after very little use, the left ear bud no longer connects reliably.
