title: Decent Wireless Earbuds
content:
I looked for a long time for good truly wireless earbuds and these seemed to have been the ones... then I turned them on.
SOUND: The Jabra Elite 65t have average sound quality at best. I prefer slightly more bass in my headphones and when I turned them on I found that these had almost no bass, even after I adjusted the EQ for extra bass that did not help. The sound quality was tinny and there was never a moment when I wanted to keep listening.
CONNECTION: One thing that these do well is connection. With bluetooth 5.0 there is no input lag when watching videos which was amazing and made watching videos awesome, this is to be expected from bluetooth 5.0. There was no serious skipping when listening to music with my phone in my pocket. This is something that was a serious problem with my Jaybird X3 earbuds.
BATTERY: The battery on these is good, with about 4 hours of play with my personal use and with the case holding another 10 hours of battery and every time you put them in the case it begins charging them. So, realistically the battery life is plenty for any normal use.
COMFORT: I have small ears so this could easily be a personal issue, but these earbuds are extremely uncomfortable. The earbud are physically very big and therefore would push against my ear while wearing them. After a normal day of wearing them my ears were sore which made wearing them even more unbearable. The earbuds are hard plastic and if you have small ears like me then these are extremely uncomfortable and this reason is ultimately the reason I returned them. However, at no point did these earbuds fall out of my ears or even feel loose. Which was very comforting knowing that $160 earbuds won't fall out and break.
CONCLUSION: These are decent true wireless earbuds, their connection are unrivaled and battery life are good. However, the sound quality is not good and noticeably worse than my wired earbuds and even my Jaybird X3. And like I said before these are extremely uncomfortable earbuds. I did end up returning these and going back to my wired earbuds. I could not get over the faults of these and for the price those faults should not be there.

title: Falls out all the time. Doesn't pair well. Call recipients said it sounded like I was in a tunnel
content: Tried to exchange these but missed the window because of work travel. Extremely dissatisfied with the product. Call recipients said it sounded like I was in a wind tunnel. They also fall out of my ears regularly while running, and when they're in my ears, there's a loud *thump* *thump**thump* with every stride. Would not recommend these. Maybe they were broken upon arrival. But I missed the return window and can't get in touch with anyone at amazon, so it seems like I'm up sh*t creek with a $165 useless paddle.

title: Must have
content: Amazing! I bought these for the gym and outdoor running, earbuds always stay securely in my ears no matter what activity I’m doing. I recently went for a 5 mile jog and the music never skipped or had any type of interference and at the gym same story, no problems with laying on a bench or any other type of workout. Very good product. The only complaint I have is with the charging case, I can definitely see it breaking at some point and very occasionally I have to put the earbuds back in the case to get them to connect but once their connected I’ve never had an issue with them disconnecting. I’ve had these for 6 months now and still very impressed.

title: Nearly perfect truly wireless earbuds
content:
I've only had the Jabra Elite Active 65t for a few weeks but they've become my favorite wireless earbuds. The overall experience is almost perfect. They've worked great in all situations including running, hiking, gym, biking and walking near traffic.

4.5/5 - well worth the retail price

PROS:
- excellent sound quality for truly wireless (supports AAC)
- very good build quality with soft touch coating
- IP56 rating which pretty much makes them dust resistant and sweat proof
- Bluetooth 5.0 - impressive range (50+ feet), no stuttering
- no audio lag with YouTube, Netflix, Hulu, etc.
- sound isolation works great if one of the included ear gels creates a good seal
- secure fit: won't fall out even while running
- hear through option for letting in specified amount of ambuent noise +great for running outside or walking near traffic)
- Jabra app with EQ, hear through options, preferences for different settings (active, focus, commute), user manual and find my Jabra
- intuitive buttons for power, assistant, hear through, volume and next song
- sounds great on phone calls
- battery life: 5 hrs on 1 charge with 2 extra charges in the charging case
- quick charge: 15 mins charging will provide 1.5 hrs battery life
- overall design: lightweight, look very minimal, don't stick way out like Bose Soundsport
- 2 year warranty covering damage from dust + sweat

CONS:
- no magnets to keep earbuds locked in case
- no included comply foam tips
- micro USB instead of USB type C
- bass is adequate and can be boosted with app but definitely not for bass heads

title: Horrible ear tips
content:
These earbuds are uncomfortable and do not feel secure in my ears. I’ve tried all three pairs of tips provided and none of them give a secure fit. This really detracts from the whole experience.
Pairing was a snap and I love how they just automatically pair when you take them out of the case. The case itself is really nice. There’s a lot to like but not having a comfortable secure fitting ear tip really ruins it.

title: Good.
content: Good.

title: Left ear bud hissing
content: I love the features, fit, and look. The only thing I don't like is the left earbuds has a noticeable hissing/static sound when audio is being played, it gets really annoying. It's harder to notice if you lower the volume a but on the earbuds rather than in your phone

title: They sound amazing! Great headphones
content: They are the perfect headphones!

title: Supreme Quality
content: This is the ONLY bluetooth earbud set that doesn't cut out when paired with my Android smartphone (Samsung Galaxy S8 or S9). Also, the volume control and sound quality is the best I've ever experienced, and I've gone through a lot of headphones!

title: Sticking to the cheaper Galaxy Buds
content:
I tried these headphones out as long as I could but the sound quality and microphone wasn't worth the ear soreness these caused.

Pros:
Good sound quality
Hearthrough feature sounded a bit robotic but worked better than the Galaxy buds I currently own.
Best wireless headphone microphone I've ever used.

Cons:
Hurt ears and doesn't fit all ear types. Large headphone.
Fell out all the time, this goes back to the fit as they weren't very secure in my ears as claimed.
If you want to only use on headphone at a time, you can only use the right earbud. This seems nitpicky but working in an office setting the hearthrough can only help so much. Being able to use either headphone at a time is a feature that doesn't seem like a big deal but when you can only wear it in your right ear it will start to hurt.

title: Best non-over the ear headphones I've ever owned!
content: These earphones fit really well in the ears and are great for working out. On top of this, the sound quality is really great for earbuds and even has the functionality of pausing music if the earbuds come out. It also has "passthrough mode" where it allows surrounding sounds to pass through alongside what you're listening to so you can hear your surroundings with the music. This can be turned off too so as to block out noise

title: Great headphone that has improved over multiple firmware updates
content:
1. It should be noted I don't use the included ear foams.  I use ComplyFoams.  This is not because of a failure of the headphones. I have large ear canals and find only the expanding complyfoams work right for me.

2. The original firmware a year ago was significantly quieter than the headphones as they exist on today's firmware.  Jabra heard the complaints and fixed many different issues that users had pointed out.

3. As is expected with a Jabra product, people have all commented on how crystal clear conversations are in a quiet environment.  That said, a couple of people have also stated the microphone is so good that I have to mute during conference calls.

Downsides:
1. I wish I could use the slave alone.
2. They are not exactly light, which leads to ear pain if I use them more than a couple hours at a time.  This again may be me and my ear sensitivity.
3. Minor complaint , the default voice in the headpiece has a pretty thick accent.  Why do 90% of these devices leave the voices up to someone at the factory?

title: Fidelity excellent; Latency intolerable.
content: The first pair I received was defective. Jabra put me through many hours and days of diagnostic work on their behalf. I gave up on Jabra and subsequently exchanged the defective pair though Amazon. (Thank you Amazon!) The fidelity of the replacement pair was excellent. However, the (presumably Bluetooth-related) latency is unacceptable--audio lags way too far behind video to provide a satisfying experience. Apple AirPods don't exhibit this problem. (Kudos Apple!)

title: Doesn't fit small ears well
content: I'm sure these are good ear buds, but unfortunately I have to return them.  I bought them as a Christmas gift for my 14 yo son.  They simply won't fit in his ear even with the smallest cup installed.  The issue isn't the piece that goes in the ear canal, but the body of the bud that sits in the outer ear.  I'm an adult and they fit me well, but just be aware that if you are buying them for a younger person they may not fit well enough for them to use them.  As much as I hate Apple, it looks like I may have to go that route instead.

title: Worth the money!
content: Amazing gym headphones! Batteries easily last 5 hours and never feel like they're going to fall out. App is great too, allowing the use of features like the jabra locate(to track your buds) and talk through so you can hear what is going on around you without removing your earbuds

title: Seriously amazing battery life.
content: Some interruption due to faulty earbud mute feature. Never out of sync, pretty good sound quality and amazing battery life.

title: Not A Good Deal
content: These earphones are so big they are uncomfortable.  I have big dumbo ears and these things are way to chunky for me. For the price they are not worth the extra bulkiness. Sound quality is very low. I ended up purchasing an Amazon recommended earphone set. 1/3 the price, 1/2 the size, and better sound quality.

title: Sound Tech is great...Case is not durable
content:
Likes: sound quality is awesome.  Pass through audio works well.  I have no issues with the fit in my ear (no pain, doesn't annoy after long periods).  I like to use when working out.

Dislikes: the case is not durable.  Case no longer turns off earbuds automatically when you place them in the case (used to).  Latch that keeps case closed broke, meaning the case won't stay closed to charge the buds.  I have to wrap a band around it to charge the ear buds.  Contacted Jabra to replace the case under warranty, but they will not ship outside U.S.  That sucks.

title: First Purchase of Buds
content: I had read a lot of feedback on several different Buds, but wasn't sure of which one to buy. I had the old Jabra ear piece for one of my phones way back when. So that was the final factor of decision for me. BOSE seems like the price is too high, and some of the off name brands couldn't measure up. So what time I have used them from Christmas to now, I love the sound and sound quality of the Jabra's 65t. The battery life is what they tell you and the recharge in the case is the best. for travel. You can watch a full movie on a charge or listen to your music on a flight to the west coast, and recharge in the case if you are flying from coast to coast. Would recommend these very highly.

title: Music OK, calls are bad
content: Music streaming is perfect. Sound quality superb. In fact, everything about this earphones are perfect except the phone call volume the other party hear. The other party always complain that they can't hear me or with much background noise

title: Unbiased review before you buy
content:
I am truly disappointed with the product overall. I read a lot of the other reviews and decided to go and purchase them anyways.

The Good:
*Look & Feel - Pairing the device is fairly easy and didn't cause any issues. The overall look and feel are pretty great as well! Compared to the Bose Wireless earbuds, these are smaller and feel lighter. I've taken these on runs, workouts, and commutes. There had been no issues of them falling out and the fit is quite snug.

*HearThrough Function - The double press to HearThrough function is definitely awesome when you don't want to take out the earbuds to listen to announcements or someone talk.

*Battery Life - I've gone a few days with a few hours of use each day and haven't had to charge the case that often. Compared to other earbuds I've owned, this has exceptional battery life.

*Mic Quality - Although I don't really use the Mic that often, I've tested it and the sound itself isn't terrible. The voice recognition can pick up your voice in relatively loud places.

The Bad:
*Static Noise - So like a lot of people, I've been hearing a white sound that's predominantly in the left earbud. The minor fix for android users goes into developer options and disable absolute volume. Then you would turn your earbud volume down 4-5 clicks, and use your phone to adjust the volume after. That being said, the sound quality won't be able to go as high as I'd like them without hearing the hissing white sound.

*Connectivity - Not sure why or how, but the Bluetooth connection sometimes breaks randomly. There would be noticeable stutters at random times, and sometimes the left side of the earbud won't connect at all.

*Jabra Sound+ App - The App is absolute garbage, just read the reviews on the app store. The different "preferences" don't change anything, the locate my earbuds function isn't that great, and it sits idle on your phone and takes up battery life.

Overall, I would definitely not recommend these. I've bought cheaper less known brands from Amazon for around ~$50 and they function about the same. For what you're paying for the Jabra earbuds, you're getting a huge markup for what essentially is cheap earbuds with HearThrough function. If these were maybe ~$60-$70, then I'd recommend buying them.

title: Truly cordless and great sound.
content: Finally, cordless freedom and great sound.  Pairing is quick and can be paired to multiple devices.  I love the access to Google Assistant as well as the auto pause feature when removing the bud.  I carry the charging case with me and when I don't need them, I pop them in and they recharge to full.  Being able to select ambient sound makes it not so isolating feeling.  The app allows you to customize other audio parameters like eq. etc.

title: Best headphones
content: I bought a pair for myself and bought another for my mom who loves it.

title: Excellent earbuds
content: This is a great product.  This is not only convenient with no wires but has excellent sound and is great for phone calls.

title: High occlusion effect when running.
content:
I perceive a high occlusion effect when running, it almost impossible to listen to my music and continue running with this earphones, due to a constant thumping every time my heel strikes the ground.
I requested support with no answer from Jabra.

title: Inconsistent option for Bluetooth earbuds
content: These sound good when they work, but there are too many times where the Bluetooth connection crackles so much that you really can't use them.

title: Worth the money.
content:
Outstanding blue tooth ear buds. I've used them for over two months now, on airplanes, the Peloton and phone calls and they are great in all situations.

In particular, they work really well for phone calls. The dual mics are very clear and sound quality is nice.

My only complaint, albeit small, is I wish the volume could go up a bit more.

title: Keep falling out !!
content: The seem to work and sound great . I just can't get them to stay in my ears they keep falling out i have tried all the different tips they sent and even some from other earphones that i have .... i have wanted these since they came out and was excited to get them .... i can't even ride my bike  !! I have several pair of less expensive brands and they never fall out !!! Really bummed 😒🤨🤨🤨  i may have return them !!

title: Nearly perfect
content:
Once I put on the larger rubber buds, I was really surprised how good these things sound. The medium (default) buds weren’t isolating the sound for me, so everything sounded thin and cheap.. I also utilized the EQ from the accompanying Jabra mobile app - Then: big improvement, shocking amount of low frequency without muddying the overall, and fairly clear separate highs and mids. It’s not a $500 set of over-ear cans, but damn, does this pack some quality into popcorn-light ear buds.

Things I kinda don’t like:
1) Faint static and pops when the device is transitioning between modes or searching for signal.
2) Delicate maneuvering in and out of the case/ears - these are soooo light and rounded, I wish the case has a magnetic element to coax them into place. But, if you hold it/them, you’ll wonder if magnets would even help.. it’s like the overall design and grip-ability could have just been slightly better. One of these days, I’m GOING to drop one, and I hope it’s not on the move in a crowded place. My hands are average/slender and pretty dexterous, so If you have enormous sausage fingers, you may want to handle these in a store before buying.
3) Very infrequent drops in signal to one side, or finicky Bluetooth auto-connection... Almost not worth complaining about 99% of the time, but it does sometimes happen. Seems industry-wide tho.
4. The need to use the app for their (very useful but highly compressed) HearThrough feature. I -could- program the Up or Down clicks on the buds themselves to toggle it, but then I’d have to give up Volume, or give up FF/Rev... which would be silly.. so the moral to this story is: Jabra, please enable a Triple click function. You’ve maxed out your single and double click navigations, so there’s only one thing left to do.....

Things I like:
1) Bass. Bass bass bass BASS. Can’t get over it. Feels like the battery should drain in 20m, but they go for hours and -then- get a couple charges from the case. Unbelievable. Make SURE you’re using the right sized rubber buds.
2) The OPTION to disable the ‘Device Narrator’. Seriously can’t stand a voice yapping to me from any device or speaker multiple times per hour, so muting it/her on Jabra was a big plus for me.
3) The 3-band EQ within the app - awesome. I wish there were more preset options like there are for the apple iTunes/Music app. And if they could get tagged/saved for specific songs/albums/artists, that would be great.
4) Now I don’t look like an Apple clone. I like Apple and use their products, but it’s nice not having those white pokeys sticking out my ears like the other 6-12 people directly surrounding me..
5. Finally, the comfort and overall quality. These were a great purchase, even if I hadn’t gotten them 33% off on Black Friday.

title: Sound quality less than expected
content: The sound quality of these earbuds isn’t as good as the apple earbuds. Bigger & more expensive. Expected more.

title: These Earbuds are Solid!
content: I've had no problems after 3 months of use and I never leave the house without them. The mic is super sensitive to keep in mind if you have a call say in a restaurant environment. Your caller may not appreciate hearing everything; and it's just certain scenarios it seems. Otherwise, I can hear great and others hear me no problem. They're small and discreet, people don't notice until you pull them out. The charging case allows me to go about 2 days straight without recharging. Last thing, these things are great for music and handling conference calls! They have never lost connection with my phone (Note 8) or suffered quality issues including voice mismatches with video (SOLID!).

title: Not worth the money!
content: Earbuds won't work individually! My son lost one on the slopes and now it's useless. This was his second pair. Also, the right earbud stopped working within 2 months of purchase and we got a replacement before the he lost it.

title: Totally Useless for listening to Music and walking
content:
The constantly cut out when walking, at least once ever 15 seconds. They seem work fine when sitting and not moving for some reason... Seeing as there Bluetooth and the phone is in my pocket I don't understand how that can happen...
 I have a Samsung S9+ totally updated and the ear buds are using the newest software. I have been using them for over a year now. but almost never use them because they car crap!

title: Question.
content: I love the product but I noticed when I go to the gym it cuts in and out when close to the cardio machine. Is that a known issue?

title: Perfect for cutting onions!
content: I keep it as a kitchen tool!

title: Wonderful fit, good sound, easy setup
content:
I could not be more happy with these headphones. They have great connectivity, have pretty nice sound quality, and are comfortable in-ear. There is a slight issue with the connection on my commute (but seems to be limited to one particular part of the bus, which suggests that there is some sort of signal broadcast interfering with the connection). That is such a small issue that is feels almost trivial to complain about it.

If you are  in the Apple device ecosystem  (as I am) and have concerns about compatibility (as I was), allow me to put your mind at ease.  These work seemlessly with all of my devices—iPhone, AppleWatch, MacBook Air.

title: Not good enough
content: Fit is poor and almost painful to put in snug enough for good sound quality. Poor fit means thin sound quality . My $25 wired ear buds sound better.

title: Excellent Wireless Headset
content: This is my 2nd Jabra Elite. The other is a Elite Sport that I use for workouts. I got this one for everyday use because it look more professional. I love the sound quality and the ability to set it with the app. So far calls with other folks have been clear and they indicate that they cannot tell that I using a wireless headset.

title: Never drive without them
content:
I drive an 18 wheel big rig and need ear buds that cancel out the sound of my loud truck engine for myself and for those I have conversations with. These do the trick. My wife appreciates the microphone when I call her and the tight sealed fit in my ear canals make my drive better. Turning on the ambient noise mode allows me to hear the sirens of first responders and warning horns from other vehicles. They are in my ear 12 hours a day with no comfort problems. After going through 4 other brands, these are the best earbuds I’ve had so far.
I have a samsung galaxy and and I phone 8. Body connect to the earbuds at the same time very fast and easy. They are snug but my gym works are very intense and I have Those muscles around my ears that cause my ears to wiggle, so I need different earbuds to do a better job at staying in. I am currently using Plantronics with the ear hooks but I am considering the Jabra elite sport with the ear wings.

title: Impressive
content: Overall this is great earbuds

title: Clear music
content: Great noise canceling headphones

title: I love these little budders. My audio file tendencies won’t let me give it a 5 star but congrats.
content: I really like these. Although the are earbuds and not headphones I was a little taken back. I wanted them to be like my crushers or beats but they are not.they have good sound quality for what they are I would recommend them. I use them everyday for at least an hour and a half they last my work week with out a recharge. A lot better quality then apple AirPods. After reading a few of the reviews I might get a warranty threw a company I did from Best Buy. Not disappointed. They have lasted me 7 months now with no problems at all. I also like the app that lets you control the equalizer. Nice feature.

title: Good buy
content: Hurt my ears a little bit but great functionality

title: Best bluetooth headphones I’ve ever used.
content: This is by far the best wireless headphones out there. By far. That said, they are not perfect. The battery is just unsuitable;  won’t even last a full day. After 4-5 hours of music it dies. The other issue is the volume could be louder. I wonder if the newer models resolved this.

title: Sound great, but didn't like the fit
content:
The sound quality and connection are excellent, really best I've heard from wireless earbuds.

Unfortunately, they are kind of large - not the tips, bit the base of the earbuds that you rotate into your ear, and I didn't like the feel or fit at all. This is a personal preference, but they kind of hurt and were definitely uncomfortable.  My child, who must have bigger ears, tried them and really likes them, so we aren't returning them.

title: Phenomenal sound for the price with nice features.
content:
These have truly great sound and features for the price. They fit comfortably and really cancel out the external noise.

One of the great features of the app for them is turning on hearthrough that uses little microphones on the earbuds to pipe in external sound. The feature has the option to mute what's playing or let it still play and works automatically based on the sound level the mics pick up.

Battery life is as advertised and the case will generally give you 2 full charges before it has to be charged again.

Highly recommend for anyone wanting great sound quality at a reasonable price.

title: Good for 3 months max then crap out.
content:
I've owned these for 3 months, have used them daily and they've basically completely failed me in the past few weeks.

Either the case itself or either one of the buds refuse to charge, I have pairing issues all the time, etc.

On top of all that, they have about the stupidest button configuration that could possibly be conceived of.

They were a gift, but I will be reaching out to Amazon tomorrow for a complete refund and if Jabra support doesn't get back in touch with me I will be filing a BBB complaint against them.

Don't waste your time with these pieces of trash.

Update: I returned the headphones, they acknowledged receipt and would send replacements "but they were on backorder".

A month later, nothing. Jabra is garbage.

title: Very "gitchy" for phone calls; convenient for music
content:
+ Good battery life to get me through a full work day.
+ Charging case is convenient and small enough to fit in my shirt pocket

- Uncomfortable in ears if I leave them on for longer than 45 mins.
- Trouble with phone calls - Callers have trouble hearing me and audio cuts out for me sporadically.  This is resolved sometimes if I put the ear bud in the case and then try connecting again (turn it off and on). I've ran all of the updates but still occasionally have the problem.
- Replacement sizes for the earbuds are nice, but they rip rendering them useless.  I started with the pre-installed medium tips.  They were mostly comfortable, but I wanted to try the small ones to see if I got a better fit.  When removing the medium sized tips, one of them ripped.  I was careful and didn't pull from the edges.  One came off just fine, but the left earbud tip just ripped.  So now I'm stuck with the small ones.  It's not unuseable but for the price, I expected better.

title: Best ear bud device overall
content: Most comfortable ear bud device I’v ever used. Pricey but worth it if you want the water/sweat resistant feature, otherwise the step down version is probably a better choice for value. Battery life a bit short but I may be noticing that because I can wear it for long periods of time due to the exceptional comfort. The portable charging case offsets the battery issue, though. Highly recommended!

title: EarDUDS
content:
I'm reviewing the earbuds I received, which likely were defective. If they weren't, then that makes them a 1 star set of earbuds.
The fit - They fit my ears very well. So well that it was a bit of a struggle to remove them. Nothing painful...
Paring to my phone - Straight up simple and automatically connected every time when powered on.
Sound - Barely audible at full volume. Ran through all of the trouble shooting and nothing helped. A lot of phones now days have a safety feature that limits volume levels to prevent hearing damage. I even overrode that and it did not improve. So the earbuds had to go back to Amazon.
One thing to note is that I purchased these from the Amazon renewed section, which guarantees the item to work like new. Well, someone failed to test these before offering them back up for sale. I will say that for used earbuds, they were spotless clean upon opening. So props for that attention to detail.
I also got them at a greatly reduced price, the price for brand new ones are a bit steep, which is why I opted not to retry another pair to see if these were just defective.

title: Great until they break!
content:
These worked great for about 9 months.  Audio is good, there is almost no delay when watching videos. Bass could be deeper, but is good enough.  I love the pass through capability, and the white noise options.
They worked great in the office, nothing better then to help block out all the noise around so I can concentrate better.
Until the audio in the left earbud stopped working right. Audio was working but the volume was so low I could hardly tell.

After going back and forth with Jabra for about 2 weeks, they authorized a replacement set under warranty.
It's now been a month since then, and the replacement order is still "being processed".  Meanwhile I am out my expensive earbuds, and had to go back to my cheap over the ear Bluetooth headphones.

title: Stopped working after 2.5 months. Jabra Warranty department was Non-Responsive
content: So I've never ever written a review on Amazon and I buy nearly 90% of my products from here. I really enjoyed these headphones when they were working. One day two weeks ago the left earbud sound was cutting in and out and sort of scratchy. There is some loose connection in there. I got as far with Jabra to the point where they told me I would receive an email from their shipping partner on instructions to return my device and receive the new one. There was no email, and basically they dropped off the map since then. Calling their customer service department is useless as there is no one there to ever take the call. I waited one hour the other day to reach someone on phone until I finally gave up. YOU DON'T JUST CHARGE THIS KIND OF MONEY FOR A PRODUCT AND HAVE NO ACCOUNTABILITY AFTER IT STOPS WORKING WITHIN THE FIRST 90 DAYS. UNACCEPTABLE!

title: Just won't stay in
content:
I really tried to like these.  The sound is fine I suppose, but it is impossible to get them to stay in my ears.  I should have known better buying earbuds without a wing, clip or hook to help them stay in.  They fall out if I even turn my head slightly.  Unfortunately, since I couldn't use them, I threw them in a drawer intending to return them but forgot about them.  An expensive lesson.
I advise looking elsewhere for earbuds.

title: Bad customer service, and will probably have buyers remorse
content:
This is ok. They aren’t as waterproof as you would think by their marketing. Also, customer service from jabra takes a super long. Took them over a month to get back to my email. Twice.

Sound quality is about as good as any apple headphone, but there is a slight buzz/ring when you have the sound canceling thing on that’s quite annoying. You have to turn up the volume to not hear it.

Honestly, super cool design and concepts, just falls short in a lot of ways.

title: Phone calls AND audio!
content: JUST got these. I read up on them before I purchased them. I just purchased a Galaxy S9+ phone (they work together). I do not like the wired ear plugs sold with phones; I like to get some type of wireless. I have used several others in the past, even a Blue Parrot over the head single speaker with a boom microphone like truck drivers wear. That one was great even if it looked strange. HOWEVER, none of the others could do phone calls, text messaging AND audio. These can. Super easy to connect. The case is cool; it holds power for offsite charging.

title: Best Earbuds Ever!
content:
Oohhh my goodness I LOVE these wireless Bluetooth earbuds!!!

I've been looking for years to find a pair that has a long battery life without having to recharge them. They legit last over 4 hours continuous use, I haven't had a chance to try for 5 hours yet. It's perfect for running long distance!

Love the app controls, noise canceling or not options, for road running safety. Easy earbud button controls. Never have connectivity issues paired with my Pixel 3.

I have absolutely no complaints or suggestions for these earbuds! Perfection!

title: The perfect gym headphones
content: I've owned like 5 different pairs of wireless headphones and most of them have been garbage. I was skeptical to pony up for these, but I have to say that I am thoroughly pleased. I mainly got these because I wanted headphones that were obnoxious loud for the gym and no other wireless headphones that I've owned did the trick.  Well these do! They're very loud and the noise cancelling is great. Even without playing sound, your hearing is noticeably suppressed with these in your ear. Ive also found that these are great at staying connected, without one ear going on and off as other wireless ear buds do. The daul connection is great too, I can be playing a song on my computer, then walk away and keep playing it on my phone without having to switch pairing. If these are a bit out of your price range the Tozo wireless ear buds are less than half the price and work great. However, I think these are definitely worth the money!

title: Another high quality product from Jabra! We are Jabra fanatics in our household!
content: Some of my favorite features of the Jabra Elite 65t are the ease of use - you literally just remove them from the case to turn them on and just put them in the case to turn them off (the case doubles as a charging station). I also like that when you remove one earbud out of your ear, it pauses whatever music you are playing which is great when working out, in the yard, etc versus having to fiddle with pausing my music app. The Jabra Elite 65t tightly seal in your ear which is better for me because I can actually play my music at a lesser volume because it is not competing with other noise. Now the difficult thing....keeping these hidden from my daughter and husband so I can keep them all to myself!

title: sound quality poor when speaking on phone
content: Not much else to say really. the sound quality for listeners when I am speaking through these on my iphone 7 is spotty and distorted at times. Pretty disappointed for $150

title: Excellent
content: I don’t write reviews. That being said, these ear buds are amazing. They sound incredible. Best sound quality I’ve found and I have tried a lot of different Bluetooth head phones. The fit is good and makes for a great listening experience. Recommend these.

title: Best in class
content: Best true wireless earbuds

title: Sound is good, but there is zero noise cancelation and they do not feel secure in the ear.
content:
Sound excellent.  But almost no noise cancellation.  But the biggest issue is that they do not stay put in the ear.
I have a wireless single earphone that works off of my office phone.  It has an ear loop and stays in all day long.  Sound is OK for phone but not for music.
Jabra does not stay in  And don't try to eat with them in.  The chewing motion pops them out of the ear.

title: Excellent sound quality and comfortable
content: Love these truly wireless earbuds!  Sound quality is excellent.  I wear them nearly all day long commuting and at work.  And they arrived well before the estimated delivery date. You won’t regret purchasing these buds... go for it!

title: Large and can’t sync with watch
content: I really enjoy them but they do not fit snug in my ears. Fall out sometimes so must be careful. Also can’t sync with Apple Watch so must always have phone with me.

title: Exactly what I was looking for!
content: Got these a few days ago and really enjoying them. The tech still has a ways to go, but these sound good enough, stay in my ears, and are so damn convenient. I love how seamlessly they connect when they come out of the charging case.

title: Excellent
content: Probably the best workout purchase I’ve e er made

title: Case Is Super Difficult to Open
content:
I was headed out on a trip and forgot my other set of Bluetooth headphones.  Stopped into the airport mobile store and picked these up. Wore them the entire time on a 6-hour cross country flight to LA. The sound was good and I have no trouble getting them into and out of my ears.

My biggest complaint is the case. The one I have is very difficult to open. It's a shame because the earbuds are really nice. Then you get to the case and it's something you'll be constantly opening and closing to store your earbuds. The case is mostly an afterthought even though it serves a very important purpose in charging your earbuds.

Fix the case please!! Make it easier to open.

title: Don’t buy these. If battery life is not an issue try the Tranya
content: Awful tinny sounding. Uncomfortable. Only plus is battery life.

title: Build the sound quality
content: not a good purchase sound quality is very low and it goes automatic to you're phone call

title: Great technology but poor everything else
content:
Overall I really like the technology. But they fall out my ears, songs skip while biking and the left ear bud goes in and out.
Usage: biking, running, lifting weights, phone calls, regular music listening
Pros: they connect quickly to my android phone. All I have to do is take them out the case. I have them connected to my computer and phone simultaneously and it works well. Also works with ok Google. And calls are clear according to people who I have spoke with. The charging case is cool. They look cool.
Cons: they don't stay in my ear. The first day I got them they fell out. I eventually got used to it and I can feel when they are coming out and I push them back in. The music skips when I begin biking. It usually only last for a minute or so but sometimes it randomly skips. I attribute this to the movement. Final strike was when the left ear bud started going out. I only had them for three weeks.
Note: I sweat a lot, and they didn't seem phased by the sweat, but who knows, maybe that's why the left bud started to malfunction. I returned them after 3 weeks.

title: Great sound and feel but too much hissing
content: I ordered these headphones and loved them. I liked the way they felt and they stayed in my ear, but to my surprise the headphones had a hiss that kept coming out the left ear. I really wanted to keep these headphones but when you raise the volume the hiss just gets louder and louder till that is all you can hear. I returned them the same day I got them. I haven't tried another pair to see if mine was defected or not but from reading on Reddit and seeing other reviews people say that no matter how many times they got another one that it would still act that way.

title: Definitely worth the money, best I have found yet!
content: Fit great, sound fantastic! Great for the gym and mowing the lawn or just lounging. Super easy to pair and wear for a long period of time. Great for taking calls but caller may hear background noise with wind or a busy street.

title: Look elewhere
content: Sound better with Comply foam tips.  These are marginally comfortable and do stay put.  BUT worst pairing earbuds I have.  Sometimes they connect sometimes they have to be paired again.  App usually doesn’t know they are connected.

title: Sounds great
content: Listen to music

title: Great headphones!
content: Probably the best set of bluetooth headphones I've ever owned.  I use them when I travel, for work phone calls, etc.  Battery is good, case charges them which is nice.  I with the case was shaped a little differently so it fit Into my pocket better, and the Alexa integration needs to work better, but I love them.

title: Very good , happy with it
content: Very good , I think it needs update to avoid the left side temporary disconnection.

title: Great headphones
content:
I wear these to the gym, to work, at work, at home etc.

In NYC static interrupts connection at some major spots (grand central, busy street intersections)

title: Great pair of headphones
content: There a good pair of headphones. I use them all the time. Keep the additional ear pieces. They help.

title: the best so far
content: I've owned a half a dozen Bluetooth headphones some are great for calls, some music playback but these are the first pair that REALLY has both!! definitely worth it.

title: Didn't last long
content: I loved these earbuds as long as they worked. They fit really well, (which is saying a lot for a woman with small ears), looked really sleek, and were hardly even noticeable in my ear. The only thing is, they have stopped charging just 3 months after they were purchased. So now they are sitting on my table useless. I guess I will be purchasing another brand since these did not last very long at all. And for the money I paid they should have lasted longer.

title: Won't go back
content: Good sound quality, awesome fit, awesome battery life and the hear through feature is a life saver at the gym and riding my bike to work. Also they don't like nearly as dorky as things like the bose or apple wireless headphones.

title: Poor product, doesn't work very long.
content: The sound was good.  I bought a cheap $50 pair on Amazon but they sounded like crap, kept turning on and etc.  That's why I spent the $$$ on the Jabra.  After only 4 months of use, the charging case quit working. Just got another case today. Hopefully they work more than a couple months.

title: Good batteries
content: They could be louder but overall good buy

title: Great sound!
content: These things sound amazing for being true wireless! The app is a big help too. Lots of customization options. The Hearthrough feature is great too. Only thing is that I get ear fatigue if I wear them too long.

title: Supper Headphone
content: Great headphones I have ever used.

title: Great fit, Sounds good
content: Could use a little more bass but otherwise they are great

title: Purchsed 13July/left earbud stopped working 15Oct..
content: Very disappointed that although have had only 3 months, the left earbud has stopped working and cannot be returned!!

title: Left ear bud defective
content: Left ear bud defective upon arrival.  Cuts in and out. - returning. Bummer.

title: Amazing! Worth the $$
content:
Amazing headphones. Features on headphones are easy to use, pause/play and double tap to hear surrounding sounds on right ear bud. Volume up/down and next/back on left ear bud.

Noice cancelling is great for such small buds. Surrounding sound is super handy to have at a simple double tap.

They are super comfy and stay put through all sorts of workouts and running.

Update: Took them out for a 20 mile bicycle ride and they worked wonders. No rushing wind sound like most other headphones.

title: I love these
content: I have a hard time with earbuds but these work great and stay in my ears!  I lost them when I droped the case and the both earbuds fell out in some tall grass.  I could not find them so had to purchase another pair.....expensive lesson.  Keep the case in my purse not in my hand....

title: Not "one-size fits all" - very uncomfortable.
content: There's always an issue with sizing with in ear headphones. I'm a woman, with average size ears, (I checked online!) and these simply don't fit and aren't comfortable. It's not about the part of the headphone that goes into your ear canal, which does come with different sized attachments, but the fact that theses are supposed to fit comfortably in the 'cup' of your ear - they don't. They fall out constantly - when I can wedge them in hard enough I get a headache and I'm concerned about damaging my ears. I bought these on reading the Wirecutter review that recommended them, but I'm disappointed. Wish I could return but I had to open the packaging fully to even know that they're uncomfortable. Oh well. Try in a store first if you can.

title: Great overall wireless earbuds
content:
To be 5 stars needs: magnetic hookup in case, usb-c
Sound quality is decent. They don't fall out.

title: Nice sounding earbuds, recommend them
content: I use them all the time. Work well. Auto detects great. Easy 2 take or end calls. Ear pieces help keep in your ear. No spurious diconnections.

title: overpriced, mediocre sound quality, failed after 3 months
content: The sound quality is mediocre at best. It seems impossible to get a decent fit so they don't fall out and get lost. No sound in one after 3 months. At least the warranty covered replacements. I expected a much much better product for the extreme cost. Don't bother.

title: Finally, true wireless phones that work!
content:
I used these on a recent plane trip.  I love these things!  They did a great job of blocking out the regular airplane noise and I watched a movie on my iPad with no wires.  These are true 'wireless', not like other bluetooth headphones that still have wires hanging around the back of your neck...I hate those because every time you move, you can hear them rubbing on your clothes.

It should go without saying that the best performance requires a good fit.  There are three sets of tips included and you should try them all before deciding which to use.  If the tips are too big, they are not comfortable...too small, and they fall out.

My flight was a total of 6 hours long, with a plane change in Chicago.  The batteries lasted just fine for the first half and I stuck them in the case to boost the charge while I ran to the next plane.  I had no trouble at all using them for the entire flight.  Speaking of the case, this is a really nice case.  It is small and hard and very lightweight, so it protects and charges them without weighing down your bag.

I have also used them a few times while walking around and again, the true wire-free comfort is wonderful.  They're paired with my iPhone for that purpose.  The sound is excellent for music or audiobooks.  I've tried both and I'm quite happy with them.

Can't find anything bad to say about these.

title: Sound, fit, quality and routine calls are awesome!  Noise cancellation on calls needs work.
content: These buds are the truth!!!  Sound is quality, fit is great!  They don’t move during burpees or even long runs!  There’s very minimal ear fatigue.  Volume is great, doesn’t get muddy or overbearing!  I tested their ability to block out noise while at a sound check for a major concert, literally standing in front of a speaker stack in section A, row 14 to be sure I wasn’t off to the side and was getting the full blast of the speaker system and I could hear every word and instrument of my music playing through the buds!!  I could feel the vibration of the  music being played On stage but I could hear my own music clear as if I were in a private room by myself!  Incredible!!  The only knock I have on there is, the mics are so sensitive in calls that people cannot hear me on a call if I’m in a loud public place.  If the get that noise cancellation down...these are a 7 star rating out of 5 stars!!!

title: Nice ear buds, just not for me.
content: I have had these for about two months. The battery life is great, and the call/media quality is great. My issue is with comfort, I have yet to find a tip for them that will allow them to stay in my ear. Because of this loose fit they hurt my ears after 30 minutes or so. The only other issue I have with them is the NFC left ear bud. The left ear bud connects to the right one not the phone, so you have to use both or only the right one.  For the price I hope they fit your ear.

title: Perfect of the office
content:
I use these solely for listening to music and podcasts at work in an office environment.

The Bluetooth connection with my MacBook is okay; the signal cuts out sometimes. The Bluetooth connection with my Windows laptop is better; almost never cuts out. However on either computer, the music doesn’t consistently automatically pause when the ear buds are removed. It seems to pause some of the time when I’m using an app, but not when I’m using a web browser (YouTube, Pandora, etc).

Works as described with an iPhone. No complaints.

Sound quality is great at low (office) volumes. Pass through feature is neat but weird at first. Takes getting used to so I’m glad I can turn it on and off.

The Jabra Sound+ app is basic but gets the job done.

I haven’t used any competing products, but since they all use Bluetooth to compress the signal, I doubt I’d notice much of a ‘sound quality’ difference. Sure, one product might produce more bass than another product. But in terms of actual sound quality, I doubt there would be enough of a difference in ear buds of this price range for me to care.

I definitely recommend these and would definitely buy these again.

title: Nice Earbuds with great Battery pack but one issue!!
content:
Nice Earbuds with great Battery pack but its not connecting to two devices.

Eg: Initially it was working with Iphone and Ipad simultaneously - It was great, immediately after taking the earbuds out of portable battery box: Ear buds were connected to both the devices automatically - GREAT Feature (Which last only for few days)
But after two months - Device stopped connected to the devices (Only one device will be remembered - last connected one): Either you need to connect and leave it as it is or need to connect to the device each time you turn ON bluetooth.

But I was so bummed at the sound quality. Very little bass. I realize bass is hard to do on earbuds. It's just not in the science. So far latest FW has not fixed the issue as of 12/25/18. Other than that everything else is fantastic. I’m keeping them & praying that Jabra releases a FW that actually fixes this.

Sometimes you answer calls by pushing the ear piece and other times it doesn't work, no rhyme or reason.  They also connect and disconnect constantly.  More often than not, they are disconnected from the phone and I have to pair with at the time of each call.  Also, everyone says this thing sounds like a freight train whenever in the car, so that's a bummer.  I can only use these things when the stars align. The sound quality is excellent, the charging case convenient and they are the most comfortable I tried.  It is weird that connected to my Surface tablet using a phone and listening to music I can’t stay in stereo - the mic only works with handsfree setting and doesn’t automatically switch back and forth.  Still, I can take calls on computer and iPhone without having to re-pair devices.  This one was defective and I returned it and bought it again from another place, but I wanted to write a review because I searched so long for a good pair.

content: This is my 10th(?) pair of BT earbuds and are by far the best I've owned.  The sound quality is great.  The fit is great.  The durability far outpaces even more expensive pairs that I've owned.  I recommend these to everyone I know.

Battery lasts 5+ hours consistently.  Fit is very secure despite the lack of inner ear prongs and they do not fall out even when running or mountain biking. title: Buy these! Great sound, durable, stylish, good battery, good noise isolation.

These are comfy as heck. Can wear them for hours and I usually can't make that happen with buds. (Jaybird X3 was too big for my ear canal) They also stay VERY secure in your ear. I wear them while I ride my motorcycle 70 mph and they are solid. Feel like I could do 100 and they'd still stay.

Sound great to me. I've been with Jaybird for a long time and these sound great.

I drop these things all the time and there's not even a scuff. Just dropped the left one in my orange juice on accident this morning. Fished it out, rinsed it off in the sink, put it in a bag of rice, hit it with the blow dryer. Still works like new! Phew!

title: Buyer beware!!!
content: I bought the Jabra Elite 65t thinking that is was going to be an awesome device. Worked great for a couple months, but then the right bud stopped working, it is the bud that controls both sides, sound comes only from the left bud and nothing happens to the right. Called support, sent them emails, even filled their online form. Since it has been less than 6 months since purchase, the warranty should still be good. For a pair of earbuds that cost 160+ support is sub par. I was just on the phone with a customer service rep, was on hold for over 15 minutes and then he would not solve my issue. I filled the warranty form and now he wants a picture of the buds. Of course, the buds are at home so I cannot get a picture. Amazon should do something to keep companies like this one from taking advantage from their customers.

title: "Tight Seal" Around Ears is a bug, not a feature.
content:
TLDR -- find a place to try these physically and don't trust online sites that have pit the headphones head to head!  The "seal" feature creates an annoying echo when you talk and these are not comfortable for more than an hour.

I spent hours researching reviews on reputable sites such as "The Wirecutter" and "TechRadar"
I have an Android phone, so didn't think AirPods would work for me.  I have Bose Soundsport wired headphones and find them very comfortable, but have been having issues using them on calls recently.

The Jabra Elite 65t were the winners by TechRadar, the WireCutter, and Tom's Guide, which is why I chose them.  All these sites touted the feature that these formed a tight seal for noise cancelling, and features such as hear through.

My main use case for the earbuds is talking on the phone whille doing chores in my apartment, and listening to audiobooks and podcasts when I walk home from work.  Talking on the phone with these headphones is a nightmare.  The "seal" around the ears makes my own voice feel like a terrible echo when talking on the phone.  The seal also bothers me when I listen to audio books in.  I find these so uncomfortable I cannot even speak to the battery life since these are so uncomfortable I can't wear them for more than an hour.

title: Close, but no cigar
content:
These are basically perfect except for the fact that they dont fit my small ears well. Cant listen longer than 30min or so without getting pretty bad ear fatigue.

These were my first pair of truly wireless earbuds after coming from the jaybird x3s.

The sound quality is pretty good, not as bassy or as loud as my x3s, but for truly wireless earbuds, i dig it. Build quality is pretty good, buttons are tactile and easy to push (though it does suck to push the earbuds in further when pushing those buttons). Microphone is exceptional for phone calls.

All in all, if you have small ears or already struggle with earbuds, pass on these. If you dont have any of those problems and are looking for an upgrade or your first truly wireless earbuds, then grab these!!

The bad: They don't stay in the ear very well.  If you do happen to get them in firmly, the speaker hole gets blocked or compressed where you can't hear anything and have to readjust it. title: New Active 65t Are Out.

So far they are great; I haven't run with them yet, but walking around they sound fantastic, and feel secure in my ears.  I like that the phone app has eq adjustment.  It's a major listening enhancement.

Edit: I've now run with them, and they stay secure.  I've always had problems with Apple earbuds staying secure during run; these work much better.  Also,, I reiterate that these probably  have the best sound of any bluetooth I have ever owned.  The only thing that I would wish for is that my Iphone would indicate battery charge percentage like my Beats do.

title: Good deal at a lower price
content:
I spent a long time researching wireless earbuds, trying to decide the best one to spend my money on. Ultimately I decided on the Jabras since they consistently get picked as top performers with the best well-rounded package of features. I also bought them on a Christmas sale for $140 - I definitely would not pay more than that after testing them out for a month. I'm a somewhat cheap person and I think there are reasonable alternatives for less (Anker Soundcore Liberty Air, Mobvoi Ticpods Free) or better alternatives if money is no concern (RHA Trueconnect) - but keep in mind that I never tried any of those devices so that's just based on my obsessive researching.
Pros:
- excellent sound quality, enjoyable experience listening to podcasts, music, or video. I've noticed very little lag in watching video
- excellent, easy pairing and bluetooth connection. The connection does not stretch far so I've had some dropped signal when I move more than 2 rooms away in my house, and occasionally when outside the signal will blink out for a second, I can't tell why, but it comes right back (probably happens once for every 2-3 hours of listening time).
- I really ended up loving the controls, especially the volume control. I found if I used one finger to stabilize the device, that pushing the buttons did not hurt my ear. Initially, I wasn't sure how much I would use the controls but after a month, I would definitely only consider devices with volume controls in the future. It is awesome to be able to skip tracks, change volume, pause/play easily while running without taking out my phone.
- good for phone calls. Even walking by heavy traffic, the other person could still hear me well (but they do get a lot of background noise), and often with better voice quality than I get on my iphone

Cons:
- the biggest con for me is the fit. While they are incredibly stable and I have no concerns about them falling out while running or doing HIIT work outs, they start to hurt my ear canal, concha, and antitragus (to be specific) within an hour of wearing them. I often have to readjust them to take pressure off certain parts of my ears. This is obviously an individual issue since a lot of people find the fit great.
- poor noise isolation. I was very disappointed by this feature, my $20 wired earbuds offer better passive noise isolation than these do. I've tried all 3 tip sizes with no improvement. The largest size tips create a weird suction feeling that is uncomfortable and noisy itself, while the medium size tips let in too much ambient noise. I'm considering Comply foam tips but those seem to get a mixed bag of reviews. If you don't mind ambient noise or listen to your music at full volume, this may not bother you very much.
- the case does seem a little cheap, I agree with reviews that question how long the plastic latch will last. Seems like Jabra should have installed the magnetic closure that most other high end wireless buds use.

Overall, the quality of these earbuds is excellent and I never have issues with their function. My two biggest cons were not things I could have predicted until I tried the earbuds on myself. I'm not sure I would purchase these again, but for now I'm keeping them because I still think they beat the competition when you consider all the features they provide, I just wish I knew how to predict which earbud would fit my ears best.

title: Be sure to buy Elite *Active* 65t and NOT Elite 65t for active lifestyle

Sure enough, as mentioned by other reviewers, Elite Active 65t does NOT fall out even during vigorous physical activity.  It also has a "fast charge" feature where a quick 15 min charge will give another 1.5 hours of use.  Given that, spending extra $20 for Active is pretty much a no-brainer.
