Only drawback is my ears are small and even with the smaller silicone insert in place I can only wear them for an hour or two before I need to take them out and give my ears a break.  Based on my limited use, I have had these for about 3 months and only had to charge them twice.

title: The best headphones
content: The best headphones I’ve owned

title: Great sound and battery.
content:
I'm very pleased with these earbuds. I have had them for a little more than a week of heavy use. This is the first pair of bluetooth headphones I have owned. Before this I used plug in ear buds. I listen to music and a lot of podcasts, neither of which my family or coworkers want to hear. These produce far richer sound than my Sony or Skull Candy earbuds. The Jabra app is a must. I'm sure you can connect these to your phone without the app, but the app has a variety of features that allow you to enhance and customize your listening experience and also manage firmware updates. In addition to those features, there are ambient sound options that are pretty cool. You can listen to the sounds of rain, a thunderstorm, ocean waves, cavern etc to help you focus on work or meditate or whatever.
Other reviewers have raved about the battery life. I have not run out of battery while using them yet and I listen for hours at a time. When I'm finished, I pop them back in the case and they charge back up.

Having buttons on the earbuds to control volume, advance tracks, take calls, manage voice features, etc is essential. Some people complain about discomfort pushing the buttons forces the earbuds into your ear canals. I can see that this might be annoying, but it wasn't that bad for me. Maybe my ears are less sensitive to this sensation.

I also give high marks to the phone handling and voice command. I have placed and received calls. Sound quality is good and the caller reports to me that they can hear me well. I am increasingly using Google by voice and it works well with these Jabra earbuds.

Here are a couple of things I think could be improved. First, these earbuds do a pretty good job of canceling outside ambient sound and isolating you. Because you sometimes want that sound to filter through to be aware of what is happening around you, they have a feature called "HearThrough" that utilizes the microphones and mixes the ambient sound from your surroundings with the music or whatever you are actively listening to and passes them through to your ears. It's not perfect. Sometimes it's spotty. It seems to drop out sometimes, the things I want to hear most (other people talking to me) is sometimes quiet and random noise is louder. I also wish that the app would allow you to control the volume of the ambient sound separately from the audio coming from your device.

I have not been successful connecting to my PC. I assume this is possible, but the computer doesn't have a driver for these and I have not yet found one online (I only searched for about 10 minutes).

I had trouble opening the case at first. I have seen other reviewers who also complain about this. The secret is to push on the ridge. The clasp is secure so your earbuds don't just fall out. Pushing back on the lid as you open it releases the clasp. It's easy once you know this.

I had some issues with the bluetooth stability. I have read that it might be a problem with Samsung phones rather than with the Jabra 65t. Resetting the bluetooth on my phone (toggling off and on again) seems to help. I also experienced some interfearance while sitting next to a TV.

title: left earbud failure
content: The left earbud has stopped pairing. customer service has you go through the ten step process of "forgetting the device"; "pairing;" standing on one foot; get a phd; re-engineer the device; count to 100 on a Tuesday...; should not have to be busy getting it to work for this kind of money. Checking online I see many others have the same issue with the left earbud not working. When the device works as it should the sound quality is good. battery life is very poor.

title: stopped charging after 2 months
content: one month after the return window closed, they stopped working. right ear no longer charging. sound quality was “ok” up until then. fine for the gym. i’ve now spent hundreds of dollars over the years, trying different wireless in-ear phones. none of them last longer than a few months for gym and/or regular use. i’ve come to the conclusion that the technology just isn’t there yet (unless maybe you spend $500 - $1000 on a pair. no thanks. back to wired earphones, i guess.

title: Bluetooth won't stay connected to Pixel 3
content: Attempted to use with a new Pixel 3 phone.  Seemed to pair fine.  However, the headset then repeatedly connected and disconnected every few seconds.  When connected, audio played fine but would not stay connected.  To make sure it was not the phone, I connected a $20 HDMX bluetooth headset to the phone and it worked fine and stayed connected.  Also connected the Pixel 3 to my car via Bluetooth and it worked fine and stayed connected.  Battery on the Jabra headset was 100% so was not a battery issue.

title: Excellent earbuds
content: Completely worth the money. I was a bit skeptical givin how much they cost but they are amazing with regard to sound quality, convenience and charging case. I couldn't recommend these more highly!

title: Love these earbuds!
content: They fit well. The battery life is great. I use them every day in the office and for workouts. Love 'em!

title: Awesome earbuds, the positive reviews were right!
content: Bought these because of all the great reviews from here and other websites and articles. Glad to say that the reviews were correct. These are awesome wireless earbuds for calls and music. It takes some getting used to with the functions but in time you'll get the hang of it. Glad I made this purchase.

title: Clumsy looking, just not right, hurts my ears
content:
They were so close to making a great product.

The fact that it isn't USB-C is a miss.

The fact that they have "Jabra" branding on them, in a silver/steel color, makes them look very cheap. The look of the earbuds and the case is just very cheap looking.

The case is such a pain to open. I learned how to get it open eventually but it is not intuitive "push from bottom" to open, more a "swipe its side" motion.

The twisting motion to insert them is awkward. And these hurt my ears after wearing for more than an hour. They fit too well. The noise cancellation works VERY WELL, but that is not a feature I need for daily commute.

The absolute last straw that made me return these is the buttons. The buttons are physical, and pressing them will jam the buds into your ear even more. It hurts.

title: Pretty good but a bit pricey
content: These buds sound reasonably good and are relatively easy to pair with a sound source.  They do drop off often enough to be an annoyance.  Good sound isolation. Good battery life for wireless earphones.

title: I am not disappointed.... after exhaustive research
content: I received these in the mail yesterday and placed on the charger for the night.  I researched these with various other competitors for this product and pretty much received the impression that there was a good probability of some fake reviews or at least some that were incentive based in some way.  I had already tried one of the cheaper brands and returned them immediately for lack of bass and sound quality.  This product, however did not disappoint.  I have been using these in the office today and have the jabra app enabled for this device.  The sound quality and function of these are spot on.  I have a critical ear, so sound quality is important.  The fit is perfect out of the box for me.... and a variety of ear pieces accompany the product for an alternate fit for different individuals.  When you take one out, the sound is paused until you re-insert and press button on outside of ear bud.... which is really kewl!  So far I am very impressed with this product and hope to update once I have used these in my workouts later this week.

title: 45 minute battery life...tops
content: read soo many great reviews on these wireless earbuds. Supposedly, fully charged earbuds are to last five hours. The earbuds are plugged in and charged for 12 hours a day. However, the battery life is not even close to 45 minutes of use before they were completely kaput. NOT WORTH THE HIGH PRICE for such little battery life.

title: Got a Replacement and happy Now
content:
I bought this in February 2019. I did read that there were some balance issues from other users. One ear bud sounding louder than the other one. Multiple tips recommended from updating firmware, resetting earbods, unpairing bluetooth, re installing english language. This only worked temporarily.
I contacted 4 times customer support. They gave me instructions but sooner or later same thing happened.

So I decided to go to Android sound settings and calibrate it for the sound to be louder in the right than the left and that seemed to take care of it. But then a hissing sound started. I called customer support and they guided me once again how to reboot, update firmware, yara yara yara.... worked again for a couple of days then the hissing started again.

So, now here I am, not sure how much time I have wasted with this product and I contact them again and they give me the same algorithm instructions...

Honestly the sound is good, and they are a decent pair but I have been dealing with these issues since very early in their life. I was going to buy the apple earpods because that is almost always GUARANTEE quality.

Do I regret buying these? Most definitely. If I hear back from customer support and they decide to change my earbuds even for refurbished once Ill consider changing this rating. For now... Im sick and tired.

Sound 4/5
Customer Support 2/5
Pleased with product... Obviously a damn zero. About to throw them to the trash

Update: Got a replacement after talking with customer support and the problems have now resolved. Happy with the sound and if this would have been my first experience I would have rated it a 5 and for that reason i am increasing it to that.

title: Okay, they only arrived today, but...
content:
... the medium gel caps that come on it fit me perfectly.  (There's smaller and larger pairs of gels if you need them.).  I did a little jogging just to test and they do not fall out.  Pairing was simple to my iPhone and iPad.  The controls work as advertised.  Phone functionality is good.  Sound is great - I up'd the bass with the equalizer in the Jabra app from the Apple App Store.  Noise canceling works - it's not hype!

Five stars.

title: the real deal
content: perfect fit. even though the Bose sound a little better these still sound great. I love that they're not as pronounced as the Bose. I unload trailers and sweat a lot and I can say these are sweat proof  love them

title: Great sound, very good design
content: Superior sound for Bluetooth. Good fit for me (I can’t wear EarPods, they fall out). Sound quality on calls is very good. The round design makes them feel awkward to handle and put in, you have to pay attention to know which way is up. Volume up down on left bud is not super convenient to use, you have to feel around to press the right place. I use the volume buttons on my phone. The hear through feature is only useful if you have the level of your music quite low. Flawless initial connection to iPhone when first put on. Very easy to pause quickly. Or just take one out and the sound will automatically pause, then resume when you put it back in. Sound skips out once in a while, not often, and it’s just a minor blip. I would highly recommend these. The sound is impressive.

title: dont stay on ear
content: i had the bose wireless earbuds and gave them to my dad to get this ones i had to trade them back because this dont stayed on my ear no matter what earbud tips i used no matter how much i push t hem inside my ear . they have great sound quality and great features with the jabra app but why would you bother paying 190$ for an wireless earbuds and  features if dont stay in your ear and fall by them self (not Kidding) when using them like your running they fall your walking they fall your staying still they falllll ll eventually but they fall this sucked i will defenetly buy them again ever ever plus i bought them because they where smaller than the bose but hell i prefer big earbuds that they stay in my ear no matter what are you going to risk 200$ earbuds and they fall out of nowhere from your ear and loose them or break them ? nah not me

title: Very Happy!
content: Okay, I waited a month to review these because I have struck out twice in trying to go wireless in the gym. I have suffered for years with wires in the gym and these have ended that fight. First I required noise cancelling these do with a good fit and the software app settings on energy and noise cancel. The sound is better than my go to wired phones, Skull Candy. I bought these, yes rather pricey, because CNET reviews said they were one of the best and is where I have bought all my electronics. They have never steered me wrong. The left ear is not as tight as my right ear. Maybe Jabra will read this and offer a solution? To sum up, if you’re put off by the price don’t be. Get rid of wires for good and love your music in the gym.

title: The DELUXE earbud
content: Wow, these are really fancy. I love that I can comfortably wear these for hours. They store nicely in a charging case, and hold a battery charge quite a long time. I also love that I can answer phone calls on these with absolute ease.

title: Great quality-just make sure it's the right fit for your ears.
content: The quality was there and they kept pushing out updates to make it better.  The problem for me was the fit. I am a taller person an in proportion I have bigger ears.  These did not feel comfortable after a period of time. I wish they had more alternatives to fit other ear sizes that were comfortable, however the quality was great and it was strictly a comfort issue that causes me to give a reduced rating of the product.

title: Sound will be higher in one ear
content: Ordered these for the gym. Turns out, these headphones have a problem with sound levels. Mine had volume higher in the left ear than the right ear. Downloaded new firmware for it and it still have volume differences. For the price I paid, it shouldn't be an issue, but sadly was. Even the sound quality was poor with a weak bass. Luckily amazon accepts returns for this within the first 7 days. Apperently I'm not alone with the volume differences, a quick google search shows that many people experience this with no fix. Don't waste your money on this and get something different.

title: Do not buy if you want to use them at a gym with other people
content: So much disconnection issues. When I take hem to the gym it’s non stop cutting out, I’m assuming due to all of the other Bluetooth headphones. Just a guess tho. They work fine by myself not near anyone using Bluetooth headphones. But, I bought them for working out and cannot do that with these

title: Great bluetooth headphones, but could be better
content: I love the option to turn on and off the noise cancellation. I can take this into meetings and still hear what people are saying. I can walk around at night and not worry that someone can sneak up behind me. I love using my headphones, and use them everyday. However, I absolutely hate that I cannot use the left headphone by itself! It's REALLY annoying (seriously who designed this). I work in an office cubicle where my door is to my right. So if I only want to listen to music in one ear, it MUST be in the right ear. I can't possibly justify the price for this lack of functionality as compared to other wireless bluetooth headphones I have used.

title: Poor sound quality for the price.
content: Absolutely no bass.

title: Sweet headphones
content: I like the these a lot.  At other review mentioned sound sound quality is on point as is the other functions.  The only gripe is that the headphones do not work independently.  If I only want to use a single headphone it always needs to be right one. Not the end of the world but annoying at times.

title: Stoped Working After 2 Months
content: I gave these earbuds to my wife for a birthday present after researching similar products.  They were rated well.  They aren't cheap but I was okay with it because I thought we were getting quality.  After less than 2 months of light use, the sound started cutting out and then completely stoped working.  It's not the internet or bluetooth connection.  The earbuds just don't work.  They are now two expensive little pieces of garbage.  Won't be purchasing anything from this maker again.

title: Can't keep them in my ear...
content:
I bought these as a truly wireless earbud to have around for work, commuting and just walking around downtown with some music going. I find that the headphones produce a great sound and have had no issues with pairing and bluetooth.

My issue is that they constantly fall out.

Regardless of which earbud size I use (it comes with 3 different sizes), none will hold the earbud in my ear well enough. If I talk at all, the earbuds will slowly work themselves out of my ear. If I'm "active" and moving around I can feel them slowly working their way out. It drives me to be paranoid and constantly pushing it further into my ear, to no avail. God forbid you want to eat something with the earbuds in, because they just fall right out.

I don't think I have particularly weird size ears, and have never had any issues with any wired earbuds, so it's frustrating that these are so expensive and won't even do one of the basic tenets of an earbud: staying in your ear..

title: Terrible product
content: Have purchased two of these now and they both worked for a few days and then the sound quality went way down and you could barely hear them. Returning for good.

title: Drops connection easily
content: Would drop connection easily. I could not use  them in the city.

title: Good Good. Very Pleased
content:
Extremely pleased with this product.  Exactly
As advertised.  Comfortable and easy to use.  Very reliable.
I highly recommend.
I know the price tag is a little steep but I’m telling you ..you won’t be disappointed.

title: Love these earbuds
content: I love these earbuds. At work I only use the right one so i can do conference calls or listen to music while also being able to hear people come to my desk. If i have both in then it cancels out all the sound around me which is awesome too. The bass on these buds are pretty good compared to my other ones that I was using before. I also didnt care for airpods hanign out of my ear, so with these jabra ear buds people don't realize i have anything in my ear which is great. I can also walk around with these in my ear without having to fear they are falling out of my ear. I recommend these.

title: Not satisfied
content:
They were really uncomfortable. Wouldn’t stay in my ears very well. Left one wouldn’t work at times. Looked it up online for help and was told that you may have
To take the left one out first???  It worked but then kept happening. I do not like this product at all!  I gave it a try but got way too frustrated.

title: Negative reviews are correct.
content: I bought these for plane trips to be able to listen to music and movies while on the plane with noise canceling on. They worked great until I got home and began using them.  Sure enough, as many reviews have stated, the left earbud loses connection the right and cuts in and out so much that I can't use them. I was trying to lay back in a recliner and found that they would cut in and out when laying back but if I brought the recliner to the upright position they worked better but still crackled once in a while. Seriously Jabra, for $170 these should not perform like this. Connecting to a device is also an issue. Most of the time it can take 1 -2 dozen tries or 10-15 minutes.  Consumers should not have to go through this when spending this high amount. I will be taking them back.  Too bad. I really wished they had worked out.

title: I can't get these to work
content: I used them once and they worked fine.  They connected to my phone fine.  I've been trying to get them to connect to my phone again for two days and they just will not connect.  Complete waste of money.  I downloaded the app thinking that would help, but they still will not connect.

title: I'd say they are comfortable - or at least not uncomfortable
content:
But the main drawback is the sound quality. Despite the "equalizer" in the app, they still sound "tinny". Then again, what did I expect from such a small device. I upgraded to Bose which has a much improved sound. Next when money permits, I'll upgrade to Masters & Design.
On a positive note, phone calls are clear and the controls easy to use,

title: Muy cómodos excelente calidad de sonido y batería.
content:
Tenía mis dudas previo a la compra al leer multitud de reseñas, sin embargo los audífonos superaron mis expectativas:

1.- Molestia en los odios: Se adecuan bien al tamaño de los oídos, a pesar que no estoy acostumbrado a los audífonos in ear, los cuales siempre me causan molestias, estos por el contrario han sido muy cómodos aún al usarlos por horas.
2.- Molesto para oídos pequeños: Las almohadillas fueron un inconveniente al principio, mi canal auditivo está justo entre el tamaño M y L, me tomó un tiempo definir cual de las dos era más conveniente.
3.- Reducción de ruido: La reducción de ruido es muy buena, en el caso de estos audífonos es pasiva, y al seleccionar el tamaño de almohadilla adecuada funcionan muy bien. Precisamente este fue el motivo por el cual decidí comprar este modelo, llevaba meses trabajando frente a una construcción escuchando el ruido por 9hrs al día y llegó el momento en que cualquier sonido me era molesto. Estos audífonos ayudaron mucho a reducir el ruido ambiental, inclusive en el metro.
4.- El peligro de no escuchar lo que pasa alrededor: La función de escuchar el entorno requiere cierta mejora, al activarla amplifica un poco el sonido del aire, un detalle que puede resolverse con una actualización de software, aunque este detalle te ayuda a saber que la función está activa y en general funciona excelente. El poder configurar el nivel de intensidad es muy útil para los diferentes ambientes: gimnasio, calle u oficina.
5.- NR activa: No posee reducción de ruido activa, aunque pareciese que el hardware es capaz de soportar esta función. Es una lástima.

En general, los audífonos superaron mis expectativas y disiparon mis temores, son muy cómodos, excelentes para hacer ejercicio en el gimnasio, una calidad e intensidad de sonido muy buena, la batería realmente dura lo que promete y más.

title: LOVE THEM!!
content:
Love, love, love these earbuds!
I've tried three wireless headsets over the years (that wrap around the neck) and in each case one side stopped working after ~5-7 months (i.e. no sound coming out of one earbud) but I will say that I used them a lot, both at work and at the gym.
Not with these! Not only are they VERY comfortable but I've had them for several months now without any problems. I mostly use them at the gym and haven't had any problems with them falling out of my ear while on the treadmill or lifting for the most part.
The sound is also EXCELLENT and the noise cancellation is superb. No issues with the bluetooth connection.
Yes they're pricey but I'd rather pay extra for something that will last longer.

title: Very Uncomfortable In Your Ears
content: The sound quality and features are excellant but after they are in your ears for more than 15 minutes they begin to hurt your ears. Very uncomfortable.

title: Connection problems, there are better options
content:
I love the fit, sound is just ok.
Could have used a magnetic docking solution for a more secure case fit, the biggest problem is that one side looses connection a fair amount of time making it super annoying listening to anything.

title: good
content: The only bad thing is that the left ear cannot be used alone.

title: These are the best
content: These are the best true wireless ear pods. I've tried them all, so I should know. They arrived quickly and are just amazing. You've gotta try these.

title: Geat Earbuds
content: These earbuds fit very well and stay put even during exercise.  Sound quality is great.  I am very satisfied with these earbuds.

title: Closest, but no Cigar... (Sad face)
content: These are the best BT ear buds I have had in a while.Great but not awesome for one reason only, that is having not noise canceling... I mean all the manufacturers have gone to this"noise canceling as in cancels sound around you from being heard to the listener. Well that is great, but isn't that an inherent trait of an in ear bud? My issue is outside noises heard to the recipient on the phone. I mean I literally watched 100 + video reviews on these this on Youtube before dropping almost $200 aaagain on some buds. No one, and I MEAN NO ONE tested these in a real noisy environment to see what the recipient heard!!! So I rolled the dice... Again... Real world these this are good for a lot of people, comfort, style (not giant bugger hanging out of your head, Air Pods...), and overall performance. All the listed features are great and perform well too. Okay so how is it Jabra can do such and amazing job at making these things perform against wind noise but other noises are... ready...? AMPLIFIED to the recipient on the phone!!!! I mean they did a stellar job on the wind noise reduction as in driving down the road in my car at 60+ MPH with the front windows down all the way and they hear nothing stellar!!! Now on the other hand if I am in the shop (automotive) it is like a ear blast to the person I am on the phone with and they can not hear me, but the pneumatic tool sounds are super clear and crisp... LOL... That one draw back prevents the 5 star rating! The only buds I have had that were able to do that was the first gen Jaybird buds but they picked up wind noise and not true wireless, oh and not around any more. The Jaybird X3 don't even bother on outside noise cancellation to the recipient. Well I just wish these manufacturers would "listen" to a call and say hmmm, I bet there are a lot of people that would pay more for this if they actually did these functions! Oh well one day... one day...

title: Bad longevity
content: They fit well but are uncomfortable after long periods of time. I'd you plan on using these at the gym, don't use them if you're using cardio machines. Something about the machines at my gym interfere with the signal, it may be the Bluetooth from the machines but this shouldn't be happening for headphones designed for active wear. The battery is starting to rapidly drain after 7 months of use they don't last a day anymore.

title: Bad product, horrible customer service
content: A little more than one month after receiving it, it stopped syncing. Spent months back and forth with Jabra's lousy customer service. When they finally realize that their product was a lemon, it took another couple of months to send a replacement. Spare yourself the aggravation of getting a flawed product with a horrific customer service and get something else instead.

title: Falls out
content: Returned...hurt ears and would fall out no matter what sized tip I used.  Main purpose was running

title: Good headphones with small flaws
content: Good sound quality but when they’re on you can hear slight white noise (static). If your music is on its harder to hear but still a little noticeable with podcasts. Easy pairing and you have some extra functions in the app. I like the ambient hearing function in case you need to be aware of your surroundings with these in. The other thing I noticed is the slight latency when watching YouTube videos. It’s not bad but a bit noticeable. I think all wireless headphones are going to have some kind of slight flaw given they’re not wired but these are good enough for what I need from my headphones. I don’t know if I could find another brand that won’t have small issues here and there. I don’t make many calls so can’t speak to call quality.

title: Best truly wireless headset I've used.
content: I've used many different headsets - wired, wireless, and truly wireless.  This is the best I've ever used.  Fit is great.  Sound is great.  Battery life is great.  Love the controls on the earbuds.  I can make changes to the song, volume, and outside noise while not breaking stride.  Love them for running, cycling, or lifting.

title: Thud thud thud in my ear when I run with it
content:
I have Bose SoundSport Free and coming from that, this is a big downgrade. Sound quality is kinda weird, I kept adjusting it with the Jabra+ app but something is just missing. Sound is not as clear as it could be especially at mid range. The worst thing is that this sealed in-ear style makes my ear painful when I run. I supposed it has something to do with pressure. Also, it does thud thud thud thud loudly in my ear when I run. Sound similar to if you tap your finger on the earbuds, on both side, every stride.

On the flip side, I think the noise canceling feature is quite impressive for such a small earbud.

title: Love them!
content: Good stuff

title: Right earbuds for me
content: I was looking for a product with good battery life and good sound and ability to isolate me from other sounds, do a lot of conference calls and I also like listening to books and music while working or working out.  This product gives me all that.  I would love to have the ability to know how much charge is there n the carrying box, hope that can be added.

title: Great--Except Right Earbud Keeps Failing (3 times in 1 year)
content: I really like my Elite 65t earbuds. Except--the right earbud keeps failing. After a few months of use, suddenly the volume level will plunge. I know, first thought is wax buildup. But I cleaned it out, that didn't make a diff. Here's the other thing: it's sporadic. Sometimes, when I first start using the buds, the right volume will be normal. But then suddenly it will plunge. By plunge, I mean maybe 20% of the volume of the left one. Of course I've tried the obvious factory reset. Now about to return the third one in 1 year.

title: Not fully functional
content:
I want to give these five stars because they are good quality, I like the app, and my boyfriend's work perfectly (he has the same ones.) However, there seems to be something wrong with mine. I went into the app to update the setting for hear through (both earbuds in but you can still hear the noise around you) and it just doesn't work. I've compared the settings to my boyfriend's set up and it's identical. I've listened to his and it works perfectly. On mine it just doesn't work, period.

I also wanted to be able to use just one earbud for everything and from the description I thought that was possible but it's not. I'm not super technical, but my understanding was that the left bud was the "slave" so if you put that in the case and use just the right one it will function fully on its own. Not so. I can listen to music, podcasts, etc with just the right earbud in, but I CANNOT answer to make phone calls with just the one. I can't talk on the phone with two earbuds in, it just drives me crazy the way it sounds and I yell too loudly but since it doesn't work with just the right bud if the phone rings or I need to make a call I have to put it in the charging case and just use the phone. Annoying. If they work properly, like the do for my boyfriend, they're worth the money. If the functions don't all work properly, like they don't for me, they're definitely not worth almost two hundred dollars. Maybe I just got a defective pair but I'm not sure I would chance it.

title: Better than the pricier pair I bought
content: I purchased these wireless headphones at the same time I purchased another, more expensive, popular brand. I tried them both and kept these. I really like the sound quality, the hear thru technology, and their low profile in my ears. I recommend these headphones.

title: Really good
content: It's perfect and a surprisingly good fit

title: As described
content: Good quality

title: Worst warranty service imaginable
content: Left earbud stopped working.  After literally hours on hold, they finally agreed to send a replacement and gave me an order number.  But never shipped it!  On hold for even longer, tech support transfers me to customer service which says I need to be transferred to the warranty team.  On hold again.  Truly disgraceful.

title: That Jabra are not fitting to my ears and become not useable at all . Very bad. Sorry.
content: That Jabra are not fitting to my ears and become not useable at all . Very bad. Sorry.

title: Weird for me
content: I'm still getting use to these making a seal on my ear. Even with heart through technology I'm not a fan of the sealed off from your surroundings feel. And when I talk on the phone the nose cancelling actually muffles the sound of my own voice. Makes me feel like I need to raise my voice as it just muffles it more. Over all they do what they are suppose to. And others may like the features. Just feels weird to me.

title: Incredible
content: Perfect

title: Fantastic truly wireless earbuds
content: Secure fit, nice form factor, interference-free. Sounds great considering the form factor. Can customize the equalizer to your preferences. The hear through feature is fantastic for exercising outdoors. You don’t look like an alien 👽

title: Failed left ear bud.
content: All attempts to listen from the left earbud failed. But the controls on it did work. Seems many had the same issue with no resolve. Returning.

title: Such a quality product!!
content: I purchased these for my husband for Christmas. He hasn’t stopped using them and bragging about them to his friends since! The sound quality is amazing and he was SO pleased that you get 2 charges from the charging box! I can’t hear the traffic noise or anything on his radio when he’s talking to me, but his voice is 100% clear!! He doesn’t have to strain to hear even if he only has one ear bud in. Music is crystal clear! You can leave your phone in the car and get way into a store before you even realize.

title: Connection lost
content: It keeps disconnect and reconnects from my phone... I only got it for a few days.

title: Convenient, but picks up way too much background noise during calls
content:
I've had these earbuds since they first came out, so almost one year now. I like the size and convenience, but they pick up and transmit way too much background noise during calls. For example, when I'm at the grocery store talking to my wife over the earbuds, sounds that are not overly loud in the store (a grocery cart going by, kids laughing) come across to her as incredibly loud and I have to move away from the sound source to continue the conversation.
I would not buy these again unless I can find some way to fix this problem.

title: As Advertised
content:
I wanted  true wireless ear buds for the gym. After researching for about a month on youtube videos, I decided to take a gamble on these. They work exactly as advertised. The materials feel solid, not fragile. The sound quality is great. The battery life is what I expected. The case is sturdy and fits in my pocket easily while working out. The call quality is great on my Samsung Note 8. I've had them for a week now without any issues.
The best part is I'm not stuck at the gym listening to their R&B music while I'm trying to work out. And they never feel like they're going to fall out while exercising.

title: packaging and shape in perfect shape. Sound quality and voice is great so ...
content:
Worked right out of the box. shipment was ahead of time. packaging and shape in perfect shape.

Sound quality and voice is great so far.

title: Good but not great
content: Headphones are good but the microphone picks up outside noises easily .. not good for on the go travel while dialing into meetings

title: I've really enjoyed these headphones.
content:
These headphones have been great for me. I did some research and decided to overlook the few negative reviews and see how they worked in my situations. I sleep with headphones in so they needed to be comfortable and secure inside my ear without being painful and also sound-blocking. I got all of those things from these headphones.
Note: If you put these headphones in incorrectly, they WILL be painful. I am a female and I have smaller ears and before I realized I was putting them in wrong, they were a bit painful. Once that was fixed, I never had another issue with them being painful.

The primary issue I've had is that I lose them pretty often but I can't knock Jabra for that. I have noticed every once in a while that the left ear will very very slightly buzz but I seat it back in the case, take it out again, no more buzzing.

ALSO!! Note that Jabra has updated the firmware on these at least 3 times so they're always improving.

Sound quality is a non-issue for me because I'm not exactly an audiophile but these are on-par or outperforming the BeatsX and AirPods (both of which I have used). No M1 chip in these but you can still check the battery levels from the swipe down menu on iOS. They instantly connect as soon as I remove the right earbud from the case. Seamless.

Very pleased overall.

title: awesome functionality.
content: Top notch sound, awesome functionality.

title: Excellent!
content: As advertised!

title: Hurts Ears Overtime
content: Hurts Ears Overtime

title: Hissing
content: Hissing in left earbud whenever it plays audio, and the sound continues a few seconds after the audio ends. It's subtle, but drives you insane when you notice.

title: Bad fit and sound
content:
I had these for a bit and they’re not terrible sounding if you tweak the EQ in the app AND get perfect placement in your ears. That’s where most of the problem is though, the fit just isn’t very good.

It’s hard to get a good seal and they often feel awkward from left to right. I found myself fidgeting with the left one all the time and it was never really comfortable. For short listening periods it was tolerable but they definitely became painful after about an hour. I was mainly comparing these to the Bose and they paled in comparison.

Call quality wasn’t good either. I ended up returning mine when people were saying they couldn’t hear me. Sorry but Jabra specializes in headsets for phones calls why wouldn’t they at least get that right? Maybe mine was defective, but so many dings just made it so these would have just ended up in a drawer instead of in my head.

title: Good bluetooth
content: I like them a lot for running. Secure fit. no issues

title: Worked well, lacks bass
content: Worked well overall and also fit will. However I did not like the way it sounded. It lacked bass and setting the eq helped slightly but not fully.

title: It is great.
content: Great size for the ear.

title: Great Investment
content: Very good quality for a good price. I would buy them again.

title: A big disappointment
content: I wanted truly wireless ear buds, and after being underwhelmed by a mid-price range pair I decided to get these, thinking the extra cost would mean better quality.  I was very disappointed.  One of the ear buds never worked correctly, and then it just stopped working.  When I researched the problem I found that it's very common for these particular ear buds.  I'll never buy another Jabra product.

title: sound quality good, staying in your ears, not so much
content: They are good and sound is very good but have fallen out of my ears a few times. If you're fairly inactive fine but if you're active, you can expect them to fall out.

title: No go !!
content: I buy wireless ear phones all the time because I’m just looking for the best sound and comfort like pretty much everyone , however these ear phone have pretty nice sound the cancelation feature of shutting off when one that falls out ( that happens often )to me is not a good feature. Also the sound is louder in one than the other the fit no matter what size ear piece you use doesn’t work well ! Maybe it’s my ears ? They seem a bit heavy and stick out a bit to far with nothing to hold them in so just walking the vibrations make them fall out I’ve had mine for about a week now but I’m returning them . They are NOT worth 189. Dollars who ever designed them definitely need to go back to the drawing board . I’ll be again going to the market looking for the best wireless ear buds/phones

title: Love it but it has it flows
content:
love them sound phenomenal very clear voice for calling recommend it for android users and when opening the charging box it connect instantly with no problem and it fast charging case also the app app app app one off the best apps i have used for wireless headphones it gives you control for almost every thing.

why i give it 3 stars:
1. when you wear it for long time it gets uncomfortable  because it seal the ear canal which is good cancel any noise around you but not for along time.
2. the main bud is the right one and cannot use the left one alone only the right and when you pull out of your ears it pause the video/audio but of forgot to return them to your ears for long period of time the left bud will lose connection and turn off and even if you turn them off manuallly it will not reconnect only the right bud will get connected you will need the charging box to reset them by put them both inside take them out no sure i that will be solved with an update or not so it will be a con until its fixed if possible.
3. when its in my pocked like all other wireless headphone there will be some time some drops in connection and as i noticed it deponds how you put your phone in your pocket and  i think thats depends where is you Bluetooth receiver inside your phone i use one plus 3t i know am being harsh with this point but i needed to clear that out because some people and youtube reviewers will tell it Bluetooth 5 and its better but in real world nothing is perfect.
4. And yes the fall of very easy i you opend the charging box becasue there is not magnatic holder or whatever it name and that is major design flow from jabra

I really recommend them if you do not have and problem with the cons i wrote in this review and yes the fair price in my opinion is 100$ as i bought these used for 110$

title: Jabra customer support is awful
content:
I love the true wireless bluetooth.  I really like the way they stay in your ears (as advertised).  The quality of the sound is impressive although for my loss of hearing they could be a little louder.  Not sure how to use the phone option yet.  The only issue I have is the dead spot when I turn my head with my phone in my pocket.  The  buds loose connection with the source often during yard work which frustrates me to no end.  Not sure how but it seems to be a line of sight issue at a distance of 3 feet??????!!!!
UPDATE!!!  Been well over a month now trying to resolve this issue with Jabra.  They keep indicating they will send a label in the mail for me to return and I have yet to receive anything.  I have made numerous contacts with the company with zero resolution.  I cannot recommend this product at this time.

title: Best wireless earbuds hands down
content: Love how easy they are to set up.  I use them everyday during my workouts and they do not fall out.  Great to use for daily activities, can use one at a time or both.  Great battery life and can adjust settings.  I have purchased other more expensive wireless earbuds and these are the best by far

title: Battery no longer charges.
content: After 6 weeks, it no longer charges. It’s a shame because I really like these.

title: glad I bought these
content: they connect automatically every time, don't lose connection and sound great.  I did upgrade to the comply tips (go to their website to make sure you are ordering the right tips that will work with the case when re-charging).  They now stay firmly in my ears when I use them to run and work out.  If are not exercising and getting sweaty, then the regular tips work fine.

title: Too high priced for battery life and sound quality
content: Picks up too much background noise. Sound quality is not what I expected,

title: Works great as headset, music and voice connection to the phone
content: Great fit and function!

title: Very loss top volume, zero bass, zero noise cancellation
content:
The bad : These have the sound quality of earbuds from Walgreens. ZERO BASS!! The top volume is just pathetic even with the app.
They have ZERO NOISE CANCELLATION! You can here other people talking right next to you. The treadmill at my gym almost completely drowns them out.

The good : They are compact and nice looking and the docking station holds a charge for 5-7 days. Good for quite walks through the woods though you would probably still hear the birds.

title: AVOID and get something else.
content: These headphones would be pretty amazing...if they only worked.  I got two different pairs and the left earbud continues to drop.  Did all the resets, updates, hardware restarts, etc and still issues.  They managed to work fine for 2 weeks and now back to broken.  JABRA support is garbage they said to just return and exchange.  NOT HAPPY with this purchase at all.

title: WOW!!
content: After days of research... all I can tell you is stop searching further and BUY THESE! They just arrived and they are amazing, they check all the boxes: built quality, sound, call quality, fit/comfort, connectivity, etc... You won't go wrong with these. Just hope I bought them earlier since they have been around in the market for a while. Thanks Jabra!!

title: Excellent product
content: Hands down the best wireless earbuds I've ever purchased.  We are now on our fifth set of earbuds trying to find ones that will be what we need.  We both go to the gym and lift.  We don't do a lot of cardio.  We've tried lower end, mid grade, and now these higher end ones.  I have never been more excited about spending $300 on a product.  These earbuds block out sound, stay charged, and have excellent musical quality.  I haven't charged the case in over a week.  I've used them for approximately five to six hours over the last week, and they still had 94% charge when I started the Jabra app yesterday.  I do recommend, if you purchase these, to download the Jabra Sound+ app.  The earbuds aren't rocket science to operate to begin with, but the app makes it child's play.  If you are on the fence about spending $170 on these, having this experience, I wouldn't hesitate to do so again.

title: Sound quality was fantastic but I'm returning them because they hurt too much ...
content: Sound quality was fantastic but I'm returning them because they hurt too much when wearing them.  After only about 15 minutes my ears were very sore.  I really hurt to push the controls.

title: Too expensive, too glitchy, too faulty
content: I’m so very disappointed in the Jabra airbuds. I decided to get them instead of the newest Apple airbuds and I’m sorry I choose Jabra. First problem, there wasn’t any sound coming from the left airbud. I called Amazon customer service and they were very helpful. I had to shake the airbud and somehow it began to work. Odd... now the right airbud won’t work and this is the bud that connects both to Bluetooth. I would have had better success with a set of cheap airbuds.

title: Buzzing
content: Slight sporadic buzzing in left earpiece even when new ... disappointing because otherwise really cool headphones!

title: Great sound, long battery life
content: Sound is great, battery life is very good. Had to buy new plugs, bought Comply Truely Wireless, as in M size a hard ring came loose and could not be used anymore.

title: returned
content: Good Sound terrible call quality. Would have been perfect if it came with noise cancelation for the phone calls.

title: Great
content: Husband only used once so far but he likes them and great quality. We also purchased a warranty should we encounter an issue

title: Husband loves them
content:
Husband loves them.  Replaced the Jabari Elite Sport earbuds that he always had
problems with.  He likes these much better.  Slightly better design on the charging case.  Better battery life.

title: Garbage!!
content: These are garbage. I would expect this type of quality from a product that’s $49.99.. not $189.00. You can just feel how cheaply they are made. Sound quality is a 3 out of 10. I watched extensive reviews on youtube and thought this was the best choice but boy was I wrong! Returned the very next day. Back to the AirPods it is. If apple made an in ear wireless earbud that would be my first choice. Quality is far superior over the Jabras.

title: Amazing
content: Having dealt with the cord of other wireless headsets (with a cord between them) sticking to my neck, where every time you turn your head one of the earpieces gets ripped out of your ear, I upgraded to these, and they are awesome. I only wear them for about 20-30 minutes at a time but they are rock solid, sound great, and I have total freedom to look around (which is helpful running in an urban environment with people and traffic around). I like the pass-through sound as well, though it gets drowned out by music pretty easily (it works between songs though). Worth every penny.

title: Not bad, but far from perfect.
content:
Pros:
[+] Sits comfortably in the ear
[+] Sound quality is good (not great)
[+] Price is OK
[+] Pretty good battery life (up to 6h play on average volume)

Cons:
[-] Frequent hissing sound when reaching out to phone (while in the ear with nothing playing)
[-] Left bud can't work at all without the right bud, so can't separate the two for twice the battery time
[-] App is not very useful, and the UX is very confusing
[-] Charging box latch is NOT magnetic, and is VERY annoying to open and close
[-] Also, buds placement in the box isn't very intuitive or smooth.
[-] Signal doesn't break easily, but stutters starting 3m distance with no obstacles in the way.

title: A huge "but" ....
content:
this product is amazing in every way, (((But))) it gives me a painful ear fatigue!
It leaves my ears sore, I have tried every silicone pieces that are provided. Yet, it is the body of the inner part of the earphone which compresses against my ear. Frustrating, and for me is a deal breaker unfortunately.

title: Really great
content:
Excellent sound quality, mic quality, audio passthrough was unexpectedly my favorite feature.

Quick charge meant that even with heavy usage at work, with audio passthrough, I never really had dead buds.

Passthrough audio seems like a gimmick, and I had no interest, but it's fantastic to be able to pop audio in for talking/awareness. I leave the feature on nearly always, until I want to concentrate on listening.  I didnt pay full price, and at my purchase price I love them.

Audio quality was unexpectedly great too. Bass is rich and balanced for all genres. Really pleased.

title: They have good sound but the left earbud stopped working
content: The left earbud stopped charging

title: Doesn't fit - Pops out immediately
content: I wiggled these earphones in every way but they popped out immediately. Also tried all the different six ear tips. I have no idea how people use these for running or gym workouts. I returned it within the hour.

title: Good headphones, terrible customer service
content:
I love the sound and feel of these earbuds but I had one of them break after a few months of light use and dealing with Jabra customer support has been a nightmare.

They first sent me a to their website to request a replacement but the website was broken.  I spoke to a person to manually have my info entered and never heard any confirmation.  Had to call twice to find out that they had my info but then told me they were out of replacement parts and I would have to wait indefinitely.  I wish I had been told that without having to contact them.  I finally was able to send my earbuds in for a replacement and have heard absolutely nothing since.  No idea if they have received it or are actually processing the request.  If this is standard for them, I'd recommend staying far away.  It's now been a month since i sent them to for replacement and still am in the dark.

title: Great service
content: Still a work in progress.

title: Nice pair
content: Love it a lot. Easy to carry. Good sound quality!

title: Exactly what I needed except.....
content: These things are awesome as long as you do not chew, yawn, swallow, sneeze, cough, chew gum, chew gum while walking, run, blow your nose, speak, talk or move your head from side to side. Also, don't run with scissors! I've tried all sizes of ear buds included but the Jabras fell out of my ears within seconds if I did any of the above! Sitting at my desk, on a plane, laying in bed... maybe they are ok. But otherwise they are useless and will inevitably be lost!

title: Keep Disconnecting in HK
content:
Good:
Fits pretty well inside my ears with light exercise
Sound about average considering the price
Works ok for calls

Bad:
It kept disconnecting when I was in HK when I was riding public transportation like the subway or in crowded areas.  If anyone plans to use this in crowded area you may experience similar problem.

title: Not worth the $$
content: Left earbud never stays on

title: Not all outer ear cavities created equal.
content: These were recommended by someone who uses these for both business calls and music while running/riding.  The sound quality was fantastic much better than the AirPods however these are not made for every ear.  I had to return because they didn’t fit into my ears and kept falling out while I was running. I believe these are made for men or those who have larger ear cavities that allow these to sit properly without issue. There are adapters provided for the portion of the device that goes in your ear cannal-however the larger round portion of the device needs to sit with in the outer ear is large-and this is where I had a issues with fit. My outter ear just isn’t big enough.

title: These are Awesome!!
content:
My one disappointment: I WISH I HAD BOUGHT THEM SOONER!!!

I am a picky purchaser, and I don't just buy a product because it's trendy. I've done my research. Not only do these Jabra Elite 65t fit perfectly, they do everything they're supposed to do! Noise cancelling? Check! Sound quality (including a healthy dose of base)? Check!  Moisture Wicking? Let's just say, I use these a lot in the gym. I run; I lift (including inverted exercises); I sweat extensively. Never once have the Jabra Elite 65t earbuds fallen out. Never. My gym often has music and commercials playing that I don't care for - guess what: I seriously don't hear them, and I'm not cranking the volume either. The battery lasts just as advertised. Syncing is really easy (all the functions are). I have only experienced interference a couple of times, bit the majority of the times, I leave my phone in my gym bag at the station I'm working on, and I can walk to pick up weight-plates or do another exercise up to 25' away sometimes without loosing signal.

I definitely recommend these! In fact I just bought my wife (a devout Apple product fan) these same ones - she shares my disappointment: WHY DIDN'T I BUY THESE SOONER!!

title: Worth it!
content: Love these. They work great. Good battery life and quality sound

title: the best i have used so far.
content: Not too loud- good for long term hearing, doesn't come out while jogging. sweat resistant too. the only problem is that it wakes up while in the box. and takes over your phone while listening through your phone...

title: Good but not Great.
content:
POSITIVE:
I have had the Jabra Elite Active 65t's for 2-3 months I think. I have carry them in my pocket and use them every single day. I use them for about 1-3 hrs a day to listen to podcast, music (metal & rap), and phone calls. After installing the Jabra app you can tune the earbuds to the music or audio source you are listening to so that all music or audio sources sound good coming through. I all through high school hated earbud because they would always fall out of my ear so getting these I was worried they wouldn't stay in but after putting on the smaller tips and figuring out how to put them in correctly I can now say they fit great and don't fall out when I wobble or shake my head. I have not ran with them in or used them out on a rainy day.

The earbuds stay charged for 3.5-4.5 hrs from what I noticed. I took a flight to NYC which was 5-6 hrs due to a delay and after what feels like using them all 5-6 hrs they never died. the carry case was charged before the trip but I never charged the earbud case while taking this trip plus the flight back and the earbuds still never died or needed to be charged.

NEGATIVE:
Only thing about the earbuds that I don't like which is also one of if not the biggest factor in me buying them is the mic quality for calls / talking. While the mic talk quality is average at best which isn't a bad thing this mic is EXTREMELY sensitive to outside sounds and there is nothing I have been able to find that will fix that. I talk to a buddy of mine every day and he has told me countless times that he is going deaf just talking to me on the phone. Everything in my background gets picked up such as fans, cars, birds, wing, and more. At my job I have to open big bay doors manually and the simple clanking of the metal chains which i'm trying carefully not to make much noise with he say's blows his eardrums out. I have called tech support lines for help with product issues and just being in a moving car is enough for them to ask me to take my phone off "speaker" because they can't hear me.
These earbuds pick out all sounds even the smallest noises possible so i'd only be able to recommend this mic for maybe a guy or girl who works in a quiet office setting who needs a mic they doesn't cut out so people can hear you clearly.

Other then the mic being sensitive everything else about these earbuds I have liked and would still recommend if you want good wireless earbuds.

title: Not good for a phone call
content: Music and voice chat sound good but when in a phone call its sound tiny even when volume max out on the ear piece and phone and cut off in a couple second to where I have to use the phone!

title: Great earbuds, poor support
content: These earbuds are wonderful and I really enjoyed the noise blocking effects while working around heavy machinery.  The only problem is Jabra support.  I have been trying to reach out to them for over a month via phone, email and even with Amazon's support and am nowhere near  to a resolution.  Somehow the right earbud has a problem that causes it to drop in volume after a while (heat?) so I can really only hear anything out of the left earbud.  Since the right earbud is master, it is obviously still functioning well enough to send sound to the left, but it's not making (much) sound itself.

title: Could have been great
content: I had very high hopes for these earbuds after reading all the reviews. I don't know how people on here say that these earbuds stay very secure in your ears during workouts. I find the exact opposite. They constantly fell out while running on the treadmill and I had to chase them down. I then decided to just use them only while lifting weights. Once again they constantly loosened up and would fall out. I had would have to readjust them constantly after and during sets to the point I just put them in my pocket. Just to give them a thorough trial, I tried all of the different size tips. The ones that came already installed seemed to be the best fit. The large tips were to big and wouldn't insert into my ears at all. The small ones were way to loose and fell out immediately. I even tried swapping tips from other brands that I currently own but none would hold them in my ears. The quality, sound and features were great, that's why I'm giving them a rating of 3. I take to points off for being totally unusable for me. Looks like I'm waiting for the Powerbeats Pro. I currently use the Powerbeats 3's and the over ear hook works great to keep them secure in my ears. I just wanted to loose the cord. I hope this review helps people like me that have a hard time finding earbuds that actually stay in your ears because these aren't the ones for you.

title: flawless connectivity
content: A high quality built earbuds, the apps really make me surprised, I'm very enjoying the functions thru apps such as raining background and hear through function.

title: Earbuds that perform as advertised
content: Finally found earbuds that worked perfectly for me, others either did not fit properly or one earbud would cut out. These are comfortable in the ears and stay in and have not once had them become intermittent.

title: Not for the UC Dependent Road Warrior
content: First of all to qualify, I work for a world leading Unified Communications provider. I spend hours on planes, coffee shops and noisy airports and although inbound sound quality and noise isolation is great. The microphone and outbound sound transmission is atrocious, even in calm rooms with some conversations people are telling me to mute. Sounds around me are AMPLIFIED, not cancelled. I will probably hang on to these for running around airports as they’re light weight, stay in the ear and sound good but NEVER for phone calls. I bought a plantronics instead and am in love.

title: Features and sound quality
content: I am extremely satisfied with the two pair of Jabra true wireless that I have bought. Sound is terrific and the fit is the most confortable I have experienced on earphones this small. I have read so many complains on amazon customers and about this no lasting but I have had my first pair for over a year and no issues so far. Every now and then when I make a call I ask my friends if they can hear me and they say that the call is incredibly clear then I show them the kind of Bluetooth I’m wearing and they do not believe how is it possible the they can hear me so clear with something so small. Now regarding fit with this some people might find this a little too big but I would say that these are perfect for me and they look super sexy on people's ear. So futuristic and stylish. I can’t wait for Jabra to see their next version although I think that these are just perfect. I’m a very happy customer and I felt like sharing my comment just because I hate so many false reviews that makes no sense to me since I own two pair of these. One for the gym and one for work and they work and sound just great. Way better than apple AirPods and I’m a very fan of apple products but Jabra stepped up on this with better product. I really hope my review will help more people and try for themselves rather than pay attention to nonsense reviews.

title: Great headphones for work or working out
content: They feel great and fit in the ear very well. You kind of twist them inside of your ear and they stay in with no issues of coming out. The battery life I believe is 5 hours but if you charge your case it can charge the headphones back up a couple of times. The only issue is when your next to your WiFi router or another device using Bluetooth, the headphones tend to studder

title: Awesome Buy
content: Very Happy, Great Sound

title: Jabra Elite 65T makes wireless earbuds easy with great sound!
content: Great sound quality and easy to take with you with the charging case. Take calls, watch movies and listen to music on the go with quality sound.

title: Puzzle
content:
My only real complaint is that the case is really hard to open.  Maybe it's just me, but i struggle(d) with it.  Like, to the point of utter frustration.  I haven't read other reviews, so maybe this is a common problem.  I wound up taking a nail file and filing down the hook on the lid.  Now it works fine.

Another issue, and perhaps its my ears, the ear pods hurt my ears.  The smallest nodule was still a bit uncomfortable.  I finally just removed them, altogether.  I haven't used them outside or exercising since doing this.  I usually just wear them in bed at night to listen to ebooks.  I'm sure when i use them for the first time outside, i will have too much ambient noise and will put the nodules back on.

You know, i don't really know how good any of these products are supposed to sound, so i can't rate that aspect.  I also have a 30$ pair that seems to sound just as good.  And the lid opens easily.

title: For the most part best headset I have had
content: I love these.  I don't like headphones on when I sleep, however these fit comfortably enough in my ears I sleep most of the night with them.  I exercise with them and they stay on.  When I want to game on my computer and tune out the teenager or sleep and tune out the snoring husband, they are amazing.  I only have 2 complaints.  1 - the left one doesn't always turn on with the right when I put both in and its a pain I sometimes have to return it to its case and then take it back out to get it to turn on.  2 - battery life.  for the most part 4-1 hours is good, but when I am hardcore gaming for an afternoon it sucks to have to break and let them charge.  Also on long drives when I want my audio book and everyone else wants their music, again it sucks to have to charge them mid way through.

title: Love these. They fit in my ear pretty well ...
content: Love these. They fit in my ear pretty well and I have small ears surprisingly they dont bother me. The fact that as soon as you pull one out of the case its cut without you having to connect it is awesome and pulling it out pauses your music. These are a good purchase so far and they hold good battery life.

title: Had to return, painful fit in my ears.
content:
I bought these based on reviews that claimed that the microphones greatly improved the quality of call audio compared to competing products, unfortunately, that hasn't been the case in my experience.  These had a similar problem to other headsets where background noise was amplified during a call, as if the sound passthrough was turned on and couldn't be turned off.  Even with 4 microphones, there seemed to be no distinction between ambient noise and my voice. The biggest problem I had with the Jabra Elite 65T was the fit; The headphones stayed in my ears better than expected, but the hard plastic casing pressed against cartilage above my ear canal, causing soreness and tenderness after a very short period of time, no amount of adjusting could fix this so I was forced to return them.

On the positive side, the sound quality was very good, the noise passthrough worked well when listening to music, and the volume went sufficiently high. If you do not need to make calls outside of a silent office and don't have the fitment problems that I had, then these could be worth your while.

title: Terrible microphone quality
content: Absolutely horrendous microphone quality.  Impossible to use this device in a public area (or any area with ambient noise) for a telephone call without significant background noise which makes it impossible for you to be heard.  Otherwise, the sound quality and connectivity are fine for music-only usage.

title: Blown away!
content: I don't write reviews very often but here goes. These are amazing, I have smaller ears for a guy, so I always had trouble getting headphones that didnt slide out of my ear. These stay in way better than expected. I can play basketball for hours, and even with sweating,  and running they stayed in my ear. But the real reason I'm writing this is the other day I put the ear bugs through the washer and dryer (had no idea) and they still work! And now they have that new washed smell. I seriously recommend these to anyone wanting a true wireless earbud. Hope that helps!

title: DO NOT BUY Chargers die within 12 months
content: Don't buy these; I bought 2 and both sets' chargers stopped working. This is a scam so Jabra can sell replacement chargers at $70 a pop.

title: Hard to get a good fit
content: I like the design and ease of use. I like the volume buttons on the left piece.  The app from the Google Store is a nice adder and allows to change the bass and sound etc.  I also like the "Hear Through" feature.  I use it at the gym so I can hear what is going on around my while I listen to my music. For some reason, none of the three ear gels seems to get a good fit.  As a barometer, if I have them on and I'm eating anything, that movement knocks them loose and they sometimes fall out.  Hmmmm....  Not sure what to do.  I put them in and rotate them, as instructed, and they seem to seat ok but just not tightly.

title: They are great!
content: WOW! Soo I did a bunch or research before picked these up. They are worth every penny. Sound quality, battery life, hear through mode, everything! Only problem I have is that I only have 1 pair lol. I will buy them as a gift and I highly recommend.

title: Jabra will NOT replace them if they stop working
content: I do not recommend buying these headphones.  I have wasted $165 on them and support will not replace them so I am out of luck.  The right ear bud volume became extremely low.  I wrote to support and they had me try some troubleshooting but when that didn't work they stopped responding to my emails and completely ignored me.  I am trying to prevent others from throwing away $165.  If you are a gambler and still want to buy them then go for it, but don't expect Jabra to help you if you have a problem.

title: Fantastic
content: Love them. Had them for a few months now and they havent let me down!

title: The Pairing Could Be Better, but <3...
content:
I actually love these, and I will probably order another pair soon (for the office). So, why  a 4 star review? I usually exercise in a hoodie, and when I keep my phone in my left pocket, the connection cuts out often enough to be annoying. It always  cuts out if I turn my head to the right. If I put my phone in the right pocket, it works perfectly. I seems obvious that the pairing happens with the right ear phone. I always keep my phone in my left pant pocket, so it's a bit inconvenient to switch it to the right side, and have my keys on the left, but it's vital with these. It's an important detail that you should be aware of, but not a deal breaker by any means.

Other than that (small) gripe, these are great for my tastes. I bought them based on the glowing Wirecutter review. In that review they mention that the battery life is about 5 hours, but I've found mine last much longer. The fit is snug, and these don't fall out, even when running. For a Bluetooth headphone, the sound is practically crystal clear. And, they seem to block out external noise almost *too* well. (I'm not sure if that's a problem because my neighborhood is pretty mellow -- I know there's a pass-through option/button press, but I haven't used it.)

I definitely think these are worth the money.

title: Left Ear Piece cut out or wouldn't work
content: I also had to return because the left ear piece cut out or wouldn't work at all. How strange is it that so many users have reported the same problem but it doesn't seem like Jabra has done anything about it.

title: These are trash.
content: Doesn't even turn on. Complete trash

title: Dead after 11 months. It's a travishamockery.
content:
These were awesome in the beginning but now they are effectively dead. On a full charge now, they sound fine for all of 30 seconds. The right one quickly loses all sound, and the left one becomes so faint that it can barely be heard at full volume. Dealing with Jabra has been a hassle, to say the least.

Guess these just don't stand up to daily use over a year period. Time to find another brand.

title: Best TWE
content:
I have tried I believe at least 6 TWE, this is just the next generation:
-Fits perfectly (you kind of twist it in).
-First TWE that are stereo when on a phone call
-First TWE where the mic is good and people don't ask me to repeat myself, because they don't hear me well.
-You don't need to press a button to activate them just put them in you ears- e voilà !

Yes they are double the price or more but for the first time everything is just the way you want it!

title: can not hear!
content: I am very unhappy with my headphones.  When I try and use them to talk to anyone it's so frustrating!!  No one can hear me so what's the point.  I just opened up my order to try and return after finally giving up and noticed the "window for returns" is expired.  That's ridiculous!!!

title: Poor fit
content: Hate them. Constantly fall out in routine gym use. And yes, tried all 3 ear plugs and have them correctly inserted into ear canal.

title: Long battery, super comfortable, sound ok
content: Love my Jabras.  Battery lasts all week... they NEVER fall out of my ear (I've had this issue with all others)... sounds quality is ok (bass lacking and sound is a bit hallow).  Overall there are great for daily use.  I wanted bose sound, but I can't have it all.  Need to set the right expectations.  Highly recommend though over other options.  I use them with my pixel 2 and my laptop.  Plus both devices can connect at the same time.

title: Moderately disappointed in the call quality and unboxing condition.
content:
Firstly, upon unboxing these earbuds I was excited until I notice the condition of the package. The charging case were dusty with an ashy white color along with the earbuds in the charging socket.

Aside, from the filthy condition of the unboxed earbuds, the quality of the call is a little distorted and several times callers had to repeatedly say “hello hello ! I’m not hearing you clearly you sound far or there is allot of background noise. And hardly hearing the voice. ” I do not rate these earbuds for making calls however the mids range sound in the speaker is sharp with a moderate amount of base clear enough to enjoy.

 It also lets background noise in from the app. Also because they fit to fill the space in your ears they act well at cancelling noise. Because they carry a little weight they can fall out your ears if the cushion gets moist feom sweat while running.

The tracking feature is pointless if they are in the case and not connected to a paired device. Not too impressed by that. It’s gimmicks for selling points. The only tracking is the location of the last connected device. Not Im real time if not connectef to the paired device.

My main issue is the echo. I use mine for business calls throughout the day. And people are always complaining about hearing their own feedback/ echo.

After finding out that it’s an issue with the device at the product level. I’ve decided to return these.
