title: Favorite "truly wireless" earbuds, so far
content:
I have really enjoyed using this set of truly wireless earbuds. They aren't perfect, but they are, by far, the best ones I've tried, to date.

What I like:
For me, the fit is very good. The silicone earpieces seal my ear canal to allow good sound, including the bass that often gets lost with earbuds that don't fit well. The size is great. They are small enough to be unobtrusive, but can easily be grabbed to remove them. I like the controls. The right button (main control) is easy to find and depress, but not so sensitive that it gets activated by accident. I tried other brands of truly wireless buds that had a touch control that was way too sensitive. Every time I brushed up against something, it was turning on/off music or trying to activate Siri. Others I've tried had buttons that I had to push so hard it hurt my ear to do it. This one has a satisfying "click" that lets you know you pressed the button, but is still quite comfortable. The left side has volume up/down buttons that are also easy to find and depress. Battery life is pretty good for this type of device. I've been getting probably 3-4 hours of continuous run time. You can also keep it in standby mode, as you would a Bluetooth phone earpiece, but it will shut itself down after a time of inactivity (30 minutes, I think?).

The accompanying app allows you to fine tune the sound and also lets you set the "hear through" characteristics. I like that feature a lot. Most of the time when I have these in, I'm perfectly happy to tune out the rest of the world. There are other times, though, that I need to pay a little more attention, and the ability to allow a certain amount of the outside world in is great.

I am not a runner and I've not used them during intense workouts, but I feel like they have been very secure in my ears. I wouldn't expect them to stay in doing Matrix-like stunts. If you're looking to get them for workouts or running, Jabra has a "sport" model which is supposed to be more water resistant.

The cons:
Not a lot, here, but I will say that with extended wearing, they can get a little uncomfortable. This is not limited to these particular buds, however. I've rarely used in-the-ear buds that didn't get a little uncomfortable after having them in a while. That being said, they are much better than the majority I've tried. As you might expect, the little drivers in these earbuds are not going to compete with larger, on or over-the-ear headphones in volume or tone, but they are still very good.

All in all, I would certainly recommend giving them a try if you're inclined to go the "truly wireless" route. I've tried a lot of other brands (Bose, Jaybird, Beoplay, Bragi), and I've liked these the best.

title: Save Your Money, Customer Service Is A Joke
content: Do not buy these headphones. They will last less than a year before the speakers fail, and Jabra's customer service is so poor that the warranty is basically a joke. I sent mine back for warranty repair over two and a half months ago and they have no idea when they'll bother to replace them. Save your money and buy something from Samsung or Apple instead.

title: Better investment than my Bose headphones
content: Much better than my Bose wireless headphones

title: I'm very happy with this purchase
content: The sound was very good, they stay in my ears and they block most but not all exterior noise. The bluetooth connection was simple, both to my Alienware laptop (Windows 10) and to my iPhone X (ios 11). Putting the phones back in the case is a little awkward compared to the AirPods that I have. However the important stuff is the Jabra sound is much better, the isolation is much better and the ear fit is  superior. A slight tilt of my head and the AirPods would fall out; the Jabras stay in even with much greater tilts. Comfort of the Jabras is also better because I'm not having to poke them all the time to get them to stay in or to try to improve the sound. I use the largest size earphone tips on the Jabras for a good fit. The AirPods, of course, have no adjustment.

title: Great!
content: My third try at wireless earphones and these are the winners!

title: Known Issue - Unbalance Playback
content:
I noticed right off when I put these in for the first time that the left side earbud had louder playback than the right side. I went on Jabra's website and learned of a firmware fix that was available and that unbalanced playback was a known issue. So I applied the update, which unfortunately didn't fix the issue at all.

My next step was to do a general search on the Internet and to my surprise this problem appears to be a common occurrence. Post after post of people applying the update, working with Jabra support, swapping headsets and finally returning the earbuds.

For the cost of these earbuds, I don't have time to fix a company's problems with faulty firmware. So I returned them and will by an earbud that has balance playback.

title: to no avail until I tried the Jabra 3t and out of the box they fit perfectly and I no longer have to look like I am drilling for the Clampets oil to get ...
content: I have to tell everyone that I have tried almost everything out there to fit my deformed (not really) ear canal....to no avail until I tried the Jabra 3t and out of the box they fit perfectly and I no longer have to look like I am drilling for the Clampets oil to get the buds to half heartedly fit in my ears....these were so simple to wear and have not even hinted at falling out. I have invested thousands of dollars looking for Jabra...where have you been all of my techno life? Oh, the reason we all buy these products. the sound..AAAAAmmmmazing. I can't find one thing that I dislike about these except, well I wish my choice in partners was as good as these....nice job Jabra...seriously great product. I might add that I have never been prompted to write a consumer review before...good or bad. so....buy these, B(*T00s)

title: The sound is great and it’s fits so snug in my ears
content: Amazing product, will buy again

title: Slightly above average
content: I had to jam them in my ear to actually noise cancel and sound was just a bit better than AirPods. They also would fall out of my ears while working out and I tried 2 different ear piece sizes they offered

title: Almost Perfect
content: In every other regard, they are perfect. I commute quite a bit for school in NYC. Every time I would walk through the train door or pass an elevator, it would cut out. I had to return because I mostly use them for commuting anyway.

title: Bad charging
content: Wow I got these a wail ago it's the best but it stop charging and I cant send them back so just know they will stop charging after about 6 months

title: Amazing sound
content: I bought these ear buds for my husband for Christmas. He loves them. They fit great and the sound quality is awesome

title: Left Earbud stopped working and Poor Customer sevice
content:
Just bought it 3 months ago and the left earbud stopped producing audio. Jabra refused to service and honor the replacement since its beyond a 30 day window.

Apparently im not the only one having the same problem

title: Great sound quality. Although.......
content:
Great sound quality, sleek design with a fun, user friendly app. Although...... the left earbud broke after one month of use, so i give 2 stars.
Would have been 5 stars if JABRA's consumer services fixed the issue, but the communication was lacking and downright unprofessional. In fact JABRA's consumer service was almost non existent, after a month of ignored emails, they finally responded with a PDF from the FAQ's page. And then radio silence, i still haven't heard back from JABRA after 6 weeks
Despite the earbud breaking, i liked the product and would have loved to give it 5 stars.... Although good customer service is a necessity in the online market, this company is lacking in that department to say the least.
Furthermore, JABRA did not honor the 2 year warranty.
~ All Love

title: Great Sound. Too Expensive. A Painful Experience.
content:
I worked out with them. Only had connection problems one time, and I was awaiting the update so I could use Alexa.
The sound quality is incredible. (I'm a studio musician)

Cons:
The charging case is REALLY difficult to open.
The material it is made from is not Great Dane proof.

Seriously, after owning these for 2 weeks, my big little buddy needed a snack, and he has expensive taste.
Not Jabra's fault. But it's ironic that I had a ton of trouble getting them out of the case: a task my idiot dog performed with the greatest of ease.

Final judgment:
If these were at a price point of $50, it would be a great buy.

But when something so expensive gets destroyed so easily, it hurts.
Painful Side note:
I replaced them with a pair of Skull Candy Bluetooth headphones for $25.

The sound quality is just as good, and the Great Dane is not interested in them.

title: Don’t count on speedy warranty help
content:
Happy with these, UNTIL I lost one, and purchased a replacement.
Received a replacement within 2days, but it wouldn’t maintain a link with the right side no matter what process/ procedures I tried.
Called Jabra. They had me return the replacement for a refund. Had to order yet another replacement. Received that one within 2days. Same exact issue. Jabra instructed me to return the entire unit for warranty replacement, and I did that, but after 12 days now waiting, I have yet to receive the replacement unit.
Good product, but poor warranty service.

title: Sound+ app ruins everything DO NOT BUY
content: The headphones are fine, the rubber tips totally block sound (and make all bodily functions amplified). The real issue is that the jabra sound+ app is complete trash. It doesn’t recognize that the phone is connected to the headphones, so there is no pass through hearing option or equalizer functions available, the main reason I selected these particular headphones. I’ve tried resetting the headphones, re-installing the app. Nothing. I did some searching and this seems like a pretty common problem. Great headphones, good sound, but they are basically $200 earplugs without this functionality. Incredibly frustrating. I’ve probably spent the last two hours searching for an answer, looks like there have been these issues since Jan of 2019. Way to totally mess this one up jabra. Would recommend air pods over these (unfortunately, air pods are the least environmentally friendly)

title: Comfortable fit
content: Excellent product

title: Pricey,  but worth it
content: I bought these to replace my old jaybird x2's. I didn't really want to shell out $180 for a new set of earphones, but I run a lot and knew they would get plenty of use. These are my new favorite things. The hear through mode is great for when I'm running on roads and a double tap blocks out noise for when I'm on a park path. They fit great in my ears and never budge even in pouring rain and running for a couple of hours. Battery life isn't as good as what i'm use to with my old wireless buds, but it was one of the better ones I found when reading specs and comparing. They are good too for talking on even with a beanie on covering them up. Nice that they dont have to be turned on or off just take them off or put them in. Definitely would recommend

title: Jabra buds wont connect 90% of the time
content:
Connected...no device connected.....coneccted.....no device connected.

Is all I ever hear from this device. They hardly ever connect to a device and maintain the connection.
Then they lose connection after a little while anyway. All while being within a few feet from my phone.

Unusable product.

title: Worth the price!
content: Love the charging case, the app it comes with, the color, and the sound quality!! Amazing headphones

title: Stutters Unless Positioned Just So
content:
When I have my phone in an armband on my left arm (anatomically the best for my use), the earbuds stutter intolerably. If I have the phone in my front left pants pocket and turn my body just so, the earbuds again stutter. Far too expensive for such connectivity issues.

As far as sound quality, there is almost no bass response, although I have yet to download the app and tweak the controls.

Update: Switched to a OnePlus 7 phone. New phone does not recognize the earbuds at all. Even with the Jabra Sound+ app. The earbuds are effectively useless now.

title: awesome!!!
content: I love these earbuds. They fit perfectly without falling out. I can run, and lift weights in them. Sound great, although I have a lot of hearing damage from the military.

title: The Case Is Like A Jigsaw Puzzle
content: As pleased as I am with these earbuds, I am equally displeased with the charging case.  Jabra's version of a joke on their customers; the case should be reworked and replaced at this price point.  Essentially a game of chance every time you want to use them.

title: Stopped Working after 3 months
content: I had this product for around 3 months.  The left ear bud stopped working.  I called Jabra, did some troubleshooting, and it came out that it was defected, and they would have to send me out a new pair.  I would be forced to send my earbuds in, and once they received them, they would then send me a new pair.  I asked if they would send me a pair, and when I received them, I would return the damaged ones.  They told me no.  This product is cheap and stops working.  I would not purchase these again.  Worst $100 plus I've ever spent.

title: If you don’t get them you are missing out
content: Very comfortably. I love the fact that they are noise isolation. If i didn’t know it i would mistake them as noise canceling. I also love the hear through function. These headphones are really good. They are worth the price as well. I am normally a Bose fan. But i would have to say these sound just as good. Also you can change the sound to fit you. All round great headphones.

title: Most reliable!
content: Never loses connection from my iPhone or between earbuds. Calls sound and work well with no complaints on both ends. Music sounds good enough for my standards. I’m more concerned with the connection and noise cancelation. This is my second pair b/c I lost one after a year of owning. You can’t go wrong with these. I’ve done hours of research and these are the ones I highly recommend.

title: Buttons hurt ears, call quality not good
content: Pressing buttons hurt ears. If making a call from a light or moderately noisy environment, other side had difficulty hearing me (was a key feature that is important to me). Ambient passthrough mode was a little weird and maybe something that needs getting used to - won't know since I returned.

title: Five Stars
content: Love them! Best I have ever had.

title: good sound and fast pairing but a little uncomfortable
content:
I purchased these a week ago and expected them to be amazing for the price. The sound quality is decent but not the best. They pair very quickly with an iPhone and the app is really nice. However, they are a tad uncomfortable after a while and pushing the buttons on the left one pushes the tip into my ear and it is quite uncomfortable.
The noise canceling is all right being that it is passive, but the hear through feature is very cool. The buds have decent treble but a pretty weak bass.
They are good buds but a little too pricey.

title: Not refined ... left ear buzz
content:
So I used to have the samsung wireless earbuds that came with my new phone ... loved em lost em ... went looking for new earbuds and decided I wanted to go with something better. I thought this would be it but it isnt.

1. Ive worn so many kinds of earbuds this is the first set that bothered me ...
2. this could effect #1 but if you are used to any kind of touch earbuds these will feel like you are 10 years back ... you have push buttons and they take good force jamming into your ear to push them ... its just not comfortable or useful really.
3. the left ear buzz is slight but widely reported and drives me nuts. when you pause you can hear it when you lower the volume you can hear it
4. when putting the left ear bud in i have to play around with it before sound will come out right ... its like it gets stuck in half on mode due to ear position.
5. sometimes when moving the sound will adjust or cut off completely. this is small movement like sitting up in my chair ... so weird

Sound is good but the negatives are just weird ... and not good at all.

title: Bad design on case; be careful of you might damage case and  buds
content: So hard to get buds out of case that one of the buds came flying out into the train tracks.  Bad design on case,

title: Only lasted about 20 months.
content: I didn't buy mine on Amazon, I bought them at Best Buy, but I feel compelled to leave a review.  If I recall correctly, I bought them in Feb of 2018.  I liked them, I thought they were pretty good, but I ended up giving them to my wife.  She would wear them around the house, not while working out or in the weather.  Sadly, the right earbud quit producing sound after just past a year and a half.  It still "works" in that it pairs, and the buttons function, it just doesn't produce sound.  The left one still produces sound. Ordinarily I wouldn't care, I'd just buy another set, but for the roughly $200 I paid, I expected better.  This was my first Jabra purchase, and I think I'll look elsewhere for replacements.

title: Warranty service was good
content: I’ve owned these for about six weeks.  The sound quality and fit are excellent.  The charging case stopped working after several charges.  I contacted support by telephone, had an appropriate email that same day, and after providing my purchase receipt, had a replacement case in about a week.  Others have reported customer support issues.  My experience was straightforward and satisfactory.

title: Great sounding headphones with some hearthrough issues
content:
The Jabra elites 65t's we're my first experience with truly wireless earbuds and I am definitely glad I chose these over others.
The Pros:
I use these to watch YouTube videos, stream music through Spotify, and just generally use my phone with them (OnePlus 6t)
There is no delay between what you see on the screen and what you hear, which is one of the biggest factors in whether I buy a product or not.
The sound is crisp and very detailed, and out of the box there's no pre-set adjustments (bass boost, high treble, etc) but the presets and equalizer in the app work wonderfully!
The hearthrough feature is definitely a factor in why I chose these over others, and once you get used to it it works (relatively) well! (More details under Cons)
They automatically pair when removed from the charging case and I've only had one issue where the left earbud didn't pair immediately but never encountered that again.

The Cons:
I would say the biggest issue I have with these is the hearthrough feature; for some reason the right earbud would seem to cut out all sound for a split second once or twice every few minutes. Imagine the opposite of hearing a clicking sound - it's like the tick tock of a clock but instead of hearing it, it's the absence of surrounding sound for a "tick" instead.
It's not noticeable when listening to music and using heathrough, but when using that feature standalone it's definitely annoying.
Also another con, the provided eargels do not fit my ears right, as the medium one that are already on the earbuds are too big for my ears and they hurt after a few minutes, and the small size ones that were provided we're too small and wouldn't stay in my ear. That's just my personal issue though and I'm sure very few people would have that problem so I did not include that in my review of this product.

title: Perfect gift, noise cancellation
content: Christmas gift, she LOVES them!

title: Three Stars
content: Good sound but hard on ear, difficult to use fot long times

title: Surprisingly good
content:
I had the usual misgivings after the various reviews, but quickly discovered that most of them could be addressed simply by downloading the full-meal-deal user manual.  The quick-start thing packaged in with the buds is next to useless for most problem-solving.  I'm a happy camper.

So far, connecting has been flawless, the range is quite good and the sound quality is better than expected -- once I spent time tweaking the mini graphic equalizer.  Minimal signal dropping, even 75-100 feet from the device.  Left bud not connecting?  Happened to me.  I tapped the bud once.  Problem solved.

Ear fit is still causing some issues, but it's early days and I haven't yet settled on an ideal size.  Consequently, a bud will fall out from time to time.  Tried the memory foam stuff but it fit no better than the silicon and doesn't work in the charging case.  But bud fit is my problem, not the device's, and I get multiple hours without discomfort even as I experiment.

Noise suppression is adequate.  Can't comment on mike or phone quality, since they aren't a major part of my usage.

It was between these Jabras and B&O.  Would have taken the latter, for the (presumed) better sound quality, but for the price difference -- it seems to me that this is emerging technology and eventually we will get a wireless bud that offers exceptional sound quality and incorporates a proper noise reduction technology.  That will make an upgrade worthwhile.

Meantime, I wouldn't hesitate to buy the Jabras again.

title: I wanted to keep them but
content:
Good: look the color, the build quality, and how easy they are to set up. The audio is good, the app is good, and calls are fine.

bad: They hurt your ears after a while, the buttons are not the best, and they kept falling out.

I just wish they did not hurt my ears, i would have kept them and the buttons did not help change my mind to return them. I wanted to love them, i just couldn't and that sucks.

title: Love these
content: Absolutely love these! Fit great and they stay in my ears when running. Amazing sound as well!

title: Not perfect, but best of the bunch.
content:
Easy to pair, stays in my ears better than the apple version.
Chunky shape pushes itself out of my ear canal with any facial expressions. None of the silicone tips fit well for me. Wish I could use the left side independently. When using the right side independently, can’t access the useful controls on the left side.
Sound quality is fine. I’m not using them for high quality listening, but for convenience. I don’t think they’re worth the high price tag. I expect fewer downsides when spending so much money on an item. But I can’t find anything better (I have very small ears and the competitor actively hurts me), so I’m keeping them.

title: buy buy buy
content: Fantastic product

title: Where have these been all my life?!
content: I was a bit skeptical that these would stay in my ears, but...no problem at all. The fit is amazing, and they're pretty tiny. The sounds is clear, and I love when it tells me that two devices are connected. I have it connected to my Windows 10 laptop and my iPhone at the same time, and have been able to talk on the phone, use Skype and M'soft Teams, listen to music, and talk to Siri. I still have to try things like, listen to music on the phone then try to answer a Skype call, or listen to music on the PC and answer a phone call to see how the transition goes. I imagine it'll be pretty smooth and effortless. I'm returning a pair of Apple AirPods today. They wouldn't work with Skype or M'soft Teams. These are just plain better for what I need them for.

title: Better than AirPods
content:
These pair, and stay paired, much better than my AirPods. Battery life seems good, on par with the AirPods. I can keep the volume lower because it seals better in my ear, which leads to a better sound for me.
I lost these for a few months in my couch, when I finally found them, they still had charge, and paired immediately. Definitely get these over AirPods.

title: Great sound if you dont mind pushing them into your ears
content: The case is compact and fits in my pocket nicely.  The earbuds and the case hold a nice charge.  I like that these can be set to automatically pause when removed from my ears. Don't put them into your pocket without the case or they will think they're still in your ears. They have the functions mentioned in their description.  Some things that aren't mentioned: The volume doesn't go very high.  If you want better than just marginally good sound you have to use your hands to keep them constantly pushed into your ears.  Occasionally, they won't connect to my phone forcing me to have to erase them from my Bluetooth menu and reinstall them.  The left earbud doesn't project bass.  I've used every fitting and the buds still fall out of my ears on a regular basis.  Definitely don't eat with these in your ears.  When I do they always work their way out.  In case you lose them it's possible to see the last place you used them but only if you were connected to the app.  This is the second pair I've had and both were defective. For this reason I've given them an overall rating of 2 stars.

title: Sound is nothing spectacular. Battery life is mediocre. Better than most earbuds sold here at Amazon
content:
This earbuds looks great. I had a different ear bud that is cheaper and this blows that out of the water.

However, this is not a perfect product. Sound is OK and battery life is mediocre.

I would recommend if you are able to get it a discount.

title: Great for working out, commuting, studying
content: These work great! They're a comfortable fit and don't fall out while I'm running or working out at the gym. You can choose whether to block outside noise or pass it through. Just discovered you can switch on various white noise or nature sound options for distracting conversations while trying to study at a coffee shop. The carrying case charges the headphones as advertised. Updates are wireless. Overall very happy with the purchase.

title: Great purchase
content: Love these. I use them 8 hours a day 5 days a week. I wish they cancelled out background noise better but I love being wireless.

title: They fit
content: My biggest problem with earbuds was finding a pair that would actually stay in my ear during a workout, and these were the only ones to succeed. The battery life of the earbuds is great, but the case can only recharge them 1.5 maybe 2 times before it is in the red, which does not bother me at all, but may bother others. The buttons are not real great. I can answer a call and pause/play very easily, but volume and skipping tracks requires pressing the PERFECT spot on the left ear bud, so for me, it is easier to just tap my phone's screen. They seem to hold up to sweat very well, and the most important thing for me is that they stay in bouncing around the weight room, and even while chewing food.

title: Great wireless headphones
content:
I was torn between these and the Bose Soundsport Free earbuds. I have the Bose Soundport HR wireless earbuds and love them (sound/comfort), though they've started to fall apart after 2 years. After a bunch of research I landed on these guys and I'm very happy with my decision. A few things that stand out to me:

- The look. These earbuds are nice and small, unlike the Bose headphones that are a bit weird looking when wearing them due to their size.
- The noise cancelling. With the Bose headphones, my noise cancelling was just turning them up loud enough to drown everything else out. Probably not safe. These headphones not only create a good seal in my ear, they also have active noise cancelling and hear-through which is a really cool feature!
- The case. I love how small and convenient the case is. My earbuds charge very quickly and the case is a perfect way to keep track of them.
- The durability. As I mentioned above, my Bose earbuds have started to fall apart quite badly after 2 years. I've only had these for about a month, but given the higher water resistance rating the the materials (no soft plastic, like Bose) I suspect that they will hold up much longer (I would guess battery life will be my first issue to come up over time).

The only thing I give to Bose is their signature sound profile. I love bass in my songs and it's something that Bose always delivers on. That said, I've found that I can tweak my equalizer and get close enough to the sound I like that it's almost unnoticeable. With all of the other positives about these, this 'issue' really doesn't bother me anymore.

title: What they don't tell you
content:
Please explain why the Jabra elite 65t,  is sold without a disclaimer. A major portion of the software Jabra advertises, does not work with Apple iPhoneX.  Other than for music listening. Jabra elite 65t, does not work with Apple products. What I am talking about is the fact that none of the text to voice function work with the iPhoneX.  I was informed by Jabra support, that Jabra is not Apple friendly. That means.  No message readout, no calendar readout, not email readout. Just listening to music..This is crap.
When will companies stop trying to fool the consumer.  At $189.00 they should do more than let you listen to tunes.  AT LEAST THEY SHOULD SAY “NOT ALL JABRA APPLICATIONS WORK, WITH ALL SOFTWARE.”

title: Connection issue
content: The constant issues with Bluetooth and the Jabra app invalidate anything positive I could say about the sound or comfort.

title: How well it fits my ears...
content: I like it all, it’s a good product and would recommend it to everyone.

title: Solid audio, horrible microphone, weak bluethooth
content:
I finally purchased a pair of earbuds to talk hands free and listen to music.
Audio is good: I listen to all genres but mostly out on the street. The earbuds provide enough power to have loud but clear music. Balanced although a bit too much bass.
The material quality of the product is excellent. They fit perfectly in my ear.
The earbuds come with a nice box (which I ve already disposed :-)) and a rechargable station. The opening mechanism is a bit fiddle.
Charging is quick and the battery last long.
Bluethooth is actually a joke. In Manhattan, I have to carry the phone (Samsung S8 but I have tried it with 3 different phones, same result) in my right hand because carring it in my left hand or even in my pocktes would result in signal loss for a second or two!). In my appartment I have to be in close aproximity of the phone (I dont own a castle...).
The worst part is where the earbuds completly fail: Calling on the streets of Manhattan is impossible with those things. All surrounding noise is heard but not my voice. Thus: Fail

title: Broke after a few uses
content: I did not buy these from Amazon, but want to share my experience with them. I used these only a handful of times over four months and now the right earbud won't produce any sound. Currently working with Jabra to troubleshoot, which takes very many back and forth emails over several weeks. Very dissatisfied after paying so much for them.

title: They fit really well, in the ear
content: Great product. Excellent sound

title: Used, incomplete item from a prior return - AVOID!!!
content:
This is advertised as a new item.  Jabra sent me the headphones, charge cable, and 2 of the 3 earbud pairs (the middle size missing) with no documentation. It was shipped in a small generic box that still has the address label the return slip for the person who sent it back (and, presumably, kept the middle size earbuds).  They didn't even both to repackage it!  PATHETIC!  Was supposed to be a birthday gift for my wife, but I'm embarrassed to even show it to her.
I actually decided not to get the refurbished version and buy new to avoid exactly this concern.
Purchase this at your own risk - who knows what you will get!  Worst Amazon purchase I've ever made.

title: Works Great
content: These work well

title: Falls out cross training
content: I needed these for going to the gym and staying in my ear. I returned them and got the elite sport options

title: Not perfect. Average for the price.
content:
Coming from Jaybird x3s.
Comfort = Jaybird
Sound = Jaybird
Battery = Jabra
Bluetooth = Jabra
Quality = Tie

I love the look. I love the features (remove bud to pause, hear through).
I am still getting over my fear of these things falling out of my ears.
Right ear, perfect. Left ear, seems to be loose or so tight it hurts.
When walking ~15 minutes, they rotate.
I am happy with the sound. It isn’t perfect, but it’s completely acceptable.

title: SURPRISINGLY COMFORTABLE, GREAT SOUND
content: Having had several bad experiences with other in-ear options I was hesitant, but very glad I gave these a try.  Other attempts were usually met with the "small" ear canal adapters still feeling too large, but with the 65t I find that I'm using the "medium" covers with great comfort!  Note that "Out of the box" sound  I found was not very good and I had to do something that I normally would never recommend; I loaded up the android app and after turning all EQ settings to MAX, I feel I achieved a better FLAT response with more ability to have extra volume headroom.  I have the Pixel XL, so you may have a different result, but certainly give it a try if you find the sound "tinny".  Will this perhaps impact battery life? Perhaps, but with plenty to start with I doubt I'll notice.  Meanwhile, People on the other end of my phone calls have complemented me for the new clarity as they often complained about my prior around the neck LG solution.  Throw in Alexa & Google Home abilities I have found very little to not like.  The volume "up" & "down" button positions are a bit awkward in my opinion.  That is a very small complaint.  I'm sure I'll get used to the feel, but it's forward & backward instead of up & down so you cannot logically infer which direction would be volume "up".  Otherwise, I'm extremely happy.

title: Excellent sound, great fit
content: Crystal clear sound, BT 5.0 makes a difference, get the iPhone app so you can use the equalizer to boost the bass.  Fits in ear very securely, great for workouts.

title: Really discreet
content: Great sound and quality

title: Great sound,  but two experiences with horrible hardware and parts
content:
I bought these to replace my Bose Soundsport Free because I felt the Bose were just too big and stuck out of my ears. These had a great sleek, low profile design.

The first pair stopped working after 1 week of gym use. These were amazing until it stopped. The right earbud just went dead. None of the reset methods could get it working and searching for answers online revealed this is a known problem.

I exchanged it through amazon and the second pair worked as expected, but about 30 minutes into my workout, the right earbud fell out of my ear. When picking it up, I realized the rubber tip was missing. From my picture, you can see the tip ripped at the base and the tip had actually stayed in my ear canal! It was a major scare when I get pinch it with my finger tips and had to ask the gym staff to let me use their first aid tweezers.

I wanted to love these and the sound quality is incredible, but at $180, getting bad parts twice is unacceptable! I rather return these and wait until Jaybird or Bose makes smaller earbuds.

title: The Best Bluetooth Earbuds I Have Ever Had!
content:
Pros:
- Charges quickly
- long battery life
- looks better than apple EarPods
- stays in the ear (it feels like it might fall off, but it never does)
- Simple Touch control
- Microphone is very good
- With just two clicks of the right earpiece you can listen to the ambient noise around you and it is pretty good, so you don't have to take off the EarPods to listen to people (so you will be less likely to drop one and lose it)
- sturdy case
- Most importantly the sound quality is superb

Cons:
- Cost
- There is no earwax screen in the headphones, so you might have to clean it once in a while.

title: Horrible bass
content: In my ear for only 1 hour and they're HURTING!!! I will be returning the bass sound is crap! My standard wired earphones that came with  my phone are way better. For $200 I expected better!

title: Will not disconnect when in the charging case.
content:
So to start I was really happy with these for the first 2 months. The sound  is good and they stay in place for the most part. The only early issue was I don't like that the left ear piece had to be in. They don't connect separate. Which would be nice because you could wear one, then when the battery gets low switch to the other. This way you always have a full charge.

Update... 6 months old now. Really NOT HAPPY for the money I spent. These are not cheap a high end price tag, with a low end quality.  These will just drop out of the ear with no warning, you won't feel it then bam, it falls out! And the worst part. When I return the ear peice back into the charge case they stay connected to the phone. This is a real problem, the only way to get it to disconnect is to turn my bluetooth off... but then my watch is not connected to my phone. So the only option is not bring my earphones with me!

title: Great!!
content:
Thank you for introducing a good product!
아마존!!!!!

title: Sound
content: There’s nothing comparable on the market. These are the best. I love them. My buddy has a pair of Bose and he said the same. If Jabra had a better way to market there name, these earbuds would dominate the market. Give them time, the quality of these buds will sell themselves.

title: Love them!
content: Sound is great. They are not bulgy at all like some models. The battery life is awesome and comes with a charging case. Love these when I go to the gym.

title: Just Would NOT Work.
content: The left earbud just would not work. Owner's manual was useless. App was useless. Sad, because I really wanted to like these after all the great reviews I read about them.

title: Nice!
content: Very nice ^^

title: Tried about 10 diff models - these are THE BEST
content: I've owned many MANY sets of stereo bluetooth headsets (with the cord behind the head or whatever) and also 7-8 diff sets of 'truly wireless headsets - so I know my way around wireless earbuds/headphones. Bottom line with the Jabra Elite 65T Active - they are easily THE BEST of all models, with no compromise at all. Yes there are cheaper ones out there - tons of choices under $50 even. But those will let you down in one way or another - either they will drop the bluetooth connection, or the sound is sketchy, or the fit is not great, or SOMEthing. These will not let you down at all. Get them and don't waste your money with all the low-end cheap ones out there. Get the Jabra Elite 65T Active. I use them all the time for running and biking and they are GREAT!

title: Headphones don't amplify sound - music is never loud enough
content: For the high price that I paid for these headphones, I expected the sound quality to be good, and it was. HOWEVER, I don't ever even bother to use these headphones anymore due to the fact that, even with your volume all the way up, whatever media you're trying to play through the headphones never gets loud enough. With any other headphones that I've used, I normally never play things at full volume, but with these you have to - and even then its not loud enough. I would have given the Jabra Elite's a higher rating for the app (with all of its great features) and the long-lasting battery life of the headphones, but because of how quietly sound is played through the headphones I don't even use these anymore - which to me indicates that buying these was a giant waste of money.

title: Ok but not great
content:
I like my earbuds.  I was looking for wireless earbuds to listen to music while I work out.  I was using wired but kept yanking them out of my ears as I exercised on an elliptical. The sound quality is excellent, most of the time.  At other times it can be crackly at which point you have to put them back in the case and put them back in your ears to clear it up.  It will also get crackly if you walk too far away from the source.

As far as noise cancellation I would say it is OK.  The plug into your ears fairly well which alone is enough to cancel out most of the noise.  Then when you are playing music it takes away most of the rest. However, at my gym there is a room they have exercise classes in.  They play the music EXTREMELY loud.  Even with the doors closed you can hear it.  The earbuds block much of that noise but not all of it.  I can still hear the music.

Overall, would I buy them again?  Probably but I would check to see what else is out there.

title: great fit
content: Sound is great and fit is perfect!  love them

title: You have to pay for return shipping
content: Had to return the ear buds as I found out the person they were set to be a gift for already had a pair.  Jabra does Not offer a return shipping label - you have to pay out of your own pocket if you send these back.

title: Does NOT Stay In Your Ear During Activty
content: Great Sound - but they fall out of your ear during even light activity. The shape does not allow for a "tight fit".

title: Stuttering and sound drops
content: After seeing the repeated reviews singing these earbuds praises I went ahead to bought a pair.  The Airpods work great but don't stay in my ears and don't provide the isolation that I want on the train.  I quickly ran into two problems with these buds.  First, they don't seal the ear very well.  In train with a lot of base noise the sound still gets in.  The second problem was fatal for me.  On the platform and often on the train I would suddenly get stuttering or sound drops.  This never happened with the Airpods.  As a result I took these back.  After some further thought I decided to give the Beoplay E8 a try since it uses BT4.2 and I was pleasantly surprised.  Not only do they sound great and insulate better but on my train ride to work this morning not a single sound drop or stutter.  I have an Iphone 8.  Shame that the Jabra's didn't work out.

title: Best Workout Earbuds with Great Sound
content:
Great workout earbuds! These stay tight in your ears and have great sound quality.  No matter how much running or jumping, etc., will
cause them to fall out. The noise cancellation works very well and if you get the app, you can adjust the sound levels (bass, etc.).  You can turn volume up and down from left earbud and answer phone or use Siri/Alexa straight from the right earbud.  I highly recommend these.  The best part is the small charging case.  It will only take two hours to charge from a USB port and will give about five hours or charge.  The case holds a charge to keep the earbuds charged as well.

title: Good buy
content: Need a little stronger bass for my taste but they still rock!!

title: Left earbud intermittent/sound dead
content:
0:000:00This video is not intended for all audiences. What date were you born?SubmitAdobe Flash Player is required to watch this video.Install Flash Player I cant give this more than 2 stars because at this price point they should be more reliable than a pair being sold for 1/3rd the price. That being said, the sound quality is very good, they fit in my ear extremely well and could shake my head with them not falling out. If you have small ears however they uncomfortably fit in my wifes ears.

But I gave it two stars because I assumed these would be working ready to go when I got them so I ordered them a week before my deployment. When I got them the left ear bud wasnt working, messed around with it putting it in the case and taking it out several times and finally worked, chalked it up to I wasnt putting it in the case correctly. Leave for my deployment, took me 30 mins to get the earbud working messing with it on the flight. Now everytime I want to use it, it takes anywhere for 5 mins to 30 mins to get it to work. When I get to my location will stick to a pair that's rated higher on Amazon. Extremely disappointed that a 160$ pair of earbud work less than a 50 dollar pair I purchased before this purchase. Wish it was working all the time because the sound quality was good.

Update: left ear still intermittent, I found a way to turn it on but, most of the time does not want to charge as you can see in the video. The right one works perfect, recognizing being pulled out and recognizes being placed in to charge.

25 Sep update: left ear bud sounds completely dead. Changes songs fine, volume up and down works. But the speaker is already dead. At this price point these ear buds are not worth it.

title: Good quality
content: Better than I even expected, battery lasts for several hours, comfortable, have not had any connection issues using with Motorola turbo 2. Seems to allow in enough outside sound as well when wanted.

title: Sound quality is great
content:
Absolutely awesome earbuds. Great quality and fit.
Wish I could listen to one at a time but you can only listen to the right one by itself, only the right one.

title: Earbuds are awesome!
content: I've always hated wireless headphones because the music would drop out in one ear for no reason. Very annoying to me!! I recently got a new iPhone, and there is no longer a headphone jack, so I reconsidered wireless. I commute into NYC everyday, so to try to relax to music is important. I made the mistake of purchasing an inexpensive set of wireless earbuds that got great reviews here at Amazon. Tried them for a week and all I got were multiple dropouts. Sent them back and did more research. The research lead me to the Jabra Elite 65t. I love these earbuds. Sound is awesome and fit comfortably. The main thing is that the music has not dropped out even once! Highly recommend these earbuds!

title: A decent pair of buds
content: Decent pair of headphones. Sound could be clearer.

title: Best truly wireless earbuds
content: Love everything about these so far except that my ears got fatigued quickly and it hurt my ears to use the buttons until I upgraded to Comply memory foam earbuds. Still struggling to figure out the right Comply earbuds that have a proper fit but even the ones that are too big immediately got rid of the ear fatigue and everything else about them is amazing. Love all the features, very responsive when you remove a earbud and it cuts off the music and when you go from one earbud to both. Great range and battery life. Sound quality is great and voice quality on the phone seems to be great from what others say. Did a lot of research to find the best truly wireless earbuds and I am very happy with these (especially since I got them used for 113$ but they seemed brand new)

title: They are worth it
content: These sound good for what I paid for but it’s not going above and beyond in my opinion, the buds are comfortable but not the most comfortable. I still use them to listen to music daily and I enjoy them.

title: Worth the money
content:
Great headphones and the battery lasts long enough for a cross country airplane trip! Great for the gym but the bass is definitely lacking compared to my OTE headphones.

Update: the volume isn’t the highest on these compared to others I’ve used. Seriously my only complaint even after months of usage!

title: Cannot believe the reviews stating 'superior audio quality' - NOT true
content:
Sound compared to: 1) Jaybird new X4 wireless bluetooth set; 2) Bose Soundsport wireless; 3) Apple Airpods.
The sound is not very loud, still a bit 'tinny' sounding/flavourless/'in the distance', for those who come from a musical background/listen to jazz/classical. I can't believe the stellar reviews these Jabras are getting from numerous sources with only a few reviews on YouTube picking up that the audio sound experience is not that great.
Note also:
- the Jabra 'app' equaliser settings cannot be 'manually changed' like with Jaybird App, there are just a few 'default settings' which truth be told don't change the sound that much;
- all the above competitor products are much louder/actually think sound quality is better;
- and the case, whilst conveniently small, doesn't 'click in' nicely the earbud parts like the Apple Airpods.
Remember that Jabra come from a 'call headset' heritage as a company, rather than years of audiophile products/experience.

title: Great product when it’s working... when it doesn’t, Jabra support service will frustrate you so bad
content:
I bought the Jabra 65t Active on a Thanksgiving deal. The earbuds is so convenient with good sound quality, but in less than a month the right earbud stopped charging turning it useless.
I’ve been trying hard to contact Jabra Assistance, but they just don’t answer the phone and takes weeks to answer your email with no solution.
Overall the earbuds are great when it works, but when it doesn’t is so frustrating the amount of money you spent on a poor life product.
They haven’t give me an option to replace the product warranty yet... let’s see

title: Good sound, poor mikes
content: Sound is good and they fit my ears fine.  But the microphones are not great.  I get a lot of complaints if there is even slight background noise.

title: “No device connected... connected”
content: The buds disconnect and connect when trying to connect to bluetooth most times. Sometimes it disconnects when it wants to. Annoying but if you are easy going, you learn to ignore. However, in less than 3 months, the left bud (the least used of the two) doesn’t work properly. It cuts out to minimal or no volume. If i touch the bud the volume returns, but disappears when I let go. These were my fave headphones, but now? Smh

title: If you have medium to large ear canal size these probably will not fit and or stay in your ear,
content: Work great, easy to use, great sound. Wish the assortment of ear foam had larger sizes as the ones that come with barely fit me. They fall out very easily,  which cannot be good on the buds

title: Wished I would have bought these sooner
content: Pleasantly surprised how well built these are. Sound quality is good. Call quality and caller ID is great. I can wear these for a full charge and they're still comfortable. Bluetooth 5.0 distance is insane. I have a basement office and I went to our second story and the music didn't cut out. Very happy with my purchase.

title: Good buds but has Video and Audio Sync
content: I like how they fit in my ear and the sound quality is good too. I also use these buds to connect to my Pelaton stationary bike Bluetooth and there is a significant issue with Video and Audi Sync and the issue exists on my iphone  apps like youtube as well. I do not use these to watch youtube but I use them while riding the peleton and it is very annoying to have the lag! hope Jabra fixes this issue.

title: Awesome
content: Good

title: The finest bluetooth earset
content: I tried several similar products such as Bose Sound Sports Free and B&O E8 but I didn't satisfied with those all because battery and unstable connection issue. But this Jabra Elite 65t showed the stablest connection I've ever experienced and I satisfied the sound quality. Even the price is the most reasonable! I really recommend this product.

title: Great sound and noise canceling but wont stay in during workouts
content: As long as I don't move or sweat, the earbuds stay in. I tried with all three inserts with the same result. Useless for workouts, which was why I bought them.

title: Perfect
content: Wonderful sound and great comfort.

title: Left bud produces loud "white noise"
content:
Very disappointed with this purchase. I recently returned my Bose Sound Sport Frees because they didn't have enough passive noise isolation. The BSSF are excellent in sound quality but you cant enjoy the sound unless you are in a completely quiet place or blast your eardrums. I decided to give the Elite 65t since it seemed to have good reviews. Got them and was very impressed in the compact size and the noise isolation compared to BSSF. The passive noise isolation great. Then I found that the left bud produces white noise a split second before, during and a second after sound plays. The only thing that can cover the white noise is music with loud percussion. Other than that, like with podcasts and classical music, it comes through and is very annoying. It is the noise that you would hear from a super cheap headset. It has nothing to do with the "Hear-through" feature. The white noise isn't there when the HT is on or off, only when playing something. I have another Bluetooth headset that doesn't make the noise at all.

I'm attempting to return these so I can purchase another set and give them another try since I'm assuming that this is not normal for an almost $200 dollar earbud. Now Amazon says that I have to pay for shipping to return this defective item. I messaged the seller saying that it is not right that I have to pay to ship back a defective item. I'm waiting to hear back from them. I'd love to love these especially since the completely wireless feature is very helpful in my line of work. I'm hoping to hear back from them and get a new set to give these another try.

title: Great buy
content: Super impressed with the sound quality. Really is a good option if you don’t want the AirPods. The Noise isolation works well. It’s not “noise cancellation” so it does not completely block the sound but it gets the job done for my noisy office.

title: Died after 2 months, support dragging their feet
content:
I was originally pleased with these. The sound quality is decent and the range is great. Compared to the $50 Tranya the sound quality is better but I miss the Tranya's great magnetic case.
I can't recommend these due to quality and support issues. After 2 months, My charging case stopped turning off the headphones automatically. Then the left earbud stopped connecting and has a lot of static. I contacted Jabra support and followed all their troubleshooting instructions to no avail. They had me fill out forms, take a photo of the device and weeks have dragged on with no response about a replacement.

title: Earbud heaven...
content:
I have had these for 3 months now and wanted to give them a good try before I reviewed them. I have not experienced any of the issues that I saw in other reviews.
1) When both earbuds are in, the sound is clean (music, podcasts and phone calls) and background noise is completely blocked out. I can't hear someone talking to me when they are standing next to me.
2) the right earpiece will work without the left, but the left does not work without the right.  I have noticed on occasion if the left is out for "a while" it doesn't reconnect when I put it back in my ear. However, just redock in the charger and it resets. But this is only after I have had it out for several minutes.
3) No issues with battery life... I use every day for a couple hours at a time and charge the base about once a week.
4) wearing at the gym is great... I haven't had issues with them falling out (comes with extra sizes) or getting sweaty and interfering with the sound.

These fit flush in my ear and don't stick out like other products and are very comfortable to wear. (Assuming you aren't irritated by in ear devices in general)

title: Impossible to use warranty
content:
They worked great for a couple months, then the right ear bud quit working and I tried to contact Jabra multiple times through the website. They have still to get back to me..

Be Cautious

title: Good, but plenty of room for improvement.
content:
The Ads are not completely honest about noise cancellation, mic, and connectivity.
Noise cancellation is not perfect. The hear through feature is clearly noticeable, but some noise still gets through.
The mic is not good at all, for calls. People on the other end cannot hear properly.
The connectivity has an issue when placing the phone in pocket. I use Oppo F7. The connection is interrupted when the camera end of the phone is lower in the trouser pockets. It appears that some other device in the phone interferes with the connection, since keeping the phone head up in the trouser pocket rectifies this problem. Same with walls, and fridge doors.

title: Top notch
content: These are a fantastic pair of earbuds. The sound quality is surprisingly good for true wireless. Also, I was very impressed with the seal/fit and water resistance during workouts.

title: Battery won't charge to full, poor microphone
content:
Received complains when I was talking to other people over the phone. They can not hear me clearly.
I was happy with it at the beginning but now it is a nightmare.
At some point they earbud won't charge to full,  it always tell me charged in hall and the app shows 50%
Lose connection fro the left side constantly.
Contacted customer service, asked me spend a lot of time to diagnose the device, turn it on, off, connect, disconnect, put in the charge case, charge with different cable, computer or wall charger ...etc. overwhelming !!!
Then they asked me if I am using the usb cable comes with the earbuds. !! does it means it will not work with 3rd party USB cables?
Also asked me to only use computers to charge.
I have never expected to spend so much time to deal with this ear bud. Very disappointed.

title: Lasted me a long time and still going.
content: These are the first wireless earbuds I've used, and I made sure to buy the best for me, and these are amazing. They're easy to carry around and don't fall out of your ear. I can tell that they're made for bigger ears than mine but they still work perfectly in every way. Look up a video on YouTube and I'm sure others will agree with me.

title: These are great but there are a few pain points that may ...
content:
These are great but there are a few pain points that may lead me to return these.
1.  I could get past this, but what's with not using magnets to help them click into place in the case,  magnets are cool, everyone loves magnets with the satisfying click.  just a missed opportunity.
2.  most importantly they fill up your earlobe and it turns out my ear lobes don't fit magically to the shape of the device like I assume only a small percentage of users do.  At least put some rubber or foam to make it more comfortable,  I can't ware these for more than 2 hours without it hurting which really helps save the battery btw.
3. It's cool the way this thing connects to all your devices at the same time but it is a mistake.  I'll be watching something on my laptop and then I open my phone and the laptop audio cuts out because the jabra is listening to both devices now and it has to catch up.  So I have to turn off the phone bluetooth for the laptop audio to come back.

Still it does everything right and I love them but #2 is the reason I may bring them back.

title: Lots of problems for the money
content:
For 190$ I expected these to sound amazing.  They sound just ok and have no base even with base boost on.  I find the buds that came with my phone sound better.  The biggest problem for me is the static and skipping, they used to skip CONSTANTLY during activities but I found out it was the auto pause that was the problem as they would stop when they are not seated in your ear hard enough.  That leads me to my next problem, for "active" ear buds they fall out of your ears A LOT!  I tried all 3 tips and the medium are best for me but still not great.  I find myself pushing them back in every 30-60 seconds while running which is super annoying.  The addition of wings or clips would completely alleviate the problem and for so much money they should be included.  While shooting around I found the jostling of stopping and picking up the ball made them fall out even faster...just unacceptable.
The static problems are real also, I tried everything in all of the FAQs and the static is greatly reduced but still there.  The passthrough option brutally increases static so it's a useless feature IMO unless you can tolerate static.

TLDR - I'm returning these because they are just not any good...sound bad, no base, static always, low range and fall out constantly.

title: Phenomenal
content: These headphones are well-designed, sturdy, and reliable. The one Issue I have is related to a feature that's actually neat when it works: when you take a headphone out, the audio playing through the headphones pauses (which is awesome) but if you take both out before turning the headphones off or disconnecting them, the audio will resume if you hold them close enough to one another instead of remaining paused. It's a very small issue for otherwise amazing headphones that I couldn't be happier with. Absolutely worth the money.

title: Jabra Elite 65t has great sound
content: I just love the sound from these small comfortable earbuds. They always stay connected and stay in your ears. Music sounds just great and with the app you can adjust the sound with the equalizer. These are fantastic truly wireless earbuds. Jabra hit it out of the park with these.

title: Sound quality mediocre at best compared to high quality ear phones
content: O.K. I get it. These are intended to be used while exercising, not critical listening. They are probably fine for that. However, listening to these and then my Shure 535 earphones the difference is stark. These sound "muddy" and lack transparency and detail.  Yes, the Shure 535s coust $500, so perhaps not a fair comparison, just don't think you are getting audiophile headphones.  Just use them for what they are and don't make the mistake I made of comparing the sound to higher end earphones. I'm returning them, but admittedly I'm picky about sound quality.

title: True wireless is the way to go! Check first to make sure they fit.
content:
Here is my straightforward opinion and experience with these. I will cover what I consider the negatives- unless you always wear both earbuds the volume control is a mystery. Because I use mine mostly for telephone use, I normally only wear one in my right ear. I have tried every size ear piece and purchased additional ones and none of them have resulted in a snug fit and reduced noise. Yes there are other adjustments for noise cancellation and they do help but marginally at best. So between these falling out of my ear on a regular basis plus some other small nuances that seem to pop up I probably wouldn’t buy them again.

Now the pro’s:  I love how small they are and not having a cord. I have always had some type of tether on my past ones and as expected the cord was a pain. These are a joy in comparison. Whenever I wear both which is not often, the sound is excellent and crisp. Not a huge amount of thump but I’m ok with that.in summary of the fit my ear better I would have no issues, however, because of the fit I will be looking at other options soon.

title: Great headphones
content: Very good headphones. The ear cups could be a little softer. If you have ear fatigue from using these try a softer ear cups. The factory Samsung ones work great.

title: Best earbuds and I've tried quite a few.
content: Great sound quality.  Very secure in ears.  Easy to use.

title: Suprisingly Amazing
content: Honestly I hate spending over $25 on earphones but I figured I'd try it and if it's similar to the $25 one I already have I would return these. Now I'm out of $119 (Prime day deal) and I am happy about the money I spent. These are absolutely amazing. If you're like me and can't justify spending that kind of money on earphones dont second guess it and do it. You wont regret it. I love the custom EQ feature in the app, I also love that if I lose them or forget them i am able to track them with GPS. It is awesome

title: Excellent Product
content: Best I've ever bought. Sound quality is great.

title: *Not for super sensitive ears* Ear cartilage ached after around 40 minutes. Can't swap out for different tips either due to size
content:
Been on a quest to find a substitution for the Apple EarPods (EarPods hurt after a short time) and REALLY wanted to love the
Jabra Elite 65t True Wireless Earbuds. Since I am only giving 2 stars, I won't list all of the obvious pros (for ex: 5 hours battery, the convenience of wireless headphones, cool app with equalizer adjustment feature)

Instead, I will explain the two main reasons these are being returned:

A. For $181.89 (order total with tax) I wasn't blown away by the sound quality. Even with the ability to adjust/customize within the app these just didn't sound like the EarPods. I understand that that's a tall order but I am thinking that for this price, the sound should've come alot closer than it did.

B. Due to the shortness of the rubber tips, they repeatedly fell out of my ears unless I did the twist to get them to suction in super tight. Presumably because the earbuds are so "top heavy," within around 45 min or so, my ears were aching. It was the slightest dullest ache but it was still frustrating. Actually, I was in the grocery store and tried to adjust them ever so slightly just to make one one of them suction more/less tight and within a few seconds it had fallen on the ground and I almost lost it under the cash register. When I got home I tried to swap out the tips for different rubber tips that never hurt my ears (the cheapies from my "wired" pair) - see pics... but the different sized plastic piece didn't allow for it. Very bummed that these weren't "the ones". I realize that this is because my ears are just sensitive (must be the shape of the cartilage) but I just find it odd that I can wear the other shaped headphone earbud tips for 6+ hours and never even really notice they are there.

title: Fall out of ear constantly
content: I wanted to like these earbuds sooooo much!  But I could never get them to stay in my ear.  They come with 3 different size ear adapters, but none seem to help me.  I just sent them back.

title: In the end, the best.
content: I think I’ve purchased every pair of wireless earbuds on the market under $200. AirPods, Indy’s, Anker’s, Jaybird’s, and even some just cheap (well rated) brands off Amazon. Personally, the Jabra Elite 65t just killed it in every category.  AirPods are a good product, the friendly controls were amazing.  In the end, I wanted noise canceling & more bass, throw in a case, to class I race.

title: Doesn't even last half of a year
content: After 3 to 4 months the case stoped taking a charge. no I can't get any gummy earpiece to stay on these earbuds they are completely worthless for me now

title: Headphones have major design defects
content: These headphones have decent sound quality but they have extreme connectivity issues with any devices. The left head-bud unpairs regularly and sometimes both head-buds unpair. Leading to frustration and a poorly designed product.

title: Very uncomfortable and don't fit well
content: These are very uncomfortable. I tried all of the different sizes for my ears and non of them fit. They are very irritating. They fall out if I try to use them at the gym. The left one always has issues connecting. I don't recommend these at all.

title: Quality ear buds
content: I am very satisfied, a little bulky.

title: Won’t stay in your ear
content: Earbuds are nice but they constantly want to fall out so you have your hands on your ears the whole time. Great features but not practical. Back they go

title: NOT a replacement (or contender) to AirPods like I was hoping :(
content:
I bought these hoping to replace my AirPods because they were making me angry and am having a lot of apple hate lately and am trying to move away from apple stuff, so thought these would be an improvement, however they make the AirPods look like MAGIC by comparison!

I decided on these on advice from an actual Jabra employee at a telecom trade show because he explicitly told me the MIC was noise cancelling as well as the speakers. I was skeptical because this is unheard of in wireless bluetooth earbuds, so I asked and asked and was confidently reassured... COMPLETE MADE UP BS!!!

NOICE CANCELLING MIC (OR LACK THEREOF) :
The first call I made, there was someone talking a couple rooms down at normal volume, and the person I was speaking too could hear every word they said almost better than I could.. I COULDN'T BELIEVE IT!!

They LITERALLY ENHANCE background noice, NOT REDUCE!! I am really not exaggerating here!! RIDICULOUS!!

FALSE ADVERTISING ON DIGITAL ASSISTANTS:
Advertised Siri, Alexa and Google assistance, however when setting up, Only Siri and Alexa where available!! BS!!

HORRIBLE CASE:
Cover for case is crap, hard to open, flimsy plastic hinge, honestly it reminds me of a pack of gum fro the dollar store! When you (force) open the lid, the earbuds are just loose sitting there, some sometimes flick out or at least bounce around!

When putting them back in, they do not sit well, seems like because the charging terminals are big pointy springs which pushes them up and makes them wiggly. While in, you can't tilt or turn upside down it they just fall out, especially compared to AirPods which never inadvertently fall out no matter what!

Also the case shows a lot of greasy finger prints, even though my hands were clean and certainly was not after handling anything greasy or dirty at all!

MULTIPLE DEVICE SUPPORT:
They are suppose to pair to 8 devices, and connect to 2 at once.. Again BS!! While I can technically connect my MacBook and iPhone at the same time, while both are connected, I CANNOT play music on my iPhone!! I plays for 1 second and pauses EVERY TIME without fail, no way around it.

Also when connected to 2 devices, put in the case and take out again, it doesn't reestablish the connection!! How dumb!!

SOUND QUALITY:
Sound quality is average at best, certainly not close to AirPods, or LG Tones with the HK speakers.. Very tinny and flat, even with the large silicon tips and equalizer settings. They are technically slightly louder than AirPods, but fuzzy and horrible at that louder volume, disgusting!

COMPUTER SUPPORT:
When paired to MacBook, I installed the Jabra app, and it detects it, can see battery life, but there is not ONE SETTING IN THERE that matches any of the settings in the mobile app, which is where you turn on noise cancelling for the speakers, change profiles, equalizer, etc... ALL MISSING form the MacBook, making them just another set of bluetooth earbuds, with none of the advertised features!!

CONCLUSION:
I have to eat my words (and hate) for my AirPods, which at the moment is the lesser of the evils, but does renew my appreciation for those things, Makes me rethink my Apple hate!

These really are $30-$40 generic bluetooth earbuds, which do not work as advertised in almost any way!

title: Terrible for Working Out
content: The fit is not tight enough to hold in when sweating. Both times I wore them running one earbud fell out. I lost it the second time and support wouldn't even replace it. Billed for using while active but can't even stay in my ears! I was excited about the size, lightweight and waterproofing but turned out to be a waste of $180. My first experience with Jabra headphones and found them to be way below expectations.

title: Good sound quality but Bluetooth reception is finicky
content: Great sound quality and useability. Uncomfortable after a couple hours of use. Biggest drawback is the reception. I usually keep my phone in my pocket with the top pointed toward the ground. At that distance, I get music skipping and drops. When I bought these, I was under the impression I'd be able to walk to the next room and leave my phone without any impact on reception, but the effective range of consistent signal is just a few feet. You need to have your phone very close.

title: Easy peasy
content: Easy to use, great while I'm on the go whether I'm at the gym or work these are my go to. I'm able to talk on the phone with BT capability.

title: good not great, fit is an issue
content: This is my first pair of "true wireless" earbuds. I've never been a fan of the flexible rubber ear tips, I've always preferred the squishy foam ones (like on my Koss wired earbuds). My only reason for getting these is to wear to the gym, so my main concerns were fit and being sweatproof. I don't care about the battery life (only use them for about an hour at a time), or much about the sound quality (I usually blast some AC/DC to drown out the pop/dance crap at the gym). I sweat a lot. I mean really a lot, so I need the sweatproof feature. So far so good with that, it hasn't been an issue during workouts, and I dry them off before I put them back in the case. And yes, the case is surprisingly hard to open. The main negative is that at least one of the buds has fallen out of my ears at least once per workout. I've managed to catch it each time, because I can feel it starting to come loose. It will be really bad news if one falls out and gets stepped on or something. Maybe it's just those hateful rubber tips (I've tried all 3 sizes), so I'll probably be buying a 3rd party set of foam tips to see if that helps. I do powerlifting at the gym, so it's not a high impact bouncing kind of effort that makes them fall out. I think they'd be even worse if I was running or doing crossfit. If you're used to these kinds of tips and are happy with them, you might have better luck. The controls are easier to use than expected, though I've only been able to get the "double-press" to activate the "hear-through" function to work a couple times. They're much smaller than I expected, and they're barely visible from a head-on view (according to people who try to talk to me and can't even tell that I'm wearing them). Also quite expensive, probably makes sense to try a cheap pair first to see if you like the general fit and feel.
